)@@G@@@D@@@@             ,MACRO\TEMP\PTR: LOCATABLE INTEGER WORD  @#@@@@      GQ
)@@G@@       !*:  @D@@@@                [END\OF\INPUT\CARD: 6 BIT CONDITION   GR
)@@G@@@F@@@@                ,CARD\ENDED\WITH\DIRECTIVE: 6 BIT CONDITION "     GS
)@@G@@@B@@@@                ,*: 6 BIT INTEGER " UNUSED@G@@@@                ,PGT
)@@G@@REVIOUS\CARD\PTR: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER] " PREV ICB  @B@@@@            GU
)@@G@@ ,MACRO\TEMP\NUM: WORD INTEGER@#@@@@             !*:  @G@@@@            GV
)@@G@@    [CARD\LENGTH: 18 BIT INTEGER " CHARACTER LENGTH OF CARD @H@@@@      GW
)@@G@@          ,CARD\INDEX : 18 BIT INTEGER] " INDEX OF LAST CHARACTER SEEN  GX
)@@G@@@G@@@@           ,INPUT\CARD\WORD(MAX\INPUT\WORD\LEN): WORD INTEGER LOCAGY
)@@G@@TABLE @F@@@@             !INPUT\CARD\LOGIC(MAX\INPUT\WORD\LEN): WORD LOGGZ
)@@G@@ICAL  @G@@@@             !INPUT\CARD(MAX\INPUT\CHAR\LEN): 9 BIT UNSIGNEDHA
)@@G@@ INTEGER];  @@@@@@@F@@@@DECLARE   OUTPUT\LENGTH: WORD INTEGER STATIC EXPHB
)@@G@@ORTED ('OUTLEN'); @@@@@@@D@@@@DECLARE   OUTPUT\CARD\WORD(OCWL): WORD INTHC

)@@G@@    END OF CARD-DEF     @@@@@@___UT\INTEGER LOCATABLE @C@C@B            HF
)@@G@@ !INPUT\CARD\LOGIC(33): *[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@"     @A@@@@" DEFINE CHECKPOINHG

)@@G@@EF')  @C@@@@          [DIRECTIVE\OPT(96): BIT CONDITION     @C@@@@      IH

)@@G@@OWN TO DPS ARE DEFINED HERE.  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DEFINE    GOPS = 13; " NMK
)@@G@@UMBER OF GRAPHIC OPERATORS    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@DECLARE   OCHR(GOPS): STML
)@@G@@ATIC 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER EXPORTED@B@@@@          !  *(GOPS): ASCII CHMM
)@@G@@ARACTER     @C@@@@          := [ ',' , '<' , '>' , '=' , '+' ,    @C@@@@MN
)@@G@@               '-' , '*' , '/' , '#' , '(' ,    @C@@@@               ')'MO
)@@G@@ , '[' , ']'             ];   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" OPERATORS ARE REFERREDMP
)@@G@@ TO INTERNALLY BY THESE TAGS. @[@@@@"     @A@@@@DEFINE    OPRCAT = 1,  "MQ
)@@G@@ CATENATION @A@@@@          OPRLSS = 2,  " LESS THAN  @B@@@@          OPMR
)@@G@@RGRT = 3,  " GREATER THAN     @A@@@@          OPREQL = 4,  " EQUAL TO   MS
)@@G@@@A@@@@          OPRADD = 5,  " ADDITION   @A@@@@          OPRSUB = 6,  "MT
)@@G@@ SUBTRACTION@B@@@@          OPRMUL = 7,  " MULTIPLICATION   @A@@@@      MU
)@@G@@    OPRDIV = 8,  " DIVISION   @A@@@@          OPRREP = 9,  " REPLICATIONMV
)@@G@@@B@@@@          OPROPR = 10,  " OPEN PARENTHESIS@C@@@@          OPRCPR =MW
)@@G@@ 11,  " CLOSE PARENTHESIS     @B@@@@          OPROBR = 12,  " OPEN BRACKMX
)@@G@@ET    @B@@@@          OPRCBR = 13;  " CLOSE BRACKET   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@MY
)@@G@@" LEAVE A HOLE FOR ADDING MORE GRAPHIC OPS.     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@DEFINEMZ
)@@G@@    VOPS = 20; " SPACE FOR SIX MORE WITHOUT RECOMPILING     @[@@@@"     NA
)@@G@@@E@@@@" THESE OPERATORS HAVE NO GRAPHICS, AND ARE INSERTED BY     @E@@@@NB
)@@G@@" VARIOUS PARTS OF DPS.  NOTE THAT IT IS IMPERATIVE THAT    @D@@@@" THEYNC
)@@G@@ REMAIN IN CORRESPONDANCE WITH THE DEFINITIONS  @C@@@@" IN ASSEMBLY LANGND
)@@G@@UAGE ELEMENT SYS-SYMBOLS.     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DEFINE    OPRBGL = VOPS+NE
)@@G@@1, " BEGINNING OF EXPRESSION  @C@@@@          OPREOL = VOPS+2, " END-OF-NF
)@@G@@EXPRESSION  @D@@@@          OPRAND = VOPS+3, " LOGICAL AND OPERATOR     NG
)@@G@@@E@@@@          OPRIOR = VOPS+4, " LOGICAL INCLUSIVE OR OPERATOR  @D@@@@NH
)@@G@@          OPRNOT = VOPS+5, " LOGICAL NOT OPERATOR     @D@@@@          OPNI

)@@G@@7, " INDEX$ OPERATOR    @C@@@@          OPRDST = VOPS+8; " DIST$ OPERATONK
)@@G@@R     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" DEFINE TOTAL NUMBER OF OPERATORS  @[@@@@"     NL
)@@G@@@C@@@@DEFINE    NOPS = 30; " TOTAL NUMBER OF OPERS    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@NM
)@@G@@" DEFINE PRIORITIES FOR OPERATORS.  THE HIGHER PRIORITY OPERATOR  @F@@@@NN
)@@G@@" IS PERFORMED FIRST EXCEPTING MONADIC OPERATORS WHICH ARE ALWAYS @^@@@@NO
)@@G@@" PERFORMED IMMEDIATELY.@[@@@@"     @E@@@@DECLARE   PRIO(NOPS): 1 STATICNP
)@@G@@ INTEGER WORD EXPORTED := [   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@"              CAT    < NQ
)@@G@@    >     =     + @C@@@@                1  ,  5  ,  5  ,  5  ,  6  ,    NR
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@"               -     *     /     #     ( @C@@@@      NS
)@@G@@          6  ,  7  ,  7  ,  8  ,  0  ,    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@"           NT
)@@G@@    )     [     ]     .     . @C@@@@                0  ,  0  ,  0  ,  0 NU
)@@G@@ ,  0  ,    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@"               .     .     .     .     . NV
)@@G@@@C@@@@                0  ,  0  ,  0  ,  0  ,  0  ,    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@NW
)@@G@@"              BGL   EOL   AND   IOR   NOT@C@@@@                0  ,  0 NX
)@@G@@ ,  3  ,  2  ,  4  ,    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@"             ENTRY INDEX  DISNY
)@@G@@T   .     . @C@@@@                9  ,  9  ,  9  ,  0  ,  0  ];   @[@@@@NZ
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@" DEFINE DATA AREAS USED WHILE PERFORMING OPERATORS IN THE DOA

)@@G@@ORE   @C@@@@" THE SPECIFIC OPERATOR SUBROUTINE IS CALLED.   @[@@@@"     OC

)@@G@@D ('PKT1'); @@@@@@@D@@@@DECLARE   GET\PACKET: WORD MACHINE POINTER STATIPM

)@@G@@E TLEN: WORD INTEGER;   @ @@@@DECLARE TNUM(2): WORD INTEGER;@ @@@@      SK
)@@G@@    NEW\CHAR\WIDTH := 0;@A@@@@          NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT := 0;     @B@@@@SL
)@@G@@          SCAN(CTRM+COMA+ALLOW\INT+EVAL); @H@@@@          TLEN := CSDLENSM
)@@G@@;    " SAVE THESE VALUES AND THEN CALL SCANNER AGAIN  @ @@@@          TNSN
)@@G@@UM(1) := DNUM(1); @ @@@@          TNUM(2) := DNUM(2); @F@@@@          SCSO
)@@G@@AN(CTRM+ALLOW\INT+EVAL); " THIS TIME PICK THEM ALL UP @^@@@@          CASP
)@@G@@SEENTRY TLEN@#@@@@          CASE 0: @A@@@@             IF CSDLEN EQ 1 THSQ
)@@G@@EN    @C@@@@                NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT := DNUM(1);     @#@@@@      SR
)@@G@@    CASE 1: @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             NEW\CHAR\WIDTH :=SS
)@@G@@ TNUM(1);   @A@@@@             IF CSDLEN EQ 1 THEN    @C@@@@            ST
)@@G@@    NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT := DNUM(1);     @A@@@@             IF CSDLEN GT 1 THSU
)@@G@@EN    @A@@@@                NEW\CHAR\WIDTH := 0;@#@@@@           END;   SV
)@@G@@@#@@@@          CASE 2: @A@@@@             IF CSDLEN EQ 0 THEN    @^@@@@SW
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @B@@@@                NEW\CHAR\WIDTH := TNUM(1);SX
)@@G@@@C@@@@                NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT := TNUM(2);     @#@@@@            SY
)@@G@@  END;@#@@@@          ENDCASE;@E@@@@          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 SZ
)@@G@@AND (NEW\CHAR\WIDTH NE 0@C@@@@                 OR NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT NE 0) TA
)@@G@@THEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             IF (NEW\CHAR\WIDTH EQ 0TB
)@@G@@ OR NEW\CHAR\WIDTH EQ 10@F@@@@                OR NEW\CHAR\WIDTH EQ 12) ATC
)@@G@@ND (NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT EQ 0@G@@@@                OR NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT EQ 6 ORTD
)@@G@@ NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT EQ 8) THEN   @^@@@@              BEGIN     @C@@@@      TE
)@@G@@          IF NEW\CHAR\WIDTH NE 0 THEN     @B@@@@                   CHANGTF
)@@G@@E\CHARS\PER\INCH; @C@@@@                IF NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT NE 0 THEN    TG
)@@G@@@B@@@@                   CHANGE\LINES\PER\INCH; @#@@@@              END;TH
)@@G@@@#@@@@             ELSE @B@@@@                WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\POINT); TI
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@          ELSE    @A@@@@             WARNITJ

)@@G@@@F@@@@" THIS ELEMENT DEFINES DATA AREAS WHICH ARE USED WHEN CALLING     WS
)@@G@@@F@@@@" THE SYSTEM FILE ASSIGN ROUTINE FIASG.  THIS SUBROUTINE WILL ONLYWT
)@@G@@@F@@@@" ISSUE A CSF$ REQUEST IF THE FILE IS NOT ASSIGNED TO THE RUN.    WU
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" FIASG$ IS PASSED A PACKET WHICH IS SIMILAR TO AN ELTWV
)@@G@@$ PACKET BUT@F@@@@" THE SIXTH WORD CHARACTER COUNTS NEED ONLY BE ZERO/NOWW
)@@G@@NZERO.  THIS@A@@@@" PACKET IS BASED FROM A POINTER.   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@WX
)@@G@@DEFINE    FIASG\PKT\LEN = 14; @@@@@@@ @@@@DECLARE   *: BASED MAPPED     WY
)@@G@@@C@@@@             [QUAL\GIVEN   : 6 BIT CONDITION    @C@@@@            WZ
)@@G@@ ,FILE\GIVEN   : 6 BIT CONDITION    @C@@@@             ,FCYCLE\GIVEN : 6XA
)@@G@@ BIT CONDITION    @C@@@@             ,RKEY\GIVEN   : 6 BIT CONDITION    XB
)@@G@@@C@@@@             ,WKEY\GIVEN   : 6 BIT CONDITION    @C@@@@            XC
)@@G@@ ,QUAL\IMPLIED : 6 BIT CONDITION    @C@@@@             ,ELEMENT\GIVEN: 6XD
)@@G@@ BIT CONDITION    @C@@@@             ,VERSION\GIVEN: 6 BIT CONDITION    XE
)@@G@@@C@@@@             ,ECYCLE\GIVEN : 6 BIT CONDITION    @D@@@@            XF
)@@G@@ ,FILE\CONTIN  : 6 BIT SIGNED INTEGER     @D@@@@             ,CYCLE\SIGNXG
)@@G@@AL : 6 BIT SIGNED INTEGER     @D@@@@             ,BINARY\CYCLE : 6 BIT SXH
)@@G@@IGNED INTEGER     @B@@@@             ,QUAL\ONE     : INTEGER WORD @B@@@@XI
)@@G@@             ,QUAL\TWO     : INTEGER WORD @B@@@@             ,FILE\ONE  XJ
)@@G@@   : INTEGER WORD @B@@@@             ,FILE\TWO     : INTEGER WORD @B@@@@XK
)@@G@@             ,FILE\CYCLE   : INTEGER WORD @B@@@@             ,READ\KEY  XL
)@@G@@   : INTEGER WORD @B@@@@             ,WRITE\KEY    : INTEGER WORD @B@@@@XM
)@@G@@             ,ELEMENT\ONE  : INTEGER WORD @B@@@@             ,ELEMENT\TWXN
)@@G@@O  : INTEGER WORD @B@@@@             ,VERSION\ONE  : INTEGER WORD @B@@@@XO
)@@G@@             ,VERSION\TWO  : INTEGER WORD @C@@@@             ,ELEMENT\CYXP
)@@G@@CLE: INTEGER WORD];     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THESE ADDITIONAL FLAGS MAY BXQ
)@@G@@E PASSED.  FIDBANK IS DEFINED @^@@@@" IN ELEMENT FIASG-PLUS.@[@@@@"     XR
)@@G@@@D@@@@" WARNING - THESE MUST AGREE WITH DEFS IN FIASG-PLUS. @[@@@@"     XS
)@@G@@@C@@@@DECLARE   *: STATIC IMPORTED ('FIDBANK') MAPPED @D@@@@            XT
)@@G@@ [INTERNAL\NAME\GIVEN : 6 BIT CONDITION   @D@@@@             ,INTERNAL\NXU
)@@G@@AME\FORCED: 6 BIT CONDITION   @D@@@@             ,ASSIGN\OPTIONS\GIVEN: XV
)@@G@@6 BIT CONDITION   @D@@@@             ,DIAGNOSE\ERRORS     : 6 BIT CONDITXW
)@@G@@ION   @E@@@@             ,PERMISSIONS\CODE    : 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER  XX
)@@G@@@E@@@@             ,FILE\FREE\CODE      : 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER  @C@@@@XY
)@@G@@             ,GIVEN\NAME\ONE      : INTEGER WORD@C@@@@             ,GIVEXZ
)@@G@@N\NAME\TWO      : INTEGER WORD@C@@@@             ,ASSIGN\OPTIONS      : YA
)@@G@@INTEGER WORD@C@@@@             ,CSF\BITS            : INTEGER WORD@D@@@@YB
)@@G@@             !CSF\BIT(36)         : BIT CONDITION];   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@YC
)@@G@@" WHEN FIASG RETURNS THE AREA FIPKT$ IS SET UP AS A FITEM$ PACKET @ @@@@YD
)@@G@@" CALLED ON THE FILENAME.     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@DECLARE   *: STATIC IMPOYE
)@@G@@RTED ('FIPKT$') MAPPED  @C@@@@             [INTERNAL\NAME\ONE: INTEGER WYF
)@@G@@ORD   @C@@@@             ,INTERNAL\NAME\TWO: INTEGER WORD   @C@@@@      YG
)@@G@@       ,EXTERNAL\FILE\ONE: INTEGER WORD   @C@@@@             ,EXTERNAL\FYH

)@@G@@ES A FIFREE$ CODE WHICH WILL FREE THE FILE UNCONDITIONALLY. @[@@@@"     YM
)@@G@@@^@@@@DEFINE    FIB\FREE = 2; @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" THE FOLLOWING DECLARATYN

)@@G@@ED INTEGER  @^@@@@                  ];    @@@@@@@@@@@@@D@ @^DECLARE   *:YZ
)@@G@@ MAPPED STATIC EXPORTED *[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@"     @A@@@@" PROCS FOUND IN EZA
)@@G@@LEMENT IO-SUBS    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE WAIT(PKT: WORD MACHINE POIZB

)@@G@@P     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@"   SEE ELEMENT IALL$   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDZH

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@"     @^@@@@" DEFINE PACKET TYPES.  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@ZM

)@@G@@PED   @B@@@@ "1-2"    [FILE\NAME: 2 FIELDATA WORDS    @B@@@@           !ZW

)@@G@@ER],  @A@@@@ "3"       EXEC\WORD: WORD INTEGER, @A@@@@ "4"       STATUS:ZY

)@@G@@     AFC: 6 BIT INTEGER,@C@@@@           INPUT\WORD\COUNT: 18 BIT INTEGEAA
)@@G@@R,    @B@@@@ "5"       WORD\COUNT: 18 BIT INTEGER,    @C@@@@           BAB
)@@G@@UFFER\ADDR: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER, @A@@@@ "6"       DRUM\ADDR: WORD INTAC
)@@G@@EGER, @B@@@@ "7"       ADDR1: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER, @B@@@@           AAD
)@@G@@DDR2: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER, @C@@@@ "8"       BUFFER\SECTOR\SIZE: 18 BIAE
)@@G@@T INTEGER,  @C@@@@           MAX\IMAGE\LENGTH: 18 BIT INTEGER,    @ @@@@AF
)@@G@@ "9"       *: 18 BIT INTEGER, @D@@@@           USER\IMAGE\BUFFER: 18 BITAG
)@@G@@ MACHINE POINTER, @ @@@@ "10"      *: 18 BIT INTEGER, @E@@@@           BAH
)@@G@@UFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER     @C@@@@           ! NEXT\AI
)@@G@@DRUM\ADDRESS: 18 BIT INTEGER, @B@@@@ "11"      CONTROL\WORD: WORD INTEGEAJ
)@@G@@R     @B@@@@           ![DATA\LENGTH: 12 BIT INTEGER, @A@@@@            AK
)@@G@@ *: 24 BIT INTEGER]     @ @@@@           ![*: 6 BIT INTEGER,@C@@@@      AL
)@@G@@       CONTROL\LENGTH: 6 BIT INTEGER,     @A@@@@             *: 24 BIT IAM
)@@G@@NTEGER]     @B@@@@           ![IMAGE\TYPE: 6 BIT INTEGER,   @B@@@@      AN
)@@G@@       IMAGE\LENGTH: 6 BIT INTEGER, @B@@@@             DELETE\COUNT: 6 BAO
)@@G@@IT INTEGER, @B@@@@             DELETE\CYCLE: 6 BIT INTEGER, @B@@@@      AP
)@@G@@       INSERT\COUNT: 6 BIT INTEGER, @B@@@@             INSERT\CYCLE: 6 BAQ
)@@G@@IT INTEGER],@D@@@@ "12"      END\OF\BUFFER: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER,     AR
)@@G@@@ @@@@           REM: 18 BIT INTEGER@C@@@@           ! REM\PTR: 18 BIT MAS
)@@G@@ACHINE POINTER,   @B@@@@ "13"     BASE\DRUM\ADDR: WORD INTEGER,   @[@@@@AT
)@@G@@"     @]@@@@" FLAGS     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@ "14"      PACKET\TYPE: 6 BIT AU
)@@G@@INTEGER,    @H@@@@           LAST\BLOCK: 6 BIT CONDITION, " SET WHEN WRIAV
)@@G@@TING LAST BLOCK OF UNIT @A@@@@           IO\DONE: 6 BIT CONDITION,@B@@@@AW

)@@G@@OINTER];    @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THE LIST OF DIRECTIVES WHICH ARE USED FOCK
)@@G@@R CONTROL STRUCTURE IN MACROS @[@@@@"     @ @@@@DEFINE    NSYS\MACRO = 1CL

)@@G@@CRO PACKET  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@"  DEFINE OUTPUT FILE STATUS CODES  @[@@@@DG
)@@G@@"     @ @@@@DEFINE    NO\OUTPUT\FILE = 0, @G@@@@          OUTPUT\FILE\ASDH

)@@G@@GTH: 18 BIT INTEGER,    @ @@@@ "9"       *: 18 BIT INTEGER, @D@@@@      DV

)@@G@@IT INTEGER, @E@@@@           BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTEDX
)@@G@@R     @C@@@@           ! NEXT\DRUM\ADDRESS: 18 BIT INTEGER, @B@@@@ "11" DY
)@@G@@     CONTROL\WORD: WORD INTEGER     @B@@@@           ![DATA\LENGTH: 12 BDZ
)@@G@@IT INTEGER, @A@@@@             *: 24 BIT INTEGER]     @ @@@@           !EA
)@@G@@[*: 6 BIT INTEGER,@C@@@@             CONTROL\LENGTH: 6 BIT INTEGER,     EB
)@@G@@@A@@@@             *: 24 BIT INTEGER]     @B@@@@           ![IMAGE\TYPE:EC
)@@G@@ 6 BIT INTEGER,   @B@@@@             IMAGE\LENGTH: 6 BIT INTEGER, @B@@@@ED
)@@G@@             DELETE\COUNT: 6 BIT INTEGER, @B@@@@             DELETE\CYCLEE
)@@G@@E: 6 BIT INTEGER, @B@@@@             INSERT\COUNT: 6 BIT INTEGER, @B@@@@EF
)@@G@@             INSERT\CYCLE: 6 BIT INTEGER],@D@@@@ "12"      END\OF\BUFFEREG
)@@G@@: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER,     @ @@@@           REM: 18 BIT INTEGER@C@@@@EH
)@@G@@           ! REM\PTR: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER,   @B@@@@ "13"     BASE\DRUEI
)@@G@@M\ADDR: WORD INTEGER,   @[@@@@"     @]@@@@" FLAGS     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@EJ
)@@G@@ "14"      PACKET\TYPE: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER, @B@@@@           LAST\BLEK
)@@G@@OCK: 6 BIT CONDITION,   @A@@@@           IO\DONE: 6 BIT CONDITION,@B@@@@EL
)@@G@@           END\FILE: 6 BIT CONDITION,     @C@@@@           FILE\FORMAT: EM

)@@G@@@B@@@@" PROCS FOUND IN ELEMENT   F-ALLOCATE     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDFB
)@@G@@URE ALLOCATE\FILE\BLOCK(NWORDS: WORD INTEGER)   @D@@@@           IMPORTEFC
)@@G@@D ('ALLFBKA') RESULT WORD INTEGER;  @@@@@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE CONDITIONAL\FRFD
)@@G@@EE\FILE\BLOCK(BLOCK\ADDR:     @G@@@@           WORD INTEGER, NWORDS: WORFE
)@@G@@D INTEGER) IMPORTED ('FREFBKA');    @@@@@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE UNCONDITIONAL\FF
)@@G@@FREE\FILE\BLOCK(BLOCK\ADDR:   @G@@@@           WORD INTEGER, NWORDS: WORFG
)@@G@@D INTEGER) IMPORTED ('UNCFREA');    @@@@@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE RELEASE\FREED\FH
)@@G@@FILE\BLOCKS IMPORTED ('RELFREEFB'); @@@@@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE RECOVER\FREED\FI
)@@G@@FILE\BLOCKS IMPORTED ('RECVFREEFB');@@@@@@@F@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\FILFJ
)@@G@@E\ALLOCATOR IMPORTED ('INITFILALLOC');    @@@@@@@A@@@@PROCEDURE MAX\ALLOFK

)@@G@@ER;   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE FORCE\WRITE\OF\BIT\MAPS IMPORTED ('FORFM
)@@G@@CEWOBM');   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" END OF BLOCK-PROCS    ___V-SFN
)@@G@@);    @@@@@@@A@]@@PROCEDURE MAX\ALLOCATED\FILE\B*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@"     FO
)@@G@@@A@@@@" PROCEDURES IN THE SCANNER COMPLEX @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DEFINE    EVFP
)@@G@@AL = O'400000',  " EVALUATE EXPRESSION    @D@@@@          COMA = O'20000FQ
)@@G@@0',  " STOP SCANNING ON COMMA @D@@@@          CNAM = O'040000',  " INTEGFR
)@@G@@ERS ARE NAME\LABEL@F@@@@          CNUM = O'020000',  " CATENATE NUMBERS FS
)@@G@@AS CHARACTERS     @E@@@@          CSTR = O'010000',  " CONVERT EVERYTHINFT
)@@G@@G TO STRING @D@@@@          ALLOW\NAM = O'004000',  " ALLOW NAME\LABEL  FU
)@@G@@@D@@@@          ALLOW\INT = O'002000',  " ALLOW INTEGER     @D@@@@      FV
)@@G@@    ALLOW\DST = O'001000',  " ALLOW DISTANCE    @C@@@@          ALLOW\STFW
)@@G@@R = O'000400',  " ALLOW STRING@C@@@@          ALLOW\TAB = O'000200',  " FX
)@@G@@ALLOW TABLES@E@@@@          ALLOW\FLP = O'000100',  " ALLOW FLOATING POIFY
)@@G@@NT    @E@@@@          CFLP = O'000040',  " CONVERT INTEGER TO FLOATING  FZ
)@@G@@@C@@@@          CTRM = O'000020',  " CHECK TERM CHAR  @D@@@@          NSGA
)@@G@@UB = O'000010';  " NO SUBSTITUTION ALLOWED@[@@@@"     @B@@@@" NOTE BITS GB
)@@G@@0-2 ARE CONVERSION FACTOR.    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE SCGC
)@@G@@AN(MODE: INTEGER WORD) IMPORTED('SCNNER');@[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE SCGD
)@@G@@AN\UNTIL(CHAR: INTEGER WORD) IMPORTED ('SCNTIL');     @@@@@@@E@@@@PROCEDGE
)@@G@@URE SCAN\TO\DIRECTIVE\END IMPORTED ('SCNDIREND');     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@GF
)@@G@@PROCEDURE SCAN\MACRO\CALL IMPORTED ('SCANMACCAL')     @D@@@@            GG
)@@G@@ RESULT MACHINE WORD POINTER; " TO ARGBUF @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE DUGH
)@@G@@MP\DESCRIPTOR(IDENT: 6 FIELDATA CHARACTERS@D@@@@                        GI
)@@G@@ ,POINT: MACHINE WORD POINTER)@ @@@@          IMPORTED ('DMPDSC');@[@@@@GJ
)@@G@@"     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" END OF SCAN-PROCS     @[@@@@"     ___@@IRGBUF GK
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE DUMP\DESCRIPTOR(IDENT: 6 FIELDATA CHARACTERSGL
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" DEFINE DATA AREAS USED BY THE SCANNER COGM
)@@G@@MPLEX.@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" THIS IS THE FORMAT OF A BASIC DPS DESCRIPTOR. GN
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @I@@@@"                  -----------------------------------GO
)@@G@@--------------------------    @I@@@@"                  :  DTYP   :  DSBTGP
)@@G@@   :         :         :         :         :    @I@@@@"                 GQ
)@@G@@ -------------------------------------------------------------    @I@@@@GR
)@@G@@"                  :            DLEN             :            DADR      GS
)@@G@@       :    @I@@@@"                  -----------------------------------GT
)@@G@@--------------------------    @[@@@@"     @#@@@@" THE FIELDS ARE: @[@@@@GU
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@" DTYP - THE 'TYPE' FOR THE DATA ITEM REPRESENTED.    @D@@@@GV
)@@G@@" DSBT - THE 'SUBTYPE' FOR THE DATA ITEM REPRESENTED. @D@@@@" DLEN - THEGW
)@@G@@ 'LENGTH' OF THE DATA ITEM REPRESENTED.   @C@@@@" DADR - THE CORE ADDRESGX
)@@G@@S OF THE DATA ITEM.     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" A DESCRIPTOR ON THE SCANNER GY
)@@G@@STACK LOOKS LIKE: @[@@@@"     @I@@@@"                  -----------------GZ
)@@G@@--------------------------------------------    @I@@@@"                 HA
)@@G@@ :  DTYP   :  DSBT   :  STAT   :  OPER   :       MSAV        :    @I@@@@HB
)@@G@@"                  -----------------------------------------------------HC
)@@G@@--------    @I@@@@"                  :            DLEN             :    HD
)@@G@@        DADR             :    @I@@@@"                  -----------------HE
)@@G@@--------------------------------------------    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" DEFIHF
)@@G@@NITIONS OF FIELDS:@[@@@@"     @ @@@@" S1 - DTYP(OS\PTR), BASE     @F@@@@HG
)@@G@@"    DURING NUMERIC SCANNING THIS FIELD IS USED UNDER THE NAME    @F@@@@HH
)@@G@@"    BASE TO HOLD 8 OR 10 AS THE NUMBER MAY BE OCTAL OR DECIMAL.  @[@@@@HI
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@" S2 - DSBT(OS\PTR)     @[@@@@"     @]@@@@" S3 - STAT @E@@@@HJ
)@@G@@"    THIS FIELD IS USED TO HOLD THE CURRENT SCANNER STATE.  @[@@@@"     HK
)@@G@@@^@@@@" S4 - DADL, OPER, SFLG @E@@@@"    DURING NUMERIC SCAN THIS IS USEHL
)@@G@@D UNDER THE NAME DADL TO@E@@@@"     HOLD THE NUMBER OF DIGITS AFTER THE HM
)@@G@@DECIMAL POINT.    @F@@@@"    DURING VALUE SCAN THIS IS USED UNDER THE NAHN
)@@G@@ME OPER TO HOLD   @D@@@@"     THE OPERATOR ASSOCIATED WITH THIS STACK ITHO
)@@G@@EM.   @G@@@@"    DURING SYMBOLIC SUBSTITUTION SCANNING THIS IS USED UNDEHP
)@@G@@R THE NAME  @E@@@@"     SFLG TO FLAG IF A STAR WAS SEEN ([*...] OR [...]HQ
)@@G@@).    @[@@@@"     @]@@@@" T3 - MSAV @H@@@@"    THIS IS USED TO SAVE THE HR
)@@G@@SCANNER MODE BITS WHEN THE STACK IS PUSHED.     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" SCANHS
)@@G@@NER STACKS.  THE POINTER OS\PTR IS USED TO INDEX INTO THE OPERATOR@G@@@@HT
)@@G@@" STACK 'OPSTK'.  NO ROUTINE WHICH EVER GIVES UP CONTROL OVER CHARACTER HU
)@@G@@@G@@@@" FETCH MAY USE A LOCAL BECAUSE OF SYMBOLIC SUBSTITUTION. THE POINHV
)@@G@@TER   @G@@@@" DS\PTR IS USED TO POINT TO A TEMPORARY DATA STACK FOR INTEHW
)@@G@@RMEDIATE    @^@@@@" EXPRESSION RESULTS.   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" SIZES FOR HX
)@@G@@THESE STACK SHOULD BE CHOSEN JUDICIOUSLY AS THEY@B@@@@" INCREASE THE SIZHY
)@@G@@E OF THE RESIDENT DBANK.@[@@@@"     @D@@@@DEFINE    OS\SIZE = 30; " MAX HZ
)@@G@@SIZE OF OPERATOR STACK  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DEFINE    DS\SIZE = 300; " MAXIA
)@@G@@ SIZE OF DATA STACK     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@DECLARE   OS\PTR: STATIC MACHIIB
)@@G@@NE POINTER WORD EXPORTED;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@DECLARE   DS\PTR: STATICIC
)@@G@@ MACHINE POINTER WORD EXPORTED;     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@DEFINE    STAR\VALID
)@@G@@UE = O'777777777777';   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS IS THE SCANNER LOCALS SIE
)@@G@@TACK.  THE AREAS NOT SPECIFICALY    @D@@@@" ASSIGNED TO DESCRIPTORS ARE IF
)@@G@@USED BY THE SCANNER.    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@DECLARE   *: BASED(OS\PTR) MAPIG
)@@G@@PED   @F@@@@              [BASE:  6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER  " ALSO DTYP(OSIH
)@@G@@\PTR) @F@@@@              ,*   :  6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER  " ALSO DSBT(OSII
)@@G@@\PTR) @F@@@@              ,STAT:  6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER  " SCANNER STATIJ
)@@G@@E     @G@@@@              ,DADL:  6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER  " DIGITS AFTERIK
)@@G@@ DECIMAL    @G@@@@              !OPER:  6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER  " VALUE IL
)@@G@@SCAN OPERATOR     @H@@@@              !SFLG:  6 BIT CONDITION         " IM
)@@G@@FLAG FOR STAR SEEN SYMB SUBST @G@@@@              ,MSAV:  12 BIT UNSIGNEIN
)@@G@@D INTEGER]; " SAVE FOR LOCAL\MODES  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THESE ITEM CONTRIO
)@@G@@OLS GLOBAL SCANNER MODES AND ARE SET WITH THE   @G@@@@" ARGUMENT TO SCANIP
)@@G@@.  THE PART UNDER 'LOCAL\MODES' IS PUSHED AND POPPED  @F@@@@" WITH THE SIQ
)@@G@@CANNER STACK AND THUS MAY BE DIFFERENT AT DIFFERENT   @A@@@@" LEVELS OF IR
)@@G@@THE SCANNING PROCESS.   @E@@@@" NOTE GLOBAL MODES IS LIMITED TO SIX BITSIS
)@@G@@ BY CODE AT TOP   @F@@@@" OF PROCEDURE SCAN IN ELEMENT SCANNER.   AGAIN IT
)@@G@@NOTE LOCAL\MODES  @E@@@@" IS LIMITED TO 12 BITS BY THE SAME CODE AND THEIU
)@@G@@ SIZE OF    @C@@@@" MSAV ON THE SCANNER LOCAL STACK (SEE ABOVE).  @[@@@@IV
)@@G@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@DECLARE   GLOBAL\MODES: STATIC INTEGER WORD EXPOIW
)@@G@@RTED ('SGMODE')   @^@@@@          !*:MAPPED     @C@@@@             [*: 3IX
)@@G@@0 BIT INTEGER " CANNOT USE    @H@@@@             ,CFLP: 1 BIT CONDITION IY
)@@G@@  " CONVERT INTEGER TO FLOATING POINT     @E@@@@             ,CTRM: 1 BIIZ
)@@G@@T CONDITION " CHECK TERM CHARACTER  @G@@@@             ,NSUB: 1 BIT CONDJA
)@@G@@ITION " INHIBIT SYMBOLIC SUBSTITUTION     @H@@@@             ,CFAC: 3 BIJB
)@@G@@T UNSIGNED INTEGER]; " CONVERSION FACTOR SPECIFIED    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@JC
)@@G@@DECLARE   LOCAL\MODES: STATIC INTEGER WORD EXPORTED ('SLMODE')    @^@@@@JD
)@@G@@          !*:MAPPED     @C@@@@             [*: 24 BIT INTEGER " CANNOT UJE
)@@G@@SE    @E@@@@             ,EVAL: 1 BIT CONDITION   " EVALUATE RESULT     JF
)@@G@@@F@@@@             ,COMA: 1 BIT CONDITION   " FLAG TO STOP ON COMMA     JG
)@@G@@@G@@@@             ,CDST: 1 BIT CONDITION   " CONVERT INTEGER TO DISTANCJH
)@@G@@E     @G@@@@             ,CNAM: 1 BIT CONDITION   " CONVERT INTEGER TO NJI
)@@G@@AME\LABEL   @F@@@@             ,CNUM: 1 BIT CONDITION   " NUMS BECOME CHJJ
)@@G@@ARS ON CAT  @G@@@@             ,CSTR: 1 BIT CONDITION   " CONVERT EVERYTJK
)@@G@@HING TO STRING    @F@@@@             ,ALLOW(6): 1 BIT CONDITION]; " FLAGJL
)@@G@@ FOR EACH TYPE    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" 'STATES' THE SCANNER CAN BE IN.  SJM
)@@G@@INCE SYMBOLIC SUBSTITUTION MAY@C@@@@" OCCUR AT ANY POINT THIS IS KEPT ONJN
)@@G@@ THE STACK. @[@@@@"     @B@@@@DEFINE    S\UNK = 1,   " UNKNOWN ITEM     JO
)@@G@@@A@@@@          S\NUM = 2,   " NUMERIC    @A@@@@          S\NAM = 3,   "JP
)@@G@@ NAME\LABEL @A@@@@          S\STR = 4,   " STRING     @C@@@@          S\JQ
)@@G@@STT = 5,   " STRING TERMINATION     @B@@@@          S\EXP = 6,   " VALUEJR
)@@G@@\EXPRESSION @B@@@@          S\SBS = 7,   " SUBSTITUTION     @D@@@@      JS
)@@G@@    S\CAL = 8,   " MACRO CALL LINE SCANNING     @D@@@@          S\FLD = JT
)@@G@@9;   " MACRO CALL FIELD SCANNING    @[@@@@"     @#@@@@" END OF SCAN-DEF JU
)@@G@@___ION@C@@@@" OCCUR AT ANY POINT THIS IS KEPT ON THE STACK. @[@@@@"     JV
)@@G@@@B@@@@DEFINE    S\UNK = 1,   " UNKNOWN ITEM     *[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@"     JW
)@@G@@@E@@@@" DECLARE THE ACTION TABLE, WHICH CONTAINS ONE ENTRY FOR    @D@@@@JX
)@@G@@" EACH OF THE 256 POSSIBLE DPS EXTENDED ASCII 8 BIT   @C@@@@" CHARACTERSJY
)@@G@@.  EACH TABLE ENTRY IS THE ROOT OF A@E@@@@" DPS BINARY TREE SYMBOL TABLEJZ
)@@G@@ CONTAINING ALL THE SPECIAL   @E@@@@" CHARACTER DEFINITIONS SUCH AS TAB,KA
)@@G@@ HYPHEN , NTB , ETC.    @C@@@@" THE FIRST CHARACTER OF A ONE- OR TWO-CHAKB
)@@G@@RACTER@E@@@@" SEQUENCE IS USED TO INDEX INTO ACTION TABLE, THUS THERE   KC
)@@G@@@C@@@@" MAY BE 256 BINARY TREES IF EACH CHARACTER HAS @B@@@@" SOME SPECIKD
)@@G@@AL ACTION DEFINED FOR IT.     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@DECLARE   *(256): MAPPEDKE

)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THESE ARE THE ERROR MESSAGE DEFINITIONS.  PLEASE USETH

)@@G@@" INVALID INTEGER GIVEN @E@@@@          ,ERROR\MAX\SYM = 4 " MAX NUMBER TO
)@@G@@OF COPIES EXCEEDED@G@@@@          ,ERROR\COMMAND\UNIMPLEMENTED = 5 " UNITP
)@@G@@MPLEMENTED COMMANDS     @G@@@@          ,ERROR\OUTPUT\SYNTAX = 6 " SYNTATQ

)@@G@@ = 7 " TRIED TO SPECIFY PROGRAM FILE ON OUTPUT  @H@@@@          ,ERROR\UTS
)@@G@@NRECOGNIZABLE\UDEF = 8 " COULD NOT PARSE UNIT DEFINITION    @]@@@@      TT
)@@G@@    ; @[@@@@"     @C@@@@DECLARE   *: MAPPED STATIC EXPORTED ('ERSUBC')  TU
)@@G@@@B@@@@          [ERROR\STATUS\CODE: WORD INTEGER@D@@@@          ![DIRECTTV
)@@G@@IVE\ERROR: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER,  @D@@@@            CONTROL\ERROR: 6 BTW
)@@G@@IT UNSIGNED INTEGER,    @D@@@@            SCANNER\ERROR: 6 BIT UNSIGNED TX
)@@G@@INTEGER,    @C@@@@            MACRO\ERROR: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER,@D@@@@TY

)@@G@@@I@@@@           ,[PRINT\ERROR\MSGS: 6 BIT CONDITION := TRUE " ON OFF ERUB
)@@G@@ROR PRINT FLAG    @B@@@@           ,*: 30 BIT CONDITION]] " UNUSED@]@@@@UC
)@@G@@           ;@[@@@@"     @ @@@@INCLUDE(LIJ\PLUS,NO SOURCE);  @[@@@@"     UD
)@@G@@@C@@@@PROCEDURE WARNING(MESSAGE\ID: WORD INTEGER)     @B@@@@          IMUE
)@@G@@PORTED ('I.DPS$WN.WARNING');  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE PRINT\ERROR\MSUF
)@@G@@G     @B@@@@          IMPORTED ('I.DPS$WN.PRTERRMSG');@[@@@@"     @]@@@@UG
)@@G@@RESUME;     @[@@@@"     @ @@@@INCLUDE(LIJ\SIM,NO SOURCE);   @[@@@@"     UH

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\TABLE\DIRECTIVE IMPORTEDUM

)@@G@@@D@@@@" DEFINE DATA ITEMS RETURNED FROM CONVERT ROUTINES.   @[@@@@"     UR
)@@G@@@G@@@@DECLARE   MONOCASE\IMAGE: MAPPED STATIC LOCATABLE EXPORTED ('MONAMUS
)@@G@@E')   @D@@@@            [MONOCASE\ASCII\CHAR(84): ASCII CHARACTER @D@@@@UT
)@@G@@            !MONOCASE\CHAR(84): 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER@D@@@@            UU
)@@G@@!MONOCASE\WORD(21): LOCATABLE INTEGER WORD@C@@@@            ,FIELDATA\CHUV
)@@G@@AR(84): 6 BIT LOGICAL   @D@@@@            !FIELDATA\WORD(14): WORD LOGICUW
)@@G@@AL LOCATABLE@B@@@@            ,NAME\LEN: INTEGER WORD];     @[@@@@"     UX
)@@G@@@G@@@@DECLARE   MONOCASE\DESCRIPTOR: STATIC LOCATABLE EXPORTED ('MODESC'UY
)@@G@@)     @^@@@@             MAPPED     @D@@@@             [*:   6 BIT UNSIGUZ
)@@G@@NED INTEGER := TYPSTR   @B@@@@             ,*:  30 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER VA
)@@G@@@D@@@@             ,MONOCASE\LEN: 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER   @F@@@@      VB
)@@G@@       ,*:  18 BIT MACHINE POINTER := LOC(MONOCASE\IMAGE)]; @[@@@@"     VC
)@@G@@@C@@@@DECLARE   MONOCASE\PTR: EXPORTED ('MODPTR')     @G@@@@            VD
)@@G@@ STATIC MACHINE WORD POINTER := LOC(MONOCASE\DESCRIPTOR);   @[@@@@"     VE
)@@G@@@G@@@@DECLARE   *(3): WORD INTEGER STATIC LOCATABLE EXPORTED ('ASCINUMBEVF
)@@G@@R')   @E@@@@          ! NUMBER\IN\ASCII(12): 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER;    VG
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @^@@@@" END OF CONVERT-DEF    ___@@[CATABLE EXPORTED ('MONAMVH
)@@G@@E')   @E@^@#DECLARE   *: MAPPED STATIC LOCATABLE EXPORTED ('MONAME')    VI
)@@G@@@G@ @^DECLARE   MONOCASE*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROC DEFINEVJ
)@@G@@S THE FIELDS IN A DESCRIPTOR AND IN A SYMBOL    @E@@@@" TABLE ENTRY, AS VK
)@@G@@WELL AS THE TYPES RETURNED BY THE SCANNER.@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" THIS IS THVL
)@@G@@E FORMAT OF A BASIC DPS DESCRIPTOR. @[@@@@"     @I@@@@"                 VM
)@@G@@ -------------------------------------------------------------    @I@@@@VN
)@@G@@"                  :  DTYP   :  DSBT   :         :         :         :  VO
)@@G@@       :    @I@@@@"                  -----------------------------------VP
)@@G@@--------------------------    @I@@@@"                  :            DLENVQ
)@@G@@             :            DADR             :    @I@@@@"                 VR
)@@G@@ -------------------------------------------------------------    @[@@@@VS
)@@G@@"     @#@@@@" THE FIELDS ARE: @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" DTYP - THE 'TYPE' FOR VT
)@@G@@THE DATA ITEM REPRESENTED.    @D@@@@" DSBT - THE 'SUBTYPE' FOR THE DATA VU
)@@G@@ITEM REPRESENTED. @D@@@@" DLEN - THE 'LENGTH' OF THE DATA ITEM REPRESENTVV
)@@G@@ED.   @C@@@@" DADR - THE CORE ADDRESS OF THE DATA ITEM.     @[@@@@"     VW
)@@G@@@B@@@@" THE FORMAT OF A SYMBOL TABLE ENTRY:     @[@@@@"     @I@@@@"     VX
)@@G@@             -----------------------------------------------------------VY
)@@G@@--    @I@@@@"                  :  DTYP   :  DSBT   :  DCTL   :  STYP   :VZ
)@@G@@  SLEN   :  SBAL   :    @I@@@@"                  -----------------------WA
)@@G@@--------------------------------------    @I@@@@"                  :    WB
)@@G@@        DLEN             :            DADR             :    @I@@@@"     WC
)@@G@@             -----------------------------------------------------------WD
)@@G@@--    @I@@@@"                  :                           SMAD         WE
)@@G@@                   :    @I@@@@"                  -----------------------WF
)@@G@@--------------------------------------    @I@@@@"                  :    WG
)@@G@@        SLLK             :            SRLK             :    @I@@@@"     WH
)@@G@@             -----------------------------------------------------------WI
)@@G@@--    @I@@@@"                  :                           SNAM         WJ
)@@G@@                   :    @I@@@@"                  -----------------------WK
)@@G@@--------------------------------------    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" FIELD DEFIWL
)@@G@@NITIONS:    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" DTYP - TYPE OF DATA ITEM    @ @@@@" DSBTWM
)@@G@@ - SUBTYPE OF DATA ITEM @E@@@@" DCTL - USED BY CONTROL PROCEDURES FOR ACWN
)@@G@@TION TABLE TREES  @A@@@@" STYP - TYPE OF SNAM (SYMBOL NAME) @D@@@@" SLENWO
)@@G@@ - LENGTH OF SNAM (SYMBOL NAME) IN WORDS (1-63) @B@@@@" SBAL - BALANCE FWP
)@@G@@ACTOR FOR BINARY TREE   @ @@@@" DLEN - DATA ITEM LENGTH     @A@@@@" DADRWQ
)@@G@@ - CORE ADDRESS OF DATA ITEM  @C@@@@" SMAD - MASS STORAGE ADDRESS IF DATWR
)@@G@@A ITEM PAGED@A@@@@" SLLK - 'LEFT' LINK FOR BINARY TREE@A@@@@" SRLK - 'RIWS
)@@G@@TE' LINK FOR BINARY TREE@D@@@@" SNAM - SYMBOL NAME LJSF ASCII (SLEN WORDWT
)@@G@@S LONG)     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   KLUGE: STATIC MACHINE POINTER EXWU
)@@G@@PORTED;     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS GLOBAL POINTER IS SET TO THE DESCRIWV
)@@G@@PTOR RETURNED BY THE    @D@@@@" SCANNER.  THIS IS ACTUALLY SOMEWHERE ON WW
)@@G@@THE STACK.  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   SCANNED: STATIC MACHINE POINTER WX
)@@G@@EXPORTED;   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   CURDESC(2): WORD INTEGER BASED(SWY
)@@G@@CANNED);    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" THIS IS THE ROOT OF THE GLOBAL SYMBOL TAWZ
)@@G@@BLE.  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@DECLARE   GLOBAL\SYMBOLS: STATIC LOCATABLE MACHIXA
)@@G@@NE POINTER WORD   @ @@@@          EXPORTED('GLOBAL'); @[@@@@"     @C@@@@XB
)@@G@@" THIS IS THE ROOT OF THE COMMAND SYMBOL TREE   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@DECLARXC
)@@G@@E   COMMAND\SYMBOLS: STATIC LOCATABLE MACHINE POINTER WORD  @ @@@@      XD
)@@G@@    EXPORTED ('COMSYM');@[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THIS IS THE ROOT OF THE SYSTXE
)@@G@@EM-DEFINED SYMBOL TREE. @[@@@@"     @F@@@@DECLARE   SYSTEM\SYMBOLS: STATXF
)@@G@@IC LOCATABLE MACHINE POINTER WORD   @ @@@@          EXPORTED ('SYSSYM');XG
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS DESCRIPTOR IS SET TO THE VALUES DEFINED AT SCANXH
)@@G@@NED   @A@@@@" JUST BEFORE THE SCANNER RETURNS.  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@DECLARXI
)@@G@@E   CSDESC(2): WORD INTEGER STATIC EXPORTED ('CSDESC')@E@@@@          ![XJ
)@@G@@CSDTYP:  6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER    " ITEM TYPE  @E@@@@           ,CSDSBTXK
)@@G@@:  6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER    " SUB TYPE   @E@@@@           ,*     :  6 BXL
)@@G@@IT UNSIGNED INTEGER    " RESERVED   @E@@@@           ,*     :18 BIT UNSIXM
)@@G@@GNED INTEGER     " RESERVED   @F@@@@           ,CSDLEN:18 BIT UNSIGNED IXN
)@@G@@NTEGER     " LENGTH OF ITEM   @F@@@@           ,CSDADR:18 BIT MACHINE POXO
)@@G@@INTER];    " TO ITEM TEXT     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" STANDARD DESCRIPTOR   XP
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@DEFINE    DESC\LEN = 2;               " LENGTH OF DESCXQ
)@@G@@RIPTOR@ @@@@DECLARE   *: BASED MAPPED     @F@@@@             [DTYP: 6 BIXR
)@@G@@T UNSIGNED INTEGER   " SEE TYPES BELOW    @D@@@@             ,DSBT: 6 BIXS
)@@G@@T UNSIGNED INTEGER   " SUBTYPE@H@@@@             ,DCTL: 6 BIT UNSIGNED IXT
)@@G@@NTEGER   " CONTROL TYPE FOR ACTION\TABLE  @A@@@@             !*: " CONTRXU
)@@G@@OL BITS     @G@@@@                [DREF: 1 BIT CONDITION " FORWARD REFERXV
)@@G@@ENCE VARIABLE     @C@@@@                ,*(5): 1 BIT CONDITION " UNUSED XW
)@@G@@@#@@@@                ] @G@@@@             ,*   :18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGERXX
)@@G@@   " RESERVED FOR SCAN\SYMTAB @F@@@@             ,DLEN:18 BIT UNSIGNED IXY
)@@G@@NTEGER   " LENGTH OF ITEM     @E@@@@             ,DADR:18 BIT MACHINE POXZ
)@@G@@INTER ]; " TO ITEM TEXT @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" STANDARD REFERENCE VARIABLESYA
)@@G@@ FOR DESCRIPED DATA ITEMS.  BECAUSE PLUS  @G@@@@" DOES NOT ALLOW EXPLICIYB
)@@G@@TLY BASED REPLICATED ARRAYS THE POINTER KLUGE   @E@@@@" MUST BE SET TO DYC
)@@G@@ADR(WHATEVER) BEFORE THESE ARE REFERENCED.@[@@@@"     @E@@@@DECLARE   DNYD
)@@G@@UM(*): LOCATABLE INTEGER WORD BASED(KLUGE);     @D@@@@DECLARE   DDST(*):YE
)@@G@@ LOCATABLE DISTANCE BASED(KLUGE);   @D@@@@DECLARE   DFLP(*): LOCATABLE FYF
)@@G@@LOATING BASED(KLUGE);   @E@@@@DECLARE   DWORD(*): LOCATABLE INTEGER WORDYG
)@@G@@ BASED(KLUGE);    @E@@@@DECLARE   DCHR(*): 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER BASED(YH
)@@G@@KLUGE);     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THE DESCRIPTOR MAY OR MAY NOT BE COINCIDYI
)@@G@@ENT WITH A SYMBOL @F@@@@" TABLE ENTRY.  THE CORE ADDRESSES WILL BE THE SYJ
)@@G@@AME,  SO THE SAME @B@@@@" POINTERS MAY BE USED TO REFERENCE THEM. @[@@@@YK
)@@G@@"     @G@@@@DEFINE    STH\LEN = 4;                " LENGTH OF SYMBOL TABYL
)@@G@@LE HEADER   @ @@@@DECLARE   *: BASED MAPPED     @F@@@@             [*   YM
)@@G@@: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER   " TYPE FLAG FOR VALUE@E@@@@             ,*   YN
)@@G@@: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER   " SUBTYPE FLAG @E@@@@             ,*   : 6 BIYO
)@@G@@T UNSIGNED INTEGER   " (EQU TREE)   @F@@@@             ,STYP: 6 BIT UNSIYP
)@@G@@GNED INTEGER   " SYMBOL NAME TYPE   @G@@@@             ,SLEN: 6 BIT UNSIYQ
)@@G@@GNED INTEGER   " NAME OR SUBSCRIPT LENGTH @G@@@@             ,SBAL: 6 BIYR
)@@G@@T   SIGNED INTEGER   " BALANCE FACTOR FOR TREE  @G@@@@             ,*   YS
)@@G@@:18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER   " LENGTH FIELD FOR VALUE   @F@@@@            YT
)@@G@@ ,*   :18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER   " POINTER TO VALUE   @G@@@@            YU
)@@G@@ ,SMAD: LOCATABLE INTEGER WORD   " DRUM ADDRESS IF PAGED    @F@@@@      YV
)@@G@@       ,SLLK:18 BIT MACHINE POINTER    " LEFT LINK IN TABLE @F@@@@      YW
)@@G@@       ,SRLK:18 BIT MACHINE POINTER    " RITE LINK IN TABLE @F@@@@      YX
)@@G@@       ,SNAM: LOCATABLE INTEGER WORD]; " ACTUAL SYMBOL NAME @[@@@@"     YY
)@@G@@@A@@@@" TYPES MAY APPEAR IN DTYP FIELD:   @F@@@@" THE VALUES OF THESE NUYZ
)@@G@@MBERS MUST!!! AGREE WITH THOSE IN ELEMENT @#@@@@" SYS-SYMBOLS.    @G@@@@ZA
)@@G@@" NOTE THAT LAST\USER\TYPE MUST BE UPDATED IF ANY MORE USER DATA TYPES  ZB
)@@G@@@]@@@@" ARE ADDED.@[@@@@"     @F@@@@DEFINE    TYPNUL = 0,               ZC
)@@G@@  " NOTHING FOUND (BY SCANNER)@D@@@@          TYPNAM = 1,               ZD
)@@G@@  " NAME - LABEL  @D@@@@          TYPINT = 2,                 " PURE INTZE
)@@G@@EGER  @E@@@@          TYPDST = 3,                 " DISTANCE (QUALIFIED)ZF
)@@G@@@D@@@@          TYPSTR = 4,                 " ASCII STRING  @G@@@@      ZG
)@@G@@    TYPTAB = 5,                 " 'TABLE' (SYMBOL TABLE ONLY)     @B@@@@ZH
)@@G@@          TYPFLP = 6, " FLOATING POINT    @H@@@@          TYPOPR = 7,   ZI
)@@G@@              " 'OPERATOR' (SCANNER INTERNAL ONLY)    @E@@@@          TYZJ
)@@G@@PFUN = 8,                 " INTERNAL FUNCTION   @G@@@@          TYPXVR =ZK
)@@G@@ 9;                 " EXECUTED VARIABLE (SEE SCANNER) @[@@@@"     @G@@@@ZL
)@@G@@" ALL DATA TYPES PASSED TO A USER MUST HAVE INDICIES LE LAST\USER\TYPE  ZM
)@@G@@@F@@@@" LARGER INDICIES ARE RESERVED FOR USE INSIDE THE SCANNER ONLY.   ZN
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @G@@@@DEFINE    LAST\USER\TYPE = TYPFLP; " LAST USER TYPE ISZO
)@@G@@ FLOATING POINT   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" SUBTYPES ARE AS FOLLOWS:    @[@@@@ZP
)@@G@@"     @B@@@@" IF TYPE IS INTEGER, SUBTYPE 0 IS DECIMAL@B@@@@"           ZQ
)@@G@@          SUBTYPE 1 IS OCTAL  @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" IF TYPE IS NAME, SUBTYZR
)@@G@@PE 0 SAYS DOES NOT END WITH $. (USER SYMBOL)    @G@@@@"                 ZS
)@@G@@ SUBTYPE 1 SAYS SYMBOL ENDS WITH $. (SYSTEM SYMBOL)   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@ZT
)@@G@@" IF TYPE IS TYPDST, SUBTYPE 0 SAYS MIXED UNITS @C@@@@"                 ZU
)@@G@@   ELSE SUBTYPE IS CF\WHATEVER@[@@@@"     @E@@@@DEFINE     CF\PICA = 1  ZV
)@@G@@              " USE PICA FACTOR     @E@@@@          ,CF\POINT= 2        ZW
)@@G@@        " USE POINT FACTOR    @E@@@@          ,CF\INCH = 3              ZX
)@@G@@  " USE INCH FACTOR     @F@@@@          ,CF\CM   = 4                " USZY
)@@G@@E CENTIMETER FACTOR     @E@@@@          ,CF\SKIP = 5                " USZZ
)@@G@@E LINE SKIP FACTOR@F@@@@          ,CF\COL  = 6 ;              " USE COLUAA
)@@G@@MN SKIP FACTOR    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" TYPE INDICES FOR DPS INTERNAL FUNCAB
)@@G@@TIONS.@[@@@@"     @G@@@@DEFINE      FUN\LEN = 1                 " LEN$ (AC
)@@G@@ITEM LENGTH) FUNCTION   @C@@@@          ,FUN\INPUT = 2               " IAD
)@@G@@NPUT$ @E@@@@          ,FUN\WID  = 3                " CWIDTH$ FUNCTION   AE
)@@G@@@I@@@@          ,FUN\CHAR  = 4               " CHAR$ FUNCTION CONVERTS NAF
)@@G@@UMBERS TO CHAR    @I@@@@          ,FUN\UC    = 5              " UC$ CONVAG
)@@G@@ERTS TO UPPER CASEUMBERS TO CHAR    @F@@@@          ,FUN\DEF  = 6     " AH
)@@G@@DEF$ CHECKS IF VARIABLE IS DEFINED. @F@@@@          ,FUN\ARG  = 7     " AI
)@@G@@ARG$ RETURNS MACRO ARG AS STRING.   @E@@@@          ,FUN\LTRIM = 8 " LTRAJ
)@@G@@IM$ - TRIM STRING FROM LEFT   @E@@@@          ,FUN\RTRIM = 9 " RTRIM$ - AK
)@@G@@TRIM STRING FROM RIGHT  @F@@@@          ,FUN\TRIM = 10 " TRIM$ - TRIM STAL

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THESE ARE THE FUNCTION CODESIM
)@@G@@ OF THE INTERMEDIATE LANGUAGE @E@@@@" THAT CAN BE PUT IN THE OUTPUT LINEIN
)@@G@@ INTERSPERSED WITH TEXT.@F@@@@" THEY CAN BE DIFFERENTIATED FROM TEXT CHAIO
)@@G@@RACTERS BECAUSE THE     @E@@@@" MAXIMUM TEXT CODE IS 255.  THESE CODES SIP
)@@G@@TART AT 400 HENCE @F@@@@" A FUNCTION ALWAYS HAS THE 9'TH BIT OF THE QUARIQ
)@@G@@TER WORD SET AND  @G@@@@" A TEXT CHARACTER ALWAYS HAS THE 9'TH BIT OF THIR
)@@G@@E QUARTER WORD CLEAR    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@DEFINE    FUNC\OFFSET      = 4IS
)@@G@@00, " BEGINNING OF FUNCTIONS  @A@@@@          FUNC\NOP         = 401,   IT
)@@G@@@D@@@@          FUNC\HEIGHT      = 402, " INTERNAL LEADING  @F@@@@      IU
)@@G@@    FUNC\WIDTH       = 403, " CHARACTER WIDTH OR POINT SIZE @E@@@@      IV
)@@G@@    FUNC\FONT        = 404,              " FONT CHANGE@D@@@@          FUIW
)@@G@@NC\FLUSH       = 405, " FLUSH FROM HERE   @E@@@@          FUNC\BLANK    IX
)@@G@@   = 406, " NONEXPANDABLE BLANK     @C@@@@          FUNC\BACKSPACE   = 4IY
)@@G@@07, " BACKSPACE   @C@@@@          FUNC\LEAD        = 408, " LEADING     IZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          FUNC\LEADU       = 409, " UNCONDITIONAL LEADING   @E@@@@JA
)@@G@@          FUNC\UNDERLINE   = 410, " BEGIN OR END UNDERLINE  @E@@@@      JB
)@@G@@    FUNC\TRANSPARENT = 411, " LINK TO TRANSPARENT DATA@B@@@@          FUJC
)@@G@@NC\TAB         = 412, " DO TAB@E@@@@          FUNC\LETTER\SPACE = 413, "JD
)@@G@@ DEFINE LETTER SPACING  @D@@@@          FUNC\CENTER      = 414, " CENTERJE
)@@G@@ CHARACTER  @C@@@@          FUNC\EOL         = 415, " END OF LINE @D@@@@JF
)@@G@@          FUNC\HYPHEN      = 416, " HYPHEN CONTROL    @D@@@@          FUJG
)@@G@@NC\BREAK       = 417, " NO HYPHEN BREAK   @D@@@@          FUNC\SPACEBANDJH
)@@G@@   = 418, " EXPANDABLE BLANK  @G@@@@          FUNC\DSIB        = 419, " JI
)@@G@@DISPLAY SUPERIOR/INFERIOR BEGIN     @G@@@@          FUNC\DSIS        = 4JJ
)@@G@@20, " DISPLAY SUPERIOR/INFERIOR SWITCH    @F@@@@          FUNC\DSIE     JK
)@@G@@   = 421, " DISPLAY SUPERIOR/INFERIOR END +@@@@[+@@@@@@D@@@@          FUJL
)@@G@@NC\VSB         = 422; " VERTICAL SPACEBAND@[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THE FOLLOWJM
)@@G@@ING FUNCTIONS ARE NEVER PUT INTO THE LINE @C@@@@" BUT ARE SAVED FOR EXECJN
)@@G@@UTION AT THE END OF THE @#@@@@" OUTPUT LINE.    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@DEFINEJO
)@@G@@     EOL\FUNC\NOP          = 100    @B@@@@          ,EOL\FUNC\LEFT\FLAG JP
)@@G@@   = 101    @B@@@@          ,EOL\FUNC\RIGHT\FLAG   = 102    @B@@@@      JQ

)@@G@@NT = 104    @B@@@@          ,EOL\FUNC\CENTER       = 105    @B@@@@      JS
)@@G@@    ,EOL\FUNC\RIGHT\FLUSH  = 106    @B@@@@          ,EOL\FUNC\HYPHEN    JT
)@@G@@   = 107    @B@@@@          ,EOL\FUNC\JUSTIFY      = 108    @B@@@@      JU
)@@G@@    ,EOL\FUNC\FILL         = 109    @B@@@@          ,EOL\FUNC\COMPACT   JV
)@@G@@   = 110    @]@@@@          ; @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THE FOLLOWING FUNCTIONJW
)@@G@@S ARE SAVED FOR EXECUTION AT THE END@ @@@@" OF AN INPUT SCRIPT LINE.    JX
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@DEFINE     EOI\FUNC\NOP         = 200     @B@@@@      JY
)@@G@@    ,EOI\FUNC\CENTER      = 201     @B@@@@          ,EOI\FUNC\RIGHT\FLUSJZ
)@@G@@H = 202     @B@@@@          ,EOI\FUNC\FILL        = 203     @B@@@@      KA
)@@G@@    ,EOI\FUNC\COMPACT     = 204     @B@@@@          ,EOI\FUNC\NOSPACE   KB
)@@G@@  = 205     @]@@@@          ; @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THE FOLLOWING FUNCTIONKC
)@@G@@S ARE SAVED FOR EXECUTION AT THE TOP@#@@@@" OF THE PAGE.    @[@@@@"     KD
)@@G@@@B@@@@DEFINE     TOP\FUNC\OFFSET          = 300 @B@@@@          ,TOP\FUNKE
)@@G@@C\AREA\VPOS\START = 301 @B@@@@          ,TOP\FUNC\AREA\HEIGHT     = 302 KF
)@@G@@@B@@@@          ,TOP\FUNC\FOOTNOTE        = 303 @]@@@@          ; @[@@@@KG
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@" END OF GETPUT-DEF     ___@@@    ,TOP\FUNC\AREA\VPOS\START KH
)@@G@@= 301 @B@@@@          ,TOP\FUNC\AREA\HEIGHT     = 302 @B@@@@          ,TKI
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\FINAL\DEVICE\HANDLER KJ
)@@G@@IMPORTED ('INILZE');    @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @G@@@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\KK
)@@G@@LEADING(LED: DISTANCE, FUNC: 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER)  @G@@@@           IKL
)@@G@@MPORTED ('PERLED');       " ACCUMULATE AND SET FUNCTION     @[@@@@      KM
)@@G@@@G@@@@PROCEDURE INSERT\LEADING(LED: DISTANCE, FUNC: 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGKN
)@@G@@ER)   @G@@@@           IMPORTED ('INSLED');       " ACCUMULATE AND SET FKO
)@@G@@UNCTION     @[@@@@      @B@@@@PROCEDURE OUTPUT\LEADING(LEAD: DISTANCE)  KP
)@@G@@@D@@@@           IMPORTED ('OUTLED'); " CALL FINAL DEVICE   @[@@@@      KQ
)@@G@@@C@@@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\PAGEUP IMPORTED ('PERPUP');   @[@@@@      @C@@@@KR
)@@G@@PROCEDURE OUTPUT\TO\DEVICE IMPORTED ('OUTDEV'); @[@@@@      @D@@@@PROCEDKS
)@@G@@URE PROCESS\START\OF\TAKE IMPORTED ('PROSOT');  @[@@@@      @D@@@@PROCEDKT
)@@G@@URE PROCESS\END\OF\TAKE IMPORTED ('PROEOT');    @[@@@@      @E@@@@PROCEDKU
)@@G@@URE OUTPUT\HARDWARE\FONT\CHANGE IMPORTED ('FONTC');   @[@@@@      @F@@@@KV

)@@G@@NGE');@[@@@@      @E@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\INTERNAL\FONT\CHANGE IMPORTED KY
)@@G@@('CKFONT'); @[@@@@      @G@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\INTERNAL\TYPESIZE\CHANGEKZ

)@@G@@GIN IMPORTED ('FDHDSIB');     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\DSI\SWLB

)@@G@@F\LINE IMPORTED ('DEVICEOL'); @[@@@@      @C@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\DEVICELE
)@@G@@\TRANSPARENT\OUTPUT     @B@@@@              IMPORTED ('DEVICETRANS');   LF

)@@G@@);    @[@@@@      @D@@@@PROCEDURE JUSTIFY\THE\LINE IMPORTED ('JUSTIFYLINLH
)@@G@@E');  @[@@@@"     @#@@@@" END OF FD-PROCS @[@@@@"     ___@@@      @D@@@@LI

)@@G@@" END OF FD-PROCS @[@@@@"     ___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@LK
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@"     @F@@@@DECLARE   LINES\PER\INCH: WORD INTEGER STALL
)@@G@@TIC EXPORTED ('LPI');   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" THE FOLLOWING CELLS ARE LOCALM
)@@G@@L TO EACH AREA    @[@@@@"     @G@@@@DECLARE   FOOTING\AREA: MAPPED STATILN
)@@G@@C LOCATABLE EXPORTED ('FOOTAREA')   @]@@@@          [ @D@@@@           *LO
)@@G@@: WORD INTEGER := 0       " SAVE\TEXT\PTR @D@@@@          ,*: WORD INTEGLP
)@@G@@ER := 0       " SAVE\WALAB\PTR@D@@@@          ,*: DISTANCE := 0         LQ
)@@G@@  " GUTTER\WIDTH  @D@@@@          ,*: DISTANCE := 0           " LEFT INDLR
)@@G@@ENT   @D@@@@          ,*: DISTANCE := 0           " RIGHT\INDENT  @[@@@@LS
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER := 1 " NUMBER\OF\COLUMNLT
)@@G@@S     @E@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER := 1 " COLUMN\NUMBER   LU
)@@G@@@D@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT CONDITION := TRUE  " JUSTIFY ON   @D@@@@      LV
)@@G@@    ,*: 6 BIT CONDITION := FALSE " HYPHEN OFF   @D@@@@          ,*: 6 BILW
)@@G@@T CONDITION := FALSE " NOSPACE OFF  @F@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT CONDITION LX
)@@G@@:= FALSE " JUSTIFY\FROM\RIGHT OFF   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          ,*: 6 BILY
)@@G@@T CONDITION := FALSE " UNUSED OFF   @D@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT CONDITION LZ
)@@G@@:= TRUE  " COMPACT ON   @C@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT CONDITION := TRUE  " FMA
)@@G@@ILL ON@D@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT CONDITION := FALSE " CENTER OFF   @D@@@@MB
)@@G@@          ,*: 6 BIT CONDITION := FALSE " RIGHTF OFF   @E@@@@          ,*MC
)@@G@@: 6 BIT CONDITION := FALSE " AREA\UNDERLINE OFF @[@@@@"     @D@@@@      MD
)@@G@@    ,*: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER := 3  " AREA\TYPE@E@@@@          ,*: 6 BIME
)@@G@@T CONDITION := TRUE  " DISTRIBUTION ON    @D@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT CONDMF
)@@G@@ITION := FALSE " BALANCING OFF@E@@@@          ,*: 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGEMG
)@@G@@R := 0 " COLUMN\LIST\PTR@[@@@@"     @D@@@@          ,*: DISTANCE := 0   MH
)@@G@@        " AREA\HEIGHT   @D@@@@          ,*: DISTANCE := 0           " ARMI
)@@G@@EA\WIDTH    @D@@@@          ,*: DISTANCE := 0           " AREA\REL\VPOS MJ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          ,*: DISTANCE := 0           " AREA\VPOS\START     @[@@@@MK
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT LOGICAL   := O'0'  " AREA\CONTROL\WORD  ML
)@@G@@@F@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT CONDITION := FALSE " INHIBIT\DISTRIBUTION OFF MM
)@@G@@@F@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT CONDITION := FALSE " AREA\END\PENDING OFF     MN
)@@G@@@E@@@@          ,*: 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER := 0 " FIXED\AREA\PTR @[@@@@MO
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@          ,*: WORD INTEGER := 0        " AREA\LINK\PTR@D@@@@MP
)@@G@@          ,*: DISTANCE := 0            " AREA\VPOS    @D@@@@          ,*MQ
)@@G@@: DISTANCE := 0            " LEFT\OFFSET  @^@@@@                      ];MR
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @F@@@@DECLARE   TEXT\AREA: MAPPED STATIC LOCATABLE EXPORTED MS
)@@G@@('TEXTAREA')@]@@@@          [ @D@@@@           *: WORD INTEGER := 0     MT

)@@G@@T CONDITION := TRUE  " JUSTIFY ON   @D@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT CONDITION NA
)@@G@@:= FALSE " HYPHEN OFF   @D@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT CONDITION := FALSE " NNB

)@@G@@RIGHT OFF   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          ,*: 6 BIT CONDITION := FALSE " UND

)@@G@@T CONDITION := FALSE " AREA\END\PENDING OFF     @H@@@@          ,*: 18 BNS

)@@G@@    DPS\EXITED = 0, " DPS SIGNED OFF NORMALLY   @C@@@@          DPS\COMMTF
)@@G@@AND = 1, " IN COMMAND MODE    @C@@@@          DPS\EDITING = 2, " IN TEXTTG

)@@G@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED;     @@@@@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE FORCE\END\OF\PARAGRABT
)@@G@@PH IMPORTED ('FOREOL'); @@@@@@@F@@@@PROCEDURE FORCE\END\OF\PAGE IMPORTEDBU
)@@G@@ ('FOREOP'); " END-OF-PAGE    @@@@@@@B@@@@PROCEDURE CLOSE\TOC EXPORTED (BV
)@@G@@'CLSTOC')   @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          IF FORMATTING AND   @B@@@@      BW
)@@G@@       TOC\PACKET NE NULL\PTR AND   @ @@@@             TOC\OPEN THEN    BX
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             CLOSE\FILE(TOC\PACKET);@A@@@@BY
)@@G@@             IMAGE\PTR := NULL\PTR; @A@@@@             IF LINK\TO\TOC NEBZ
)@@G@@ 0 AND@F@@@@                LINK\TO\TOC NE START\DRUM\ADDR(TOC\PACKET) TCA
)@@G@@HEN   @^@@@@              BEGIN     @E@@@@                LINK\TO\TOC :=CB
)@@G@@: START\DRUM\ADDR(TOC\PACKET);@E@@@@                INITIALIZE\FILE(%TOCCC
)@@G@@\PACKET, %IMAGE\PTR,    @C@@@@                   START\DRUM\ADDR(TOC\PACCD
)@@G@@KET));@F@@@@                RELEASE\FILE(TOC\PACKET);   " RELEASE OLD TOCE
)@@G@@C     @E@@@@                START\DRUM\ADDR(TOC\PACKET) := LINK\TO\TOC; CF
)@@G@@@#@@@@              END;@G@@@@             LINK\TO\TOC := START\DRUM\ADDCG
)@@G@@R(TOC\PACKET); " SET NEW LINK @A@@@@             TOC\OPEN := FALSE;     CH
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@TERM; ___THE@A@@@@            CI
)@@G@@ TOC\OPEN := FALSE;     @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@TERM; CJ

)@@G@@GE\CONTROL\SIZE = 4;    @@@@@@@F@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\PAGE(%PAGE\CONTCQ
)@@G@@ROL: MACHINE WORD POINTER,    @E@@@@           %CORE\ADDRESS: MACHINE WOCR

)@@G@@" THIS MODULE HANDLES ADDITION, SUBTRACTION, MULTIPLICATION, DIVISION   ER
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@E@@@@          COES
)@@G@@PY ('CHAR-SIZE',IMPORTED); " GET CONV\FACTORS   @B@@@@          COPY ('OET

)@@G@@WORD) IMPORTED ('PUTWRD');    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTEDEX
)@@G@@;     @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS OPERAEY
)@@G@@TION IS CALLED TO EXECUTE ADDITION AND SUBTRACTION    @F@@@@" ARITHMETICEZ
)@@G@@ OPERATORS.  THE ARGUMENTS MUST BE INTEGER OR DISTANCE@F@@@@" AND OF THEFA
)@@G@@ SAME SIZE.  THE RESULT IS THE SAME SHAPE AS THE ARGS @E@@@@" AND CONSISFB
)@@G@@TS OF THE CORRESPONDING ITEMS OPERATED UPON.    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDFC
)@@G@@URE ADD\OPS(OP: INTEGER WORD) EXPORTED    @[@@@@BEGIN @^@@@@          LFFD
)@@G@@AC := 1;    @^@@@@          RFAC := 1;    @C@@@@          IF LTYP EQ TYPFE
)@@G@@NUL THEN " UNARY SIGN   @D@@@@           BEGIN " TO MAKE LEFTARG LOOK LIFF
)@@G@@KE ZERO     @D@@@@             LTYP := RTYP; " BUT SAME SHAPE AS RITEARGFG
)@@G@@@ @@@@             LSBT := RSBT;    @ @@@@             LCTR := RCTR;    FH
)@@G@@@D@@@@             LPTR := RPTR; " POINT AT RIGHT VALUE BUT @D@@@@      FI
)@@G@@       LFAC := 0; " SET FACTOR TO MAKE ZERO     @A@@@@           END; " FJ
)@@G@@OF UNARY OP CODE  @C@@@@          IF LCTR NE RCTR THEN " CANNOT DO IT   FK
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR6;     FL
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@          ELSE    @D@@@@             IF LTFM
)@@G@@YP EQ TYPINT AND RTYP EQ TYPINT OR  @D@@@@                LTYP EQ TYPDSTFN
)@@G@@ AND RTYP EQ TYPDST THEN@A@@@@                DTYP(OS\PTR) := LTYP@#@@@@FO
)@@G@@             ELSE @E@@@@                IF LTYP EQ TYPINT AND RTYP EQ TYFP
)@@G@@PDST THEN   @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @D@@@@                   LSBT FQ
)@@G@@:= CFAC; " SET LEFT SUBTYPE   @E@@@@                   LFAC := CONV\FACTFR
)@@G@@ORS(CFAC); " SET FACTOR @B@@@@                   DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPDST;FS
)@@G@@@^@@@@                 END    @^@@@@                ELSE    @E@@@@      FT
)@@G@@             IF LTYP EQ TYPDST AND RTYP EQ TYPINT THEN@ @@@@            FU
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @D@@@@                      RSBT := CFAC; " SET RITE SFV
)@@G@@UBTYPE@F@@@@                      RFAC := CONV\FACTORS(CFAC); " AND FACTFW
)@@G@@OR    @C@@@@                      DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPDST;   @^@@@@      FX
)@@G@@              END @^@@@@                   ELSE @C@@@@                  FY
)@@G@@    SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR7;  @C@@@@          IF LSBT EQ RSBT THEN " SUBFZ
)@@G@@TYPES AGREE @A@@@@             DSBT(OS\PTR) := RSBT;  @D@@@@          IFGA
)@@G@@ SCANNER\ERROR EQ 0 THEN " OK TO DO IT    @A@@@@             IF OP EQ OPGB
)@@G@@RADD THEN   @B@@@@                FOR I := 1 TO RCTR DO     @E@@@@      GC
)@@G@@             PUT\WORD( LFAC*LNUM(I) + RFAC*RNUM(I) ); @#@@@@            GD
)@@G@@ ELSE @A@@@@                IF OP EQ OPRSUB THEN@B@@@@                  GE
)@@G@@ FOR I := 1 TO RCTR DO  @F@@@@                      PUT\WORD( LFAC*LNUM(GF
)@@G@@I) - RFAC*RNUM(I) );    @^@@@@                ELSE    @ @@@@            GG
)@@G@@       ERROR;     @#@@@@END; " OF ADD\OP  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@GH
)@@G@@"     @G@@@@" IF LEFT AND RIGHT ARGS ARE NULL THEN IS NILADIC STAR.  FORGI
)@@G@@ ARGUMENT   @E@@@@" SUBSTITUTION THIS WILL BE GIVEN THE VALUE STAR\VALUEGJ
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE STAR\OP EXPORTED    @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@GK
)@@G@@          IF LTYP EQ TYPNUL AND RTYP EQ TYPNUL THEN " STAROP@C@@@@      GL
)@@G@@     BEGIN " TO SET VALUE WE CAN RECOGNIZE@D@@@@             DTYP(OS\PTRGM
)@@G@@) := TYPINT; " TYPE INTEGER   @A@@@@             PUT\WORD( STAR\VALUE); GN
)@@G@@@A@@@@           END " OF SET STAR\VALUE  @B@@@@          ELSE " IS NORMGO
)@@G@@AL MULTIPLICATION @^@@@@             MULT\OP;   @#@@@@END; " OF STAR\OP GP
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" THIS CODE PROCESSES THE MULTIPLY OPERATOR.    @[@@@@GQ
)@@G@@"     @#@@@@PROCEDURE MULT\OP @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          IF LCTR NE RCTGR
)@@G@@R THEN " CANNOT DO MUCH @A@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR6@#@@@@GS
)@@G@@          ELSE    @F@@@@             IF LTYP EQ TYPINT AND RTYP EQ TYPINGT
)@@G@@T THEN " INTEGERS @B@@@@              BEGIN " TO RETURN INTEGER   @B@@@@GU
)@@G@@                DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPINT;   @D@@@@                IF LSBT GV
)@@G@@EQ RSBT THEN " SAME SUBTYPE   @B@@@@                   DSBT(OS\PTR) := RGW
)@@G@@SBT;  @#@@@@              END @#@@@@             ELSE @G@@@@            GX
)@@G@@    IF LTYP EQ TYPINT AND RTYP EQ TYPDST THEN " MIXMODES    @A@@@@      GY
)@@G@@           BEGIN " MIXMODE    @B@@@@                   DTYP(OS\PTR) := TGZ
)@@G@@YPDST;@B@@@@                   DSBT(OS\PTR) := RSBT;  @ @@@@            HA
)@@G@@     END " MIXMODE@^@@@@                ELSE    @G@@@@                  HB
)@@G@@ IF LTYP EQ TYPDST AND RTYP EQ TYPINT THEN " MIXMODES @A@@@@            HC
)@@G@@        BEGIN " MIXMODE @C@@@@                      DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPDHD
)@@G@@ST;   @C@@@@                      DSBT(OS\PTR) := LSBT;     @A@@@@      HE
)@@G@@              END " MIXMODE   @^@@@@                   ELSE @C@@@@      HF
)@@G@@                SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR7;  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          IFHG
)@@G@@ SCANNER\ERROR EQ 0 THEN " DO IT    @A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO RCTHH
)@@G@@R DO  @C@@@@                PUT\WORD( LNUM(I) * RNUM(I) );  @#@@@@END; "HI
)@@G@@ OF MULT\OP @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" THIS CODE PROCESSES THE DIVIDE OPERATOR.HJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE DIV\OP EXPORTED     @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@      HK
)@@G@@    IF LCTR NE RCTR THEN " LENGTHS DIFFER SO    @F@@@@             SCANNHL
)@@G@@ER\ERROR := ERROR6 " FLAG AN OPERATION ERROR    @D@@@@          ELSE " LHM
)@@G@@ENGTHS ARE THE SAME, CHECK TYPES    @D@@@@             IF LTYP EQ TYPINTHN
)@@G@@ AND RTYP EQ TYPINT THEN@C@@@@              BEGIN " INTEGER DIVIDES INTEHO
)@@G@@GER   @G@@@@                DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPINT; " SET INTEGER TYPE IHP
)@@G@@N RESULT    @D@@@@                IF LSBT EQ RSBT THEN " IF BOTH OCTAL  HQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@                   DSBT(OS\PTR) := RSBT; " RESULT WILL BE OCTAL   HR
)@@G@@@C@@@@              END " OF INTEGER DIVIDES INTEGER  @#@@@@            HS
)@@G@@ ELSE @E@@@@                IF LTYP EQ TYPDST AND RTYP EQ TYPDST THEN   HT
)@@G@@@D@@@@                 BEGIN " DISTANCE DIVIDES DISTANCE    @G@@@@      HU
)@@G@@             DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPINT; " RESULT WILL BE INTEGER     @D@@@@HV
)@@G@@                 END; " DISTANCE DIVIDES DISTANCE     @^@@@@            HW
)@@G@@    ELSE    @E@@@@                   IF LTYP EQ TYPDST AND RTYP EQ TYPINHX
)@@G@@T THEN@D@@@@                    BEGIN " DISTANCE DIVIDES INTEGER  @G@@@@HY
)@@G@@                      DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPDST; " SET RESULT TYPE DISTANCEHZ
)@@G@@@G@@@@                      DSBT(OS\PTR) := LSBT; " AND SUBTYPE OF LEFT IA
)@@G@@ARG   @D@@@@                    END " DISTANCE DIVIDES INTEGER    @E@@@@IB
)@@G@@                   ELSE " NO OTHER POSSIBLE COMBINATIONS    @G@@@@      IC
)@@G@@                SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR7; " SO FLAG TYPE ERROR     @[@@@@ID
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@          IF SCANNER\ERROR EQ 0 THEN " IF NO ERROR FOUND ABOIE
)@@G@@VE    @D@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO RCTR DO " LOOP OVER MEMBERS@G@@@@IF
)@@G@@                PUT\WORD( LNUM(I) // RNUM(I) ); " PUT DIVIDED RESULT    IG
)@@G@@@#@@@@END; " OF DIV\OP  @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@YP EQ TYPDST AND RTYP EQ TYPINIH
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);II
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDIJ
)@@G@@URE ATREAD(PTR: MACHINE WORD POINTER) IMPORTED ('ASCIITREAD');    @[@@@@IK

)@@G@@H: WORD INTEGER) EXPORTED ('TYPEANDREAD') @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   MEIP
)@@G@@SSAGE(*): WORD INTEGER BASED (MSG\PTR);   @@@@@@@F@@@@          READ\LENIQ
)@@G@@GTH := (MESSAGE\LENGTH+3)//4; " GET WORD LENGTH @B@@@@          FOR I :=IR

)@@G@@(1)));@C@@@@          FOR I := READ\LENGTH TO 1 BY -1 DO    @#@@@@      IV

)@@G@@1) GE O'770' THEN " FUNNY MODE INPUT@#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@      JB

)@@G@@     BEGIN  @C@@@@             NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(I) := WIDTHS(I);   @D@@@@KN

)@@G@@ND;   @A@@@@" CARD MUST BE RELEASED BY CALLER   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@TERM; KP

)@@G@@@G@@@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\LEADING(LEAD: DISTANCE, FUNC: 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTLF
)@@G@@EGER) @A@@@@           IMPORTED ('PERLED');     @@@@@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE MALG
)@@G@@KE\TOC\ENTRY(THIS\LEVEL: WORD INTEGER) EXPORTED @^@@@@           ('MAKTOLH
)@@G@@C')   @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          IF FORMATTING THEN " WRITE TOC ENTRY  LI
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             IF TOC\PACKET EQ NULL\PTR OR LJ
)@@G@@@G@@@@                FUNCTION(TOC\PACKET) EQ 0 THEN " NOT YET INITIALIZLK
