)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" OUTPUT THE TABLE OF CONTENTS NOW  @[@@@@LU
)@@G@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE OUTPUT\TOC EXPORTED ('OUTTOC')  @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@LV
)@@G@@DECLARE   NUMBERING(9): WORD INTEGER;     @@@@@@@C@@@@          CLOSE\TOLW
)@@G@@C; " CLOSE BEFORE PRINTING    @D@@@@          IF LINK\TO\TOC EQ 0 THEN "LX
)@@G@@ NO TOC TO OUTPUT @^@@@@             RETURN;    @ @@@@          FOR I :=LY
)@@G@@ 1 TO 9 DO  @E@@@@             NUMBERING(I) := 0; " INITIALIZE CHAPTERINLZ
)@@G@@G     @G@@@@          FORCE\END\OF\PARAGRAPH;          " FLUSH OUT LAST MA
)@@G@@CARD IF ANY @C@@@@          FORCE\END\OF\PAGE; " GET NEW PAGE     @E@@@@MB
)@@G@@          SCAN(EVAL+CTRM+ALLOW\STR); " PICK UP TOC CARD     @E@@@@      MC
)@@G@@    INITIALIZE\NEXT\WORD\ASSEMBLY; " START NEW WORD   @C@@@@          PUMD
)@@G@@T\FUNCTION\INTO\WORD(FUNC\CENTER,0);@A@@@@          FOR I := 1 TO CSDLENME
)@@G@@ DO   @D@@@@             PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD(DCHR(I));   @D@@@@MF
)@@G@@          INITIALIZE\LINE\ASSEMBLY; " START NEW LINE  @C@@@@          INMG
)@@G@@HIBIT\INDENT := TRUE; " NO INDENTION@B@@@@          OUTPUT\NEXT\WORD; " MH
)@@G@@INSERT IT   @D@@@@          FORCE\END\OF\PARAGRAPH; " OUTPUT TOC HEADER MI
)@@G@@@H@@@@          PERFORM\LEADING(LEADING,FUNC\LEAD); " SKIP A LINE BEFOREMJ
)@@G@@ TOC OUPUT  @F@@@@          INITIALIZE\FILE(%TOC\PACKET, %IMAGE\PTR,LINKMK
)@@G@@\TO\TOC);   @[@@@@NEXT: @C@@@@          READ\FILE(TOC\PACKET, %IMAGE\LENML
)@@G@@);    @D@@@@          IF IMAGE\LEN GE 0 THEN " NOT END OF FILE    @#@@@@MM
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@             NUMBERING(TOC\LEVEL) := NUMBERING(TMN
)@@G@@OC\LEVEL) + 1;    @B@@@@             FOR I := TOC\LEVEL+1 TO 9 DO @G@@@@MO
)@@G@@                NUMBERING(I) := 0; " CLEAR LEVELS ABOVE CURRENT ONE     MP
)@@G@@@C@@@@             INITIALIZE\NEXT\WORD\ASSEMBLY;     @D@@@@            MQ
)@@G@@ IF TOC\LEVEL GT 1 THEN " INDENT SUB LEVEL@A@@@@                FOR I :=MR
)@@G@@ 1 TO 6 DO  @E@@@@                   PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD(BLANK)MS
)@@G@@;     @B@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO TOC\LEVEL DO   @^@@@@            MT
)@@G@@  BEGIN     @E@@@@                CONVERT\AND\INSERT\NUMBER(NUMBERING(I)MU
)@@G@@);    @D@@@@                PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD(PERIOD); @#@@@@MV
)@@G@@              END;@D@@@@             PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD(BLANK)MW
)@@G@@;     @D@@@@             PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD(BLANK);     @C@@@@MX
)@@G@@             FOR I := 1 TO IMAGE\LEN-TOC\MISC DO@E@@@@                PUMY
)@@G@@T\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD( IMAGE(I) );   @E@@@@             FLUSH\FROM\MZ
)@@G@@HERE; " FLUSH REST TO RIGHT MARGIN  @F@@@@             IF EDIT\CHAP\NUMBNA
)@@G@@ER THEN " EDIT IN CHAPTER NUMBER TOO@^@@@@              BEGIN     @H@@@@NB
)@@G@@                CONVERT\AND\INSERT\NUMBER(NUMBERING(1)); " INSERT CHAPTENC
)@@G@@R     @F@@@@                PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD(MINUS); " SEPARND
)@@G@@ATOR  @#@@@@              END;@D@@@@             CONVERT\AND\INSERT\NUMBNE
)@@G@@ER(TOC\PAGE);     @B@@@@             INITIALIZE\LINE\ASSEMBLY;    @A@@@@NF
)@@G@@             INHIBIT\INDENT := TRUE;@ @@@@             OUTPUT\NEXT\WORD;NG
)@@G@@@F@@@@             FORCE\END\OF\PARAGRAPH;          " OUTPUT TOC ENTRY  NH
)@@G@@@^@@@@             GOTO NEXT; @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@NI
)@@G@@" END OF FILE , TOC OUTPUT DONE     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          CLOSE\FINJ
)@@G@@LE(TOC\PACKET); " CLOSE INPUT @A@@@@          IMAGE\PTR := NULL\PTR;    NK
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@       FORCE\END\OF\PARAGRAPH;          " NL
)@@G@@OUTPUT TOC ENTRY  @^@@@@             GOTO NEXT; @#@@@@           END;   NM
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @A@@@@" END *[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@NN
)@@G@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',NO
)@@G@@IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('OPERATOR-DEF',IMPORTED); @E@@@@      NP
)@@G@@    COPY ('SYMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED); " GET SYMBOL EQUATES@D@@@@          CONQ
)@@G@@PY ('SCAN-DEF',IMPORTED); " GET DATA AREAS@B@@@@          COPY ('WARNINGNR
)@@G@@-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED;     @[@@@@NS
)@@G@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDURE POP IMPORTED ('SCANPOP'); @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" DEFINT
)@@G@@NE OPERATOR SUBROUTINES @[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE ADD\OPS(OP: INTEGER NU
)@@G@@WORD) IMPORTED; " IN ELEMENT OPER-ARITH   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE STNV
)@@G@@AR\OP IMPORTED; " IN ELEMENT OPER-ARITH   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE DINW
)@@G@@V\OP IMPORTED; " IN ELEMENT OPER-ARITH    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE RENX
)@@G@@PLIC\OP IMPORTED; " IN ELEMENT OPER-CATEN @[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE LONY
)@@G@@GIC\OPS(OP: INTEGER WORD) IMPORTED; " IN ELEMENT OPER-LOGIC @[@@@@"     NZ
)@@G@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE LOGIC\NOT IMPORTED; " IN ELEMENT OPER-LOGIC @[@@@@"     OA
)@@G@@@H@@@@PROCEDURE COMPARE\OPS(OP: LOGICAL WORD) IMPORTED; " IN ELEMENT OPEOB
)@@G@@R-COMPARE   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE CATENATE\OP IMPORTED; " IN ELEMEOC
)@@G@@NT OPER-CATEN     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE OPAREN\OP IMPORTED; " IN EOD
)@@G@@LEMENT OPER-PAREN @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE OBRACK\OP IMPORTED; " IN EOE
)@@G@@LEMENT OPER-PAREN @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE ENTRY\OP IMPORTED; " IN ELOF
)@@G@@EMENT OPER-OPERS  @@@@@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE INDEX\OP IMPORTED; " IN ELEMENT OG
)@@G@@OPER-OPERS  @@@@@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE DIST\OP IMPORTED; " IN ELEMENT OPER-OPOH
)@@G@@ERS   @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEOI
)@@G@@DURE IS CALLED BY THE VALUE SCANNER TO PERFORM  @A@@@@" THE TOP OPERATIOOJ
)@@G@@N ON THE STACK    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\OP EXPORTED ('PFRMOK
)@@G@@OP')  @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@DECLARE   OP: INTEGER WORD; " TEMP  @[@@@@"     OL
)@@G@@@C@@@@          RTYP := DTYP(OS\PTR); " COPY RITEARG  @A@@@@          RSOM
)@@G@@BT := DSBT(OS\PTR);     @A@@@@          RCTR := DLEN(OS\PTR);     @A@@@@ON
)@@G@@          RPTR := DADR(OS\PTR);     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@          OP := OPOO
)@@G@@ER;   @A@@@@          POP; " THE SCANNER STACK  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@      OP
)@@G@@    LTYP := DTYP(OS\PTR); " COPY LEFTARG  @A@@@@          LSBT := DSBT(OOQ
)@@G@@S\PTR);     @A@@@@          LCTR := DLEN(OS\PTR);     @A@@@@          LPOR
)@@G@@TR := DADR(OS\PTR);     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          DSBT(OS\PTR) := 0; "OS
)@@G@@ SET NO SUBTYPE   @C@@@@          DLEN(OS\PTR) := 0; " AND LENGTH ZERO  OT
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DADR(OS\PTR) := DS\PTR; " AND DATASTACK POINTER   @A@@@@OU
)@@G@@"         DISPLAY('PFRMOP',OP);     @^@@@@"         DUMP\STACKTOP;@B@@@@OV
)@@G@@          CASEENTRY OP " PROCESS OPERATOR @G@@@@             CASE OPRCATOW
)@@G@@: CATENATE\OP;            " COMMA (CATENATION)  @G@@@@             CASE OX
)@@G@@OPRLSS: COMPARE\OPS(CMP\LESS);  " COMPARE LESS THAN   @G@@@@            OY
)@@G@@ CASE OPRGRT: COMPARE\OPS(CMP\GRTR);  " COMPARE GRTR THAN   @F@@@@      OZ
)@@G@@       CASE OPREQL: COMPARE\OPS(CMP\EQUL);  " COMPARE EQUAL @E@@@@      PA
)@@G@@       CASE OPRADD: ADD\OPS(OP);            " ADDITION@F@@@@            PB
)@@G@@ CASE OPRSUB: ADD\OPS(OP);            " SUBTRACTION   @F@@@@            PC
)@@G@@ CASE OPRMUL: STAR\OP;                " MULTIPLICATION@E@@@@            PD
)@@G@@ CASE OPRDIV: DIV\OP;                 " DIVISION@F@@@@             CASE PE
)@@G@@OPRREP: REPLIC\OP;              " REPLICATION   @F@@@@             CASE PF
)@@G@@OPRENT: ENTRY\OP;               " TABLE ENTRY   @D@@@@             CASE PG
)@@G@@OPRIND: INDEX\OP;  " INDEX TO VECTOR@E@@@@             CASE OPRDST: DISTPH
)@@G@@\OP;   " INTEGER TO DISTANCE  @F@@@@             CASE OPRAND: LOGIC\OPS(PI
)@@G@@OP);          " LOGICAL AND   @F@@@@             CASE OPRIOR: LOGIC\OPS(PJ
)@@G@@OP);          " LOGICAL OR    @F@@@@             CASE OPRNOT: LOGIC\NOT;PK
)@@G@@              " LOGICAL NOT   @G@@@@             CASE OPROPR: OPAREN\OP;PL
)@@G@@              " OPEN PARENTHESIS    @F@@@@             CASE OPROBR: OBRAPM
)@@G@@CK\OP;              " OPEN BRACKET  @G@@@@             CASE OPRCPR:     PN
)@@G@@                    " CLOSE PARENTHESIS   @F@@@@                SCANNER\PO
)@@G@@ERROR := ERROR16; " UNBALANCED PARENTHESIS@F@@@@             CASE OPRCBRPP
)@@G@@:                         " CLOSE BRACKET @F@@@@                SCANNER\PQ
)@@G@@ERROR := ERROR16; " UNBALANCED PARENTHESIS@^@@@@             CASE *:    PR
)@@G@@@^@@@@              BEGIN     @B@@@@                DISPLAY('OPRERR',OP)PS
)@@G@@;     @^@@@@                ERROR;  @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@      PT
)@@G@@    ENDCASE;@^@@@@END; " OF PERFORM\OP;   @[@@@@TERM; ___UT @^@@@@END; "PU
)@@G@@ OF PERFORM\OP;   @[@@@@TERM; ___UT FILE IS ON NON MASS STORAGE EQUIPMENPV
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS MODULE HANDLES THPW
)@@G@@E CATENATION OPERATOR (COMMA) AND   @A@@@@" THE REPLICATION OPERATOR (#)PX
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@      PY
)@@G@@    COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @E@@@@          COPY ('CHAR-SIZE',IMPZ
)@@G@@PORTED); " GET CONV\FACTORS   @B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-DEF',IMPORTQA
)@@G@@ED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-PROC',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COQB
)@@G@@PY ('OPERATOR-DEF',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('SCAN-DEF',IMPORTED)QC
)@@G@@;     @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COQD
)@@G@@PY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\CHAR(C: INQE
)@@G@@TEGER WORD) IMPORTED ('PUTCHR');    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\WORDQF
)@@G@@(I: INTEGER WORD) IMPORTED ('PUTWRD');    @@@@@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\DISTQG
)@@G@@ANCE(D: DISTANCE) IMPORTED ('PUTWRD');    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PUQH
)@@G@@T\FLOATING(F: FLOATING) IMPORTED ('PUTWRD');    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDQI
)@@G@@URE ERROR IMPORTED;     @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     QJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@PROCEDURE CATENATE\OP EXPORTED@[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" FIRSQK
)@@G@@T COMPUTE THE RESULTANT TYPE. @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          DTYP(OS\PTR) :QL
)@@G@@= TYPNUL; " SET RESULTANT TYPE NULL @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          IF (LTYPQM
)@@G@@ EQ TYPINT) OR (RTYP EQ TYPINT) THEN@F@@@@             DTYP(OS\PTR) := TQN
)@@G@@YPINT; " SET RESULTANT TYPE INTEGER @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          IF (LTYPQO
)@@G@@ EQ TYPFLP) OR (RTYP EQ TYPFLP) THEN@G@@@@             DTYP(OS\PTR) := TQP
)@@G@@YPFLP; " SET RESULTANT TYPE FLOATING POINT@[@@@@"     @D@@@@          IFQQ
)@@G@@ (LTYP EQ TYPDST) OR (RTYP EQ TYPDST) THEN@F@@@@             DTYP(OS\PTRQR
)@@G@@) := TYPDST; " SET RESULTANT TYPE DISTANCE@[@@@@"     @F@@@@          IFQS
)@@G@@ CSTR OR (LTYP EQ TYPSTR) OR (RTYP EQ TYPSTR) THEN    @F@@@@            QT
)@@G@@ DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPSTR; " SET RESULTANT TYPE STRING  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@QU
)@@G@@" NOW COMPUTE RESULTANT SUBTYPE.    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          IF (LTYPQV
)@@G@@ EQ RTYP) AND (LSBT EQ RSBT) AND    @B@@@@             (LTYP EQ DTYP(OS\QW
)@@G@@PTR)) THEN  @A@@@@             DSBT(OS\PTR) := LSBT;  @[@@@@"     @^@@@@QX
)@@G@@" NOW DO CATENATION     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          CAT\ITEM( LOC(LEFT\AQY
)@@G@@RG) ); " CATENATE IN LEFTARG  @E@@@@          CAT\ITEM( LOC(RITE\ARG) );QZ
)@@G@@ " CATENATE IN RITEARG  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@"         DUMP\DESCRIPTOR('CATRA
)@@G@@EN',OS\PTR);@^@@@@END; " OF CATENATE\OP   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCERB
)@@G@@DURE IS CALLED TO HANDLE THE REPLICATION OPERATOR     @D@@@@" WHICH CATERC
)@@G@@NATES N COPIES OF THE RITEARG TOGETHER.   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE RERD
)@@G@@PLIC\OP EXPORTED  @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          IF LTYP NE TYPINT OR LCTR RE
)@@G@@NE 1 THEN   @B@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR7;     @#@@@@      RF
)@@G@@    ELSE    @B@@@@           BEGIN " TO HANDLE REPLICATION  @B@@@@"     RG
)@@G@@       DISPLAY ('REPCTR',LNUM(1));  @D@@@@             DTYP(OS\PTR) := RRH
)@@G@@TYP; " SET RESULT TYPE  @C@@@@             DSBT(OS\PTR) := RSBT; " AND SRI
)@@G@@UBTYPE@B@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO LNUM(1) DO     @D@@@@            RJ
)@@G@@    CAT\ITEM( LOC(RITE\ARG) ); " CATENATE @A@@@@           END; " OF VALRK
)@@G@@IDITY TEST  @^@@@@END; " OF REPLIC\OP     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS ROUTIRL
)@@G@@NE IS CALLED ON THE LEFTARG AND THE RITEARG OF THE    @F@@@@" CATENATIONRM
)@@G@@ PRIMITIVE TO CATENATE THEM IN, IS CALLED MULTIPLE    @F@@@@" TIMES ON TRN
)@@G@@HE RIGHTARG FOR THE DUPLICATION PRIMITIVE, AND IS ALSO@F@@@@" CALLED FRORO
)@@G@@M THE SCANNER WHEN THE DATA ABOUT TO BE RETURNED TO   @C@@@@" THE CALLERRP
)@@G@@ MUST BE CONVERTED TO TYPE STRING.  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE CAT\ITEMRQ
)@@G@@(ITEM: MACHINE POINTER WORD) " TO DESCRIPTOR    @ @@@@          EXPORTEDRR
)@@G@@ ('CATITM') @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   PTR: MACHINE POINTERRS
)@@G@@ WORD; " TO DATA VALUE  @C@@@@DECLARE   CHR(*): 9 BIT INTEGER BASED(PTR)RT
)@@G@@;     @B@@@@DECLARE   NUM(*): INTEGER WORD BASED(PTR);@E@@@@DECLARE   LORU
)@@G@@G(*): LOGICAL WORD BASED(PTR); " BECAUSE OF LAND@[@@@@"     @D@@@@DECLARRV
)@@G@@E   CAT\FAC: INTEGER WORD; " CONVERSION FACTOR  @F@@@@DECLARE   CAT\QUO:RW
)@@G@@ INTEGER WORD; " TEMP FOR DISTANCE CONVERSION   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@      RX
)@@G@@    PTR := DADR(ITEM); " GET DATA ADDRESS @D@@@@          CASEENTRY DTYPRY
)@@G@@(OS\PTR) " ON OUTPUT CASE     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" IF OUTPUT IS NULL THENRZ
)@@G@@ INPUT MUST BE NULL.    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@          CASE TYPNUL:  @B@@@@SA
)@@G@@             IF DTYP(ITEM) NE TYPNUL THEN @B@@@@                SCANNER\SB
)@@G@@ERROR := ERROR7;  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" IF OUTPUT IS INTEGER INPUT MUST BESC
)@@G@@ NULL OR INTEGER. @[@@@@"     @B@@@@          CASE TYPINT: " OUTPUT IN ISD
)@@G@@NTEGER@D@@@@             CASEENTRY DTYP(ITEM) " ON INPUT CASE     @B@@@@SE
)@@G@@             CASE TYPNUL: " DO NOTHING    @A@@@@                BEGIN "NSF
)@@G@@OTHING" END;@C@@@@             CASE TYPINT: " INTEGER TO INTEGER  @C@@@@SG
)@@G@@                FOR I := 1 TO DLEN(ITEM) DO     @D@@@@                  SH
)@@G@@ PUT\WORD(NUM(I)); " STASH WORD     @ @@@@             CASE *: " ELSE   SI
)@@G@@@B@@@@                SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR7;  @^@@@@             ENDCASJ
)@@G@@SE;   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" OUTPUT IS DISTANCE - INPUT MAY BE NULL, INTEGESK
)@@G@@R(MAYBE) OR DISTANCE.   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          CASE TYPDST: " OUTPUSL
)@@G@@T IN DISTANCE     @D@@@@             CASEENTRY DTYP(ITEM) " ON INPUT CASSM
)@@G@@E     @B@@@@             CASE TYPNUL: " DO NOTHING    @A@@@@            SN
)@@G@@    BEGIN "NOTHING" END;@E@@@@             CASE TYPINT: " INTEGER TO DISSO
)@@G@@TANCE CONVERSION  @C@@@@                IF CDST THEN " IF WE CAN DO IT  SP
)@@G@@@C@@@@                   FOR I := 1 TO DLEN(ITEM) DO  @F@@@@            SQ
)@@G@@          PUT\DISTANCE( NUM(I) * CONV\FACTORS(CFAC) ) @D@@@@            SR
)@@G@@    ELSE " NO CONVERSION FACTOR GIVEN     @C@@@@                   SCANNSS
)@@G@@ER\ERROR := ERROR7;     @ @@@@             CASE TYPDST:     @C@@@@      ST
)@@G@@          FOR I := 1 TO DLEN(ITEM) DO     @B@@@@                   PUT\DSU
)@@G@@ISTANCE(NUM(I));  @ @@@@             CASE *: " ELSE   @B@@@@            SV
)@@G@@    SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR7;  @^@@@@             ENDCASE;   @[@@@@"     SW
)@@G@@@B@@@@" OUTPUT IS STRING - INPUT MAY BE ANYTHING@[@@@@"     @B@@@@      SX
)@@G@@    CASE TYPSTR: " OUTPUT IN STRING @D@@@@             CASEENTRY DTYP(ITSY
)@@G@@EM) " ON INPUT CASE     @B@@@@             CASE TYPNUL: " DO NOTHING    SZ
)@@G@@@A@@@@                BEGIN "NOTHING" END;@C@@@@             CASE TYPINTTA
)@@G@@: " INTEGER TO STRING   @C@@@@                IF CNUM THEN " MAKE CHARACTB
)@@G@@TERS  @C@@@@                   FOR I := 1 TO DLEN(ITEM) DO  @C@@@@      TC
)@@G@@                IF LOG(I) GT 255 OR "     @E@@@@                        TD
)@@G@@ LOG(I) LT 0 THEN " TRUNCATE IT     @E@@@@                         PUT\CTE
)@@G@@HAR(TRUNCATED\CHARACTER);     @D@@@@                      ELSE " TAKE CHTF
)@@G@@ARACTER AS IS     @B@@@@                         PUT\CHAR(LOG(I));@^@@@@TG
)@@G@@                ELSE    @C@@@@                   FOR I := 1 TO DLEN(ITEMTH
)@@G@@) DO  @D@@@@                    BEGIN " TO CONVERT IT TO ASCII    @F@@@@TI
)@@G@@                      PUT\INTEGER\IN\ASCII( NUM(I) ); " PUT IT    @F@@@@TJ
)@@G@@                      IF I NE DLEN(ITEM) THEN " IF NOT LAST ONE   @F@@@@TK
)@@G@@                         PUT\CHAR(BLANK); " EDIT IN ONE BLANK     @D@@@@TL
)@@G@@                    END; " CONVERTING IT TO ASCII     @C@@@@            TM
)@@G@@ CASE TYPSTR: " STRING TO STRING    @C@@@@                FOR I := 1 TO TN
)@@G@@DLEN(ITEM) DO     @D@@@@                   PUT\CHAR( CHR(I) ); " CAT IT TO
)@@G@@IN    @C@@@@             CASE TYPDST: " DISTANCE TO STRING  @^@@@@      TP
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @E@@@@                IF DSBT(ITEM) EQ 0 THEN " IT IS TQ
)@@G@@TYPELESS    @F@@@@                   CAT\FAC := INCH\DISTANCE; " INCHES TR
)@@G@@FOR NOW     @C@@@@                ELSE " GET CONVERSION FACTOR    @G@@@@TS
)@@G@@                   CAT\FAC := CONV\FACTORS(DSBT(ITEM)); " FOR DIVIDE    TT
)@@G@@@C@@@@                FOR I := 1 TO DLEN(ITEM) DO     @D@@@@            TU
)@@G@@     BEGIN " TO CATENATE THE I'TH VALUE   @F@@@@                   CAT\QTV
)@@G@@UO := NUM(I)//CAT\FAC; " GET INTEGER PART @E@@@@                   PUT\ITW
)@@G@@NTEGER\IN\ASCII( CAT\QUO ); " PUT IT@D@@@@                   PUT\CHAR(PETX
)@@G@@RIOD); " DECIMAL POINT  @G@@@@                   CAT\QUO := MOD(ABS(NUM(TY
)@@G@@I)),CAT\FAC); " GET REMAINDER @B@@@@                   FOR J := 1 TO 3 DTZ
)@@G@@O     @B@@@@                      IF CAT\QUO GT 0 THEN@E@@@@            UA
)@@G@@           BEGIN " TO GET NEXT FRACTIONAL DIGIT @H@@@@                  UB
)@@G@@       PUT\CHAR(ASCII\ZERO+(10*CAT\QUO)//CAT\FAC); " EDIT IT@E@@@@      UC
)@@G@@                   CAT\QUO := MOD(10*CAT\QUO,CAT\FAC);@D@@@@            UD
)@@G@@           END; " OF NEXT FRACTIONAL DIGIT@F@@@@                   PUT\QUE
)@@G@@UAL\CHR(DSBT(ITEM)); " QUAL CHARS IF ANY  @D@@@@                   IF I UF
)@@G@@NE DLEN(ITEM) THEN " SPACE OUT@B@@@@                      PUT\CHAR(BLANKUG
)@@G@@);    @D@@@@                 END; " OF CATENATING THE I'TH VALUE  @D@@@@UH
)@@G@@              END; " OF DISTANCE TO STRING CONVERSION @^@@@@            UI
)@@G@@ CASE *:    @B@@@@                SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR7;  @^@@@@      UJ
)@@G@@       ENDCASE;   @C@@@@          CASE TYPFLP: " OUTPUT FLOATING POINT  UK
)@@G@@@D@@@@             CASEENTRY DTYP(ITEM) " CHECK INPUT TYPE  @B@@@@      UL
)@@G@@       CASE TYPFLP: " JUST COPY IT  @^@@@@              BEGIN     @C@@@@UM
)@@G@@                FOR I := 1 TO DLEN(ITEM) DO     @A@@@@                  UN
)@@G@@ PUT\WORD(NUM(I));@B@@@@              END; " COPY FLOATING POINT  @D@@@@UO
)@@G@@             CASE TYPINT: " COPY DOING CONVERSION     @^@@@@            UP
)@@G@@  BEGIN     @C@@@@                FOR I := 1 TO DLEN(ITEM) DO     @G@@@@UQ
)@@G@@                   PUT\FLOATING(NUM(I)); " PLUS CONVERTS ARG TO FLOATINGUR
)@@G@@@D@@@@              END; " CONVERTING INTEGER TO FLOATING   @D@@@@      US
)@@G@@       CASE *: " ALL OTHERS NOT ALLOWED FOR NOW @B@@@@                SCUT
)@@G@@ANNER\ERROR := ERROR7;  @B@@@@             ENDCASE; " ON INPUT TYPE     UU
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" OUTPUT NONE OF THE ABOVE - TABLE MAYBE - UGLY @[@@@@UV
)@@G@@"     @#@@@@          CASE *: @^@@@@             ERROR;     @#@@@@      UW
)@@G@@    ENDCASE;@#@@@@END; " OF CAT\ITEM@[@@@@"     @B@@@@" PUT THE INTEGER UX
)@@G@@GIVEN INTO DESCRIPTOR.  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\INTEGER\IN\ASCIIUY
)@@G@@(NUMBER: INTEGER WORD)  @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          CVT\NUM\TO\ASCII(NUMUZ
)@@G@@BER); " GET ASCII CHARS @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO 12 DO @F@@@@      VA
)@@G@@       IF NUMBER\IN\ASCII(I) NE BLANK THEN " WE WANT IT     @E@@@@      VB
)@@G@@          PUT\CHAR( NUMBER\IN\ASCII(I) ); " SO PUT IT @ @@@@END; " OF PUVC
)@@G@@T\INTEGER\IN\ASCII@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" EDIT THE QUALIFICATION CHARACTERS VD
)@@G@@FOR THE SUBTYPE PASSED. @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\QUAL\CHR(SUBTYPEVE
)@@G@@: INTEGER WORD)   @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          CASEENTRY SUBTYPE " WHICH VF
)@@G@@IS IT @ @@@@          CASE 0: "NOT KNOWN" @C@@@@             PUT\CHAR(DOVG
)@@G@@UBLE\QUOTE); " INCHES   @D@@@@          CASE CF\CM,CF\COL: " CENTIMETERSVH
)@@G@@ AND COLUMNS@#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             PUT\CHAR(ASCII\C)VI
)@@G@@; " C @D@@@@             IF SUBTYPE EQ CF\CM THEN " ADD THE M     @B@@@@VJ
)@@G@@                PUT\CHAR(ASCII\M); " M    @A@@@@           END; " OF COLVK
)@@G@@ AND CM     @A@@@@          CASE CF\INCH: " INCHES    @A@@@@            VL
)@@G@@ PUT\CHAR(DOUBLE\QUOTE);@A@@@@          CASE CF\PICA: " PICAS     @#@@@@VM
)@@G@@             BEGIN@#@@@@             END; @A@@@@          CASE CF\POINT:VN
)@@G@@ " POINTS   @A@@@@             PUT\CHAR(ASCII\P);     @A@@@@          CAVO
)@@G@@SE CF\SKIP: " LINE SKIP @A@@@@             PUT\CHAR(ASCII\L); " L @B@@@@VP
)@@G@@          CASE *: " INTERNAL DPS ERROR !!!@A@@@@           BEGIN " TO HAVQ
)@@G@@NDLE IT     @D@@@@             ODISPLAY('BADSBT',SUBTYPE); " DUMP IT    VR
)@@G@@@A@@@@             ERROR; " AND ABORT     @B@@@@           END; " OF INTVS
)@@G@@ERNAL ERROR CODE  @#@@@@          ENDCASE;@^@@@@END; " OF PUT\QUAL\CHR  VT
)@@G@@@[@@@@TERM; ___ AN@^@@@@END; " OF PUT\QUAL\CHR  @[@@@@TERM; ___ ANYTHINGVU
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@          CASE TYPSTR: " OUTPUT IN STRING @D@@@@      VV
)@@G@@       CASEENTRY DTYP(IT*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@VW
)@@G@@" THIS MOLULE HANDLES COMPARISONS BETWEEN DATA ITEMS. @[@@@@"     @A@@@@VX
)@@G@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',VY
)@@G@@IMPORTED);  @E@@@@          COPY ('CHAR-SIZE',IMPORTED); " GET CONV\FACTVZ
)@@G@@ORS   @B@@@@          COPY ('OPERATOR-DEF',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COWA
)@@G@@PY ('SCAN-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-DEF',IMPORTEWB
)@@G@@D);   @B@@@@          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@WC
)@@G@@DECLARE   LTMP: INTEGER WORD; " LEFT ITEM FOR COMPARISON    @E@@@@DECLARWD
)@@G@@E   RTMP: INTEGER WORD; " RITE ITEM FOR COMPARISON    @D@@@@DECLARE   REWE
)@@G@@L: LOGICAL WORD; " RESULT OF COMPARISON   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PUWF
)@@G@@T\WORD(I: INTEGER WORD) IMPORTED ('PUTWRD');    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDWG
)@@G@@URE ERROR IMPORTED;     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" THISWH
)@@G@@ CODE IS USED TO DO COMPARISONS.    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE COMPARE\WI
)@@G@@OPS(OP: LOGICAL WORD) EXPORTED@[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@DECLARE   I: INTEGER WORWJ
)@@G@@D; " SUBSCRIPT    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          LFAC := 1; " SET CONVERSIOWK
)@@G@@N FACTORS TO ONE  @^@@@@          RFAC := 1;    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" SET WL
)@@G@@ITEMS EQUAL FOR FIRST PASS THRU COMPARE LOOP.   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@      WM
)@@G@@    LTMP := 0;    @^@@@@          RTMP := 0;    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" IF CWN
)@@G@@ONVERSION FACTOR IS SPECIFIED FOR THIS COMMAND WE ALLOW     @D@@@@" THE WO
)@@G@@MIX MODE COMPARISON OF DISTANCES AND INTEGERS.  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@      WP
)@@G@@    IF CFAC NE 0 THEN   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             IF LTWQ
)@@G@@YP EQ TYPDST AND RTYP EQ TYPINT THEN@D@@@@              BEGIN " TO MAKE WR
)@@G@@IT LOOK LIKE INTEGERS   @A@@@@                LTYP := TYPINT;     @C@@@@WS
)@@G@@                RFAC := CONV\FACTORS(CFAC);     @#@@@@              END;WT
)@@G@@@D@@@@             IF RTYP EQ TYPDST AND LTYP EQ TYPINT THEN@D@@@@      WU
)@@G@@        BEGIN " TO MAKE IT LOOK LIKE INTEGERS   @A@@@@                RTWV
)@@G@@YP := TYPINT;     @C@@@@                LFAC := CONV\FACTORS(CFAC);     WW
)@@G@@@#@@@@              END;@B@@@@           END; " OF MIXMODE COMPARISONS  WX
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" TO ALLOW COMPARISONS OF DISTANCE KLUGE THEM TO BE INWY
)@@G@@TEGER.@[@@@@"     @D@@@@          IF LTYP EQ TYPDST AND RTYP EQ TYPDST TWZ
)@@G@@HEN   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @ @@@@             LTYP := TYPINT;  @ @@@@XA
)@@G@@             RTYP := TYPINT;  @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@XB
)@@G@@" NOW TO DO THE COMPARISONS.  SINCE ERROR IS SIGNALED BY PROCEDURE@D@@@@XC
)@@G@@" CMP\ITEM NULLS WILL ALL TEST EQUAL TO EACH OTHER.   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@XD
)@@G@@          I := 0; " LOOP OVER MEMBERS     @D@@@@          REL := CMP\LOOXE
)@@G@@P; " SET COMPARISON LOOPING   @A@@@@          WHILE (REL EQ CMP\LOOP) DOXF
)@@G@@@B@@@@           BEGIN " TO LOOK AT NEXT MEMBER @C@@@@             IF LTXG
)@@G@@MP LT RTMP THEN " LESS THAN   @D@@@@                REL := CMP\LESS; " IXH
)@@G@@T IS LESS THAN    @D@@@@             ELSE IF LTMP GT RTMP THEN " GREATERXI
)@@G@@ THAN @C@@@@                REL := CMP\GRTR; " IT IS GREATER@B@@@@      XJ
)@@G@@       ELSE " CHECK NEXT MEMBER     @C@@@@              BEGIN " INCREMENXK
)@@G@@T TO NEXT MEMBER  @C@@@@                I := I+1; " LOOK AT NEXT MEMBER XL
)@@G@@@D@@@@                IF (I GT LCTR) AND (I GT RCTR) THEN   @D@@@@      XM
)@@G@@             REL := CMP\EQUL; " THEY ARE EQUAL  @^@@@@                ELXN
)@@G@@SE    @C@@@@                 BEGIN " TO GET NEXT MEMBERS    @F@@@@      XO
)@@G@@             LTMP := CMP\ITEM(LTYP,LCTR,LPTR,I) * LFAC;     @F@@@@      XP
)@@G@@             RTMP := CMP\ITEM(RTYP,RCTR,RPTR,I) * RFAC;     @C@@@@      XQ
)@@G@@           END; " OF BEYOND THE END CHECK @C@@@@              END; " OF XR
)@@G@@INCREMENT TO NEXT MEMBER@B@@@@           END; " LOOK AT NEXT MEMBER     XS
)@@G@@@D@@@@          DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPINT; " SET RESULT INTEGER@D@@@@      XT
)@@G@@    IF (OP LAND REL) NE 0 THEN " IT IS TRUE     @^@@@@             PUT\WXU
)@@G@@ORD(1)@#@@@@          ELSE    @ @@@@             PUT\WORD(0);     @^@@@@XV
)@@G@@END; " OF COMPARE\OPS   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO GEXW
)@@G@@T ITEMS TO COMPARE.  IF THE TYPE    @C@@@@" IS CHARACTER IT RETURNS CHARXX
)@@G@@ACTERS ELSE WORDS.@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE CMP\ITEM(TYP: INTEGER WORDXY
)@@G@@ " TYPE OF ITEM   @D@@@@                  ,LEN: INTEGER WORD " LENGTH OFXZ
)@@G@@ ITEM @D@@@@                  ,PTR: MACHINE WORD POINTER " TO ITEM@D@@@@YA
)@@G@@                  ,IND: INTEGER WORD) " INDEX WE WANT @ @@@@          REYB
)@@G@@SULT INTEGER WORD @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   CHR(*): 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTYC
)@@G@@EGER BASED(PTR);  @B@@@@DECLARE   NUM(*): INTEGER WORD BASED(PTR);@D@@@@YD
)@@G@@DECLARE   V: INTEGER WORD; " VALUE RETURNED HELD HERE @[@@@@"     @^@@@@YE
)@@G@@          CASEENTRY TYP @^@@@@          CASE TYPINT:  @D@@@@            YF
)@@G@@ IF IND GT LEN THEN " WE ARE OFF THE END  @B@@@@                V := 0 "YG
)@@G@@ FILL WITH ZERO   @#@@@@             ELSE @E@@@@                V := NUMYH
)@@G@@(IND); " ELSE GET NUMBER TO COMPARE @^@@@@          CASE TYPSTR:  @D@@@@YI
)@@G@@             IF IND GT LEN THEN " WE ARE OFF THE END  @C@@@@            YJ
)@@G@@    V := BLANK " FILL WITH BLANK    @#@@@@             ELSE @F@@@@      YK
)@@G@@          V := CHR(IND); " ELSE GET CHARACTER TO COMPARE    @#@@@@      YL
)@@G@@    CASE *: @C@@@@             REL := CMP\NOTC; " ABORT COMPARISON@#@@@@YM
)@@G@@          ENDCASE;@^@@@@          RETURN(V);    @#@@@@END; " OF CMP\ITEMYN
)@@G@@@[@@@@TERM; ___@@@);    *[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@YO
)@@G@@" THIS MODULE HANDLES THE LOGICAL OPERATORS AND OR NOT.     @[@@@@"     YP
)@@G@@@A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PYQ
)@@G@@ROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('OPERATOR-DEF',IMPORTED); @B@@@@YR
)@@G@@          COPY ('SCAN-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-YS
)@@G@@DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@YT
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\WORD(I: INTEGER WORD) IMPORTED ('PUTWRD');    YU
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED;     @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROYV
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" LOGICAL 'AND' AND 'OR'.     @[@@@@"     YW
)@@G@@@C@@@@PROCEDURE LOGIC\OPS(OP: INTEGER WORD) EXPORTED  @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@YX
)@@G@@DECLARE   LLNUM(*): LOGICAL WORD BASED(LPTR);   @C@@@@DECLARE   LRNUM(*)YY
)@@G@@: LOGICAL WORD BASED(RPTR);   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          IF LTYP NE TYPYZ
)@@G@@INT OR RTYP NE TYPINT THEN    @D@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR7ZA
)@@G@@; " ILLEGAL MODES @#@@@@          ELSE    @A@@@@             IF LCTR NE ZB
)@@G@@RCTR THEN   @E@@@@                SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR6; " UNEQUAL LENZC
)@@G@@GTHS  @#@@@@             ELSE @C@@@@              BEGIN " TO DO LOGICAL ZD
)@@G@@OPERATOR    @E@@@@                DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPINT; " SET RESULT TZE
)@@G@@YPE   @E@@@@                FOR I := 1 TO LCTR DO " RANGE OVER ALL ITEMSZF
)@@G@@@^@@@@                 BEGIN  @E@@@@                   IF ( LNUM(I) NE 0ZG
)@@G@@ AND LNUM(I) NE 1 ) OR  @E@@@@                      ( RNUM(I) NE 0 AND RZH
)@@G@@NUM(I) NE 1 ) THEN@F@@@@                      SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR11; ZI
)@@G@@" BAD DATA TYPE   @^@@@@                   ELSE @E@@@@                  ZJ
)@@G@@    CASEENTRY OP " ACTUALLY DO OPERATOR   @D@@@@                      CAZK
)@@G@@SE OPRIOR: " INCLUSIVE OR     @E@@@@                         PUT\WORD(LLZL
)@@G@@NUM(I) LOR LRNUM(I));   @B@@@@                      CASE OPRAND: " AND  ZM
)@@G@@@E@@@@                         PUT\WORD(LLNUM(I) LAND LRNUM(I));  @C@@@@ZN
)@@G@@                      CASE *: " ANOTHER OPERATOR@A@@@@                  ZO
)@@G@@       ERROR;     @ @@@@                      ENDCASE;@B@@@@            ZP
)@@G@@     END; " OF LOOP ON ITEMS  @C@@@@              END; " OF LOGICAL OPERZQ
)@@G@@ATOR CODE   @^@@@@END; " OF LOGIC\OPS     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEZR
)@@G@@DURE HANDLES LOGICAL 'NOT' MONADIC OPERATOR.    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDZS
)@@G@@URE LOGIC\NOT EXPORTED  @[@@@@BEGIN @G@@@@          IF LTYP NE TYPNUL ORZT
)@@G@@ RTYP NE TYPINT THEN " MODE ERROR TEST    @B@@@@             SCANNER\ERRZU
)@@G@@OR := ERROR7;     @#@@@@          ELSE    @C@@@@           BEGIN " TO INZV
)@@G@@VERT LOGICAL VARIABLE   @F@@@@             DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPINT; " SETZW
)@@G@@ RESULT TYPE INTEGER    @A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO RCTR DO  @A@@@@ZX
)@@G@@                CASEENTRY RNUM(I)   @B@@@@                 CASE 0: PUT\WZY
)@@G@@ORD(1);     @B@@@@                 CASE 1: PUT\WORD(0);     @D@@@@      ZZ
)@@G@@           CASE *: SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR11;    @^@@@@                ENAA
)@@G@@DCASE;@C@@@@           END; " OF INVERTING LOGICAL VARIABLE @^@@@@END; "AB
)@@G@@ OF LOGIC\NOT     @[@@@@TERM; ___^H9@^@@@@END; " OF LOGIC\NOT     @[@@@@AC
)@@G@@TERM; ___^H9R;@^DP'=@@@#R7G@@#:8@@@ %8K@@[/K@^Z1^#0^XER#@^H9:@@^XH/K@^)%AD
)@@G@@:8K@@[/K@^Z;R\)^?1:8)@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@AE
)@@G@@" THIS MODULE CONTAINS ROUTINES TO HANDLE MACRO ARGUMENTS.  @G@@@@" SCANAF
)@@G@@\MACRO\CALL - SCAN IMAGE AND BUILD POINTER BUFFER AND ARG ICB.    @D@@@@AG
)@@G@@" STATE\SUBSTITUTE - SUBSTITUTE IN MACRO ARGUMENT.    @F@@@@" PERFORM\ARAH
)@@G@@G\FUNCTION - RETURN MACRO ARGUMENT IN STRING FORM.    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@AI
)@@G@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',AJ
)@@G@@IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@      AK
)@@G@@    COPY ('CORE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-DEF',AL
)@@G@@IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-PROC',IMPORTED); @A@@@@      AM
)@@G@@    COPY ('IO-DEF1',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('MACRO-DEF',IMPORTEDAN
)@@G@@);    @B@@@@          COPY ('OPERATOR-DEF',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COAO
)@@G@@PY ('PACKET-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('PUSH-PROCS',IMPORTEAP
)@@G@@D);   @B@@@@          COPY ('STAGING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COAQ
)@@G@@PY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('SCAN-DEF',IMPORTED)AR
)@@G@@;     @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@AS
)@@G@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\SCANNER\STACKS IMPORTED ('INITSS');    @[@@@@"     AT
)@@G@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE DOSCAN IMPORTED ('DOSCAN'); " IN ELEMENT SCANNER  @[@@@@AU
)@@G@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE END\OF\SCAN IMPORTED ('SCANEND')@C@@@@          REAV
)@@G@@SULT CONDITION; " IN ELEMENT SCANNER@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\CHARAW
)@@G@@\INTO\DESC(DESC: MACHINE WORD POINTER     @C@@@@                        AX
)@@G@@    ,CHAR: INTEGER WORD)@E@@@@          IMPORTED ('PUTCHRDESC'); " IN ELAY
)@@G@@EMENT SCANNER     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE GET\NEXT\CHAR IMPORTED ('GAZ
)@@G@@ETCHR'); " IN ELEMENT SCAN-CHAR     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDURE PUSH(STABA
)@@G@@TE: INTEGER WORD  @A@@@@              ,NMODE: INTEGER WORD) @D@@@@      BB
)@@G@@    IMPORTED ('SCANPUSH'); " IN ELEMENT SCANNER @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDBC
)@@G@@URE POP IMPORTED ('SCANPOP'); " IN ELEMENT SCANNER    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@BD
)@@G@@PROCEDURE NULL\OUT(SCANNED: MACHINE WORD POINTER)     @D@@@@          IMBE
)@@G@@PORTED ('NULOUT'); " IN ELEMENT SCANNER   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE DUBF
)@@G@@MP\DESCRIPTOR(IDENT: 6 FIELDATA CHARACTERS@D@@@@                        BG
)@@G@@ ,POINT: MACHINE WORD POINTER)@D@@@@          IMPORTED ('DMPDSC'); " IN BH
)@@G@@ELEMENT SCANNER   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED;     @[@@@@BI
)@@G@@"     @G@@@@" THE FOLLOWING POINTERS ARE GLOBAL, AND PERTAIN TO THE IMAGBJ
)@@G@@E BEING     @G@@@@" BUILT BY SCAN\MACRO\CALL.  THE LOCALS IN STATE\SUBSTBK
)@@G@@ITUTE ARE USED    @B@@@@" WHEN AN IMAGE IS ACTUALLY SUBSTITUTED.  @[@@@@BL
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   FP: INTEGER WORD; " USED AS FIELD POINTER   @[@@@@BM
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   SP: INTEGER WORD; " USED AS SUBFIELD POINTER@[@@@@BN
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   QF: CONDITION WORD; " FALSE IF INSIDE QUOTES@[@@@@BO
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   MACRO\POINTERS: STATIC MACHINE WORD POINTER;@[@@@@BP
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   MACRO\IMAGE: STATIC MACHINE WORD POINTER;   @[@@@@BQ
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" SYMBOLIC SUBSTITUTION POINTER BUFFER IS BUILT AT THE TIME BR
)@@G@@@E@@@@" THE MACRO IS CALLED.  IT IS LOOKED AT IN STATE\SUBSTITUTE.@[@@@@BS
)@@G@@"     @G@@@@DECLARE   FRSTLAST(*): LOCATABLE INTEGER WORD BASED(MACRO\POBT
)@@G@@INTERS)     @^@@@@          !*(*):MAPPED  @G@@@@             [FRST: 18 BBU
)@@G@@IT UNSIGNED INTEGER   " NUMBER OR FIRST COL     @E@@@@             ,LASTBV
)@@G@@: 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER]; " LAST COL    @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@BW
)@@G@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED FROM MACRO-INPUT WHENBX
)@@G@@ A MACRO CALL IS  @G@@@@" ABOUT TO BE PERFORMED.  IT SCANS THE IMAGE WHIBY
)@@G@@CH CALLED THE MACRO     @G@@@@" AND BUILDS A POINTER BUFFER AND A SUBSTIBZ
)@@G@@TUTED ICB WHICH ARE SAVED     @D@@@@" AND USED IF ARGUMENTS ARE REQUESTECA
)@@G@@D IN THE MACRO.   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE SCAN\MACRO\CALL EXPORTED('CB
)@@G@@SCANMACCAL')@E@@@@             RESULT MACHINE WORD POINTER " TO ARG BUFFCC
)@@G@@ER    @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@DEFINE    MAXFLD = 100; " TEMP@C@@@@DECLARE   ICCD
)@@G@@B\PTR\SAVE: MACHINE WORD POINTER,   @A@@@@          ICBLEN: INTEGER WORDCE
)@@G@@;     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@          MACRO\POINTERS := ALLOCATE\CORE(MAXFLDCF
)@@G@@); " GET POINTER BUFFER @A@@@@          INITIALIZE\SCANNER\STACKS;@B@@@@CG
)@@G@@          SP := 2; " SKIP OPTIONS FIELD   @B@@@@          FRST(1) := 0; CH
)@@G@@" NO FIELDS YET   @A@@@@          FRST(2) := 0; " NO OPTIONS@B@@@@      CI
)@@G@@    QF := TRUE; " NO QUOTES SEEN    @C@@@@          PUSH(S\CAL,0); " SETCJ
)@@G@@ UP CALL SCANNER  @F@@@@          MACRO\IMAGE := OS\PTR; " POINT TO DESCCK
)@@G@@RIPTOR OF ITEM    @A@@@@          IF CHARACTER EQ COMMA THEN@B@@@@      CL
)@@G@@     BEGIN " TO SET UP OPTIONS SCAN @B@@@@             GET\NEXT\CHAR; " CM
)@@G@@SCAN PAST IT@D@@@@             FP := 2; " SET INITIAL FIELD POINTER     CN
)@@G@@@D@@@@             SP := 3; " SET INITIAL SUBFIELD POINTER  @C@@@@      CO
)@@G@@       FRST(2) := 1; " OPTIONS PRESENT    @C@@@@             FRST(3) := CP
)@@G@@1; " OPTIONS START HERE @ @@@@             PUSH(S\FLD,0);   @A@@@@      CQ
)@@G@@     END; " OPTIONS SETUP     @A@@@@          DOSCAN; " DO SCANNING     CR
)@@G@@@C@@@@"         PDISPLAY('MACPTR',MACRO\POINTERS);    @B@@@@"         PDCS
)@@G@@ISPLAY('MACIMG',MACRO\IMAGE); @C@@@@"         SNAP('MACALL',20,MACRO\POICT
)@@G@@NTERS);     @G@@@@          ICBLEN := (DLEN(MACRO\IMAGE)+3)//4; " GET ICCU
)@@G@@B WORD LENGTH     @D@@@@          ICB\PTR\SAVE := ICB\PTR; " TEMP SAVE ICV
)@@G@@CB\PTR@H@@@@          ICB\PTR := ALLOCATE\CORE(ICBH\LEN+ICBLEN+SP); " ALCW
)@@G@@LOCATE ARGBUF     @B@@@@          MACRO\ARG\OFFSET := ICBLEN;     @ @@@@CX
)@@G@@          CARD\REFS := 1;     @B@@@@          KLUGE := DADR(MACRO\IMAGE)CY
)@@G@@;     @C@@@@          FOR I := 1 TO ICBLEN DO " COPY IMAGE  @C@@@@      CZ
)@@G@@       INPUT\CARD\WORD(I) := DNUM(I);     @C@@@@          FOR I := 1 TO DA
)@@G@@SP DO " COPY POINTERS   @D@@@@             INPUT\CARD\WORD(ICBLEN+I) := DB
)@@G@@FRSTLAST(I);@D@@@@          RELEASE\CORE(MACRO\POINTERS); " CLEAN UP    DC
)@@G@@@B@@@@"         PDISPLAY('ARGBUF',ICB\PTR);     @C@@@@          ICB\PTR DD
)@@G@@:=: ICB\PTR\SAVE; " SWITCH IT @A@@@@          RETURN(ICB\PTR\SAVE);     DE
)@@G@@@^@@@@END; " SCAN\MACRO\CALL  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@DF
)@@G@@" IN THE MACRO CALL SCANNING OPERATION TWO THINGS ARE BEING BUILT.@F@@@@DG
)@@G@@" ONE IS A 'POINTER BUFFER' WHICH POINTS TO THE BEGINNING AND END @F@@@@DH
)@@G@@" OF EACH FIELD AND SUBFIELD.  THE SECOND IS THE ACTUAL ARGUMENT  @F@@@@DI
)@@G@@" IMAGE, WHICH IS FULLY SUBSTITUTED.  THIS KEEPS US FROM HAVING TO@D@@@@DJ
)@@G@@" GO ARBITRARILY FAR BACK IN THE EXECUTION STACK.     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@DK
)@@G@@PROCEDURE STATE\MACRO\CALL EXPORTED ('STMACALL')@[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@      DL
)@@G@@    IF END\OF\SCAN THEN " WE MUST STOP    @B@@@@           BEGIN " TO TEDM
)@@G@@RMINATE SCANNING  @F@@@@             LAST(1) := DLEN(MACRO\IMAGE); " SETDN
)@@G@@ LAST CHAR ON CARD@ @@@@             POP; " THE STACK @B@@@@           EDO
)@@G@@ND; " SCANNING TERMINATION    @ @@@@          ELSE " CHECK IT OUT @D@@@@DP
)@@G@@             IF CHARACTER EQ BLANK THEN " JUST SKIP IT@B@@@@            DQ
)@@G@@  BEGIN " TO HANDLE BLANK     @E@@@@                PUT\CHAR\INTO\DESC(MDR
)@@G@@ACRO\IMAGE,CHARACTER);  @ @@@@                GET\NEXT\CHAR;@A@@@@      DS
)@@G@@        END; " BLANK CHAR     @B@@@@             ELSE " IS BEGINNING OF DT
)@@G@@FIELD @A@@@@              BEGIN " NEW FIELD     @G@@@@                FRDU
)@@G@@ST(1) := FRST(1) + 1; " INCREMENT NUMBER OF FIELDS    @D@@@@            DV
)@@G@@    FP := SP + 1; " SET NEW FIELD POSITION@D@@@@                FRST(FP)DW
)@@G@@ := 1; " SO FAR 1 SUBFIELD    @C@@@@                SP := FP+1; " SET NEDX
)@@G@@XT AVAIL SP @H@@@@                FRST(SP) := DLEN(MACRO\IMAGE)+1; " SETDY
)@@G@@ BEGINNING OF SUBFIELD  @D@@@@                PUSH(S\FLD,0); " BEGIN TO DZ
)@@G@@SCAN FIELD  @B@@@@              END; " OF NEW FIELD SETUP   @^@@@@END; "EA
)@@G@@ STATE\MACRO\CALL @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED WHEN A NEEB
)@@G@@W FIELD IS FOUND, AND KEEPS CONTROL @B@@@@" UNTIL THE END OF THE FIELD IEC
)@@G@@S FOUND.    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE STATE\MACRO\FIELD EXPORTED ('STMED
)@@G@@AFLD')@[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          IF CHARACTER EQ QUOTE THEN " FLIP FLAGEE
)@@G@@@ @@@@             QF := NOT QF;    @G@@@@          IF END\OF\SCAN OR (CEF
)@@G@@HARACTER EQ BLANK AND QF) THEN " MUST TERM@A@@@@           BEGIN " FIELDEG
)@@G@@ TERMINATION@G@@@@             LAST(SP) := DLEN(MACRO\IMAGE); " SET FINAEH
)@@G@@L CHAR IN SUBFIELD@G@@@@             LAST(FP) := DLEN(MACRO\IMAGE); " SEEI
)@@G@@T FINAL CHAR IN FIELD   @B@@@@             POP; " THE SCANNER STACK     EJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@           END; " TERMINATION @#@@@@          ELSE    @C@@@@      EK
)@@G@@     BEGIN " TO HANDLE NEXT CHAR IN FIELD @E@@@@             PUT\CHAR\INEL
)@@G@@TO\DESC(MACRO\IMAGE,CHARACTER);     @G@@@@             IF CHARACTER EQ CEM
)@@G@@OMMA AND QF THEN " START NEW SUBFIELD     @A@@@@              BEGIN " NEEN
)@@G@@W SUBFIELD  @H@@@@                LAST(SP) := DLEN(MACRO\IMAGE)-1; " SETEO
)@@G@@ FINAL CHAR IN SUBFIELD @H@@@@                FRST(FP) := FRST(FP) + 1; EP
)@@G@@" INCREMENT NUMBER OF SUBFIELDS     @D@@@@                SP := SP + 1; EQ
)@@G@@" INCREMENT SUBFLD PTR  @H@@@@                FRST(SP) := DLEN(MACRO\IMAER
)@@G@@GE)+1; " SET FIRST CHAR IN SUBF     @A@@@@              END; " NEW SUBFIES
)@@G@@ELD   @B@@@@             GET\NEXT\CHAR; " SCAN PAST IT@A@@@@           EET
)@@G@@ND; " OF CHAR IN FIELD  @^@@@@END; " STATE\MACRO\FIELD@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECEU
)@@G@@T);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" WHEN A SUBSTITUTION CHARACTER ([) IS SEEN IN TEV
)@@G@@HE INPUT SCANNER, @E@@@@" THREE ITEMS ARE STACKED.  THE TOPMOST IS A S\UEW
)@@G@@NK WHICH IN @F@@@@" CONJUCTION WITH THE SECOND, A S\EXP, SCANS THE EXPREEX
)@@G@@SSION WHICH @F@@@@" SHOULD EVALUATE TO AN INTEGER OF LENGTH 1 OR 2 OR A EY
)@@G@@NULL.  WHEN @F@@@@" THE S\EXP HITS THE CLOSE (]) CONTROL PASSES TO THE TEZ
)@@G@@HIRD ITEM   @ @@@@" STACKED, WHICH IS HERE.     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDFA
)@@G@@URE STATE\SUBSTITUTE EXPORTED ('STSUBST') @[@@@@BEGIN @H@@@@DECLARE   MAFB
)@@G@@CRO\PTR\SAVE: MACHINE WORD POINTER; " SAVE GLOBAL FRSTLAST POINTER@F@@@@FC
)@@G@@DECLARE   ARG\ICB: MACHINE WORD POINTER; " TO ICB TO SUBSTITUTE   @[@@@@FD
)@@G@@"     @H@@@@" NOTE THAT MACRO\POINTERS MUST BE SAVED AND RESTORED AS THIFE
)@@G@@S ROUTINE MAY     @G@@@@" BE CALLED DURING THE SCAN OF A MACRO CALL IMAGFF
)@@G@@E, AND CANNOT BE ALLOWED@C@@@@" TO TRASH THE GLOBAL MACRO\POINTERS. (CBCFG
)@@G@@)     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          MACRO\PTR\SAVE := MACRO\POINTERS; " SAFH
)@@G@@VE GLOBAL   @G@@@@          ARG\ICB := GET\MACRO\ARGUMENT(SCANNED,SFLG);FI
)@@G@@ " GET ARG ICB    @F@@@@          IF (ARG\ICB NE NULL\PTR) THEN " IF NONFJ
)@@G@@-NULL ARGUMENT    @G@@@@             PUSH\THIS\ICB(SUBSTI\CARD,ARG\ICB);FK
)@@G@@ " SUBSTITUTE ARGUMENT  @E@@@@          MACRO\POINTERS := MACRO\PTR\SAVEFL

)@@G@@          POP; " THE SCANNER STACK  @^@@@@END; " STATE\SUBSTITUTE @[@@@@FO
)@@G@@"     @G@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED FROM OPER-FUNCS TO PERFORM ARG$ FFP
)@@G@@UNCTION.    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\ARG\FUNCTION@ @@@@      FQ
)@@G@@    EXPORTED ('FUNARG$')@[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@DECLARE   ICB\PTR\SAVE: MACHINFR

)@@G@@          ICB\PTR\SAVE := ICB\PTR; " SAVE GLOBAL@C@@@@          IF (PACKFU
)@@G@@ET\TYPE(CIP) NE PKT\MACRO) AND@D@@@@             (PACKET\TYPE(CIP) NE PKFV

)@@G@@" RELEASE IT@B@@@@              END; " COPY ICB TO STACK    @A@@@@      GF

)@@G@@ THE ARG$ FUNCTION.     @D@@@@" IT RETURNS AN ICB CONTAINING THE DESIREDGJ

)@@G@@;     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS SCANNER IS CALLEDMY

)@@G@@NED) NE TYPNUL ) THEN   @C@@@@             STACK\DATA; " SETS SCANNED TONO
)@@G@@ NULL @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" IF RETURNED ITEM IS NULL THEN WE MUST CHECK TONP
)@@G@@ SEE IF AN  @F@@@@" OPERATOR TERMINATED SCANNING.  IF SO, WE CREATE A DENQ

)@@G@@IMITIVE SCANNER AGAIN   @#@@@@             ELSE @E@@@@                DTNY
)@@G@@YP(SCANNED) := TYPOPR; " SET TYPE OPERATOR@#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@NZ
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" IF IT IS AN OPERATOR COMPARE PRIORITIES AGAINST STACK.    OA
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@          WHILE (DTYP(SCANNED) EQ TYPOPR) AND " WHILE OB
)@@G@@OP TO CHECK @F@@@@            OK\TO\PERFORM(OPER,DLEN(SCANNED)) DO " ANDOC
)@@G@@ OK TO DO IT@ @@@@           BEGIN " PERFORM    @A@@@@             PERFOOD
)@@G@@RM\OP; " ON STACK @ @@@@           END; " PERFORM     @F@@@@          IFOE
)@@G@@ (DTYP(SCANNED) EQ TYPOPR) THEN " STILL HAVE OPERATOR @C@@@@            OF
)@@G@@ IF OK\TO\STACK(DLEN(SCANNED)) THEN @C@@@@                STACK\OPERATOROG
)@@G@@(DLEN(SCANNED));  @#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@              BEGIN " ENOH

)@@G@@                POP; " THE SCANNER STACK  @A@@@@              END; " ENDOJ
)@@G@@ SCANNING   @^@@@@END; " OF STATE\VALUE   @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@OK
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE CHECKS THE CURRENT CHARACTER TO SEE IF IT IOL
)@@G@@S     @F@@@@" AN OPERATOR. IF NOT, IT RETURNS ZERO, ELSE THE OPERATOR INOM
)@@G@@DEX.  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE IS\OPER RESULT INTEGER WORD     @[@@@@ON
)@@G@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   OPR: INTEGER WORD; " OPERATOR WE WILL RETURN@B@@@@OO
)@@G@@DECLARE   I : INTEGER WORD; " SEARCH INDEX@[@@@@"     @C@@@@          OPOP
)@@G@@R := 0; " CLEAR ANY OLD OPERATOR    @C@@@@          IF (NOT ALPHA) AND (OQ
)@@G@@NOT NUMERIC) AND  @A@@@@             CHARACTER NE BLANK AND @A@@@@      OR
)@@G@@       CHARACTER NE QUOTE AND @D@@@@             (CHARACTER NE COMMA OR OS
)@@G@@NOT COMA) THEN    @B@@@@           BEGIN " TO FIND OPERATOR INDEX @B@@@@OT
)@@G@@             I := 1; " INITIALIZE SEARCH  @D@@@@             OPR := OPREOU
)@@G@@OL; " DEFAULT IS END-OF-LINE  @C@@@@             WHILE I LE GOPS DO " SEOV

)@@G@@          IF CHARACTER EQ OCHR(I) THEN " FOUND IT     @B@@@@            OX

)@@G@@                   GET\NEXT\CHAR; " SCAN PAST OPERATOR@C@@@@            PA
)@@G@@     END; " OF SETTING FOUND FLAG   @D@@@@                I := I + 1; " PB
)@@G@@NEXT ENTRY TO SEARCH    @B@@@@              END; " OF TEST THIS ENTRY   PC
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          RETURN(OPR); " TO CALLER  @#@@@@PD
)@@G@@END; " OF IS\OPER @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" LOOK UP NAME LABEL SYMBOL IN VARIOPE
)@@G@@US SYMBOL TABLES. @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE LOOKUP\NAME\LABEL   @[@@@@PF
)@@G@@BEGIN @D@@@@          MONOCASE(SCANNED); " CONVERT TO MONOCASE    @F@@@@PG
)@@G@@          SCANNED := LOOKUP\SYMBOL(MONOCASE\PTR); " SYMTAB LOOKUP @C@@@@PH
)@@G@@"         DUMP\DESCRIPTOR('AFTLOK',SCANNED);    @E@@@@          IF SCANNPI
)@@G@@ED EQ NULL\PTR THEN " IT WAS UNDEFINED    @C@@@@           BEGIN " TO SEPJ
)@@G@@ARCH SYSTEM SYMBOLS     @G@@@@             SCANNED := LOOKUP\SYSTEM\SYMBPK
)@@G@@OL(MONOCASE\PTR); " LOOKUP    @E@@@@             IF SCANNED EQ NULL\PTR PL

)@@G@@@D@@@@                SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR8; " SO SAY SO  @E@@@@      PN

)@@G@@           END; " OF HANDLE UNDEF SYMB    @ @@@@END; " OF LOOKUP\NAME\LAPQ
)@@G@@BEL   @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE RETURNSPR
)@@G@@ TRUE WHEN IT IS OK TO PERFORM THE  @^@@@@" STACKTOP OPERATOR.    @[@@@@PS
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE OK\TO\PERFORM(STAKOP: INTEGER WORD,SCANOP: INTEGERPT
)@@G@@ WORD)@ @@@@          RESULT CONDITION    @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@"         ODPU
)@@G@@ISPLAY('STAKOP',STAKOP);@B@@@@"         ODISPLAY('PRIO',PRIO(STAKOP));  PV
)@@G@@@A@@@@"         ODISPLAY('SCANOP',SCANOP);@B@@@@"         ODISPLAY('PRIOPW
)@@G@@',PRIO(SCANOP));  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" DECISION MUST BE MADE HERE TO STACPX
)@@G@@K OPERATOR AND CONTINUE OR    @F@@@@" PERFORM OPERATOR ON STACK.  ALGORIPY
)@@G@@THM WAS DEVELOPED BY ME (BEN) @F@@@@" AND KERN FOR CPMD.  IF OPERATOR ISPZ
)@@G@@ OPEN PARENTHESIS, OR IF THE  @G@@@@" TOP DATA ITEM ON THE STACK IS A NUQA
)@@G@@LL AND THE OPERATOR LAST SCANNED    @F@@@@" IS NOT END-OF-LINE, OR IF THQB
)@@G@@E TOP OPERATOR ON THE STACK HAS A   @G@@@@" LOWER PRIORITY THAN OPERATORQC
)@@G@@ SCANNED, THE OPERATOR SCANNED IS STACKED @G@@@@" AND A NEW SCAN IS STARQD

)@@G@@FORMED.     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          IF (SCANOP EQ 0) OR " IF CLOSE TQF

)@@G@@WAYS STACKED@D@@@@             RETURN(FALSE); " FORCE IT TO BE STACKED  QI
)@@G@@@G@@@@          IF PRIO(STAKOP) LT PRIO(SCANOP) THEN " HIGHER PRIO STACKQJ
)@@G@@ED    @D@@@@             RETURN(FALSE); " FORCE IT TO BE STACKED  @G@@@@QK
)@@G@@          IF (STAKOP EQ OPRBGL) THEN " IF BEGINNING OF LINE OPERATOR    QL
)@@G@@@C@@@@             RETURN(FALSE); " DONT EXECUTE IT   @A@@@@          IFQM
)@@G@@ (SCANOP EQ OPREOL) OR  @A@@@@             (SCANOP EQ OPRCPR) OR  @A@@@@QN
)@@G@@             (SCANOP EQ OPRCBR) THEN@D@@@@             RETURN(TRUE); " DQO

)@@G@@EN " MONADIC OP   @D@@@@             RETURN(FALSE); " ALWAYS STACK MONADQQ
)@@G@@IC    @C@@@@          RETURN(TRUE); " ELSE OK TO PERFORM    @^@@@@END; "QR
)@@G@@ OK\TO\PERFORM    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE DECIDES IF THE OPERQS
)@@G@@ATOR PASSED MAY BE STACKED.   @C@@@@" IF IT MAY NOT, THEN THE VALUE SCANQT

)@@G@@)     @ @@@@          RESULT CONDITION    @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          IFQV

)@@G@@DURE IS CALLED BY THE EXPRESSION SCANNER AFTER EACH ITEM    @F@@@@" TO SRA

)@@G@@T EVAL)) OR @E@@@@             END\OF\SCAN THEN " KLUGE AN END OF LINE ORE

)@@G@@@E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO STACK THE OPERATOR SCANNED.   @[@@@@RM

)@@G@@@F@@@@          PUSH(STAT,LOCAL\MODES); " EXTEND SCAN ANOTHER LEVEL     RO

)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE ITS

)@@G@@IABLE TO CREATE.  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\DECLARATION(VAR\TYVF

)@@G@@ACKET @E@@@@             IF (MACRO NE NULL\PTR) THEN " OK TO GO MORE    XK
)@@G@@@G@@@@                MACRO := FIND\INSERT\POINT(IO\PACKET\BACK\LINK(MACXL
)@@G@@RO)); @D@@@@             IF (MACRO EQ NULL\PTR) THEN " NOT LOCAL  @D@@@@XM
)@@G@@                GLOBAL\SYMBOLS := INSERT\NEW\VARIABLE @C@@@@            XN
)@@G@@       (GLOBAL\SYMBOLS,SYMBOL);     @#@@@@             ELSE @E@@@@      XO
)@@G@@          LOCAL\SYMBOLS(MACRO) := INSERT\NEW\VARIABLE @D@@@@            XP
)@@G@@       ( LOCAL\SYMBOLS(MACRO) , SYMBOL ); @[@@@@"     @A@@@@           EXQ
)@@G@@ND; " CREATE VARIABLE   @ @@@@          RETURN(SYMBOL);     @ @@@@END; "XR
)@@G@@ DECLARE\DOCUMENT\GLOBAL@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED BY THXS
)@@G@@E LOCAL DIRECTIVE TO DEFINE   @A@@@@" A DIRECTIVE MACRO LOCAL VARIABLE. XT
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @H@@@@PROCEDURE DECLARE\DOCUMENT\LOCAL(NAME: MACHINE POINTERXU
)@@G@@) " TO NAME TO DECLARE  @C@@@@          RESULT MACHINE POINTER " TO SYMBXV
)@@G@@OL    @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@DECLARE   SYMBOL: MACHINE POINTER; " TO THE NODEXW
)@@G@@ WE CREATE  @D@@@@DECLARE   MACRO: MACHINE POINTER; " TO MACRO LOCAL TO XX
)@@G@@@E@@@@DECLARE   NAME\LEN: INTEGER WORD; " NAME LENGTH IN WORDS    @[@@@@XY
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@          MACRO := FIND\INSERT\POINT(CIP); " FIND MACRO     XZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          IF (MACRO EQ NULL\PTR) THEN " NO LOCAL CONTEXT    @D@@@@YA
)@@G@@             DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR14; " DIAGNOSE   @#@@@@          ELYB
)@@G@@SE    @C@@@@           BEGIN " MAKE SURE NOT ALREADY THERE  @G@@@@      YC
)@@G@@       NAME\LEN := DESC\DATA\LEN(NAME); " GET LENGTH IN WORDS     @B@@@@YD
)@@G@@             SYMBOL := SEARCH\FOR\NODE    @F@@@@                (LOCAL\SYE
)@@G@@YMBOLS(MACRO),TYPSTR,NAME\LEN,DADR(NAME));@B@@@@             IF (SYMBOL YF
)@@G@@NE NULL\PTR) THEN @F@@@@                DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR15; " ALYG
)@@G@@READY DEFINED     @#@@@@             ELSE @C@@@@              BEGIN " CRYH
)@@G@@EATE\LOCAL\VARIABLE     @E@@@@                SYMBOL := CREATE\NEW\NODE(YI
)@@G@@NAME); " CREATE IT@E@@@@                LOCAL\SYMBOLS(MACRO) := INSERT\NYJ
)@@G@@EW\NODE     @D@@@@                   (LOCAL\SYMBOLS(MACRO),SYMBOL);     YK
)@@G@@@B@@@@              END; " CREATE LOCAL VARIABLE@C@@@@           END; " YL
)@@G@@MAKE SURE NOT ALREADY THERE   @ @@@@          RETURN(SYMBOL);     @ @@@@YM
)@@G@@END; " DECLARE\DOCUMENT\LOCAL @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@YN
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED BY THE LET COMMAND WHEN A VALUE IYO
)@@G@@S     @C@@@@" STORED INTO A PREVIOUSLY UNDEFINED VARIABLE.  @[@@@@"     YP
)@@G@@@H@@@@PROCEDURE CREATE\COMMAND\VARIABLE (NAME: MACHINE POINTER) " TO DESYQ
)@@G@@CR FOR NAME @E@@@@             EXPORTED ('STMCOM') RESULT MACHINE POINTEYR
)@@G@@R     @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@DECLARE   NNODE: MACHINE POINTER; " TO THE NODE YS
)@@G@@WE WILL CREATE    @F@@@@DECLARE   MACRO: MACHINE POINTER; " TO MACRO TO YT
)@@G@@BE INSERTED TO    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          NNODE := CREATE\NEW\NODE(NYU
)@@G@@AME); " CREATE NODE     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" UNLESS SPECIFIED BY COMMAND,YV
)@@G@@ VARIABLES ARE CREATED AS LOCAL TO  @^@@@@" THE EXECUTING CONTEXT.@F@@@@YW
)@@G@@" NOTE: UNTIL COMMAND MACROS IMPLEMENTED THIS ROUTINE STARTS OUT  @E@@@@YX
)@@G@@" FROM ZERO, SO THERE WILL BE NO LOCAL COMMAND SYMBOLS.     @[@@@@"     YY
)@@G@@@I@@@@          MACRO := FIND\INSERT\POINT(NULL\PTR); " START AT CURRENTYZ
)@@G@@ MACRO PACKET     @D@@@@          IF (MACRO EQ NULL\PTR) THEN " NOT LOCAZA
)@@G@@L     @H@@@@             COMMAND\SYMBOLS := INSERT\NEW\VARIABLE(COMMAND\ZB
)@@G@@SYMBOLS,NNODE);   @#@@@@          ELSE    @E@@@@             LOCAL\SYMBOZC
)@@G@@LS(MACRO) := INSERT\NEW\VARIABLE    @D@@@@                ( LOCAL\SYMBOLZD
)@@G@@S(MACRO) , NNODE );     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          RETURN(NNODE); " TO ZE
)@@G@@CALLER@ @@@@END; " CREATE\COMMAND\VARIABLE@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@ZF
)@@G@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED BY THE LET DIRECTIVE WHEN A VALUE IS   @C@@@@ZG
)@@G@@" STORED INTO A PREVIOUSLY UNDEFINED VARIABLE.  @[@@@@"     @H@@@@PROCEDZH
)@@G@@URE CREATE\DOCUMENT\VARIABLE (NAME: MACHINE POINTER) " TO DESCR FOR NAMEZI
)@@G@@@E@@@@             EXPORTED ('STMDOC') RESULT MACHINE POINTER     @[@@@@ZJ
)@@G@@BEGIN @F@@@@DECLARE   NNODE: MACHINE POINTER; " TO THE NODE WE WILL CREAZK
)@@G@@TE    @F@@@@DECLARE   MACRO: MACHINE POINTER; " TO MACRO TO BE INSERTED ZL
)@@G@@TO    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          NNODE := CREATE\NEW\NODE(NAME); " CREAZM
)@@G@@TE NODE     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" UNLESS SPECIFIED BY COMMAND, VARIABLES AZN
)@@G@@RE CREATED AS LOCAL TO  @^@@@@" THE EXECUTING CONTEXT.@[@@@@"     @H@@@@ZO
)@@G@@          MACRO := FIND\INSERT\POINT(CIP); " START AT CURRENT INPUT PACKZP
)@@G@@ET    @D@@@@          IF (MACRO EQ NULL\PTR) THEN " NOT LOCAL     @H@@@@ZQ
)@@G@@             GLOBAL\SYMBOLS := INSERT\NEW\VARIABLE(GLOBAL\SYMBOLS,NNODE)ZR
)@@G@@;     @#@@@@          ELSE    @E@@@@             LOCAL\SYMBOLS(MACRO) :=ZS
)@@G@@ INSERT\NEW\VARIABLE    @D@@@@                ( LOCAL\SYMBOLS(MACRO) , NZT
)@@G@@NODE );     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          RETURN(NNODE); " TO CALLER@A@@@@ZU
)@@G@@END; " CREATE\DOCUMENT\VARIABLE     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     ZV
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO MOVE UP ONE INSERT POINTZW
)@@G@@ IN THE     @F@@@@" DYNAMIC MACRO TREE.  IF THE TREE IS EXHAUSTED, A NULZX
)@@G@@L POINTER   @E@@@@" IS RETURNED TO FLAG THE CALLER TO CREATE GLOBAL VARIZY
)@@G@@ABLE. @[@@@@"     @H@@@@PROCEDURE FIND\INSERT\POINT(START: MACHINE POINTZZ
)@@G@@ER) " OF PACKET TO START AT   @F@@@@          RESULT MACHINE POINTER " TAA
)@@G@@O NEXT INSERT POINT OR NULL   @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   MACRO: MACHINEAB
)@@G@@ POINTER; " TO CURRENT PACKET @E@@@@DECLARE   FOUND: MACHINE POINTER; " AC
)@@G@@TO NEXT INSERT POINT    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          MACRO := START;     AD
)@@G@@@ @@@@          FOUND := NULL\PTR;  @F@@@@          WHILE (MACRO NE NULLAE
)@@G@@\PTR) AND (FOUND EQ NULL\PTR) DO    @A@@@@           BEGIN " CHECK THIS AF
)@@G@@PACKET@D@@@@             IF PACKET\TYPE(MACRO) EQ PKT\MACRO OR    @D@@@@AG
)@@G@@                PACKET\TYPE(MACRO) EQ PKT\IMACRO THEN @E@@@@            AH
)@@G@@    FOUND := MACRO; " FLAG THIS IS THE POINT    @F@@@@             MACROAI
)@@G@@ := IO\PACKET\BACK\LINK(MACRO); " LINK BACK     @A@@@@           END; " AJ
)@@G@@CHECK THIS PACKET @B@@@@          RETURN(FOUND); " INSERT POINT   @^@@@@AK
)@@G@@END; " FIND\INSERT\POINT@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS ROUTINE INSAL
)@@G@@ERTS THE NEW VARIABLE INTO THE SELECTED TABLE.  @E@@@@" NOTE THAT IF THEAM
)@@G@@ INSERT ROUTINE WERE CHANGED TO DO ITS OWN@C@@@@" SEARCHING THIS ROUTINEAN
)@@G@@ WOULD NOT BE NECESSARY.@[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE INSERT\NEW\VARIABLE(AO
)@@G@@SYMBOL\TABLE: MACHINE POINTER " TO ROOT   @H@@@@                        AP
)@@G@@     ,NEW\VARIABLE: MACHINE POINTER) " TO NEW ENTRY   @D@@@@          REAQ
)@@G@@SULT MACHINE POINTER " TO NEW SYMBOL TABLE@[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@DECLARE   NEAR
)@@G@@W\SYMBOL\TABLE: MACHINE POINTER; " TO NEW TABLE @E@@@@DECLARE   NAME\LENAS
)@@G@@GTH: INTEGER WORD; " NAME LENGTH IN WORDS @D@@@@DECLARE   FOUND\PTR: MACAT
)@@G@@HINE POINTER; " TO ENTRY FOUND@[@@@@"     @G@@@@          NAME\LENGTH :=AU
)@@G@@ SLEN(NEW\VARIABLE); " GET LENGTH FOR SEARCH    @G@@@@          FOUND\PTAV
)@@G@@R := SEARCH\FOR\NODE " CHECK IF ITS THERE ALREADY     @G@@@@            AW
)@@G@@ (SYMBOL\TABLE,TYPSTR,NAME\LENGTH,LOC(SNAM(NEW\VARIABLE)) );@B@@@@      AX
)@@G@@    IF (FOUND\PTR NE NULL\PTR) THEN @D@@@@             ERROR; " SHOULD HAY
)@@G@@AVE BEEN DETECTED BY NOW@#@@@@          ELSE    @G@@@@             NEW\SAZ
)@@G@@YMBOL\TABLE := INSERT\NEW\NODE " INSERT NEW SYMBOL    @C@@@@            BA
)@@G@@    (SYMBOL\TABLE,NEW\VARIABLE);    @A@@@@          RETURN(NEW\SYMBOL\TABB
)@@G@@BLE); @ @@@@END; " INSERT\NEW\VARIABLE    @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@BC
)@@G@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO SET THE VALUE OF ABD
)@@G@@ SYMBOL EQUAL TO  @E@@@@" A NEW VALUE.  THE OLD VALUE BUFFER IS USED IF BE
)@@G@@POSSIBLE.   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE SET\VALUE(SYMB: MACHINE POINTER BF
)@@G@@  " TO SYMBOL TABLE ENTRY     @G@@@@                   ,VALU: MACHINE POBG
)@@G@@INTER)  " TO DESCRIPTOR FOR VALUE   @ @@@@          EXPORTED ('SETVAL') BH
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@DECLARE   OLDLEN: INTEGER WORD; " LENGTH OF OLD VALUE BI
)@@G@@BUFFER@E@@@@DECLARE   OLD\DATA\PTR: MACHINE POINTER; " TO OLD VALUE     BJ
)@@G@@@E@@@@DECLARE   OLD\DATA(1): INTEGER WORD BASED(OLD\DATA\PTR);    @[@@@@BK
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@DECLARE   NEWLEN: INTEGER WORD; " LENGTH OF NEW VALUE BUFFERBL
)@@G@@@E@@@@DECLARE   NEW\DATA\PTR: MACHINE POINTER; " TO NEW VALUE     @E@@@@BM
)@@G@@DECLARE   NEW\DATA(1): INTEGER WORD BASED(NEW\DATA\PTR);    @[@@@@"     BN
)@@G@@@B@@@@" IF OLD VALUE IS A TABLE RELEASE IT.     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@      BO
)@@G@@    IF DTYP(SYMB) EQ TYPTAB THEN    @A@@@@             RELEASE\VALUE(SYMBP
)@@G@@B);   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" IF NEW VALUE IS A TABLE COPY IT   @[@@@@"     BQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@          IF DTYP(VALU) EQ TYPTAB THEN    @A@@@@           BEGIN "BR
)@@G@@ TO COPY TABLE    @D@@@@             RELEASE\VALUE(SYMB); " RELEASE OLD BS
)@@G@@VALUE @F@@@@             DADR(SYMB) := COPY\TABLE( DADR(VALU) ); " COPY BT
)@@G@@TABLE @A@@@@           END; " OF COPYING TABLE  @#@@@@          ELSE    BU
)@@G@@@C@@@@           BEGIN " TO SET VALUE TO A DATA ITEM  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@BV
)@@G@@" COMPARE THE WORD SIZES OF THE OLD AND NEW VALUE SO THE SAME     @B@@@@BW
)@@G@@" BUFFER CAN BE USED IF ITS LONG ENOUGH.  @[@@@@"     @G@@@@            BX
)@@G@@ OLDLEN := DESC\DATA\LEN(SYMB); " GET LENGTH OF OLD BUFFER  @F@@@@      BY
)@@G@@       NEWLEN := DESC\DATA\LEN(VALU); " GET SPACE NEEDED    @[@@@@"     BZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@" IF THE OLD VALUE BUFFER IS SMALLER THAN THE NEW VALUE BUFFER    CA
)@@G@@@G@@@@" THEN WE NEED MORE SPACE SO RELEASE AND REACQUIRE.  NOTE THAT THICB
)@@G@@S     @B@@@@" IS NOT REQUIRED UNDER MOST CONDITIONS.  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@CC
)@@G@@             IF OLDLEN LT NEWLEN THEN     @D@@@@              BEGIN " TOCD
)@@G@@ GET A LARGER VALUE BUFFER    @D@@@@                RELEASE\VALUE(SYMB);CE
)@@G@@ " RELEASE VALUE  @F@@@@                DADR(SYMB) := ALLOCATE\CORE(NEWLCF
)@@G@@EN); " GET NEW ONE@D@@@@              END; " OF ALLOCATING NEW VALUE BUFCG
)@@G@@FER   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" NOW COPY VALUE WORD FOR WORD TO NEW CORE AREA.CH
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@             OLD\DATA\PTR := DADR(SYMB);  @B@@@@      CI
)@@G@@       NEW\DATA\PTR := DADR(VALU);  @A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO NEWCJ
)@@G@@LEN DO@E@@@@                OLD\DATA(I) := NEW\DATA(I); " COPY VALUE    CK
)@@G@@@B@@@@           END; " OF COPYING DATA ITEM    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" NOW CL
)@@G@@SET ALL CORRESPONDING FIELDS IN THE NEW DESCRIPTOR    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@CM
)@@G@@          DTYP(SYMB) := DTYP(VALU); " COPY TYPE @C@@@@          DSBT(SYMCN
)@@G@@B) := DSBT(VALU); " SUBTYPE   @C@@@@          DLEN(SYMB) := DLEN(VALU); CO
)@@G@@" AND LENGTH@#@@@@END; " SET\VALUE  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     CP
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@" PRODUCE A COPY OF THE TABLE PASSED AS ARGUMENT.     CQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE COPY\TABLE(OLD: MACHINE POINTER)@C@@@@      CR
)@@G@@    RESULT MACHINE POINTER " TO COPY MADE @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@DECLARE   NECS
)@@G@@W: MACHINE POINTER; " TO COPY WE WILL BUILD     @F@@@@DECLARE   NEWLEN: CT
)@@G@@INTEGER WORD; " LENGTH OF NEW NODE IN WORDS     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@DECLARCU
)@@G@@E   OLD\NODE(1): INTEGER WORD BASED(OLD); @C@@@@DECLARE   NEW\NODE(1): ICV
)@@G@@NTEGER WORD BASED(NEW); @[@@@@"     @A@@@@"         PDISPLAY('CPYIN',OLDCW
)@@G@@);    @C@@@@          NEW := NULL\PTR; " INITIALIZE TO NULL @A@@@@      CX
)@@G@@    IF (OLD NE NULL\PTR) THEN @ @@@@           BEGIN " COPY TABLE @G@@@@CY
)@@G@@             NEWLEN := STH\LEN+SLEN(OLD); " GET WORD LENGTH TO COPY     CZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@             NEW := ALLOCATE\CORE(NEWLEN); " GET CORE FOR NODE    DA
)@@G@@@A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO NEWLEN DO@E@@@@                NEW\NODEDB
)@@G@@(I) := OLD\NODE(I); " COPY NODE     @G@@@@             SLLK(NEW) := COPYDC
)@@G@@\TABLE( SLLK(OLD) ); " COPY LEFT TREE     @G@@@@             SRLK(NEW) :DD
)@@G@@= COPY\TABLE( SRLK(OLD) ); " COPY RITE TREE     @E@@@@             DTYP(DE
)@@G@@NEW) := TYPNUL; " INHIBIT VALUE RELEASE   @D@@@@             DADR(NEW) :DF
)@@G@@= NULL\PTR; " IN SET\VALUE    @D@@@@             SET\VALUE(NEW,OLD); " CDG
)@@G@@OPY VALUE IF ANY  @ @@@@           END; " COPY TABLE  @A@@@@"         PDDH
)@@G@@ISPLAY('CPYOUT',NEW);   @A@@@@          RETURN(NEW); " TO CALLER  @#@@@@DI
)@@G@@END; " COPY\TABLE @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" INTEGER FUNCTION TO REDJ
)@@G@@TURN THE NUMBER OF WORDS NEEDED TO STORE  @B@@@@" THE DATA REPRESENTED BDK
)@@G@@Y A DESCRIPTOR.   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE DESC\DATA\LEN(SYMBOL: MACHDL
)@@G@@INE POINTER) " TO DESCRIPTOR  @ @@@@          EXPORTED ('DSCDLN') @C@@@@DM
)@@G@@          RESULT INTEGER WORD " LENGTH OF DATA  @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@DECLARDN
)@@G@@E   LENGTH: INTEGER WORD; " DATA LENGTH   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          CADO
)@@G@@SEENTRY DTYP(SYMBOL) " FIND LENGTH OF NEW VALUE @^@@@@          CASE TYPDP
)@@G@@NUL:  @ @@@@             LENGTH := 0;     @ @@@@          CASE TYPINT,TYDQ
)@@G@@PDST: @D@@@@             LENGTH := DLEN(SYMBOL); " ONE PER WORD   @ @@@@DR
)@@G@@          CASE TYPSTR,TYPNAM: @G@@@@             LENGTH := ( DLEN(SYMBOLDS
)@@G@@)+3 ) // 4; " SET LENGTH NEEDED     @^@@@@          CASE TYPTAB:  @ @@@@DT
)@@G@@             LENGTH := 0;     @#@@@@          CASE *: @#@@@@           BDU
)@@G@@EGIN  @B@@@@             PDISPLAY('DSCLEN',SYMBOL);   @^@@@@            DV
)@@G@@ ERROR;     @A@@@@           END; " OF ERROR CASE     @#@@@@          ENDW
)@@G@@DCASE;@B@@@@          RETURN(LENGTH); " TO CALLER     @^@@@@END; " DESC\DX
)@@G@@DATA\LEN    @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THISDY
)@@G@@ PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO RELEASE AN ENTIRE SYMBOL TABLE@E@@@@" BACK TO FRDZ
)@@G@@EE CORE.  IT IS CALLED WHEN A MACRO TERMINATES, @B@@@@" FOR EXAMPLE, TO EA
)@@G@@GET RID OF ALL LOCALS.  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE RELEASE\SYMBOL\TABLEEB
)@@G@@ (ROOT: MACHINE POINTER) " TO TABLE @ @@@@          EXPORTED('STBREL')  EC
)@@G@@@D@@@@          RESULT MACHINE POINTER " NULL\PTR TO STORE  @[@@@@BEGIN ED
)@@G@@@A@@@@          IF (ROOT NE NULL\PTR) THEN@B@@@@           BEGIN " TO REEE
)@@G@@LEASE THIS NODE   @I@@@@             SLLK(ROOT) := RELEASE\SYMBOL\TABLE(EF
)@@G@@SLLK(ROOT)); " RELEASE LEFT SUBT    @I@@@@             SRLK(ROOT) := RELEG
)@@G@@EASE\SYMBOL\TABLE(SRLK(ROOT)); " RELEASE RITE SUBT    @D@@@@            EH
)@@G@@ RELEASE\VALUE(ROOT); " RELEASE VALUE CORE@D@@@@             RELEASE\COREI
)@@G@@E(ROOT); " RELEASE NODE ITSELF@A@@@@           END; " OF NODE RELEASE   EJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@          RETURN(NULL\PTR);   @ @@@@END; " RELEASE\SYMBOL\TABLE   EK
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" RELEASE VALUE CORE AND SET VALUE TO NULLEL
)@@G@@ (TYPELESS).@[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE RELEASE\VALUE(SYMBOL: MACHINE POEM
)@@G@@INTER) " TO DESCRIPTOR  @ @@@@          EXPORTED('RELVAL')  @[@@@@BEGIN EN
)@@G@@@F@@@@          CASEENTRY DTYP(SYMBOL) " WHAT KIND OF VALUE DOES IT HAVEEO
)@@G@@@C@@@@          CASE TYPNUL,TYPINT,TYPDST,TYPSTR:     @F@@@@            EP
)@@G@@ IF DADR(SYMBOL) NE NULL\PTR THEN " IF CORE BUFFER    @E@@@@            EQ
)@@G@@    RELEASE\CORE(DADR(SYMBOL)); " RELEASE IT    @^@@@@          CASE TYPER
)@@G@@TAB:  @F@@@@             DADR(SYMBOL) := RELEASE\SYMBOL\TABLE( DADR(SYMBES
)@@G@@OL) );@#@@@@          CASE *: @^@@@@             ERROR;     @#@@@@      ET
)@@G@@    ENDCASE;@A@@@@          DTYP(SYMBOL) := TYPNUL;   @ @@@@          DSEU
)@@G@@BT(SYMBOL) := 0;  @ @@@@          DLEN(SYMBOL) := 0;  @A@@@@          DAEV
)@@G@@DR(SYMBOL) := NULL\PTR; @^@@@@END; " RELEASE\VALUE    @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECEW
)@@G@@T);   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THE FOLLOWING ROUTINES ARE USED TO MAINTAIN ANEX
)@@G@@D ACCESS THE@F@@@@" BALANCED (AVL) BINARY TREES USED BY DPS FOR ITS SYMBEY
)@@G@@OL TABLES.  @F@@@@" MANY OF THE ALGORITHMS USED WERE TAKEN FROM SECTION EZ
)@@G@@6.2.3 OF    @F@@@@" DONALD KNUTH'S 'THE ART OF COMPUTER PROGRAMMING', VOFA
)@@G@@LUME 3.     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" PROGRAMMERS OF THE WORLD, UNITE   @C@@@@FB
)@@G@@"  YOU HAVE NOTHING TO LOSE BUT YOUR CHAINS.    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     FC
)@@G@@@F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO SEARCH A BINARY TREE FOR A GIVEN    FD
)@@G@@@F@@@@" KEY VALUE.  THE ARGUMENTS ARE THE ROOT OF THE TREE, THE TYPE    FE
)@@G@@@D@@@@" AND LENGTH OF THE KEY, AND A POINTER TO THE KEY.    @[@@@@"     FF
)@@G@@@E@@@@" NOTE THAT THIS ROUTINE MUST BE CALLED BEFORE AN ATTEMPT TO@E@@@@FG
)@@G@@" INSERT OR DELETE NODES FROM A TREE, AS INFORMATION STORED @E@@@@" IN TFH
)@@G@@HE TEMPORARY STACK IS USED BY THESE TWO ROUTINES.     @[@@@@"     @ @@@@FI
)@@G@@PROCEDURE SEARCH\FOR\NODE     @E@@@@             (ROOT: MACHINE POINTER FJ
)@@G@@  " TO ROOT OF TREE     @C@@@@             ,KTYP: INTEGER WORD      " KEFK
)@@G@@Y TYPE@F@@@@             ,KLEN: INTEGER WORD      " NUMBER OF WORDS IN KFL
)@@G@@EY    @D@@@@             ,KPTR: MACHINE POINTER)  " TO KEY IN CORE@ @@@@FM
)@@G@@          EXPORTED ('TRESRC') @E@@@@          RESULT MACHINE POINTER " TFN
)@@G@@O SYMBOL TABLE ENTRY    @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          NODE := ROOT; " STARFO
)@@G@@T AT ROOT OF TREE @A@@@@          TSTK := 0; " NULL STACK   @C@@@@      FP
)@@G@@    TPTR(1) := ROOT; " PUT ROOT ON STACK  @A@@@@          WHILE NODE NE FQ
)@@G@@NULL\PTR DO @#@@@@           BEGIN  @G@@@@             FLAG := COMPARE\KFR
)@@G@@EYS(NODE,KTYP,KLEN,KPTR); " COMPARE KEYS  @C@@@@             IF (FLAG EQFS
)@@G@@ 0) THEN " THIS IS IT   @B@@@@                RETURN(NODE); " TO CALLER FT
)@@G@@@#@@@@             ELSE @B@@@@              BEGIN " TO GO DOWN IN TREE  FU
)@@G@@@D@@@@                VPUSH(FLAG,NODE); " PUSH ONTO STACK   @F@@@@      FV
)@@G@@          NODE := GETLINK(FLAG,NODE); " AND GET NEXT ONE    @#@@@@      FW
)@@G@@        END;@#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          RETURN(NODE) " TO USFX
)@@G@@ER    @^@@@@END; " SEARCH\FOR\NODE  @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THISFY
)@@G@@ PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO CREATE A NODE.  THE ARGUMENT PASSED @F@@@@" IS AFZ
)@@G@@ POINTER TO A DESCRIPTOR FOR THE NAME FOR THE NODE.  NOTE   @F@@@@" THATGA
)@@G@@ THE NODE CREATED IS NOT INSERTED INTO A TABLE AT THIS TIME.@[@@@@"     GB
)@@G@@@F@@@@PROCEDURE CREATE\NEW\NODE(SYMBOL: MACHINE POINTER) " TO SUBSCRIPT GC
)@@G@@@ @@@@          EXPORTED ('TRECRE') @C@@@@          RESULT MACHINE POINTGD
)@@G@@ER " TO NEW NODE  @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@DECLARE   NNODE: MACHINE POINTER; " GE
)@@G@@TO THE NODE WE WILL CREATE    @E@@@@DECLARE   LNAME: INTEGER WORD;    " GF
)@@G@@LENGTH OF NAME IN WORDS @D@@@@DECLARE   SNAME\PTR: MACHINE POINTER; " TOGG
)@@G@@ SYMBOL NAME@F@@@@DECLARE   SNAME(1): INTEGER WORD BASED(SNAME\PTR); " SGH
)@@G@@YMBOL NAME  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@          LNAME := DESC\DATA\LEN(SYMBOL); GI
)@@G@@" GET LENGTH IN WORDS   @B@@@@          IF (LNAME EQ 0) THEN ERROR;     GJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          NNODE := ALLOCATE\CORE(LNAME+STH\LEN); " ALLOCATE NODE  GK
)@@G@@@E@@@@          KLUGE := DADR(SYMBOL); " SET UP FOR REFERENCE     @B@@@@GL
)@@G@@          SNAME\PTR := LOC( SNAM(NNODE) );@A@@@@          FOR I := 1 TO GM
)@@G@@LNAME DO    @C@@@@             SNAME(I) := DNUM(I); " COPY NAME   @D@@@@GN
)@@G@@          STYP(NNODE) := DTYP(SYMBOL); " SET TYPE     @C@@@@          SLGO
)@@G@@EN(NNODE) := LNAME; " AND SET LENGTH@^@@@@          RETURN(NNODE);@^@@@@GP
)@@G@@END; " CREATE\NEW\NODE  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     GQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO INSERT A NODE IN A BINARY     @E@@@@GR
)@@G@@" TREE.  THE ARGUMENTS ARE THE ROOT OF THE TREE AND THE     @E@@@@" ADDRGS
)@@G@@ESS OF THE NEW NODE.  AS REBALANCING MAY CHANGE THE   @C@@@@" ROOT NODE,GT
)@@G@@ IT IS RETURNED AS A FUNCTION VALUE.@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" NOTE THAT THE SEGU
)@@G@@ARCH ROUTINE MUST BE CALLED BEFORE USING  @E@@@@" THIS ROUTINE AS IT USEGV
)@@G@@S DATA FROM THE TEMPORARY STACK.    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE INSERT\NGW
)@@G@@EW\NODE     @E@@@@             (ROOT: MACHINE POINTER   " TO ROOT OF TREGX
)@@G@@E     @F@@@@             ,NEWN : MACHINE POINTER) " TO NODE TO BE INSERTGY
)@@G@@ED    @ @@@@          EXPORTED ('TREINS') @D@@@@          RESULT MACHINEGZ
)@@G@@ POINTER " TO NEW ROOT OF TREE@[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          SLHA
)@@G@@LK(NEWN) := NULL\PTR;   @A@@@@          SRLK(NEWN) := NULL\PTR;   @ @@@@HB
)@@G@@          SBAL(NEWN) := 0;    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          IF ROOT EQ NULHC
)@@G@@L\PTR THEN " TREE IS NULL SO  @F@@@@             RETURN(NEWN);         "HD
)@@G@@ RETURN NEW ENTRY AS ROOT     @#@@@@          ELSE    @A@@@@           BHE
)@@G@@EGIN " TO INSERT TO TREE@C@@@@             IF (ROOT NE TPTR(1)) THEN ERRHF
)@@G@@OR;   @B@@@@             VPOP; " GET TOP STACK ENTRY  @E@@@@            HG
)@@G@@ IF GETLINK(FLAG,NODE) NE NULL\PTR THEN ERROR;  @E@@@@             SETLIHH
)@@G@@NK(FLAG,NODE,NEWN); " PUT IT INTO TREE    @E@@@@             WHILE (TSTKHI
)@@G@@ GT 0) AND (SBAL(NODE) EQ 0) DO     @C@@@@              BEGIN " TO UPDATHJ
)@@G@@E BALANCE FACTORS @A@@@@                SBAL(NODE) := FLAG; @A@@@@      HK
)@@G@@          VPOP; " MOVE UP ONE @C@@@@              END; " OF UPDATING BALHL
)@@G@@ANCE FACTORS@D@@@@             IF SBAL(NODE) NE FLAG THEN " UPDATE THIS HM
)@@G@@@D@@@@                SBAL(NODE) := SBAL(NODE)+FLAG; " NODE @C@@@@      HN
)@@G@@       ELSE " TREE MUST BE REBALANCED     @B@@@@              BEGIN " TOHO
)@@G@@ REBALANCE TREE   @ @@@@                BALANCE\TREE; @A@@@@            HP
)@@G@@    IF (TSTK EQ 0) THEN @D@@@@                   RETURN(NODE); " AS NEW HQ
)@@G@@ROOT OF TREE@^@@@@                ELSE    @G@@@@                   SETLIHR
)@@G@@NK(TFLG(TSTK),TPTR(TSTK),NODE); " CHANGE LINK   @A@@@@              END;HS
)@@G@@ " REBALANCE TREE @B@@@@           END; " OF NON-TRIVIAL INSERT   @C@@@@HT
)@@G@@          RETURN(ROOT); " NO CHANGE IN ROOT     @^@@@@END; " INSERT\NEW\HU
)@@G@@NODE  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @H@@@@" **********HV
)@@G@@  WARNING!  THIS ROUTINE NOT YET DEBUGGED!!! (BEN)  **********    @[@@@@HW
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO DELETE A NODE FROM A BINARY TRHX
)@@G@@EE.   @E@@@@" THE ARGUMENTS ARE THE ROOT OF THE TREE AND THE ADDRESS OF HY
)@@G@@@F@@@@" THE NODE TO BE DELETED.  AS REBALANCING MAY CHANGE THE ROOT     HZ
)@@G@@@C@@@@" NODE, IT IS RETURNED AS A FUNCTION VALUE.     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@IA
)@@G@@" NOTE THAT THE SEARCH ROUTINE MUST BE CALLED BEFORE USING THIS   @D@@@@IB
)@@G@@" ROUTINE AS IT USES DATA FROM THE TEMPORARY STACK.   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@IC
)@@G@@PROCEDURE DELETE\OLD\NODE     @D@@@@          (ROOT: MACHINE POINTER   "ID
)@@G@@ TO ROOT OF TREE  @E@@@@          ,OLDN: MACHINE POINTER)  " TO NODE TO IE
)@@G@@BE DELETED  @ @@@@          EXPORTED('TREDEL')  @D@@@@          RESULT MIF
)@@G@@ACHINE POINTER " TO NEW ROOT NODE   @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@DECLARE   OLDS: INIG
)@@G@@TEGER WORD; " STACK ENTRY POINTS TO OLDN  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@          IFIH
)@@G@@ (ROOT NE TPTR(1)) THEN ERROR;@B@@@@          IF (NODE NE OLDN) THEN ERRII
)@@G@@OR;   @C@@@@          IF (NODE EQ NULL\PTR) THEN ERROR;     @[@@@@"     IJ
)@@G@@@C@@@@" THERE ARE THREE CASES FOR DELETING A NODE.    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@IK
)@@G@@          OLDS := TSTK; " SAVE CURRENT STACK POSITION @B@@@@          IFIL
)@@G@@ SRLK(NODE) EQ NULL\PTR THEN  @A@@@@           BEGIN " RELEASE CASE 1   IM
)@@G@@@C@@@@             PDISPLAY('STREL1',NODE); " DUMP IT @E@@@@            IN
)@@G@@ NODE := SLLK(NODE); " RELEASE NODE FROM HERE   @A@@@@           END; " IO
)@@G@@RELEASE CASE 1    @#@@@@          ELSE    @C@@@@           BEGIN " TO FIIP
)@@G@@ND INORDER SUCCESSOR    @C@@@@             NODE := SRLK(NODE); " GO RIGHIQ
)@@G@@T     @C@@@@             IF SLLK(NODE) EQ NULL\PTR THEN     @A@@@@      IR
)@@G@@        BEGIN " TO DO IT HERE @D@@@@                PDISPLAY('STREL2',OLIS
)@@G@@DN); " DUMP IT    @F@@@@                SLLK(NODE) := SLLK(OLDN); " BRINIT
)@@G@@G UP RIGHT DESC   @C@@@@                IF SLLK(OLDN) NE NULL\PTR THEN  IU
)@@G@@@F@@@@                   SBAL(NODE) := SBAL(NODE) - 1; " UPDATE BAL FAC IV
)@@G@@@B@@@@              END; " OF DOING IT HERE     @#@@@@             ELSE IW
)@@G@@@D@@@@              BEGIN " TO SWAP WITH INORDER SUCCESSOR  @D@@@@      IX
)@@G@@          PDISPLAY('STREL3',OLDN); " DUMP IT    @D@@@@                VPIY
)@@G@@USH(1,NULL\PTR); " GO DOWN TO RIGHT @C@@@@                WHILE SLLK(NODIZ
)@@G@@E) NE NULL\PTR DO @D@@@@                 BEGIN " SEARCH FOR NULL LEFT POJA
)@@G@@INTER @C@@@@                   VPUSH(-1,NODE); " GO TO LEFT @D@@@@      JB
)@@G@@             NODE := SLLK(NODE); " AND LINK     @E@@@@                 EJC
)@@G@@ND; " OF SEARCH FOR NULL LEFT POINTER     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" NODE IS INJD
)@@G@@ORDER SUCCESSOR TO OLDN.@[@@@@"     @G@@@@                SLLK(TPTR(TSTKJE
)@@G@@)) := SRLK(NODE); " SET LINK TO RIGHT     @G@@@@                SLLK(NODJF
)@@G@@E) := SLLK(OLDN); " SWAP NODE AND OLDN IN TREE  @B@@@@                SRJG
)@@G@@LK(NODE) := SRLK(OLDN); @B@@@@                SBAL(NODE) := SBAL(OLDN); JH
)@@G@@@E@@@@                IF TPTR(OLDS+1) NE NULL\PTR THEN ERROR;     @F@@@@JI
)@@G@@                TPTR(OLDS+1) := NODE; " OVERLAY NULL PUSHED ABOVE @E@@@@JJ
)@@G@@              END; " OF SWAPPING WITH INORDER SUCCESSOR     @C@@@@      JK
)@@G@@     END; " OF FINDING INORDER SUCCESSOR  @ @@@@          IF (OLDS EQ 0)JL
)@@G@@ THEN @C@@@@             TPTR(1) := NODE; " SET NEW ROOT    @#@@@@      JM
)@@G@@    ELSE    @G@@@@             SETLINK(TFLG(OLDS),TPTR(OLDS),NODE); " REJN
)@@G@@LINK NODE IN TREE @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" NODE HAS BJO
)@@G@@EEN DELETED FROM TREE.  NOW GO BACK AND UPDATE THE    @ @@@@" INTERVENINJP
)@@G@@G BALANCE FACTORS.@[@@@@"     @E@@@@          WHILE (TSTK GT 0) DO " UPDJQ
)@@G@@ATE BALANCE FACTORS     @A@@@@           BEGIN " TO CHAIN UP TREE @A@@@@JR
)@@G@@             VPOP; " POP ONE LEVEL  @E@@@@             WHILE (TSTK GT 0)JS
)@@G@@ AND (SBAL(NODE) EQ 0) DO     @D@@@@              BEGIN " TO JUST UPDATEJT
)@@G@@ BALANCE FACTOR   @E@@@@                SBAL(NODE) := -FLAG; " DECREASE JU
)@@G@@BALANCE     @B@@@@                VPOP; " AND POP ONE LEVEL @D@@@@      JV
)@@G@@        END; " OF UPDATING ZERO BALANCE FACTORS @B@@@@             IF SBJW
)@@G@@AL(NODE) NE -FLAG THEN  @B@@@@              BEGIN " TO END BALANCE HERE JX
)@@G@@@F@@@@                SBAL(NODE) := SBAL(NODE) - FLAG; " SET NEW BALANCEJY
)@@G@@@D@@@@                TSTK := 0; " AND TERMINATE ROUTINE    @B@@@@      JZ
)@@G@@        END; " OF REBALANCE HERE    @#@@@@             ELSE @C@@@@      KA
)@@G@@        BEGIN " TO CALL TREE REBALANCER   @C@@@@                BALANCE\KB
)@@G@@TREE; " DO ROTATIONS    @A@@@@                IF (TSTK EQ 0) THEN @D@@@@KC
)@@G@@                   TPTR(1) := NODE; " SET NEW ROOT    @^@@@@            KD
)@@G@@    ELSE    @G@@@@                   SETLINK(TFLG(TSTK),TPTR(TSTK),NODE)KE
)@@G@@; " RELINK NODE   @E@@@@                IF (FLAG EQ 3) THEN " FUNNY SINGKF
)@@G@@LE ROTATION @D@@@@                   TSTK := 0; " TERMINATE REBALANCE   KG
)@@G@@@C@@@@              END; " OF CALLING TREE REBALANCER @D@@@@           EKH
)@@G@@ND; " OF LOOP UPDATING BALANCE FACTORS    @B@@@@          RETURN( TPTR(1KI
)@@G@@) ); " TO CALLER  @^@@@@END; " DELETE\OLD\NODE  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   KJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED BY THE TREE INSKK
)@@G@@ERTION AND DELETION     @F@@@@" ROUTINES TO REBALANCE THE TREE.  NODE ISKL
)@@G@@ PASSED AS THE NODE     @E@@@@" AT WHICH THE BALANCE FACTOR EXCEEDS ONE.KM
)@@G@@  NODE IS RETURNED@F@@@@" AS THE NEW ROOT OF THE SUBTREE, AND FLAG IS REKN
)@@G@@TURNED AS THE     @F@@@@" TYPE OF ROTATION PERFORMED, AS THE DELETE ROUTKO
)@@G@@INE MUST KNOW.    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE BALANCE\TREE  @[@@@@BEGIN KP
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@DECLARE   SUB1: MACHINE POINTER WORD;     @B@@@@DECLARKQ
)@@G@@E   SUB2: MACHINE POINTER WORD;     @E@@@@DECLARE   CASEKLUGE: INTEGER WKR
)@@G@@ORD; " KLUGE FOR PLUS BUG     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@"         PDISPLAY('BALAKS
)@@G@@NS',NODE);  @D@@@@          FLAG := SBAL(NODE); " HOW IS IT UNBALANCED  KT
)@@G@@@C@@@@          IF (FLAG EQ 0) THEN ERROR; " $$$DEBUG @F@@@@          SUKU
)@@G@@B1 := GETLINK(FLAG,NODE); " GET SUBTREE ON HEAVY SIDE @D@@@@          IFKV
)@@G@@ (SUB1 EQ NULL\PTR) THEN ERROR; " $$$DEBUG@F@@@@          CASEKLUGE := SKW
)@@G@@BAL(SUB1)*FLAG; " WHAT KIND OF ROTATION   @A@@@@          CASEENTRY CASEKX
)@@G@@KLUGE+1     @D@@@@          CASE 0: " SBAL(SUB1)=-A   (DOUBLE ROTATION) KY
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@"            PDISPLAY('DOUBLE',SUB1);     KZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@             SUB2 := GETLINK(-FLAG,SUB1); " GET OTHER SIDE  @B@@@@LA
)@@G@@"            PDISPLAY('DOUBL2',SUB2);     @E@@@@             IF (SUB2 EQLB
)@@G@@ NULL\PTR) THEN ERROR; " $$$DEBUG   @G@@@@             CASEKLUGE := SBALLC
)@@G@@(SUB2)*FLAG; " UPDATE BALANCE FACTORS     @B@@@@             IF (CASEKLULD
)@@G@@GE EQ -1) THEN    @A@@@@                SBAL(SUB1) := FLAG; @#@@@@      LE
)@@G@@       ELSE @A@@@@                SBAL(SUB1) := 0;    @B@@@@            LF
)@@G@@ IF (CASEKLUGE EQ 1) THEN     @A@@@@                SBAL(NODE) := -FLAG;LG
)@@G@@@#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@                SBAL(NODE) := 0;    @ @@@@LH
)@@G@@             SBAL(SUB2) := 0; @D@@@@             SETLINK(-FLAG,SUB1,GETLLI
)@@G@@INK(+FLAG,SUB2)); @D@@@@             SETLINK(+FLAG,NODE,GETLINK(-FLAG,SULJ
)@@G@@B2)); @B@@@@             SETLINK(+FLAG,SUB2,SUB1);    @B@@@@            LK
)@@G@@ SETLINK(-FLAG,SUB2,NODE);    @D@@@@             NODE := SUB2; " GET NEWLL
)@@G@@ SUBTREE ROOT     @B@@@@             FLAG := 2; " DOUBLE ROTATION @A@@@@LM
)@@G@@           END; " OF DOUBLE ROTATION@E@@@@          CASE 1: " SBAL(SUB2)LN
)@@G@@=0   (FUNNY SINGLE ROTATION)  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@            LO
)@@G@@ PDISPLAY('FUNNYS',SUB1);     @F@@@@             ERROR; " SHOULD NOT HAPLP
)@@G@@PEN TILL DELETE IS WRITTEN    @A@@@@             SBAL(NODE) := FLAG;    LQ
)@@G@@@A@@@@             SBAL(SUB1) := FLAG;    @D@@@@             SETLINK(+FLLR
)@@G@@AG,NODE,GETLINK(-FLAG,SUB1)); @B@@@@             SETLINK(-FLAG,SUB1,NODELS
)@@G@@);    @D@@@@             NODE := SUB1; " GET NEW SUBTREE ROOT     @B@@@@LT
)@@G@@             FLAG := 3; " FUNNY SINGLE    @B@@@@           END; " FUNNY LU
)@@G@@SINGLE ROTATION   @E@@@@          CASE 2: " SBAL(SUB1)=A   (NORMAL SINGLLV
)@@G@@E ROTATION) @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@"            PDISPLAY('SINGLE'LW
)@@G@@,SUB1);     @ @@@@             SBAL(NODE) := 0; @ @@@@             SBAL(LX
)@@G@@SUB1) := 0; @D@@@@             SETLINK(+FLAG,NODE,GETLINK(-FLAG,SUB1)); LY
)@@G@@@B@@@@             SETLINK(-FLAG,SUB1,NODE);    @B@@@@             NODE LZ
)@@G@@:= SUB1; " GET NEW ROOT @B@@@@             FLAG := 1; " SINGLE ROTATION MA
