)@@G@@PTR) := TYPSTR; " STRING INPUT@ @@@@END; " PERFORM\INPUT\FUNCTION @[@@@@AX
)@@G@@"     @H@@@@" CWIDTH$(S) - RETURNS TOTAL CHARACTER WIDTH OF CHARACTERS IAY
)@@G@@N STRING 'S'.     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\CWIDTH\FUNCTION   AZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@DECLARE   WIDTH: DISTANCE; " CHARACTER WIDTHS ACCUMULABA
)@@G@@TED HERE    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@          IF RTYP NE TYPSTR THEN " ERROR  BB
)@@G@@@F@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR11; " UNEXPECTED DATA TYPE     BC
)@@G@@@^@@@@          ELSE " ALL OK @#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@            BD
)@@G@@ WIDTH := 0; " ZERO WIDTH TO START  @F@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO RCTBE
)@@G@@R DO " LOOP OVER ALL CHARACTERS     @E@@@@                WIDTH := WIDTHBF
)@@G@@ + CHAR\WIDTH(RCHR(I)+1);     @C@@@@             PUT\WORD(WIDTH); " PUT BG
)@@G@@ON STACK    @F@@@@             DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPDST; " DISTANCE TYPE RBH
)@@G@@ETURNED     @A@@@@           END; " DATA TYPE CHECK   @ @@@@END; " PERFOBI
)@@G@@RM\CWIDTH\FUNCTION@[@@@@"     @H@@@@" CHAR$(I) - RETURNS CHARACTERS CORRBJ
)@@G@@ESPONDING TO THE INTEGERS IN VECTOR 'I'.  @H@@@@" IF ANY INTEGER IS GREABK
)@@G@@TER THAN 225 THE TRUNCATION CHARACTER IS RETURNED.    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@BL
)@@G@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\CHAR\FUNCTION     @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          IF RTYP BM
)@@G@@NE TYPINT THEN    @F@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR11; " UNEXPECBN
)@@G@@TED DATA TYPE     @^@@@@          ELSE " ALL OK @#@@@@           BEGIN  BO
)@@G@@@F@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO RCTR DO " LOOP OVER ALL NUMBERS INPUT  BP
)@@G@@@A@@@@                IF RNUM(I) GT 255 OR@D@@@@                   RNUM(BQ
)@@G@@I) LT 0 THEN " TRUNCATE IT    @D@@@@                   PUT\CHAR(TRUNCATEBR
)@@G@@D\CHARACTER);     @ @@@@                ELSE " OK     @B@@@@            BS
)@@G@@       PUT\CHAR(RNUM(I));     @D@@@@             DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPSTR;BT
)@@G@@ " STRING OUTPUT  @A@@@@           END; " DATA TYPE CHECK   @ @@@@END; "BU
)@@G@@ PERFORM\CHAR\FUNCTION  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" UC$(S) - RETURNS UPPER-CASE BV
)@@G@@OF CHARACTERS IN STRING 'S'.  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\UC\FUNBW
)@@G@@CTION @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          IF RTYP NE TYPSTR THEN " BAD NEWS     BX
)@@G@@@F@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR11; " UNEXPECTED DATA TYPE     BY
)@@G@@@^@@@@          ELSE " OK     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@            BZ
)@@G@@ DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPSTR; " STRING OUTPUT  @E@@@@             FOR I := 1 CA
)@@G@@TO RCTR DO " LOOP OVER ALL CHARS    @C@@@@                PUT\CHAR(XLFA(CB
)@@G@@XLAF(RCHR(I))));  @ @@@@           END; " CONVERSION  @ @@@@END; " PERFOCC
)@@G@@RM\UC\FUNCTION    @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" DEF$(S) - RETURNS 1 IF A DEFINED SCD
)@@G@@YMBOL BY THE NAME OF 'S' EXISTS.    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\CE
)@@G@@DEF\FUNCTION@[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   FOUND: MACHINE POINTER; " TO ENTCF
)@@G@@RY, IF FOUND@[@@@@"     @B@@@@          IF RTYP NE TYPSTR THEN " ERROR  CG
)@@G@@@F@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR11; " UNEXPECTED DATA TYPE     CH
)@@G@@@^@@@@          ELSE " OKAY   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@            CI
)@@G@@ DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPINT; " INTEGER OUTPUT @F@@@@             MONOCASE(LOCJ
)@@G@@C(RITE\ARG)); " CONVERT SYMBOL TO MONOCASE@H@@@@             FOUND := LOCK
)@@G@@OKUP\SYMBOL(MONOCASE\PTR); " TRY TO FIND THE SYMBOL   @D@@@@            CL
)@@G@@ IF (FOUND EQ NULL\PTR) THEN " NOT FOUND  @C@@@@                PUT\WORDCM
)@@G@@ (0); " GIVE HIM A ZERO @#@@@@             ELSE @D@@@@                PUCN
)@@G@@T\WORD(1); " FOUND, GIVE HIM A ONE  @A@@@@           END; " OF ELSE CLAUCO
)@@G@@SE    @ @@@@END; " PERFORM\DEF\FUNCTION   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" LTRIM$(S) CP
)@@G@@- TRIM LEADING SPACES FROM STRING 'S'.    @D@@@@" RTRIM$(S) - TRIM TRAILCQ
)@@G@@ING SPACES FROM STRING 'S'.   @F@@@@" TRIM$(S) - TRIM LEADING AND TRAILICR
)@@G@@NG SPACES FROM STRING 'S'.    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\TRIM\FCS
)@@G@@UNCTION     @D@@@@          (LEFT\TRIM: CONDITION " FLAG TRIM FROM LEFT CT
)@@G@@@E@@@@          ,RITE\TRIM: CONDITION) " FLAG TRIM FROM RIGHT     @[@@@@CU
)@@G@@BEGIN @ @@@@DEFINE    TRIM\CHAR = BLANK;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@DECLARE   COCV
)@@G@@PY\BEG: 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER; " BEGIN OF COPY@E@@@@DECLARE   COPY\ENDCW
)@@G@@: 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER; " END OF COPY  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          IFCX
)@@G@@ (RTYP NE TYPSTR) THEN  @F@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR11; " UCY
)@@G@@NEXPECTED DATA TYPE     @#@@@@          ELSE    @ @@@@           BEGIN "CZ
)@@G@@ TRIM STRING@B@@@@             COPY\BEG := 1; " START AT ONE@ @@@@      DA
)@@G@@       IF LEFT\TRIM THEN@H@@@@                WHILE (COPY\BEG LE RCTR) ADB
)@@G@@ND (RCHR(COPY\BEG) EQ TRIM\CHAR) DO @F@@@@                   COPY\BEG :=DC
)@@G@@ COPY\BEG + 1; " TRIM LEFT BLANKS   @C@@@@             COPY\END := RCTR;DD
)@@G@@ " START AT RIGHT @ @@@@             IF RITE\TRIM THEN@I@@@@            DE
)@@G@@    WHILE (COPY\END GE COPY\BEG) AND (RCHR(COPY\END) EQ TRIM\CHAR) DO   DF
)@@G@@@F@@@@                   COPY\END := COPY\END - 1; " TRIM RIGHT BLANKS  DG
)@@G@@@D@@@@             DTYP(OS\PTR) := TYPSTR; " STRING RESULT  @D@@@@      DH
)@@G@@       FOR COPY\IDX := COPY\BEG TO COPY\END DO  @B@@@@                PUDI
)@@G@@T\CHAR(RCHR(COPY\IDX)); @ @@@@           END; " TRIM STRING @ @@@@END; "DJ
)@@G@@ PERFORM\TRIM\FUNCTION  @[@@@@TERM; ___UT\"     @B@@@@          IF RTYP DK
)@@G@@NE TYPSTR THEN " ERROR  @F@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR11; " UDL
)@@G@@NEXPECTED DATA TYPE     *[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@DM
)@@G@@" THIS MODULE HANDLES PARENTHESIS IN DPS INTERNAL LANGUAGE. @[@@@@"     DN
)@@G@@@A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PDO
)@@G@@ROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('OPERATOR-DEF',IMPORTED); @B@@@@DP
)@@G@@          COPY ('SCAN-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('STAGINGDQ
)@@G@@-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@DR
)@@G@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('WARNINGDS
)@@G@@-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE PARSE\SUBSCRIPT     @G@@@@DT
)@@G@@             (VAR\DESC: MACHINE POINTER " TO VARIABLE TO BE SUBSCRIPTED DU
)@@G@@@F@@@@             ,SUB\DESC: MACHINE POINTER " TO SUBSCRIPT EXPRESSION DV
)@@G@@@A@@@@             ) IMPORTED ('PARSUB')  @D@@@@          RESULT INTEGERDW
)@@G@@ WORD; " SUBSCRIPT LIMITS     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\CHAR(C: INDX
)@@G@@TEGER WORD) IMPORTED ('PUTCHR');    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\WORDDY
)@@G@@(I: INTEGER WORD) IMPORTED ('PUTWRD');    @@@@@@@F@@@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\DZ
)@@G@@INTERNAL\FUNCTION(FUNCTION\INDEX: INTEGER WORD) @A@@@@          IMPORTEDEA
)@@G@@ ('INTERNALFUNC');@[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE NULL\OUT(SYMBOL: MACHINE WEB
)@@G@@ORD POINTER) IMPORTED ('NULOUT');   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMEC
)@@G@@PORTED;     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS CODE HANDLEED
)@@G@@S THE OPEN-PAREN OPERATOR.  IF THE LEFTARG IS A NULL  @F@@@@" THEN IT ISEE
)@@G@@ ARITHMETIC PARENS AND VALUE IS COPIED FROM RITEARG.  @C@@@@" IF LEFTARGEF
)@@G@@ IS TABLE IT IS ASSOCIATIVE FETCH.  @C@@@@" IF LEFTARG IS FUNCTION IT ISEG
)@@G@@ FUNCTION CALL.   @B@@@@" ALL OTHER LEFTARGS GET SYNTAX ERRORS.   @D@@@@EH
)@@G@@" NOTE ALSO THAT DTYP(SCANNED) IS CLEARED TO GET THE  @G@@@@" SCANNER PAEI
)@@G@@ST THE CLOSE PAREN WHICH OSTENSIBLY TERMINATED STACKING.    @[@@@@"     EJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@PROCEDURE OPAREN\OP EXPORTED  @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          IF DLEN(EK
)@@G@@SCANNED) NE OPRCPR THEN @B@@@@           BEGIN " MISSING RIGHT PAREN    EL
)@@G@@@B@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR16;    @B@@@@           END; " EM
)@@G@@MISSING RIGHT PAREN     @B@@@@          ELSE " SCAN PAST CLOSE PAREN    EN
)@@G@@@ @@@@           BEGIN " CONTINUE   @B@@@@             DTYP(SCANNED) := EO
)@@G@@TYPNUL;     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" ACTUALLY EXECUTE THE OPERATION SPECIFIEDEP
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@             CASEENTRY LTYP " DEPENDING ON LEFT EQ
)@@G@@ARG TYPE    @E@@@@             CASE TYPNUL:  " IF LEFTARG IS NULL JUST CER
)@@G@@OPY   @B@@@@              BEGIN " ARITHMETIC PARENS   @B@@@@            ES
)@@G@@    DTYP(OS\PTR) := RTYP;     @B@@@@                DSBT(OS\PTR) := RSBTET
)@@G@@;     @B@@@@                DLEN(OS\PTR) := RCTR;     @B@@@@            EU
)@@G@@    DADR(OS\PTR) := RPTR;     @B@@@@              END; " ARITHMETIC PAREEV
)@@G@@NS    @B@@@@             CASE TYPINT,TYPDST,TYPSTR:   @E@@@@            EW
)@@G@@    SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR11; " NOT ALLOWED     @ @@@@             CASE EX
)@@G@@TYPTAB:     @D@@@@                SUBSCRIPT\TABLE; " FETCH FROM TABLE   EY
)@@G@@@ @@@@             CASE TYPFUN:     @G@@@@                PERFORM\INTERNEZ
)@@G@@AL\FUNCTION(LCTR); " LCTR SELECTS FUNCTION@^@@@@             CASE *:    FA
)@@G@@@A@@@@              BEGIN " HANDLE ERROR  @B@@@@                DISPLAY(FB
)@@G@@'OPAREN',LTYP);   @^@@@@                ERROR;  @A@@@@              END;FC
)@@G@@ " HANDLE ERROR   @^@@@@             ENDCASE;   @ @@@@           END; " FD
)@@G@@CONTINUE    @^@@@@END; " OF OPAREN\OP     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS CODE FE
)@@G@@HANDLES THE OPEN BRACKET OPERATOR.  THE ONLY CURRENT USE    @A@@@@" FOR FF
)@@G@@THIS OPERATOR IS SUBSTRINGS.  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE OBRACK\OP EXPOFG
)@@G@@RTED  @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          IF DLEN(SCANNED) NE OPRCBR THEN @B@@@@FH
)@@G@@           BEGIN " MISSING RIGHT BRACKET  @B@@@@             SCANNER\ERRFI
)@@G@@OR := ERROR16;    @B@@@@           END; " MISSING RIGHT BRACKET   @B@@@@FJ
)@@G@@          ELSE " SCAN PAST CLOSE BRACKET  @ @@@@           BEGIN " CONTIFK
)@@G@@NUE   @B@@@@             DTYP(SCANNED) := TYPNUL;     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@FL
)@@G@@" ACTUALLY EXECUTE THE OPERATION SPECIFIED.     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@      FM
)@@G@@       CASEENTRY LTYP " DEPENDING ON LEFT ARG TYPE    @B@@@@            FN
)@@G@@ CASE TYPINT,TYPDST,TYPSTR:   @D@@@@                SUBSCRIPT\VALUE; " DFO
)@@G@@O SUBSCRIPTING    @B@@@@             CASE TYPNUL,TYPTAB,TYPFUN:   @B@@@@FP
)@@G@@                SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR11; @^@@@@             CASE *:    FQ
)@@G@@@A@@@@              BEGIN " HANDLE ERROR  @B@@@@                DISPLAY(FR
)@@G@@'OBRACK',LTYP);   @^@@@@                ERROR;  @A@@@@              END;FS
)@@G@@ " HANDLE ERROR   @^@@@@             ENDCASE;   @ @@@@           END; " FT
)@@G@@CONTINUE    @^@@@@END; " OF OBRACK\OP     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@FU
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO SUBSCRIPT A DATA VALUE. @[@@@@FV
)@@G@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE SUBSCRIPT\VALUE     @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@DECLARE   SUFW
)@@G@@BSCRIPT\FORM: INTEGER WORD    @F@@@@            ![BSUB: 18 BIT UNSIGNED FX
)@@G@@INTEGER " BEGIN SUBSCRIPT     @E@@@@             ,ESUB: 18 BIT UNSIGNED FY
)@@G@@INTEGER " END SUBSCRIPT @#@@@@             ];   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@      FZ
)@@G@@    IF RTYP NE TYPINT THEN    @F@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR1GA
)@@G@@7; " ILLEGAL SUBSCRIPT TYPE   @#@@@@          ELSE    @C@@@@            GB
)@@G@@ SUBSCRIPT\FORM := PARSE\SUBSCRIPT  @D@@@@                ( LOC(LEFT\ARGGC
)@@G@@) , LOC(RITE\ARG) );    @B@@@@          IF (ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0) THENGD
)@@G@@@ @@@@           BEGIN " GET DATA   @C@@@@             CASEENTRY LTYP " GE
)@@G@@WHAT TYPE IS IT   @A@@@@             CASE TYPINT,TYPDST:    @B@@@@      GF
)@@G@@          FOR I := BSUB TO ESUB DO  @F@@@@                   PUT\WORD( LGG
)@@G@@NUM(I) ); " PUT WORD INTO STACK     @ @@@@             CASE TYPSTR:     GH
)@@G@@@B@@@@                FOR I := BSUB TO ESUB DO  @F@@@@                  GI
)@@G@@ PUT\CHAR( LCHR(I) ); " PUT CHARACTER INTO STACK@^@@@@             CASE GJ
)@@G@@*:    @^@@@@                ERROR;  @^@@@@             ENDCASE;   @ @@@@GK
)@@G@@           END; " GET DATA    @C@@@@          DTYP(OS\PTR) := LTYP; " COGL
)@@G@@PY LEFT TYPE@D@@@@          DSBT(OS\PTR) := LSBT; " COPY LEFT SUBTYPE   GM
)@@G@@@ @@@@END; " OF SUBSCRIPT\VALUE     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IGN
)@@G@@S CALLED TO EXTRACT A VALUE FROM A TABLE  @B@@@@" REFERENCE USING THE SUGO
)@@G@@BSCRIPT SPECIFIED.@[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE SUBSCRIPT\TABLE     @[@@@@GP
)@@G@@BEGIN @C@@@@          CASEENTRY RTYP " FIND SUBSCRIPT TYPE  @^@@@@      GQ
)@@G@@    CASE TYPNUL:  @ @@@@             RPTR := NULL\PTR;@ @@@@          CAGR
)@@G@@SE TYPINT,TYPDST: @G@@@@             RPTR := SEARCH\FOR\NODE(LPTR,RTYP,RGS
)@@G@@CTR,RPTR); " SEARCH IT  @^@@@@          CASE TYPSTR:  @F@@@@            GT
)@@G@@ RPTR := SEARCH\FOR\NODE(LPTR,RTYP,(RCTR+3)//4,RPTR); @#@@@@          CAGU
)@@G@@SE *: @A@@@@           BEGIN " TO FLAG AN ERROR @B@@@@             SCANNGV
)@@G@@ER\ERROR := ERROR11;    @ @@@@             RPTR := NULL\PTR;@#@@@@      GW
)@@G@@     END;   @#@@@@          ENDCASE;@C@@@@          IF RPTR EQ NULL\PTR GX
)@@G@@THEN " NO ENTRY   @C@@@@             NULL\OUT(OS\PTR); " RETURN NULL    GY
)@@G@@@#@@@@          ELSE    @A@@@@           BEGIN " TO RETURN VALUE  @B@@@@GZ
)@@G@@             DTYP(OS\PTR) := DTYP(RPTR);  @B@@@@             DSBT(OS\PTRHA
)@@G@@) := DSBT(RPTR);  @B@@@@             DLEN(OS\PTR) := DLEN(RPTR);  @B@@@@HB
)@@G@@             DADR(OS\PTR) := DADR(RPTR);  @A@@@@           END; " OF RETHC
)@@G@@URNING VALUE@ @@@@END; " OF SUBSCRIPT\TABLE     @[@@@@TERM; ___T D      HD
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS MODULE IS CALLED HE
)@@G@@TO DO VERTICAL SPACING OR LEADING.  @E@@@@" IT DOES THE LEADING BY CRAMMHF
)@@G@@ING THE FUNCTION INTO LEAD\POS@F@@@@" IF THERE ARE NO CHARACTERS IN LINEHG
)@@G@@ OR INSERTING THE FUNCTION    @E@@@@" INTO A WORD OTHERWISE.  IT ALSO SUHH
)@@G@@PPRESSES LEADING AT THE @C@@@@" TOP OF THE PAGE UNLESS IT IS UNCONDITIONHI
)@@G@@AL.   @F@@@@" THE TESTS FOR ENOUGH ROOM ON THE PAGE MUST BE DONE BEFORE HJ
)@@G@@THIS  @^@@@@" ROUTINE IS CALLED.    @F@@@@" IT DOES THE LEADING REGARDLEHK
)@@G@@SS OF THE SPACE REMAINING !!!!!!!   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DHL
)@@G@@EFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-PROC',IMPORTED); @B@@@@HM
)@@G@@          COPY ('GETPUT-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('GETPUT-HN
)@@G@@PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@HO
)@@G@@          COPY ('SKIP-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('STAGINGHP
)@@G@@-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-COMMON',IMPORTED);  @@@@@@HQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\LEADING (LEAD: DISTANCE, FUNC: 9 BIT UNSIGNED INHR
)@@G@@TEGER)@ @@@@           EXPORTED ('PERLED')@[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@DECLARE   ROHS
)@@G@@UNDED\LEADING: DISTANCE;@@@@@@@G@@@@          IF LEAD GT 0 THEN         HT
)@@G@@  " NO NEGATIVE LEADING FOR NOW     @E@@@@           BEGIN              HU
)@@G@@        " NON-ZERO LEADING    @D@@@@             ROUNDED\LEADING := ROUNHV
)@@G@@D\HEIGHT(LEAD);   @B@@@@             IF FUNC EQ FUNC\LEADU OR     @A@@@@HW
)@@G@@                CHARS\IN\LINE OR    @A@@@@                NOT PAGE\EMPTYHX
)@@G@@ THEN @^@@@@              BEGIN     @D@@@@                IF LINE\EMPTY HY
)@@G@@AND WORD\INDEX EQ 0 THEN@^@@@@                 BEGIN  @H@@@@            HZ
)@@G@@       LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(LEAD\POS) := ROUNDED\LEADING; " CRAM IT    @D@@@@IA
)@@G@@                   LINE\BUFFER(LEAD\POS) := FUNC;     @^@@@@            IB
)@@G@@     END;   @^@@@@                ELSE    @F@@@@                   PUT\FIC
)@@G@@UNCTION\INTO\WORD(FUNC,ROUNDED\LEADING);  @B@@@@                IF FUNC ID
)@@G@@EQ FUNC\LEADU OR  @E@@@@                   AREA\VPOS GT 0 THEN " NOT AT IE
)@@G@@TOP OF PAGE @D@@@@                   UPDATE\AREA\VPOS(ROUNDED\LEADING); IF
)@@G@@@D@@@@                UPDATE\AREA\REL\VPOS(ROUNDED\LEADING);@#@@@@      IG
)@@G@@        END;@A@@@@           END; " ZERO LEADING CHECK@ @@@@END; " OF PEIH
)@@G@@RFORM\LEADING     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE TAKES CARE OF SKIP,II
)@@G@@I.    @[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE INSERT\LEADING (LEAD: DISTANCE, FUNC: IJ
)@@G@@9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER) @ @@@@           EXPORTED ('INSLED')@[@@@@BEGIN IK
)@@G@@@A@@@@DECLARE   ROUNDED\LEADING: DISTANCE;@@@@@@@G@@@@          IF LEAD IL
)@@G@@GT 0 THEN           " NO NEGATIVE LEADING FOR NOW     @E@@@@           BIM
)@@G@@EGIN                      " NON-ZERO LEADING    @D@@@@             ROUNDIN
)@@G@@ED\LEADING := ROUND\HEIGHT(LEAD);   @B@@@@             IF FUNC EQ FUNC\LIO
)@@G@@EADU OR     @A@@@@                CHARS\IN\LINE OR    @A@@@@            IP
)@@G@@    NOT PAGE\EMPTY THEN @^@@@@              BEGIN     @G@@@@            IQ
)@@G@@    LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(LEAD\POS) := LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(LEAD\POS)  @F@@@@      IR
)@@G@@                                       + ROUNDED\LEADING;   @C@@@@      IS
)@@G@@          LINE\BUFFER(LEAD\POS) := FUNC;  @B@@@@                IF FUNC IT
)@@G@@EQ FUNC\LEADU OR  @E@@@@                   AREA\VPOS GT 0 THEN " NOT AT IU
)@@G@@TOP OF PAGE @D@@@@                   UPDATE\AREA\VPOS(ROUNDED\LEADING); IV
)@@G@@@D@@@@                UPDATE\AREA\REL\VPOS(ROUNDED\LEADING);@#@@@@      IW
)@@G@@        END;@A@@@@           END; " ZERO LEADING CHECK@^@@@@END; " OF INIX
)@@G@@SERT\LEADING@[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___^<G/!@[PH*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULEIY
)@@G@@;     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS MODULE PROCESSES THE DICTIONARY ENTRIES FIZ

)@@G@@ IMPORTED); @C@@@@PROCEDURE READ\NEXT\CARD IMPORTED ('READ');     @D@@@@JI
)@@G@@PROCEDURE GET\NEXT\CHARACTER IMPORTED ('GETCHR');     @^@@@@DEFINE    SWJJ
)@@G@@\LEN = 8,   @^@@@@          SC\LEN = 32,  @^@@@@          VW\LEN = 3,   JK
)@@G@@@^@@@@          VC\LEN = 12;  @A@@@@DECLARE   INDEX: STATIC WORD INTEGERJL
)@@G@@@B@@@@          ,VINDEX: STATIC WORD INTEGER    @B@@@@          ,NULL\TAJM
)@@G@@BLE: STATIC CONDITION   @B@@@@          ,INSERTED: STATIC CONDITION     JN
)@@G@@@E@@@@          ,SYMBOL(SC\LEN): STATIC 9 BIT MACHINE LOGICAL     @E@@@@JO
)@@G@@          !SYMWRD(SW\LEN): LOCATABLE MACHINE WORD INTEGER   @E@@@@      JP
)@@G@@    ,VECTOR(VC\LEN): STATIC 9 BIT MACHINE LOGICAL     @C@@@@          !VJQ
)@@G@@ECWRD(VW\LEN): MACHINE WORD INTEGER @A@@@@          ,CHR: STATIC WORD INJR
)@@G@@TEGER @ @@@@          !VTR: WORD INTEGER  @B@@@@          ,SYM\LEN: STATJS
)@@G@@IC WORD INTEGER   @B@@@@          ,VEC\LEN: STATIC WORD INTEGER   @A@@@@JT
)@@G@@          ,ENDL: 4 ASCII CHARACTERS @C@@@@          !DCHAR(4): 9 BIT MACJU
)@@G@@HINE LOGICAL;     @A@@@@DECLARE   NODE: MACHINE POINTER     @G@@@@      JV
)@@G@@    ,TABP: STATIC LOCATABLE MACHINE POINTER IMPORTED ('TBLROOT'); @#@@@@JW
)@@G@@CONTROL (EJECT);  @[@@@@"     @]@@@@"   .LEXICON@C@@@@"   <LIST OF WORD JX
)@@G@@WITH DESIGNATED HYPHEN POINTS>@]@@@@"   .ENDL   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDJY
)@@G@@URE PROCESS\DICTIONARY\ENTRIES EXPORTED ('PRODICENT') @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@JZ
)@@G@@          NULL\TABLE:=TRUE;   @^@@@@          SET\INDEXES;  @]@@@@NEXT\CKA
)@@G@@ARD:  @ @@@@          READ\NEXT\CARD;     @ @@@@          IF END\OF\UNITKB
)@@G@@ THEN @^@@@@             RETURN;    @B@@@@          IF INPUT\CARD(1) EQ KC
)@@G@@PERIOD AND  @A@@@@             CARD\LENGTH GT 0 THEN  @#@@@@           BKD
)@@G@@EGIN  @ @@@@             FOR I:=1 TO 4 DO @^@@@@              BEGIN     KE
)@@G@@@B@@@@                DCHAR(I):=INPUT\CARD(I+1);@G@@@@                DCKF
)@@G@@HAR(I):=DCHAR(I) LAND O'137';  " TURN TO MONOCASE     @#@@@@            KG
)@@G@@  END;@A@@@@             IF ENDL EQ 'ENDL' THEN @^@@@@              BEGIKH
)@@G@@N     @A@@@@                IF NULL\TABLE AND   @B@@@@                  KI
)@@G@@ TABP NE NULL\PTR THEN  @D@@@@                   TABP:=RELEASE\SYMBOL\TAKJ
)@@G@@BLE(TABP);  @B@@@@                ERROR\STATUS\CODE:=0;     @^@@@@      KK
)@@G@@          RETURN; @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           END;   @]@@@@KL
)@@G@@NEXT\CHAR:  @ @@@@          GET\NEXT\CHARACTER; @B@@@@          IF NOT EKM
)@@G@@ND\OF\INPUT\CARD THEN   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             IF CHKN
)@@G@@ARACTER GE ASCII\LOWER\A AND  @C@@@@                CHARACTER LE ASCII\LKO
)@@G@@OWER\Z THEN @^@@@@              BEGIN     @A@@@@                INSERTEDKP
)@@G@@:=FALSE;    @A@@@@                INDEX:=INDEX+1;     @B@@@@            KQ
)@@G@@    SYMBOL(INDEX):=CHARACTER; @A@@@@                GOTO NEXT\CHAR;     KR
)@@G@@@#@@@@              END;@B@@@@             IF CHARACTER EQ MINUS THEN   KS
)@@G@@@^@@@@              BEGIN     @A@@@@                VINDEX:=VINDEX+1;   KT
)@@G@@@B@@@@                VECTOR(VINDEX):=INDEX;    @A@@@@                GOKU
)@@G@@TO NEXT\CHAR;     @#@@@@              END;@B@@@@             IF CHARACTEKV
)@@G@@R EQ COMMA OR     @B@@@@                CHARACTER EQ BLANK THEN   @^@@@@KW
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @A@@@@                IF NOT INSERTED THEN@^@@@@KX
)@@G@@                 BEGIN  @A@@@@                   INSERT\ENTRY;    @A@@@@KY
)@@G@@                   GOTO NEXT\CHAR;  @^@@@@                 END;   @^@@@@KZ
)@@G@@                ELSE    @C@@@@                   IF CHARACTER EQ BLANK TLA
)@@G@@HEN   @B@@@@                      GOTO NEXT\CHAR;     @#@@@@            LB
)@@G@@  END;@A@@@@             WARNING (W\BAD\ENTRY); @ @@@@             PRINTLC
)@@G@@\INPUT\CARD;@ @@@@             GOTO NEXT\CARD;  @#@@@@           END;   LD
)@@G@@@^@@@@          INSERT\ENTRY; @ @@@@          GOTO NEXT\CARD;     @[@@@@LE
)@@G@@END;  @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE SELF
)@@G@@T\INDEXES   @[@@@@ BEGIN@ @@@@          INSERTED:=TRUE;     @^@@@@      LG
)@@G@@    INDEX:=0;     @^@@@@          VINDEX:=1;    @A@@@@          FOR I:=1LH
)@@G@@ TO SW\LEN DO     @ @@@@             SYMWRD(I):=0;    @A@@@@          FOLI
)@@G@@R I:=1 TO VW\LEN DO     @ @@@@             VECWRD(I):=0;    @#@@@@      LJ
)@@G@@    RETURN; @[@@@@ END; @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE INSERT\ELK
)@@G@@NTRY  @[@@@@ BEGIN@ @@@@          NULL\TABLE:=FALSE;  @ @@@@          VELL
)@@G@@CTOR(1):=VINDEX;  @A@@@@          SYM\LEN:=(INDEX+3)//4;    @A@@@@      LM
)@@G@@    VEC\LEN:=(VINDEX+3)//4;   @C@@@@          NODE:=SEARCH\FOR\NODE(TABPLN
)@@G@@,TYPSTR,    @B@@@@                SYM\LEN,LOC(SYMWRD(1)));  @A@@@@      LO
)@@G@@    IF NODE EQ NULL\PTR THEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@            LP
)@@G@@ NODE:=ALLOCATE\CORE(STH\LEN+SYM\LEN);    @A@@@@             SLEN(NODE):LQ
)@@G@@=SYM\LEN;   @A@@@@             STYP(NODE):=TYPSTR;    @A@@@@            LR
)@@G@@ FOR I:=1 TO SYM\LEN DO @D@@@@                CORE(LOC(SNAM(NODE))+I-1):LS
)@@G@@=SYMWRD(I); @A@@@@             DLEN(NODE):=VEC\LEN;   @C@@@@            LT
)@@G@@ DADR(NODE):=ALLOCATE\CORE(VEC\LEN);@A@@@@             FOR I:=1 TO VEC\LLU
)@@G@@EN DO @C@@@@                CORE(DADR(NODE)+I-1):=VECWRD(I);@C@@@@      LV
)@@G@@       TABP:=INSERT\NEW\NODE(TABP,NODE);  @#@@@@           END;   @^@@@@LW
)@@G@@          SET\INDEXES;  @#@@@@          RETURN; @[@@@@ END; @[@@@@"     LX
)@@G@@@[@@@@TERM; ___@@@          COPY ('CORE-PROCS', IMPORTED);  @B@@@@      LY
)@@G@@    COPY ('CARD-DEF', IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('DIRECT-DEF', LZ
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);MA
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CMB
)@@G@@ORE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('FTNOTE-PROCS',IMPORTED); MC
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('GETPUT-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SMD
)@@G@@TAGING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-COMMON',IMPORTED);  ME
)@@G@@@@@@@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\OUT\HEADING IMPORTED ('PUTOUTHEDING');  @@@@@@MF
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" PROCEDURE SAVE\TOP\FUNCTION SAVES FUNCTION AND VALUEMG
)@@G@@ UNTIL TOP  @]@@@@" OF PAGE.  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE SAVE\TOP\FUNCTMH
)@@G@@ION(FUNCTION: WORD INTEGER,   @E@@@@             VALUE: WORD INTEGER) EXMI
)@@G@@PORTED ('SAVETOPFUNC')  @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          NUM\TOP\FUNCTIONS :=MJ
)@@G@@ NUM\TOP\FUNCTIONS+1;   @D@@@@          IF NUM\TOP\FUNCTIONS GT TOP\FUNCMK
)@@G@@\LEN THEN   @E@@@@             NUM\TOP\FUNCTIONS := TOP\FUNC\LEN;  " TRUML
)@@G@@NCATE @D@@@@          TOP\FUNCTION(NUM\TOP\FUNCTIONS) := FUNCTION;@C@@@@MM
)@@G@@          TOP\VALUE(NUM\TOP\FUNCTIONS) := VALUE;@ @@@@END; " OF SAVE\TOPMN
)@@G@@\FUNCTIONS  @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" PROCEDURE DO\TOP\FUNCTIONS PERFORMS FUNCMO
)@@G@@TIONS AT THE TOP OF PAGE.     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE DO\TOP\FUNCTIOMP
)@@G@@NS EXPORTED ('DOTOPFUNCS')    @[@@@@BEGIN @@@@@@@ @@@@DECLARE   VALUE: DMQ
)@@G@@ISTANCE     @A@@@@          !PTR: WORD MACHINE POINTER@ @@@@          ,FMR
)@@G@@UNC: WORD INTEGER;@A@@@@DECLARE   AREA\SAVE: MACHINE POINTER@B@@@@      MS
)@@G@@    ,NEXT\FOOTNOTE: MACHINE POINTER @C@@@@          ,FOOTNOTE\CONTROL\WOMT
)@@G@@RD: LOGICAL WORD  @C@@@@          !EXTENDED\FOOTNOTE: WORD CONDITION;   MU
)@@G@@@@@@@@@B@@@@          FOR I:=1 TO NUM\TOP\FUNCTIONS DO@#@@@@           BMV
)@@G@@EGIN  @E@@@@             AREA\SAVE := AREA\PTR;  " SAVE CURRENT AREA    MW
)@@G@@@E@@@@             AREA\PTR := LOC(TEXT\AREA);  " GET TEXT AREA   @B@@@@MX
)@@G@@             FUNC := TOP\FUNCTION(I);     @A@@@@             VALUE := TOMY
)@@G@@P\VALUE(I); @ @@@@             CASEENTRY FUNC   @B@@@@             CASE MZ
)@@G@@TOP\FUNC\AREA\HEIGHT:   @B@@@@                AREA\HEIGHT := VALUE;     NA
)@@G@@@C@@@@             CASE TOP\FUNC\AREA\VPOS\START:     @B@@@@            NB
)@@G@@    AREA\VPOS\START := VALUE; @A@@@@             CASE TOP\FUNC\FOOTNOTE:NC
)@@G@@@^@@@@              BEGIN     @F@@@@                IF PTR NE NULL\PTR TND
)@@G@@HEN  " WE HAVE A FOOTNOTE     @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @E@@@@      NE
)@@G@@             AREA\PTR := PTR;  " GO TO FOOTNOTE AREA  @H@@@@            NF
)@@G@@       NEXT\FOOTNOTE := NEXT\AREA\PTR  " GET EXTENDED FOOTNOTE    @^@@@@NG
)@@G@@                 END;   @E@@@@                AREA\PTR := LOC(TEXT\AREA)NH
)@@G@@;  " GET TEXT AREA@G@@@@                AREA\VPOS\START := TOP\MARGIN;  NI
)@@G@@" RESET START AND HEIGHT@G@@@@                AREA\HEIGHT := PAGE\HEIGHTNJ
)@@G@@-TOP\MARGIN-BOTTOM\MARGIN;    @D@@@@                RELEASE\CORE(PTR);  NK
)@@G@@" RELEASE FOOTNOTE@H@@@@                IF NEXT\FOOTNOTE EQ NULL\PTR THENL
)@@G@@N  " NO EXTENDED FOOTNOTE     @F@@@@                   FIXED\AREA\PTR :=NM
)@@G@@ LOC(FOOTING\AREA); " RE-LINK @^@@@@                ELSE    @^@@@@      NN
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @I@@@@                   FIXED\AREA\PTR := NEXT\FOOTNONO
)@@G@@TE;  " LINK NEXT FOOTNOTE TO TEXT   @G@@@@                   AREA\PTR :=NP
)@@G@@ FIXED\AREA\PTR;  " GO TO FOOTNOTE AREA   @G@@@@                   EXTENNQ
)@@G@@DED\FOOTNOTE := FALSE;  " CLEAR EXTENSION FLAG  @F@@@@                  NR
)@@G@@ AREA\CONTROL\WORD := FOOTNOTE\CONTROL\WORD;    @A@@@@                  NS
)@@G@@ PROCESS\ENDFOOT; @G@@@@                   PUT\OUT\HEADING; " THIS PUTS NT
)@@G@@OUT FOOTNOTE EVEN IF    @F@@@@                   PAGE\EMPTY := FALSE;  "NU
)@@G@@ THERE IS NO MORE TEXT  @^@@@@                 END;   @#@@@@            NV
)@@G@@  END;@^@@@@             ENDCASE;   @D@@@@             AREA\PTR := AREA\NW
)@@G@@SAVE;  " RESTORE AREA   @#@@@@           END;   @F@@@@          NUM\TOP\NX
)@@G@@FUNCTIONS := 0;  " CLEAR NUMBER OF FUNCTIONS    @ @@@@END; " OF DO\TOP\FNY
)@@G@@UNCTIONS    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___   NS    @ @@@@END; " OF DO\TOP\FNZ
)@@G@@UNCTIONS    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___   @[D^+EINPUT FILE IS EMPTY     OA
)@@G@@@[^^+OINPUT FILE IS ON NON MASS STORAGE EQUIPMEN*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULEOB
)@@G@@;     @F@@@@" THIS MODULE IS RESPONSIBLE FOR INTERPRETING THE SIMPLEST FOC
)@@G@@ORM   @F@@@@" OF DOCUMENT, CHAPTER, AND SECTION IDENTIFICATION AND NUMBEOD
)@@G@@RING. @F@@@@" MORE COMPLICATED FORMS OF HEADINGS MAY BE DONE THROUGH MACOE
)@@G@@ROS.  @A@@@@" THE FOLLOWING FORMS ARE ALLOWED:  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@"   .0OF
)@@G@@[,P/R/C/O/N/F] '<ID>'   @G@@@@"             DOCUMENT HEADING SAVED FOR TOG
)@@G@@HE NEXT CALL TO GET\NEXT\PAGE @[@@@@"     @#@@@@"   .<N> '<TEXT>' @G@@@@OH
)@@G@@"             CHAPTER AND SECTION IDENTIFICATION IN DECENDING ORDER.    OI
)@@G@@@F@@@@"             THESE ARE OUTPUT IMMEDIATELY.  N RANGES FROM 1 TO 9.OJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @@@@@@@A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@      OK
)@@G@@    COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',OL
)@@G@@IMPORTED);  @G@@@@          COPY ('DIRECT-PROCS',IMPORTED); " GET PROCESOM
)@@G@@S\SECTION\BREAK   @B@@@@          COPY ('GETPUT-PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@ON
)@@G@@          COPY ('GETPUT-DEF', IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('DIRECT-OO
)@@G@@DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@OP

)@@G@@OCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SKIP-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@OR

)@@G@@DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@OT
)@@G@@          COPY ('TITLE-DEF',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-COOU
)@@G@@MMON',IMPORTED);  @@@@@@@@@@@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE MAKE\TOC\ENTRY(TOC\LEVEL: OV
)@@G@@WORD INTEGER) IMPORTED  @^@@@@           ('MAKTOC');  @@@@@@@G@@@@PROCEDOW
)@@G@@URE FORCE\END\OF\PARAGRAPH IMPORTED ('FOREOL'); " END-OF-LINE     @@@@@@OX
)@@G@@@F@@@@PROCEDURE FORCE\END\OF\PAGE IMPORTED ('FOREOP'); " END-OF-PAGE    OY
)@@G@@@@@@@@@F@@@@PROCEDURE FORCE\END\OF\COLUMN IMPORTED ('FOREOC'); " END-OF-OZ
)@@G@@PAGE  @@@@@@@I@@@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\LEADING (LED: DISTANCE, FUNC: 9 BIT PA
)@@G@@UNSIGNED INTEGER) IMPORTED    @^@@@@           ('PERLED'); "@@@@@@@#@@@@PB
)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\SECTIONING\DIRECTIPC
)@@G@@VE(TOC\LEVEL: INTEGER WORD)   @ @@@@          EXPORTED ('TOCLVN') @[@@@@PD
)@@G@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" BEGIN EXECUTABLE CODE @[@@@@"     @ @@@@      PE
)@@G@@    OUTPUT\NEXT\WORD;   @G@@@@          FORCE\END\OF\PARAGRAPH;         PF
)@@G@@ " FLUSH OUT PARTIAL TEXT LINE@A@@@@          IF TOC\LEVEL EQ 1 THEN    PG
)@@G@@@H@@@@             FORCE\END\OF\PAGE; " GET NEW PAGE BEFORE WE CHANGE CHPH
)@@G@@APTER NUMBER@G@@@@          PROCESS\SECTION\BREAK(TOC\LEVEL); " DO UNIT PI
)@@G@@BREAK IF REQUIRED @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" NOTE: CODE TO UPDATE CHAPTER NUMBEPJ
)@@G@@RS IS NOW IN PROCESS\SECTION\BREAK  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          IF TOC\LPK
)@@G@@EVEL EQ 1 THEN    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" WE RESET PPL
)@@G@@AGE NUMBER TO ONE IF WE ARE PRINTING@B@@@@" CHAP-PAGE  OR IF WE HAVE CHAPM
)@@G@@PTER ONE.   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@             IF EDIT\CHAP\NUMBER THEN     PN
)@@G@@@A@@@@                PAGE\NUMBER := 1;   @A@@@@             IF ODD\PAGEPO
)@@G@@\FACING AND @I@@@@                (MOD(PAGE\NUMBER,2) EQ 0) THEN " CHAPTPP
)@@G@@ERS ALWAYS HAVE ODD PAGES     @C@@@@                PAGE\NUMBER := PAGE\PQ
)@@G@@NUMBER + 1; @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          SCAN(EVAL+CTRM+ALLOWPR
)@@G@@\STR);@A@@@@          IF CSDTYP EQ TYPSTR THEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  PS
)@@G@@@F@@@@             INITIALIZE\LINE\ASSEMBLY; " THIS STARTS NEW LINE     PT
)@@G@@@E@@@@             INITIALIZE\NEXT\WORD\ASSEMBLY; " START NEW WORD@E@@@@PU
)@@G@@             IF CAN\SKIP(SECTION\LEADING\AFTER(TOC\LEVEL)+  @D@@@@      PV
)@@G@@          SECTION\LEADING\BEFORE(TOC\LEVEL) +   @A@@@@                2 PW
)@@G@@* LEADING) THEN   @H@@@@                PERFORM\LEADING(SECTION\LEADING\PX
)@@G@@BEFORE(TOC\LEVEL),FUNC\LEAD); @A@@@@             ELSE " NEED NEW PAGE   PY
)@@G@@@D@@@@                FORCE\END\OF\COLUMN; " GET NEW COLUMN @B@@@@      PZ
)@@G@@       FOR I := 1 TO TOC\LEVEL DO   @^@@@@              BEGIN     @F@@@@QA
)@@G@@                CONVERT\AND\INSERT\NUMBER(CHAPTER\NUMBER(I));     @D@@@@QB
)@@G@@                PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD(PERIOD); @#@@@@            QC
)@@G@@  END;@H@@@@             PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD(BLANK);  " ADD BLAQD
)@@G@@NK AFTER PERIOD   @H@@@@             PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD(BLANK)QE
)@@G@@;  " ADD BLANK AFTER PERIOD   @A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO CSDLEN DOQF
)@@G@@@E@@@@                PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD( DCHR(I) );    @A@@@@QG
)@@G@@             INHIBIT\INDENT := TRUE;@E@@@@             OUTPUT\NEXT\WORD;QH
)@@G@@ " OUTPUT ACCULUMATED LINE    @A@@@@             FORCE\END\OF\PARAGRAPH;QI
)@@G@@@E@@@@             MAKE\TOC\ENTRY(TOC\LEVEL); " ENTER INTO TOC    @H@@@@QJ
)@@G@@             PERFORM\LEADING(SECTION\LEADING\AFTER(TOC\LEVEL),FUNC\LEAD)QK
)@@G@@;     @A@@@@             FORCE\END\OF\PARAGRAPH;@#@@@@           END;   QL
)@@G@@@#@@@@          ELSE    @E@@@@             TITLE\ERROR;             " PRQM
)@@G@@INT ERROR MESSAGE @B@@@@END; " OF PROCESS\SECTIONING\DIRECTIVE    @D@@@@QN
)@@G@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\TITLE\DIRECTIVE EXPORTED ('TOCLV0') @[@@@@BEGIN @H@@@@QO
)@@G@@          DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\H) :=       " ASSUME H IF NO F OR N OPTIONQP
)@@G@@S     @G@@@@             NOT (DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\F) OR DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASQQ
)@@G@@CII\N));    @D@@@@          IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\H) THEN " HEADING    QR
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             CENTER\HEADING := DIRECTIVE\OQS
)@@G@@PT(ASCII\C);@#@@@@           END;   @^@@@@          ELSE " FOOTING@#@@@@QT
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             CENTER\FOOTING := DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCQU
)@@G@@II\C);@#@@@@           END;   @D@@@@          ODD\PAGE\FACING := DIRECTIQV
)@@G@@VE\OPT(ASCII\O); "@I@@@@          EDIT\CHAP\NUMBER := NOT DIRECTIVE\OPT(QW
)@@G@@ASCII\P); " NO CHAPTERS IF P GIV    @B@@@@          IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCQX
)@@G@@II\B) THEN "@C@@@@             NUMBER\BOTTOM\OF\PAGE := TRUE;     @E@@@@QY
)@@G@@          IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\R) THEN " RESET AND NUMBER @#@@@@      QZ
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @D@@@@             PAGE\NUMBER := 0; " RESET PAGE NUMBER    RA
)@@G@@@E@@@@             START\PAGE\NUMBERING := TRUE; " BEGIN EDITING  @#@@@@RB
)@@G@@           END;   @E@@@@          IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\N) THEN " TURN RC
)@@G@@OFF SETTINGS@#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             PROCESS\SECTION\BRD
)@@G@@REAK(0); " RESET SECTIONING   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" NOTE: CODE TO UPDATE CRE
)@@G@@HAPTER NUMBER IS NOW IN PROCESS\SECTION\BREAK   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@      RF
)@@G@@       EDIT\CHAP\NUMBER := TRUE;    @F@@@@             START\PAGE\NUMBERRG
)@@G@@ING := FALSE; " NO NUMBERING YET    @F@@@@             NUMBER\BOTTOM\OF\RH
)@@G@@PAGE := FALSE; " NUMBER TOP OF PAGE @F@@@@             HEADING\LENGTH :=RI
)@@G@@ 0; " CLEAR ANY PREVIOUS HEADING    @F@@@@             FOOTING\LENGTH :=RJ
)@@G@@ 0; " CLEAR ANY PREVIOUS FOOTING    @B@@@@             HEADING\REQUESTEDRK
)@@G@@ := FALSE;  @B@@@@             FOOTING\REQUESTED := FALSE;  @#@@@@      RL
)@@G@@     END;   @C@@@@          SCAN(EVAL+CTRM+ALLOW\STR+CNUM+CSTR);  @D@@@@RM
)@@G@@          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN " CONTINUE   @F@@@@            RN
)@@G@@ IF CSDTYP NE TYPNUL THEN " ONLY IF SOMETHING FOUND   @^@@@@            RO
)@@G@@  BEGIN     @C@@@@                IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\H) THEN  @^@@@@RP
)@@G@@                 BEGIN  @C@@@@                   HEADING\REQUESTED := TRRQ
)@@G@@UE;   @C@@@@                   HEADING\LENGTH := CSDLEN;    @E@@@@      RR
)@@G@@             FOR I := 1 TO CSDLEN DO " MOVE HEADING   @C@@@@            RS
)@@G@@          HEADING(I) := DCHR(I);    @^@@@@                 END;   @C@@@@RT
)@@G@@                IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\F) THEN  @^@@@@                 BRU
)@@G@@EGIN  @C@@@@                   FOOTING\REQUESTED := TRUE;   @C@@@@      RV
)@@G@@             FOOTING\LENGTH := CSDLEN;    @E@@@@                   FOR IRW
)@@G@@ := 1 TO CSDLEN DO " MOVE HEADING   @C@@@@                      FOOTING(RX
)@@G@@I) := DCHR(I);    @^@@@@                 END;   @#@@@@              END;RY
)@@G@@@ @@@@          ELSE " ERROR FOUND  @ @@@@             TITLE\ERROR;     RZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE TITLE\ERROR   @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@SA
)@@G@@          WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\TITLING);     @ @@@@          PRINT\INPUT\CASB
)@@G@@RD;   @[@@@@END;  @@@@@@@[@@@@TERM; ___AGE      *[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULESC
)@@G@@;     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS MODULE IS CALLED BY ANYONE WHO WISHES TO SD
)@@G@@READ INPUT SCRIPT @E@@@@" IT READS FROM THE CURRENT INPUT PACKET.   IF TSE
)@@G@@HE USER DOES@F@@@@" AN .INCLUDE DIRECTIVE THEN THE INPUT PACKET WILL BE SF
)@@G@@PUSHED AND  @F@@@@" A .INCLUDE DIRECTIVE, THE INPUT PACKET WILL HAVE BEESG
)@@G@@N PUSHED    @D@@@@" AND A NEW ONE CHAINED IN AS THE CURRENT PACKET.     SH
)@@G@@@E@@@@" WHEN AN END OF FILE OCCURS THIS ROUTINE IS RESPONSIBLE FOR@A@@@@SI
)@@G@@" POPPING UP TO THE PREVIOUS PACKET.@[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DSJ
)@@G@@EFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('STAT-DEF',IMPORTED);     @D@@@@SK
)@@G@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED); " ***DEBUG   @B@@@@          COSL
)@@G@@PY ('FILE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('CORE-PROCS',IMPORTESM
)@@G@@D);   @E@@@@          COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED); " GET I/O CARD DEFS   SN
)@@G@@@G@@@@          COPY ('DIRECT-PROCS',IMPORTED); " GET UPDATE\NEW\UNIT\ENSO
)@@G@@TRY   @B@@@@          COPY ('MACRO-DEF',IMPORTED);    @D@@@@          COSP
)@@G@@PY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED); " GET FORMATTING@B@@@@          COPY ('PIO-PROSQ
)@@G@@CS',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('PRINT-DEF',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@SR
)@@G@@          COPY ('PUSH-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @E@@@@          COPY ('RUN-DATSS
)@@G@@A-DEF',IMPORTED); " FOR OPTIONS     @B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-DEF',IMPST
)@@G@@ORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('PACKET-DEF',IMPORTED);   @A@@@@      SU
)@@G@@    COPY ('IO-DEF1',IMPORTED);@[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTEDSV
)@@G@@;     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" ROUTINE TOSW
)@@G@@ READ THE NEXT CARD FROM THE INPUT FILE   @B@@@@" NOTE ALL IMAGES ARE ASSX
)@@G@@SUMED TO BE ASCII @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE READ\NEXT\CARD EXPORTED ('SY
)@@G@@READ')@[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@DECLARE   READ\FLAG: WORD CONDITION; " FLAG TO RSZ
)@@G@@EAD IMAGE   @C@@@@DECLARE   NEW\CARD\LEN: WORD INTEGER LOCATABLE; @[@@@@TA
)@@G@@"     @B@@@@" POP ANY ICBS THAT ARE STILL PUSHED.     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@TB
)@@G@@          POP\PUSHED\ICBS; " POP ANY LEFTOVER CARDS   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@TC
)@@G@@" SET FLAG TO CAUSE IMAGE READ@[@@@@"     @ @@@@          READ\FLAG := TTD
)@@G@@RUE;  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" LOOP READING CARDS WHILE READ\FLAG IS TRUE.   TE
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@          WHILE READ\FLAG DO  @ @@@@           BEGIN "TF
)@@G@@ READ IMAGE @C@@@@"            DISPLAY('PKTTYP',PACKET\TYPE(CIP));@[@@@@TG
)@@G@@"     @B@@@@" IF VALID IMAGE AND FORMATTING OUTPUT IT.@[@@@@"     @C@@@@TH
)@@G@@"            DISPLAY('VALIDI',VALID\IMAGE);     @G@@@@             IF PATI
)@@G@@CKET\TYPE(CIP) EQ PKT\NORMAL AND VALID\IMAGE THEN     @A@@@@            TJ
)@@G@@    STASH\THIS\CARD;    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" ACTUALLY READ IMAGE   @[@@@@TK
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@             READ\FILE(CIP,%NEW\CARD\LEN); " READ NEXT CARD TL
)@@G@@@C@@@@             READ\FLAG := FALSE; " SET NO REREAD@[@@@@"     @C@@@@TM
)@@G@@" HANDLE INPUT ACCORDING TO WHERE IT'S FROM     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@      TN
)@@G@@       CASEENTRY PACKET\TYPE(CIP)   @B@@@@             CASE PKT\MACRO, PTO
)@@G@@KT\IMACRO:  @^@@@@              BEGIN     @D@@@@                MACRO\XFTP
)@@G@@ER\PTR := MACRO\TEMP\PTR;     @D@@@@                MACRO\LINE\NUM := MATQ
)@@G@@CRO\TEMP\NUM;     @E@@@@                CARD\SEQ\NUMBER(CIP) := MACRO\TETR
)@@G@@MP\NUM;     @D@@@@                NEW\CARD\LEN := NEW\CARD\LEN - 8;     TS
)@@G@@@D@@@@"               ODISPLAY('XF-PTR',MACRO\XFER\PTR);    @D@@@@"     TT
)@@G@@          ODISPLAY('LN-NUM',MACRO\LINE\NUM);    @#@@@@              END;TU
)@@G@@@D@@@@             CASE *: " EVERYTHING EXCEPT MACRO INPUT  @^@@@@      TV
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @A@@@@                MACRO\XFER\PTR := 0;@A@@@@      TW
)@@G@@          MACRO\LINE\NUM := 0;@#@@@@              END;@^@@@@            TX
)@@G@@ ENDCASE;   @A@@@@             MACRO\TEMP\PTR := 0;   @A@@@@            TY
)@@G@@ MACRO\TEMP\NUM := 0;   @F@@@@             CARD\LENGTH := NEW\CARD\LEN; TZ
)@@G@@" XFER TO CARD\LENGTH   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" CHECK FOR END-OF-FILE AND POUA
)@@G@@P IF NECESSARY.   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@             IF END\FILE(CIP) THEN  UB
)@@G@@@A@@@@              BEGIN " END OF FILE   @F@@@@                CASEENTRUC
)@@G@@Y PACKET\TYPE(CIP) " WHAT KIND OF PACKET  @A@@@@                CASE PKTUD
)@@G@@\NORMAL:    @F@@@@                   IF (IO\PACKET\BACK\LINK(CIP) NE NULUE
)@@G@@L\PTR) THEN @D@@@@                      ERROR; " SHOULD BE FIRST PACKET UF
)@@G@@@^@@@@                   ELSE @C@@@@                    BEGIN " EOF ON NUG
)@@G@@ORMAL PACKET@F@@@@                      END\OF\UNIT := TRUE; " SET END OUH
)@@G@@F UNIT FLAG @F@@@@                      END\OF\INPUT\CARD := TRUE; " ANDUI
)@@G@@ END OF CARD@D@@@@                      CARD\LENGTH := 0; " CLEAR LENGTHUJ
)@@G@@@C@@@@                    END; " EOF ON NORMAL PACKET @C@@@@            UK
)@@G@@    CASE PKT\INCLUDE,PKT\MACRO:     @C@@@@                 BEGIN " EOF OUL
)@@G@@N PUSHED PACKET   @F@@@@                   IF (IO\PACKET\BACK\LINK(CIP) UM
)@@G@@EQ NULL\PTR) THEN @E@@@@                      ERROR; " SHOULDNT BE FIRSTUN
)@@G@@ IN CHAIN   @E@@@@                   END\OF\INPUT\CARD := TRUE; " END OFUO
)@@G@@ CARD @D@@@@                   CARD\LENGTH := 0; " CREAM CARD     @D@@@@UP
)@@G@@                   POP\INPUT\PKT; " POP UP ONE LEVEL  @C@@@@            UQ
)@@G@@       IF END\OF\INPUT\CARD THEN    @E@@@@                      READ\FLAUR
)@@G@@G := TRUE; " READ ANOTHER CARD@C@@@@                 END; " EOF ON PUSHEUS
)@@G@@D PACKET    @A@@@@                CASE PKT\EXTERNAL:  @D@@@@            UT
)@@G@@       READ\FLAG := FALSE; " DONT REREAD  @^@@@@                CASE *: UU
)@@G@@@B@@@@                   ERROR; " UNKNOWN PACKET@^@@@@                ENUV
)@@G@@DCASE;@A@@@@              END; " END OF FILE    @A@@@@             ELSE UW
)@@G@@" NO EOF FOUND    @C@@@@                MASSAGE\CARD\IMAGE; " $$$TEMP   UX
)@@G@@@ @@@@           END; " READ IMAGE  @F@@@@          CARD\ENDED\WITH\DIREUY
)@@G@@CTIVE := FALSE; " CARD JUST STARTING@^@@@@END; " OF READ\NEXT\CARD@[@@@@UZ
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" DO REQUIRED THINGS TO CARD IMAGE BEFORE PASSING IT ON.    VA
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE MASSAGE\CARD\IMAGE  @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     VB
)@@G@@@ @@@@" SET VALID CARD IMAGE FLAG.  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          IF FORMAVC
)@@G@@TTING AND   @C@@@@             PACKET\TYPE(CIP) EQ PKT\NORMAL THEN@A@@@@VD
)@@G@@             VALID\IMAGE := TRUE;   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" MAKE SURE NO CHAVE
)@@G@@RACTER ON THE CARD CAN BE GREATER THAN 0377 (255)     @E@@@@" BECAUSE DPVF
)@@G@@S USES CHARACTERS ABOVE THIS FOR FUNCTION CODES.@[@@@@"     @F@@@@      VG
)@@G@@    IF CARD\LENGTH GT MAX\CHAR\IL THEN " IF IMAGE TOO LONG  @D@@@@      VH
)@@G@@       CARD\LENGTH := MAX\CHAR\IL; " TRUNCATE   @C@@@@          FOR I :=VI

)@@G@@" THIS MODULE IS RESPONSIBLE FOR SCANNING DPS COMMANDS, DIRECTIVES,     WJ
)@@G@@@G@@@@" AND IS CALLED BY THE TEXT-GET ROUTINES TO HANDLE SYMBOLIC SUBSTIWK
)@@G@@TUTION@G@@@@" BY PUSHING DOWN AN INPUT CARD BUFFER. SCAN IS CALLED WITH WL

)@@G@@ED);  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" SET GLOBAL VARIABLES FOR CALLERS. @[@@@@"     YR

)@@G@@     END;   @#@@@@END; " OF SCAN    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" INITIALIZE STACKYY

)@@G@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE CHECK\ITEM    @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@          IF DTYP(ZF

)@@G@@AL SCANNER.  CONTROL RETURNS TO THE TOP AFTER PROCESSING    @F@@@@" EACHAS
)@@G@@ CHARACTER AS SYMBOLIC SUBSTITUTION MAY OCCUR AT ANY POINT. @[@@@@"     AT
)@@G@@@ @@@@PROCEDURE DOSCAN EXPORTED     @[@@@@BEGIN @G@@@@          WHILE OSAU
)@@G@@\PTR GT LOC( OPSTAK(1) ) AND SCANNER\ERROR EQ 0 DO    @#@@@@           BAV

)@@G@@ IS ALRIGHT TO DO SUBSTITUTION.     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE SUBSTITUBQ

)@@G@@NE PKT\MACRO OR NSUB THEN     @ @@@@             RETURN(FALSE);   @#@@@@BS
)@@G@@          ELSE    @ @@@@             RETURN(TRUE);    @^@@@@END; " OF SUBT
)@@G@@BSTITUTING  @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED WHEN AN OPEN [ ISBU
)@@G@@ SEEN TO PUSH STATES ONTO     @G@@@@" THE STACK WHICH WOULD RESULT IN THBV
)@@G@@E EVALUATION OF THE ARGUMENT OR     @G@@@@" EXPRESSION TO BE SUBSTITUTEDBW

)@@G@@ AN EQU.    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE BEGIN\SYMBOLIC\SUBSTITUTION     BY
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          GET\NEXT\CHAR;              " SKIP PAST IT  BZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          PUSH(S\SBS,0);              " PUSH SUBSTITUTER    @E@@@@CA

)@@G@@CANNER@B@@@@END; " OF BEGIN\SYMBOLIC\SUBSTITUTION     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECCK
)@@G@@T);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS SCANNER IS CALLED WHEN THE ITEM IS AS YETCL
)@@G@@ UNIDENTIFIED.    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE STATE\UNKNOWN @[@@@@BEGIN CM
)@@G@@@F@@@@          CASEENTRY CHARACTER         " DEPENDING ON CHARACTER    CN

)@@G@@\CHAR;@^@@@@          CASE QUOTE:   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@      CR

)@@G@@ OF STATE\UNKNOWN @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" CALLED WITH NONTRIVIAL PERIOD OR NDR

)@@G@@          PUT\WORD(0);                " CLEAR NUMBER  @ @@@@END; " OF SEDU

)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THIS SCANNER IS CALLED TO SCAN A NDZ

)@@G@@       GET\NEXT\CHAR;           " AND GET NEXT ONE    @D@@@@            EI

)@@G@@ TO SCAN A QUOTED STRING@[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE STATE\STRING  @[@@@@EP

)@@G@@T\NEXT\CHAR;              " AND SCAN PAST IT    @^@@@@END; " OF STATE\STEV
)@@G@@RING  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS SCANNER IS CALLED AFTER THE CLOSING QUOTEEW
)@@G@@ ON A QUOTED@F@@@@" LITERAL TO CHECK FOR DOUBLED QUOTES.  IF DOUBLED QUOEX
)@@G@@TES ARE     @B@@@@" FOUND IT SWITCHES BACK TO STATE\STRING. @[@@@@"     EY
)@@G@@@ @@@@PROCEDURE STATE\STRING\TERM   @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          IF CHARAEZ
)@@G@@CTER EQ QUOTE THEN@C@@@@           BEGIN " SWITCH BACK TO STATE\STRING  FA
)@@G@@@A@@@@"            DISPLAY('DQUOTE',0);   @F@@@@             PUT\CHAR(CHFB
)@@G@@ARACTER);     " SHOVE IN ONE QUOTE PLEASE @D@@@@             GET\NEXT\CHFC
)@@G@@AR;           " SCAN PAST IT  @D@@@@             STAT := S\STR;         FD
)@@G@@  " SET STATE     @D@@@@           END                        " SWITCH BFE
)@@G@@ACK   @#@@@@          ELSE    @B@@@@           BEGIN " STRING TERMINATIOFF
)@@G@@N     @A@@@@"            DISPLAY('STERM ',0);   @A@@@@             SCANNFG
)@@G@@ED := OS\PTR;     @E@@@@             DTYP(SCANNED) := TYPSTR; " SET TYPEFH
)@@G@@ STRING     @F@@@@             POP;                     " DECREMENT STACFI
)@@G@@K POINTER   @#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@END; " OF STATE\STRING\TERM   FJ
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS SCANNER IS CALLED TO SCFK
)@@G@@AN A NUMERIC (INCLUDING QUALIFICATION)    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE STFL
)@@G@@ATE\NUMERIC @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   SCALE: INTEGER WORD;        " SCFM
)@@G@@ALE FACTOR  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          IF NUMERIC THEN     @A@@@@      FN
)@@G@@     BEGIN " TO HANDLE DIGIT  @A@@@@             KLUGE := DADR(OS\PTR); FO
)@@G@@@F@@@@             IF CHARACTER GE BASE+ASCII\ZERO THEN " ILLEGAL DIGIT FP
)@@G@@@B@@@@                SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR9;  @I@@@@             ELSE FQ
)@@G@@IF DADL LT 5 THEN" FIX OVERFLOW AFTER DECIMAL (DOESN'T FIX BEFORE)@^@@@@FR
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @F@@@@                DNUM(1) := DNUM(1)*BASE + FS
)@@G@@CHARACTER-ASCII\ZERO;   @E@@@@                IF DADL GE 1 THEN     " PEFT
)@@G@@RIOD ALREADY SEEN @D@@@@                   DADL := DADL + 1;  " KEEP COUFU
)@@G@@NT    @B@@@@              END; " ADDING ANOTHER DIGIT @D@@@@            FV
)@@G@@ GET\NEXT\CHAR;           " SCAN PAST CHAR@D@@@@           END          FW
)@@G@@              " DIGIT HANDLER @#@@@@          ELSE    @B@@@@            FX
)@@G@@ IF CHARACTER EQ PERIOD THEN  @E@@@@                IF DADL GE 1 THEN   FY
)@@G@@  " PERIOD SEEN ALREADY @C@@@@                   SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR1FZ
)@@G@@;     @^@@@@                ELSE    @C@@@@                 BEGIN " TO FLGA
)@@G@@AG PERIOD SEEN    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" IF DECIMAL SEEN IN OCTAL NUMBER CHGB
)@@G@@ECK TO SEE IF VALUE     @B@@@@" IS STILL ZERO.  IF SO SWITCH TO DECIMAL.GC
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @A@@@@                   IF BASE EQ 8 THEN@B@@@@            GD
)@@G@@        BEGIN " TO CHECK VALUE@C@@@@                      KLUGE := DADR(GE
)@@G@@OS\PTR);    @B@@@@                      IF DNUM(1) EQ 0 THEN@A@@@@      GF
)@@G@@                   BASE := 10;@ @@@@                      ELSE    @F@@@@GG
)@@G@@                         SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR9; " ILLEGAL CHAR  @D@@@@GH
)@@G@@                    END; " DISALLOW OCTAL FRACTION    @E@@@@            GI
)@@G@@       DADL := 1;         " FLAG PERIOD SEEN    @E@@@@                  GJ
)@@G@@ GET\NEXT\CHAR;     " SKIP PAST PERIOD    @B@@@@                 END; " GK
)@@G@@OF PERIOD CODE    @D@@@@             ELSE " CHAR IS NEITHER DIGIT NOR PEGL
)@@G@@RIOD  @B@@@@              BEGIN " NUMERIC TERMINATION @ @@@@            GM
)@@G@@    SCALE := 1;   @A@@@@                IF BASE EQ 8 THEN   @D@@@@      GN
)@@G@@             DSBT(OS\PTR) := 1; " SET SUBTYPE   @^@@@@                ELGO
)@@G@@SE    @D@@@@                   IF DADL GT 0 THEN  " PERIOD SEEN   @D@@@@GP
)@@G@@                      SCALE := INTEXP(BASE,DADL-1);   @A@@@@            GQ
)@@G@@    SCANNED := OS\PTR;  @B@@@@                KLUGE := DADR(OS\PTR);    GR
)@@G@@@H@@@@                QUALIFY\NUMERIC;      " HANDLE ALL QUALIFICATION CGS
)@@G@@HARACTERS   @H@@@@                IF DTYP(SCANNED) EQ TYPFLP THEN " DO FGT
)@@G@@LOATING POINT DIVISION  @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @G@@@@            GU
)@@G@@       DFLP(1) := DNUM(1) / SCALE; " MAKE FINAL CONVERSION  @E@@@@      GV
)@@G@@           END; " FLOATION POINT FINAL CONVERSION     @B@@@@            GW
)@@G@@    ELSE " DO INTEGER DIVISION@G@@@@                   DNUM(1) := DNUM(1GX
)@@G@@) // SCALE; " MAKE FINAL CONVERSION @D@@@@                POP;          GY
)@@G@@        " POP STACK     @C@@@@              END; " OF NUMERIC TERMINATIOGZ
)@@G@@N     @^@@@@END; " OF STATE\NUMERIC @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IHA
)@@G@@S CALLED UPON TERMINATION OF A NUMBER, IN @E@@@@" ORDER TO EXAMINE THE LHB
)@@G@@AST CHARACTER TO QUALIFY THE NUMBER,@#@@@@" IF NECESSARY.   @[@@@@"     HC
)@@G@@@ @@@@PROCEDURE QUALIFY\NUMERIC     @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @G@@@@      HD
)@@G@@    DTYP(SCANNED) := TYPDST;    " TENATIVELY SET TYPE DISTANCE    @E@@@@HE
)@@G@@          CASEENTRY CHARACTER         " DEPENDING ON CHAR   @B@@@@      HF
)@@G@@    CASE ASCII\P, ASCII\LOWER\P:    @B@@@@           BEGIN " QUALIFIER IHG
)@@G@@S POINTS    @D@@@@             GET\NEXT\CHAR;           " SCAN PAST 'P' HH
)@@G@@@B@@@@             IF CHARACTER EQ ASCII\C OR   @D@@@@                CHHI
)@@G@@ARACTER EQ ASCII\LOWER\C THEN " PICA@^@@@@                 BEGIN  @E@@@@HJ
)@@G@@                   GET\NEXT\CHAR;     " SCAN PAST C OF PC   @G@@@@      HK
)@@G@@             DDST(1) := DNUM(1) * PICA\DISTANCE; " QUALIFY PICA   @F@@@@HL
)@@G@@                   DSBT(SCANNED) := CF\PICA; " SET PICA SUB TYPE  @A@@@@HM
)@@G@@                 END; " PICA TEST   @C@@@@             ELSE IF CHARACTERHN
)@@G@@ EQ ASCII\T OR    @F@@@@                     CHARACTER EQ ASCII\LOWER\T HO
)@@G@@THEN " POINTS     @^@@@@              BEGIN     @E@@@@                GEHP
)@@G@@T\NEXT\CHAR;        " SCAN PAST T OF PT   @F@@@@                DDST(1) HQ
)@@G@@:= DNUM(1) * POINT\DISTANCE; " QUALIFY IT @E@@@@                DSBT(SCAHR
)@@G@@NNED) := CF\POINT; " SET SUBTYPE    @A@@@@              END; " POINT TESHS
)@@G@@T     @ @@@@             ELSE " ERROR     @D@@@@                SCANNER\HT
)@@G@@ERROR := ERROR10; " ERROR     @#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@          CAHU
)@@G@@SE DOUBLE\QUOTE:  @B@@@@           BEGIN " QUALIFIER IS INCHES    @F@@@@HV
)@@G@@             GET\NEXT\CHAR;           " SCAN PAST DOUBLE QUOTE    @F@@@@HW
)@@G@@             DDST(1) := DNUM(1) * INCH\DISTANCE; " QUALIFY IT     @D@@@@HX
)@@G@@             DSBT(SCANNED) := CF\INCH; " SET SUBTYPE  @#@@@@           EHY
)@@G@@ND;   @B@@@@          CASE ASCII\L, ASCII\LOWER\L:    @B@@@@           BHZ
)@@G@@EGIN " QUALIFIER IS LINES     @D@@@@             GET\NEXT\CHAR;         IA
)@@G@@  " SCAN PAST L   @C@@@@             DDST(1) := DNUM(1) * SKIP\DISTANCE;IB
)@@G@@@E@@@@             DSBT(SCANNED) := CF\SKIP; " SUBTYPE OF SKIP    @#@@@@IC
)@@G@@           END;   @B@@@@          CASE ASCII\C, ASCII\LOWER\C:    @E@@@@ID
)@@G@@           BEGIN " QUALIFIER MAY BE CENTIMETERS OR COLUMNS  @D@@@@      IE
)@@G@@       GET\NEXT\CHAR;           " SCAN PAST 'C' @B@@@@             IF CHIF
)@@G@@ARACTER EQ ASCII\M OR   @C@@@@                CHARACTER EQ ASCII\LOWER\MIG
)@@G@@ THEN @^@@@@              BEGIN     @D@@@@                GET\NEXT\CHAR;IH
)@@G@@        " SCAN PAST M   @D@@@@                DDST(1) := DNUM(1) * CM\DIII
)@@G@@STANCE;     @D@@@@                DSBT(SCANNED) := CF\CM; " SET SUBTYPE IJ
)@@G@@@#@@@@              END;@A@@@@             ELSE " MUST BE COLUMNS @^@@@@IK
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @G@@@@                DDST(1) := DNUM(1) * COLUMIL
)@@G@@N\DISTANCE; " SET COLUMNS     @F@@@@                DSBT(SCANNED) := CF\IM
)@@G@@COL; " SET SUBTYPE OF COLUMNS @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           EIN
)@@G@@ND;   @F@@@@          CASE *:                     " ELSE NO QUALIFICATIOIO
)@@G@@N     @B@@@@           BEGIN " UNQUALIFIED INTEGER    @H@@@@            IP
)@@G@@ IF DADL GE 1 THEN        " PERIOD SEEN MAKES IT FLOATING POINT   @^@@@@IQ
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @F@@@@                DTYP(SCANNED) := TYPFLP; "IR
)@@G@@ SET FLOATING POINT TYPE@#@@@@              END @#@@@@             ELSE IS
)@@G@@@E@@@@                DTYP(SCANNED) := TYPINT; " PURE INTEGER     @#@@@@IT
)@@G@@           END;   @#@@@@          ENDCASE;@ @@@@END; " OF QUALIFY\NUMERIIU
)@@G@@C     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" TEST FOR ALPHA CHARACTIV
)@@G@@ER    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE ALPHA EXPORTED ('ALPHATEST') RESULT COIW
)@@G@@NDITION     @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          IF (CHARACTER GE ASCII\A AND    IX
)@@G@@@B@@@@              CHARACTER LE ASCII\Z) OR    @C@@@@             (CHARIY
)@@G@@ACTER GE ASCII\LOWER\A AND    @C@@@@              CHARACTER LE ASCII\LOWIZ
)@@G@@ER\Z) THEN  @ @@@@             RETURN(TRUE);    @#@@@@          ELSE    JA
)@@G@@@ @@@@             RETURN(FALSE);   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" TESTJB
)@@G@@ FOR NUMERIC CHARACTER  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE NUMERIC EXPORTED ('NJC
)@@G@@UMERTEST') RESULT CONDITION   @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          IF CHARACTER GJD
)@@G@@E ASCII\ZERO AND  @B@@@@             CHARACTER LE ASCII\NINE THEN @ @@@@JE
)@@G@@             RETURN(TRUE);    @#@@@@          ELSE    @ @@@@            JF
)@@G@@ RETURN(FALSE);   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS USEDJG
)@@G@@ TO PUSH THE SCANNER STATE STACK.  THE NEW@G@@@@" STATE IS PASSED AS THEJH
)@@G@@ FIRST ARGUMENT, THE SCAN MODE AS THE SECOND.   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDJI
)@@G@@URE PUSH(STATE: INTEGER WORD  @E@@@@              ,NMODE: INTEGER WORD) JJ
)@@G@@EXPORTED ('SCANPUSH')   @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          MSAV := LOCAL\MODES;JK
)@@G@@        " SAVE SCAN MODE@D@@@@          LOCAL\MODES := NMODE;       " SEJL
)@@G@@T NEW MODE  @F@@@@          OS\PTR := OS\PTR + DESC\LEN; " INCREMENT STAJM
)@@G@@CK POINTER  @F@@@@          IF OS\PTR GT LOC(OPSTAK(OS\SIZE)) THEN " STAJN
)@@G@@CK OVERFLOW @B@@@@           BEGIN " STACK OFLO HANDLER     @B@@@@      JO
)@@G@@       DISPLAY('STKOVR',STATE);     @D@@@@             ERROR;           JP
)@@G@@        " TEMPORARILY   @#@@@@           END;   @D@@@@          NULL\OUTJQ
)@@G@@(OS\PTR);           " SET TYPE NULL @D@@@@          STAT := STATE;      JR
)@@G@@        " SET NEW STATE @E@@@@          OPER := OPRBGL;             " SEJS
)@@G@@T DELIMITER OP    @E@@@@          DADR(OS\PTR) := DS\PTR;     " POINTER JT
)@@G@@TO DSTACK   @A@@@@          DS\PTR := DS\PTR + 1;     @D@@@@          REJU
)@@G@@TURN;                     " TO CALLER     @#@@@@END; " OF PUSH    @[@@@@JV
)@@G@@"     @B@@@@" PROCEDURE TO POP THE SCANNER STATE STACK@[@@@@"     @A@@@@JW
)@@G@@PROCEDURE POP EXPORTED ('SCANPOP')  @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @B@@@@      JX
)@@G@@    OS\PTR := OS\PTR - DESC\LEN;    @D@@@@          LOCAL\MODES := MSAV;JY
)@@G@@        " SET SCAN MODE @#@@@@END; " OF POP     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   JZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO STORE A CHARACTER INTO TKA
)@@G@@HE    @#@@@@" TEMPORARY STACK.@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\CHAR(C: INKB
)@@G@@TEGER WORD) EXPORTED ('PUTCHR')     @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          PUT\CHARKC
)@@G@@\INTO\DESC(OS\PTR,C);   @#@@@@END; " OF PUT\CHAR@[@@@@"     @G@@@@" SAMEKD
)@@G@@ AS ABOVE, BUT DESCRIPTOR IS EXPLICIT.  NOTE DATA ITEM STILL MUST @^@@@@KE
)@@G@@" BE IN THE DATA STACK. @[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\CHAR\INTO\DESC(DKF
)@@G@@ESC: MACHINE POINTER WORD " TO DESCRIPTOR @C@@@@                        KG
)@@G@@    ,CHAR: INTEGER WORD)@A@@@@          EXPORTED ('PUTCHRDESC')   @[@@@@KH
)@@G@@BEGIN @ @@@@DECLARE   I: INTEGER WORD;    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          KLKI
)@@G@@UGE := DADR(DESC);@E@@@@          I := DLEN(DESC) // 4;       " GET WORDKJ
)@@G@@ COUNTER    @B@@@@          IF DLEN(DESC) EQ 4 * I THEN     @A@@@@      KK
)@@G@@     BEGIN " TO GET MORE ROOM @F@@@@             DS\PTR := DADR(DESC) + KL
)@@G@@I + 1; " GET LAST WORD NEEDED @E@@@@             IF DS\PTR GT LOC(DTSTAKKM
)@@G@@(DS\SIZE)) THEN " OFLO  @A@@@@              BEGIN " OVERFLOW CODE @B@@@@KN
)@@G@@"               DISPLAY('PCHOVR',CHAR);   @B@@@@                SCANNER\KO
)@@G@@ERROR := ERROR20; @D@@@@              END                     " OVERFLOWKP
)@@G@@ CODE @#@@@@             ELSE @B@@@@              BEGIN " TO  GET NEXT WKQ
)@@G@@ORD   @E@@@@                DWORD(I+1) := BLANKS; " BLANK OUT NEXT WORD KR
)@@G@@@C@@@@                DLEN(DESC) := DLEN(DESC) + 1;   @B@@@@            KS
)@@G@@  END; " OF GET NEXT WORD     @C@@@@           END; " OF CODE TO GET ANOKT
)@@G@@THER WORD   @A@@@@          ELSE " NEXT CHAR SAME WORD@G@@@@            KU
)@@G@@ DLEN(DESC) := DLEN(DESC) + 1; " INCREMENT CHAR COUNTER     @[@@@@"     KV
)@@G@@@F@@@@" NOTE THAT THE ABOVE SEQUENCE DOES NOT INCREMENT DLEN(OS\PTR) IF KW
)@@G@@@G@@@@" THERE IS NOT ENOUGH ROOM ON THE STACK.  THEREFORE THE FOLLOWING KX
)@@G@@STORE @]@@@@" IS SAFE.  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          DCHR(DLEN(DESC)) := KY
)@@G@@CHAR;   " STORE CHAR    @D@@@@          RETURN;                     " TOKZ
)@@G@@ CALLER     @ @@@@END; " OF PUT\CHAR\INTO\DESC  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDLA
)@@G@@URE PUT\WORD(I: INTEGER WORD) EXPORTED ('PUTWRD')     @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@LB
)@@G@@          PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(OS\PTR,I);   @#@@@@END; " OF PUT\WORD@[@@@@LC
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" THE SAME AS ABOVE, EXCEPT DESCRIPTOR IS EXPLICIT.  NOTE   LD
)@@G@@@C@@@@" THE DATA ITEM MUST BE ON THE TEMPORARY STACK. @[@@@@"     @E@@@@LE
)@@G@@PROCEDURE PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(DESC: MACHINE POINTER WORD     @C@@@@      LF
)@@G@@                      ,WORD: INTEGER WORD)@A@@@@          EXPORTED ('PUTLG
)@@G@@WRDDESC')   @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          KLUGE := DADR(DESC);@G@@@@      LH
)@@G@@    DS\PTR := DADR(DESC) + DLEN(DESC) + 1; " GET LAST WORD NEEDED @E@@@@LI
)@@G@@          IF DS\PTR GT LOC(DTSTAK(DS\SIZE)) THEN " OFLO     @A@@@@      LJ
)@@G@@     BEGIN " TO HANDLE OFLO   @A@@@@"            DISPLAY('PWDOVR',I);   LK
)@@G@@@B@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := ERROR20;    @D@@@@           END    LL
)@@G@@                    " STACK OFLO    @#@@@@          ELSE    @B@@@@      LM
)@@G@@     BEGIN " TO PUT WORD ON STACK   @B@@@@             DLEN(DESC) := DLELN
)@@G@@N(DESC) + 1;@D@@@@             DWORD(DLEN(DESC)) := WORD; " STORE WORD  LO
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @D@@@@          RETURN;                     " TOLP
)@@G@@ CALLER     @#@@@@END; " PUT\WORD   @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     LQ
)@@G@@@D@@@@" THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO SET A DESCRIPTOR TO NULL. @[@@@@"     LR
)@@G@@@G@@@@PROCEDURE NULL\OUT(SCANNED: MACHINE WORD POINTER) EXPORTED ('NULOULS
)@@G@@T')   @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          DTYP(SCANNED) := TYPNUL;    " SET TYPELT
)@@G@@ NULL @ @@@@          DSBT(SCANNED) := 0; @ @@@@          DLEN(SCANNED) LU
)@@G@@:= 0; @A@@@@          DADR(SCANNED) := NULL\PTR;@#@@@@          RETURN; LV
)@@G@@@#@@@@END; " OF NULL\OUT@[@@@@"     @B@@@@" PROCEDURE TO DUMP A GIVEN DELW
)@@G@@SCRIPTOR    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE DUMP\DESCRIPTOR(IDENT: 6 FIELDATLX
)@@G@@A CHARACTERS@D@@@@                         ,POINT: MACHINE WORD POINTER)LY
)@@G@@@ @@@@          EXPORTED('DMPDSC')  @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@          PDISPLAYLZ
)@@G@@(IDENT,POINT);      " FIRST DUMP POINTER  @A@@@@          IF POINT NE NUMA
)@@G@@LL\PTR THEN @C@@@@           BEGIN " TO DUMP REST OF DESCRIPTOR   @C@@@@MB
)@@G@@             DISPLAY('-TYPE-',DTYP(POINT));     @C@@@@             DISPLMC
)@@G@@AY('-SUBT-',DSBT(POINT));     @C@@@@             DISPLAY('-SIZE-',DLEN(PMD
)@@G@@OINT));     @C@@@@             PDISPLAY('-ADDR-',DADR(POINT));    @E@@@@ME
)@@G@@             KLUGE := DADR(POINT);    " SET DATA POINTER    @E@@@@      MF
)@@G@@       IF DTYP(POINT) NE TYPNUL THEN " DUMP SOME DATA @A@@@@            MG
)@@G@@    FOR I := 1 TO 4 DO  @C@@@@                   ODISPLAY('-VALU-',DNUM(MH
)@@G@@I));  @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@          RETURN; @ @@@@END; " OF DUMI
)@@G@@MP\DESCRIPTOR     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" PROCEDURE TO DUMP THE TOP FIVE STAMJ
)@@G@@CK ITEMS WITH POINTER   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE DUMP\STACKTOP;@[@@@@MK
)@@G@@BEGIN @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO 20 DO @E@@@@             IF OS\PTR EML
)@@G@@Q LOC(OPSTAK(I)) THEN " THIS IS IT  @C@@@@                ODISPLAY('OSPTMM
)@@G@@R->',OPSTAK(I))   @#@@@@             ELSE @C@@@@                ODISPLAYMN
)@@G@@('::::::',OPSTAK(I));   @#@@@@          RETURN; @^@@@@END; " OF DUMP\STAMO
)@@G@@CKTOP @A@@@@PROCEDURE INTEXP(BASE: INTEGER WORD @A@@@@                ,EMP
)@@G@@XPR: INTEGER WORD)@ @@@@          RESULT INTEGER WORD @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@MQ
)@@G@@DECLARE   RESU: INTEGER WORD;         " RESULT OF EXPONENTIATION  @[@@@@MR
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@          RESU := 1;    @A@@@@          FOR I := 1 TO EXPR DMS
)@@G@@O     @A@@@@             RESU := RESU * BASE;   @^@@@@          RETURN(RMT
)@@G@@ESU); @#@@@@END; " OF INTEXP  @[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___R :TION  @[@@@@MU
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@          RESU := 1;    @A@@@@      *[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULEMV
)@@G@@;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS MODULE MAINTAINS THE INDEX TO THE UNIT DIMW
)@@G@@RECTORY     @D@@@@" ALL DIRECTORY OPERATIONS ARE DONE THRU THIS MODULE. MX
)@@G@@@E@@@@" THE DIRECTORY IS A LINEAR SET OF INDEXES TO THE UNITS     @F@@@@MY
)@@G@@" THE DIRECTORY ITSELF IS IN INTERNAL BLOCKS WHICH ARE LINKED.    @F@@@@MZ
)@@G@@" EVENTUALLY WE WILL PROBABLY KEEP AN INDEX TABLE OF THE DIRECTORY@E@@@@NA
)@@G@@" BLOCKS BUT FOR NOW WE JUST SEARCH SEQUENTIALLY FOR THEM IF@F@@@@" THE NB
)@@G@@DESIRED UNIT IS NOT IN THE DIRECTORY PAGE CURRENTLY IN CORE @[@@@@"     NC
)@@G@@@A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PND
)@@G@@ROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@NE
)@@G@@          COPY ('BLOCK-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('BREAK-PNF
)@@G@@ROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('CHKPT-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@NG
)@@G@@          COPY ('CORE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('EDIT-DENH
)@@G@@F',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('FILE-HDR-DEF',IMPORTED); @B@@@@NI
)@@G@@          COPY ('HEADER-PROCS',IMPORTED); @A@@@@          COPY ('IO-DEF1NJ
)@@G@@',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('PACKET-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@      NK
)@@G@@    COPY ('PAGE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('PIO-PROCS',IMNL
)@@G@@PORTED);    @F@@@@          COPY ('PRINT-PROCS',IMPORTED); " GET OUTPUT\NM
)@@G@@EDITED\CARD @B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-COMMON',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@      NN
)@@G@@    COPY ('UNIT-DEF',IMPORTED);     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     NO
)@@G@@@F@@@@DECLARE   PAGE\CONTROL: WORD MACHINE POINTER LOCATABLE, "  POINTERNP
)@@G@@@E@@@@          CURRENT\DIRECTORY: WORD MACHINE POINTER LOCATABLE,@E@@@@NQ
)@@G@@          NEW\DIRECTORY: WORD MACHINE POINTER LOCATABLE,    @D@@@@      NR
)@@G@@    CORE\PTR: WORD MACHINE POINTER LOCATABLE,   @B@@@@          UDIR\PTRNS
)@@G@@: MACHINE WORD POINTER, @C@@@@          NEW\UDIR\PTR: MACHINE WORD POINTNT
)@@G@@ER,   @C@@@@          NEW\NUMBER\OF\UNITS: WORD INTEGER,    @ @@@@      NU
)@@G@@    PAGE: WORD INTEGER; @[@@@@"     @C@@@@DECLARE   UNIT\ENTRY: MAPPED BNV
)@@G@@ASED(UDIR\PTR)    @D@@@@             [UNIT\FLAGS: 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGENW
)@@G@@R     @#@@@@             !*:  @D@@@@                [FIRST\OF\COMPOUND: NX
)@@G@@BIT CONDITION     @D@@@@                ,SUBSQ\OF\COMPOUND: BIT CONDITIONY
)@@G@@N     @C@@@@                ,UNIT\WAS\CHANGED: BIT CONDITION@B@@@@      NZ
)@@G@@          ,*(15): BIT CONDITION]    @D@@@@             ,UNIT\PAGE:    18OA
)@@G@@ BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER   @D@@@@             ,UNIT\CHAPTER: 18 BIT UNSIGNEOB
)@@G@@D INTEGER   @D@@@@             ,UNIT\SECTION: 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER   OC
)@@G@@@B@@@@             ,UNIT\ADDR:  INTEGER WORD    @B@@@@             ,UNITOD
)@@G@@\CKPT:  INTEGER WORD    @#@@@@             ];   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@DEFINEOE
)@@G@@    WORDS\PER\UNIT\ENTRY = 4; @C@@@@DEFINE    UNIT\CTL\SIZE = 2+BLOCK\COOF
)@@G@@NTROL\SIZE; @E@@@@DEFINE    WORDS\PER\PAGE = BLOCK\WORD\SIZE - UNIT\CTL\OG
)@@G@@SIZE; @F@@@@DEFINE    UNITS\PER\PAGE = WORDS\PER\PAGE // WORDS\PER\UNIT\OH
)@@G@@ENTRY;@[@@@@"     @B@@@@          COPY ('PAGE-DEF',IMPORTED);     @[@@@@OI
)@@G@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED;     @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECOJ
)@@G@@T);   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" INITIALIZE CURRENT DIRECTORY.     @[@@@@"     OK
)@@G@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\UNIT\DIRECTORY EXPORTED ('INITUD')     @[@@@@OL
)@@G@@BEGIN @D@@@@          IF CURRENT\DIRECTORY NE NULL\PTR THEN ERROR;@D@@@@OM
)@@G@@          CORE\PTR := NULL\PTR; " CLEAR SO ALLOCATED  @C@@@@          INON
)@@G@@ITIALIZE\PAGE(%CURRENT\DIRECTORY    @A@@@@                         ,%COROO

)@@G@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED FROM COMMANDS TO LIST THE UNIT DIRECTORY.    PA
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE LIST\UNIT\DIRECTORY @A@@@@             (STARPB
)@@G@@T: INTEGER WORD   @A@@@@             ,LAST: INTEGER WORD)   @A@@@@      PC

)@@G@@@^@@@@          EDIT\PRINT(1);@A@@@@          CURRENT\UNIT := START;    PJ

)@@G@@             TEMP\PAGE := UNIT\PAGE; " SAVE DATA@^@@@@             EDIT\PO
)@@G@@OPEN; @B@@@@             EDIT\DECIMAL(CURRENT\UNIT);  @B@@@@            PP
)@@G@@ IF FIRST\OF\COMPOUND THEN    @B@@@@              BEGIN " GET LAST FOR EPQ
)@@G@@DIT   @A@@@@                GET\NEXT\REAL\UNIT; @B@@@@                EDPR

)@@G@@1); " EDIT LAST OF COMPOUND   @D@@@@                EDIT\CHARACTER(STAR)PT

)@@G@@" WHEN A REAL LIVE UNIT BREAK IS TO OCCUR, THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED.@F@@@@VN

)@@G@@DURE IS CALLED TO OPEN A NEW UNIT.  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE OPEN\NEXVW
)@@G@@T\NEW\UNIT EXPORTED ('OPENNNU')     @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@DECLARE   PAGE\INDVX

)@@G@@; " FLAG UPDATE   @ @@@@END; " OPEN\NEXT\NEW\UNIT     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@WU
)@@G@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED WHEN THE IMAGE WHICH CAUSED THE UNIT BREAK ISWV

)@@G@@IT\DIRECTORY@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED IF THE NEW DIRECTXY

)@@G@@TORY EXPORTED ('ABORTUD')     @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          IF NEW\DIRECTOYA

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLYG

)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS MODULE CONTAINS RZB

)@@G@@NITS.  IT SETS THE CALL PACKETS UP, CHECKPOINTS DPS IN@F@@@@" ORDER TO FZD
)@@G@@ACILITATE RECOVERY, AND CALLS THE SUBROUTINE EDLINK.  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@ZE
)@@G@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('BLOCK-PROCS',ZF

)@@G@@    COPY ('CHKPT-DEF',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('CHKPT-PROCS',ZH
)@@G@@IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('EDITOR-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@      ZI
)@@G@@    COPY ('RUN-DATA-DEF',IMPORTED); @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE GET\UNITZJ
)@@G@@S\FOR\EDITOR(FIRST: WORD INTEGER,   @D@@@@          LAST: WORD INTEGER) ZK
)@@G@@IMPORTED ('GETUFE');    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@INCLUDE(LIJ\PLUS,NO SOURCE);  ZL

)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED IF THE INPUZT
)@@G@@T SCRIPT IS TO BE GOTTEN BY   @B@@@@" CALLING THE EDITOR WITH THE 'I' OPZU
)@@G@@TION. @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE GET\INPUT\FROM\TEXT\EDITOR EXPORTED ('ZV
)@@G@@GIFTED')    @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          EDLQUAL := TRUE;    @ @@@@      ZW
)@@G@@    EDLFILE := TRUE;    @ @@@@          EDLELT := FALSE;    @B@@@@      ZX
)@@G@@    EDQUAL(1) := ED\SCRATCH\QUAL(1);@B@@@@          EDQUAL(2) := ED\SCRAZY
)@@G@@TCH\QUAL(2);@B@@@@          EDFILE(1) := ED\CALL\NAME(1);   @B@@@@      ZZ
)@@G@@    EDFILE(2) := ED\CALL\NAME(2);   @E@@@@          IF DPS\OPTION(P\OPTIAA
)@@G@@ON) THEN " FIELDATA TERMINAL  @ @@@@             EDOPTS := IP\OPT;@D@@@@AB
)@@G@@          ELSE " ASCII TERMINAL USE Q MODE EDITOR     @ @@@@            AC
)@@G@@ EDOPTS := IQ\OPT;@C@@@@          CHECKPOINT\DPS(DPS\INPUTTING,1,1);    AD
)@@G@@@C@@@@          CALL\TEXT\EDITOR(LOC(ED\CALL\PKT));   @E@@@@          INAE
)@@G@@ITIALIZE\CONTINGENCIES; " EDITOR TURNED THEM OFF@A@@@@          CASEENTRAF
)@@G@@Y RETURN\STATUS   @^@@@@          CASE EDNORM:  @C@@@@           BEGIN "AG
)@@G@@ TO PUT IT IN SCRATCH FILE    @C@@@@             CHECKPOINT\DPS(DPS\ADSOAH
)@@G@@RBING,1,1); @C@@@@             REPLACE\UNITS\FROM\EDITOR(1,1);    @#@@@@AI
)@@G@@           END;   @^@@@@          CASE EDEOF:   @#@@@@           BEGIN  AJ
)@@G@@@C@@@@             CHECKPOINT\DPS(DPS\ADSORBING,1,1); @C@@@@            AK
)@@G@@ REPLACE\UNITS\FROM\EDITOR(1,1);    @ @@@@             READ\EOF := TRUE;AL
)@@G@@@C@@@@             HARD\EOF := TRUE; " TERMINATE DPS  @#@@@@           EAM
)@@G@@ND;   @#@@@@          CASE *: @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@            AN
)@@G@@ DPS\ABORT := TRUE; " ABORT EVERYTHING    @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@AO
)@@G@@          ENDCASE;@A@@@@END; " OF GET\INPUT\FROM\TEXT\EDITOR@#@@@@CONTROAP
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO EDIT SPECIFIAQ
)@@G@@C UNITS.    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE EDIT\UNITS(FIRST: INTEGER WORD  AR
)@@G@@@F@@@@                    ,LAST : INTEGER WORD) EXPORTED ('EDUNIT')     AS
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          EDLQUAL := TRUE; " QUALIFIER    @C@@@@      AT
)@@G@@    EDLFILE := TRUE; " FILE NAME GIVEN    @C@@@@          EDLELT := FALSAU
)@@G@@E; " NO ELEMENT NAME    @C@@@@          EDQUAL(1) := ED\SCRATCH\QUAL(1);AV
)@@G@@ "    @B@@@@          EDQUAL(2) := ED\SCRATCH\QUAL(2);@B@@@@          EDAW
)@@G@@FILE(1) := ED\CALL\NAME(1); " @B@@@@          EDFILE(2) := ED\CALL\NAME(AX
)@@G@@2);   @E@@@@          IF DPS\OPTION(P\OPTION) THEN " FIELDATA TERMINAL  AY
)@@G@@@D@@@@             EDOPTS := UP\OPT; " SET U AND P OPTIONS  @A@@@@      AZ
)@@G@@    ELSE " USE ASCII OPTIONS  @D@@@@             EDOPTS := UQ\OPT; " SETBA
)@@G@@ U AND Q OPTIONS  @C@@@@          GET\UNITS\FOR\EDITOR(FIRST,LAST);     BB
)@@G@@@G@@@@          CHECKPOINT\DPS(DPS\EDITING,FIRST,LAST); " CHECKPOINT STABC
)@@G@@TUS   @E@@@@          CALL\TEXT\EDITOR(LOC(ED\CALL\PKT)); " CALL EDITOR BD
)@@G@@@E@@@@          INITIALIZE\CONTINGENCIES; " TURNED OFF BY EDITOR  @B@@@@BE
)@@G@@          IF RETURN\STATUS EQ EDNORM OR   @E@@@@             RETURN\STATBF
)@@G@@US EQ EDEOF THEN " NORMAL RETURN    @D@@@@           BEGIN " TO COPY BACBG
)@@G@@K TO DPS SCRATCH FILE   @D@@@@             CHECKPOINT\DPS(DPS\ADSORBING,BH
)@@G@@FIRST,LAST);@G@@@@             REPLACE\UNITS\FROM\EDITOR(FIRST,LAST); " BI
)@@G@@INSERT NEW UNITS  @D@@@@           END; " COPYING BACK TO DPS SCRATCH FIBJ
)@@G@@LE    @#@@@@          ELSE    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @H@@@@            BK
)@@G@@ RECOVER\FREED\FILE\BLOCKS; " DON'T RELEASE BLOCKS PASSED TO ED   @#@@@@BL
)@@G@@           END;   @E@@@@          IF RETURN\STATUS EQ EDEOF THEN " NO MOBM
)@@G@@RE READ$'S  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             READ\EOF := TRUE;BN
)@@G@@ "    @A@@@@             HARD\EOF := TRUE; "    @#@@@@           END;   BO
)@@G@@@^@@@@END; " OF EDIT\UNITS    @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@BP
)@@G@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO EDIT THE PRODUCED OUTPUT FILE.@[@@@@"     BQ
)@@G@@@C@@@@PROCEDURE EDIT\OUTPUT\FILE EXPORTED ('EDOFIL')  @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@BR
)@@G@@          EDLQUAL := FALSE;   @ @@@@          EDLELT := FALSE;    @ @@@@BS
)@@G@@          EDLFILE := TRUE;    @E@@@@          EDFILE(1) := OUTPUT\FILENABT

)@@G@@       HARD\EOF := TRUE;@#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@END; " OF EDIT\OUTCA
)@@G@@PUT\FILE    @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE ICB
)@@G@@S CALLED FROM ELEMENT RECOVERY WHEN DPS WAS     @B@@@@" LINKED TO THE TECC
)@@G@@XT EDITOR BEFORE CRASH. @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE RECOVER\EDITING EXPOCD
)@@G@@RTED ('RECED')    @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          EDLQUAL := FALSE;   @ @@@@CE
)@@G@@          EDLFILE := FALSE;   @ @@@@          EDLELT := FALSE;    @B@@@@CF
)@@G@@          IF DPS\OPTION(P\OPTION) THEN    @ @@@@             EDOPTS := PCG
)@@G@@\OPT; @#@@@@          ELSE    @ @@@@             EDOPTS := Q\OPT; @E@@@@CH
)@@G@@          CALL\TEXT\EDITOR(LOC(ED\CALL\PKT)); " CALL HIM    @E@@@@      CI
)@@G@@    INITIALIZE\CONTINGENCIES; " EDITOR TURNED THEM OFF@B@@@@          IFCJ
)@@G@@ RETURN\STATUS EQ EDNORM OR   @E@@@@             RETURN\STATUS EQ EDEOF CK
)@@G@@THEN " NORMAL RETURN    @D@@@@           BEGIN " TO COPY BACK TO DPS SCRCL

)@@G@@                                      ,LAST\UNIT); " GET IT @D@@@@      CO

)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             IF DPS\STATUS EQ DPS\INPUTTINCQ
)@@G@@G AND @C@@@@                RETURN\STATUS EQ EDABORT THEN   @A@@@@      CR
)@@G@@          DPS\ABORT := TRUE;  @#@@@@             ELSE @H@@@@            CS
)@@G@@    RECOVER\FREED\FILE\BLOCKS; " DON'T RELEASE BLOCKS PASSED TO ED@#@@@@CT
)@@G@@           END;   @E@@@@          IF RETURN\STATUS EQ EDEOF THEN " NO MOCU
