)@@G@@ TRUE; "    @#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@END; "*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULECZ
)@@G@@;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS MODULE CONTAINS ALL FOOTNOTE PROCESSING PDA
)@@G@@ROCEDURES.  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@DB
)@@G@@          INCLUDE (DEBUG\CODE, NO SOURCE);@B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PDC
)@@G@@ROCS',IMPORTED);  @#@@@@          RESUME; @B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEDD
)@@G@@F',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CHAR-SIZE',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@DE
)@@G@@          COPY ('FD-PROCS',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('GETPUT-DF
)@@G@@DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('GETPUT-PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@DG
)@@G@@          COPY ('PUSH-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SKIP-PRDH
)@@G@@OCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('STAGING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@DI
)@@G@@          COPY ('UNIT-COMMON',IMPORTED);  @@@@@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE ALLOCATEDJ
)@@G@@\AREA(TYPE: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER) @D@@@@          IMPORTED ('GETAREA')DK
)@@G@@ RESULT MACHINE POINTER;@@@@@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE CHECK\FOR\LINE\BREAK IMPORDL
)@@G@@TED ('CHKLNBRK'); @@@@@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE FORCE\END\OF\COLUMN IMPORTED ('FDM
)@@G@@OREOC');    @@@@@@@C@@@@PROCEDURE FORCE\END\OF\LINE IMPORTED ('FOREOL');DN
)@@G@@@@@@@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE SWITCH\TO\AREA(NEW\AREA: MACHINE POINTER)   @B@@@@DO
)@@G@@             IMPORTED ('SWITCHAREA');     @@@@@@@#@@@@CONTROL (EJECT);  DP
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @#@@@@"   .FOOTNOTE     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THE TEXT WHICH FDQ
)@@G@@OLLOWS THIS DIRECTIVE IS PROCESSED AS A FOOTNOTE@B@@@@" UNTIL AN .ENDF DDR
)@@G@@IRECTIVE IS ENCOUNTERED.@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\FOOTNOTE\DIRDS
)@@G@@ECTIVE EXPORTED ('PROFTNOTE') @[@@@@BEGIN @@@@@@@A@@@@DECLARE   FOOTNOTEDT
)@@G@@\START: DISTANCE  @A@@@@          ,FOOTNOTE\HEIGHT: DISTANCE@C@@@@      DU
)@@G@@    ,FOOTNOTE\CONTROL\WORD: LOGICAL WORD  @C@@@@          !EXTENDED\FOOTDV
)@@G@@NOTE: CONDITION WORD;   @@@@@@@D@@@@          IF AREA\TYPE EQ TEXT THEN DW
)@@G@@ " ACCEPT FOOTNOTE@#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             IF NUMBER\ODX
)@@G@@F\COLUMNS GT 1 THEN  " ****** @E@@@@                RETURN;  " NO MULTIPDY
)@@G@@LE COLUMNS FOR NOW!     @D@@@@             PUSH\WORD\BUFFER;  " SAVE CURDZ
)@@G@@RENT LINE   @E@@@@             IF FIXED\AREA\PTR EQ LOC(FOOTING\AREA) THEA
)@@G@@EN    @E@@@@                FIXED\AREA\PTR := ALLOCATE\AREA(FOOTNOTE);  EB
)@@G@@@E@@@@             AREA\PTR := FIXED\AREA\PTR;  " GO TO FOOTNOTE  @C@@@@EC
)@@G@@             WHILE NEXT\AREA\PTR NE NULL\PTR DO @F@@@@                ARED
)@@G@@EA\PTR := NEXT\AREA\PTR;  " GO TO LAST FOOTNOTE @E@@@@             FOOTNEE
)@@G@@OTE\CONTROL\WORD := AREA\CONTROL\WORD;    @B@@@@             AREA\END\PEEF
)@@G@@NDING := FALSE;   @B@@@@             IF NOT EXTENDED\FOOTNOTE THEN@^@@@@EG
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @G@@@@                AREA\PTR := LOC(TEXT\AREA)EH
)@@G@@;  " GO BACK TO TEXT AREA     @C@@@@                IF NOT CAN\SKIP(2*LEEI
)@@G@@ADING) THEN @H@@@@                " THIS INSURES WE HAVE SPACE FOR THE PEJ
)@@G@@USHED TEXT LINE AND     @D@@@@                " THE DIVIDER LINE FOR THEEK
)@@G@@ FOOTNOTE.  @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @B@@@@                   FORCEEL
)@@G@@\END\OF\COLUMN;   @G@@@@                   " THIS ACTUALLY FORCES END OFEM
)@@G@@ PAGE FOR SINGLE COLUMN @G@@@@                   " OUTPUT AND RELEASES TEN
)@@G@@HE FOOTNOTE AREA SO WE HAVE   @E@@@@                   " TO GET ANOTHER EO
)@@G@@ONE FOR CURRENT PAGE.   @F@@@@                   FIXED\AREA\PTR := ALLOCEP
)@@G@@ATE\AREA(FOOTNOTE);     @^@@@@                 END;   @G@@@@            EQ
)@@G@@    FOOTNOTE\START := AREA\VPOS\START+AREA\VPOS+LEADING;    @F@@@@      ER
)@@G@@          FOOTNOTE\HEIGHT := AREA\HEIGHT-AREA\VPOS-LEADING; @F@@@@      ES
)@@G@@          AREA\HEIGHT := FOOTNOTE\START-AREA\VPOS\START;    @F@@@@      ET
)@@G@@          AREA\PTR := FIXED\AREA\PTR;  " GO TO FOOTNOTE AREA@D@@@@      EU
)@@G@@          AREA\VPOS\START := FOOTNOTE\START;    @E@@@@                AREV
)@@G@@EA\HEIGHT := FOOTNOTE\HEIGHT+AREA\VPOS;   @F@@@@                " ADD HEEW
)@@G@@IGHT OF FOOTNOTES ALREADY ACCUMULATED     @#@@@@              END;@B@@@@EX
)@@G@@             INITIALIZE\FOOTNOTE\AREA;    @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@EY
)@@G@@END; " OF PROCESS\FOOTNOTE\DIRECTIVE@#@@@@CONTROL (EJECT);  @[@@@@"     EZ
)@@G@@@]@@@@"   .ENDF   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\ENDF\DIRECTIVE EXPFA
)@@G@@ORTED ('PROENDF') @[@@@@BEGIN @@@@@@@C@@@@DECLARE   FOOTNOTE\CONTROL\WORFB
)@@G@@D: LOGICAL WORD   @C@@@@          !EXTENDED\FOOTNOTE: CONDITION WORD;   FC
)@@G@@@@@@@@@F@@@@          IF AREA\TYPE EQ FOOTNOTE THEN  " ACCEPT ENDF DIRECFD
)@@G@@TIVE  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             AREA\END\PENDING := TRUFE
)@@G@@E;    @A@@@@             CHECK\FOR\LINE\BREAK;  @E@@@@             FOOTNFF
)@@G@@OTE\CONTROL\WORD := AREA\CONTROL\WORD;    @B@@@@             IF EXTENDEDFG
)@@G@@\FOOTNOTE THEN    @C@@@@                SWITCH\TO\AREA(LOC(TEXT\AREA)); FH
)@@G@@@#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@                PROCESS\ENDFOOT;    @ @@@@FI
)@@G@@             POP\WORD\BUFFER; @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@END; " OF PRFJ
)@@G@@OCESS\ENDF\DIRECTIVE    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" PROCESS\ENDFOOT RETURNS CONTFK
)@@G@@ROL TO THE TEXT AREA TO FINISH@ @@@@" SETTING THE REFERENCE LINE. @[@@@@FL
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\ENDFOOT EXPORTED ('ENDFOOT')  @[@@@@BEGIN FM
)@@G@@@@@@@@@A@@@@DECLARE   FOOTNOTE\START: DISTANCE; @@@@@@@B@@@@          IFFN
)@@G@@ AREA\TYPE EQ FOOTNOTE THEN   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@            FO
)@@G@@ AREA\VPOS\START := AREA\VPOS\START+AREA\HEIGHT @C@@@@                  FP
)@@G@@              -AREA\VPOS;     @C@@@@             FOOTNOTE\START := AREA\FQ
)@@G@@VPOS\START; @C@@@@             SWITCH\TO\AREA(LOC(TEXT\AREA));    @E@@@@FR
)@@G@@             AREA\HEIGHT := FOOTNOTE\START-AREA\VPOS\START; @#@@@@      FS
)@@G@@     END;   @ @@@@END; " OF PROCESS\ENDFOOT     @#@@@@CONTROL (EJECT);  FT
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" PROCESS\FOOTNOTE\OVERFLOW IS CALLED WHEN A FOOTNOTE FU
)@@G@@CANNOT FIT  @F@@@@" ON THE CURRENT PAGE AND HAS TO BE CONTINUED ON THE NFV
)@@G@@EXT PAGE.   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\FOOTNOTE\OVERFLOW EXPORTFW
)@@G@@ED ('PROFTOVFL')  @[@@@@BEGIN @@@@@@@B@@@@DECLARE   END\OF\FOOTNOTE: WORFX
)@@G@@D CONDITION @C@@@@          ,FOOTNOTE\CONTROL\WORD: LOGICAL WORD  @C@@@@FY
)@@G@@          !EXTENDED\FOOTNOTE: CONDITION WORD;   @@@@@@@C@@@@          ENFZ
)@@G@@D\OF\FOOTNOTE := AREA\END\PENDING;  @D@@@@          NEXT\AREA\PTR := ALLGA
)@@G@@OCATE\AREA(FOOTNOTE);   @E@@@@          AREA\PTR := NEXT\AREA\PTR;  " GOGB
)@@G@@ TO NEW FOOTNOTE  @C@@@@          AREA\VPOS\START := TOP\MARGIN+LEADING;GC
)@@G@@@D@@@@          AREA\HEIGHT := PAGE\HEIGHT-BOTTOM\MARGIN    @B@@@@      GD
)@@G@@                   -AREA\VPOS\START;@A@@@@          EXTENDED\FOOTNOTE :=GE
)@@G@@ TRUE;@D@@@@          AREA\CONTROL\WORD := FOOTNOTE\CONTROL\WORD; @B@@@@GF
)@@G@@          IF NOT END\OF\FOOTNOTE THEN     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @ @@@@GG
)@@G@@             PUSH\WORD\BUFFER;@B@@@@             INITIALIZE\FOOTNOTE\AREGH
)@@G@@A;    @ @@@@             POP\WORD\BUFFER; @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@GI
)@@G@@END; " OF PROCESS\FOOTNOTE\OVERFLOW @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" PROCEDURE INITIAGJ
)@@G@@LIZE FOOTNOTE AREA STARTS OFF THE AREA BY INSERTING   @E@@@@" A DIVIDINGGK
)@@G@@ LINE OF 12 UNDERLINE CHARACTERS AND SPACE.     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDGL
)@@G@@URE INITIALIZE\FOOTNOTE\AREA  @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          IF AREA\VPOS EGM
)@@G@@Q 0 THEN  " FIRST FOOTNOTE    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@            GN
)@@G@@ PERFORM\LEADING(LEADING,FUNC\LEADU);     @A@@@@             FOR I:= 1 TGO
)@@G@@O 12 DO     @E@@@@                PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD(UNDERLINEGP
)@@G@@);    @C@@@@             IF CAN\SKIP(SKIP\DISTANCE) THEN    @E@@@@      GQ
)@@G@@          PERFORM\LEADING(SKIP\DISTANCE,FUNC\LEADU);  @H@@@@            GR
)@@G@@ INHIBIT\LEADING := TRUE;  " DO NOT ALLOW EOL ROUTINE TO LEAD     @A@@@@GS
)@@G@@             MOVE\NEXT\WORD\TO\LINE;@A@@@@             FORCE\END\OF\LINEGT
)@@G@@;     @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@END; " OF INITIALIZE\FOOTNOTE\AREA  GU
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___    FORCE\END\OF\LINE;     @#@@@@           EGV
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS MODULE CONTAINS AGW
)@@G@@LL TABLE PROCESSING PROCEDURES.     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DGX
)@@G@@EFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@GY
)@@G@@          COPY ('GETPUT-PROCS',IMPORTED); @@@@@@@C@@@@PROCEDURE FORCE\ENGZ
)@@G@@D\OF\LINE IMPORTED ('FOREOL');@@@@@@@#@@@@CONTROL (EJECT);  @[@@@@"     HA
)@@G@@@]@@@@"   .TABLE  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\TABLE\DIRECTIVE EXHB
)@@G@@PORTED ('PROTABLE')     @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          OUTPUT\NEXT\WORD;   HC
)@@G@@@E@@@@          FORCE\END\OF\LINE;  " ALWAYS CAUSE LINE BREAK     @A@@@@HD
)@@G@@END; " OF PROCESS\TABLE\DIRECTIVE   @#@@@@CONTROL (EJECT);  @[@@@@"     HE
)@@G@@@]@@@@"   .ENDT   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\ENDT\DIRECTIVE EXPHF
)@@G@@ORTED ('PROENDT') @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          OUTPUT\NEXT\WORD;   @E@@@@HG
)@@G@@          FORCE\END\OF\LINE;  " ALWAYS CAUSE LINE BREAK     @A@@@@END; "HH
)@@G@@ OF PROCESS\ENDT\DIRECTIVE    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___600          FOHI
)@@G@@RCE\END\OF\LINE;  " ALWAYS CAUSE LINE BREAK     @A@@@@END; " OF PROCESS\HJ
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@"     DOCUMENT PROCESSINHK
)@@G@@G SYSTEM (DPS)    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@"     BY  KERN E. SIBBALD     @[@@@@HL
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@"         COPYRIGHT 1976@A@@@@"         UNIVERSITY OF MARYLAHM
)@@G@@ND    @A@@@@"         COMPUTER SCIENCE CENTER   @B@@@@"         COLLEGE HN
)@@G@@PARK, MARYLAND 20742    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THIS MODULE DOESHO
)@@G@@ THE LEADING FOR THE PHOTON 7445.   @D@@@@" LEADING IS DONE BY OUTPUTTINHP
)@@G@@G A PRIMARY LEAD FLAG,  @C@@@@" FOLLOWED BY TWO CODES REPRESENTING THE LHQ
)@@G@@EADING@D@@@@" IN 1/2 UNITS FOR THE CARRIAGE RETURN AND LINE FEED  @D@@@@HR
)@@G@@" RESPECTIVELY.  WE SET THE LEADING FOR THE CARRIAGE  @F@@@@" RETURN TO HS
)@@G@@ZERO AND PERFORM LEADING WITH THE LINE FEED ONLY.     @E@@@@" THE SET SEHT
)@@G@@QUENCE IS FOLLOWED BY A CARRIAGE RETURN BECAUSE @B@@@@" OF THE INTERNAL HU
)@@G@@BUFFERING OF THE PHOTON.@[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPOHV
)@@G@@RTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('CHAR-SIZE',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COHW
)@@G@@PY ('PHOTON-DEF',IMPORTED);   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DEFINE    MAX\LEAD = 40;HX
)@@G@@ " MAXIMUM LEAD IN ONE REQUEST@[@@@@"     @H@@@@DECLARE   LEAD: DISTANCEHY
)@@G@@ STATIC IMPORTED ('LEDDEV'); " PASSED BY FD-SELECT    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@HZ
)@@G@@DECLARE   LAST\LEAD: WORD INTEGER STATIC; @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PAIA
)@@G@@CK\CHARACTER(CHARACTER: WORD INTEGER)     @A@@@@           IMPORTED ('PAIB
)@@G@@CKPHCHAR'); @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE LEADING\FOR\PHOTON EXPORTED ('PHIC
)@@G@@7445LEADNG')@[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@DECLARE   OUT\LEAD: WORD INTEGER;   @[@@@@ID
)@@G@@"     @G@@@@          OUT\LEAD := LEAD//UNIT\LEADING; " CONVERT TO DEVICIE
)@@G@@E UNITS     @D@@@@          IF OUT\LEAD NE 0 THEN " DO NOT DO NIL LEAD  IF
)@@G@@@ @@@@           BEGIN " DO LEADING @E@@@@             IF OUT\LEAD NE LAIG
)@@G@@ST\LEAD THEN " MUST WE RESET  @C@@@@              BEGIN " RESET STANDARDIH
)@@G@@ LEADING    @E@@@@                PACK\CHARACTER(PH\PR\LEAD); " BEGIN SEII
)@@G@@QUENCE@E@@@@                PACK\CHARACTER(PH\FEED); " ZERO FOR CRTN    IJ
)@@G@@@G@@@@                IF OUT\LEAD GT MAX\LEAD THEN " TOO MUCH FOR ONE STIK
)@@G@@ROKE  @A@@@@                 BEGIN " BREAK IT UP@E@@@@                  IL
)@@G@@ PACK\CHARACTER(MAX\LEAD); " PACK MAXIMUM @F@@@@                   PACK\IM
)@@G@@CHARACTER(PH\CR); " CR TO TERMINATE LINE  @F@@@@                   WHILEIN
)@@G@@ OUT\LEAD GT MAX\LEAD DO " BREAK IT UP    @D@@@@                    BEGIIO
)@@G@@N " LOOP OUTPUTTING LINE FEEDS@F@@@@                      PACK\CHARACTERIP
)@@G@@(PH\LF); " DO MAX LEADING     @D@@@@                      OUT\LEAD := OUIQ
)@@G@@T\LEAD - MAX\LEAD;@D@@@@                    END; " LOOP OUTPUTTING LINE IR
)@@G@@FEEDS @F@@@@                   PACK\CHARACTER(PH\CR); " CR TO TERMINATE IS
)@@G@@LINE  @F@@@@                   PACK\CHARACTER(PH\PR\LEAD); " RESET LEADIIT
)@@G@@NG    @E@@@@                   PACK\CHARACTER(PH\FEED); " ZERO FOR CRTN IU
)@@G@@@A@@@@                 END; " BREAK IT UP @F@@@@                PACK\CHAIV
)@@G@@RACTER(OUT\LEAD); " OUTPUT LEADING VALUE  @F@@@@                PACK\CHAIW
)@@G@@RACTER(PH\CR); " CR TO TERMINATE LINE     @F@@@@                LAST\LEAIX
)@@G@@D := OUT\LEAD; " REMEMBER LAST LEAD DONE  @C@@@@              END; " RESIY
)@@G@@ET STANDARD LEADING     @D@@@@             PACK\CHARACTER(PH\LF); " DO TIZ
)@@G@@HE LEADING  @E@@@@             PACK\CHARACTER(PH\CR); " CR TO TERMINATE JA
)@@G@@LINE  @ @@@@           END; " DO LEADING  @^@@@@END; " LEAD FOR PHOTON  JB
)@@G@@@[@@@@TERM; ___@@@O MAX *[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@JC
)@@G@@" THIS MODULE CONTAINS THE AREA ALLOCATION AND SWITCHING ROUTINES.@[@@@@JD
)@@G@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          INCLUDE JE
)@@G@@(DEBUG\CODE, NO SOURCE);@B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED);  JF
)@@G@@@#@@@@          RESUME; @B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED);     JG
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('CORE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('DJH
)@@G@@IRECT-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SKIP-PROCS',IMPORTED);   JI
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-COMMON',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@      @E@@@@PROCEDJJ
)@@G@@URE DO\DEFERRED\FUNCTIONS IMPORTED ('DODEFUNCS');     @[@@@@      @#@@@@JK
)@@G@@CONTROL (EJECT);  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE GETS A NEW AREA ANDJL
)@@G@@ INITIALIZES IT.  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE ALLOCATE\AREA(TYPE: 6 BIT JM
)@@G@@UNSIGNED INTEGER) @E@@@@             EXPORTED ('GETAREA') RESULT MACHINEJN
)@@G@@ POINTER    @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      @A@@@@DECLARE   NEW\AREA: MACHINE POJO
)@@G@@INTER;@B@@@@DECLARE   KEEP\CONTROL\WORD: 6 BIT LOGICAL@^@@@@          !*JP
)@@G@@: MAPPED    @A@@@@              [*: 2 BIT LOGICAL     @B@@@@            JQ
)@@G@@  ,B\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDITION  @B@@@@              ,F\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDIJR
)@@G@@TION  @B@@@@              ,I\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDITION  @B@@@@            JS
)@@G@@  ,T\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDITION];@[@@@@      @F@@@@          NEW\AREA := ALJT
)@@G@@LOCATE\CORE(AREA\LNG);  " GET NEXT AREA   @G@@@@          FOR I:=2 TO ARJU
)@@G@@EA\LNG-1 DO  " COPY CURRENT SPECS TO NEXT AREA  @D@@@@             CORE(JV
)@@G@@NEW\AREA+I) := CORE(AREA\PTR+I);    @F@@@@          " SAVE\TEXT\PTR AND JW
)@@G@@SAVE\WALAB\PTR ARE NOT COPIED!!!    @D@@@@          NEW\AREA :=: AREA\PTJX
)@@G@@R;  " SWITCH POINTERS   @A@@@@          " WE ARE NOW IN NEW AREA  @F@@@@JY
)@@G@@          AREA\TYPE := TYPE;  " ALWAYS TYPE THE NEW AREA FIRST    @E@@@@JZ
)@@G@@          NEXT\AREA\PTR := NULL\PTR;  " CLEAR FORWARD LINK  @F@@@@      KA
)@@G@@    COLUMN\NUMBER := 1;  " ALWAYS SET BACK COLUMN\NUMBER    @G@@@@      KB
)@@G@@    COLUMN\LIST\PTR := NULL\PTR; " CLEAR IT TO AVOID CONFUSION    @ @@@@KC
)@@G@@          SET\AREA\VPOS(0);   @A@@@@          SET\AREA\REL\VPOS(0);     KD
)@@G@@@A@@@@          AREA\CONTROL\WORD := O'0';@^@@@@          CASEENTRY TYPEKE
)@@G@@@^@@@@          CASE KEEP:    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @G@@@@            KF
)@@G@@ LAST\AREA\PTR := NEW\AREA;  " LINK BACK TO REQUESTING AREA @F@@@@      KG
)@@G@@       AREA\HEIGHT := PAGE\HEIGHT-TOP\MARGIN-BOTTOM\MARGIN; @F@@@@      KH
)@@G@@       KEEP\CONTROL\WORD := O'0';  " CLEAR CONTROL WORD     @C@@@@      KI
)@@G@@       IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\F) THEN     @^@@@@              BEGIN     KJ
)@@G@@@E@@@@                F\OPTION := TRUE;  " MARK AS FLOATING KEEP  @D@@@@KK
)@@G@@                I\OPTION := DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\I);   @D@@@@            KL
)@@G@@    T\OPTION := DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\T);   @D@@@@                B\OPTIONKM
)@@G@@ := DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\B);   @C@@@@                IF NUMBER\OF\COLUMNSKN
)@@G@@ GT 1 THEN  @G@@@@                   COLUMN\LIST\PTR := ALLOCATE\CORE(NUKO
)@@G@@MBER\OF\COLUMNS); @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@             ELSE @^@@@@KP
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @D@@@@                I\OPTION := DIRECTIVE\OPT(KQ
)@@G@@ASCII\I);   @G@@@@                NUMBER\OF\COLUMNS := 1; " KEEP AREA HAKR
)@@G@@S SINGLE COLUMN   @#@@@@              END;@D@@@@             AREA\CONTROKS
)@@G@@L\WORD := KEEP\CONTROL\WORD;  @#@@@@           END;   @^@@@@          CAKT
)@@G@@SE FOOTNOTE:@#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             FIXED\AREA\PTR :=KU
)@@G@@ LOC(FOOTING\AREA);     @F@@@@             NUMBER\OF\COLUMNS := 1; " SINKV
)@@G@@GLE COLUMN FOOTNOTES    @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@          ENDCASE;KW
)@@G@@@E@@@@          AREA\PTR :=: NEW\AREA;  " RETURN TO MAIN AREA     @ @@@@KX
)@@G@@          RETURN(NEW\AREA);   @^@@@@END; " OF ALLOCATE\AREA @#@@@@CONTROKY
)@@G@@L (EJECT);  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" PROCEDURE SWITCH\TO\AREA SWITCHES TO THEKZ
)@@G@@ AREA SPECIFIED IN THE  @E@@@@" ARGUMENT AND RETURNS THE POINTER TO THE LA
)@@G@@AREA WE CAME FROM.@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE SWITCH\TO\AREA(NEW\AREA: MLB
)@@G@@ACHINE POINTER)   @A@@@@             EXPORTED ('SWITCHAREA')@[@@@@BEGIN LC
)@@G@@@D@@@@          DO\DEFERRED\FUNCTIONS;  " ALWAYS CLEAN UP   @C@@@@      LD
)@@G@@    AREA\PTR := NEW\AREA;  " GO TO AREA   @#@@@@          RETURN; @^@@@@LE
)@@G@@END; " OF SWITCH\TO\AREA@[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@EDITOR SCRATCH FILLF
)@@G@@E COULD NOT BE CATALOGED*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @F@@@@" THIS MODULLG
)@@G@@E IS RESPONSIBLE FOR JUSTIFICATION.   END-OF-LINE     @E@@@@" SHOULD CALLH
)@@G@@L THIS MODULE SO THAT WHEN PROOFING IS DONE     @E@@@@" THE SAME NUMBER LI
)@@G@@OF CHARACTERS WILL FIT ON AN OUTPUT LINE. @F@@@@" WHEN PROOFING IS DONE LJ
)@@G@@THE CHARACTER WIDTH TABLES ARE LEFT FOR   @F@@@@" THE FINAL DEVICE.  ONLLK
)@@G@@Y THE FINAL PACK ROUTINE KNOWS THAT OUTPUT@E@@@@" IS TO BE DIRECTED TO ALL
)@@G@@ PRINTER RATHER THAN THE REAL FINAL @]@@@@" DEVICE.   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@LM
)@@G@@"  AT THIS TIME THIS ROUTINE ONLY CHANGES INTER WORD SPACING@G@@@@"  TO LN
)@@G@@ACCOMPLISH THE JUSTIFICATION.  INTRA WORD JUSTIFICATION IS PLANNED@G@@@@LO
)@@G@@"  IN THE FUTURE FOR THOSE FINAL DEVICES WHICH SUPPORT IT SUCH AS THE   LP
)@@G@@@#@@@@"  PHOTON 7445.   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@"  EXTRA SPACES ARE INSERTED BLQ
)@@G@@ETWEEN WORDS IN ONE PASS STARTING FROM    @G@@@@"  THE LEFT OR RIGHT MOSLR
)@@G@@T CHARACTER ON ALTERNATE TEXT LINES JUSTIFIED.  @G@@@@"  IT RELIES ON A LS
)@@G@@TABLE OF THE POSITIONS OF SPACE-BANDS BUILT AS THE    @C@@@@"  WORDS WERLT
)@@G@@E ADDED TO FORM THE FINAL LINE.     @[@@@@"     @[@@@@      @A@@@@      LU
)@@G@@    COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED)LV
)@@G@@;     @D@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED); " ***DEBUG   @B@@@@LW
)@@G@@          COPY ('CHAR-SIZE',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('CARD-DELX
)@@G@@F',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CONTROL-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@LY
)@@G@@          COPY ('PRINT-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('STAGINGLZ
)@@G@@-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-COMMON',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@MA
)@@G@@          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @A@@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTEDMB
)@@G@@; " ***DEBUG@[@@@@"     @^@@@@DEFINE    NUM\TRIES = 3;@D@@@@DECLARE   WOMC
)@@G@@RD\MAX(NUM\TRIES): REAL WORD STATIC :=    @A@@@@           [0.375, 0.437MD
)@@G@@5, 0.4999 ];@D@@@@DECLARE   LET\MAX(NUM\TRIES): REAL WORD STATIC :=     ME
)@@G@@@B@@@@           [ 0.03125, 0.0625, 0.09375 ];  @A@@@@DECLARE   LETW: WOMF
)@@G@@RD INTEGER STATIC;@C@@@@DECLARE   LLR: DISTANCE; " LINE LENGTH REMAINDERMG
)@@G@@@C@@@@DECLARE   BLANKS\TO\ADD: WORD INTEGER STATIC;   @C@@@@DECLARE   NOMH
)@@G@@T\FOUND: 6 BIT CONDITION STATIC;    @[@@@@      @[@@@@"     @B@@@@"  JUSMI
)@@G@@TIFY THE LINE IF REQUESTED TO DO SO @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE JUSTIFY\MJ
)@@G@@THE\LINE EXPORTED ('JUSTIFYLINE')   @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      @B@@@@DECLARMK
)@@G@@E   BLANKS\PER\POS: WORD INTEGER,   @B@@@@          FIRST\COLUMN: WORD IML
)@@G@@NTEGER,     @A@@@@          LAST\COLUMN: WORD INTEGER,@ @@@@          PTMM
)@@G@@R: WORD INTEGER,  @ @@@@          TRY: WORD INTEGER,  @ @@@@          CHMN
)@@G@@ARS: WORD INTEGER,@ @@@@          INC: WORD INTEGER;  @[@@@@      @C@@@@MO
)@@G@@          IF NUM\BLANKS LE 0 OR NOT JUSTIFY THEN@^@@@@             RETURMP
)@@G@@N;    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" JUSTIFY BY BLANK FILLING FROM ALTERNATE ENDS OMQ
)@@G@@F THE LINE  @B@@@@" AS DETERMINED BY JUSTIFY\FROM\RIGHT     @[@@@@"     MR
)@@G@@@G@@@@          LLR := MAX\WIDTH - LINE\WIDTH; " COMPUTE LINE LENGTH REMMS
)@@G@@AINDER@D@@@@          BLANKS\TO\ADD := LLR // UNIT\INTERNAL\WIDTH;@A@@@@MT
)@@G@@          IF LLR // NUM\BLANKS GT   @F@@@@             MAX\WORD\SPACE*COMU
)@@G@@LUMN\DISTANCE THEN " CANNOT JUSTIFY @B@@@@           BEGIN " POSSIBLE LEMV
)@@G@@TTER SPACING@E@@@@             BLANKS\TO\ADD := 0; " INHIBIT JUSTIFICATIMW
)@@G@@ON    @G@@@@             IF DEVICE\LETTER\SPACES THEN " TRY LETTER SPACIMX
)@@G@@NG ALGORITHM@^@@@@              BEGIN     @H@@@@                CHARS :=MY
)@@G@@ LINE\INDEX-NUM\FUNCTIONS-NUM\BLANKS-LAST\FIXED\POS-1;@D@@@@            MZ
)@@G@@    LETW := CHARS * UNIT\INTERNAL\SPACE;  @A@@@@                NOT\FOUNNA
)@@G@@D := TRUE;  @ @@@@                TRY := 0;     @E@@@@                WHNB
)@@G@@ILE TRY LT NUM\TRIES AND NOT\FOUND DO     @^@@@@                 BEGIN  NC
)@@G@@@D@@@@                   TRY := TRY + 1; " GO TO NEXT TRY   @G@@@@      ND
)@@G@@             TRY\LETTER\SPACING(TRY); " ATTEMPT LETTER SPACING    @E@@@@NE
)@@G@@                 END; " LOOPING OVER LETTER SPACE TRIES     @B@@@@      NF
)@@G@@        END; " DOING LETTER SPACING @C@@@@           END; " CHECK FOR NONG
)@@G@@T JUSTIFIABLE     @D@@@@          IF BLANKS\TO\ADD LT 0 THEN " PRINT MESNH
)@@G@@SAGE  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             WARNING(W\JUSTIFY\ERRORNI
)@@G@@);    @ @@@@             PRINT\INPUT\CARD;@D@@@@             BLANKS\TO\ANJ
)@@G@@DD := 0; " DO NOT JUSTIFY     @#@@@@           END;   @E@@@@          BLNK
)@@G@@ANKS\PER\POS := BLANKS\TO\ADD // NUM\BLANKS;    @H@@@@          BLANKS\TNL
)@@G@@O\ADD := MOD (BLANKS\TO\ADD, NUM\BLANKS); " GET REMAINDER   @E@@@@      NM
)@@G@@    IF BLANKS\PER\POS NE 0 OR BLANKS\TO\ADD NE 0 THEN @#@@@@           BNN
)@@G@@EGIN  @B@@@@             IF JUSTIFY\FROM\RIGHT THEN   @^@@@@            NO
)@@G@@  BEGIN     @C@@@@                FIRST\COLUMN := NUM\BLANKS;     @A@@@@NP
)@@G@@                LAST\COLUMN := 1;   @ @@@@                INC := -1;    NQ
)@@G@@@#@@@@              END;@#@@@@             ELSE @^@@@@              BEGINR
)@@G@@N     @A@@@@                FIRST\COLUMN := 1;  @B@@@@                LANS
)@@G@@ST\COLUMN := NUM\BLANKS;@ @@@@                INC := 1;     @#@@@@      NT
)@@G@@        END;@E@@@@             JUSTIFY\FROM\RIGHT := NOT JUSTIFY\FROM\RINU
)@@G@@GHT;  @E@@@@             FOR I := FIRST\COLUMN BY INC TO LAST\COLUMN DO NV
)@@G@@@^@@@@              BEGIN     @C@@@@                PTR := SPACEBAND\LOCNW
)@@G@@ATION(I);   @F@@@@                LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(PTR) := LINE\CHAR\WIDTNX
)@@G@@H(PTR) +    @E@@@@                   UNIT\INTERNAL\WIDTH * BLANKS\PER\PONY
)@@G@@S;    @B@@@@                IF BLANKS\TO\ADD > 0 THEN @^@@@@            NZ
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @F@@@@                   LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(PTR) := LINE\CHAR\WOA
)@@G@@IDTH(PTR) + @B@@@@                    UNIT\INTERNAL\WIDTH;  @D@@@@      OB
)@@G@@             BLANKS\TO\ADD := BLANKS\TO\ADD - 1;@C@@@@                 EOC
)@@G@@ND; " ADD REMAINDER BLANKS    @A@@@@              END;  " OF FOR LOOP   OD
)@@G@@@C@@@@           END;  " OF IF BLANKS\PER\POS ...     @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@OE
)@@G@@"     @A@@@@" PROCEDURE TO TRY LETTER SPACING   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDOF
)@@G@@URE TRY\LETTER\SPACING(TRY: WORD INTEGER) @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@DECLARE LETSOG
)@@G@@: WORD INTEGER; " NUMBER OF LETTERS FOR LETTER SPACING@[@@@@"     @G@@@@OH
)@@G@@          LETS := (LET\MAX(TRY)*COLUMN\DISTANCE)//UNIT\INTERNAL\SPACE;  OI
)@@G@@@ @@@@          IF LETS GT 0 AND    @H@@@@             (LETS*LETW+COLUMNOJ
)@@G@@\DISTANCE*MAX\WORD\SPACE*NUM\BLANKS) GE LLR AND @H@@@@             (LETSOK
)@@G@@*LETW+COLUMN\DISTANCE*WORD\MAX(TRY)*NUM\BLANKS) GE LLR THEN @#@@@@      OL
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @G@@@@             LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(LETSP\POS) := LETS * UNITOM
)@@G@@\INTERNAL\SPACE;  @G@@@@             BLANKS\TO\ADD := (LLR-LETS*LETW)//UON
)@@G@@NIT\INTERNAL\WIDTH;     @A@@@@             NOT\FOUND := FALSE;    @B@@@@OO
)@@G@@           END; " ADDING LETTER SPACING   @A@@@@END; " PROCEDURE TRY\LETOP
)@@G@@TER\SPACING @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@@C@@@@"  WORDS WERE ADDED TO FORM THE FINAOQ
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS MODULE IS RESPONSOR
)@@G@@IBLE FOR FORMATING THE TEXT ON A PAGE     @G@@@@" IT COULD PROBABLY BE COS
)@@G@@ONSIDERED THE HEART OF DPS.  IT MUST GET THE    @F@@@@" NEXT WORD FROM TOT
)@@G@@HE TEXT AND PLACE IT IN THE OUTPUT BUFFER.  WHEN@G@@@@" THE BUFFER IS FUOU
)@@G@@LL IT MUST CALL THE END OF LINE ROUTINES.  IT MUST    @D@@@@" ALSO BE WAOV
)@@G@@RY OF EMBEDDED MACRO CALLS AND DIRECTIVES.@[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COOW
)@@G@@PY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@D@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED); "OX
)@@G@@$$$DEBUG    @B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@      OY
)@@G@@    COPY ('BREAK-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPOZ
)@@G@@ORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CHKPT-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@      PA
)@@G@@    COPY ('CONTROL-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('DIRECT-DEF',IPB
)@@G@@MPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('DIRECT-PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@      PC
)@@G@@    COPY ('FD-PROCS',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('GETPUT-PROCS'PD
)@@G@@,IMPORTED); @A@@@@          COPY ('IO-DEF1',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPE
)@@G@@PY ('PACKET-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('PUSH-PROCS',IMPORTEPF
)@@G@@D);   @B@@@@          COPY ('STAGING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPG
)@@G@@PY ('SYMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('TITLE-DEF',IMPORTEDPH
)@@G@@);    @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPI
)@@G@@PY ('UNIT-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-COMMON',IMPORTPJ
)@@G@@ED);  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE CLOSE\TOC IMPORTED ('CLSTOC'); " TOC  PK
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\ACTION\TABLE IMPORTED ('INITACTIOPL
)@@G@@N');  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\OUTPUT\LINE IMPORTED ('INITPM
)@@G@@OUTLINE');  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\ENDKEEP IMPORTED ('ENDKEPN
)@@G@@EP'); @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE SEARCH\VPOS(ITEM: DISTANCE, HEAD: WORDPO
)@@G@@ MACHINE    @C@@@@           POINTER) IMPORTED ('SEARCHEQUS');    @[@@@@PP
)@@G@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE RELEASE\AT\CARD(AT: WORD INTEGER) IMPORTED ('RELATPQ
)@@G@@CARD$RS');  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE FILL\AREA IMPORTED ('FILLAREA');PR
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\DIRECTIVE IMPORTED ('PRODIR');@[@@@@PS
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE FORCE\END\OF\LINE IMPORTED ('FOREOL');@[@@@@"     PT
)@@G@@@C@@@@PROCEDURE OPEN\UNIT\INPUT IMPORTED ('OPENUI');  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PU
)@@G@@PROCEDURE CLOSE\UNIT\INPUT IMPORTED ('CLOSUI'); @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDPV
)@@G@@URE FORCE\END\OF\PAGE IMPORTED ('FOREOP'); " END-OF-PAGE    @[@@@@"     PW
)@@G@@@F@@@@DECLARE   SPACE\REMAINING: STATIC WORD INTEGER IMPORTED ('SPR')   PX
)@@G@@@E@@@@          ,CHARS\THIS\LINE: STATIC 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER  @C@@@@PY
)@@G@@                            IMPORTED ('CTL')    @E@@@@          ,CHARS\NPZ
)@@G@@EXT\LINE: STATIC 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER  @C@@@@                        QA
)@@G@@    IMPORTED ('CNL');   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@DECLARE   *: MAPPED BASED     QB
)@@G@@@C@@@@           [BACK\LINK: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER   @C@@@@           ,QC
)@@G@@FORWARD\LINK: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER@^@@@@           ,*: DISTANCE @^@@@@QD
)@@G@@           ,*: DISTANCE @C@@@@           ,VPOS\CARD: WORD MACHINE POINTEQE
)@@G@@R     @#@@@@             ];   @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@QF
)@@G@@"  * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *QG
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE FORMAT\UNITS  @D@@@@             (FIRST: WORQH
)@@G@@D INTEGER " FIRST UNIT TO DO  @D@@@@             ,LAST:  WORD INTEGER " QI
)@@G@@LAST UNIT TO DO   @A@@@@             ) EXPORTED ('FORMAT')  @[@@@@BEGIN QJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@          INITIALIZE\ACTION\TABLE; " $$$TEMP    @[@@@@QK
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@" RELEASE ANY OLD AT'S  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          FOR AT :QL
)@@G@@= 1 TO NUM\ATS DO @#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             IF AT\PTRS(QM
)@@G@@AT) NE NULL\PTR THEN    @A@@@@                RELEASE\AT\CARD(AT);@#@@@@QN
)@@G@@           END;   @D@@@@          PENDING\AT := 0;         " CLEAR ALL DQO
)@@G@@O\AT'S@[@@@@"     @A@@@@" $$$ END OF THINGS TO CHECKPOINT   @[@@@@"     QP
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @G@@@@" SET UP DPS FOR TAKE.  THESE THINGS MUST BE INITIALIZQQ
)@@G@@ED INDEPENDANT    @F@@@@" OF UNITS.  SHOULD BE SUBROUTINIZED SOMEDAY... QR
)@@G@@(KERN TAKE NOTE). @[@@@@"     @F@@@@          INITIALIZE\OUTPUT\LINE;   QS
)@@G@@  " START NEW OUTPUT LINE     @I@@@@          FIRST\PAGE := TRUE;       QT
)@@G@@  " CAUSE PAGEUP AFTER FIRST TEXT WORD SCANNED  @E@@@@          PAGE\EMPQU
)@@G@@TY := TRUE;         " FIRST PAGE IS EMPTY @F@@@@          COLUMN\EMPTY :QV
)@@G@@= TRUE;       " FIRST COLUMN IS EMPTY TOO @D@@@@          FUNC\PENDING :QW
)@@G@@= 0; " CLEAR GET-WORD FUNCTION@E@@@@          NUM\EOL\FUNCTIONS := 0; " QX
)@@G@@CLEAR EOL-FUNCTIONS     @A@@@@          END\OF\INPUT\CARD := TRUE;@A@@@@QY
)@@G@@          BUFFER\TEXT := FALSE;     @B@@@@          INCLUDE\ALL\FLOATS :QZ
)@@G@@= FALSE;    @B@@@@          INHIBIT\DISTRIBUTION := FALSE;  @B@@@@      RA
)@@G@@    TRANSPARENT\OUTPUT := FALSE;    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" READ IN FIRST CHRB
)@@G@@ECKPOINT ALWAYS.  MUST BE BEFORE ASSEMBLY INIT. @[@@@@"     @A@@@@      RC
)@@G@@    READ\UNIT\CKPT(FIRST);    @B@@@@          INITIALIZE\FINAL\DEVICE\HARD
)@@G@@NDLER;+@@@@[+@@@@@@F@@@@          PROCESS\START\OF\TAKE;      " INITIALIRE
)@@G@@ZE START OF TAKE  @D@@@@          INITIALIZE\WORD\ASSEMBLY;  " START NEWRF
)@@G@@ WORD @D@@@@          INITIALIZE\LINE\ASSEMBLY; " START NEW LINE  @[@@@@RG
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@" IF FORMATTING TAKE ALL ACTIONS NECESSARY TO RELEASE THE OLRH
)@@G@@D     @F@@@@" TEXT SPACE AND CREATE NEW TEXT SPACE AND A NEW UNIT DIRECTRI
)@@G@@ORY.  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          IF FORMATTING THEN  @C@@@@           BRJ
)@@G@@EGIN " SETUP FOR FORMAT PROCESS     @G@@@@             GLOBAL\SYMBOLS :=RK
)@@G@@ RELEASE\SYMBOL\TABLE(GLOBAL\SYMBOLS);    @G[@@@             READ\AND\RERL
)@@G@@LEASE(GET\PACKET) := TRUE; " RELEASE OLD TEXT   @B@@@@             OPEN\RM
)@@G@@NEW\UNIT\DIRECTORY;     @C@@@@             OPEN\NEXT\NEW\UNIT; " OPEN UNRN
)@@G@@IT ONE@B@@@@           END; " SETUP FOR FORMAT PROCESS@[[@@@"     @A@@@@RO
)@@G@@" NOW FORMAT THE REQUESTED UNITS.   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          CURRENT\RP
)@@G@@UNIT := FIRST; " SET FIRST UNIT     @E@@@@          WHILE CURRENT\UNIT LRQ
)@@G@@E LAST AND NOT REMOTE\BREAK DO@ @@@@           BEGIN " FORMAT UNIT@ [@@@RR
)@@G@@             OPEN\UNIT\INPUT; @E@@@@             WHILE NOT (END\OF\UNIT RS
)@@G@@OR REMOTE\BREAK) DO     @ @@@@                FORMAT\AREA;  @F@@@@      RT
)@@G@@       CLOSE\UNIT\INPUT;        " CLOSE INPUT ON THIS ONE   @H@@@@      RU
)@@G@@       GET\NEXT\REAL\UNIT;      " SET CURRENT\UNIT TO NEXT UNIT NUMBER  RV
)@@G@@@ @@@@           END; " UNIT FORMAT @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" IF FORMATTING PORW
)@@G@@ST NEW UNIT DIRECTORY   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          IF FORMATTING THEN  RX
)@@G@@@A@@@@           BEGIN " CLOSE FORMAT     @D[@@@             READ\AND\RERY
)@@G@@LEASE(GET\PACKET) := FALSE;   @B@@@@             CLOSE\PREVIOUS\NEW\UNITRZ
)@@G@@;     @A@@@@             IF REMOTE\BREAK THEN   @D@@@@                ABSA
)@@G@@ORT\NEW\UNIT\DIRECTORY; " AS ITS BAD@#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@      SB
)@@G@@        BEGIN " ACCEPT FORMAT @B[@@@                POST\NEW\UNIT\DIRECTSC
)@@G@@ORY;  @A@@@@                WRITE\GLOBAL\CKPT;  @A@@@@              END;SD
)@@G@@ " ACCEPT FORMAT  @ @@@@           END; " CLOSE FORMAT@^]@@@          CLSE
)@@G@@OSE\TOC;    @C@@@@          OUTPUT\NEXT\WORD; " PUSH OUT LAST WORD@G@@@@SF
)@@G@@          FORCE\END\OF\LINE;          " FORCE OUT LAST LINE NO JUSTIFY  SG
)@@G@@@B@@@@          INCLUDE\ALL\FLOATS := TRUE;     @ @@@@          PROCESS\SH
)@@G@@ENDKEEP;    @E@@@@          FORCE\END\OF\PAGE;          " OUTPUT LAST PASI
)@@G@@GE    @ @@@@          PROCESS\END\OF\TAKE;@F@@@@          POP\PUSHED\ICBSJ
)@@G@@S;            " REMOVE ANY LEFTOVER CARDS @H@@@@          CLOSE\UNIT\INPSK
)@@G@@UT; " REMOVE LEFTOVER MACROS, INPUT PACKETS, AND CARDS@#@@@@END; " OF FOSL
)@@G@@RMAT  @[@@@@"     @G@@@@"  * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *SM
)@@G@@ * * * * * * * * * * * *@[@@@@"     @G@@@@"  * * * * * * * * * * * * * *SN
)@@G@@ * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" THIS PROCESO
)@@G@@DURE IS CALLED TO FORMAT AN AREA.   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE FORMAT\ASP
)@@G@@REA   @[@@@@BEGIN @^@@@@          FILL\AREA; "  @ @@@@          IF END\OSQ
)@@G@@F\AREA THEN @F@@@@           BEGIN                      " TO CHECK WHY ASR
)@@G@@REA ENDED   @A@@@@             IF ATVPOS\REACHED THEN @D@@@@            SS
)@@G@@  BEGIN                   " ATVPOS CODE   @B@@@@                ATVPOS\RST
)@@G@@EACHED := FALSE;  @B@@@@" PUT VPOS EQUATE INTO THE STREAM HERE    @ @@@@SU
)@@G@@" NOT YET IMPLEMENTED !!!!    @B@@@@                END\OF\AREA := FALSESV
)@@G@@;     @D@@@@                NEXT\VPOS := FORWARD\LINK(NEXT\VPOS); @A@@@@SW
)@@G@@              END; " ATVPOS CODE    @#@@@@             ELSE @E@@@@      SX
)@@G@@        BEGIN                   " TOP OF PAGE CODE    @A@@@@            SY
)@@G@@    FORCE\END\OF\PAGE;  @F@@@@                SEARCH\VPOS(VERTICAL\POSITSZ
)@@G@@ION,LOC(ATVPOS\HEAD));  @D@@@@                NEXT\VPOS := FORWARD\LINK(TA
)@@G@@INSERT\PTR);@B@@@@              END; " TOP OF PAGE CODE     @A@@@@      TB
)@@G@@     END; " END OF AREA CODE  @^@@@@END; " OF FORMAT\AREA   @[@@@@"     TC
)@@G@@@G@@@@"  * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *TD
)@@G@@ * * *@[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@DE    @A@@@@                FORCE\ENTE
)@@G@@D\OF\PAGE;  @F@@@@                SEARCH\VPOS(VERTICAL\POSITION,LOC(ATVPTF
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);TG
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('FILE-CVT-DEF',IMPORTED); @A@@@@          COPY ('ITH
)@@G@@O-DEF1',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('IO-PROCS',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@TI
)@@G@@          COPY ('BLOCK-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('FILE-HDTJ
)@@G@@R-DEF',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('PACKET-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@TK
)@@G@@          COPY ('RUN-DATA-DEF',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('WARNINGTL
)@@G@@-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED;     @#@@@@TM
)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@DEFINE    COPYSIZE = 16; " SECTORS  TN
)@@G@@@A@@@@DEFINE    COPYWORDS = 16*28; " WORDS@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE COTO
)@@G@@NVERT\LEVEL2\TO\LEVEL3 IMPORTED ('CVTL23');     @E@@@@PROCEDURE CONVERT\TP
)@@G@@LEVEL4\TO\LEVEL5 IMPORTED ('CVTL45');     @[@@@@"     @H@@@@DECLARE   BATQ
)@@G@@SIN: STATIC INTEGER WORD IMPORTED('INDAD'); " INPUT BASE ADDRES   @G@@@@TR
)@@G@@DECLARE   INIO: STATIC LOCATABLE INTEGER WORD IMPORTED , " IOPACKETS    TS
)@@G@@@E@@@@          OUTIO: STATIC LOCATABLE INTEGER WORD IMPORTED;    @[@@@@TT
)@@G@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE COPY\BLOCK(DRUM: INTEGER WORD)  @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@TU
)@@G@@          DRUM\ADDR(CUR\PKT) := CUR\BAS + DRUM; " SET DRUM ADDR   @B@@@@TV
)@@G@@          IOWWEC(CUR\PKT); " READ AND WAIT@C@@@@          WAITEC(NXT\PKTTW
)@@G@@); " WAIT FOR LAST WRITE@C@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR(CUR\PKT) :=:  " SWITTX
)@@G@@CH    @C@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR(NXT\PKT);     " BUFFERS   @E@@@@      TY
)@@G@@    DRUM\ADDR(NXT\PKT) := DRUM; " SET DRUM ADDRESS    @B@@@@          IOTZ
)@@G@@(NXT\PKT); " WRITE AND NO WAIT@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" DOUBLE BUFUA
)@@G@@FERED COPY ROUTINE.  BLOX ARE COPIED BACKWARDS  @D@@@@" AS IT IS EASIER.UB
)@@G@@  THIS IS KNOWN AS 'BACKTRACKING' . @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE COPY\CURUC
)@@G@@RENT\LEVEL  @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@DECLARE   SECTOR: INTEGER WORD;     @B@@@@UD
)@@G@@          WORD\COUNT(CUR\PKT):=COPYWORDS; @B@@@@          WORD\COUNT(NXTUE
)@@G@@\PKT):=COPYWORDS; @E@@@@          SECTOR:=TRACKS\IN\FILE+1; " COUNT SECTUF
)@@G@@OR ZERO     @D@@@@          WHILE SECTOR GT COPYSIZE DO " LAST COPY     UG
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @G@@@@             SECTOR:=SECTOR-COPYSIZE; " DEUH
)@@G@@CREMENT NUMBER OF SECTORS     @D@@@@             COPY\BLOCK(SECTOR); " DUI
)@@G@@O STANDARD SIZE   @#@@@@           END;   @E@@@@          WAITEC(NXT\PKTUJ
)@@G@@); " WAIT BEFORE CHANGING PACKET    @B@@@@          WORD\COUNT(CUR\PKT):UK
)@@G@@=SECTOR*28; @B@@@@          WORD\COUNT(NXT\PKT):=SECTOR*28; @D@@@@      UL
)@@G@@    COPY\BLOCK(0); " COPY REMAINING SECTORS     @D@@@@          WAITEC(NUM
)@@G@@XT\PKT); " WAIT FOR FINAL WRITE     @[@@@@END;  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   UN
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED TO EXAMINE THE SCRIPT ABOUNT UO
)@@G@@TO BE READ  @G@@@@" AND CONVERT TO CURRENT LEVEL IF NECESSARY.  IT IS DEUP
)@@G@@SIGNED SO THAT    @G@@@@" AS THE DPS SCRIPT FORMAT GROWS, CONVERTERS CANUQ
)@@G@@ BE WRITTEN TO TRANSLATE@F@@@@" TO THE NEXT LEVEL UP, AND IN THE WORST CUR
)@@G@@ASE THEY WILL BE CALLED @D@@@@" SEQUENTIALLY TO CONVERT UP TO THE CURRENUS
)@@G@@T LEVEL.    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE CONVERT\FILE\LEVEL EXPORTED('CVTUT
)@@G@@FLV') @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          CUR\PKT:=LOC(INIO); " SET POINTERS    UU
)@@G@@@D@@@@          CUR\BAS := BASIN; " SET BASE DRUM ADDRESS   @[@@@@"     UV
)@@G@@@C@@@@          NXT\PKT:=LOC(OUTIO); " TO PACKETS     @D@@@@          FIUW
)@@G@@LE\NAME1(NXT\PKT) := DPS\SCRATCH\NAME(1); @D@@@@          FILE\NAME2(NXTUX
)@@G@@\PKT) := DPS\SCRATCH\NAME(2); @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" LOOP CONVERTING UNTIL UY
)@@G@@CONVERTED TO CURRENT LEVEL.   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          WHILE NOT DPS\UZ
)@@G@@ABORT AND   @D@@@@             (FILE\HEADER\LEVEL NE DPS\FILE\LEVEL) DO VA
)@@G@@@A@@@@           BEGIN " CONVERSION PASS  @E@@@@             INITIALIZE\VB
)@@G@@FILE\ALLOCATOR; " CLEAR BITMAPS     @E@@@@             WARNING(W\CONV\LEVC
)@@G@@VEL); " WARN HIM WHATS HAPNIN @B@@@@             CASEENTRY FILE\HEADER\LVD
)@@G@@EVEL  @C@@@@             CASE 2: CONVERT\LEVEL2\TO\LEVEL3;  @E@@@@      VE
)@@G@@       CASE 3: FILE\HEADER\LEVEL := 4; " NO CONVERSION@C@@@@            VF
)@@G@@ CASE 4: CONVERT\LEVEL4\TO\LEVEL5;  @^@@@@             CASE *:    @C@@@@VG
)@@G@@              BEGIN " TO HANDLE UNKNOWN LEVEL   @B@@@@                WAVH
)@@G@@RNING(W\BAD\LEVEL);     @D@@@@                DPS\ABORT := TRUE; " SET FVI
)@@G@@LAG TO ABORT@B@@@@              END; " OF UNKNOWN FILE LEVEL@^@@@@      VJ
)@@G@@       ENDCASE;   @B@@@@           END; " OF LOOP OVER FILE LEVELS@E@@@@VK
)@@G@@          IF NOT DPS\ABORT AND CUR\PKT NE LOC(OUTIO) THEN   @A@@@@      VL
)@@G@@     BEGIN " WRONG FILE COPY  @A@@@@             COPY\CURRENT\LEVEL;    VM
)@@G@@@A@@@@           END; " WRONG FILE COPY   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@VN
)@@G@@" WHEN AN ACTUAL CONVERTER IS FINISHED IT SHOULD CALL THIS ROUTINE@G@@@@VO
)@@G@@" TO SWITCH FILES, SETTING UP FOR THE NEXT CONVERTER.  NOTE THAT THE    VP
)@@G@@@F@@@@" CONVERTER **MUST** SET FILE\HEADER\LEVEL TO THE CORRECT VALUE ORVQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@" THE LOOP ABOVE WILL NEVER TERMINATE.    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDVR
)@@G@@URE SWITCH\FILES  @ @@@@          EXPORTED ('CVTSWT') @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@VS
)@@G@@          CUR\PKT :=: NXT\PKT; " SWITCH PACKETS @ @@@@          IF CUR\BVT
)@@G@@AS NE 0 THEN@C@@@@           BEGIN " USING SECOND SCRATCH FILE    @B@@@@VU
)@@G@@             CUR\BAS := 0; " CLEAR BASE   @F@@@@             FILE\NAME1(VV
)@@G@@NXT\PKT) := 0; " TEMP FORCE ERROR LATER   @D@@@@"            FILE\NAME1(VW
)@@G@@NXT\PKT) := ED\CALL\NAME(1);  @D@@@@"            FILE\NAME2(NXT\PKT) := VX
)@@G@@ED\CALL\NAME(2);  @C@@@@           END; " USING SECOND SCRATCH FILE     VY
)@@G@@@^@@@@END; " OF SWITCH\FILES  @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@E     @^@@@@END; " OF SWVZ
)@@G@@ITCH\FILES  @[@@@@TERM; *[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @A@@@@          COWA
)@@G@@PY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('BLOCK-PROCS',IMPORTED);  WB
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @C@@@@   COPY ('DEBUG-PRWC
)@@G@@OCS',IMPORTED); " *****DEBUG  @B@@@@          COPY ('DIRECT-PROCS',IMPORWD
)@@G@@TED); @B@@@@          COPY ('EDITOR-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COWE
)@@G@@PY ('FILE-HDR-DEF',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('FILE-PROCS',IMPORTEWF
)@@G@@D);   @B@@@@          COPY ('HEADER-PROCS',IMPORTED); @A@@@@          COWG
)@@G@@PY ('IO-DEF1',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('PIO-PROCS',IMPORTED);    WH
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('IO-PROCS',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('UWI
)@@G@@NIT-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('PACKET-DEF',IMPORTED);   WJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED;             " ****DEBUG     WK
)@@G@@@@@@@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\OUTPUT\PACKET IMPORTED ('INITOP');     WL

)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @G@@@@" GET TEXT FROM EDITOR SCRATCH FILE AND PUT BACK IN DPWR

)@@G@@@ @@@@          (START: WORD INTEGER@ @@@@          ,LAST: WORD INTEGER)WT
)@@G@@@ @@@@           EXPORTED ('REPUFE')@[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          INITIALIWU
)@@G@@ZE\EDITOR\PACKET; @C@@@@          FUNCTION(ED\PACKET) := IO\FUNC\READ;  WV
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@          PSDFIO(ED\PACKET);  @ @@@@          PSDFOO(PWW
)@@G@@UT\PACKET); @]@@@@REPLOOP:    @ @@@@          PSDFI(ED\PACKET);   @E@@@@WX

)@@G@@     BEGIN  @F@@@@             CONTROL\WORD(PUT\PACKET) := CONTROL\WORD(WZ

)@@G@@\PACKET;    @A@@@@END; " REPLACE\UNITS\FROM\EDITOR    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@XK
)@@G@@" GET UNITS FROM DPS FILE AND BUILD SDF FILE FOR EDITOR     @[@@@@"     XL
)@@G@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE GET\UNITS\FOR\EDITOR (START: WORD INTEGER, LAST:  @C@@@@XM
)@@G@@           WORD INTEGER) EXPORTED ('GETUFE')    @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@      XN
)@@G@@    IF LAST > NUMBER\OF\UNITS THEN " ****DEBUG  @D@@@@             ERRORXO
)@@G@@;                   " ****DEBUG     @A@@@@          INITIALIZE\EDITOR\PAXP
)@@G@@CKET; @C@@@@          FUNCTION(ED\PACKET) := IO\FUNC\WRITE; @ @@@@      XQ
)@@G@@    PSDFOO(ED\PACKET);  @H@@@@          CONTROL\WORD(ED\PACKET) := O'420XR
)@@G@@000000001'; " ASCII SWITCH FOR ED   @C@@@@          PSDFO(ED\PACKET);   XS
)@@G@@        " WRITE IT@H@@@@          PSDFIC(GET\PACKET);         " CLOSE ANXT
)@@G@@Y POSIBLE INPUT ON GET\PACKET @H@@@@          READ\AND\RELEASE(GET\PACKEXU
)@@G@@T) := TRUE; " CONDITIONAL RELEASE AS READ @A@@@@          CURRENT\UNIT :XV
)@@G@@= START;    @G@@@@          WHILE CURRENT\UNIT LE LAST DO " LOOP OVER ALXW
)@@G@@L UNITS REQUESTED @#@@@@           BEGIN  @ @@@@             OPEN\UNIT\IXX
)@@G@@NPUT; @]@@@@GETLOOP:    @A@@@@             PSDFI(GET\PACKET);     @F@@@@XY
)@@G@@             IF NOT END\FILE(GET\PACKET) THEN " OUTPUT AND LOOP   @^@@@@XZ

)@@G@@@ @@@@                GOTO GETLOOP; @#@@@@              END;@ @@@@" END YC

)@@G@@     END; " OF LOOP OVER ALL UNITS  @D@@@@          PSDFOC(ED\PACKET);  YF
)@@G@@        " CLOSE OUTPUT  @I@@@@          READ\AND\RELEASE(GET\PACKET) := YG
)@@G@@FALSE; " TURN OFF CONDITIONAL RELEASE     @A@@@@          RELEASE\EDITORYH
)@@G@@\PACKET;    @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" INITIALIZE THE EDITOR'S I/O YI
)@@G@@PACKET@[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\EDITOR\PACKET  @[@@@@BEGIN YJ

)@@G@@    INITIALIZE\FILE(%ED\PACKET,%BUFFER,0);@D@@@@          FILE\NAME1(ED\YM

)@@G@@@E@@@@          DRUM\ADDR(ED\PACKET) := 0; " ALWAYS SECTOR ZERO   @[@@@@YP
)@@G@@END;  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" PROCEDURE TO RELEASE THE EDITOR PACKET  @[@@@@YQ

)@@G@@    RELEASE\FILE\BUFFERS(ED\PACKET);@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" GET YT
)@@G@@UNITS FROM DPS SCRATCH FILE AND BUILD PACKET OUTPUT FILE    @[@@@@"     YU
)@@G@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE COPY\TEXT\TO\OUTPUT\FILE EXPORTED ('CTTOF') @[@@@@BEGIN YV
)@@G@@@A@@@@          INITIALIZE\OUTPUT\PACKET; @E@@@@          INITIALIZE\FILYW
)@@G@@E\ALLOCATOR; " START WITH FRESH FILE@G@@@@          BASE\DRUM\ADDR(LOC(GYX
)@@G@@ENPKT)) := INITIAL\OUTPUT\DRUM\ADDRESS;   @G@@@@          BASE\DRUM\ADDRYY
)@@G@@(PUT\PACKET) := INITIAL\OUTPUT\DRUM\ADDRESS; "  @G@@@@          BASE\DRUYZ
)@@G@@M\ADDR(BIT\PACKET) := INITIAL\OUTPUT\DRUM\ADDRESS; "  @B@@@@          FOZA
)@@G@@R I:= 1 TO NUMBER\OF\UNITS DO @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@            ZB
)@@G@@ IF REAL\UNIT(I) THEN   @C@@@@              BEGIN " COPY AND UPDATE FILEZC
)@@G@@S     @G@@@@                UPDATE\DIRECTORY\DRUM\ADDRESS(I, COPY\LINKEDZD
)@@G@@\BLOCKS(    @D@@@@                   GET\DIRECTORY\DRUM\ADDRESS(I)));   ZE
)@@G@@@G@@@@                UPDATE\DIRECTORY\CKPT\ADDRESS(I, COPY\LINKED\BLOCKZF
)@@G@@S(    @D@@@@                   GET\DIRECTORY\CKPT\ADDRESS(I)));   @B@@@@ZG
)@@G@@              END; " COPY AND UPDATE FILES@#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@ZH
)@@G@@          WRITE\UNIT\DIRECTORY;     @A@@@@          LINK\TO\UNIT\DIRECTOZI
)@@G@@RY := @E@@@@             COPY\LINKED\BLOCKS(LINK\TO\UNIT\DIRECTORY);    ZJ
)@@G@@@A@@@@          HEADER\GLOBAL\CKPT :=     @D@@@@             COPY\LINKEDZK
)@@G@@\BLOCKS(HEADER\GLOBAL\CKPT);  @C@@@@          LINK\TO\TOC := 0; " DO NOTZL
)@@G@@ SAVE TOC   @A@@@@          LINK\TO\FILE\BIT\MAP := 0;@A@@@@          FOZM
)@@G@@RCE\WRITE\OF\BIT\MAPS;  @G@@@@          MAXIMUM\OUTPUT\DRUM\ADDRESS := MZN
)@@G@@AX\ALLOCATED\FILE\BLOCK +     @B@@@@             INITIAL\OUTPUT\DRUM\ADDZO
)@@G@@RESS; @D@@@@          TRACKS\IN\FILE := MAX\ALLOCATED\FILE\BLOCK; @ @@@@ZP
)@@G@@          WRITE\FILE\HEADER;  @ @@@@          INSERT\NEW\ELEMENT; @[@@@@ZQ
)@@G@@END;  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" COPY LINKED UNITS USING DOUBLE BUFFERED I/O   ZR
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE COPY\LINKED\BLOCKS(LINK: WORD INTEGER)@ @@@@ZS
)@@G@@           RESULT WORD INTEGER@[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          IF LINK EQ 0 TZT
)@@G@@HEN   @^@@@@             RETURN(0); @ @@@@          WAIT(PUT\PACKET);   ZU
)@@G@@@ @@@@          WAIT(GET\PACKET);   @F@@@@          DRUM\ADDR(GET\PACKETZV
)@@G@@) := LINK; " BEGIN DRUM ADDRESS     @D@@@@          PSDFIO(GET\PACKET); ZW
)@@G@@" READ FIRST BUFFER     @C@@@@          PSDFOO(PUT\PACKET); " OPEN OUTPUZX
)@@G@@T     @[@@@@NEXT: @D@@@@          IF NEXT\BLOCK(ADDR1(GET\PACKET)) NE 0 ZY
)@@G@@THEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             WRITE\NEXT\BUFFER;     ZZ
)@@G@@@B@@@@             READ\NEXT\BUFFER(GET\PACKET);@C@@@@             GOTO AA
)@@G@@NEXT; " WHILE NEXT\BLOCK NE 0 @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@AB
)@@G@@" WRITE THE LAST BLOCK  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@          LAST\BLOCK(PUT\PACKEAC
)@@G@@T) := TRUE; @ @@@@          WRITE\NEXT\BUFFER;  @ @@@@          WAIT(GETAD
)@@G@@\PACKET);   @ @@@@          WAIT(PUT\PACKET);   @F@@@@          RETURN(SAE
)@@G@@TART\DRUM\ADDR(PUT\PACKET)); " RETURN NEW LINK  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     AF
)@@G@@@E@@@@" PROCEDURE TO EXCHANGE DATA IN INPUT AND OUTPUT BUFFERS    @E@@@@AG
)@@G@@" BY EXCHANGEING THE BUFFER ADDRESSES AND REEXCHANGING THE  @E@@@@" BLOCAH
)@@G@@K LINKS SO THAT LOGICALLY ONLY THE DATA IS EXCHANGED. @[@@@@"     @ @@@@AI
)@@G@@PROCEDURE WRITE\NEXT\BUFFER   @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@DECLARE   TEMP: WORD INTAJ
)@@G@@EGER; @@@@@@@G@@@@          ADDR1(PUT\PACKET) :=: ADDR1(GET\PACKET); " EAK
)@@G@@XCHANGE BUFFERS   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" NOW RESET OLD BUFFER CONTROL WORDSAL
)@@G@@@D@@@@"     NOTE PLUS BUG IN EXCHANGE OPERATOR REQUIRES TEMP@[@@@@"     AM
)@@G@@@D@@@@          TEMP := BLOCK\LINK1(ADDR1(PUT\PACKET));     @C@@@@      AN
)@@G@@    BLOCK\LINK1(ADDR1(PUT\PACKET)) :=     @C@@@@             BLOCK\LINK1AO
)@@G@@(ADDR1(GET\PACKET));    @D@@@@          BLOCK\LINK1(ADDR1(GET\PACKET)) :AP
)@@G@@= TEMP;     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" NOW DO THE SAME FOR THE HEADER\LINK WORDAQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@          TEMP := BLOCK\LINK2(ADDR1(PUT\PACKET));     AR
)@@G@@@C@@@@          BLOCK\LINK2(ADDR1(PUT\PACKET)) :=     @C@@@@            AS
)@@G@@ BLOCK\LINK2(ADDR1(GET\PACKET));    @D@@@@          BLOCK\LINK2(ADDR1(GEAT
)@@G@@T\PACKET)) := TEMP;     @B@@@@          WRITE\THE\BUFFER(PUT\PACKET);   AU
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@TERM; ___T\PET)) := TEMP;     @B@@@@          WRITE\THAV
)@@G@@E\BUFFER(PUT\PACKET);   *[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @A@@@@          COAW
)@@G@@PY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('IO-PROCS',IMPORTED);     AX
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('FILE-HDR-DEF',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('PAY
)@@G@@IO-PROCS',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-DEF',IMPORTED);     AZ
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('BLOCK-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('PBA
)@@G@@ACKET-DEF',IMPORTED);   @A@@@@          COPY ('IO-DEF',IMPORTED); @[@@@@BB
)@@G@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED; " ****DEBUG     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@BC
)@@G@@" READ HEADER FROM SCRATCH FILE     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE READ\FILBD
)@@G@@E\HEADER EXPORTED ('RDFH')    @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          PACKET := LOC(BE
)@@G@@GENPKT);    @C@@@@          DRUM\ADDR := BASE\DRUM\ADDR; " AT TOP @A@@@@BF
)@@G@@          FUNCTION := IO\FUNC\READ; @C@@@@          WORD\COUNT := FILE\HBG
)@@G@@EADER\LENGTH;     @F@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR := LOC(FILE\HEADER); " REABH
)@@G@@D INTO OUR PLACE  @A@@@@          IOWWEC(PACKET); " READ IT @ @@@@END; "BI
)@@G@@ OF READ\FILE\HEADER    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" WRITE HEADER LABEL TO DPS FIBJ
)@@G@@LE    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\FILE\HEADER EXPORTED ('WRTFH')  BK
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@          PACKET := LOC(GENPKT); " INITIALIZE PACKET PBL
)@@G@@OINTER@G@@@@          DRUM\ADDR := BASE\DRUM\ADDR; " AT HEAD OF FILE OR BM
)@@G@@ELEMENT     @A@@@@          FUNCTION := IO\FUNC\WRITE;@C@@@@          WOBN
)@@G@@RD\COUNT := FILE\HEADER\LENGTH;     @B@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR := LOC(FBO
)@@G@@ILE\HEADER);@ @@@@          IOWWEC(PACKET);     @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@TERM; BP
)@@G@@___@[\ADER);@ @@@@          IOWWEC(PACKET);     @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@TERM; BQ
)@@G@@___@[\/K@@]O/CG@[XAT@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@BR
)@@G@@" PROCEDURES EXPORTED FROM THIS MODULE ARE DEFINED IN BLOCK-PROCS @[@@@@BS
)@@G@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('DBT
)@@G@@EBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('FILE-HDR-DEF',IMPORTED); BU
)@@G@@@A@@@@          COPY ('IO-DEF1',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('IO-PROCBV
)@@G@@S',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('PACKET-DEF',IMPORTED);   @#@@@@BW
)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@"          ********** FILE ALLOCATIOBX
)@@G@@N ROUTINES **********   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" FILE FORMAT IS AS FOLLOWS:  BY
)@@G@@@D@@@@"     1) A HEADER SECTION DEFINED BY THE NAME 'FIRST' @ @@@@"     BZ
)@@G@@2) A BITMAP CONTAINING  @E@@@@"        A) ALLOCATION TABLE, 1 BIT PER SECA
)@@G@@CTOR ALLOCATED    @F@@@@"        B) RELEASE TABLE, MARKED WHEN AREAS CONCB
)@@G@@DITIONALLY FREE   @C@@@@"     3) DATA SECTORS ALLOCATED BY THE ABOVE MAPCC
)@@G@@@ @@@@"     4) REPETITIONS OF 2 & 3 @[@@@@"     @#@@@@" DEFINITIONS     CD
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@DEFINE    ATTRIBUTE INT =  WORD INTEGER;  @H@@@@DEFINECE
)@@G@@    FIRSTMAP\ADDRESS = 4;       " THE FOLLOWING UNITS ARE IN SECTORS    CF
)@@G@@@^@@@@DEFINE    ABTSIZE = 4;  @ @@@@DEFINE    RBTSIZE = ABTSIZE;  @A@@@@CG
)@@G@@DEFINE    MAPSIZE = ABTSIZE+RBTSIZE;@G@@@@DEFINE    SECTORSIZE = 28;    CH
)@@G@@        " FOLLOWING UNITS ARE IN WORDS    @B@@@@DEFINE    ABTWORDS = ABTCI
)@@G@@SIZE*SECTORSIZE;  @ @@@@DEFINE    RBTWORDS = ABTWORDS;@B@@@@DEFINE    MACJ
)@@G@@PWORDS = ABTWORDS+RBTWORDS;   @G@@@@DEFINE    ABITS = ABTWORDS*36;      CK
)@@G@@  " FOLLOWING UNITS ARE IN BITS     @^@@@@DEFINE    RBITS = ABITS;@H@@@@CL
)@@G@@DEFINE    DATASIZE = ABITS;           " A BIT IN THE MAP IS WORTH A SECTCM
)@@G@@OR    @C@@@@DEFINE    PAGESIZE = MAPSIZE+DATASIZE; " SECTORS@G@@@@DEFINECN
)@@G@@    CONDITIONAL = FALSE;        " ARGUMENT TO FREE\FILE\BLOCK     @G@@@@CO
)@@G@@DEFINE    UNCONDITIONAL = NOT CONDITIONAL; " ARGUMENT TO FREE\FILE\BLOCKCP
)@@G@@@G@@@@DEFINE    FREE = TRUE;                " ARGUMENT TO RELEASE\FILE\BCQ
)@@G@@LOCKS @G@@@@DEFINE    RETAIN = NOT FREE;          " ARGUMENT TO RELEASE\CR
)@@G@@FILE\BLOCKS @[@@@@"     @]@@@@" GLOBALS   @[@@@@"     @I@@@@DECLARE    MCS
)@@G@@AP\CHANGED: 6 BIT CONDITION STATIC := FALSE " SET WHEN CORE CHANGED     CT
)@@G@@@C@@@@          ,*: 12 BIT LOGICAL STATIC   " UNUSED  @I@@@@          ,CCU
)@@G@@URRENT\MAP: 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER STATIC := 0 " CURRENT MAP NUMBER    CV
)@@G@@@B@@@@          ,MAPP: STATIC LOCATABLE MAPPED  @B@@@@           [MAP(MACW
)@@G@@PWORDS): INTEGER WORD]  @B@@@@          ![ABT(ABITS): BIT CONDITION     CX
)@@G@@@B@@@@           ,RBT(RBITS): BIT CONDITION];   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     CY
)@@G@@@ @@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED;     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     CZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO FORCE A WRITE OF THE LAST BIT MAP   DA
)@@G@@@E@@@@" WHEN WRITING THE OUTPUT FILE AND WHEN DOING A CHECKPOINT. @[@@@@DB
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE FORCE\WRITE\OF\BIT\MAP EXPORTED ('FORCEWOBM')     DC
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@          GET\MAP(CURRENT\MAP);       " READ CURRENT MDD
)@@G@@AP    @E@@@@          MAP\CHANGED := TRUE;        " MARK MAP CHANGED    DE
)@@G@@@D@@@@          WRITE\CURRENT\MAP;          " WRITE IT OUT  @D@@@@      DF
)@@G@@    LINK\TO\FILE\BIT\MAP := FIRSTMAP\ADDRESS;   @^@@@@END; " FORCE\WRITEDG
)@@G@@ MAP  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@"           ********** ADH
)@@G@@LLOCATE **********@[@@@@"     @B@@@@" CALLED WITH NUMBER OF WORDS TO ALLDI
)@@G@@OCATE @C@@@@" RETURNS SECTOR ADDRESS OF FIRST BLOCK FOUND   @[@@@@"     DJ
)@@G@@@C@@@@"            1) LOOK IN CURRENT MAP. IF NO FIND,@B@@@@"           DK
)@@G@@ 2) SEARCH UP TO END OF FILE  @D@@@@"            3) SEARCH FROM BEGINNINDL
)@@G@@G OF FILE UP TO   @B@@@@"               WHERE WE STARTED LOOKING  @C@@@@DM
)@@G@@"            4) IF STILL NO FIND, EXTEND FILE   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     DN
)@@G@@@C@@@@PROCEDURE ALLOCATE\FILE\BLOCK(BLOCK\LEN: INT)   @B@@@@          EXDO
)@@G@@PORTED('ALLFBKA') RESULT INT  @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@DECLARE   REQSEC: INT;  DP
)@@G@@              " REQUESTED SIZE IN SECTORS @F@@@@DECLARE   MAPNUM: INT;  DQ
)@@G@@              " NEXT MAP NUMBER TO READ   @F@@@@DECLARE   SECTOR: INT;  DR
)@@G@@              " SECTOR SEARCHING FROM     @F@@@@DECLARE   ALLOCA: INT;  DS
)@@G@@              " SECTOR ADDRESS ALLOCATED  @D@@@@DECLARE   MAPSEEN: INT; DT
)@@G@@              " MAPS SEEN     @E@@@@DECLARE   LASTDA: INT;              DU
)@@G@@  " LAST SECTOR TO TEST @[@@@@"     @I@@@@          REQSEC := (BLOCK\LENDV
)@@G@@+SECTORSIZE-1)//SECTORSIZE; " CONVERT WORDS TO SECTORS@[@@@@"     @A@@@@DW
)@@G@@          IF REQSEC GT ABITS THEN   @F@@@@             ERROR;           DX
)@@G@@        " CANT ALLOCATE ACROSS MAPS @[@@@@"     @F@@@@          ALLOCA :DY
)@@G@@= 0;                " SET NO ALLOCATION YET     @G@@@@          MAPNUM :DZ
)@@G@@= CURRENT\MAP;      " START SEARCH IN CURRENT MAP     @E@@@@          MAEA
)@@G@@PSEEN := 0;               " NO MAPS SEARCHED YET@E@@@@          WHILE (MEB
)@@G@@APSEEN LE MAXBITMAPS) AND (ALLOCA EQ 0) DO@#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@EC
)@@G@@             IF MAPSEEN EQ MAXBITMAPS THEN " EXTEND FILE    @^@@@@      ED
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @A@@@@                CREATE\NEXT\BIT\MAP;@B@@@@      EE
)@@G@@        END; " CREATING ANOTHER MAP @B@@@@             ELSE " EXISTING CEF
)@@G@@URRENT\MAP  @B@@@@              BEGIN " TO READ EXISTING MAP@D@@@@      EG
)@@G@@          GET\MAP(MAPNUM);      " READ NEXT MAP @G@@@@                MAEH
)@@G@@PNUM := NEXT\MAP;   " GET NUMBER OF NEXT MAP TO READ  @B@@@@            EI
)@@G@@  END; " READ OF EXISTING MAP @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" TRY TO ALLOCATE FROM CEJ
)@@G@@URRENT BITMAP.    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@             SECTOR := 0;           EK
)@@G@@  " START AT SECTOR ZERO@G@@@@             WHILE (SECTOR LT ABITS) AND (EL
)@@G@@ALLOCA EQ 0) DO " SEARCH MAP  @D@@@@              BEGIN " TO SEARCH STAREM
)@@G@@TING AT SECTOR    @F@@@@                SECTOR := SECTOR+1;   " INCREMENEN
)@@G@@T SEARCH ADDRESS  @G@@@@                LASTDA := SECTOR+REQSEC-1; " COMEO
)@@G@@PUTE LAST SECTOR NEEDED @F@@@@                IF LASTDA LE ABITS THEN " EP
)@@G@@IF ENUF ROOM IN THIS MAP@C@@@@                 BEGIN " TO CHECK ALLOCATIEQ
)@@G@@ON    @E@@@@                   ALLOCA := SECTOR;  " TENATIVE ALLOCATION ER
)@@G@@@F@@@@                   WHILE (SECTOR LE LASTDA) AND NOT ABT(SECTOR) DOES
)@@G@@@F@@@@                      SECTOR := SECTOR+1; " CHECK NOT ALLOCATED   ET
)@@G@@@G@@@@                   IF (SECTOR NE LASTDA+1) THEN " ALREADY ALLOCATEEU
)@@G@@D     @E@@@@                      ALLOCA := 0;    " SO CLEAR ALLOCATION EV
)@@G@@@C@@@@                 END; " OF TEST THIS ALLOCATION @B@@@@            EW
)@@G@@  END; " OF PASS OVER THIS MAP@E@@@@             MAPSEEN := MAPSEEN + 1;EX
)@@G@@  " INCREMENT MAPS SEEN @B@@@@           END; " OF BIT MAP SCAN LOOP    EY
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" AT THIS POINT ALLOCA WILL BE EITHER ZERO, SIGNIFYINGEZ
)@@G@@ NO FIND,   @F@@@@" OR THE SECTOR ADDRESS IN THE CURRENT MAP FOR THE ALLFA
)@@G@@OCATION.    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          IF (ALLOCA EQ 0) THEN ERROR; " NFB
)@@G@@O FIND FOR SPACE  @E@@@@          FOR SECTOR := ALLOCA TO LASTDA DO " SEFC
)@@G@@T ALLOCATED @D@@@@             ABT(SECTOR) := TRUE;     " SET ALLOCATED FD
)@@G@@@E@@@@          MAP\CHANGED := TRUE;        " SET CHANGE FLAG     @I@@@@FE
)@@G@@          ALLOCA := MAP\ADDRESS(CURRENT\MAP)+MAPSIZE+ALLOCA-1; " COMPUTEFF
)@@G@@ ADDRESS    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          INCLUDE(DEBUG\CODE);@A@@@@      FG
)@@G@@       IF DEBUG GT 0 THEN     @D@@@@                ODISPLAY('FALL',ALLOFH
)@@G@@CA); " *** DEBUG  @D@@@@          RESUME;                     " NON DEBUFI
)@@G@@G CODE@[@@@@"     @F@@@@          RETURN(ALLOCA);             " SECTOR AFJ
)@@G@@DDRESS ALLOCATED  @ @@@@END; " OF ALLOCATE\FILE\BLOCK @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECFK
)@@G@@T);   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@"           ********** MAX **********     @[@@@@FL
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@" LOOK BACKWARDS THRU MAPS AND RETURN HIGHEST SECTOR ALLOCATFM
)@@G@@ED    @E@@@@" USED FOR OBTAINING THE NEXT WRITE ADDRESS FOR THE PFI$    FN
)@@G@@@B@@@@" WHEN WRITING OUT THE USER'S ELEMENT     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDFO
)@@G@@URE MAX\ALLOCATED\FILE\BLOCK EXPORTED('MAXAFB') RESULT INT  @[@@@@BEGIN FP
)@@G@@@C@@@@          FOR K := MAXBITMAPS TO 1 BY -1 DO     @#@@@@           BFQ
)@@G@@EGIN  @^@@@@             GET\MAP(K);@B@@@@             FOR J := ABITS TOFR
)@@G@@ 1 BY -1 DO @ @@@@                IF ABT(J) THEN@^@@@@                 BFS
)@@G@@EGIN  @F@@@@                   RETURN(MAP\ADDRESS(CURRENT\MAP)+MAPSIZE+JFT
)@@G@@-1);  @E@@@@                 END; " END CHECK FOR FIRST ALLOCATED SECTORFU
)@@G@@@D@@@@           END; " FOR LOOP BACKWARDS THRU BIT MAPS    @F@@@@      FV
)@@G@@    RETURN(0);                  " NOT FOUND RETURN ZERO     @C@@@@END; "FW
)@@G@@ OF PROCEDURE MAX\ALLOCATED\FILE\BLOCK    @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@FX
)@@G@@"     @B@@@@"           ********** FREE **********    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@FY
)@@G@@" FREE A GIVEN SIZE AREA AT A GIVEN ADDRESS     @A@@@@" THERE ARE TWO TYFZ
)@@G@@PES OF FREES:     @E@@@@" 1) UNCONDITIONAL- DE-ALLOCATES THE SPACE, UNREGA
)@@G@@COVERABLE   @E@@@@" 2) CONDITIONAL- MARKS AS FREE, BUT SPACE CAN BE RECOGB
)@@G@@VERED @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE UNCONDITIONAL\FREE\FILE\BLOCK(BLOCK\ADGC
)@@G@@DRESS: INT  @C@@@@          ,BLOCK\LEN: INT) EXPORTED('UNCFRE')   @[@@@@GD
)@@G@@BEGIN @F@@@@          FREE\FILE\BLOCK(BLOCK\ADDRESS,BLOCK\LEN,UNCONDITIOGE
)@@G@@NAL); @C@@@@END; " PROCDURE UNCONDITIONA\FREE\FILE\BLOCK    @[@@@@"     GF
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE CONDITIONAL\FREE\FILE\BLOCK(BLOCGG
)@@G@@K\ADDRESS: INT,   @D@@@@             BLOCK\LEN: INT) EXPORTED ('FREFBKA'GH
)@@G@@)     @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@          FREE\FILE\BLOCK(BLOCK\ADDRESS,BLOCK\LEGI
)@@G@@N,CONDITIONAL);   @C@@@@END; " PROCDURE CONDITIONAL\FREE\FILE\BLOCK     GJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@"           ********** CLEAR **********   GK
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\FILE\ALLOCATOR EXPORTGL
)@@G@@ED ('INITFILALLOC')     @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          MAXBITMAPS := 0;    GM
)@@G@@        " NO MAPS YET   @E@@@@          MAP\CHANGED := FALSE;       " MAGN
)@@G@@RK AS BEING NEW   @D@@@@          CURRENT\MAP := 0;           " NO CURREGO
)@@G@@NT MAP@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE RELEASE\FREED\FILE\BLOCKS GP
)@@G@@EXPORTED ('RELFREEFB')  @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          RELEASE\FILE\BLOCKS(GQ
)@@G@@FREE);@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE RECOVER\FREED\FILE\BLOCKS GR
)@@G@@EXPORTED ('RECVFREEFB') @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          RELEASE\FILE\BLOCKS(GS
)@@G@@RETAIN);    @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@"         ********** NONEXPORTGT
)@@G@@ED UTILITY ROUTINES ********  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" READ MAP NUMBER REQUESGU
)@@G@@TED IF NOT THE CURRENT MAP IN CORE  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE GET\MAP(GV
)@@G@@REQMAP: WORD INTEGER)   @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@          IF REQMAP EQ 0 THEN GW
)@@G@@        " MAP NOT INITIALIZED @D@@@@             REQMAP := 1;           GX
)@@G@@  " READ FIRST MAP@D@@@@          IF REQMAP NE CURRENT\MAP THEN " READ IGY
)@@G@@T     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@             WRITE\CURRENT\MAP;     GZ
)@@G@@  " WRITE CURRENT MAP FIRST   @E@@@@             DRUM\ADDR(BIT\PACKET) :HA
)@@G@@= MAP\ADDRESS(REQMAP) + @C@@@@                    BASE\DRUM\ADDR(BIT\PACHB
)@@G@@KET); @D@@@@             FUNCTION(BIT\PACKET) := IO\FUNC\READ;    @G@@@@HC
)@@G@@             WORD\COUNT(BIT\PACKET) := MAPWORDS; " SET WORDS TO READ    HD
)@@G@@@G@@@@             BUFFER\ADDR(BIT\PACKET) := LOC(MAPP); " BUFFER ADDRESHE
)@@G@@S     @A@@@@             IOWWEC(BIT\PACKET);    @F@@@@             CURREHF
)@@G@@NT\MAP := REQMAP;   " SET CURRENT MAP NUMBER    @#@@@@           END;   HG
)@@G@@@ @@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE GET\MAP   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" WRITE OUT THE MAHH
)@@G@@P TO REQUESTED LOCATION ONLY IF THE MAP IS CHANGED    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@HI
)@@G@@PROCEDURE WRITE\CURRENT\MAP   @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          IF MAP\CHANGEDHJ
)@@G@@ THEN         " WRITE IT@#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             FUNCTHK
)@@G@@ION(BIT\PACKET) := IO\FUNC\WRITE;   @G@@@@             WORD\COUNT(BIT\PAHL
)@@G@@CKET) := MAPWORDS; " SET WORDS TO WRITE   @G@@@@             BUFFER\ADDRHM
)@@G@@(BIT\PACKET) := LOC(MAPP); " BUFFER ADDRESS     @F@@@@             DRUM\HN
)@@G@@ADDR(BIT\PACKET) := MAP\ADDRESS(CURRENT\MAP) +  @C@@@@                BAHO
)@@G@@SE\DRUM\ADDR(BIT\PACKET);     @A@@@@             IOWWEC(BIT\PACKET);    HP
)@@G@@@E@@@@             MAP\CHANGED := FALSE;    " MAP NOLONGER CHANGED@B@@@@HQ
)@@G@@           END; " CHECK FOR CHANGED MAP   @B@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE WRITHR
)@@G@@E\CURRENT\MAP     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" COMPUTE SECTOR ADDRESS OF REQUESTEHS
)@@G@@D MAP NUMBER@[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE MAP\ADDRESS(REQMAP: INT) RESULT HT
)@@G@@INT   @[@@@@BEGIN @H@@@@          RETURN(FIRSTMAP\ADDRESS+(REQMAP-1)*PAGHU
)@@G@@ESIZE); " MAP SECTOR ADDRESS  @B@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE COMPUT\BITMAP\ADHV
)@@G@@DRESS @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" RETURN THE NEXT MAP NUMBER.  IT WRAPS AROUND FHW
)@@G@@ROM   @#@@@@" MAXBITMAPS TO 1.@[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE NEXT\MAP RESULHX
)@@G@@T WORD INTEGER    @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@DECLARE   NEXT: WORD INTEGER; @@@@@@HY
)@@G@@@C@@@@          NEXT := CURRENT\MAP + 1;    " NEXT MAP@E@@@@          IFHZ
)@@G@@ NEXT GT MAXBITMAPS THEN  " START AT ONE AGAIN  @^@@@@             NEXT IA
)@@G@@:= 1; @^@@@@          RETURN(NEXT); @ @@@@END; " OF PROCEUDRE NEXT\MAP  IB
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @^@@@@" CREATE A NEW BIT MAP  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE CRIC
)@@G@@EATE\NEXT\BIT\MAP @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@          WRITE\CURRENT\MAP;        ID
)@@G@@  " WRITE OUT CURRENT MAP     @E@@@@          MAXBITMAPS := MAXBITMAPS+1IE
)@@G@@; " ADD ANOTHER MAP     @B@@@@"         DISPLAY('MORMAP',MAXBITMAPS);   IF
)@@G@@@F@@@@          CURRENT\MAP := MAXBITMAPS;  " WHICH BECOMES THE CURRENT IG
)@@G@@@E@@@@          FOR J := 1 TO MAPWORDS DO   " INITIALIZE NEW MAP  @E@@@@IH
)@@G@@             MAP(J) := 0;             " WITH NOTHING IN IT  @B@@@@END; "II
)@@G@@ OF PROCEDURE CREATE\NEXT\BIT\MAP   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDIJ
)@@G@@URE FREE\FILE\BLOCK(BLOCK\ADDR: INT,BLOCK\LEN: INT,   @B@@@@            IK
)@@G@@ UNCOND\REQ: WORD CONDITION)  @[@@@@BEGIN @^@@@@DECLARE   SECTOR: INT   IL
)@@G@@@^@@@@          ,REQUEST: INT @^@@@@          ,LAST: INT;   @[@@@@"     IM
)@@G@@@B@@@@"         ODISPLAY ('FREL',BLOCK\ADDR);   @H@@@@          GET\MAP(IN
)@@G@@1+(BLOCK\ADDR-FIRSTMAP\ADDRESS)//PAGESIZE); " READ THE MAP  @J@@@@      IO
)@@G@@    SECTOR := BLOCK\ADDR-MAP\ADDRESS(CURRENT\MAP)-MAPSIZE+1;" GET RELATIIP
)@@G@@VE SECTOR   @I@@@@          REQUEST := (BLOCK\LEN+SECTORSIZE-1)//SECTORSIQ
)@@G@@IZE;" CONVERT WORDS TO SECTORS@G@@@@          LAST := SECTOR+REQUEST-1; IR
)@@G@@  " COMPUTE LAST SECTOR TO FREE     @H@@@@          IF LAST GT RBITS THEIS
)@@G@@N       " ***DEBUG*** CANNOT FREE ACROSS MAPS   @D@@@@             ERRORIT
)@@G@@;                   " *** DEBUG**** @G@@@@          FOR J := SECTOR TO LIU
)@@G@@AST DO  " LOOP OVER SECTORS TO BE FREED   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@IV
)@@G@@             IF UNCOND\REQ THEN       " IF UNCONDITIONAL FREE     @D@@@@IW
)@@G@@                ABT(J) := FALSE;      " DE-ALLOCATE   @B@@@@            IX
)@@G@@ ELSE " CONDITIONAL RELEASE   @G@@@@                RBT(J) := TRUE;     IY
)@@G@@  " REMEMBER RELEASED FOR LATER USE @#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@      IZ
)@@G@@    MAP\CHANGED := TRUE;@A@@@@END; " PROCEDURE FREE\FILE\BLOCK    @[@@@@JA
)@@G@@"     @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE RELEASE\FILE\BLOCKS(FREE\BJB
)@@G@@LOCKS: WORD CONDITION)  @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@DECLARE   MAPNUM: WORD INTEGERJC
)@@G@@;       " MAP NUMBER TO READ  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@          MAPNUM := CURRJD
)@@G@@ENT\MAP;      " START WITH CURRENT MAP    @F@@@@          FOR K := 1 TO JE
)@@G@@MAXBITMAPS DO " LOOP THROUGH ALL MAPS     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@JF
)@@G@@             GET\MAP(MAPNUM);         " READ NEXT MAP @F@@@@            JG
)@@G@@ MAPNUM := NEXT\MAP;      " COMPUTE NEXT MAP IN LOOP  @C@@@@            JH
)@@G@@ IF FREE\BLOCKS THEN      " RELEASE @^@@@@              BEGIN     @E@@@@JI
)@@G@@                FOR J := 1 TO RBITS DO " FOR ALL BITS IN MAP@C@@@@      JJ
)@@G@@             IF RBT(J)  THEN    " IF FREED@ @@@@                    BEGIJK
)@@G@@N     @D@@@@                      ABT(J) := FALSE; " THEN ACTUALLY@D@@@@JL
)@@G@@                      RBT(J) := FALSE; " RELEASE IT   @^@@@@            JM
)@@G@@        END;@#@@@@              END;@E@@@@             ELSE " CLEAR THE JN
)@@G@@BITS NOT FREEING THE BLOCKS   @^@@@@              BEGIN     @G@@@@      JO
)@@G@@         FOR J := 1+ABTWORDS TO MAPWORDS DO " FOR ALL WORDS IN RBT@D@@@@JP
)@@G@@                  MAP(J) := 0;        " ZERO THEM     @C@@@@            JQ
)@@G@@  END; " CLEARING THE FREE BITS     @#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@      JR
)@@G@@    MAP\CHANGED := TRUE;@B@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE RELEASE\FILE\BLOCKS   JS
)@@G@@@[@@@@TERM; ___   @ @@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@MODULE@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" SET JT
)@@G@@UP INPUT IF A MACRO IS BEING INVOKED.     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COJU
)@@G@@PY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED);  JV
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CJW
)@@G@@ORE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('FILE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   JX
)@@G@@@A@@@@          COPY ('IO-DEF1',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('IO-PROCJY
)@@G@@S',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('MACRO-DEF',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@JZ
)@@G@@          COPY ('SCAN-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-KA
)@@G@@PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   @F@@@@KB
)@@G@@          COPY ('PACKET-DEF',IMPORTED); " IO PACKET DEFINITIONS   @E@@@@KC
)@@G@@          COPY ('PUSH-PROCS',IMPORTED); " PUSH AND POP PROCS@B@@@@      KD
)@@G@@    COPY ('PIO-PROCS',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('PRINT-DEF',IMKE
)@@G@@PORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@"     KF
)@@G@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE COMPILE\INTERNAL\MACRO IMPORTED ('CINMAC')  @^@@@@ RESULKG
)@@G@@T MACHINE POINTER;@[@@@@"     @@@@@@@@@@@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE ERKH
)@@G@@ROR IMPORTED; " *****DEBUG    @@@@@@@A@@@@DECLARE MPKT: MACHINE WORD POIKI
)@@G@@NTER; @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" INVOKE THEKJ
)@@G@@ MACRO WHOSE DEFINITION IS POINTED TO BY MAC    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDKK
)@@G@@URE INVOKE\DEFINED\MACRO(MAC: MACHINE POINTER WORD)   @ @@@@          EXKL
)@@G@@PORTED('IDFMAC')  @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@DECLARE   TEMP: LOCATABLE MACHINE POKM
)@@G@@INTER WORD, @ @@@@          SECT: INTEGER WORD; @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" SCANKN
)@@G@@ MACRO CALL LINE, GET ARGS, PUSH EVERYTHING DOWN@[@@@@"     @G@@@@      KO
)@@G@@    TEMP := ALLOCATE\CORE(XQTMACSIZ); " ALLOCATE CORE FOR PACKET  @F@@@@KP
)@@G@@          MACRO\ARGS(TEMP) := SCAN\MACRO\CALL; " GET ARGUMENTS    @D@@@@KQ
)@@G@@          SECT := SMAD(MAC); " GET SECTOR ADDRESS     @A@@@@"         ODKR
)@@G@@ISPLAY('SECT  ',SECT);  @E@@@@          INITIALIZE\FILE(%TEMP,%TEMP,SECTKS
)@@G@@); " OPEN INPUT   @B@@@@          MACRO\DEF\LINK(TEMP) := MAC;    @B@@@@KT
)@@G@@          PUSH\INPUT\PKT(PKT\MACRO,TEMP); @G@@@@          USER\IMAGE\BUFKU
)@@G@@FER(TEMP) := LOC(MACRO\TEMP\PTR); " SET BUFADR  @F@@@@          IF DLEN(KV
)@@G@@MAC) NE 0 THEN " TEST IF MACRO RESIDENT IN CORE @D@@@@           BEGIN "KW
)@@G@@ RESIDENT IN CORE - NO IO NEEDED    @B@@@@             RELEASE\CORE(ADDRKX
)@@G@@1(CIP));    @B@@@@             RELEASE\CORE(ADDR2(CIP));    @A@@@@      KY
)@@G@@       ADDR2(CIP) := NULL\PTR;@B@@@@"             PDISPLAY('RESIDN',CIP)KZ
)@@G@@;     @C@@@@              FUNCTION(CIP) := IO\FUNC\READ;    @B@@@@      LA
)@@G@@        END\FILE(CIP) := FALSE;     @C@@@@              IMAGE\DRUM\ADDR(LB
)@@G@@CIP) := SECT;     @A@@@@              ADDR1(CIP):=DADR(MAC);@B@@@@      LC
)@@G@@        BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR(CIP) :=@A@@@@                    ADDR1(CIP)LD
)@@G@@ + 2; @A@@@@              END\OF\BUFFER(CIP) := @D@@@@              BUFFLE
)@@G@@ER\IMAGE\LOCATOR(CIP) + DLEN(MAC);  @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  LF
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED FROM POP\INPUT\PKT WHEN THELG
)@@G@@@B@@@@" PACKET BEING RELEASED IS TYPED MACRO.   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDLH
)@@G@@URE RELEASE\MACRO(PKT: MACHINE WORD POINTER)    @A@@@@             EXPORLI
)@@G@@TED ('RELMAC')    @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          LOCAL\SYMBOLS(PKT) := RELELJ
)@@G@@ASE\SYMBOL\TABLE  @F@@@@             ( LOCAL\SYMBOLS(PKT) ); " RELEASE LLK
)@@G@@OCAL VARIABLES    @F@@@@          RELEASE\CORE(MACRO\ARGS(PKT)); " ALSO LL
)@@G@@RELEASE ARGUMENTS @E@@@@          IF DADR(MACRO\DEF\LINK(PKT)) NE NULL\PLM
)@@G@@TR THEN     @F@@@@             ADDR1(PKT) := NULL\PTR; " DONT RELEASE INLN
)@@G@@CORE MACRO  @E@@@@          USER\IMAGE\BUFFER(PKT) := NULL\PTR; " DONT RLO
)@@G@@EL BUF@B@@@@          CLOSE\FILE(PKT); " CLOSE IT     @C@@@@          RELP
)@@G@@LEASE\CORE(PKT); " AND RELEASE CORE @^@@@@END; " OF RELEASE\MACRO @#@@@@LQ
)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" INVOKE THE CONTROL STRUCTURE COMMALR
)@@G@@ND SPECIFIED BY THE INDEX     @G@@@@" PASSED, WHICH IS THE INDEX OF THE LS
)@@G@@COMMAND INTO THE SYSTEM MACRO TABLE @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE INVOKE\SLT
)@@G@@YSTEM\MACRO(IMAGE\TYPE: INTEGER WORD)     @ @@@@          EXPORTED('ISYMLU
)@@G@@AC')  @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@DECLARE   TEMP: MACHINE WORD POINTER;     @[@@@@LV
)@@G@@"     @B@@@@" BRANCH ON CONTROL STRUCTURE TO EXECUTE. @[@@@@"     @ @@@@LW
)@@G@@          CASEENTRY IMAGE\TYPE@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" IF A .MACRO IS SEEN ITLX
)@@G@@ MUST BE FROM THE ORIGINAL TEXT AND SO    @F@@@@" IT IS COMPILED BY THE LY
)@@G@@'COMPILE\INTERNAL\MACRO' ENTRY INTO THE   @^@@@@" MACRO MODE COMPILER.  LZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@          CASE MACRO\CS\MACRO:@A@@@@           BEGIN "MA
)@@G@@ SOURCE CHECK     @B@@@@             IF MACRO\LINE\NUM NE 0 THEN  @F@@@@MB
)@@G@@                WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\DIRECTIVE); " FROM MACRO (UGLY) @A@@@@MC
)@@G@@             ELSE " OK TO EXECUTE   @ @@@@              BEGIN " .MACRO  MD
)@@G@@@E@@@@                SCAN(CTRM+CNAM+ALLOW\NAM); " SCAN MACRO NAME@I@@@@ME
)@@G@@                TEMP := COMPILE\INTERNAL\MACRO; " COMPILE MACRO UNTIL .EMF
)@@G@@ND SEEN     @ @@@@              END; " .MACRO   @ @@@@           END; " MG
)@@G@@SOURCE CHECK@[@@@@"     @G@@@@" FOR BOTH 'IF' AND 'WHILE' THE ACTIONS ARMH
)@@G@@E THE SAME.  IF THE EXPRESSION@G@@@@" IS NONZERO THEN CONTROL CONTINUES MI
)@@G@@INLINE.  IF THE EXPRESSION IS ZERO  @G@@@@" A JUMP IS TAKEN TO THE POINTMJ
)@@G@@ER IMAGE.  FOR 'IF' THIS POINTS AFTER THE @H@@@@" ASSOCIATED 'ELSE' OR 'MK
)@@G@@ENDIF', FOR 'WHILE' THIS POINTS AFTER THE 'ENDREP'.   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@ML
)@@G@@          CASE MACRO\CS\IF,MACRO\CS\WHILE:@A@@@@           BEGIN " SOURCMM
)@@G@@E CHECK     @B@@@@             IF MACRO\LINE\NUM EQ 0 THEN  @F@@@@      MN
)@@G@@          WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\DIRECTIVE); " NOT FROM MACRO    @A@@@@      MO
)@@G@@       ELSE " OK TO EXECUTE   @A@@@@              BEGIN " .IF OR .WHILE MP
)@@G@@@G@@@@                SCAN(EVAL+CTRM+ALLOW\INT); " SCAN FOR BOOLEAN VALUMQ
)@@G@@E     @G@@@@                IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE NE 0 THEN " MUST TERMINMR
)@@G@@ATE LOOP    @D@@@@                   SDFMOV(CIP); " BY TAKING THE JUMP  MS
)@@G@@@D@@@@                ELSE " OK SO CHECK DATA ITEM RETURNED @G@@@@      MT
)@@G@@             IF CSDLEN EQ 1 AND DNUM(1) EQ 0 THEN "  IF FALSE     @E@@@@MU
)@@G@@                      SDFMOV(CIP); " THEN TAKE THE JUMP     @A@@@@      MV
)@@G@@        END; " .IF OR .WHILE  @ @@@@           END; " SOURCE CHECK@[@@@@MW
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" FOR 'UNTIL' SAME AS ABOVE EXCEPT FOR SENSE OF TEST AND    MX
)@@G@@@E@@@@" DISPOSITION OF EXPRESSION ERROR SO AS TO TERMINATE LOOP.  @[@@@@MY
)@@G@@"     @ @@@@          CASE MACRO\CS\UNTIL:@A@@@@           BEGIN " SOURCMZ
)@@G@@E CHECK     @B@@@@             IF MACRO\LINE\NUM EQ 0 THEN  @F@@@@      NA
)@@G@@          WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\DIRECTIVE); " NOT FROM MACRO    @A@@@@      NB
)@@G@@       ELSE " OK TO EXECUTE   @ @@@@              BEGIN " .UNTIL  @G@@@@NC
)@@G@@                SCAN(EVAL+CTRM+ALLOW\INT); " SCAN FOR BOOLEAN VALUE     ND
)@@G@@@G@@@@                IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE NE 0 THEN " MUST TERMINATE LONE
)@@G@@OP    @D@@@@                   SDFMOV(CIP); " BY TAKING THE JUMP  @D@@@@NF
)@@G@@                ELSE " OK SO CHECK DATA ITEM RETURNED @F@@@@            NG
)@@G@@       IF CSDLEN EQ 1 AND DNUM(1) NE 0 THEN " IF TRUE @E@@@@            NH
)@@G@@          SDFMOV(CIP); " THEN TAKE THE JUMP     @ @@@@              END;NI
)@@G@@ " .UNTIL   @ @@@@           END; " SOURCE CHECK@[@@@@"     @G@@@@" FOR NJ
)@@G@@'ELSE' AND 'ENDREP' THE ACTIONS ARE THE SAME.  TAKE THE JUMP TO   @G@@@@NK
)@@G@@" THE XFER IMAGE.  FOR 'ELSE' THIS POINTS TO THE ASSOCIATED 'ENDIF'     NL
)@@G@@@E@@@@" AND FOR 'ENDREP' THIS POINTS BACK TO THE 'REPEAT' IMAGE.  @[@@@@NM
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@          CASE MACRO\CS\ELSE,MACRO\CS\ENDREP,MACRO\CS\LOOP: NN
)@@G@@@A@@@@           BEGIN " SOURCE CHECK     @B@@@@             IF MACRO\LINO
)@@G@@NE\NUM EQ 0 THEN  @F@@@@                WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\DIRECTIVE); " NP
)@@G@@NOT FROM MACRO    @A@@@@             ELSE " OK TO EXECUTE   @C@@@@      NQ
)@@G@@          SDFMOV(CIP); " TAKE THE JUMP    @ @@@@           END; " SOURCENR
)@@G@@ CHECK@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THE ABOVE STRUCTURES ARE THE ONLY ONES WHICH SNS
)@@G@@HOULD BE FOUND    @E@@@@" IN THE MACRO FILE, AS THE COMPILER PURGES THE NT
)@@G@@OTHERS.     @D@@@@" THEREFORE ANY OTHER IMAGE HERE GETS DIAGNOSTIC.     NU
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @#@@@@          CASE *: @F@@@@             WARNING(W\ILLEGALNV
)@@G@@\DIRECTIVE); " ISSUE DIAGNOSTIC     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          ENDCASE;NW
)@@G@@ " DONE STRUCTURE @ @@@@END; " INVOKE\SYSTEM\MACRO    @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECNX
)@@G@@T);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO 'MOVE' THE LOGICALNY
)@@G@@ READ POINT WITHIN@G@@@@" AN INTERNAL FORMAT FILE TO THE ADDRESS GIVEN, NZ
)@@G@@WHICH WAS PREVIOUSLY    @C@@@@" SET INTO MACRO\XFER\PTR BY THE MACRO COMOA
)@@G@@PILER.@[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE SDFMOV(PKT: MACHINE WORD POINTER)     OB
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@"         ODISPLAY('SDFMOV',MACRO\XFER\PTR);    @ @@@@OC
)@@G@@"         PRINT\INPUT\CARD;   @B@@@@          IF MACRO\XFER\PTR EQ 0 THEOD
)@@G@@N     @A@@@@           BEGIN " TO SAY SOMETHING @C@@@@             ODISPOE
)@@G@@LAY('BADMOV',MACRO\XFER\PTR); @ @@@@             PRINT\INPUT\CARD;@^@@@@OF
)@@G@@             ERROR;     @#@@@@           END;   @E@@@@          IF MACROOG
)@@G@@\XFER\DADD NE IMAGE\DRUM\ADDR(PKT) THEN   @C@@@@           BEGIN " BUF NOH
)@@G@@OT CURRENT, READ IN     @D@@@@"            ODISPLAY('SDFMV1',IMAGE\DRUM\OI
)@@G@@ADDR(PKT)); @I@@@@             IF MACRO\XFER\DADD EQ NEXT\BLOCK(ADDR1(PKOJ
)@@G@@T)) THEN " IN NEXT BUFFER     @F@@@@                READ\NEXT\BUFFER(PKTOK
)@@G@@); " SET UP TO READ FROM IT   @A@@@@             ELSE " MUST WORK HARDEROL
)@@G@@@E@@@@              BEGIN " NOT NEXT, MUST ACTUALLY READ IT IN    @D@@@@OM
)@@G@@                PSDFIC(PKT); " CLOSE CURRENT INPUT    @G@@@@            ON
)@@G@@    DRUM\ADDR(PKT) := MACRO\XFER\DADD; " SET DESIRED ADDRESS@D@@@@      OO
)@@G@@          PSDFIO(PKT); " OPEN TO CORRECT SPOT   @D@@@@              END;OP
)@@G@@ " OF READING APPROPRIATE BUFFER    @C@@@@           END; " OF CHECK FOROQ
)@@G@@ IN CURRENT BUFFER@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" NOW POINT TO BEGINNING OF IMAGE INOR
)@@G@@ BUFFER     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@          BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR(PKT) := ADDOS
)@@G@@R1(PKT) + MACRO\XFER\DISP; "  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@TERM; ___ CAER\DISP; "  OT
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS MODULE IS RESPONSOU
)@@G@@IBLE FOR ASSIGNING THE SCRATCH FILES@F@@@@" USED BY DPS.  CURRENTLY TWO OV
)@@G@@SCRATCH FILES ARE USED, ONE CONTAINS@F@@@@" THE SCRIPT BEING PROCESSED AOW
)@@G@@ND THE OTHER IS USED TO HOLD TEXT   @H@@@@" BEING PASSED TO AND FROM THEOX

)@@G@@ED F4 FILES ARE USED SO THAT DPS CAN RECOVER IN CASE OF     @H@@@@" A SYOZ
)@@G@@STEM CRASH.  IF THE USER IS BATCH OR CATALOGGED SCRATCH FILES ARE NOT   PA
)@@G@@@B@@@@" AVAILABLE TEMPORARY FILES ARE USED.     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@      PB
)@@G@@    COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('CHKPT-DEF',IMPORTEDPC
)@@G@@);    @B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPD

)@@G@@PY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@PI
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@" THIS FIASG PACKET IS USED TO GET SCRATCH FILES.     @[@@@@PJ
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@DECLARE   SCRATCH\FIP: STATIC LOCATABLE MAPPED  @A@@@@      PK
)@@G@@       [*(8): INTEGER WORD];  @[@@@@"     @G@@@@DECLARE   FIP\SCRATCH: SPL
)@@G@@TATIC WORD MACHINE POINTER := LOC(SCRATCH\FIP); @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THISPM
)@@G@@ IS THE ONLY PLACE WHERE THE ACTUAL SCRATCH FILE NAMES ARE  @F@@@@" CODEPN
)@@G@@D.  THE EDITOR FILE NAMES ARE PLACED IN THE EDITOR CALL     @E@@@@" PACKPO
)@@G@@ET, THE DPS FILE NAME IS PLACED IN THE DUMMY PACKET.  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PP

)@@G@@ CHARACTERS := 'DPS$SF';@[@@@@"     @B@@@@DECLARE   ED\SCRATCH: INTEGER PR
