)@@G@@"     @B@@@@DECLARE   ED\CALL: INTEGER WORD STATIC    @C@@@@          !*PT
)@@G@@: 6 FIELDATA CHARACTERS := 'DPS$EC';@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@DECLARPU

)@@G@@ATIC  @C@@@@          !*: 6 FIELDATA CHARACTERS := '$PERM$';@[@@@@"     PX
)@@G@@@C@@@@DECLARE   AKQZ\OPTIONS: INTEGER WORD STATIC     @C@@@@          !*PY
)@@G@@: 6 FIELDATA CHARACTERS := 'AKQZ  ';@[@@@@"     @B@@@@DECLARE   AKZ\OPTIPZ
)@@G@@ONS: INTEGER WORD STATIC@C@@@@          !*: 6 FIELDATA CHARACTERS := 'AKQA
)@@G@@Z   ';@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS FLAG WILL BE SET FALSE WHEN A CATALOGGED QB
)@@G@@FILE CANNOT BE    @G@@@@" OBTAINED.  THUS ONLY IF ALL FILES ARE AVAILABLQC
)@@G@@E DO WE USE CATTED.     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@DECLARE   ALL\FILES\AVAILABLE:QD
)@@G@@ WORD CONDITION;  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE RECOV\ASK\USER IMPORTED ('QE
)@@G@@RECOVASK')  @A@@@@          RESULT CONDITION WORD;    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@QF
)@@G@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED;     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @C@@@@PROCEDURE GEQG
)@@G@@T\SCRATCH\FILES EXPORTED ('ASGSCR') @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@          QUAL\GIVQH
)@@G@@EN(FIP\SCRATCH) := TRUE; " SET QUALIFIER GIVEN  @F@@@@          QUAL\ONEQI

)@@G@@          IF REALLY\DEMAND THEN     @B@@@@             GET\CATALOGGED\SCQQ
)@@G@@RATCH\FILES;@#@@@@          ELSE    @B@@@@             GET\TEMPORARY\SCRQR
)@@G@@ATCH\FILES; @ @@@@END; " OF GET\SCRATCH\FILES   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" TERMQS
)@@G@@INAL SESSION.  IF TEMPORARY FILES ALREADY EXIST WE MAY HAVE TO    @ @@@@QT
)@@G@@" SWITCH TO PERMANENT ONES.   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE GET\CATALOGGEDQU
)@@G@@\SCRATCH\FILES    @[@@@@BEGIN @G@@@@          INTERNAL\NAME\ONE := DPS\SQV
)@@G@@CRATCH; " DO FACIT$ TO FIND OUT     @F@@@@          INTERNAL\NAME\TWO :=QW
)@@G@@ TEMP\NAME; " IF SCRATCH FILE EXISTS@ @@@@          GET\FACILITIES\DATA;QX
)@@G@@@B@@@@          IF EQUIPMENT\CODE EQ 0 THEN     @C@@@@           BEGIN "QY
)@@G@@ FIRST CALL TO DPS IN JOB     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" DPS HAS NEVER BEEN CALQZ
)@@G@@LED YET IN THIS JOB.    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@             IF CATALOGGED\FILRA
)@@G@@ES\AVAILABLE(TRUE) THEN @C@@@@              BEGIN " TO USE CATALOGGED FIRB
)@@G@@LES   @F@@@@                READ\RECOVERY\BUFFER(PERM\NAME); " AND ASK URC
)@@G@@SER   @F@@@@                USE\CATALOGGED\FILES; " SET UP TABLES FOR DPRD
)@@G@@S     @D@@@@              END; " NORMAL USE OF CATALOGGED FILES   @D@@@@RE
)@@G@@             ELSE " CATALOGGED FILES NOT AVAILABLE SO @C@@@@            RF
)@@G@@  BEGIN " TO USE TEMPORARY FILES    @G@@@@                GET\TEMPORARY\RG
)@@G@@SCRATCH\FILES; " SET UP TABLES FOR DPS    @G@@@@                WARNING(RH
)@@G@@W\RECOVERY\DISABLED); " AND TELL USER ABOUT IT  @E@@@@              END;RI
)@@G@@ " OF INITIAL DIVERSION TO TEMP FILES     @C@@@@           END; " OF CODRJ
)@@G@@E IF NO TEMP FILE FOUND @E@@@@          ELSE " TEMP FILE FOUND SO DPS USRK
)@@G@@ED IN THE MEANTIME@E@@@@           BEGIN " TO CHECK FOR RECOVERY FROM TERL
)@@G@@MP FILE     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" DPS HAS ALREADY BEEN CALLED.  CHECK FOR RM
)@@G@@RECOVERY FROM TEMPORARY @C@@@@" FILE BEFORE SWITCHING TO CATALOGGED FILERN
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@             READ\RECOVERY\BUFFER(TEMP\NAME); " RO
)@@G@@AND ASK USER@D@@@@             IF RECOVERING THEN " DO NOT SWITCH YET   RP
)@@G@@@D@@@@              BEGIN " USE TEMP BUT TRY FOR CAT ANYWAY @E@@@@      RQ
)@@G@@          IF CATALOGGED\FILES\AVAILABLE(FALSE) THEN   @E@@@@            RR
)@@G@@       WARNING(W\CAT\AVAIL\UNUSED); " WARN USER @F@@@@                GERS
)@@G@@T\TEMPORARY\SCRATCH\FILES; " SET UP DPS TABLES  @C@@@@              END;RT
)@@G@@ " OF RECOVERY OF TEMP FILE   @E@@@@             ELSE " NO RECOVERY SWITRU
)@@G@@CH TO CATALOGGED FILES  @B@@@@              BEGIN " TRY FOR CATALOGGED  RV
)@@G@@@E@@@@                IF CATALOGGED\FILES\AVAILABLE(FALSE) THEN   @D@@@@RW
)@@G@@                 BEGIN " SWITCH TO CATALOGGED FILE    @A@@@@            RX
)@@G@@       FREE\TEMP\FILES; @G@@@@                   WARNING(W\RECOVERY\ENABRY
)@@G@@LED); " TELL USER WATS UP     @F@@@@                   READ\RECOVERY\BUFRZ
)@@G@@FER(PERM\NAME); " AND ASK USER@E@@@@                   USE\CATALOGGED\FISA
)@@G@@LES; " SET UP DPS DATA  @D@@@@                 END; " SWITCH TO CATALOGGSB
)@@G@@ED FILE     @F@@@@                ELSE " CATALOGGED FILES STILL NOT AVAISC
)@@G@@LABLE SO    @E@@@@                   GET\TEMPORARY\SCRATCH\FILES; " USE SD
)@@G@@TEMPS @C@@@@              END; " OF TRY FOR CATALOGGED FILES@C@@@@      SE
)@@G@@     END; " OF TRY FOR SWITCH TEMP -> PERM@B@@@@END; " OF GET\CATALOGGEDSF
)@@G@@\SCRATCH\FILES    @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCESG
)@@G@@DURE IS CALLED TO FIND OUT IF CATALOGGED SCRATCH FILES@F@@@@" ARE AVAILASH
)@@G@@BLE.  IT WILL NOT RETURN TRUE UNTIL ALL OF THE SCRATCH@ @@@@" FILES BECOSI
)@@G@@ME AVAILABLE.     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE CATALOGGED\FILES\AVAILABLESJ
)@@G@@(SPEAK: CONDITION WORD) @A@@@@          RESULT WORD CONDITION     @[@@@@SK
)@@G@@BEGIN @E@@@@          ALL\FILES\AVAILABLE := TRUE; " SET FILES AVAILABLESL
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" SET UP FIASG PACKETS FOR SCRATCH FILE ASSIGN  @[@@@@SM
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@          FILE\TWO(FIP\SCRATCH) := PERM\NAME;   @G@@@@      SN
)@@G@@    INTERNAL\NAME\GIVEN := TRUE; " INTERNAL NAME AVALABLE BUT     @F@@@@SO
)@@G@@          INTERNAL\NAME\FORCED := FALSE; " BUT DONT FORCE @USE    @B@@@@SP
)@@G@@          GIVEN\NAME\TWO := PERM\NAME;    @B@@@@          ASSIGN\OPTIONSSQ
)@@G@@\GIVEN := TRUE; " @[@@@@"     @F@@@@          GET\CAT\FILE(DPS\SCRATCH,SSR
)@@G@@PEAK); " GET DPS SCRATCH FILE @G@@@@          GET\CAT\FILE(ED\SCRATCH,SPSS
)@@G@@EAK); " GET EDITOR SCRATCH FILE     @F@@@@          GET\CAT\FILE(ED\CALLST
)@@G@@,SPEAK); " GET EDITOR CALL FILE     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@          RETURN(ASU
)@@G@@LL\FILES\AVAILABLE); " RETURN STATUS TO CALLER  @A@@@@END; " OF CATALOGGSV
)@@G@@ED\FILES\AVAILABLE@[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE GET\CAT\FILE(NAME1: INTEGESW
)@@G@@R WORD,SPEAK: CONDITION WORD) @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          DIAGNOSE\ERRORSX
)@@G@@S := FALSE; @B@@@@          FILE\ONE(FIP\SCRATCH) := NAME1; @A@@@@      SY
)@@G@@    GIVEN\NAME\ONE := NAME1;  @B@@@@          ASSIGN\OPTIONS := AKZ\OPTISZ
)@@G@@ONS; "@F@@@@          ASSIGN\FILE\FOR\WRITING(FIP\SCRATCH); " @ASG,AKXZ TA
)@@G@@FILE  @F@@@@          IF CSF\BIT(28) OR CSF\BIT(30) THEN " FILE DESTROYETB
)@@G@@D     @C@@@@           BEGIN " TO DELETE AND REASSIGN IT    @C@@@@      TC
)@@G@@       ASSIGN\OPTIONS := AKQZ\OPTIONS; "  @D@@@@             ASSIGN\FILETD
)@@G@@\FOR\WRITING(FIP\SCRATCH);    @E@@@@             FILE\FREE\CODE := FIB\FTE
)@@G@@REE; " K OPTION FILE    @^@@@@             FREE\FILE; @E@@@@            TF
)@@G@@ CSF\BITS := O'400010000000'; " NOTE SETS BIT 15@D@@@@           END; " TG
)@@G@@OF KLUGE TO GET RID OF DISABLED FILE@D@@@@          IF CSF\BIT(15) THEN TH
)@@G@@" FILE DOES NOT EXIST   @A@@@@           BEGIN " TO CATALOG IT    @B@@@@TI
)@@G@@             DIAGNOSE\ERRORS := TRUE;     @E@@@@             CSF\BITS :=TJ
)@@G@@ CATALOG\FAST\FILE(FIP\SCRATCH); "  @A@@@@             IF CSF\BITS GE 0 TK
)@@G@@THEN  @G@@@@                ASSIGN\FILE\FOR\WRITING(FIP\SCRATCH); " @ASGTL
)@@G@@,AKXZ FILE  @A@@@@           END; " CATALOGGING FILE  @C@@@@          IFTM
)@@G@@ SPEAK THEN DIAGNOSE\FIASG\ERROR;   @D@@@@          IF CSF\BITS LT 0 THETN
)@@G@@N " FILE NOT AVAILABLE  @F@@@@             ALL\FILES\AVAILABLE := FALSE;TO
)@@G@@ " TRIGGER TEMP FILE USE@^@@@@END; " OF GET\CAT\FILE  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@TP
)@@G@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO SET THE INTERNAL PACKETS TO USE     @B@@@@TQ
)@@G@@" THE NEWLY CATALOGGED SCRATCH FILES.     @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE USTR
)@@G@@E\CATALOGGED\FILES@[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          DPS\SCRATCH\NAME(2) := PERTS
)@@G@@M\NAME;     @B@@@@          ED\SCRATCH\NAME(2) := PERM\NAME;@D@@@@      TT
)@@G@@    ED\SCRATCH\INTERNAL\NAME(2) := PERM\NAME;   @B@@@@          ED\CALL\TU
)@@G@@NAME(2) := PERM\NAME;   @ @@@@END; " OF USE\CATALOGGED\FILES@#@@@@CONTROTV
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO GET TEMPORARTW
)@@G@@Y FILES IN CASE OF@C@@@@" BATCH RUN OR CATALOGGED FILES NOT AVAILABLE.  TX
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE GET\TEMPORARY\SCRATCH\FILES     @[@@@@BEGIN TY
)@@G@@@A@@@@          DIAGNOSE\ERRORS := TRUE;  @B@@@@          INTERNAL\NAME\TZ
)@@G@@TWO := TEMP\NAME; @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          GET\TEMP\FILE(DPS\SCRATCH)UA
)@@G@@; " GET DPS SCRATCH FILE@C@@@@          DPS\SCRATCH\NAME(2) := TEMP\NAMEUB
)@@G@@;     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@          GET\TEMP\FILE(ED\SCRATCH); " GET EDITOUC
)@@G@@R SCRATCH FILE    @D@@@@          ED\SCRATCH\INTERNAL\NAME(2) := TEMP\NAUD
)@@G@@ME;   @B@@@@          ED\SCRATCH\NAME(2) := TEMP\NAME;@[@@@@"     @E@@@@UE
)@@G@@          GET\TEMP\FILE(ED\CALL); " GET EDITOR CALL FILE    @F@@@@      UF
)@@G@@    ED\CALL\NAME(2) := TEMP\NAME; " SET EDITOR CALL NAME    @B@@@@END; "UG
)@@G@@ OF GET\TEMPORARY\SCRATCH\FILES     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE GET\TEMPUH
)@@G@@\FILE(NAME1: INTEGER WORD)    @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          INTERNAL\NAME\UI
)@@G@@ONE := NAME1;     @ @@@@          GET\FACILITIES\DATA;@B@@@@          IFUJ
)@@G@@ EQUIPMENT\CODE EQ 0 THEN     @A@@@@           BEGIN " TO @ASG,T FILE   UK
)@@G@@@C@@@@             FILE\ONE(FIP\SCRATCH) := NAME1;    @C@@@@            UL
)@@G@@ FILE\TWO(FIP\SCRATCH) := TEMP\NAME;@E@@@@             CSF\BITS := ASSIGUM
)@@G@@N\TEMP\FILE(FIP\SCRATCH);     @B@@@@             IF CSF\BITS LT 0 THEN EUN
)@@G@@RROR; @ @@@@           END; " OF ASG,T    @^@@@@END; " OF GET\TEMP\FILE UO
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO FREE THE TEMPORARY FILESUP
)@@G@@ WHEN @A@@@@" CATALOGGED FILES BECOME AVAILABLE.@[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDUQ
)@@G@@URE FREE\TEMP\FILES     @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          GIVEN\NAME\TWO := TEUR
)@@G@@MP\NAME;    @B@@@@          FILE\FREE\CODE := FIB\FREE;     @[@@@@"     US
)@@G@@@B@@@@          GIVEN\NAME\ONE := DPS\SCRATCH;  @^@@@@          FREE\FILUT
)@@G@@E;    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@          GIVEN\NAME\ONE := ED\SCRATCH;   @^@@@@UU
)@@G@@          FREE\FILE;    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          GIVEN\NAME\ONE := EDUV
)@@G@@\CALL;@^@@@@          FREE\FILE;    @ @@@@END; " OF FREE\TEMP\FILES     UW
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO UX
)@@G@@READ THE RECOVERY BUFFER IN SECTOR  @G@@@@" ONE OF THE SCRATCH FILE.  IFUY
)@@G@@ IT IS THERE WE WILL ASK THE USER IF HE   @G@@@@" WANTS TO RECOVER.  IF UZ
)@@G@@SO THE GLOBAL FLAG 'RECOVERING' WILL BE SET.    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDVA
)@@G@@URE READ\RECOVERY\BUFFER(NAME2: INTEGER WORD)   @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     VB
)@@G@@@B@@@@DECLARE   PACKET: MACHINE POINTER WORD;   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@      VC
)@@G@@    COPY ('IO-DEF',IMPORTED); @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          RECOVERING := VD
)@@G@@FALSE;@A@@@@          PACKET := LOC(GENPKT);    @E@@@@          FILE\NAMVE
)@@G@@E1 := DPS\SCRATCH; " READ FROM DPS FILE   @E@@@@          FILE\NAME2 := VF
)@@G@@NAME2; " ARG TELLS US TEMP OR PERM  @A@@@@          FUNCTION := IO\FUNC\VG
)@@G@@READ; @ @@@@          WORD\COUNT := 28;   @C@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR :=VH
)@@G@@ LOC(RECOVERY\BUFFER);  @ @@@@          DRUM\ADDR := 1;     @D@@@@      VI
)@@G@@    IOW(PACKET); " NO ERROR CHECK CAUSE OF IO 5 @ @@@@          IF STATUVJ
)@@G@@S EQ 0 AND  @D@@@@             RECOVERY\IDENT EQ DPS\ABSOLUTE\ID AND    VK
)@@G@@@B@@@@             DPS\STATUS NE DPS\EXITED THEN@G@@@@             RECOVVL
)@@G@@ERING := RECOV\ASK\USER; " ASK USER ABOUT RECOVERY    @#@@@@          REVM
)@@G@@TURN; @ @@@@END; " OF READ\RECOVERY\BUFFER@[@@@@TERM; ___ GEAD\RECOVERY\VN
)@@G@@BUFFER@[@@@@TERM; ___ GET\CAT\FILE(DPS\SCRATCH,SPEAK); " GET DPS SCRATCHVO
)@@G@@ FILE @G@@@@          GE*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@MODULE@[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THISVP
)@@G@@ MODULE CONTAINS A COLLECTION OF SUBROUTINES FOR MANIPULATING     @A@@@@VQ
)@@G@@" NON TEXT UNIT SCRATCH FILE SPACE. @F@@@@"  THEY ACQUIRE AND RELEASE I/VR
)@@G@@O PACKETS, SCRATCH FILE SPACE, AND  @F@@@@" ALLOW THE CALLER TO WRITE IMVS
)@@G@@AGES AND TO LATER READ THEM BACK.   @G@@@@"  THESE ROUTINES ARE USED BY VT
)@@G@@THE TOC HANDLERS AND THE MACRO HANDLERS.  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COVU
)@@G@@PY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('BLOCK-PROCS',IMPORTED);  VV
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CVW
)@@G@@ORE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @A@@@@          COPY ('IO-DEF1',IMPORTED);@B@@@@VX
)@@G@@          COPY ('IO-PROCS',IMPORTED);     @F@@@@          COPY ('MACRO-DVY
)@@G@@EF',IMPORTED); " KLUGE - GET XQTMACSIZ    @B@@@@          COPY ('PIO-PROVZ
)@@G@@CS',IMPORTED);    @@@@@@@E@@@@DECLARE   DUMMY\PACKET(PACKET\LENGTH): WORWA
)@@G@@D INTEGER STATIC  @A@@@@           IMPORTED ('DUMMYP');     @@@@@@@ @@@@WB
)@@G@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED;     @@@@@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\FILE(%PACWC
)@@G@@KET: WORD MACHINE POINTER,    @F@@@@           %BUFFER: WORD MACHINE POIWD
)@@G@@NTER,ADDRESS: WORD INTEGER)   @ @@@@           EXPORTED ('INITFI')@[@@@@WE
)@@G@@BEGIN @@@@@@@D@@@@DECLARE   NEW\PACKET(*): WORD INTEGER BASED (PACKET); WF
)@@G@@@@@@@@@A@@@@          IF PACKET EQ NULL\PTR THEN@H@@@@             PACKEWG
)@@G@@T := ALLOCATE\CORE(PACKET\LENGTH); " ALLOCATE THE PACKET    @B@@@@      WH
)@@G@@    IF FILE\NAME1(PACKET) EQ 0 THEN @H@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO PACWI
)@@G@@KET\LENGTH DO " COPY DUMMY PACKET TO NEW PACKET @C@@@@              BEGIWJ
)@@G@@N " TO COPY OVER THE PACKET   @E@@@@                IF NEW\PACKET(I) NE WK
)@@G@@0 THEN " *** DEBUG P    @A@@@@                   ERROR; " ***DEBUG@D@@@@WL
)@@G@@                NEW\PACKET(I) := DUMMY\PACKET(I);     @#@@@@            WM
)@@G@@  END;@B@@@@          FILE\FORMAT(PACKET) := DPS\FILE;@C@@@@          IFWN
)@@G@@ ADDR1(PACKET) EQ NULL\PTR THEN     @F@@@@             ADDR1(PACKET) := WO
)@@G@@ALLOCATE\CORE(BLOCK\WORD\SIZE);     @C@@@@          IF ADDR2(PACKET) EQ WP
)@@G@@NULL\PTR THEN     @F@@@@             ADDR2(PACKET) := ALLOCATE\CORE(BLOCWQ
)@@G@@K\WORD\SIZE);     @E@@@@          IF USER\IMAGE\BUFFER(PACKET) EQ NULL\PWR
)@@G@@TR THEN     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             IF BUFFER EQ NULLWS
)@@G@@\PTR THEN   @G@@@@                USER\IMAGE\BUFFER(PACKET) := ALLOCATE\WT
)@@G@@CORE(INPUT\LEN);  @#@@@@             ELSE @D@@@@                USER\IMAWU
)@@G@@GE\BUFFER(PACKET) := BUFFER;  @#@@@@           END;   @H@@@@          BUWV
)@@G@@FFER := USER\IMAGE\BUFFER(PACKET); " RETURN IMAGE BUFFER POINTER  @C@@@@WW
)@@G@@          START\DRUM\ADDR(PACKET) := ADDRESS;   @A@@@@          FUNCTIONWX
)@@G@@(PACKET) := 0;    @F@@@@          CARD\SEQ\NUMBER(PACKET) := 0; " INITIAWY
)@@G@@LIZE CARD NUMBER  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS SUBROUTINE IS USEWZ
)@@G@@D TO INITIALIZE A FILE FOR READING  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIXA
)@@G@@ZE\FILE\READING(%PACKET: WORD MACHINE     @G@@@@           POINTER LOCATXB
)@@G@@ABLE, %BUFFER: WORD MACHINE POINTER LOCATABLE,  @D@@@@           ADDRESSXC
)@@G@@: WORD INTEGER) EXPORTED ('INITFIR')@[@@@@"     @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@      XD
)@@G@@    INITIALIZE\FILE(%PACKET,%BUFFER,ADDRESS);   @C@@@@          FUNCTIONXE
)@@G@@(PACKET) := IO\FUNC\READ;     @E@@@@          DRUM\ADDR(PACKET) := STARTXF
)@@G@@\DRUM\ADDR(PACKET);     @ @@@@          PSDFIO(PACKET);     @[@@@@END;  XG
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" INITIALIZE PACKET TO READ FROM EXTERNAL XH
)@@G@@(SDF) FILE/ELEMENT.     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\EXTERNAL\XI
)@@G@@READ  @G@@@@             (FILE\NAME\ONE: INTEGER WORD " FIRST WORD OF FIXJ
)@@G@@LE NAME     @G@@@@             ,FILE\NAME\TWO: INTEGER WORD " SECOND WORXK
)@@G@@D OF FILE NAME    @F@@@@             ,FILE\ADDRESS:  INTEGER WORD " SECTXL
)@@G@@OR ADDR START     @A@@@@             ) EXPORTED ('INITFEXT')@F@@@@      XM
)@@G@@       RESULT MACHINE POINTER WORD " TO PACKET ALLOCATED    @[@@@@BEGIN XN
)@@G@@@F@@@@DECLARE   PACKET: LOCATABLE MACHINE WORD POINTER; " TO PACKET     XO
)@@G@@@G@@@@DECLARE   BUFFER: LOCATABLE MACHINE WORD POINTER; " TO INPUT BUFFEXP
)@@G@@R     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" ALLOCATE PACKET AND INITIALIZE    @[@@@@"     XQ
)@@G@@@C@@@@          PACKET := ALLOCATE\CORE(XQTMACSIZ);   @D@@@@          BUXR
)@@G@@FFER := PACKET; " SO NO IMAGE ALLOCATED   @E@@@@          INITIALIZE\FILXS
)@@G@@E(%PACKET,%BUFFER,FILE\ADDRESS);    @[@@@@"     @#@@@@" RESET FILE NAME XT
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@          FILE\NAME1(PACKET) := FILE\NAME\ONE;  @C@@@@XU
)@@G@@          FILE\NAME2(PACKET) := FILE\NAME\TWO;  @D@@@@          EXEC\WORXV
)@@G@@D(PACKET) := 0; " CLEAR EXEC LINK   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" INITIALIZE EXTERXW
)@@G@@NAL PACKET. @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          FILE\FORMAT(PACKET) := SDF\FILE;XX
)@@G@@ " SET SDF TYPE   @G@@@@          DRUM\ADDR(PACKET) := START\DRUM\ADDR(PXY
)@@G@@ACKET); " DRUM ADDR     @B@@@@          RETURN(PACKET); " TO CALLER     XZ
)@@G@@@A@@@@END; " INITIALIZE\EXTERNAL\READ     @E@@@@" THIS SUBROUTINE IS USEYA
)@@G@@D TO INITIALIZE A FILE FOR WRITTING @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIYB
)@@G@@ZE\FILE\WRITTING(%PACKET: WORD MACHINE    @ @@@@           POINTER LOCATYC
)@@G@@ABLE, @G@@@@           %BUFFER: WORD MACHINE POINTER LOCATABLE) EXPORTEDYD
)@@G@@ ('INITFIW')@[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          INITIALIZE\FILE(%PACKET,%BUFFER,YE
)@@G@@0);   @C@@@@          FUNCTION(PACKET) := IO\FUNC\WRITE;    @ @@@@      YF
)@@G@@    PSDFOO(PACKET);     @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDYG
)@@G@@URE WRITE\FILE(PACKET: WORD MACHINE POINTER,    @D@@@@           CHARS: YH
)@@G@@WORD INTEGER) EXPORTED ('WRITFI')   @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@          IF FUNCTYI
)@@G@@ION(PACKET) EQ IO\FUNC\READ THEN " ****DEBUG    @C@@@@             ERRORYJ
)@@G@@;                   " ***DEBUG@B@@@@          IF FUNCTION(PACKET) EQ 0 TYK
)@@G@@HEN   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             FUNCTION(PACKET) := IO\YL
)@@G@@FUNC\WRITE; @ @@@@             PSDFOO(PACKET);  @E@@@@             STARTYM
)@@G@@\DRUM\ADDR(PACKET) := DRUM\ADDR(PACKET);  @#@@@@           END;   @E@@@@YN
)@@G@@          CONTROL\WORD(PACKET) := 0; " CLEAR CONTROL WORD   @G@@@@      YO
)@@G@@    DATA\LENGTH(PACKET) := (CHARS+3)//4; " CONVERT CHARS TO WORDS @^@@@@YP
)@@G@@          PSDFO(PACKET);@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE READ\FILYQ
)@@G@@E(PACKET: WORD MACHINE POINTER,     @D@@@@           %CHARS: WORD INTEGEYR
)@@G@@R) EXPORTED ('READFI')  @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@          IF FUNCTION(PACKET) YS
)@@G@@EQ IO\FUNC\WRITE THEN " ****DEBUG   @C@@@@             ERROR;           YT
)@@G@@        " ***DEBUG@B@@@@          IF FUNCTION(PACKET) EQ 0 THEN   @#@@@@YU
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             FUNCTION(PACKET) := IO\FUNC\READ;  YV
)@@G@@@E@@@@             DRUM\ADDR(PACKET) := START\DRUM\ADDR(PACKET);  @ @@@@YW
)@@G@@             PSDFIO(PACKET);  @#@@@@           END;   @^@@@@          PSYX
)@@G@@DFI(PACKET);@A@@@@          IF END\FILE(PACKET) THEN  @F@@@@            YY
)@@G@@ CHARS := -1; " SET NEGATIVE TO INDICATE END OF FILE  @#@@@@          ELYZ
)@@G@@SE    @G@@@@             CHARS := DATA\LENGTH(PACKET) * 4; " RETURN CHARZA
)@@G@@ACTER LENGTH@F@@@@          CARD\SEQ\NUMBER(PACKET) := CARD\SEQ\NUMBER(PZB
)@@G@@ACKET) + 1; @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE CLOSE\FILE(PACKET: WZC
)@@G@@ORD MACHINE POINTER)    @ @@@@           EXPORTED ('CLOSFI')@[@@@@BEGIN ZD
)@@G@@@F@@@@          IF FUNCTION(PACKET) EQ 0 THEN " FILE ALREADY CLOSED     ZE
)@@G@@@^@@@@             RETURN;    @D@@@@          IF FUNCTION(PACKET) EQ IO\ZF
)@@G@@FUNC\READ THEN    @ @@@@             PSDFIC(PACKET);  @#@@@@          ELZG
)@@G@@SE    @D@@@@             IF FUNCTION(PACKET) EQ IO\FUNC\WRITE THEN@A@@@@ZH
)@@G@@                PSDFOC(PACKET);     @ @@@@             ELSE " ***DEBUG  ZI
)@@G@@@D@@@@                ERROR;                " ****DEBUG     @B@@@@      ZJ
)@@G@@    RELEASE\FILE\BUFFERS(PACKET);   @A@@@@          FUNCTION(PACKET) := ZK
)@@G@@0;    @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE RELEASE\FILE(PACKET: WORD ZL
)@@G@@MACHINE POINTER)  @A@@@@           EXPORTED ('RELSEFI')     @[@@@@BEGIN ZM
)@@G@@@D@@@@          IF ADDR1(PACKET) EQ NULL\PTR THEN " ***DEBUG@C@@@@      ZN
)@@G@@       ERROR;                   " ***DEBUG@C@@@@          FUNCTION(PACKEZO
)@@G@@T) := IO\FUNC\READ;     @E@@@@          DRUM\ADDR(PACKET) := START\DRUM\ZP
)@@G@@ADDR(PACKET);     @C@@@@          READ\AND\RELEASE(PACKET) := TRUE;     ZQ
)@@G@@@ @@@@          PSDFIO(PACKET);     @[@@@@NEXT: @C@@@@          IF NEXT\ZR
)@@G@@BLOCK(ADDR1(PACKET)) NE 0 THEN@#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@            ZS
)@@G@@ READ\NEXT\BUFFER(PACKET);    @^@@@@             GOTO NEXT; @#@@@@      ZT
)@@G@@     END;   @C@@@@          READ\AND\RELEASE(PACKET) := FALSE;    @A@@@@ZU
)@@G@@          RELEASE\FREED\FILE\BLOCKS;@D@@@@          FUNCTION(PACKET) := ZV
)@@G@@0; " CLEAR FUNCTION     @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE RELEASE\ZW
)@@G@@FILE\BUFFERS(PACKET: MACHINE WORD POINTER)@A@@@@           EXPORTED ('REZX
)@@G@@LFIBU')     @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          IF ADDR1(PACKET) NE NULL\PTR THEZY
)@@G@@N     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             RELEASE\CORE(ADDR1(PACKZZ
)@@G@@ET)); @B@@@@             ADDR1(PACKET) := NULL\PTR;   @#@@@@           EAA
)@@G@@ND;   @C@@@@          IF ADDR2(PACKET) NE NULL\PTR THEN     @#@@@@      AB
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @B@@@@             RELEASE\CORE(ADDR2(PACKET)); @B@@@@      AC
)@@G@@       ADDR2(PACKET) := NULL\PTR;   @#@@@@           END;   @E@@@@      AD
)@@G@@    IF USER\IMAGE\BUFFER(PACKET) NE NULL\PTR THEN     @#@@@@           BAE
)@@G@@EGIN  @D@@@@             RELEASE\CORE(USER\IMAGE\BUFFER(PACKET)); @D@@@@AF
)@@G@@             USER\IMAGE\BUFFER(PACKET) := NULL\PTR;   @#@@@@           EAG
)@@G@@ND;   @[@@@@END;  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THE FOLLOWAH
)@@G@@ING PROCEDURES ARE SIMILAR TO THE PRECEDING ONES EXCEPT     @F@@@@" THATAI
)@@G@@ THEY DO NOT TRANSFER DATA IMAGES BUT DO BLOCK I/O ONLY.    @G@@@@" USEDAJ
)@@G@@ FOR ROUTINES THAT HANDLE NON SDF DATA  E.G. THE UNIT HEADERS.    @[@@@@AK
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\FILE\BLOCK(%PACKET: WORD MACHINE POINTEAL
)@@G@@R,    @F@@@@           %BUFFER: WORD MACHINE POINTER, ADDRESS: WORD INTEAM
)@@G@@GER)  @A@@@@           EXPORTED ('INITFIBLK')   @[@@@@BEGIN @@@@@@@D@@@@AN
)@@G@@DECLARE   NEW\PACKET(*): WORD INTEGER BASED (PACKET); @@@@@@@A@@@@      AO
)@@G@@    IF PACKET EQ NULL\PTR THEN@D@@@@             PACKET := ALLOCATE\COREAP
)@@G@@(PACKET\LENGTH);  @B@@@@          IF FILE\NAME1(PACKET) EQ 0 THEN @C@@@@AQ
)@@G@@             FOR I := 1 TO PACKET\LENGTH DO     @D@@@@                NEAR
)@@G@@W\PACKET(I) := DUMMY\PACKET(I);     @A@@@@          IF BUFFER EQ NULL\PTAS
)@@G@@R THEN@D@@@@             BUFFER := ALLOCATE\CORE(BLOCK\WORD\SIZE);@A@@@@AT
)@@G@@          ADDR1(PACKET) := BUFFER;  @B@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR(PACKET) AU
)@@G@@:= BUFFER;  @B@@@@          NEXT\BLOCK(BUFFER) := ADDRESS;  @A@@@@      AV
)@@G@@    END\FILE(PACKET) := FALSE;@B@@@@          LAST\BLOCK(PACKET) := FALSAW
)@@G@@E;    @B@@@@          PREVIOUS\BLOCK(BUFFER) := 0;    @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@AX
)@@G@@"     @B@@@@" PROCEDURE TO READ THE NEXT FILE BLOCK   @E@@@@" IT EXPECTSAY
)@@G@@ THAT GET\PACKET HAS BEEN USED TO READ A UNIT   @E@@@@" HENCE THE UNIT HAZ
)@@G@@EADER LINK CAN BE FOUND IN ITS BUFFER.    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE REBA
)@@G@@AD\FILE\BLOCK(PACKET: WORD MACHINE POINTER)     @A@@@@           EXPORTEBB
)@@G@@D ('READFIBLK')   @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          IF NEXT\BLOCK(ADDR1(PACKETBC
)@@G@@)) EQ 0 THEN@B@@@@             END\FILE(PACKET) := TRUE;    @#@@@@      BD
)@@G@@    ELSE    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             DRUM\ADDR(PACKET)BE
)@@G@@ := NEXT\BLOCK(ADDR1(PACKET));@D@@@@             WORD\COUNT(PACKET) := BBF
)@@G@@LOCK\WORD\SIZE;   @C@@@@             FUNCTION(PACKET) := IO\FUNC\READ;  BG
)@@G@@@D@@@@             DRUM\ADDR(PACKET) := DRUM\ADDR(PACKET) + @B@@@@      BH
)@@G@@          BASE\DRUM\ADDR(PACKET);   @ @@@@             IOW(PACKET);     BI
)@@G@@@B@@@@             IF STATUS(PACKET) NE 0 THEN  @E@@@@                LIBJ
)@@G@@NK\TO\ERROR\REP\FOR\IO\ERROR(PACKET);     @C@@@@             IF READ\ANDBK
)@@G@@\RELEASE(PACKET) THEN   @G@@@@                CONDITIONAL\FREE\FILE\BLOCBL
)@@G@@K(DRUM\ADDR(PACKET),224);     @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@BM
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@" WRITE A FILE BLOCK    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\FIBN
)@@G@@LE\BLOCK(PACKET: MACHINE WORD POINTER)    @A@@@@            EXPORTED ('WBO
)@@G@@RITFIBLK')  @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          FUNCTION(PACKET) := IO\FUNC\WRITBP
)@@G@@E;    @C@@@@          WORD\COUNT(PACKET) := BLOCK\WORD\SIZE;@D@@@@      BQ
)@@G@@    IF PREVIOUS\BLOCK(ADDR1(PACKET)) EQ 0 THEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  BR
)@@G@@@H@@@@             DRUM\ADDR(PACKET) := ALLOCATE\FILE\BLOCK(224); " GET BS
)@@G@@FIRST BLOC  @E@@@@             START\DRUM\ADDR(PACKET) := DRUM\ADDR(PACKBT
)@@G@@ET);  @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@          ELSE    @E@@@@            BU
)@@G@@ DRUM\ADDR(PACKET) := NEXT\BLOCK(ADDR1(PACKET));@A@@@@          IF LAST\BV
)@@G@@BLOCK(PACKET) THEN@C@@@@             NEXT\BLOCK(ADDR1(PACKET)) := 0;    BW
)@@G@@@#@@@@          ELSE    @G@@@@             NEXT\BLOCK(ADDR1(PACKET)) := BX
)@@G@@ALLOCATE\FILE\BLOCK(224);     @D@@@@          DRUM\ADDR(PACKET) := DRUM\BY
)@@G@@ADDR(PACKET) +    @A@@@@             BASE\DRUM\ADDR(PACKET);@^@@@@      BZ
)@@G@@    IOW(PACKET);  @B@@@@          IF STATUS(PACKET) NE 0 THEN     @D@@@@CA
)@@G@@             LINK\TO\ERROR\REP\FOR\IO\ERROR(PACKET);  @E@@@@          HECB
)@@G@@ADER\LINK(ADDR1(PACKET)) := 0; " CLEAR LINK WORD@F@@@@          PREVIOUSCC
)@@G@@\BLOCK(ADDR1(PACKET)) := DRUM\ADDR(PACKET) -    @D@@@@             BASE\CD
)@@G@@DRUM\ADDR(PACKET); " SAVE BACK LINK @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THISCE
)@@G@@ ROUTINE ADDS ANOTHER PAGE TO CURRENTLY ACTIVE  @E@@@@" PAGE SET.  IT ASCF
)@@G@@SUMES THE CURRENT PAGE IS THE LAST PAGE   @F@@@@" AND THAT IT HAS JUST BCG
)@@G@@EEN READ OR WRITTEN BY A BOLCK ROUTINE    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE ADCH
)@@G@@D\FILE\BLOCK(PACKET: MACHINE WORD POINTER)@A@@@@            EXPORTED ('ACI
)@@G@@DDFIBLK')   @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          FUNCTION(PACKET) := IO\FUNC\WRITCJ
)@@G@@E;    @F@@@@          NEXT\BLOCK(ADDR1(PACKET)) := ALLOCATE\FILE\BLOCK(2CK
)@@G@@24);  @^@@@@          IOW(PACKET);  @B@@@@          IF STATUS(PACKET) NECL
)@@G@@ 0 THEN     @D@@@@             LINK\TO\ERROR\REP\FOR\IO\ERROR(PACKET);  CM
)@@G@@@E@@@@          HEADER\LINK(ADDR1(PACKET)) := 0; " CLEAR LINK WORD@F@@@@CN

)@@G@@             BASE\DRUM\ADDR(PACKET); " SAVE BACK LINK @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@CP
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" WILL WRITE A BLOCK JUST READ OR JUST WRITTEN, CALLED AFTERCQ
)@@G@@@^@@@@" TEXT CHANGE IN BLOCK  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE REWRITE\FILE\BCR
)@@G@@LOCK(PACKET: WORD MACHINE POINTER)  @A@@@@           EXPORTED ('REWRITFICS
)@@G@@BLK') @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          FUNCTION(PACKET) := IO\FUNC\WRITE;    CT
)@@G@@@^@@@@          IOW(PACKET);  @B@@@@          IF STATUS(PACKET) NE 0 THECU
)@@G@@N     @D@@@@             LINK\TO\ERROR\REP\FOR\IO\ERROR(PACKET);  @[@@@@CV
)@@G@@END;  @[@@@@TERM; ___  B*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @B@@@@          COCW
)@@G@@PY ('FILE-CVT-DEF',IMPORTED); @A@@@@          COPY ('IO-DEF1',IMPORTED);CX
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('IO-PROCS',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('BCY
)@@G@@LOCK-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('PACKET-DEF',IMPORTED);   CZ
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('RUN-DATA-DEF',IMPORTED); @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDDA
)@@G@@URE ERROR IMPORTED;     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @]@@@@" GLOBDB
)@@G@@ALS   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DEFINE    BLOCKSIZE = 8,                 " SECTODC
)@@G@@RS    @C@@@@          SECTORSIZE = 28,               " WORDS@C@@@@      DD
)@@G@@    BLOCKWORDS = BLOCKSIZE*SECTORSIZE;    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE SWDE
)@@G@@ITCH\FILES IMPORTED ('CVTSWT');     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@DECLARE   WRITE\BUDF
)@@G@@FFER: MACHINE WORD POINTER; " TO CURRENT WRITE BUFFER @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DG
)@@G@@DECLARE UNIT\DIRECTORY\BUFFER: MAPPED STATIC LOCATABLE@ @@@@          [*DH
)@@G@@(2): INTEGER WORD @E@@@@          , UNIT\DIRECTORY(222): LOCATABLE INTEGDI
)@@G@@ER WORD];   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" LEVEL 2 OVERLAY OF FILE HEADER.   @[@@@@DJ
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@DEFINE    FILE\HEADER\LENGTH = 28; " WORD LENGTH OF HEADER  DK
)@@G@@@F@@@@DECLARE   FILE\HEADER: MAPPED STATIC LOCATABLE IMPORTED ('FILHDR')DL
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@      "1" [*: WORD LOGICAL    @ @@@@      "2" ,*: WORDDM

)@@G@@          ,FILE\HEADER\BLOCK\WORD\SIZE: 18 BIT INTEGER@C@@@@      "4" ,LDO
)@@G@@INK\TO\UNIT\DIRECTORY: WORD INTEGER @C@@@@      "5" ,LINK\TO\FILE\BIT\MADP

)@@G@@@C@@@@      "7" ,LINK\TO\TOC: WORD INTEGER LOCATABLE  @B@@@@      "8" ,LDR

)@@G@@S     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @]@@@@" UTILITIES @[@@@@"     DW
)@@G@@@^@@@@PROCEDURE SWITCH\BUFFERS@[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR(CUDX
)@@G@@R\PKT):=: " SWITCH@C@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR(NXT\PKT);   " BUFFERS     DY
)@@G@@@F@@@@          WRITE\BUFFER := BUFFER\ADDR(NXT\PKT); " SET BUFFER ADDR DZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE DRUM\READ(DRUM: INTEGER WORD)   EA
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@          DRUM\ADDR(CUR\PKT):=CUR\BAS + ABS(DRUM); " SEB
)@@G@@ET DRUM ADDR@ @@@@          IF DRUM LT 0 THEN   @E@@@@             IO(CUEC
)@@G@@R\PKT);                " NO WAIT IF NEG   @#@@@@          ELSE    @E@@@@ED
)@@G@@             IOWWEC(CUR\PKT);               " NORMALLY WAIT @[@@@@END;  EE
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE DRUM\WRITE(DRUM: INTEGER WORD)  @[@@@@BEGIN EF
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DRUM\ADDR(NXT\PKT):=ABS(DRUM); " SET DRUM ADDRESS @ @@@@EG
)@@G@@          IF DRUM LT 0 THEN   @E@@@@             IO(NXT\PKT);           EH
)@@G@@     " NO WAIT IF NEG   @#@@@@          ELSE    @E@@@@             IOWWEEI
)@@G@@C(NXT\PKT);               " NORMALLY WAIT @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@EJ
)@@G@@PROCEDURE READ\UNIT\DIRECTORY @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@DECLARE   TEMP\PTR: MACHEK
)@@G@@INE WORD POINTER; @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          TEMP\PTR := BUFFER\ADDR(CUEL
)@@G@@R\PKT); " SAVE BUFFER   @I@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR(CUR\PKT):=LOC(UNIT\DEM
)@@G@@IRECTORY\BUFFER); " READ UNIT DIRECTOR    @F@@@@          DRUM\READ(LINKEN
)@@G@@\TO\UNIT\DIRECTORY); " INTO ITS OWN BUFFER@E@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR(CUEO
)@@G@@R\PKT):=TEMP\PTR; " RESTORE BUFFER  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDEP
)@@G@@URE WRITE\UNIT\DIRECTORY@[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@DECLARE   TEMP\PTR: MACHINE WOEQ
)@@G@@RD POINTER; @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          TEMP\PTR := BUFFER\ADDR(NXT\PKT)ER
)@@G@@; " SAVE BUFFER   @G@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR(NXT\PKT):=LOC(UNIT\DIRECTOES
)@@G@@RY\BUFFER); " WRITE UNIT@G@@@@          DRUM\WRITE(LINK\TO\UNIT\DIRECTORET
)@@G@@Y); " DIR FROM ITS BUFFER     @E@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR(NXT\PKT):=TEMPEU
)@@G@@\PTR; " RESTORE BUFFER  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\FIEV
)@@G@@LE\HEADER   @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@DECLARE   TEMP\PTR: MACHINE WORD POINTER; EW
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@          TEMP\PTR := BUFFER\ADDR(NXT\PKT); " SAVE BUFEX
)@@G@@FER   @F@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR(NXT\PKT):=LOC(FILE\HEADER); " WRITE HEEY
)@@G@@ADER  @F@@@@          WORD\COUNT(NXT\PKT) := FILE\HEADER\LENGTH; " SET LEZ
)@@G@@ENGTH @D@@@@          DRUM\WRITE(0); " HEADER FROM ITS BUFFER     @E@@@@FA
)@@G@@          BUFFER\ADDR(NXT\PKT):=TEMP\PTR; " RESTORE BUFFER  @[@@@@END;  FB
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" MOVE DATA BLOCKS CHANGING LIFC
)@@G@@NX    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE COPY\LINKED\BLOCKS(OLD\ADDR: INTEGER WFD
)@@G@@ORD)  @ @@@@          RESULT INTEGER WORD @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   NEFE
)@@G@@W\ADDR: INTEGER WORD; " RESULT ADDRESS    @C@@@@DECLARE   COPY\LAST: INTFF
)@@G@@EGER WORD; " FOR LINKING@C@@@@DECLARE   COPY\THIS: INTEGER WORD; " TWO WFG
)@@G@@AYS   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@          NEW\ADDR := 0;@A@@@@          IF OLD\AFH
)@@G@@DDR NE 0 THEN     @B@@@@           BEGIN " COPYING A LINKED FILE  @[@@@@FI
)@@G@@"     @ @@@@" DO 1ST BLOCK AND UNIT HEADER@[@@@@"     @D@@@@            FJ
)@@G@@ DRUM\READ(OLD\ADDR); " READ 1ST BLOCK    @G@@@@             NEW\ADDR:=AFK
)@@G@@LLOCATE\FILE\BLOCK(BLOCKWORDS); " UPDATE ADDR   @D@@@@             SWITCFL
)@@G@@H\BUFFERS; " BLOCK TO WRITE\BUFFER  @F@@@@             DRUM\READ(HEADER\FM
)@@G@@LINK(WRITE\BUFFER)); " READ UNIT HDR@G@@@@             COPY\THIS := ALLOFN
)@@G@@CATE\FILE\BLOCK(BLOCKWORDS); " ALLOCATE   @G@@@@             HEADER\LINKFO
)@@G@@(WRITE\BUFFER) := COPY\THIS; " AND SET POINTER  @E@@@@             SWITCFP
)@@G@@H\BUFFERS; " UNIT HEADER TO WRITE\BUFFER  @D@@@@             DRUM\WRITE(FQ
)@@G@@COPY\THIS); " WRITE IT OUT    @D@@@@             SWITCH\BUFFERS; " BLOCKFR
)@@G@@ TO WRITE\BUFFER  @F@@@@             COPY\LAST:=0;                   " NFS
)@@G@@O PREVIOUS BLOCK  @F@@@@             COPY\THIS := NEW\ADDR; " SET THIS BFT
)@@G@@UFFERS ADDRESS    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" DO INTERMEDIATE BLOX, IF ANY@[@@@@FU
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@             WHILE NEXT\BLOCK(WRITE\BUFFER) NE 0 DO " MORE BFV
)@@G@@LOX   @B@@@@              BEGIN " COPYING A BLOCK     @G@@@@            FW
)@@G@@    DRUM\READ(-NEXT\BLOCK(WRITE\BUFFER)); " READ NEXT BLOCK @H@@@@      FX
)@@G@@          PREVIOUS\BLOCK(WRITE\BUFFER):=COPY\LAST; " UPDATE BACK LINK   FY
)@@G@@@D@@@@                COPY\LAST := COPY\THIS; " MOVE LINKS  @G@@@@      FZ
)@@G@@          COPY\THIS := ALLOCATE\FILE\BLOCK(BLOCKWORDS); " FWD LINK@D@@@@GA
)@@G@@                NEXT\BLOCK(WRITE\BUFFER) := COPY\THIS;@F@@@@            GB
)@@G@@    DRUM\WRITE(-COPY\LAST); " WRITE CURRENT BLOCK     @E@@@@            GC
)@@G@@    WAITEC(CUR\PKT);              " SYNCHRO-    @D@@@@                WAGD
)@@G@@ITEC(NXT\PKT);              " -NIZE @A@@@@                SWITCH\BUFFERSGE
)@@G@@;     @A@@@@              END; " COPYING A BLOCK@[@@@@"     @^@@@@" NOW GF
)@@G@@DO LAST BLOCK     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@             PREVIOUS\BLOCK(WRITE\BUGG
)@@G@@FFER):=COPY\LAST; " PUT IN BACK LINK@D@@@@             DRUM\WRITE(COPY\TGH
)@@G@@HIS); " WRITE LAST BLOCK@B@@@@           END; " COPYING LINKED FILE     GI
)@@G@@@ @@@@          RETURN(NEW\ADDR);   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDGJ
)@@G@@URE CONVERT\LEVEL2\TO\LEVEL3  @ @@@@          EXPORTED ('CVTL23') @[@@@@GK
)@@G@@BEGIN @C@@@@          WORD\COUNT(CUR\PKT) := BLOCKWORDS;    @C@@@@      GL
)@@G@@    WORD\COUNT(NXT\PKT) := BLOCKWORDS;    @G@@@@          LINK\TO\TOC :=GM
)@@G@@ COPY\LINKED\BLOCKS(LINK\TO\TOC); " COPY TOC    @ @@@@          READ\UNIGN
)@@G@@T\DIRECTORY;@H@@@@          LINK\TO\UNIT\DIRECTORY:=ALLOCATE\FILE\BLOCK(GO
)@@G@@BLOCKWORDS); " GET SPA  @G@@@@          UNIT\DIRECTORY(4) := COPY\LINKEDGP
)@@G@@\BLOCKS(UNIT\DIRECTORY(1));   @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO 3 DO  @E@@@@GQ
)@@G@@             UNIT\DIRECTORY(I) := 0; " CLEAR FLAGS AND PAGE @A@@@@      GR
)@@G@@    WRITE\UNIT\DIRECTORY;     @D@@@@          TRACKS\IN\FILE:=MAX\ALLOCAGS
)@@G@@TED\FILE\BLOCK;   @D@@@@          FILE\HEADER\LEVEL := 3; " SET NEXT LEVGT

)@@G@@" FOR NEXT CONVERSION   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@TERM; ___   @G@@@@          LIGV
)@@G@@NK\TO\TOC := COPY\LINKED\BLOCKS(LINK\TO\TOC); " COPY TOC    @ @@@@      GW
)@@G@@    READ\UNIT\DIRECTORY;*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @B@@@@" THIS MODULGX
)@@G@@E CONTAINS THE INPUT ROUTINES @C@@@@" PSDFI RETURNS THE NEXT NON-DELETEDGY
)@@G@@ DATA IMAGE @F@@@@" I/O ERRORS ARE CONSIDERED FATAL AND THE ERROR$ REP IGZ
)@@G@@S CALLED    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@HA
)@@G@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('IO-PROCHB
)@@G@@S',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('BLOCK-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@HC
)@@G@@      @A@@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED; " ***DEBUG@[@@@@      @E@@@@PROCEDHD
)@@G@@URE PSDFI (PACKET: WORD MACHINE POINTER) EXPORTED     @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@HE
)@@G@@          COPY('IO-DEF');     @A@@@@DECLARE   REM\BUF: INTEGER WORD;    HF
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @D@@@@DECLARE   USER\IMAGE\LOCATOR: MACHINE WORD POINTER;   HG
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @F@@@@DECLARE   USER\IMAGE(*): WORD INTEGER BASED(USER\IMAGEHH
)@@G@@\LOCATOR);  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@DECLARE   DATA\IMAGE(*): WORD INTEGER BASEHI
)@@G@@D(BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR);@[@@@@"     @^@@@@" BEGIN EXECUTABLE CODE @[@@@@HJ
)@@G@@"     @[@@@@      @C@@@@          IF ADDR1 = NULL\PTR OR " ***DEBUG     HK
)@@G@@@E@@@@             USER\IMAGE\BUFFER = NULL\PTR THEN " ***DEBUG   @A@@@@HL
)@@G@@                ERROR; " ***DEBUG   @]@@@@NEXT\IMAGE: @B@@@@          COHM
)@@G@@NTROL\WORD := DATA\IMAGE(1);  @D@@@@          IF (IMAGE\TYPE = O'077') THN
)@@G@@HEN  " END OF FILE@#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             END\FILE :=HO
)@@G@@ TRUE; " SET END OF FILE FLAG @^@@@@             RETURN;    @#@@@@      HP
)@@G@@     END;   @A@@@@          IF CONTROL\WORD < 0 THEN  @A@@@@            HQ
)@@G@@ REM := CONTROL\LENGTH; @#@@@@          ELSE    @A@@@@             REM :HR
)@@G@@= DATA\LENGTH;    @E@@@@          BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR := BUFFER\IMAGE\LHS
)@@G@@OCATOR + 1; @D@@@@          IF BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR = END\OF\BUFFER THENHT
)@@G@@@B@@@@             GET\NEXT\BUFFER(PACKET);     @D@@@@          USER\IMAHU
)@@G@@GE\LOCATOR := USER\IMAGE\BUFFER;    @]@@@@REM\LOOP:   @B@@@@          IFHV
)@@G@@ BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR + REM LE@A@@@@             END\OF\BUFFER THEN     HW
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO REM DO   @C@@@@HX
)@@G@@                USER\IMAGE(I) := DATA\IMAGE(I); @F@@@@             BUFFEHY
)@@G@@R\IMAGE\LOCATOR := BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR + REM;  @E@@@@             IF BUHZ
)@@G@@FFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR = END\OF\BUFFER THEN   @B@@@@                GET\NEXTIA
)@@G@@\BUFFER(PACKET);  @#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@          ELSE " IMAGE SIB
)@@G@@PANS BUFFERS"     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @G@@@@             REM\BUF := IC
)@@G@@OFFSET( END\OF\BUFFER , BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR ); @B@@@@             FOR IID
)@@G@@ := 1 TO REM\BUF DO     @G@@@@                USER\IMAGE(I) := DATA\IMAGIE
)@@G@@E(I); " COPY PARTIAL IMAGE    @F@@@@             REM := REM - REM\BUF; "IF
)@@G@@ DECREMENT REMAINDER OF IMAGE @G@@@@             USER\IMAGE\LOCATOR := UIG
)@@G@@SER\IMAGE\LOCATOR + REM\BUF; " BUMP @B@@@@             GET\NEXT\BUFFER(PIH
)@@G@@ACKET);     @ @@@@             GOTO REM\LOOP;   @#@@@@           END;   II
)@@G@@@D@@@@          IF IMAGE\TYPE NE 0 OR DELETE\CYCLE NE 0 THEN@ @@@@      IJ
)@@G@@       GOTO NEXT\IMAGE; @F@@@@          IMAGE\CORE\DISP := OFFSET(BUFFERIK
)@@G@@\IMAGE\LOCATOR,ADDR1);  @B@@@@"         ODISPLAY('IIMADR',IMAGE\ADDR);  IL
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @E@@@@PROCEDURE PSDFIO (PACKET: WORDIM
)@@G@@ MACHINE POINTER) EXPORTED    @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          COPY('IO-DEF')IN
)@@G@@;     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" BEGIN EXECUTABLE CODE @[@@@@"     @D@@@@      IO
)@@G@@    STATUS := 0; " CLEAR POSSIBLE BAD STATUS    @E@@@@          NEXT\BLOIP
)@@G@@CK := DRUM\ADDR; " FOR INTERNAL FORMAT    @C@@@@          ADDR1 :=: ADDRIQ
)@@G@@2; " SWITCH BUFFERS     @D@@@@          DRUM\ADDR := DRUM\ADDR - BUFFER\IR
)@@G@@SECTOR\SIZE;@A@@@@          GET\NEXT\BUFFER(PACKET);  @A@@@@          GEIS
)@@G@@T\NEXT\BUFFER(PACKET);  @C@@@@          END\FILE := FALSE; " NOT AT EOF IT
)@@G@@YET   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @E@@@@PROCEDURE GEIU
)@@G@@T\NEXT\BUFFER (PACKET: MACHINE WORD POINTER)    @ @@@@           EXPORTEIV
)@@G@@D ('GNB')   @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          COPY('IO-DEF');     @#@@@@CONTROIW
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" BEGIN EXECUTABLE CODE @[@@@@"     @C@@@@IX
)@@G@@          IF ADDR1 = NULL\PTR OR " ***DEBUG     @E@@@@             USER\IY
)@@G@@IMAGE\BUFFER = NULL\PTR THEN " ***DEBUG   @A@@@@                ERROR; "IZ
)@@G@@ ***DEBUG   @^@@@@          WAIT(PACKET); @D@@@@          IF STATUS NE 0JA
)@@G@@ AND INPUT\WORD\COUNT = 0 THEN@#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@            JB
)@@G@@ LINK\TO\ERROR\REP\FOR\IO\ERROR(PACKET);  @F@@@@             RETURN;    JC
)@@G@@              " SHOULD NEVER GET HERE     @#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@JD
)@@G@@          IMAGE\DRUM\ADDR := DRUM\ADDR;   @C@@@@          ADDR1 :=: ADDRJE
)@@G@@2; " SWITCH BUFFERS     @D@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR := ADDR2; " NEW ACCEJF
)@@G@@SS WORD     @A@@@@          CASEENTRY FILE\FORMAT "   @B@@@@          CAJG
)@@G@@SE DPS\FILE: " INTERNAL FORMAT@#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@            JH
)@@G@@ BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR := ADDR1 + 2; @D@@@@             IF NEXT\BLOCK NE JI
)@@G@@0 THEN " NOT LAST BLOCK @^@@@@              BEGIN     @B@@@@            JJ
)@@G@@    DRUM\ADDR := NEXT\BLOCK;  @B@@@@                IF READ\AND\RELEASE JK
)@@G@@THEN  @F@@@@                   CONDITIONAL\FREE\FILE\BLOCK(DRUM\ADDR,224JL
)@@G@@);    @E@@@@                DRUM\ADDR := DRUM\ADDR + BASE\DRUM\ADDR;    JM
)@@G@@@ @@@@                IO(PACKET);   @B@@@@              END; " TEST FOR JN
)@@G@@LAST BLOCK  @A@@@@           END; " INTERNAL FORMAT   @C@@@@          CAJO
)@@G@@SE SDF\FILE: " STANDARD DATA FORMAT @#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@      JP
)@@G@@       BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR := ADDR1;     @E@@@@             DRUM\ADDR :JQ
)@@G@@= DRUM\ADDR + BUFFER\SECTOR\SIZE;   @^@@@@             IO(PACKET);@ @@@@JR
)@@G@@           END; " SDF FORMAT  @B@@@@          ENDCASE; " FILE FORMAT SELJS
)@@G@@ECTION@C@@@@          END\OF\BUFFER := ADDR1 + WORD\COUNT;  @F@@@@      JT
)@@G@@    IMAGE\CORE\DISP := OFFSET(BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR,ADDR1);  @B@@@@"     JU
)@@G@@    ODISPLAY('IIMADR',IMAGE\ADDR);  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDJV
)@@G@@URE PSDFIC (PACKET: WORD MACHINE POINTER) EXPORTED    @[@@@@BEGIN @^@@@@JW

)@@G@@;     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('DJZ
)@@G@@EBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('IO-PROCS',IMPORTED);     KA
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('BLOCK-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@      @A@@@@PROCEDKB
)@@G@@URE ERROR IMPORTED; " ***DEBUG@[@@@@      @C@@@@DECLARE   BLOCK\ADDR: WOKC
)@@G@@RD INTEGER LOCATABLE;   @[@@@@      @E@@@@PROCEDURE PSDFO (PACKET: WORD KD
)@@G@@MACHINE POINTER) EXPORTED     @[@@@@BEGIN @I@@@@          COPY('IO-DEF')KE
)@@G@@;             " THIS MUST FOLLOW DEFINITION OF 'PACKET'     @A@@@@DECLARKF
)@@G@@E   REM\BUF: INTEGER WORD;    @[@@@@      @D@@@@DECLARE   USER\IMAGE\LOCKG
)@@G@@ATOR: MACHINE WORD POINTER;   @[@@@@      @F@@@@DECLARE   USER\IMAGE(*):KH
)@@G@@ WORD INTEGER BASED(USER\IMAGE\LOCATOR);  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@DECLARE   DAKI
)@@G@@TA\IMAGE(*): WORD INTEGER BASED(BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR);@[@@@@      @[@@@@KJ
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@" BEGIN EXECUTABLE CODE @[@@@@"     @[@@@@      @C@@@@      KK
)@@G@@    IF ADDR1 EQ NULL\PTR OR " ***DEBUG    @E@@@@             USER\IMAGE\KL
)@@G@@BUFFER = NULL\PTR THEN " ***DEBUG   @A@@@@                ERROR; " ***DEKM
)@@G@@BUG   @C@@@@          IF FILE\FORMAT EQ COPYV\FILE THEN     @#@@@@      KN
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @B@@@@             IF CONTROL\WORD LT 0 THEN    @B@@@@      KO
)@@G@@          REM := 0; " IGNORE IT     @#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@      KP
)@@G@@          REM := DATA\LENGTH; @B@@@@           END; " OF COPYV\FILE SETUKQ
)@@G@@P     @A@@@@          ELSE " ALL OTHER FILES    @#@@@@           BEGIN  KR
)@@G@@@F@@@@             DATA\IMAGE(1) := CONTROL\WORD; " SET CONTROL WORD    KS
)@@G@@@B@@@@             IF CONTROL\WORD LT 0 THEN    @B@@@@                REKT
)@@G@@M := CONTROL\LENGTH;    @#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@                REKU
)@@G@@M := DATA\LENGTH; @F@@@@             BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR := BUFFER\IMAGKV
)@@G@@E\LOCATOR + 1;    @C@@@@           END; " OF FILE SETUP OTHER THAN COPYVKW
)@@G@@@E@@@@          IF BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR EQ END\OF\BUFFER THEN     @B@@@@KX
)@@G@@             WRITE\THE\BUFFER(PACKET);    @D@@@@          USER\IMAGE\LOCKY
)@@G@@ATOR := USER\IMAGE\BUFFER;    @]@@@@REM\LOOP:   @B@@@@          IF BUFFEKZ
)@@G@@R\IMAGE\LOCATOR + REM LE@A@@@@             END\OF\BUFFER THEN     @#@@@@LA
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO REM DO   @C@@@@      LB
)@@G@@          DATA\IMAGE(I) := USER\IMAGE(I); @F@@@@             BUFFER\IMAGLC
)@@G@@E\LOCATOR := BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR + REM;  @E@@@@             IF BUFFER\ILD
)@@G@@MAGE\LOCATOR EQ END\OF\BUFFER THEN  @B@@@@                WRITE\THE\BUFFLE
)@@G@@ER(PACKET); @#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@          ELSE " IMAGE SPANS BLF
)@@G@@UFFERS"     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @G@@@@             REM\BUF := OFFSETLG
)@@G@@( END\OF\BUFFER , BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR ); @A@@@@             REM := REM LH
)@@G@@- REM\BUF;  @B@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO REM\BUF DO     @^@@@@      LI
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @C@@@@                DATA\IMAGE(I) := USER\IMAGE(I); LJ
)@@G@@@#@@@@              END;@F@@@@             USER\IMAGE\LOCATOR := USER\IMLK
)@@G@@AGE\LOCATOR + REM\BUF;  @B@@@@             WRITE\THE\BUFFER(PACKET);    LL
)@@G@@@ @@@@             GOTO REM\LOOP;   @#@@@@           END;   @G@@@@      LM
)@@G@@    IMAGE\CORE\DISP := OFFSET( BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR , ADDR1 );    @[@@@@LN
)@@G@@END;  @E@@@@PROCEDURE PSDFOC(PACKET: WORD MACHINE POINTER) EXPORTED     LO
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          COPY ('IO-DEF');    @[@@@@"     LP
)@@G@@@F@@@@DECLARE   DATA\IMAGE(*): WORD INTEGER BASED(BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR);LQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @A@@@@DECLARE   CORE: WORD INTEGER BASED; @[@@@@"     @B@@@@LR
)@@G@@DECLARE   COPYV\EOF: WORD INTEGER STATIC  @C@@@@          !*: 6 FIELDATALS
)@@G@@ CHARACTERS := '$@EOF$';@[@@@@"     @A@@@@DECLARE   LAST\LENGTH: WORD INLT
)@@G@@TEGER;@[@@@@      @C@@@@          IF FILE\FORMAT NE COPYV\FILE THEN     LU
)@@G@@@D@@@@             DATA\IMAGE(1) := -1; " SET END OF FILE   @D@@@@      LV
)@@G@@    ELSE " COMPUTE SECTOR LENGTH OF LAST WRITE  @^@@@@              BEGILW
)@@G@@N     @E@@@@             IF OFFSET(BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR,ADDR1) EQ 1 THENLX
)@@G@@@G@@@@                LAST\LENGTH := 0; " NO WORDS WRITTEN IN LAST BUFFELY
)@@G@@R     @F@@@@             ELSE " COMPUTE SECTOR LENGTH OF LAST BUFFER WRILZ
)@@G@@TTEN  @ @@@@                LAST\LENGTH :=@H@@@@                  ( 27+OMA
)@@G@@FFSET( BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR , ADDR1 ))//28; " SECTORS @F@@@@            MB
)@@G@@  END; " OF COMPUTING SECTOR LENGTH OF LAST WRITE     @E@@@@          LAMC
)@@G@@ST\BLOCK := TRUE; " INDICATE WRITING LAST BLOCK @A@@@@          WRITE\THMD
)@@G@@E\BUFFER(PACKET); @ @@@@          LAST\BLOCK := FALSE;@^@@@@          WAME
)@@G@@IT(PACKET); @ @@@@          IF STATUS NE 0 THEN @#@@@@           BEGIN  MF
)@@G@@@D@@@@             LINK\TO\ERROR\REP\FOR\IO\ERROR(PACKET);  @#@@@@      MG
)@@G@@     END;   @E@@@@          IF FILE\FORMAT EQ COPYV\FILE THEN " UNDO FUDMH
)@@G@@GE    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             DRUM\ADDR := DRUM\ADDR MI
)@@G@@+ LAST\LENGTH;    @B@@@@             WORD\COUNT := WORD\COUNT - 1;@E@@@@MJ
)@@G@@             BUFFER\SECTOR\SIZE := BUFFER\SECTOR\SIZE - 1;  @C@@@@      MK
)@@G@@       CORE(BUFFER\ADDR) := COPYV\EOF;    @C@@@@             IOWWEC(PACKML
)@@G@@ET); " WRITE LAST BLOCK @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  @#@@@@CONTROMM
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @E@@@@PROCEDURE PSDFOO (PACKET: WORD MACHINE POINTER) EXPORTMN
)@@G@@ED    @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          COPY('IO-DEF');     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECMO
)@@G@@T);   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" BEGIN EXECUTABLE CODE @[@@@@"     @C@@@@      MP
)@@G@@    STATUS := 0; " CLEAR ANY BAD STATUS   @E@@@@          CASEENTRY FILEMQ
)@@G@@\FORMAT " SELECT ROUTINE FOR FORMAT @C@@@@          CASE SDF\FILE: " STAMR
)@@G@@NDARD DATA FORMAT @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             DRUM\ADDR :MS
)@@G@@= DRUM\ADDR - BUFFER\SECTOR\SIZE;   @C@@@@             BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCAMT
)@@G@@TOR := ADDR1;     @#@@@@           END;   @^@@@@          CASE DPS\FILE:MU
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             BLOCK\ADDR := ALLOCATE\FILE\BMV
)@@G@@LOCK(224);  @B@@@@             NEXT\BLOCK := BLOCK\ADDR;    @G@@@@      MW
)@@G@@       DRUM\ADDR := BLOCK\ADDR; " RETURN BEGIN ADDRESS OF UNIT    @F@@@@MX
)@@G@@             START\DRUM\ADDR := DRUM\ADDR; " SAVE START ADDRESS   @A@@@@MY
)@@G@@             PREVIOUS\BLOCK := 0;   @C@@@@             BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCAMZ
)@@G@@TOR := ADDR1 + 2; @C@@@@             HEADER\LINK := 0; " NO HEADER YET  NA
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @D@@@@          CASE COPYV\FILE: " @COPY,V FORMANB
)@@G@@T OUTPUT    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             PREVIOUS\BLOCK :=NC
)@@G@@ 0; " NONE  @D@@@@             WORD\COUNT := WORD\COUNT + 1; " FUDGE IT ND
)@@G@@@E@@@@             BUFFER\SECTOR\SIZE := BUFFER\SECTOR\SIZE + 1;  @E@@@@NE
)@@G@@             DRUM\ADDR := DRUM\ADDR - BUFFER\SECTOR\SIZE;   @H@@@@      NF
)@@G@@       BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR := ADDR1 + 1; " DATA STARTS AFTER LENGTH    NG
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@          ENDCASE; " FILE FORMAT SELECTIONNH
)@@G@@@B@@@@          IMAGE\DRUM\ADDR := BLOCK\ADDR;  @G@@@@          IMAGE\CONI
)@@G@@RE\DISP := OFFSET( BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR , ADDR1 );    @C@@@@          ENNJ
)@@G@@D\OF\BUFFER := ADDR1 + WORD\COUNT;  @D@@@@          IO\DONE := FALSE; " NK
)@@G@@NO BLOCKS OUTPUT YET    @D@@@@          LAST\BLOCK:= FALSE; " NOT LAST BNL
)@@G@@LOCK YET    @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @E@@@@PROCEDNM
)@@G@@URE WRITE\THE\BUFFER (PACKET: MACHINE WORD POINTER)   @ @@@@           ENN
)@@G@@XPORTED ('WTB')   @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      @ @@@@          COPY('IO-DEF')NO
)@@G@@;     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" BEGIN EXECUTABLE CODE @[@@@@"     @^@@@@      NP
)@@G@@    WAIT(PACKET); @B@@@@          IF STATUS NE 0 THEN " I/O ERROR @#@@@@NQ
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             LINK\TO\ERROR\REP\FOR\IO\ERROR(PACKNR
)@@G@@ET);  @H@@@@             RETURN;                  " SHOULD NEVER COME BANS
)@@G@@CK FROM ERROR$    @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          CASEENTRY FILENT
)@@G@@\FORMAT "   @C@@@@          CASE DPS\FILE: " DPS LINKED BLOCKS    @#@@@@NU
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             IF LAST\BLOCK THEN     @D@@@@      NV
)@@G@@          BLOCK\ADDR := 0; " ZERO FORWARD LINK  @#@@@@             ELSE NW
)@@G@@@G@@@@                BLOCK\ADDR := ALLOCATE\FILE\BLOCK(224); " GET NEXTNX
)@@G@@ BLOCK@C@@@@             IMAGE\DRUM\ADDR := BLOCK\ADDR;     @F@@@@      NY
)@@G@@       NEXT\DRUM\ADDRESS := NEXT\BLOCK; " SAVE DRUM ADDRESS @G@@@@      NZ
)@@G@@       NEXT\BLOCK := BLOCK\ADDR; " SET FORWARD LINK IN OLD BUFFER @C@@@@OA
)@@G@@             ADDR1 :=: ADDR2; " SWITCH BUFFERS  @H@@@@             PREVIOB
)@@G@@OUS\BLOCK := NEXT\DRUM\ADDRESS; " SET BACK LINK IN NEW BUFF @G@@@@      OC
)@@G@@       DRUM\ADDR := NEXT\DRUM\ADDRESS; " SET CURRENT DRUM ADDRESS @C@@@@OD
)@@G@@             BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR := ADDR1 + 2; @G@@@@             NEXT\OE
)@@G@@BLOCK := BLOCK\ADDR; " SAVE ADDRESS OF NEXT BUFFER    @E@@@@            OF
)@@G@@ HEADER\LINK := 0; " NO HEADER IN FREE BUFFER   @A@@@@           END; " OG
)@@G@@INTERNAL FORMAT   @C@@@@          CASE SDF\FILE: " STANDARD DATA FORMAT OH
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             ADDR1 :=: ADDR2; " SWITCH BUFOI
)@@G@@FERS  @C@@@@             BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR := ADDR1;     @E@@@@      OJ
)@@G@@       DRUM\ADDR := DRUM\ADDR + BUFFER\SECTOR\SIZE;   @ @@@@           EOK
)@@G@@ND; " SDF FORMAT  @B@@@@          CASE COPYV\FILE: " @COPY,V FILE @#@@@@OL
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             IF LAST\BLOCK THEN " PARTIAL IMAGE OM
)@@G@@@H@@@@                BLOCK\ADDR := OFFSET(BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR,ADDR1) -ON
)@@G@@ 1; " WRDLEN@ @@@@             ELSE " FULL IMAGE@E@@@@                BLOO
)@@G@@OCK\ADDR := WORD\COUNT - 1; " FULL BUFFER @E@@@@             NEXT\BLOCK OP
)@@G@@:= BLOCK\ADDR; " SET WORD LENGTH    @C@@@@             ADDR1 :=: ADDR2; OQ
)@@G@@" SWITCH BUFFERS  @G@@@@             PREVIOUS\BLOCK := BLOCK\ADDR; " LENOR
)@@G@@GTH OF PREVIOUS BLOCK   @G@@@@             BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR := ADDR1OS
)@@G@@ + 1; " NEW IMAGE POINTER     @E@@@@             DRUM\ADDR := DRUM\ADDR OT
)@@G@@+ BUFFER\SECTOR\SIZE;   @#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@          ENDCASE;OU
)@@G@@ " FILE TYPE SELECTION  @C@@@@          END\OF\BUFFER := ADDR1 + WORD\COOV
)@@G@@UNT;  @D@@@@          BUFFER\ADDR := ADDR2; " NEW ACCESS WORD     @F@@@@OW
)@@G@@          DRUM\ADDR := DRUM\ADDR + BASE\DRUM\ADDR; " ADD OFFSET   @^@@@@OX
)@@G@@          IO(PACKET);   @B@@@@          IO\DONE := TRUE; " SET I/O DONE OY
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@:= BLOCK\ADDR; " SET WORD LENGTH    @C@@@@OZ
)@@G@@             ADDR1 :=: ADDR2; " SWITCH BUFFERS  @G@@@@             PREVIPA
)@@G@@OUS\BLOCK := BLOCK\ADDR; " LENGTH OF PREVIOUS BL*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULEPB
)@@G@@;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS MODULE CONTAINS ALL KEEP AND FLOATING KEEPC
)@@G@@P PROCEDURES@[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@PD
)@@G@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEPE
)@@G@@F',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CHAR-SIZE',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@PF
)@@G@@          COPY ('CORE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('DIRECT-PG
)@@G@@DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('GETPUT-PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@PH
)@@G@@          COPY ('PUSH-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SKIP-PRPI
)@@G@@OCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-COMMON',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@PJ
)@@G@@          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE ALPK
)@@G@@LOCATE\AREA(TYPE: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER) @E@@@@             IMPORTED ('PL
)@@G@@GETAREA') RESULT MACHINE POINTER;   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE CHECK\FOPM
)@@G@@R\LINE\BREAK IMPORTED ('CHKLNBRK'); @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE DUMP\TEXPN
)@@G@@T(%TEXT\PTR: MAPPED     @C@@@@                   [TAIL: 18 BIT MACHINE PPO
)@@G@@OINTER@G@@@@                   ,HEAD: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER]) IMPORTED PP
)@@G@@('DMPTXT'); @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE DO\END\OF\LINE\PROCESSING IMPORTPQ
)@@G@@ED ('EOLPRO');    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE LEAD\TO\TOP\OF\AREA IMPORTPR
)@@G@@ED ('LEDTOA');    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\END\OF\COLUMN IMPOPS
)@@G@@RTED ('PROEOC');  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\OUT\HEADING IMPORTED (PT
)@@G@@'PUTOUTHEDING');  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE REPLACE\TOP\LEADING(%PTR: PU
)@@G@@MAPPED@F@@@@                                    [TAIL: 18 BIT MACHINE POPV
)@@G@@INTER @F@@@@                                    ,HEAD: 18 BIT MACHINE POPW
)@@G@@INTER]@G@@@@                              ,LEADING: DISTANCE) IMPORTED (PX
)@@G@@'RETOPL');  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE SWITCH\TO\AREA(NEW\AREA: MACHINEPY
)@@G@@ POINTER)   @B@@@@             IMPORTED ('SWITCHAREA');     @[@@@@"     PZ
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL (EJECT);  @[@@@@"     @#@@@@"   .KEEP[,I]     @[@@@@" OR  QA
)@@G@@@#@@@@"   .KEEP,F[/T/B] @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" THE AREAS ARE ORGANIZED AS FQB
)@@G@@OLLOWS:     @B@@@@"         T => 1 => 2 => ... => N => NULL @E@@@@" WHERQC
)@@G@@E => INDICATE FORWARD CHAINING USING NEXT\AREA\PTR.   @E@@@@" ALL THE ARQD
)@@G@@EAS NUMBERED 1 TO N POINT BACK TO THE AREA THAT @A@@@@" REQUESTED IT VIAQE
)@@G@@ LAST\AREA\PTR.   @F@@@@" WHENEVER A .KEEP DIRECTIVE IS ENCOUNTERED, INCQF
)@@G@@LUDE\ALL\FLOATS   @#@@@@" IS ALWAYS RESET.@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PRQG
)@@G@@OCESS\KEEP\DIRECTIVE EXPORTED ('PROKEEP') @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @A@@@@QH
)@@G@@DECLARE   SAVE\OPTION: CONDITION    @B@@@@          ,NEW\AREA: MACHINE PQI
)@@G@@OINTER;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          IF AREA\END\PENDING AND AREA\TYPQJ
)@@G@@E EQ KEEP THEN    @C@@@@           BEGIN  " WE MUST HAVE I-OPTION ON    QK
)@@G@@@D@@@@             SAVE\OPTION := DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\I);   @C@@@@      QL
)@@G@@       DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\I) := FALSE;   @A@@@@             CHECK\FOR\LQM
)@@G@@INE\BREAK;  @D@@@@             DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\I) := SAVE\OPTION;   QN
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @G@@@@          IF AREA\TYPE EQ TEXT THEN  " OKAQO
)@@G@@Y, OTHERWISE WE ARE IN TROUBLE@#]@@@           BEGIN  @G@@@@            QP
)@@G@@ IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\I) AND DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\F) THEN  @A@@@@      QQ
)@@G@@          PUSH\WORD\BUFFER;   @A@@@@             CHECK\FOR\LINE\BREAK;  QR
)@@G@@@F@@@@             NEW\AREA := ALLOCATE\AREA(KEEP);  " GET NEXT AREA    QS
)@@G@@@A@@@@             IF BUFFER\TEXT THEN    @E@@@@                INHIBIT\QT
)@@G@@DISTRIBUTION := TRUE; " CURRENT AREA@C@@@@             WHILE NEXT\AREA\PQU
)@@G@@TR NE NULL\PTR DO @F@@@@                AREA\PTR := NEXT\AREA\PTR;  " CHQV
)@@G@@AIN THROUGH AREAS @E@@@@             NEXT\AREA\PTR := NEW\AREA;  " CHAINQW
)@@G@@ IN NEW AREA@B@@@@             SWITCH\TO\AREA(NEW\AREA);    @#@@@@      QX
)@@G@@     END;   @#@@@@          ELSE    @A@@@@             WARNING(W\KEEP\ERQY
)@@G@@ROR); @A@@@@END; " OF PROCESS\KEEP\DIRECTIVE    @[@@@@"     @]@@@@"   .EQZ
)@@G@@NDK   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\ENDK\DIRECTIVE EXPORTED ('PROERA
)@@G@@NDK') @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @B@@@@DECLARE   KEEP\CONTROL\WORD: 6 BIT LRB
)@@G@@OGICAL@^@@@@          !*: MAPPED    @A@@@@              [*: 2 BIT LOGICARC
)@@G@@L     @B@@@@              ,B\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDITION  @B@@@@            RD
)@@G@@  ,F\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDITION  @B@@@@              ,I\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDIRE
)@@G@@TION  @B@@@@              ,T\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDITION];@[@@@@"     @ @@@@RF
)@@G@@"         DISPLAY('-ENDKD',0);@B@@@@"         DISPLAY('ARTYPE',AREA\TYPERG
)@@G@@);    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@          IF (AREA\TYPE EQ KEEP) THEN     @#@@@@RH
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             KEEP\CONTROL\WORD := AREA\CONTROL\WRI
)@@G@@ORD;  @A@@@@             IF NOT(F\OPTION) THEN  @F@@@@                INRJ
)@@G@@CLUDE\ALL\FLOATS := TRUE; " FORCE THEM OUT NOW  @B@@@@             IF I\RK
)@@G@@OPTION AND F\OPTION THEN@G@@@@                CLOSE\I\OPTION\KEEP; " CLORL
)@@G@@SE LINE W/O DOING ENDKEEP     @C@@@@             ELSE " WE CAN CAUSE A LRM
)@@G@@INE BREAK   @^@@@@              BEGIN     @D@@@@                DIRECTIVRN
)@@G@@E\OPT(ASCII\I) := I\OPTION;   @I@@@@                AREA\END\PENDING := RO
)@@G@@TRUE; " FORCE E-O-L TO CALL PROCESS\ENDKEEP     @F@@@@                CHRP
)@@G@@ECK\FOR\LINE\BREAK; " THIS CALLS END\OF\LINE    @#@@@@              END;RQ
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @A[@@@END; " OF PROCESS\ENDK\DIRECTIVE    @#@@@@RR
)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" PROCESS\ENDKEEP IS CALLED:  @[@@@@RS
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@" 1. BY END-OF-LINE, IF AREA\END\PENDING AND TYPE=KEEP OR TERT
)@@G@@XT.   @G@@@@"    AT THE NEXT END-OF-LINE AFTER A .ENDK IS PROCESSED, PRORU
)@@G@@CESS\ENDKEEP@#@@@@"    IS CALLED TO:@F@@@@"      A. FIT THE KEEP ONTO THRV
)@@G@@E CURRENT PAGE (IF IT FITS), OR     @F@@@@"      B. FORCE A BREAK TO NEXRW
)@@G@@T PAGE (FOR NON-FLOAT KEEP), OR     @E@@@@"      C. LEAVE IT CHAINED IN RX
)@@G@@TO FLOAT TO THE NEXT PAGE.    @H@@@@"    NOTE THAT FOR NON-I-OPTION KEEPRY
)@@G@@S THE END-OF-LINE IS GENERATED BY THE     @G@@@@"    CALL TO CHECK\FOR\LRZ
)@@G@@INE\BREAK IN PROCESS\ENDK\DIRECTIVE, ABOVE!     @[@@@@"     @H@@@@" 2. BSA
)@@G@@Y END-OF-PAGE, IF TYPE=KEEP. IF NOT REALLY END-OF-PAGE (MULTI-COLUMN),  SB
)@@G@@@I@@@@"    ADVANCE COLUMN POINTER AND TAKE NONSTANDARD RETURN WITHOUT ENSC
)@@G@@DING THE KEEP.    @H@@@@"    BUT IF IN THE LAST (OR ONLY) COLUMN, ALL STSD
)@@G@@ACKED KEEPS ARE FORCED OUT.   @[@@@@"     @I@@@@" 3. BY END-OF-PAGE, IF SE
)@@G@@TYPE=TEXT AND NEXT\AREA\POINTER NE NULL (FLOATS EXIST).     @H@@@@"    SSF
)@@G@@ETS FLAG FLOAT\TEXT TO OUTPUT AT MOST ONE ADDITIONAL PAGE OF FLOATS.    SG
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @I@@@@" 4. AT ZONE-BREAK. FLAG INCLUDE-ALL-FLOATS IS SET BY SH
)@@G@@CALLER TO FORCE OUT KEEPS.    @[@@@@"     @H@@@@" 5. AT END-OF-TAKE, BY SI
)@@G@@MODULE FORMAT, WITH INCLUDE-ALL-FLOATS SET (DITTO).   @[@@@@"     @#@@@@SJ
)@@G@@" KNOWN PROBLEMS: @[@@@@"     @H@@@@" BECAUSE IT FORCES AN END-OF-PAGE ASK
)@@G@@ND THEN OUTPUTS KEEPS, THE USER HEADING   @H@@@@" MACRO (AT PAGETOP TRAPSL
)@@G@@) WILL NEVER BE TAKEN. THIS CAUSES THE USER HEADING   @F@@@@" TO COME OUSM
)@@G@@T BELOW THE KEEP, RATHER THAN AT THE TOP OF PAGE.     @[@@@@"     @H@@@@SN
)@@G@@" SOMETIMES BOTTOM FLOATS CAUSE THE REST OF THE DOCUMENT TO BE OUTPUT INSO
)@@G@@ SHORT@H@@@@" PAGES (PAGEHEIGHT-FLOATSIZE) UNTIL ZONE BREAK, WHEN THE FLSP
)@@G@@OAT THAT IS DOING @G@@@@" IT IS FINALLY FORCED OUT. SOMEWHAT TRICKY TO DSQ
)@@G@@UPLICATE, SEE KEEP2FIB. @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     SR
)@@G@@@C@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\ENDKEEP EXPORTED ('ENDKEEP')  @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@SS
)@@G@@"     @B@@@@DECLARE   SAVE\NEXT\PTR: MACHINE POINTER; @B@@@@DECLARE   FLST
)@@G@@OAT\TEXT: WORD CONDITION;     @B@@@@DECLARE   KEEP\CONTROL\WORD: 6 BIT LSU
)@@G@@OGICAL@^@@@@          !*: MAPPED    @A@@@@              [*: 2 BIT LOGICASV
)@@G@@L     @B@@@@              ,B\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDITION  @B@@@@            SW
)@@G@@  ,F\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDITION  @B@@@@              ,I\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDISX
)@@G@@TION  @B@@@@              ,T\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDITION];@[@@@@"     @ @@@@SY
)@@G@@"         DISPLAY('-PRENK',0);@B@@@@"         DISPLAY('ARTYPE',AREA\TYPESZ
)@@G@@);    @C@@@@"         DISPLAY('INCALL',INCLUDE\ALL\FLOATS); @C@@@@"     TA
)@@G@@    DISPLAY('AEPEND',AREA\END\PENDING);   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          FLTB
)@@G@@OAT\TEXT := FALSE;@F@@@@          IF NOT(INCLUDE\ALL\FLOATS OR AREA\END\TC
)@@G@@PENDING) THEN     @B@@@@           BEGIN " MUST BE END OF COLUMN  @B@@@@TD
)@@G@@             IF (AREA\TYPE EQ KEEP) THEN  @C@@@@              BEGIN " ENTE
)@@G@@D-OF-COLUMN IN KEEP     @H@@@@                IF (COLUMN\NUMBER EQ NUMBETF
)@@G@@R\OF\COLUMNS) THEN  " FULL PAGE     @G@@@@                   INCLUDE\ALLTG
)@@G@@\FLOATS := TRUE;  " FORCE OUT ALL FLOATS  @^@@@@                ELSE    TH
)@@G@@@C@@@@                 BEGIN " E-O-C BUT NOT E-O-P    @B@@@@            TI
)@@G@@       PROCESS\END\OF\COLUMN; @G@@@@                   RETURN;  " *** NOTJ
)@@G@@NSTANDARD RETURN - DONT END KEEP    @C@@@@                 END; " E-O-C TK
)@@G@@BUT NOT E-O-P     @B@@@@              END; " END-OF-COLUMN IN KEEP@B@@@@TL
)@@G@@             ELSE " HOPEFULLY IS TEXT     @G@@@@                FLOAT\TETM
)@@G@@XT := TRUE; " SET FLAG TO OUTPUT ONE COLUMN     @A@@@@           END; " TN
)@@G@@END-OF-COLUMN     @B@@@@" IF WE ARE IN KEEP AREA, TERMINATE IT.   @B@@@@TO
)@@G@@          IF (AREA\TYPE EQ KEEP) THEN     @A@@@@           BEGIN " CLOSETP
)@@G@@ THE KEEP   @D@@@@             KEEP\CONTROL\WORD := AREA\CONTROL\WORD;  TQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@             IF I\OPTION AND F\OPTION THEN@^@@@@              BEGITR
)@@G@@N     @A@@@@                CLOSE\I\OPTION\KEEP;@F@@@@                IFTS
)@@G@@ INCLUDE\ALL\FLOATS AND NOT(LINE\EMPTY) THEN    @C@@@@                  TT
)@@G@@ DO\END\OF\LINE\PROCESSING;   @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@            TU
)@@G@@ ELSE @G@@@@                SWITCH\TO\AREA(LAST\AREA\PTR);  " GO BACK TOTV
)@@G@@ TEXT AREA  @A@@@@           END; " CLOSE THE KEEP    @B@@@@" WE ARE NOWTW
)@@G@@ WORKING ON THE TEXT AREA     @A@@@@          AREA\END\PENDING := FALSE;TX
)@@G@@@C@@@@          WHILE NEXT\AREA\PTR NE NULL\PTR DO    @#@@@@           BTY
)@@G@@EGIN  @G@@@@             SAVE\NEXT\PTR := FORWARD\LINK\PTR;  " SAVE FOR TZ
)@@G@@RECHAINING  @C@@@@             INCLUDE (DEBUG\CODE, NO SOURCE);   @D@@@@UA
)@@G@@                RDISPLAY ('VPOS', VERTICAL\POSITION); @^@@@@            UB
)@@G@@ RESUME;    @C@@@@             WHILE NOT CAN\INCLUDE\NEXT\KEEP DO @^@@@@UC
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @E@@@@                IF INCLUDE\ALL\FLOATS OR FUD
)@@G@@LOAT\TEXT THEN    @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @B@@@@                  UE
)@@G@@ PROCESS\END\OF\COLUMN; @B@@@@                   FLOAT\TEXT := FALSE;   UF
)@@G@@@^@@@@                 END;   @^@@@@                ELSE    @H@@@@      UG
)@@G@@             RETURN; " ****NONSTANDARD RETURN - DONE ONE PAGE OF FLOATS UH
)@@G@@@#@@@@              END;@A@@@@             INCLUDE\NEXT\KEEP;     @F@@@@UI
)@@G@@             RELEASE\CORE(NEXT\AREA\PTR);  " RELEASE AFTER INCLUDE@C@@@@UJ
)@@G@@             NEXT\AREA\PTR := SAVE\NEXT\PTR;    @#@@@@           END;   UK
)@@G@@@H@@@@          INCLUDE\ALL\FLOATS := FALSE;  " ALL FLOATS HAVE BEEN PUSUL
)@@G@@HED OUT     @^@@@@END; " PROCESS\ENDKEEP  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@UM
)@@G@@"     @G@@@@" ROUTINE TO FORCE OUT LAST LINE OF KEEP,I AND SWITCH BACK TUN
)@@G@@O NORMAL    @B@@@@" AREA AND LINE-ASSEMBLY BUFFER (WORD).   @[@@@@"     UO
)@@G@@@ @@@@PROCEDURE CLOSE\I\OPTION\KEEP @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          OUTPUT\NUP
)@@G@@EXT\WORD;   @A@@@@          IF NOT(LINE\EMPTY) THEN   @E@@@@            UQ
)@@G@@ DO\END\OF\LINE\PROCESSING; " THIS PUTS OUT LINE@G@@@@          SWITCH\TUR
)@@G@@O\AREA(LAST\AREA\PTR); " GET BACK NORMAL TEXT AREA    @E@@@@          POUS
)@@G@@P\WORD\BUFFER; " POP WORD BUFFER PUSHED ABOVE   @H@@@@          AREA\ENDUT
)@@G@@\PENDING := TRUE; " SET FLAG TO CALL PROCESS\ENDKEEP AT EOL @ @@@@END; "UU
)@@G@@ CLOSE\I\OPTION\KEEP    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" INCLUDE\NEXT\KEEUV
)@@G@@P IS AN INTERNAL SUBROUTINE WHOSE MAIN FUNCTION @C@@@@" IS TO ADD THE NEUW
)@@G@@XT AREA TO THE CURRENT AREA.  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE INCLUDE\NEXT\KUX
)@@G@@EEP   @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @ @@@@DECLARE   LENGTH: DISTANCE    @C@@@@UY
)@@G@@          ,LPTR: WORD MACHINE POINTER BASED;    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@      UZ
)@@G@@    IF AREA\HEAD\PTR NE NULL\PTR THEN     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@VA
)@@G@@             IF PAGE\EMPTY THEN     @A@@@@                PUT\OUT\HEADINVB
)@@G@@G;    @F@@@@             IF AREA\VPOS EQ 0 OR AREA\COLUMN\NUMBER GT 1 THVC
)@@G@@EN    @B@@@@                LENGTH := NEXT\AREA\VPOS; @#@@@@            VD
)@@G@@ ELSE @C@@@@                LENGTH := NEXT\AREA\REL\VPOS;   @E@@@@      VE
)@@G@@       IF BUFFER\TEXT THEN  " LINK KEEP TO SAVE\TEXT  @^@@@@            VF
)@@G@@  BEGIN     @C@@@@                IF HEAD\PTR EQ NULL\PTR THEN    @C@@@@VG
)@@G@@                   HEAD\PTR := AREA\HEAD\PTR;   @^@@@@                ELVH
)@@G@@SE    @D@@@@                   LPTR(TAIL\PTR) := AREA\HEAD\PTR;   @B@@@@VI
)@@G@@                TAIL\PTR := AREA\TAIL\PTR;@C@@@@                INHIBIT\VJ
)@@G@@DISTRIBUTION := TRUE;   @G@@@@                IF AREA\COLUMN\NUMBER GT 1VK
)@@G@@ THEN  " COPY COLUMN POINTERS @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @D@@@@      VL
)@@G@@             FOR I:=1 TO AREA\COLUMN\NUMBER DO  @F@@@@                  VM
)@@G@@    CORE(COLUMN\LIST\PTR+COLUMN\NUMBER+I-2)     @E@@@@                  VN
)@@G@@        := CORE(AREA\COLUMN\LIST\PTR+I-1);@G@@@@                   COLUMVO
)@@G@@N\NUMBER := COLUMN\NUMBER+AREA\COLUMN\NUMBER-1; @^@@@@                 EVP
)@@G@@ND;   @E@@@@                IF AREA\COLUMN\LIST\PTR NE NULL\PTR THEN    VQ
)@@G@@@D@@@@                   RELEASE\CORE(AREA\COLUMN\LIST\PTR);@#@@@@      VR
)@@G@@        END;@A@@@@             ELSE  " DUMP KEPT TEXT @^@@@@            VS
)@@G@@  BEGIN     @E@@@@                IF VERTICAL\POSITION LT AREA\VPOS\STARVT
)@@G@@T THEN@B@@@@                   LEAD\TO\TOP\OF\AREA;   @C@@@@            VU
)@@G@@    DUMP\TEXT(%AREA\SAVE\TEXT\PTR); @B@@@@                INITIALIZE\LINVV
)@@G@@E\ASSEMBLY; @#@@@@              END;@B@@@@             UPDATE\AREA\VPOS(VW
)@@G@@LENGTH);    @D@@@@             UPDATE\AREA\REL\VPOS(NEXT\AREA\REL\VPOS);VX
)@@G@@@A@@@@             PAGE\EMPTY := FALSE;   @B@@@@             IF NOT CAN\VY
)@@G@@SKIP(LEADING) THEN@B@@@@                PROCESS\END\OF\COLUMN;    @#@@@@VZ
)@@G@@           END;   @ @@@@END; " OF INCLUDE\NEXT\KEEP   @#@@@@CONTROL (EJEWA
)@@G@@CT);  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" CAN\INCLUDE\NEXT\KEEP CHECKS TO SEE IF THE KEEWB
)@@G@@P CAN BE INCLUDED @ @@@@" IN THE APPROPRIATE AREA.    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@WC
)@@G@@PROCEDURE CAN\INCLUDE\NEXT\KEEP RESULT CONDITION@[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     WD
)@@G@@@A@@@@DECLARE   TEMP\HEIGHT: DISTANCE;    @B@@@@DECLARE   KEEP\CONTROL\WWE
)@@G@@ORD: 6 BIT LOGICAL@^@@@@          !*: MAPPED    @A@@@@              [*: WF
)@@G@@2 BIT LOGICAL     @B@@@@              ,B\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDITION  @B@@@@WG
)@@G@@              ,F\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDITION  @B@@@@              ,I\OPTION:WH
)@@G@@ 1 BIT CONDITION  @B@@@@              ,T\OPTION: 1 BIT CONDITION];@[@@@@WI
)@@G@@"     @I@@@@          AREA\HEIGHT := NEXT\AREA\HEIGHT;  " RESTORE AREA\HWJ
)@@G@@EIGHT FOR BOTTOM FLOATS @D@@@@          KEEP\CONTROL\WORD := NEXT\AREA\CWK
)@@G@@ONTROL\WORD;@D@@@@          IF AREA\VPOS EQ 0 THEN  " TOP OF COLUMN     WL
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             IF AREA\COLUMN\NUMBER EQ 1 THWM
)@@G@@EN    @^@@@@              BEGIN     @C@@@@                IF NOT B\OPTIOWN
)@@G@@N OR T\OPTION OR  @B@@@@                   INCLUDE\ALL\FLOATS THEN@A@@@@WO
)@@G@@                   RETURN(TRUE);    @D@@@@                ELSE  " WE MUSWP
)@@G@@T FIT A BOTTOM FLOAT    @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @F@@@@            WQ
)@@G@@       TEMP\HEIGHT := AREA\HEIGHT-NEXT\AREA\REL\VPOS; @E@@@@            WR
)@@G@@       IF TEMP\HEIGHT LE 0 THEN " FLOAT CAN FIT @ @@@@                  WS
)@@G@@  BEGIN     @G@@@@                      TEMP\HEIGHT := NEXT\AREA\HEIGHT-WT
)@@G@@NEXT\AREA\VPOS    @D@@@@                                     +SKIP\DISTAWU
)@@G@@NCE;  @E@@@@                      NEXT\AREA\VPOS := NEXT\AREA\HEIGHT;   WV
)@@G@@@H@@@@                      REPLACE\TOP\LEADING(%AREA\SAVE\TEXT\PTR,TEMPWW
)@@G@@\HEIGHT);   @A@@@@                      RETURN(TRUE); @^@@@@            WX
)@@G@@        END;@^@@@@                   ELSE @G@@@@                      ARWY
)@@G@@EA\HEIGHT := TEMP\HEIGHT;  " MODIFY AREA\HEIGHT @^@@@@                 EWZ
)@@G@@ND;   @#@@@@              END;@E@@@@             ELSE IF (COLUMN\NUMBER+XA
)@@G@@AREA\COLUMN\NUMBER-1) LE@G@@@@                NUMBER\OF\COLUMNS THEN  " XB
)@@G@@WE CAN FIT EVERYTHING ON PAGE @ @@@@                RETURN(TRUE); @#@@@@XC
)@@G@@           END;   @D@@@@          ELSE  " COLUMN IS PARTIALLY FILLED WITXD
)@@G@@H TEXT@#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             IF AREA\COLUMN\NUMBER EXE
)@@G@@Q 1 THEN    @^@@@@              BEGIN     @C@@@@                IF B\OPTXF
)@@G@@ION OR NOT T\OPTION OR  @B@@@@                   INCLUDE\ALL\FLOATS THENXG
)@@G@@@^@@@@                 BEGIN  @F@@@@                   IF B\OPTION AND NXH
)@@G@@OT INCLUDE\ALL\FLOATS THEN    @ @@@@                    BEGIN     @E@@@@XI
)@@G@@                      TEMP\HEIGHT := AREA\HEIGHT-AREA\VPOS  @E@@@@      XJ
)@@G@@                               -NEXT\AREA\REL\VPOS;   @C@@@@            XK
)@@G@@          IF TEMP\HEIGHT EQ 0 THEN  @B@@@@                         RETURXL
)@@G@@N(TRUE);    @C@@@@                      IF TEMP\HEIGHT GT 0 THEN  @G@@@@XM
)@@G@@                         AREA\HEIGHT := AREA\HEIGHT-NEXT\AREA\REL\VPOS; XN
)@@G@@@^@@@@                    END;@E@@@@                   ELSE IF CAN\SKIP(XO
)@@G@@NEXT\AREA\REL\VPOS) THEN@A@@@@                      RETURN(TRUE); @^@@@@XP
)@@G@@                 END;   @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           END;   XQ
)@@G@@@C@@@@          RETURN(FALSE);  " FOR ALL OTHER CASES @A@@@@END; " OF CAXR
)@@G@@N\INCLUDE\NEXT\KEEP     @[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@                  XS
)@@G@@ -NEXT\AREA\REL\VPOS;   @C@@@@                      IF TEMP\HEIGHT EQ 0 XT
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);XU
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CXV
)@@G@@HAR-SIZE',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('STAGING-DEF',IMPORTED);  XW
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('SXX
)@@G@@YMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDXY
)@@G@@URE INITIALIZE\NEXT\WORD\ASSEMBLY IMPORTED ('INXTWA');@[@@@@      @E@@@@XZ
)@@G@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\WORD\ASSEMBLY IMPORTED ('INXTWA');     @[@@@@      YA
)@@G@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\LINE\ASSEMBLY IMPORTED ('ILINEA');     @[@@@@YB
)@@G@@      @D@@@@PROCEDURE ASSEMBLE\NEXT\WORD IMPORTED ('ASBLNW');     @[@@@@YC
)@@G@@      @F@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD (CHARACTER: WORD INTEYD
)@@G@@GER)  @D@@@@           IMPORTED ('PUTNXW');       " GET-PUT-WORD  @[@@@@YE
)@@G@@      @E@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\FUNCTION\INTO\LINE (FUNCTION: WORD INTEGER,   YF
)@@G@@@D@@@@           VALUE: DISTANCE) IMPORTED ('PUTFUNLINE');  @[@@@@      YG
)@@G@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\FUNCTION\INTO\WORD (FUNCTION: WORD INTEGER,   @D@@@@YH
)@@G@@             VALUE: DISTANCE) IMPORTED ('PUTFUNWORD');@[@@@@      @C@@@@YI
)@@G@@PROCEDURE FLUSH\FROM\HERE IMPORTED ('FLSHFH');  @[@@@@      @C@@@@PROCEDYJ
)@@G@@URE LINE\EMPTY IMPORTED ('LINEMT') RESULT @ @@@@           WORD CONDITIOYK
)@@G@@N;    @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@YL
)@@G@@DECLARE   *(128): MAPPED STATIC IMPORTED('PXLTAB') " ENTRY TRANSLATE    YM
)@@G@@@C@@@@             [*: 12 BIT LOGICAL       " UNUSED  @F@@@@            YN
)@@G@@ ,XLAF: 6 BIT LOGICAL     " CONVERSION TO FIELDATA    @E@@@@            YO
)@@G@@ ,XLFA: 18 BIT LOGICAL];  " CONVERSION TO ASCII @[@@@@      @[@@@@      YP
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" MOVE FROM ITEM\SCANNED (SCANYQ
)@@G@@NED) TO MONOCASE\CHAR CONVERTING TO @#@@@@" UPPERCASE ASCII @[@@@@"     YR
)@@G@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE CONVERT\TO\MONOCASE EXPORTED ('CVTMON')     @[@@@@BEGIN YS
)@@G@@@E@@@@          MONOCASE(SCANNED);          " TEMP FOR CONVERSION @#@@@@YT
)@@G@@          RETURN; @ @@@@END; " OF CONVERT\TO\MONOCASE @[@@@@"     @F@@@@YU
)@@G@@" SAME AS ABOVE BUT TAKES AN ARGUMENT - POINTER TO DESCRIPTOR     @B@@@@YV
)@@G@@" FOR ITEM TO BE CONVERTED TO MONOCASE.   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE MOYW
)@@G@@NOCASE(SYMBOL: MACHINE WORD POINTER) EXPORTED('MONOCS')     @[@@@@BEGIN YX
)@@G@@@ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO 14 DO @B@@@@             MONOCASE\WORD(I) YY
)@@G@@:= BLANKS;  @F@@@@          KLUGE := DADR(SYMBOL);      " SET UP TO REFEYZ
)@@G@@RENCE CHARS @A@@@@          NAME\LEN := DLEN(SYMBOL); @A@@@@          IFZA
)@@G@@ NAME\LEN GT 84 THEN    @C@@@@             NAME\LEN := 84;          " TRZB
)@@G@@UNCATE@A@@@@          FOR I := 1 TO NAME\LEN DO @#@@@@           BEGIN  ZC
)@@G@@@B@@@@             IF DCHR(I) GE O'0140' THEN   @D@@@@                MOZD
)@@G@@NOCASE\CHAR(I) := DCHR(I) - O'040'; @#@@@@             ELSE @C@@@@      ZE
)@@G@@          MONOCASE\CHAR(I) := DCHR(I);    @#@@@@           END;   @C@@@@ZF
)@@G@@          MONOCASE\LEN := NAME\LEN;   " TMP     @#@@@@END; " OF MONOCASEZG
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" CONVERT THE NAME JUST SCANNED TO FIELDATA     @[@@@@ZH
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE CONVERT\TO\FIELDATA EXPORTED ('CTOFDT')     @[@@@@ZI
)@@G@@BEGIN @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO 14 DO @F@@@@             FIELDATA\WOZJ
)@@G@@RD(I) := O'050505050505'; " BLANK BUFFER  @A@@@@          FOR I := 1 TO ZK
)@@G@@NAME\LEN DO @G@@@@             FIELDATA\CHAR(I) := XLAF(MONOCASE\CHAR(I)ZL
)@@G@@); " XLATE TO FD  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" INSERT THE CHAPTER ANDZM
)@@G@@ SECTION NUMBER   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE CONVERT\AND\INSERT\NUMBER(ZN
)@@G@@NUMBER: WORD INTEGER)   @ @@@@           EXPORTED ('CVTINS')@[@@@@BEGIN ZO
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @A@@@@          CVT\NUM\TO\ASCII(NUMBER); @ @@@@          FOZP
)@@G@@R K := 1 TO 12 DO @C@@@@          IF NUMBER\IN\ASCII(K) NE BLANK THEN   ZQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@             PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD( NUMBER\IN\ASCII(K) );  ZR
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" CONVERT A BINARY NUMBER TO ASCII LEFT JUZS
)@@G@@STIFIED AND SPACE FILLED@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE CVT\NUM\TO\ASCII( BIZT
)@@G@@NARY\NUMBER: WORD INTEGER)    @ @@@@          EXPORTED('CVTASC')  @[@@@@ZU
)@@G@@      @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@DECLARE   QUO: WORD INTEGER;  @ @@@@DECLARE   REZV
)@@G@@M: WORD INTEGER;  @ @@@@DECLARE   START: WORD INTEGER;@[@@@@"     @[@@@@ZW
)@@G@@"     @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO 12 DO @B@@@@             NUMBER\IN\AZX
)@@G@@SCII(I) := BLANK; @C@@@@          IF BINARY\NUMBER LT 0 THEN  " NEGATIVEZY
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             START := 2;              " EDZZ
)@@G@@IT NUMBER AFTER - @G@@@@             REM := -BINARY\NUMBER;   " CONVERT AA
)@@G@@POSITIVE NUMBER ONLY    @F@@@@             NUMBER\IN\ASCII(1) := MINUS; AB
)@@G@@ " PUT IN MINUS SIGN    @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          ELSE " PAC
)@@G@@OSITIVE NUMBER    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @^@@@@             START := 1;AD
)@@G@@@A@@@@             REM := BINARY\NUMBER;  @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@AE
)@@G@@          FOR I := START TO 12 DO   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @ @@@@      AF
)@@G@@       QUO := REM // 10;@A@@@@             REM := MOD( REM,10 );  @E@@@@AG
)@@G@@             NUMBER\IN\ASCII( 13 - I) := REM + ASCII\ZERO;  @ @@@@      AH
)@@G@@       IF QUO GT 9 THEN @^@@@@              BEGIN     @ @@@@            AI
)@@G@@    REM := QUO;   @^@@@@                ITERATE;@#@@@@              END;AJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@             IF QUO NE 0 THEN @F@@@@                NUMBER\IN\ASCIAK
)@@G@@I( 12 - I ) := QUO + ASCII\ZERO;    @^@@@@             RETURN;    @#@@@@AL
)@@G@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@AM
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@" SEARCH KEYWORD TABLE.  THIS ROUTINE IS PASSED THE WORD LENAN
)@@G@@GTH   @F@@@@" AND LOCATION OF A KEYWORD TABLE.  THE CURRENT SCANNER SYMBAO
)@@G@@OL    @F@@@@" IS CONVERTED TO MONOCASE, AND THE KEYWORD TABLE IS SEARCHEAP
)@@G@@D.    @F@@@@" THE PARAMETER ALLOW\AB CONTROLS SEARCHING ON ABBREVIATIONSAQ
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@" IF PASSED TRUE, ABBREVIATION OF KEYWORD IS ALLOWED. @F@@@@AR
)@@G@@" THE RETURN IS AN INTEGER INDEX OF MATCH WITHIN LIST, OR ONE     @C@@@@AS
)@@G@@" GREATER THAN THE NUMBER OF NAMES FOR NO-MATCH.@[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDAT
)@@G@@URE KEYWORD\SEARCH@F@@@@             (TABLE\PTR: MACHINE WORD POINTER " AU
)@@G@@TO TABLE IN CORE  @F@@@@             ,TABLE\NUM: INTEGER WORD " NUMBER OAV
)@@G@@F ENTRIES IN TABLE@G@@@@             ,ALLOW\ABR: WORD CONDITION) " FLAG AW
)@@G@@TO ALLOW ABBREVIATIONS  @ @@@@          EXPORTED ('KWSRCH') @C@@@@      AX
)@@G@@    RESULT INTEGER WORD " INDEX OF FIND   @[@@@@BEGIN @G@@@@DECLARE   TAAY
)@@G@@BLE(*): 9 BIT LOGICAL BASED (TABLE\PTR); " KEYWORD TABLE    @F@@@@DECLARAZ
)@@G@@E   CHARS\TO\SEARCH: WORD INTEGER; " LOCAL CHARACTER LIMIT  @[@@@@"     BA
)@@G@@@F@@@@          CONVERT\TO\MONOCASE; " MONOCASE CURRENT SCANNER TOKEN   BB
)@@G@@@G@@@@          IF (NAME\LEN EQ 0) OR (NAME\LEN GT 8) OR NOT(ALLOW\ABR) BC
)@@G@@THEN  @E@@@@             CHARS\TO\SEARCH := 8; " REQUIRE FULL MATCH     BD
)@@G@@+@@@@[+@@@@@@#@@@@          ELSE    +@@@@[+@@@@@@G@@@@             CHARSBE
)@@G@@\TO\SEARCH := NAME\LEN; " LOCAL COPY OF SEARCH LIMIT  @C@@@@          FOBF
)@@G@@R W := 0 TO (TABLE\NUM-1)*8 BY 8 DO @ @@@@           BEGIN " WORD LOOP  BG
)@@G@@@C@@@@             FOR C := 1 TO CHARS\TO\SEARCH DO   @A@@@@            BH
)@@G@@  BEGIN " CHARACTER LOOP@D@@@@                IF TABLE(W+C) NE MONOCASE\BI
)@@G@@CHAR(C) THEN@D@@@@                   ITERATE W;      " TRY NEXT WORD    BJ
)@@G@@@A@@@@              END; " CHARACTER LOOP @E@@@@             RETURN(1+W/BK
)@@G@@/8);       " FOUND IT! RETURN INDEX @ @@@@           END; " WORD LOOP   BL
)@@G@@+@@@@[+@@@@@@G@@@@          RETURN( TABLE\NUM + 1); " RETURN INDEX LARGEBM
)@@G@@R THAN ENTRIES    @^@@@@END; " KEYWORD\SEARCH   @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROBN
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE TAKES A DEVICE UNIT AS INBO
)@@G@@PUT AND PRODUCES  @^@@@@" INTERNAL UNITS OUTPUT.@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDBP
)@@G@@URE INTERNAL\WIDTH(WIDTH: DISTANCE) EXPORTED    @B@@@@           ('INTERBQ
)@@G@@NWIDTH') RESULT DISTANCE@[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          RETURN(ROUND\WIDTH(WBR
)@@G@@IDTH*IU\DU\FACTOR));    @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE RBS
)@@G@@ETURNS A DEVICE UNIT GIVEN AN INTERNAL UNIT     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDBT
)@@G@@URE DEVICE\WIDTH(WIDTH: DISTANCE) EXPORTED@B@@@@           ('DEVICEWIDTHBU
)@@G@@') RESULT DISTANCE@[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          RETURN(ROUND\WIDTH(WIDTH) BV
)@@G@@// IU\DU\FACTOR); @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE ROUNDS BW
)@@G@@AN INTERNAL HEIGHT NUMBER SO THAT   @E@@@@" IT IS  A MULTIPLE OF THE ACTBX
)@@G@@UAL PHYSICAL DISTANCE THAT    @A@@@@" CAN BE SPACED BY THE FINAL DEVICE.BY
