)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE ROUND\WIDTH(WIDTH: DISTANCE) EXPORTED @B@@@@BZ
)@@G@@           ('ROUNDWIDTH') RESULT DISTANCE @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          IFCA
)@@G@@ WIDTH GE 0 THEN " ROUND A POSITIVE NUMBER@G@@@@             RETURN(UNITCB
)@@G@@\INTERNAL\WIDTH*((WIDTH+UNIT\INTERNAL\WIDTH//2) @B@@@@                //CC
)@@G@@UNIT\INTERNAL\WIDTH)); "@C@@@@          ELSE " DO ROUND ON NEGATIVE NUMBCD
)@@G@@ER    @G@@@@             RETURN(UNIT\INTERNAL\WIDTH*((WIDTH-UNIT\INTERNACE
)@@G@@L\WIDTH//2) @B@@@@                //UNIT\INTERNAL\WIDTH)); "@[@@@@END;  CF
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE WILL ROUND A DISTANCE TO BE A MULTIPLCG
)@@G@@E     @E@@@@" OF WHAT THE PHYSICAL DEVICE CAN ACTULLY SPACE VERTICALLY. CH
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE ROUND\HEIGHT(HEIGHT: DISTANCE) EXPORTED     CI
)@@G@@@B@@@@           ('ROUNDHEIGHT') RESULT DISTANCE@[@@@@BEGIN @G@@@@      CJ
)@@G@@    RETURN(UNIT\LEADING*((HEIGHT+UNIT\LEADING//2)//UNIT\LEADING));@[@@@@CK
)@@G@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" TRANSFER PROCEDURES FROM CONDITION AND POINTERCL
)@@G@@ TO INTEGER.@F@@@@" INTRODUCED TO FOIL TIGHTER TYPE CHECKING IN PLUS COMCM
)@@G@@PILER 2R2D1.@[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE CVT\COND\TO\INTE(COND: CONDITIONCN
)@@G@@ WORD)@A@@@@          EXPORTED ('CVTCONDINTE')  @ @@@@          RESULT ICO
)@@G@@NTEGER WORD @[@@@@BEGIN @^@@@@          IF COND THEN  @^@@@@            CP
)@@G@@ RETURN(1)  @#@@@@          ELSE    @^@@@@             RETURN(0); @^@@@@CQ
)@@G@@END; " CVT\COND\TO\INTE @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE CVT\PTR\TO\INTE(PTR:CR
)@@G@@ MACHINE WORD POINTER)  @A@@@@          EXPORTED ('CVTPTRINTE')   @ @@@@CS
)@@G@@          RESULT INTEGER WORD @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@DECLARE    INTEGER\OVERLCT
)@@G@@AY: WORD INTEGER STATIC @D@@@@          !POINTER\OVERLAY: WORD MACHINE PCU
)@@G@@OINTER;     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          POINTER\OVERLAY := PTR;   @A@@@@CV
)@@G@@          RETURN( INTEGER\OVERLAY );@^@@@@END; " CVT\PTR\TO\INTE  @[@@@@CW
)@@G@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@@E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE ROUNDS AN INTERNAL HEIGHTCX
)@@G@@ NUMBER SO THAT   @E@@@@" IT IS  A MULTIPLE OF THE ACTUAL PHYSICAL DISTACY
)@@G@@NCE THAT    @A@@@@" CAN *[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @F@@@@DEFINE    COCZ
)@@G@@MPILER\DEBUG = FALSE; " TRUE TO TURN ON DEBUG CODE    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@DA
)@@G@@" THIS MODULE IS CALLED TO 'COMPILE' A MACRO, COPYING THE   @F@@@@" TEXTDB
)@@G@@ INTO THE SCRATCH FILE, ADDING LINKAGES FOR THE CONTROL     @F@@@@" STRUDC
)@@G@@CTURE ELEMENTS, AND TRANSLATING CODES, ETC.  IF THE MACRO   @G@@@@" WILLDD
)@@G@@ FIT INTO A SINGLE 224 WORD BUFFER THEN A COPY IS LEFT INCORE     @G@@@@DE
)@@G@@" FOR FAST ACCESS.  TWO WORDS ARE APPENDED AT THE BEGINNING OF EACH     DF
)@@G@@@G@@@@" IMAGE IN THE SCRATCH FILE.  THE FIRST WORD IS THE LINE NUMBER WIDG
)@@G@@THIN  @H@@@@" THE SOURCE FOR THE MACRO.  THE SECOND WORD IS A LINK ADDREDH
)@@G@@SS WITHIN THE     @G@@@@" MACRO.  THIS POINTER IS A HALF WORD SECTOR ADDDI
)@@G@@RESS AND WORD OFFSET.   @F@@@@" THE POINTER IS NORMALLY ZERO, BUT IS SETDJ
)@@G@@ FOR THE FOLLOWING:     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" 'IF'     - POINTS TO THE IMADK
)@@G@@GE AFTER THE ASSOCIATED 'ELSE' OR 'ENDIF' @F@@@@" 'ELSE'   - POINTS TO TDL
)@@G@@HE IMAGE AFTER THE ASSOCIATED 'ENDIF'     @F@@@@" 'WHILE'  - POINTS TO TDM
)@@G@@HE IMAGE AFTER THE ASSOCIATED 'ENDREP'    @F@@@@" 'UNTIL'  - POINTS TO TDN
)@@G@@HE IMAGE AFTER THE ASSOCIATED 'ENDREP'    @C@@@@" 'ENDREP' - POINTS TO TDO
)@@G@@HE ASSOCIATED 'REPEAT'  @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" AN IN-CORE PACKET IS MADE FODP
)@@G@@R EACH MACRO, AND CHAINED INTO A LIST THAT@G@@@@" EMENATES FROM THE CELLDQ
)@@G@@ DEFINED\MACROS.  THIS PACKET CONTAINS POINTERS @D@@@@" TO THE CORE AND DR
)@@G@@DRUM IMAGES OF THE COMPILED MACROS. @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DDS
)@@G@@EFINES',IMPORTED);@A@@@@          COPY ('BREAK-PROCS');     @B@@@@      DT
)@@G@@    COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-DEF',DU
)@@G@@IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-PROC',IMPORTED); @B@@@@      DV
)@@G@@    COPY ('CORE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',DW
)@@G@@IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('EDIT-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@      DX
)@@G@@    COPY ('FILE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @A@@@@          COPY ('IO-DEF1',IMPODY
)@@G@@RTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('IO-PROCS',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          CODZ
)@@G@@PY ('MACRO-DEF',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('PACKET-DEF',IMPORTEEA
)@@G@@D);   @B@@@@          COPY ('PIO-PROCS',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COEB
)@@G@@PY ('PRINT-DEF',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('PUSH-PROCS',IMPORTEEC
)@@G@@D);   @D@@@@          COPY ('RUN-DATA-DEF',IMPORTED); " $$$TEMP   @B@@@@ED
)@@G@@          COPY ('SCAN-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('STAGINGEE
)@@G@@-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@EF
)@@G@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-PROCS',IMPORTED); @E@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-DEEG
)@@G@@F',IMPORTED); " GET END\OF\UNIT     @B@@@@          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',EH
)@@G@@IMPORTED);  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" GLOBAL DATA FOR EI
)@@G@@THE COMPILATION PROCESS.@[@@@@"     @H@@@@DECLARE   CURRENT\MACRO: STATIEJ
)@@G@@C MACHINE WORD POINTER; " MACRO CURRENTLY COMP  @D@@@@DECLARE   MACRO\OUEK
)@@G@@TPUT\PACKET: MACHINE WORD POINTER   @E@@@@             STATIC LOCATABLE;EL
)@@G@@ " POINTER TO OUTPUT PACKET   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS STATIC DATA AREA EM
)@@G@@IS USED TO STORE THE SENTINEL (IF ANY)    @A@@@@" NEEDED TO CLOSE THE CUEN
)@@G@@RRENT MACRO.@[@@@@"     @E@@@@DECLARE   SNTL: INTEGER WORD; " LENGTH OF EO
)@@G@@SENTINEL IN WORDS @F@@@@DECLARE   SENT(8): INTEGER WORD STATIC LOCATABLEEP
)@@G@@; " SENTINEL DATA @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS STATIC DATA AREA COMPRISES THEQ
)@@G@@E MACRO COMPILER STACK.  THE  @G@@@@" EQUATE 'STACK\SIZE' DEFINES THE MAER
)@@G@@XIMUM DEPTH IN CONTROL STRUCTURE    @G@@@@" THAT THE COMPILER CAN HANDLEES
)@@G@@.  AS THE MACRO IMAGE ITSELF TAKES THE    @G@@@@" FIRST ENTRY, A VALUE OET
)@@G@@F 20 ALLOWS 19 LEVELS OF CONTROL STRUCTURE.     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@DEFINEEU
)@@G@@    STACK\SIZE = 20; " ALLOW 19 LEVELS    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@DECLARE   STEV
)@@G@@ACK\PTR: INTEGER WORD LOCATABLE;    @[@@@@"     @H@@@@DECLARE   STACK\TOEW
)@@G@@P(STACK\SIZE): WORD INTEGER STATIC LOCATABLE; " STRUC TYPE  @H@@@@DECLAREX
)@@G@@E   STACK\ADR(STACK\SIZE): WORD INTEGER STATIC LOCATABLE; " XFER ADDR   EY
)@@G@@@H@@@@DECLARE   STACK\LIN(STACK\SIZE): WORD INTEGER STATIC LOCATABLE; " EZ
)@@G@@LINE NUM    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THE STATIC DID CHARACTER IN COLUMN ONE FFA
)@@G@@LAGS THE IMAGE    @C@@@@" AS A DIRECTIVE.  DEFINED HERE TEMPORARILY.    FB
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@DEFINE    STATIC\DID = PERIOD; " IN DEFINES     @[@@@@FC
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@" ERROR MESSAGES GENERATED BY THE MACRO COMPILER.     @[@@@@FD
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@DECLARE   ERR\MSG\UNOPENED: STATIC LOCATABLE UNALTERABLE    FE
)@@G@@@E@@@@             20 ASCII CHARACTERS := 'NO & FOR & OF LINE &'; @[@@@@FF
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   ERR\MSG\SECOND: STATIC LOCATABLE UNALTERABLE@F@@@@FG
)@@G@@             24 ASCII CHARACTERS := 'SECOND & FOR & OF LINE &';   @[@@@@FH
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@DECLARE   ERR\MSG\UNCLOSED: STATIC LOCATABLE UNALTERABLE    FI
)@@G@@@F@@@@             23 ASCII CHARACTERS := '& OF LINE & NOT CLOSED&';    FJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   ERR\MSG\STACK: STATIC LOCATABLE UNALTERABLE FK
)@@G@@@A@@@@             51 ASCII CHARACTERS := @G@@@@             'MACRO COMPFL
)@@G@@ILER STACK DEPTH (&) EXCEEDED, & IGNORED&';     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DECLARFM
)@@G@@E   ERR\MSG\ERROR: STATIC LOCATABLE UNALTERABLE @A@@@@             36 ASFN
)@@G@@CII CHARACTERS := @D@@@@             'ERRORS DETECTED AT LINE & OF MACROFO
)@@G@@ &';  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@DEFINE    KEY\WORD\WHUN\LEN = 18; " LENGTH IN CHFP
)@@G@@ARACTERS    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   KEY\WORD\WHUN: STATIC LOCATABLE FQ
)@@G@@UNALTERABLE @D@@@@             ASCII CHARACTER(KEY\WORD\WHUN\LEN) :=    FR
)@@G@@@B@@@@             '''WHILE'' OR ''UNTIL''';    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDFS
)@@G@@URE READ\NEXT\CARD IMPORTED ('READ'); " IN ELEMENT READ     @[@@@@"     FT
)@@G@@@ @@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED;     @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   FU
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO PROCESS A LIFV
)@@G@@ST OF MACROS IN A FILE  @F@@@@" ELEMENT.  ALL MACROS ARE DEFINED.  THIS FW
)@@G@@PROCEDURE IS PASSED AN  @F@@@@" EXTERNAL PACKET INITIALIZED BY THE SEARCFX
)@@G@@H ROUTINE.  THIS PACKET @C@@@@" IS PUSHED ONTO THE CURRENT INPUT CHAIN CFY
)@@G@@IP.   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE COMPILE\EXTERNAL\MACRO(MIP: MACHINE POFZ
)@@G@@INTER WORD) @E@@@@          EXPORTED ('CMPEXT') RESULT MACHINE WORD POINGA
)@@G@@TER   @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   CHAR\SAVE: INTEGER WORD; " SAVE CHARACGB
)@@G@@TER   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" SAVE CHARACTER ACROSS COMPILATION.@[@@@@"     GC
)@@G@@@A@@@@          CHAR\SAVE := CHARACTER;   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" CHAIN IN PGD
)@@G@@ACKET PASSED AS ARGUMENT TO ALLOW READING IMAGES@ @@@@" AS IF THEY WERE GE
)@@G@@SCRIPT.     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          PUSH\INPUT\PKT(PKT\EXTERNAL,MIP)GF
)@@G@@; " PUSH IT @E@@@@          USER\IMAGE\BUFFER(MIP) := LOC(INPUT\CARD\WORGG
)@@G@@D(1));@D@@@@          IF (CIP NE MIP) THEN ERROR; " $$$ DEBUG     @[@@@@GH
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@" OPEN MACRO COMPILATION@[@@@@"     @^@@@@          COMPILE\GI
)@@G@@OPEN; @E@@@@          MACRO\LINE\NUM := 0; " IMPLIED MACRO LINE ZERO    GJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@          COMPILE\OPEN\MACRO; " OPEN IMPLIED MACRO    @C@@@@      GK
)@@G@@    READ\NEXT\CARD; " READ FIRST IMAGE    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" COMPILE UNGL
)@@G@@TIL END OF FILE ON INPUT PACKET     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          WHILE NOGM
)@@G@@T END\OF\MACRO DO @A@@@@           BEGIN " HANDLE IMAGE     @B@@@@      GN
)@@G@@       IF (STACK\PTR EQ 0) THEN     @ @@@@                SKIP\IMAGE;   GO
)@@G@@@#@@@@             ELSE @ @@@@                COMPILE\IMAGE;@C@@@@      GP
)@@G@@       READ\NEXT\CARD; " READ NEXT IMAGE  @ @@@@           END; " HANDLEGQ
)@@G@@ IMAGE@[@@@@"     @^@@@@" CLOSE ANY OPEN MACRO  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@      GR
)@@G@@    IF (STACK\PTR NE 0) THEN  @F@@@@             COMPILE\CLOSE\MACRO(FALGS
)@@G@@SE); " CLOSE REMAINING MACRO  @D@@@@          COMPILE\CLOSE; " CLOSE ANDGT
)@@G@@ ENTER MACROS     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" CLOSE INPUT FROM MACRO ELEMENT.   GU
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@          IF (CIP NE MIP) THEN ERROR; " $$$ DEBUG     GV
)@@G@@@^@@@@          POP\INPUT\PKT;@[@@@@"     @^@@@@" RESTORE CHARACTER     GW
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @A@@@@          CHARACTER := CHAR\SAVE;   @A@@@@          REGX
)@@G@@TURN(CURRENT\MACRO);    @ @@@@END; " COMPILE\EXTERNAL\MACRO @[@@@@"     GY
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO SKIP A LINE IN BETWEEN MGZ
)@@G@@ACRO DEFS IN@F@@@@" THE EXTERNAL ELEMENT.  IF IT RECOGNIZES A MACRO IMAGHA
)@@G@@E, IT PUSHES@F@@@@" THE MACRO ONTO THE COMPILATION STACK, FORCING THE ABHB
)@@G@@OVE ROUTINE @C@@@@" COMPILE\EXTERNAL\MACRO INTO COMPILATION MODE. @[@@@@HC
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE SKIP\IMAGE    @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@DECLARE   IMAGE\TYHD
)@@G@@PE: INTEGER WORD; " IMAGE CLASSIFICATION  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          IMHE
)@@G@@AGE\TYPE := CLASSIFY\MACRO\IMAGE; " SCAN IT     @C@@@@          IF (IMAGHF
)@@G@@E\TYPE EQ MACRO\CS\MACRO) THEN@A@@@@           BEGIN " ANOTHER MACRO DEFHG
)@@G@@@E@@@@             SCAN(CTRM+CNAM+ALLOW\NAM); " SCAN MACRO NAME   @C@@@@HH
)@@G@@             CONVERT\TO\MONOCASE; " FOR SEARCH  @G@@@@             MACROHI
)@@G@@\LINE\NUM := CARD\SEQ\NUMBER(CIP); " SET LINE NUMBER  @D@@@@            HJ
)@@G@@ COMPILE\OPEN\MACRO; " REOPEN COMPILATION @D@@@@             ACQUIRE\SENHK
)@@G@@TINEL; " AND SCAN SENTINEL    @A@@@@           END; " ANOTHER MACRO DEF HL
)@@G@@@#@@@@END; " SKIP\IMAGE @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     HM
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS GIVEN CONTROL WHEN A .MACRO IMAGE HN
)@@G@@IS    @F@@@@" READ IN THE TEXT.  AT THE TIME OF THE CALL THE MACRO NAME HO
)@@G@@IS    @F@@@@" EXPECTED TO BE READ AND IN SCANNED\CHAR.  CARDS ARE READ AHP
)@@G@@ND    @E@@@@" MACRO COMPILED UNTIL THE MATCHING .END CARD OR AN END-    HQ
)@@G@@@ @@@@" OF-FILE IS ENCOUNTERED.     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE COMPILE\HR
)@@G@@INTERNAL\MACRO EXPORTED('CINMAC')   @A@@@@          RESULT MACHINE POINTHS
)@@G@@ER    @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          COMPILE\OPEN; " OPEN COMPILATION@H@@@@HT
)@@G@@          MACRO\LINE\NUM := CARD\SEQ\NUMBER(CIP); " INITIALIZE IMAGE COUHU
)@@G@@NTER  @C@@@@          CONVERT\TO\MONOCASE; " THE MACRO NAME @C@@@@      HV
)@@G@@    COMPILE\OPEN\MACRO; " OPEN NEW MACRO  @B@@@@          ACQUIRE\SENTINHW
)@@G@@EL; " AND SAVE IT @D@@@@          READ\NEXT\CARD; " READ FIRST MACRO IMAHX
)@@G@@GE    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" LOOP COMPILING IMAGES UNTIL MACRO IS CLOSED.  HY
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@          WHILE (STACK\PTR NE 0) AND NOT END\OF\MACRO HZ
)@@G@@DO    @A@@@@           BEGIN " PROCESS IMAGE    @ @@@@             COMPIIA
)@@G@@LE\IMAGE;   @D@@@@             IF (STACK\PTR NE 0) THEN " IF NOT CLOSED IB
)@@G@@@C@@@@                READ\NEXT\CARD; " FROM SCRIPT   @ @@@@           EIC
)@@G@@ND; " READ IMAGE  @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" END OF COMPILING MACRO@[@@@@"     ID
)@@G@@@F@@@@          IF (STACK\PTR NE 0) THEN " IF STRUCTURE OUTSTANDING     IE
)@@G@@@F@@@@             COMPILE\CLOSE\MACRO(FALSE); " CLOSE AND DIAGNOSE     IF
)@@G@@@D@@@@          COMPILE\CLOSE; " CLOSE AND INSERT MACRO     @E@@@@      IG
)@@G@@    RETURN(CURRENT\MACRO); " RETURN MACRO TO CALLER   @ @@@@END; " COMPIIH
)@@G@@LE\INTERNAL\MACRO @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" RETURN TRUE IF TIME TO CLOSE MACROII
)@@G@@ INPUT.     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE END\OF\MACRO  @ @@@@          REIJ
)@@G@@SULT CONDITION    @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          RETURN(END\FILE(CIP) OR REIK
)@@G@@MOTE\BREAK);@^@@@@END; " END\OF\MACRO     @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECIL
)@@G@@T);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO COMPILIM
)@@G@@E AN IMAGE FROM THE MACRO.    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" A COMPILE TIME STACK IIN
)@@G@@S KEPT, CONSISTING OF STACK\TOP, WHICH    @F@@@@" CONTAINS A CODE FOR THIO
)@@G@@E STATEMENT WHICH CAUSED THE STACK, AND   @G@@@@" STACK\ADDR, WHICH IS TIP
)@@G@@HE DRUM ADDRESS OF THE STATEMENT WHICH CAUSED   @G@@@@" THE STACK.  THE IQ
)@@G@@PRIMITIVE PUSH PUSHES THE CURRENT IMAGE ADDRESS AND   @F@@@@" THE ARGUMEIR
)@@G@@NT ONTO THE STACK.  THE PRIMITIVE UPDATE POPS THE     @G@@@@" TOP ENTRY IS
)@@G@@OF THE STACK AND UPDATES THE STACK IMAGES POINTER TO THE    @B@@@@" ADDRIT
)@@G@@ESS OF THE NEXT LINE TO BE OUTPUT.  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" NOTE THIS ROUTINIU
)@@G@@E CLOBBERS THE INPUT CARD SO IT IS  @E@@@@" ASSUMED THAT A NEW TEMPORARYIV
)@@G@@ INPUT CARD BUFFER HAS BEEN   @B@@@@" OBTAINED PRIOR TO CALLING THIS ROUIW
)@@G@@TINE. @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE COMPILE\IMAGE @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@DECLARIX
)@@G@@E   IMAGE\TYPE: INTEGER WORD; " WHAT KIND OF IMAGE    @D@@@@DECLARE   ADIY
)@@G@@DR\SAVE: INTEGER WORD; " SAVE ADDRESS     @[@@@@"     @H@@@@          MAIZ
)@@G@@CRO\XFER\PTR := IMAGE\ADDR(MACRO\OUTPUT\PACKET); " SET XFER ADDR  @G@@@@JA
)@@G@@          MACRO\LINE\NUM := CARD\SEQ\NUMBER(CIP); " SET LINE NUMBER     JB
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@" BRANCH ON CARD TYPE.  MOST CARDS ARE PASSED AS-IS.  JC
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@          IMAGE\TYPE := CLASSIFY\MACRO\IMAGE; " SCAN AJD
)@@G@@ND CLASSIFY @E@@@@          CASEENTRY IMAGE\TYPE " WHAT KIND OF CARD IS JE
)@@G@@IT    @[@@@@"     @#@@@@" .MACRO DIRECTIVE@[@@@@"     @ @@@@          CAJF
)@@G@@SE MACRO\CS\MACRO:@ @@@@           BEGIN " NEW MACRO  @E@@@@            JG
)@@G@@ COMPILE\CLOSE\MACRO(FALSE); " AND DIAGNOSE     @E@@@@             SCAN(JH
)@@G@@CTRM+CNAM+ALLOW\NAM); " SCAN MACRO NAME   @D@@@@             CONVERT\TO\JI
)@@G@@MONOCASE; " THE MACRO NAME    @D@@@@             COMPILE\OPEN\MACRO; " OJJ
)@@G@@PEN NEW MACRO     @C@@@@             ACQUIRE\SENTINEL; " AND SAVE IT    JK
)@@G@@@ @@@@           END; " NEW MACRO   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" .ENDM DIRECTIVE.JL
)@@G@@  THIS ONLY CAUSES TERMINATION IF THE SENTINEL ON     @E@@@@" THE .ENDM JM
)@@G@@DIRECTIVE MATCHES THE SENTINEL ACQUIRED ABOVE.  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@      JN
)@@G@@    CASE MACRO\CS\END,MACRO\CS\ENDM:@A@@@@           BEGIN " SENTINEL CHJO
)@@G@@ECK   @B@@@@             IF SENTINEL\MATCHES THEN     @D@@@@            JP
)@@G@@    COMPILE\CLOSE\MACRO(TRUE); " CLOSE IT @#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@JQ
)@@G@@                COMPILE\WRITE(0);   @A@@@@           END; " SENTINEL CHEJR
)@@G@@CK    @[@@@@"     @#@@@@" .IF DIRECTIVE   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          CAJS
)@@G@@SE MACRO\CS\IF:   @ @@@@           BEGIN " MACRO IF   @F@@@@            JT
)@@G@@ COMPILE\PUSH(MACRO\CS\IF); " PUSH IF STMT ONTO STACK @ @@@@            JU
)@@G@@ COMPILE\WRITE(0);@ @@@@           END; " MACRO IF    @[@@@@"     @#@@@@JV
)@@G@@" .ELSE DIRECTIVE @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          CASE MACRO\CS\ELSE: @ @@@@JW
)@@G@@           BEGIN " NEST CHECK @E@@@@             IF STACK\TOP(STACK\PTR)JX
)@@G@@ NE MACRO\CS\IF THEN    @D@@@@                DIAGNOSE\MACRO\ERROR(MACROJY
)@@G@@\CS\ELSE);  @#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@              BEGIN " MACRO ELJZ
)@@G@@SE    @G@@@@                ADDR\SAVE := STACK\ADR(STACK\PTR); " SAVE ADKA
)@@G@@DRESS OF IF @C@@@@                COMPILE\POP; " POP THE STACK    @C@@@@KB
)@@G@@                COMPILE\PUSH(MACRO\CS\ELSE);    @A@@@@                COKC
)@@G@@MPILE\WRITE(0);   @E@@@@                COMPILE\UPDATE(ADDR\SAVE); " UPDKD
)@@G@@ATE ADDRESS @A@@@@              END; " MACRO ELSE     @ @@@@           EKE
)@@G@@ND; " NEST CHECK  @[@@@@"     @#@@@@" .ENDIF DIRECTIVE@[@@@@"     @ @@@@KF
)@@G@@          CASE MACRO\CS\ENDIF:@ @@@@           BEGIN " NEXT CHECK @E@@@@KG
)@@G@@             IF STACK\TOP(STACK\PTR) NE MACRO\CS\IF AND     @E@@@@      KH
)@@G@@          STACK\TOP(STACK\PTR) NE MACRO\CS\ELSE THEN  @D@@@@            KI
)@@G@@    DIAGNOSE\MACRO\ERROR(MACRO\CS\ENDIF); @#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@KJ
)@@G@@              BEGIN " MACRO ENDIF   @H@@@@                ADDR\SAVE := SKK
)@@G@@TACK\ADR(STACK\PTR); " SAVE ADDRESS OF IF STMT  @E@@@@                COKL
)@@G@@MPILE\UPDATE(ADDR\SAVE); " UPDATE ADDRESS @B@@@@                COMPILE\KM
)@@G@@POP; " POP STACK  @A@@@@              END; " MACRO ENDIF    @ @@@@      KN
)@@G@@     END; " NEST CHECK  @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" .REPEAT DIRECTIVE     @[@@@@KO
)@@G@@"     @A@@@@          CASE MACRO\CS\REPEAT:     @A@@@@           BEGIN "KP
)@@G@@ MACRO REPEAT     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" SHOULD PROBABLY BE WRITTEN ANYWAY KQ
)@@G@@FOR TRACING.@[@@@@"     @C@@@@             COMPILE\PUSH(MACRO\CS\REPEAT)KR
)@@G@@;     @ @@@@           END; " MACRO REPEAT@[@@@@"     @#@@@@" .WHILE DIRKS
)@@G@@ECTIVE@#@@@@" .UNTIL DIRECTIVE@[@@@@"     @C@@@@          CASE MACRO\CS\KT
)@@G@@WHILE,MACRO\CS\UNTIL:   @ @@@@           BEGIN " NEST CHECK @E@@@@      KU
)@@G@@       IF STACK\TOP(STACK\PTR) NE MACRO\CS\REPEAT THEN@D@@@@            KV
)@@G@@    DIAGNOSE\MACRO\ERROR(IMAGE\TYPE);     @#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@KW
)@@G@@              BEGIN " MACRO TESTS   @F@@@@                COMPILE\PUSH(IKX
)@@G@@MAGE\TYPE); " FLAG WHILE\UNTIL SEEN @A@@@@                COMPILE\WRITE(KY
)@@G@@0);   @A@@@@              END; " MACRO TESTS    @ @@@@           END; " KZ
)@@G@@NEST CHECK  @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" .ENDREP DIRECTIVE     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@LA
)@@G@@          CASE MACRO\CS\LOOP,MACRO\CS\ENDREP:   @ @@@@           BEGIN "LB
)@@G@@ NEST CHECK @E@@@@             IF STACK\TOP(STACK\PTR) NE MACRO\CS\WHILELC
)@@G@@ AND  @E@@@@                STACK\TOP(STACK\PTR) NE MACRO\CS\UNTIL THEN LD
)@@G@@@D@@@@                DIAGNOSE\MACRO\ERROR(MACRO\CS\ENDREP);@#@@@@      LE
)@@G@@       ELSE @A@@@@              BEGIN " MACRO ENDREP  @H@@@@            LF
)@@G@@    COMPILE\WRITE(STACK\ADR(STACK\PTR-1)); " POINT AT 'REPEAT'    @G@@@@LG
)@@G@@                COMPILE\UPDATE( STACK\ADR(STACK\PTR) ); " UPDATE ADDRESSLH
)@@G@@@B@@@@                COMPILE\POP; " POP STACK  @C@@@@                COLI
)@@G@@MPILE\POP; " POP STACK AGAIN  @A@@@@              END; " MACRO ENDREP   LJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@           END; " NEST CHECK  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" CARDS OF UNKNOWNLK
)@@G@@ TYPE END UP HERE.@[@@@@"     @#@@@@          CASE *: @A@@@@           BLL
)@@G@@EGIN " UNKNOWN CARD     @ @@@@             COMPILE\WRITE(0);@ @@@@      LM
)@@G@@     END; " UNKNOWN CARD@#@@@@          ENDCASE;@[@@@@"     @D@@@@" IF CLN
)@@G@@OMPILER\DEBUG IS ON DUMP RELEVANT INFORMATION.  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@      LO
)@@G@@    INCLUDE(COMPILER\DEBUG);  @B@@@@             DISPLAY('STKPTR',STACK\LP
)@@G@@PTR); @D@@@@             DISPLAY('STKTOP',STACK\TOP(STACK\PTR));  @#@@@@LQ
)@@G@@          RESUME; @[@@@@"     @^@@@@END; " COMPILE\IMAGE    @[@@@@"     LR
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" OPEN THE COMPILALS
)@@G@@TION PROCESS@[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE COMPILE\OPEN  @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@LT
)@@G@@          CURRENT\MACRO := NULL\PTR; " EMPTY QUEUE    @D@@@@          ERLU
)@@G@@ROR\COMPILING\MACRO := FALSE; " NO ERRORS @^@@@@END; " COMPILE\OPEN     LV
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" CLOSE COMPILATION PROCESS AND POST OR ABLW
)@@G@@ORT NEW MACRO DEFINITIONS.    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE COMPILE\CLOSE LX
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@DECLARE   NEXT\MACRO: MACHINE POINTER WORD; " TO NEXT LY
)@@G@@TO DO @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" RELEASE DATA ACQUIRED FOR MACRO COMPILATION.  LZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@          RELEASE\CORE(MACRO\OUTPUT\PACKET); " RELEASEMA
)@@G@@ PACKET     @E@@@@          MACRO\OUTPUT\PACKET := NULL\PTR; " POST RELEMB
)@@G@@ASE   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" ENTER THE TEMPORARY CHAIN OF MACROS INTO THE MMC
)@@G@@ACRO TREE, WHICH IS     @F@@@@" POINTED TO BY MACROS.  THIS IS DONE SO TMD
)@@G@@HAT NO MACROS WILL BE   @E@@@@" WIPED OUT UNTIL THE ENTIRE ELEMENT IS SYME
)@@G@@NTAX-CHECKED.     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          NEXT\MACRO := CURRENT\MACRMF
)@@G@@O; " GET START OF CHAIN @F@@@@          WHILE (NEXT\MACRO NE NULL\PTR) DMG
)@@G@@O " LOOP OVER ALL MACROS@B@@@@           BEGIN " PROCESS NEXT MACRO     MH
)@@G@@@D@@@@             CURRENT\MACRO := NEXT\MACRO; " UNCHAIN IT@E@@@@      MI
)@@G@@       NEXT\MACRO := SRLK(NEXT\MACRO); " AND GET NEXT @B@@@@            MJ
)@@G@@ IF ERROR\COMPILING\MACRO THEN@D@@@@                COMPILE\ABORT\MACRO;MK
)@@G@@ " RELEASE IT     @A@@@@             ELSE " NO ERRORS FOUND @E@@@@      ML
)@@G@@          COMPILE\POST\MACRO; " POST IT INTO TREE     @A@@@@           EMM
)@@G@@ND; " PROCESS NEXT MACRO@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" IF DEBUG CONFIGURED DUMP SUMMN
)@@G@@MARY INFORMATION. @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          INCLUDE(COMPILER\DEBUG);  MO
)@@G@@@D@@@@             DISPLAY('MACERR',ERROR\COMPILING\MACRO); @C@@@@      MP
)@@G@@       PDISPLAY('CURMAC',CURRENT\MACRO);  @B@@@@             PDISPLAY('MMQ
)@@G@@ACROS',MACROS);   @#@@@@          RESUME; @[@@@@"     @^@@@@END; " COMPIMR
)@@G@@LE\CLOSE    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" ABORT THE DEFINITION OF 'CURMS
)@@G@@RENT\MACRO' @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE COMPILE\ABORT\MACRO @[@@@@BEGIN MT
)@@G@@@F@@@@          IF DADR(CURRENT\MACRO) NE NULL\PTR THEN " BUFFER EXISTS MU
)@@G@@@F@@@@             RELEASE\CORE(DADR(CURRENT\MACRO)); " SO RELEASE IT   MV
)@@G@@@G@@@@          RELEASE\CORE(CURRENT\MACRO); " RELEASE MACRO ENTRY ITSELMW
)@@G@@F     @E@@@@          CURRENT\MACRO := NULL\PTR; " SET NULL FOR RETURN  MX
)@@G@@@ @@@@END; " COMPILE\ABORT\MACRO    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" POSTMY
)@@G@@ THE DEFINITION OF 'CURRENT\MACRO'  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE COMPILE\MZ
)@@G@@POST\MACRO  @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   TMP: MACHINE WORD POINTER; " TO NA
)@@G@@FOUND MACRO @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          DTYP(CURRENT\MACRO) := TYPINT; "NB
)@@G@@ SET TYPE INTEGER @C@@@@          TMP := SEARCH\FOR\NODE(MACROS, TYPSTR,NC
)@@G@@@F@@@@             SLEN(CURRENT\MACRO) , LOC(SNAM(CURRENT\MACRO)) );    ND
)@@G@@@A@@@@          IF TMP EQ NULL\PTR THEN   @A@@@@           BEGIN " INSERNE
)@@G@@T MACRO     @F@@@@             MACROS := INSERT\NEW\NODE(MACROS,CURRENT\NF
)@@G@@MACRO);     @ @@@@           END; " INSERT MACRO@B@@@@          ELSE " ENG
)@@G@@NTRY ALREADY EXISTS     @A@@@@           BEGIN " SET NEW MACRO    @D@@@@NH
)@@G@@             SET\VALUE(TMP,CURRENT\MACRO); " COPY DATA@C@@@@            NI
)@@G@@ SMAD(TMP) := SMAD(CURRENT\MACRO);  @G@@@@             IF DADR(CURRENT\MNJ
)@@G@@ACRO) NE NULL\PTR THEN " BUFFER EXISTS    @F@@@@                RELEASE\NK
)@@G@@CORE(DADR(CURRENT\MACRO)); " SO RELEASE IT@F@@@@             RELEASE\CORNL
)@@G@@E(CURRENT\MACRO); " RELEASE CORE BUFFER   @F@@@@             CURRENT\MACNM
)@@G@@RO := TMP; " SET CORRECT VALUE POINTER    @A@@@@           END; " SET NENN
)@@G@@W MACRO     @ @@@@END; " COMPILE\ABORT\MACRO    @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTRONO
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" OPEN THE DEFINITION OF A NEWNP
)@@G@@ MACRO.  MACRO NAME IS ASSUMED TO   @ @@@@" BE SCANNED AND MONOCASED.   NQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE COMPILE\OPEN\MACRO  @[@@@@BEGIN @G@@@@DECLARNR
)@@G@@E   TEMP\PTR: MACHINE WORD POINTER LOCATABLE; " TEMP FOR INIT CALL@[@@@@NS
)@@G@@"     @ @@@@" CREATE ENTRY FOR MACRO TREE @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          IFNT
)@@G@@ (MONOCASE\LEN EQ 0) THEN " NULL MACRO NAME     @#@@@@           BEGIN  NU
)@@G@@@G@@@@             DISPLAY('MACNAM',MONOCASE\LEN); " DISPLAY ERROR MESSANV
)@@G@@GE    @C@@@@             ERROR\COMPILING\MACRO := TRUE;     @G@@@@      NW
)@@G@@       MONOCASE\LEN := 4; " TO AVOID ERROR IN CREATE\NEW\NODE     @#@@@@NX
)@@G@@           END;   @E@@@@          IF (MONOCASE\LEN GT 20) THEN " MACRO NNY
)@@G@@AME TOO LONG@B@@@@           BEGIN " TO TELL HIM ABOUT IT   @C@@@@      NZ
)@@G@@       DISPLAY('MACNAM',MONOCASE\LEN);    @E@@@@             MONOCASE\LEOA
)@@G@@N := 20; " TRUNCATE TO 20 CHARACTERS@#@@@@           END;   @F@@@@      OB
)@@G@@    TEMP\PTR := CREATE\NEW\NODE(MONOCASE\PTR); " CREATE NODE@[@@@@"     OC
)@@G@@@D@@@@" PUT THIS MACRO ENTRY ON THE QUEUE OF MACROS CREATED.@[@@@@"     OD
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SRLK(TEMP\PTR) := CURRENT\MACRO; " SET LINK TO REST     OE
)@@G@@@E@@@@          CURRENT\MACRO := TEMP\PTR; " SAVE POINTER TO IT   @[@@@@OF
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@" SET UP FOR COMPILATION@[@@@@"     @G@@@@          TEMP\PTROG
)@@G@@ := LOC(MACRO\TEMP\PTR); " GET INPUT BUFFER ADDRESS   @A@@@@          INOH
)@@G@@ITIALIZE\FILE\WRITTING  @F@@@@             (%MACRO\OUTPUT\PACKET,%TEMP\POI
)@@G@@TR); " OPEN OUTPUT FILE @B@@@@          STACK\PTR := 0; " EMPTY STACK   OJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          COMPILE\PUSH(MACRO\CS\MACRO); " PUSH MACRO ONTO STACK   OK
)@@G@@@B@@@@          SNTL := 0; " CLEAR SENTINEL     @ @@@@END; " COMPILE\OPEOL
)@@G@@N\MACRO     @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     OM
)@@G@@@D@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO CLOSE THE CURREN MACRO. @D@@@@" IF CON
)@@G@@ONTROL STRUCTURE IS STACKED ISSUE DIAGNOSTIC.   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDOO
)@@G@@URE COMPILE\CLOSE\MACRO(NORMAL: CONDITION) " FLAG ENDM SEEN @[@@@@BEGIN OP
)@@G@@@D@@@@          IF (STACK\PTR EQ 0) THEN ERROR; " $$$DEBUG  @[@@@@"     OQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@" CLOSE ANY REMAINING CONTROL STRUCTURES. @[@@@@"     @E@@@@      OR
)@@G@@    IF (STACK\PTR GT 1) THEN " STRUCTURE TO CLOSE     @G@@@@            OS
)@@G@@ DIAGNOSE\MACRO\ERROR(MACRO\CS\ENDM); " CLOSE ALL STRUCTURES@[@@@@"     OT
)@@G@@@G@@@@" FIRST MACRO IN EXTERNAL ELEMENT IS FLAGGED WITH ZERO LINE NUMBEROU
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@" INHIBIT ENDM DIAGNOSTIC IN THIS MACRO.  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@OV
)@@G@@          IF NORMAL OR (STACK\LIN(1) EQ 0) THEN @C@@@@             COMPIOW
)@@G@@LE\POP; " POP MACRO ENTRY     @#@@@@          ELSE    @F@@@@            OX
)@@G@@ DIAGNOSE\MACRO\ERROR(0); " CLOSE MACRO AND DIAGNOSE  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@OY
)@@G@@          IF (STACK\PTR NE 0) THEN ERROR; " $$$DEBUG  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@OZ
)@@G@@" IF THE MACRO USES ONLY ONE 224 WORD BLOCK, WE LEAVE A COPY@F@@@@" OF TPA
)@@G@@HE COMPILED TEXT IN CORE FOR QUICK ACCESS.  IF MORE THAN    @F@@@@" ONE PB
)@@G@@BUFFER IS REQUIRED, THE MACRO RESIDES IN THE SCRATCH FILE.  @[@@@@"     PC
)@@G@@@G@@@@          IF IO\DONE(MACRO\OUTPUT\PACKET) THEN " NOT ALL IN ONE BUPD
)@@G@@FFER  @B@@@@           BEGIN " RELEASE CORE BUFFER    @B@@@@            PE
)@@G@@ DLEN(CURRENT\MACRO) := 0;    @C@@@@             DADR(CURRENT\MACRO) := PF
)@@G@@NULL\PTR;   @B@@@@           END; " RELEASE CORE BUFFER     @A@@@@      PG
)@@G@@    ELSE " ALL IN ONE BUFFER  @F@@@@             COMPILE\CLOSE\BUFFER; "PH
)@@G@@ CLOSE AND POST CORE BUFFER   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" SAVE DRUM ADDRESS AND PI
)@@G@@CLOSE OUTPUT PACKET.    @[@@@@"     @G@@@@          SMAD(CURRENT\MACRO) PJ
)@@G@@:= START\DRUM\ADDR(MACRO\OUTPUT\PACKET);  @I@@@@          USER\IMAGE\BUFPK
)@@G@@FER(MACRO\OUTPUT\PACKET) := NULL\PTR; " SO NOT RELEASED     @E@@@@      PL
)@@G@@    CLOSE\FILE(MACRO\OUTPUT\PACKET); " RELEASE BUFFERS@D@@@@"         ODPM
)@@G@@ISPLAY('DRMADR',SMAD(CURRENT\MACRO));     @ @@@@END; " COMPILE\CLOSE\MACPN
)@@G@@RO    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THE MACRO ONLY USES ONE BUFFER.  MPO
)@@G@@AKE A COPY OF IT FOR THE TREE.@[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE COMPILE\CLOSE\PP
)@@G@@BUFFER@[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@DECLARE   MOP: MACHINE POINTER WORD; " TO OUTPUTPQ
)@@G@@ PACKET     @E@@@@DECLARE   MAC\LEN: INTEGER WORD; " LENGTH OF CORE NEEDPR
)@@G@@ED    @E@@@@DECLARE   MAC\PTR: MACHINE WORD POINTER; " POINTER TO CORE  PS
)@@G@@@E@@@@DECLARE   IOB\PTR: MACHINE WORD POINTER; " POINTER TO BUFFER@[@@@@PT
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@DECLARE   MAC(1): INTEGER WORD BASED(MAC\PTR); " CORE WORD  PU
)@@G@@@E@@@@DECLARE   IOB(1): INTEGER WORD BASED(IOB\PTR); " BUFFER WORD@[@@@@PV
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@          MOP := MACRO\OUTPUT\PACKET; " SET PACKET ADDRESS  PW
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@" NOTE FIRST 2 WORDS OF ADDR1 ARE BUFFER CONTROL WORDSPX
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@          CORE(BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR(MOP)) := -1; " SETPY
)@@G@@ EOF  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" COMPUTE LENGTH OF CORE BUFFER NEEDED.   @A@@@@PZ
)@@G@@" NOTE 1 IS ADDED TO ALLOW FOR EOF  @[@@@@"     @H@@@@          MAC\LEN QA
)@@G@@:= 1 + OFFSET( BUFFER\IMAGE\LOCATOR(MOP) , ADDR1(MOP) );    @F@@@@      QB
)@@G@@    MAC\PTR := ALLOCATE\CORE(MAC\LEN); " GET CORE BUFFER    @D@@@@      QC
)@@G@@    IOB\PTR := ADDR1(MOP); " GET BUFFER ADDRESS @A@@@@          FOR I :=QD
)@@G@@ 1 TO MAC\LEN DO  @B@@@@             MAC(I) := IOB(I); " COPY TEXT@E@@@@QE
)@@G@@          DLEN(CURRENT\MACRO) := MAC\LEN; " SET DATA LENGTH @E@@@@      QF
)@@G@@    DADR(CURRENT\MACRO) := MAC\PTR; " SET CORE BUFFER @ @@@@END; " COMPIQG
)@@G@@LE\CLOSE\BUFFER   @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@QH
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@" SCAN THE CURRENT IMAGE AND DECIDE WHAT IT IS. @A@@@@" IF DQI
)@@G@@ATA (TEXT) IMAGE RETURNS ZERO.@A@@@@" IF DIRECTIVE RETURNS DWTS INDEX.  QJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@" NOTE TO MYSELF - SOMEDAY DONT ALLOW ABBREVIATIONS.  QK
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE CLASSIFY\MACRO\IMAGE@ @@@@          RESULT IQL
)@@G@@NTEGER WORD @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@DECLARE   IMAGE\TYPE: INTEGER WORD; @[@@@@QM
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@          IMAGE\TYPE := 0; " INITIALLY UNKNOWN  @G@@@@      QN
)@@G@@    IF (CARD\LENGTH GT 0) AND (INPUT\CARD(1) EQ STATIC\DID) THEN  @B@@@@QO
)@@G@@           BEGIN " SCAN FOR DIRECTIVE NAME@ @@@@             CARD\INDEX QP
)@@G@@:= 2; @C@@@@             SCANNER\ERROR := 0; " INITIALIZE   @ @@@@      QQ
)@@G@@       SCAN(ALLOW\NAM); @C@@@@             CONVERT\TO\MONOCASE; " THE NAQR
)@@G@@ME    @F@@@@             IMAGE\TYPE := KEYWORD\SEARCH " SEARCH MACRO KEYQS
)@@G@@WORDS @G@@@@                ( LOC(SYSTEM\MACROS(1)) , NSYS\MACRO , DISABQT
)@@G@@LE\AB );    @B@@@@           END; " SCAN FOR DIRECTIVE NAME @A@@@@      QU
)@@G@@    INCLUDE(COMPILER\DEBUG);  @G@@@@             PRINT(LOC(INPUT\CARD\WOQV
)@@G@@RD(1)),CARD\LENGTH,1); " PRINT IMAGE@C@@@@             DISPLAY('LINE',MAQW
)@@G@@CRO\LINE\NUM);    @D@@@@             DISPLAY('CLASS',IMAGE\TYPE); " AND QX
)@@G@@CLASS @#@@@@          RESUME; @ @@@@          RETURN(IMAGE\TYPE); @ @@@@QY
)@@G@@END; " CLASSIFY\MACRO\IMAGE   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" SCAN AND SQZ
)@@G@@AVE SENTINEL FOR LATER USE.   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE ACQUIRE\SENTINRA
)@@G@@EL    @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@          SCAN(CTRM+CNAM+ALLOW\NAM+ALLOW\STR); "RB
)@@G@@ SCAN SENTINEL    @D@@@@          SNTL := (CSDLEN+3)//4; " GET WORD LENGRC
)@@G@@TH    @ @@@@          IF SNTL GT 8 THEN   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @^@@@@RD
)@@G@@             SNTL := 8; @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          FOR I :=RE
)@@G@@ 1 TO SNTL DO     @C@@@@             SENT(I) := DNUM(I); " COPY SENTINELRF
)@@G@@@^@@@@END; " ACQUIRE\SENTINEL @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" SCAN SENTIRG
)@@G@@NEL AND COMPARE AGAINST THAT ONE SAVED.   @A@@@@" IF THEY MATCH RETURN ARH
)@@G@@ TRUE VALUE.@[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE SENTINEL\MATCHES    @ @@@@      RI
)@@G@@    RESULT CONDITION    @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@DECLARE   MATCH: CONDITION; " RJ
)@@G@@IF IT MATCHES     @E@@@@DECLARE   TSNTL: INTEGER WORD; " LENGTH OF TEST RK
)@@G@@SENTINEL    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          MATCH := TRUE; " INITIALLY SET TRL
)@@G@@RUE   @F@@@@          SCAN(CTRM+CNAM+ALLOW\STR+ALLOW\NAM); " GET SENTINERM
)@@G@@L     @D@@@@          TSNTL := (CSDLEN+3)//4; " GET WORD LENGTH   @ @@@@RN
)@@G@@          IF TSNTL GT 8 THEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @^@@@@            RO
)@@G@@ TSNTL := 8;@#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          IF TSNTL NE SNTL THERP
)@@G@@N     @E@@@@             MATCH := FALSE; " IF LENGTHS DIFFER NO MATCH   RQ
)@@G@@@#@@@@          ELSE    @A@@@@           BEGIN " COMPARE VALUES   @A@@@@RR
)@@G@@             FOR I := 1 TO TSNTL DO @B@@@@                IF SENT(I) NE RS
)@@G@@DNUM(I) THEN@E@@@@                   MATCH := FALSE; " NO MATCH IF DIFFERT
)@@G@@R     @A@@@@           END; " COMPARE VALUES    @A@@@@          RETURN(MRU
)@@G@@ATCH); " TO CALLER@^@@@@END; " SENTINEL\MATCHES @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTRORV
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @H@@@@" COMPILE\PUSH(T)  PUSHES THE RW
)@@G@@CURRENT OUTPUT ADDRESS AND T ONTO THE STACK     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDRX
)@@G@@URE COMPILE\PUSH(TYPE: INTEGER WORD)@[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          IF STACKRY
)@@G@@\PTR GE STACK\SIZE THEN " OVERFLOW  @F@@@@             DIAGNOSE\MACRO\ERRZ
)@@G@@ROR(TYPE); " GENERATE DIAGNOSTIC    @#@@@@          ELSE    @ @@@@      SA
)@@G@@     BEGIN " STACK PUSH @E@@@@             STACK\PTR := STACK\PTR+1; " ISB
)@@G@@NCREMENT POINTER  @G@@@@             STACK\TOP(STACK\PTR) := TYPE; " STASC
)@@G@@CK TYPE OF CONTROL ELT  @G@@@@             STACK\ADR(STACK\PTR) := MACROSD
)@@G@@\XFER\PTR; " AND IMAGE ADDRESS@G@@@@             STACK\LIN(STACK\PTR) :=SE
)@@G@@ MACRO\LINE\NUM; " SAVE LINE NUMBER @ @@@@           END; " STACK PUSH  SF
)@@G@@@^@@@@END; " COMPILE\PUSH     @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" COMPILE\POSG
)@@G@@P      POPS THE STACK ONE LEVEL     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE COMPILE\SH
)@@G@@POP   @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          IF STACK\PTR LE 0 THEN " POP WHAT     SI
)@@G@@@B@@@@             ERROR; " SHOULD NEVER HAPPEN @#@@@@          ELSE    SJ
)@@G@@@B@@@@             STACK\PTR := STACK\PTR-1;    @#@@@@END; " COMPILE\POPSK
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE WRITES THE CURRENT IMAGE SL
)@@G@@TO THE SCRATCH FILE.    @D@@@@" THE ARGUMENT GOES TO THE TRANSFER ADDRESSM
)@@G@@S FIELD.    @[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE COMPILE\WRITE(ADDRESS: INTEGER WSN
)@@G@@ORD) " ADDRESS FOR MACRO\XFER @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@DECLARE   LEN: INTEGER WSO
)@@G@@ORD; " LENGTH OF IMAGE  @D@@@@DECLARE   SAVE(2): INTEGER WORD; " SAVE BUSP
)@@G@@FFER CONTROL@[@@@@"     @F@@@@          LEN := CARD\LENGTH + 8; " SAVE OSQ
)@@G@@VER STORE INTO TEMPS    @C@@@@          SAVE(1) := MACRO\TEMP\PTR; " SAVSR
)@@G@@E     @C@@@@          SAVE(2) := MACRO\TEMP\NUM; " CONTROL  @A@@@@      SS
)@@G@@    MACRO\TEMP\PTR := ADDRESS;@C@@@@          MACRO\TEMP\NUM := MACRO\LIST
)@@G@@NE\NUM;     @C@@@@          WRITE\FILE(MACRO\OUTPUT\PACKET,LEN);  @C@@@@SU
)@@G@@          MACRO\TEMP\PTR := SAVE(1); " RESTORE  @C@@@@          MACRO\TESV
)@@G@@MP\NUM := SAVE(2); " CONTROL  @^@@@@END; " COMPILE\WRITE    @[@@@@"     SW
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THE FUNCTION OF SX
)@@G@@THIS PROCEDURE IS TO INSERT LINKAGES FOR THE FORWARD  @G@@@@" REFERENCESSY
)@@G@@ IN THE COMPILED MACRO.  WHEN CALLED IT DEPOSITS THE CURRENT@G@@@@" OUTPSZ
)@@G@@UT ADDRESS IN THE XFER FIELD OF THE IMAGE WHOSE DRUM ADDRESS IS   @G@@@@TA
)@@G@@" IN THE FORMAL PARAMETER DRUMAD.  IF THE IMAGE IS STILL IN CORE THEN   TB
)@@G@@@H@@@@" THE UPDATE IS MADE IMMEDIATELY, ELSE THE SDF OUTPUT PACKET IS TETC
)@@G@@MPORARILY   @G@@@@" USED TO READ THE REQUIRED BUFFER INTO THE ALTERNATE TD
)@@G@@BUFFER, WHERE THE @D@@@@" UPDATE IS MADE.  THE BUFFER IS WRITTEN BACK OUTE
)@@G@@T.    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE COMPILE\UPDATE(DRUMAD: WORD INTEGER)  TF
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@DECLARE   TEMP: WORD INTEGER; @ @@@@DECLARE   DISP: WOTG
)@@G@@RD INTEGER; @E@@@@DECLARE   OUT: MACHINE WORD POINTER; " TO OUTPUT PACKETH
)@@G@@T     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          OUT := MACRO\OUTPUT\PACKET; " GET PACKTI
)@@G@@ET ADDRESS  @D@@@@          MACRO\XFER\PTR := DRUMAD; " GET DRUM ADDRESSTJ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          IF MACRO\XFER\DADD EQ IMAGE\DRUM\ADDR(OUT) THEN   @C@@@@TK
)@@G@@           BEGIN " THE IMAGE IS STILL IN CORE   @G@@@@             CORE(TL
)@@G@@ADDR1(OUT)+MACRO\XFER\DISP+1) := IMAGE\ADDR(OUT);     @#@@@@           ETM
)@@G@@ND    @G@@@@          ELSE IF (MACRO\XFER\DADD EQ PREVIOUS\BLOCK(ADDR1(OTN
)@@G@@UT))) AND   @E@@@@             (MACRO\XFER\DISP+1 EQ WORD\COUNT(OUT)) THTO
)@@G@@EN    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             CORE(ADDR1(OUT) + 2) :=TP
)@@G@@ IMAGE\ADDR(OUT); @#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@          ELSE " NOT IN TQ
)@@G@@CORE  @C@@@@           BEGIN " MUST READ BUFFER BACK IN     @C@@@@      TR
)@@G@@       WAIT(OUT);" WAIT FOR IO TO FINISH  @E@@@@             TEMP := DRUTS
)@@G@@M\ADDR(OUT); " SAVE DRUM ADDRESS    @C@@@@             DRUM\ADDR(OUT) :=TT
)@@G@@ MACRO\XFER\DADD; @F@@@@             BUFFER\ADDR(OUT) := ADDR2(OUT); " STU
)@@G@@ET CORE ADDRESS   @F@@@@             FUNCTION(OUT) := IO\FUNC\READ; " SETV
)@@G@@T FUNCTION TO R$  @D@@@@             IOWWEC(OUT); " READ BUFFER INTO CORTW
)@@G@@E     @F@@@@             DISP := MACRO\XFER\DISP; " SAVE DISPLACEMENT RETX
)@@G@@QUIRED@H@@@@             IF MACRO\XFER\DISP+1 EQ WORD\COUNT(OUT) THEN " TY
)@@G@@IN NEXT BUFFER    @^@@@@              BEGIN     @E@@@@                DRTZ
)@@G@@UM\ADDR(OUT) := NEXT\BLOCK(ADDR2(OUT));   @D@@@@                IOWWEC(OUA
)@@G@@UT); " READ CORRECT BLOCK     @E@@@@                DISP := 1; " AND COMUB
)@@G@@PUTE NEW DISPLACEMENT   @#@@@@              END;@E@@@@             CORE(UC
)@@G@@ADDR2(OUT)+DISP+1) := IMAGE\ADDR(OUT);    @G@@@@             FUNCTION(OUUD
)@@G@@T) := IO\FUNC\WRITE; " RESET FUNCTION TO W$     @D@@@@             IOWWEUE
)@@G@@C(OUT); " WRITE THE BUFFER OUT AGAIN@E@@@@             DRUM\ADDR(OUT) :=UF
)@@G@@ TEMP; " RESTORE DRUM ADDRESS @#@@@@           END;   @^@@@@END; " COMPIUG
)@@G@@LE\UPDATE   @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     UH
)@@G@@@G@@@@" THE FOLLOWING PROCEDURES PURPORT TO GENERATE MEANINGFUL DIAGNOSTUI
)@@G@@ICS   @G@@@@" FOR USER ERRORS IN MACRO CONSTRUCTION.  THE TWO RELEVANT PUJ
)@@G@@ARAMETERS   @E@@@@" ARE THE CURRENT IMAGE TYPE AND THE STACK-TOP IMAGE TUK
)@@G@@YPE.  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE DIAGNOSE\MACRO\ERROR(IMAGE\TYPE: INTEGUL
)@@G@@ER WORD)    @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          ERROR\COMPILING\MACRO := TRUE; "UM
)@@G@@ FLAG ERROR @A@@@@          IF NOT REMOTE\BREAK THEN  @D@@@@            UN
)@@G@@ DIAGNOSE\GENERAL\ERROR; " GENERAL MESSAGE@[@@@@"     @G@@@@" BRANCH ON UO
)@@G@@IMAGE WHICH CAUSED THE ERROR.  NOTE THAT THIS ROUTINE MAKES @E@@@@" VERYUP
)@@G@@ EXPLICIT ASSUMPTIONS ABOUT THE REASONS IT WAS CALLED.@[@@@@"     @F@@@@UQ
)@@G@@          CASEENTRY IMAGE\TYPE " WHAT KIND OF IMAGE GENERATED     @[@@@@UR
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@" THE ONLY ERROR ON IF OR REPEAT IS STACK OVERFLOW    @[@@@@US
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@          CASE MACRO\CS\IF,MACRO\CS\REPEAT:     @G@@@@      UT
)@@G@@       DIAGNOSE\STACK\ERROR(IMAGE\TYPE); " DIAGNOSE STACK OVERFLOW@[@@@@UU
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@" ELSE ERRORS INCLUDE TWO ELSES OR MISSING IF.  @[@@@@"     UV
)@@G@@@ @@@@          CASE MACRO\CS\ELSE: @E@@@@             IF (STACK\TOP(STAUW
)@@G@@CK\PTR) EQ MACRO\CS\ELSE) THEN@I@@@@                DIAGNOSE\SECOND(MACRUX
)@@G@@O\CS\ELSE,MACRO\CS\IF); " SECOND ELSE FOR IF    @#@@@@             ELSE UY
)@@G@@@H@@@@                DIAGNOSE\UNOPENED(MACRO\CS\IF,MACRO\CS\ELSE); " UNUZ
)@@G@@OPENED IF   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" THE ENDIF ERROR IS MISSING IF.    @[@@@@VA
)@@G@@"     @ @@@@          CASE MACRO\CS\ENDIF:@H@@@@             DIAGNOSE\UNVB
)@@G@@OPENED(MACRO\CS\IF,MACRO\CS\ENDIF); " UNOPENED IF     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@VC
)@@G@@" THE WHILE ERRORS INCLUDE DUPLICATE WHILE/UNTIL AND MISSING REPEAT.    VD
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@          CASE MACRO\CS\WHILE,MACRO\CS\UNTIL:   @E@@@@VE
)@@G@@             IF (STACK\TOP(STACK\PTR) EQ MACRO\CS\WHILE) OR @F@@@@      VF
)@@G@@          (STACK\TOP(STACK\PTR) EQ MACRO\CS\UNTIL) THEN     @F@@@@      VG
)@@G@@          DIAGNOSE\SECOND(0,MACRO\CS\REPEAT); " SECOND WHILE@#@@@@      VH
)@@G@@       ELSE @I@@@@                DIAGNOSE\UNOPENED(MACRO\CS\REPEAT,IMAGVI
)@@G@@E\TYPE); " UNOPENED REPEAT    @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THE ENDREP ERRORS INCLVJ
)@@G@@UDE MISSING REPEAT AND MISSING WHILE/UNTIL.     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@      VK
)@@G@@    CASE MACRO\CS\ENDREP:     @F@@@@             IF (STACK\TOP(STACK\PTRVL
)@@G@@) EQ MACRO\CS\REPEAT) THEN    @G@@@@                DIAGNOSE\UNOPENED(0,VM
)@@G@@MACRO\CS\ENDREP); " NO WHILE\UN     @#@@@@             ELSE @I@@@@      VN
)@@G@@          DIAGNOSE\UNOPENED(MACRO\CS\REPEAT,MACRO\CS\ENDREP); " UNOPENEDVO
)@@G@@ R    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" IF CALLED WITH CODE 'ENDM' CLOSE ALL CONTROL SVP
)@@G@@TRUCTURES BUT DONT@ @@@@" DIAGNOSE UNCLOSED MACRO     @[@@@@"     @ @@@@VQ
)@@G@@          CASE MACRO\CS\ENDM: @B@@@@             WHILE (STACK\PTR GT 1) VR
)@@G@@DO    @F@@@@                DIAGNOSE\UNCLOSED\AND\POP; " DO IF AND REPEAVS
)@@G@@T     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" IF CALLED WITH CODE ZERO (FORCED CLOSE) DIAGNOVT
)@@G@@SE UNCLOSED MACRO.@[@@@@"     @#@@@@          CASE 0: @D@@@@            VU
)@@G@@ DIAGNOSE\UNCLOSED\AND\POP; " DO MACRO    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" ANY OTHER VV
)@@G@@CODE IS AN INTERNAL ERROR     @[@@@@"     @#@@@@          CASE *: @^@@@@VW
)@@G@@             ERROR;     @[@@@@"     @#@@@@          ENDCASE;@[@@@@"     VX
)@@G@@@C@@@@" NOW DUMP IMAGE AT WHICH ERROR IS DETECTED.    @C@@@@" (NOTE PRINVY
)@@G@@T\INPUT\CARD GETS IGDM IF EOF !!!!) @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          IF NOT (VZ
)@@G@@END\FILE(CIP) OR REMOTE\BREAK) THEN @ @@@@             PRINT\INPUT\CARD;WA
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@END; " DIAGNOSE\MACRO\ERROR   @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROWB
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" ISSUE GENERAL ERROR MESSAGE WC
)@@G@@WITH LINE NUMBER AND MACRO NAME.    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDURE DIAGNOSEWD
)@@G@@\GENERAL\ERROR    @[@@@@BEGIN @^@@@@          EDIT\OPEN;    @C@@@@      WE
)@@G@@    EDIT\MESSAGE( LOC(ERR\MSG\ERROR) );   @G@@@@          EDIT\DECIMAL(MWF
)@@G@@ACRO\LINE\NUM); " INSERT CURRENT LINE NUMBER    @ @@@@          EDIT\MORWG
)@@G@@E\MESSAGE;  @I@@@@          EDIT\COPY( LOC(SNAM(CURRENT\MACRO)) , 4*SLENWH
)@@G@@(CURRENT\MACRO) ); " NAME     @C@@@@          EDIT\PRINT(2); " SKIP BEFOWI
)@@G@@RE LINE     @ @@@@END; " DIAGNOSE\GENERAL\ERROR @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     WJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@" ISSUE ERROR MESSAGE FOR USER-CAUSED STACK OVERFLOW  @[@@@@"     WK
)@@G@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE DIAGNOSE\STACK\ERROR(IMAGE\TYPE: INTEGER WORD)    @[@@@@WL
)@@G@@BEGIN @^@@@@          EDIT\OPEN;    @C@@@@          EDIT\MESSAGE( LOC(ERWM
)@@G@@R\MSG\STACK) );   @E@@@@          EDIT\DECIMAL(STACK\SIZE); " TELL HIM WWN
)@@G@@HAT MAX IS  @ @@@@          EDIT\MORE\MESSAGE;  @A@@@@          EDIT\KEYWO
)@@G@@WORD(IMAGE\TYPE); @ @@@@          EDIT\MORE\MESSAGE;  @^@@@@          EDWP
)@@G@@IT\PRINT(1);@ @@@@END; " DIAGNOSE\STACK\ERROR   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     WQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@" ISSUE ERROR MESSAGE FOR SECOND KEYWORD IN CONTEXT ALLOWING ONLY WR
)@@G@@ONE.  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE DIAGNOSE\SECOND(KEY1: INTEGER WORD,KEYWS
)@@G@@2: INTEGER WORD)  @[@@@@BEGIN @^@@@@          EDIT\OPEN;    @C@@@@      WT
)@@G@@    EDIT\MESSAGE( LOC(ERR\MSG\SECOND) );  @ @@@@          EDIT\KEYWORD(KWU
)@@G@@EY1); @ @@@@          EDIT\MORE\MESSAGE;  @ @@@@          EDIT\KEYWORD(KWV
)@@G@@EY2); @ @@@@          EDIT\MORE\MESSAGE;  @G@@@@          EDIT\DECIMAL( WW
)@@G@@STACK\LIN(STACK\PTR) ); " EDIT START LINE NUMBER@^@@@@          EDIT\PRIWX
)@@G@@NT(1);@^@@@@END; " DIAGNOSE\SECOND  @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" ISSUWY
)@@G@@E ERROR MESSAGE FOR UNOPENED CONTROL STRUCTURE  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDWZ
)@@G@@URE DIAGNOSE\UNOPENED(KEY1: INTEGER WORD,KEY2: INTEGER WORD)@[@@@@BEGIN XA
)@@G@@@^@@@@          EDIT\OPEN;    @C@@@@          EDIT\MESSAGE( LOC(ERR\MSG\XB
)@@G@@UNOPENED) );@C@@@@          EDIT\KEYWORD(KEY1); " FIRST INSERTION @ @@@@XC
)@@G@@          EDIT\MORE\MESSAGE;  @C@@@@          EDIT\KEYWORD(KEY2); " SECOXD
)@@G@@ND INSERTION@ @@@@          EDIT\MORE\MESSAGE;  @G@@@@          EDIT\DECXE
)@@G@@IMAL(MACRO\LINE\NUM); " INSERT CURRENT LINE NUMBER    @^@@@@          EDXF
)@@G@@IT\PRINT(1);@^@@@@END; " DIAGNOSE\UNOPENED@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@XG
)@@G@@" ISSUE ERROR MESSAGE FOR UNCLOSED CONTROL STRUCTURE.  NOTE THAT  @F@@@@XH
)@@G@@" THIS ROUTINE ALSO POPS THE COMPILER STACK BY ONE STRUCTURE.     @[@@@@XI
)@@G@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDURE DIAGNOSE\UNCLOSED\AND\POP @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@      XJ
)@@G@@    IF NOT REMOTE\BREAK THEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @^@@@@            XK
)@@G@@ EDIT\OPEN; @D@@@@             EDIT\MESSAGE( LOC(ERR\MSG\UNCLOSED) );   XL
)@@G@@@H@@@@             EDIT\KEYWORD( STACK\TOP(STACK\PTR) ); " TOP OF STACK XM
)@@G@@STRUCTURE   @A@@@@             EDIT\MORE\MESSAGE;     @H@@@@            XN
)@@G@@ EDIT\DECIMAL( STACK\LIN(STACK\PTR) ); " LINE NUMBER WHERE OPENED @A@@@@XO
)@@G@@             EDIT\MORE\MESSAGE;     @ @@@@             EDIT\PRINT(1);   XP
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @C@@@@          COMPILE\POP; " POP COMPILER STACXQ
)@@G@@K     @A@@@@END; " DIAGNOSE\UNCLOSED\AND\POP    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     XR
)@@G@@@A@@@@" EDIT (IN QUOTES) KEYWORD PASSED.  @D@@@@" NOTE SPECIAL CODE ZEROXS
)@@G@@ MEANS EDIT 'WHILE' OR 'UNTIL'@[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE EDIT\KEYWORD(KXT
)@@G@@EY: INTEGER WORD) @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   KEY\PTR: MACHINE POINTER WXU
)@@G@@ORD; " TO KEY     @H@@@@DECLARE   KEYWORD(8): 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER BASXV
)@@G@@ED(KEY\PTR); " KEY ITSELF     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          IF (KEY EQ 0) XW
)@@G@@THEN " SPECIAL FLAG     @I@@@@             EDIT\COPY( LOC(KEY\WORD\WHUN)XX
)@@G@@ , KEY\WORD\WHUN\LEN ); " COPY KEYWORD    @#@@@@          ELSE    @A@@@@XY
)@@G@@           BEGIN " NORMAL KEYWORD   @C@@@@             EDIT\CHARACTER(QUXZ
)@@G@@OTE); " OPEN QUOTE@H@@@@             KEY\PTR := LOC( SYSTEM\MACROS(2*KEYYA
)@@G@@-1) ); " GET FROM OUR TABLE   @A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO 8 DO     YB
)@@G@@@C@@@@                IF (KEYWORD(I) NE BLANK) THEN   @C@@@@            YC
)@@G@@       EDIT\CHARACTER( KEYWORD(I) );@D@@@@             EDIT\CHARACTER(QUYD
)@@G@@OTE); " CLOSE QUOTE     @A@@@@           END; " NORMAL KEYWORD    @^@@@@YE
)@@G@@END; " EDIT\KEYWORD     @[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@@D@@@@DECLARE   MAYF
)@@G@@CRO\OUTPUT\PACKET: MACHI*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@MODULE@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THISYG
)@@G@@ MODULE HANDLES THE SEARCH FOR ALL MACROS AND THE     @ @@@@" DEFINITIONYH
)@@G@@ OF MACROS FOUND. @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);YI
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('CYJ
)@@G@@ONVERT-PROC',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('CORE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   YK
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('FYL
)@@G@@IASG-DEF',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('FIASG-PROCS',IMPORTED);  YM
)@@G@@@G@@@@          COPY ('FILE-PROCS',IMPORTED); " GET INITIALIZE\EXTERNAL\YN
)@@G@@READ  @A@@@@          COPY ('IO-DEF1',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('MYO
)@@G@@ACRO-DEF',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   YP
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('WYQ
)@@G@@ARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@DEFINE    FIELDATA\BLANKS = O'YR
)@@G@@050505050505'; " A WORD OF BLANKS   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" SEARCH PACKET FOYS
)@@G@@R PROGRAM FILE SEARCH (PFS)   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@DECLARE   PFS\PKT: STATIYT
)@@G@@C LOCATABLE MAPPED@F@@@@             [PFS\FNAME(2): INTEGER WORD    " INYU
)@@G@@TERNAL FILE NAME  @E@@@@             ,PFS\ENAME(2): INTEGER WORD    " ELYV
)@@G@@EMENT NAME  @E@@@@             ,*: LOGICAL WORD := O'0'       " HASH LINYW
)@@G@@KS    @F@@@@             ,PFS\BITS: 12 BIT INTEGER      " DESCRIPTION BIYX
)@@G@@TS    @F@@@@             !*:[PFS\DEL: 1 BIT CONDITION      " ELEMENT DELYY
)@@G@@ETED  @E@@@@                ,*(6)   : 1 BIT CONDITION      " IRRELEVANT YZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@                ,PFS\ASC: 1 BIT CONDITION      " ASCII SYMBOLIC   ZA
)@@G@@@E@@@@                ,*(4)   : 1 BIT CONDITION]     " IRRELEVANT @G@@@@ZB
)@@G@@             ,PFS\TYPE:  6 BIT INTEGER := 1 " ELEMENT TYPE (1=SYMB)     ZC
)@@G@@@E@@@@             ,*: 18 BIT LOGICAL := O'0'     " HASH LINK     @E@@@@ZD
)@@G@@             ,PFS\VNAME(2): INTEGER WORD    " VERSION NAME  @E@@@@      ZE
)@@G@@       ,*(2): INTEGER WORD            " TYPE DEPENDANT@G@@@@            ZF
)@@G@@ ,PFS\ADDR: INTEGER WORD        " ELEMENT SECTOR ADDRESS    @E@@@@      ZG
)@@G@@       ,*: INTEGER WORD];             " TDATE$ WORD   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@ZH
)@@G@@DECLARE   NUMBER\OF\LIBRARIES: STATIC INTEGER WORD    @D@@@@            ZI
)@@G@@ IMPORTED ('LIBFILNUM'); " IN MACRO-FILE  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@DECLARE   LIZJ
)@@G@@BRARY\FILE\PACKET(9): STATIC MACHINE WORD POINTER     @D@@@@            ZK
)@@G@@ IMPORTED ('LIBFILPTR'); " IN MACRO-FILE  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE COZL
)@@G@@MPILE\EXTERNAL\MACRO(PKT: MACHINE POINTER WORD) @D@@@@           IMPORTEZM
)@@G@@D ('CMPEXT') RESULT MACHINE POINTER;@[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE INVOKE\DZN
)@@G@@EFINED\MACRO(MAC:MACHINE POINTER) IMPORTED('IDFMAC'); @[@@@@"     @G@@@@ZO
)@@G@@PROCEDURE INVOKE\SYSTEM\MACRO(KEY:INTEGER WORD) IMPORTED ('ISYMAC');    ZP
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE PFS(BUF:MACHINE POINTER) IMPORTED RESULT INTZQ
)@@G@@EGER WORD;  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS ROUTINE IS ZR
)@@G@@CALLED AFTER ALL SCANNING FOR MACROS AND  @F@@@@" DIRECTIVES HAVE FAILEDZS
)@@G@@ TO FIND A MATCH.  HERE WE SEARCH FOR     @ @@@@" EXTERNAL UNDEFINED MACZT
)@@G@@ROS.  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE SEARCH\FOR\UNDEFINED\MACRO EXPORTED ('ZU
)@@G@@SFUM')@[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@DECLARE   PACKET: MACHINE WORD POINTER; " TO INPZV
)@@G@@UT PACKET   @F@@@@DECLARE   MACRO\ENTRY: MACHINE WORD POINTER; " TO COMPZW
)@@G@@ILED MACRO  @D@@@@DECLARE   SECTOR: INTEGER WORD; " DRUM ADDRESS OF TEXTZX
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@          MACRO\FOUND := FALSE; " CLEAR FOUND FLAG    ZY
)@@G@@@F@@@@          CONVERT\TO\FIELDATA; " CONVERT MACRO NAME INTO FIELDATA ZZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@          PFS\ENAME(1) := FIELDATA\WORD(1); " SET ELEMENT NAME    AA
)@@G@@@F@@@@          PFS\ENAME(2) := FIELDATA\WORD(2); " INTO PFS PACKET     AB
)@@G@@@E@@@@          PFS\VNAME(1) := FIELDATA\BLANKS; " AND BLANK OUT  @E@@@@AC
)@@G@@          PFS\VNAME(2) := FIELDATA\BLANKS; " VERSION NAME   @F@@@@      AD
)@@G@@    SECTOR := SEARCH\LIBRARY\FILES; " SEARCH FOR ELEMENT    @D@@@@      AE
)@@G@@    IF SECTOR NE 0 THEN " ELEMENT WAS FOUND     @B@@@@           BEGIN "AF
)@@G@@ TO TRY TO COMPILE IT   @C@@@@             PACKET := INITIALIZE\EXTERNALAG
)@@G@@\READ @F@@@@                (PFS\FNAME(1),PFS\FNAME(2),SECTOR); " OPEN RAH
)@@G@@EAD   @G@@@@             ASSIGN\STATUS(PACKET) := FILE\FREE\CODE; " SAVEAI
)@@G@@ FREE CODE  @H@@@@             MACRO\ENTRY := COMPILE\EXTERNAL\MACRO(PACAJ
)@@G@@KET); " CALL COMPILER   @C@@@@             IF NOT ERROR\COMPILING\MACRO AK
)@@G@@THEN  @A@@@@              BEGIN " TO CALL IT    @D@@@@                MAAL
)@@G@@CRO\FOUND := TRUE; " TELL OUR CALLER@G@@@@                INVOKE\DEFINEDAM
)@@G@@\MACRO(MACRO\ENTRY); " AND INVOKE MACRO   @B@@@@              END; " OF AN
)@@G@@CALLING MACRO     @C@@@@           END; " OF TRYING TO COMPILE MACRO    AO
)@@G@@@A@@@@END; " OF SEARCH\FOR\UNDEFINED\MACRO@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@AP
)@@G@@" RELEASE INPUT FROM EXTERNAL PACKET.     @C@@@@" (CALLED BY POP\INPUT\PAQ
)@@G@@ACKET BY MACRO COMPILER)@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE RELEASE\EXTERNAL\MACAR
)@@G@@RO(PKT: MACHINE POINTER WORD) @ @@@@          EXPORTED ('RELEXT') @[@@@@AS
)@@G@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" CLOSE FILE INPUT.     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@      AT
)@@G@@    USER\IMAGE\BUFFER(PKT) := NULL\PTR; " ALREADY RELEASED (POP)  @B@@@@AU
)@@G@@          CLOSE\FILE(PKT); " CLOSE I/O    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" FREE FILE AV
)@@G@@ASSIGNED BY SEARCH\LIBRARY\FILES    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          GIVEN\NAAW
)@@G@@ME\ONE := FILE\NAME1(PKT);    @C@@@@          GIVEN\NAME\TWO := FILE\NAMAX
)@@G@@E2(PKT);    @C@@@@          FILE\FREE\CODE := ASSIGN\STATUS(PKT); @B@@@@AY
)@@G@@          FREE\FILE; " FREE\FILE HAS PKTS @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" RELEASE PAAZ
)@@G@@CKET CORE   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          RELEASE\CORE(PKT); " RELEASE IO BA
)@@G@@PACKET@ @@@@END; " RELEASE\EXTERNAL\MACRO @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@BB
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS USED TO SEARCH A SPECIFIC MACRO LIBRARY BC
)@@G@@FOR   @E@@@@" THE MACRO NAMED IN THE SCAN OUTPUT BUFFER, WHICH HAS BEEN BD
)@@G@@@F@@@@" CONVERTED TO FIELDATA.  THE ARGUMENT IS A 24 CHARACTER FIELDATA BE
)@@G@@@D@@@@" ENTITY WHICH CONSISTS OF QUALIFIER AND FILENAME.    @[@@@@"     BF
)@@G@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE SEARCH\LIBRARY\FILES RESULT INTEGER WORD    @[@@@@BEGIN BG
)@@G@@@B@@@@DECLARE   THIS\LIBRARY: INTEGER WORD;     @B@@@@DECLARE   SEARCH\SBH
)@@G@@TATUS: INTEGER WORD;    @A@@@@DECLARE   FIND\SECTOR: INTEGER WORD;@[@@@@BI
)@@G@@"     @ @@@@" INITIALIZE FIASG$ INTERFACE.@[@@@@"     @B@@@@          INBJ
)@@G@@TERNAL\NAME\GIVEN := FALSE;   @B@@@@          INTERNAL\NAME\FORCED := FABK
)@@G@@LSE;  @B@@@@          ASSIGN\OPTIONS\GIVEN := FALSE;  @A@@@@          DIBL
)@@G@@AGNOSE\ERRORS := FALSE; @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" LOOP OVER DEFINED LIBRARY FIBM
)@@G@@LES.  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          THIS\LIBRARY := 1;  @ @@@@          FIBN
)@@G@@ND\SECTOR := 0;   @B@@@@          WHILE (FIND\SECTOR EQ 0) AND    @E@@@@BO
)@@G@@                (THIS\LIBRARY LE NUMBER\OF\LIBRARIES) DO    @B@@@@      BP
)@@G@@     BEGIN " TO SEARCH THIS LIBRARY @G@@@@             ASSIGN\FILE\FOR\RBQ
)@@G@@EADING(LIBRARY\FILE\PACKET(THIS\LIBRARY));@D@@@@             IF CSF\BITSBR
)@@G@@ GE 0 THEN " FILE ASSIGNED SO @A@@@@              BEGIN " TO SEARCH FILEBS
)@@G@@@F@@@@                PFS\FNAME(1) := GIVEN\NAME\ONE; " MOVE FILE NAME  BT
)@@G@@@F@@@@                PFS\FNAME(2) := GIVEN\NAME\TWO; " TO PFS PACKET   BU
)@@G@@@C@@@@                PFS\BITS := 0; " CLEAR BITS     @G@@@@            BV
)@@G@@    SEARCH\STATUS := PFS(LOC(PFS\PKT)); " SEARCH FOR ELEMENT@E@@@@      BW
)@@G@@          IF SEARCH\STATUS EQ 0 THEN " ELEMENT FOUND  @F@@@@            BX
)@@G@@       FIND\SECTOR := PFS\ADDR; " SET FIND ADDRESS    @^@@@@            BY
)@@G@@    ELSE    @B@@@@                 BEGIN " ELEMENT NOT FOUND@D@@@@      BZ
)@@G@@             FIND\SECTOR := 0; " CLEAR FOUND    @F@@@@                  CA
)@@G@@ IF SEARCH\STATUS NE 1 THEN " STRANGE ERROR     @D@@@@                  CB
)@@G@@    DISPLAY('PFSERR',SEARCH\STATUS);@ @@@@                   FREE\FILE; CC
)@@G@@@C@@@@                 END; " OF ELEMENT NOT FOUND    @A@@@@            CD
)@@G@@  END; " OF FILE SEARCH @G@@@@             THIS\LIBRARY := THIS\LIBRARY+CE
)@@G@@1; " MOVE TO NEXT LIBRARY     @C@@@@           END; " OF SEARCH ON THIS CF
)@@G@@LIBRARY     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" SINCE DPS WILL NOT HANDLE FIELDATA SYMBOCG
)@@G@@LICS, THE LACK OF @B@@@@" AN ASCII BIT CAUSES THE SEARCH TO ABORT.@[@@@@CH
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@          IF (FIND\SECTOR NE 0) AND NOT PFS\ASC THEN  @B@@@@CI
)@@G@@           BEGIN " TO PRINT DIAGNOSTIC    @B@@@@             WARNING(W\NCJ
)@@G@@OT\ASCII\ELT);    @D@@@@             ODISPLAY('NOTASC',PFS\BITS); " TELLCK
)@@G@@ HIM  @C@@@@             FIND\SECTOR := 0; " ABORT FIND     @B@@@@      CL
)@@G@@       FREE\FILE; " AND RELEASE FILE@C@@@@           END; " OF HANDLING CM
)@@G@@FIELDATA ELEMENT  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          RETURN(FIND\SECTOR);@ @@@@CN
)@@G@@END; " SEARCH\LIBRARY\FILES   @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@CO
)@@G@@"     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS ROUTINE IS CALLED WHEN A DIRECTIVE HAS BECP
)@@G@@EN DETECTED BUT BEFORE  @H@@@@" THE SEARCH FOR INTRINSIC DIRECTIVES, THECQ
)@@G@@REBY ALLOWING MACROS TO OVERRIDE    @G@@@@" INTERNAL DIRECTIVES.   AT THCR
)@@G@@IS ENTRY POINT THE MACRO MUST BE ALREADY  @]@@@@" KNOWN.    @[@@@@"     CS
)@@G@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE SEARCH\FOR\DEFINED\MACRO EXPORTED ('SFDM')  @[@@@@BEGIN CT
)@@G@@@ @@@@DECLARE KEY:INTEGER WORD;     @A@@@@DECLARE MAC:MACHINE POINTER WOCU
)@@G@@RD;   @[@@@@      @A@@@@          MACRO\FOUND := FALSE;     @A@@@@      CV
)@@G@@    KEY := KEYWORD\SEARCH     @F@@@@             ( LOC(SYSTEM\MACROS(1))CW
)@@G@@ , NSYS\MACRO , DISABLE\AB ); @A@@@@"         DISPLAY('DEFKEY',KEY);    CX
)@@G@@@G@@@@          IF KEY LE NSYS\MACRO THEN " MACRO NAME FOUND IN SYSTEM LCY
)@@G@@IST   @ @@@@           BEGIN " TO DO IT   @A@@@@             MACRO\FOUNDCZ
)@@G@@ := TRUE;   @B@@@@             INVOKE\SYSTEM\MACRO(KEY);    @#@@@@      DA
)@@G@@     END    @#@@@@          ELSE    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@      DB
)@@G@@       KEY := (NAME\LEN+3)//4; " COMPUTE WORD LENGTH  @ @@@@            DC
)@@G@@ IF KEY GT 5 THEN @A@@@@              BEGIN " TO DIAGNOSE   @B@@@@      DD
)@@G@@          DISPLAY('MACNAM',KEY);    @ @@@@                KEY := 5;     DE
)@@G@@@#@@@@              END;@B@@@@             IF KEY GT 0 THEN " SEARCH    DF
)@@G@@@^@@@@              BEGIN     @C@@@@                MAC := SEARCH\FOR\NODG
)@@G@@DE(MACROS,  @E@@@@                   TYPSTR,KEY, LOC(MONOCASE\WORD(1)) )DH
)@@G@@;     @D@@@@                IF MAC NE NULL\PTR THEN " WE FOUND IT @^@@@@DI
)@@G@@                 BEGIN  @E@@@@                   MACRO\FOUND := TRUE; " DJ
)@@G@@SET FOUND FLAG    @E@@@@                   INVOKE\DEFINED\MACRO(MAC); " DK
)@@G@@GO AND DO IT@^@@@@                 END;   @A@@@@              END; " NULDL
)@@G@@L KEY TEST  @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@END; " SEARCH\FOR\DEFINED\MACRDM
)@@G@@O     @[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@@A@@@@END; " SEARCH\FOR\DEFINED\MACRDN
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS MODULE PROCESSES DO
)@@G@@THE  CONDITIONAL MACRO DEFINITION   @A@@@@"   .AT <KEYWORD>[,N,M] <MACRODP
)@@G@@-CALL>@[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@      DQ
)@@G@@    COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @A@@@@  COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTEDDR
)@@G@@);    @B@@@@          COPY ('CONTROL-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          CODS
)@@G@@PY ('CONVERT-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-PROC',IMPORDT
)@@G@@TED); @B@@@@          COPY ('CORE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          CODU
)@@G@@PY ('DIRECT-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED)DV
)@@G@@;     @D@@@@          COPY ('PRINT-DEF',IMPORTED); " **** TEMP    @B@@@@DW
)@@G@@          COPY ('PUSH-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SCAN-PRDX
)@@G@@OCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@DY
)@@G@@          COPY ('STAGING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-CODZ
)@@G@@MMON',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@EA
)@@G@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THESE NAMES ARE ACCEPTED AS ARGUMENTS TO THE AEB
)@@G@@T DIRECTIVE.@[@@@@"     @^@@@@DEFINE    MAXAT = 5;    @C@@@@DECLARE   ATEC
)@@G@@\NAMES: STATIC LOCATABLE MAPPED     @B@@@@          [*(MAXAT): 8 ASCII CED
)@@G@@HARACTERS :=@^@@@@             ['VPOS    '@^@@@@             ,'LINEND  'EE
)@@G@@@^@@@@             ,'PAGETOP '@^@@@@             ,'COLTOP  '@^@@@@      EF
)@@G@@       ,'BEGSCRIP'@#@@@@             ]    @^@@@@          ]; " AT\NAMES EG
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @ @@@@DECLARE   *: MAPPED BASED     @C@@@@           [BACK\LEH
)@@G@@INK: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER,  @D@@@@           FORWARD\LINK: 18 BIT MACHEI
)@@G@@INE POINTER];     @[@@@@      @A@@@@DECLARE   *: MAPPED BASED (TEMP\PTR)EJ
)@@G@@@A@@@@          [*: WORD INTEGER, " LINKS @B@@@@           START\ATVPOS:EK
)@@G@@ WORD INTEGER,    @C@@@@          VPOS\CARD: WORD MACHINE POINTER];     EL
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@DEFINE    ATVPOS\CORE = 4; " NEED 4 WORDS PER ENTRY   EM
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @F@@@@PROCEDURE HEIGHT\NUMBER(NUM: WORD INTEGER) IMPORTED ('EN
)@@G@@HEIGHTNUM') @A@@@@           RESULT WORD INTEGER;     @[@@@@      @F@@@@EO
)@@G@@PROCEDURE SEARCH\LISTS(ITEM: WORD INTEGER, HEAD: WORD MACHINE     @C@@@@EP
)@@G@@           POINTER) IMPORTED ('SEARCHEQUS');    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDEQ
)@@G@@URE PROCESS\AT\DIRECTIVE EXPORTED ('PROATDIR')  @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@      ER
)@@G@@    SCAN(CTRM+COMA+ALLOW\NAM);@H@@@@          AT\INDEX := KEYWORD\SEARCHES
)@@G@@( LOC(AT\NAMES) , MAXAT , ENABLE\AB );    @ @@@@          GOTO AT\SWITCHET
)@@G@@;     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@SWITCH    AT\SWITCH = CASE AT\INDEX OF    @#@@@@EU
)@@G@@           [ATVPOS@#@@@@           ,ATEOL @#@@@@           ,ATTOP @#@@@@EV
)@@G@@           ,ATTOC @#@@@@           ,ATSOI @^@@@@           ,*:ATERROR]; EW
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @A@@@@"   .AT VPOS,N[,M] <MACRO-CALL>     @[@@@@"     @]@@@@EX
)@@G@@ATVPOS:     @B@@@@          SCRATCH(1) := HEIGHT\NUMBER(0); @D@@@@      EY
)@@G@@    SEARCH\LISTS(SCRATCH(1),LOC(ATVPOS\HEAD));  @ @@@@          IF CSDLEEZ
)@@G@@N NE 0 THEN @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             TEMP\PTR := ALLOCFA
)@@G@@ATE\CORE (ATVPOS\CORE); @B@@@@             START\ATVPOS := SCRATCH(1);  FB
)@@G@@@D@@@@             VPOS\CARD := MOVE\NAME\TO\CARD; " GET IT @B@@@@      FC
)@@G@@       CHAIN\BUFFER\AFTER(TEMP\PTR);@#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@      FD
)@@G@@    IF FOUND\EQUATE THEN@#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             UNCHAFE
)@@G@@IN\BUFFER(FOUND\PTR);   @E@@@@             TEMP\PTR := FOUND\PTR; " POINFF
)@@G@@T TO VPOS BUFFER  @E@@@@             RELEASE\CORE(VPOS\CARD); " RELEASE FG
)@@G@@THE CARD    @B@@@@             RELEASE\CORE(FOUND\PTR);     @#@@@@      FH
)@@G@@     END;   @E@@@@          SEARCH\LISTS(VERTICAL\POSITION,LOC(ATVPOS\HEFI
)@@G@@AD)); @ @@@@          IF FOUND\EQUATE THEN@A@@@@             END\OF\AREAFJ
)@@G@@ := TRUE;   @C@@@@          NEXT\VPOS := FORWARD\LINK(INSERT\PTR);@B@@@@FK
)@@G@@"  DUMP\LINKED\CHAIN(LOC(ATVPOS\HEAD));   @#@@@@          RETURN; @[@@@@FL
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" DEFINE A EQUATE TO BE CALLED AT THE END OF EVERY OUTPUT   FM
)@@G@@@]@@@@" LINE.     @ @@@@"   .AT LINEND <MACRO-CALL>   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@FN
)@@G@@ATEOL:@D@@@@          RELEASE\AT\CARD(EOL\EQUATE); " GET RID OF IT@D@@@@FO
)@@G@@          AT\PTRS(EOL\EQUATE) := MOVE\NAME\TO\CARD;   @#@@@@          REFP
)@@G@@TURN; @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" EQUATE TO BE DONE AT THE TOP OF A PAGE. @ @@@@FQ
)@@G@@"   .AT PAGETOP <MACRO-CALL>  @[@@@@"     @[@@@@ATTOP:@D@@@@          REFR
)@@G@@LEASE\AT\CARD(TOP\EQUATE); " GET RID OF IT@D@@@@          AT\PTRS(TOP\EQFS
)@@G@@UATE) := MOVE\NAME\TO\CARD;   @#@@@@          RETURN; @[@@@@"     @ @@@@FT
)@@G@@" EQUATE FOR TOP OF COLUMN.   @ @@@@"   .AT COLTOP <MACRO-CALL>   @[@@@@FU
)@@G@@"     @[@@@@ATTOC:@D@@@@          RELEASE\AT\CARD(COL\EQUATE); " GET RIDFV
)@@G@@ OF IT@D@@@@          AT\PTRS(COL\EQUATE) := MOVE\NAME\TO\CARD;   @#@@@@FW
)@@G@@          RETURN; @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" EQUATE PERFORMED AT BEGINING OF SCFX
)@@G@@RIPT LINE.  @ @@@@"   .AT BEGSCRIPT <MACRO-CALL>@[@@@@"     @[@@@@ATSOI:FY
)@@G@@@D@@@@          RELEASE\AT\CARD(SOI\EQUATE); " GET RID OF IT@D@@@@      FZ
)@@G@@    AT\PTRS(SOI\EQUATE) := MOVE\NAME\TO\CARD;   @#@@@@          RETURN; GA
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @]@@@@ATERROR:    @A@@@@          CONTROL\ERROR := ERROR15; GB
)@@G@@@#@@@@          RETURN; @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" SCAN THE NAME GIGC
)@@G@@VEN AND PUT IT INTO A CARD BUFFER   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE MOVE\NAMGD
)@@G@@E\TO\CARD RESULT MACHINE WORD POINTER     @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          SCGE
)@@G@@AN(CTRM+ALLOW\STR+EVAL);@F@@@@          RETURN(MOVE\SCANNED\TO\CARD); " GF
)@@G@@RETURN POINTER OF CARD  @B@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE MOVE\NAME\TO\CARD     GG
)@@G@@@F@@@@PROCEDURE RELEASE\AT\CARD(AT: WORD INTEGER) EXPORTED ('RELATCARD')GH
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@DECLARE   ICB\SAVE: MACHINE WORD POINTER; @[@@@@"     GI
)@@G@@@B@@@@          IF AT\PTRS(AT) NE NULL\PTR THEN @#@@@@           BEGIN  GJ
)@@G@@@C@@@@             ICB\SAVE := ICB\PTR; " SAVE POINTER@E@@@@            GK
)@@G@@ ICB\PTR := AT\PTRS(AT); " POINT TO AT CARD     @B@@@@             CARD\GL
)@@G@@REFS := CARD\REFS - 1;  @C@@@@             IF CARD\REFS LE 0 THEN " RELEGM
)@@G@@ASE IT@B@@@@                RELEASE\CORE(ICB\PTR);    @C@@@@            GN
)@@G@@ ICB\PTR := ICB\SAVE; " RESTORE ICB @E@@@@             AT\PTRS(AT) := NUGO
)@@G@@LL\PTR; " CLEAR OLD ENTRY     @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@GP
)@@G@@TERM; ___@@@: MACHINE WORD POINTER; @[@@@@"     @B@@@@          IF AT\PTGQ
)@@G@@RS(AT) NE NULL\PTR THEN @#@@@@           BEGIN  *[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@MODULEGR
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" THIS MODULE PROCESS THE '.CONTROL' DIRECTIVE  @[@@@@GS
)@@G@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@C@@@@ COPY('DEBUG-PROCSGT
)@@G@@',IMPORTED ); " ****** DEBUG  @B@@@@          COPY ('ACTION-DEF',IMPORTEGU
)@@G@@D);   @B@@@@          COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COGV
)@@G@@PY ('CONTROL-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-PROC',IMPORGW
)@@G@@TED); @B@@@@          COPY ('CORE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COGX
)@@G@@PY ('DIRECT-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SCAN-PROCS',IMPORTEGY
)@@G@@D);   @B@@@@          COPY ('STAGING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COGZ
)@@G@@PY ('SYMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-PROCS',IMPORHA
)@@G@@TED); @B@@@@          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECHB
)@@G@@T);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@DECLARE   SPACE\REMAINING: STATIC WORD INTEGER IHC
)@@G@@MPORTED ('SPR')   @E@@@@          ,CHARS\THIS\LINE: STATIC 18 BIT UNSIGNHD
)@@G@@ED INTEGER  @C@@@@                            IMPORTED ('CTL')    @E@@@@HE
)@@G@@          ,CHARS\NEXT\LINE: STATIC 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER  @C@@@@      HF
)@@G@@                      IMPORTED ('CNL');   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE DEHG
)@@G@@FINE\EQUATE(EQU\TYPE: WORD INTEGER) @A@@@@           IMPORTED ('DEFINEQUHH
)@@G@@ATE');@[@@@@"     @A@@@@" DEFINE INDICES FOR CONTROL NAMES. @[@@@@"     HI
)@@G@@@^@@@@DEFINE    CNI\BKSP = 1, @^@@@@          CNI\BREAK = 2,@ @@@@      HJ
)@@G@@    CNI\CENTER = 3,     @^@@@@          CNI\DEQU = 4, @^@@@@          CNHK

)@@G@@@ @@@@          CNI\LNEXT = 10,     @^@@@@          CNI\NTB = 11, @^@@@@HN

)@@G@@I\WIDTH = 16,     @ @@@@          CNI\TRY\HYPHEN = 17,@ @@@@          CNHQ
)@@G@@I\CHAR\SPACE = 18,@ @@@@          CNI\WORD\SPACE = 19,@ @@@@          CNHR
)@@G@@I\SENT\SPACE = 20,@^@@@@          CNI\DSUP = 21,@^@@@@          CNI\DINFHS
)@@G@@ = 22,@^@@@@          CNI\DSIS = 23,@^@@@@          CNI\DSIE = 24,@E@@@@HT
)@@G@@          CNI\MAX = 24; " MAX CONTROL NAME INDEX FOR SIZING @[@@@@"     HU
)@@G@@@F@@@@" THESE NAMES ARE ACCEPTED AS ARGUMENTS TO THE CONTROL DIRECTIVE. HV
)@@G@@@C@@@@" MUST CORRESPOND TO INDICES DEFINED ABOVE.     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@HW
)@@G@@DECLARE   CONTROL\NAMES: STATIC LOCATABLE MAPPED@C@@@@          [*(CNI\MHX
)@@G@@AX): 8 ASCII CHARACTERS :=    @^@@@@             ['BKSP    '@^@@@@      HY
)@@G@@       ,'BREAK   '@^@@@@             ,'CENTER  '@^@@@@             ,'DEQHZ

)@@G@@             ,'WORDSPAC'@^@@@@             ,'SENTSPAC'@^@@@@            IG
