)@@G@@             LEADING\FOR*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@AJ
)@@G@@" ENTRY POINT FOR QUALTERM FINAL DEVICE HANDLER.@[@@@@"     @A@@@@      AK
)@@G@@    COPY ('FD-DEF',IMPORTED); @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS MODULE CONTAINS TAL
)@@G@@HE SINGLE ENTRY POINT FOR THIS FINAL DEVICE     @F@@@@" HANDLER.  IT CALAM

)@@G@@T');  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@DECLARE   FD\FUNCTION: WORD INTEGER STATIC IMPORBI
)@@G@@TED ('FUNC');     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PARSE\HANDLER\FUNCTION EXPBJ
)@@G@@ORTED ('QUALTFDFUNC')   @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          CASEENTRY FD\FUNCTIOBK
)@@G@@N     @ @@@@          CASE FD\OUTPUT:     @A@@@@             OUTPUT\FOR\BL
)@@G@@HANDLER;    @ @@@@          CASE FD\INITIALIZE: @A@@@@             INITIBM

)@@G@@ LEADING\FOR\HANDLER;   @ @@@@          CASE FD\PAGEUP:     @B@@@@      BO
)@@G@@       TOP\OF\FORM\FOR\HANDLER;     @^@@@@          CASE FD\SOT:  @B@@@@BP
)@@G@@             START\OF\TAKE\FOR\HANDLER;   @^@@@@          CASE FD\EOT:  BQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@             END\OF\TAKE\FOR\HANDLER;     @A@@@@          CASE FD\BR
)@@G@@EXTERNAL\FONT:    @B@@@@             EXTERNAL\FONT\FOR\HANDLER;   @A@@@@BS

)@@G@@ INTERNAL\SIZE\FOR\HANDLER;   @B@@@@          CASE FD\EXTERNAL\HEIGHT\CHBV
)@@G@@ANGE: @B@@@@             EXTERNAL\HEIGHT\FOR\HANDLER; @B@@@@          CABW
)@@G@@SE FD\EXTERNAL\WIDTH\CHANGE:  @B@@@@             EXTERNAL\WIDTH\FOR\HANDBX
)@@G@@LER;  @^@@@@          CASE FD\DSIB: @ @@@@             DSIB\FOR\HANDLER;BY
)@@G@@@^@@@@          CASE FD\DSIS: @ @@@@             DSIS\FOR\HANDLER;@^@@@@BZ
)@@G@@          CASE FD\DSIE: @ @@@@             DSIE\FOR\HANDLER;@ @@@@      CA
)@@G@@    CASE FD\END\OF\LINE:@B@@@@             END\OF\LINE\FOR\HANDLER;     CB

)@@G@@E   *(128): MAPPED STATIC IMPORTED ('PHOWID')   @D@@@@          [STYLE\ACW

)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@DECLARE   *: MAPPED STATIC    @B@@@@          [EX\FONTDH
)@@G@@: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER@C@@@@           ,IN\FONT: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGEDI

)@@G@@@[@@@@      @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @D@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\PHOTON EXDL
)@@G@@PORTED ('PH7445INIT')   @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" INITIALIZE ALLOWDM
)@@G@@ED POINT SIZES THIS IS REQUIRED BECAUSE OF@D@@@@" A DEFICIENCY IN ALLOWEDN
)@@G@@D INITIALAZATIONS IN PLUS     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@          PH\ALLOWED\POIDO
)@@G@@NT\SIZES(1) := POINT\DISTANCE * 6.75;     @F@@@@          PH\ALLOWED\POIDP
)@@G@@NT\SIZES(2) := POINT\DISTANCE * 8.65;     @F@@@@          PH\ALLOWED\POIDQ
)@@G@@NT\SIZES(3) := POINT\DISTANCE * 10.5;     @F@@@@          PH\ALLOWED\POIDR
)@@G@@NT\SIZES(4) := POINT\DISTANCE * 12.8;     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" INITIALIZEDS
)@@G@@ FONT I.E. CHARACTER SIZES    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          FOR I := 129 TDT
)@@G@@O 256 DO    @A@@@@             CHAR\WIDTH(I) := 0;    @G@@@@          UNDU
)@@G@@IT\DEVICE\WIDTH := 1; " SMALLEST WIDTH IN JUSTIFICATION     @B@@@@      DV
)@@G@@    IN\FONT := 1; " SET FONT ONE    @D@@@@          EX\FONT := IN\FONT; DW
)@@G@@" OUR EXTERNAL FONT TOO @E@@@@          IN\LENS := 3; " USE 10.5 POINTSIDX
)@@G@@ZE AS DEFAULT     @ @@@@          EX\LENS := IN\LENS; @D@@@@          CHDY
)@@G@@ANGE\SIZE\PARAMETERS(IN\LENS); " PS 10.5  @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @[@@@@DZ
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@" SET STANDARD MARGINS  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@          TOP\MARGEA
)@@G@@IN := INCH\DISTANCE;    @B@@@@          BOTTOM\MARGIN := INCH\DISTANCE; EB
)@@G@@@C@@@@          PAGE\HEIGHT := INCH\DISTANCE * 11;    @C@@@@          PAEC
)@@G@@GE\WIDTH := INCH\DISTANCE * 8.5;    @B@@@@          LEFT\MARGIN := INCH\ED
)@@G@@DISTANCE;   @B@@@@          RIGHT\MARGIN := INCH\DISTANCE;  @A@@@@      EE
)@@G@@    SET\ALL\AREA\LINE\WIDTHS; @F@@@@          PAGE\OFFSET := 0; " VIRTUAEF
)@@G@@L AND PHYSICAL PAGE THE SAME  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" SET STANDARD LEADING FEG
)@@G@@OR PHOTON   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@          UNIT\LEADING := POINT\DISTANCE//EH
)@@G@@2; " LEADING IS IN 1/2 POINTS @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" DEFINE SECTION LEADINGEI
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@          SECTION\LEADING\BEFORE(1) := 0; @E@@@@      EJ
)@@G@@    SECTION\LEADING\AFTER(1) := SKIP\DISTANCE * 3;    @E@@@@          SEEK
)@@G@@CTION\LEADING\BEFORE(2) := SKIP\DISTANCE * 2;   @D@@@@          SECTION\EL
)@@G@@LEADING\AFTER(2) := SKIP\DISTANCE;  @D@@@@          SECTION\LEADING\BEFOEM
)@@G@@RE(3) := SKIP\DISTANCE; @D@@@@          SECTION\LEADING\AFTER(3) := SKIPEN
)@@G@@\DISTANCE;  @E@@@@          DEVICE\BACKSPACES := FALSE; " WE CAN'T BACKSEO
)@@G@@PACE  @F@@@@          DEVICE\LETTER\SPACES := FALSE; " CANNOT LETTERSPACEP
)@@G@@E     @D@@@@          DEVICE\JUSTIFIES := FALSE; " WE MUST DO IT  @G@@@@EQ
)@@G@@          DEVICE\HYPHEN\CHAR := 127; " SPECIAL CHARACTER (SHORT DASH)   ER
)@@G@@@C@@@@          MUTILATE := FALSE; " DO NOT MUTILATE  @[@@@@END;  @#@@@@ES
)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @E@@@@PROCEDURE PHOTON\START\OF\TAKE EXPORTED ('PH7445ET
)@@G@@STRTAK')    @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" INITIALIZE STYLE AND PRIMARYEU
)@@G@@ LEADING    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          IF OUTPUT\MEDIA EQ MEDIA\PUNCH TEV
)@@G@@HEN   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @ @@@@             INITIALIZE\PUNCH;@#@@@@EW
)@@G@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PHEX
)@@G@@OTON\END\OF\TAKE EXPORTED ('PH7445ENDTAK')@[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          FOEY
)@@G@@R I := 1 TO 40 DO @B@@@@             PACK\PHOTON\CHARACTER(PH\LF);@E@@@@EZ
)@@G@@          PACK\PHOTON\CHARACTER(PH\STOP); " STOP CHARACTER  @ @@@@      FA
)@@G@@    FOR I := 1 TO 200 DO@F@@@@             PACK\PHOTON\CHARACTER(PH\FEEDFB
)@@G@@); " RUN OUT LEADER     @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PHOTON\PFC
)@@G@@AGEUP EXPORTED ('PH7445TOPFRM')     @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          SKIP := FD
)@@G@@0; " KILL ANY IMPENDING SKIP  @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO 20 DO @H@@@@FE
)@@G@@             PACK\PHOTON\CHARACTER(PH\FEED); " RUN OUT LEADER AT TOP OF FF
)@@G@@PAGE  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" AT TOP OF EACH PAGE SET FONT AND LENS SIZE    FG
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@          NEW\FONT := EX\FONT; " GET CURRENT FONT     FH
)@@G@@@E@@@@          CHANGE\PHOTON\EXTERNAL\FONT; " OUTPUT FONT CODE   @F@@@@FI
)@@G@@          NEW\CHAR\WIDTH := EX\LENS; " CAUSE LENS TO BE RESET TOO @A@@@@FJ
)@@G@@          CHANGE\PHOTON\POINT\SIZE; @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THISFK
)@@G@@ PROCEDURE OUTPUTS THE HARDWARE CODE FOR A FONT CHANGE@D@@@@" THE FONT NFL
)@@G@@UMBER (1 TO 4) MUST BE PASSED IN NEW\FONT.@[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE CHFM
)@@G@@ANGE\PHOTON\EXTERNAL\FONT EXPORTED ('PH7445EXFONT')   @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@FN
)@@G@@          EX\FONT := NEW\FONT; " SET NEW EXTERNAL FONT@D@@@@          PAFO
)@@G@@CK\PHOTON\CHARACTER(PH\STYLE\A+EX\FONT-1);@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@FP
)@@G@@" THIS PROCEDURE OUTPUTS THE HARDWARE POINT SIZE (LENS) CHANGES   @E@@@@FQ
)@@G@@" IT EXPECTS THE LENS NUMBER (1 TO 4) IN NEW\CHAR\WIDTH     @[@@@@"     FR
)@@G@@@F@@@@PROCEDURE CHANGE\PHOTON\POINT\SIZE EXPORTED ('PH7445EXWIDT');     FS
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@          EX\LENS := NEW\CHAR\WIDTH; " SET NEW LENS COFT
)@@G@@DE    @I@@@@          PACK\PHOTON\CHARACTER(PH\LENS\A+EX\LENS-1); " LENSFU
)@@G@@ CODES ARE SEQUENTIAL   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" WIDTH\FACTOR IS USED TO CONVFV
)@@G@@ERT SPACING CODES TO APPROPRIATE PHOTON   @D@@@@          WIDTH\FACTOR :FW
)@@G@@= PH\ALLOWED\POINT\SIZES(     @#@@@@" OUTPUT CODES    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@FX
)@@G@@             NEW\CHAR\WIDTH) // 18; " INTERNAL CONVERSION FACTOR  @[@@@@FY
)@@G@@END;  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" PROCEDURE TO VERIFY A REQUESTED PHOTON FONT CHFZ
)@@G@@ANGE  @E@@@@" THE INTERNAL TABLES ARE MODIFIED TO REFLECT THE WIDTHS OF GA
)@@G@@@E@@@@" THE NEW FONT, AND A FUNCTION IS PUT INTO THE CURRENT WORD @E@@@@GB
)@@G@@" SO THAT WHEN THE WORD IS ACTUALLY OUTPUT THIS HANDLER     @E@@@@" WILLGC
)@@G@@ BE CALLED TO PRODUCE THE HARDWARE CODES NECESSARY TO @F@@@@" EFFECT THEGD
)@@G@@ FONT CHANGE IN THE DEVICE.   NOTE THERE IS A LAG     @F@@@@" BETWEEN THGE
)@@G@@E INTERNAL DPS FONT CHANGE AND THE ACTUAL HARDWARE    @F@@@@" CHANGE IN GF
)@@G@@THE DEVICE.  THIS IS BECAUSE OUTPUT TO THE DEVICE     @F@@@@" IS NOT DONGG
)@@G@@E UNTIL A COMPLETE LINE HAS BEEN SET, OR IN SOME CASES@F@@@@" (MULTICOLUGH
)@@G@@MNS) OUTPUT TO THE DEVICE IS NOT DONE UNTIL A COMPLETE@ @@@@" PAGE HAS BGI
)@@G@@EEN FORMATTED.    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE CHECK\PHOTON\FONT\CHANGE EGJ
)@@G@@XPORTED ('PH7445INFONT')@[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          SCAN(EVAL+CTRM+ALLOWGK
)@@G@@\INT);@B@@@@          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 AND   @D@@@@            GL
)@@G@@ (DNUM(1) GE 1 AND DNUM(1) LE 4) THEN     @^@@@@           BEGIN " OK   GM
)@@G@@@G@@@@             CHANGE\CHARACTER\WIDTH\TABLES(DNUM(1)); " SET NEW FONGN
)@@G@@T     @E@@@@             PUT\FUNCTION\INTO\WORD(FUNC\FONT,DNUM(1));     GO
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @^@@@@          ELSE " ERROR  @#@@@@           BGP
)@@G@@EGIN  @B@@@@             WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\FONT);     @#@@@@           EGQ
)@@G@@ND;   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" PROCEDURE TO CHANGE THE PHOTON INCGR
)@@G@@ORE CHARACTER WIDTH TABLES    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE CHANGE\CHARACTGS
)@@G@@ER\WIDTH\TABLES(NEW\FONT: WORD INTEGER)   @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          FOGT
)@@G@@NT := NEW\FONT; " SET NEW FONT@E@@@@          CASEENTRY NEW\FONT " SET NGU
)@@G@@EW WIDTHS FOR CHARACTERS@ @@@@          CASE 1: " FONT 1    @ @@@@      GV
)@@G@@    FOR I := 1 TO 128 DO@I@@@@             CHAR\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDGW
)@@G@@TH(STYLE\A\WIDTH(I)); " SET NEW WIDTHS    @ @@@@          CASE 2: " FONTGX
)@@G@@ 2    @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO 128 DO@I@@@@             CHAR\WIDTH(GY
)@@G@@I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(STYLE\B\WIDTH(I)); " SET NEW WIDTHS    @ @@@@      GZ
)@@G@@    CASE 3: " FONT 3    @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO 128 DO@I@@@@      HA
)@@G@@       CHAR\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(STYLE\C\WIDTH(I)); " SET NEW WIDTHB
)@@G@@HS    @ @@@@          CASE 4: " FONT 4    @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO HC
)@@G@@128 DO@I@@@@             CHAR\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(STYLE\D\WIDTH(IHD
)@@G@@)); " SET NEW WIDTHS    @ @@@@          CASE *: " ERROR     @^@@@@      HE
)@@G@@       ERROR;     @#@@@@          ENDCASE;@E@@@@          SPACEBAND\WIDTHF
)@@G@@H := CHAR\WIDTH(ASCII\LOWER\A+1);   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THISHG
)@@G@@ PROCEDURE MAKES THE POINT SIZE PARAMETER CHANGES     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@HH
)@@G@@" THE INDEX TO THE POINT SIZE CHANGE IS PASSED AS AN ARGUMENT     @[@@@@HI
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE CHANGE\SIZE\PARAMETERS(NEW\SIZE\INDEX: WORD INTEGEHJ
)@@G@@R)    @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@          IN\LENS := NEW\SIZE\INDEX; " SAVE INTEHK
)@@G@@RNAL SIZE INDEX   @H@@@@          TYPESIZE\WIDTH := PH\ALLOWED\POINT\SIZHL
)@@G@@ES(IN\LENS); " NEW POINT SIZE @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" CHANGE LEADING TO TYPEHM
)@@G@@SIZE\WIDTH + 2 POINTS   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          LEADING := TYPESIZE\HN
)@@G@@WIDTH + 2 * POINT\DISTANCE;   @C@@@@          TYPESIZE\HEIGHT := TYPESIZHO
)@@G@@E\WIDTH;    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THE UNITS FOR CHARACTER WIDTHS FOR THE 7HP
)@@G@@445 ARE KEPT@D@@@@" IN PHOTON UNITS.  THESE WIDTHS DO NOT CHANGE WHEN   HQ
)@@G@@@D@@@@" POINT SIZE IS CHANGED.  THE INTERNAL UNITS DO CHANGE@E@@@@" IU\DHR
)@@G@@U\FACTOR TAKES FROM CHARACTER WIDTHS TO INTERNAL UNITS@D@@@@" IT MUST BEHS
)@@G@@ CHANGED WHEN THE POINT SIZE IS CHANGED   @C@@@@" THE DEVICE WIDTHS ARE HT
)@@G@@KEPT IN UNITS WHERE     @E@@@@" ONE UNIT IS ONE EIGHTEENTH OF THE CHARACHU
)@@G@@TER WIDTH DIVIDED @B@@@@" BY THE CHARACTER HEIGTH (POINT SIZE)    @C@@@@HV
)@@G@@"   I.E. UNITS := (1/18)*(WIDTH/POINT-SIZE)     @B@@@@" A SQUARE CHARACTHW
)@@G@@ER IS 18 UNITS WIDE     @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          IU\DU\FAHX
)@@G@@CTOR := TYPESIZE\WIDTH // 18; @F@@@@          UNIT\INTERNAL\WIDTH := IU\HY
)@@G@@DU\FACTOR * UNIT\DEVICE\WIDTH;@H@@@@          CHANGE\CHARACTER\WIDTH\TABHZ
)@@G@@LES(IN\FONT); " CHANGE INTERNAL TABLES    @A@@@@          SKIP\DISTANCE IA
)@@G@@:= LEADING; @C@@@@          COLUMN\DISTANCE := TYPESIZE\WIDTH;    @[@@@@IB
)@@G@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" HERE WE READ THE CARD GIVEN ON A TYPESIZE CHANIC
)@@G@@GE AND CHECK@F@@@@" TO INSURE THAT IT IS A VALID LENS SIZE. IF SO, CHANGID
)@@G@@E INTERNAL  @C@@@@" TABLES AND ALSO PUT A FUNCTION INTO THE WORD. @[@@@@IE
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE CHECK\PHOTON\SIZE\CHANGE EXPORTED ('PH7445INSIZE')IF
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @G@@@@DECLARE   NEW\SIZE\INDEX: WORD INTEGER; " INDEX TO LISIG
)@@G@@T OF LEGAL SIZES  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          SCAN(CTRM+ALLOW\INT+ALLOW\IH
)@@G@@DST+EVAL);  @ @@@@          IF CSDLEN NE 1 THEN @A@@@@             WARNIII
)@@G@@NG(W\DIR\SYNTAX); @#@@@@          ELSE    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@IJ
)@@G@@             IF CSDTYP EQ TYPINT THEN     @G@@@@                IF DNUM(IK
)@@G@@1) GT PH\NUM\POINT\SIZES OR DNUM(1) LE 0 THEN   @C@@@@                  IL
)@@G@@ WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\POINT);    @^@@@@                ELSE    @C@@@@      IM
)@@G@@           BEGIN " SIZE INDEX SPECIFIED   @C@@@@                   NEW\SIN
)@@G@@IZE\INDEX := DNUM(1);   @^@@@@                END;    @#@@@@            IO
)@@G@@ ELSE @^@@@@              BEGIN     @D@@@@                NEW\SIZE\INDEXIP
)@@G@@ := PH\NUM\POINT\SIZES; @E@@@@                WHILE NEW\SIZE\INDEX GT 0 IQ
)@@G@@AND DNUM(1) NE    @F@@@@                    PH\ALLOWED\POINT\SIZES(NEW\SIR
)@@G@@IZE\INDEX) DO     @E@@@@                   NEW\SIZE\INDEX := NEW\SIZE\INIS
)@@G@@DEX - 1;    @C@@@@                IF NEW\SIZE\INDEX LE 0 THEN     @C@@@@IT
)@@G@@                   WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\POINT);    @#@@@@              END;IU
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN  IV
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@             PUT\FUNCTION\INTO\WORD(FUNC\WIW
)@@G@@IDTH, NEW\SIZE\INDEX);  @H@@@@             CHANGE\SIZE\PARAMETERS(NEW\SIIX
)@@G@@ZE\INDEX); " CHANGE INTERNAL TABLES @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  IY
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@@H@@@@             CHANGE\SIZE\PARAMETERS(IZ
)@@G@@NEW\SIZE\INDEX); " CHANGE INTERNAL TABLES @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@JA
)@@G@@END;  @[@#@]"     @B@#@]" UNUSED ENTRY POINTS FO*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULEJB
)@@G@@;     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('DJC

)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE SET\ALL\AREA\LINE\WIDTHS IMPORTED ('SETALLINJO

)@@G@@C     @A@@@@             IMPORTED ('LEDDEV');   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@DECLARJQ
)@@G@@E   SKIP: WORD INTEGER STATIC IMPORTED;   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@"         LOJR
)@@G@@CAL STORAGE AS NEEDED BY TYPESETTER FINAL DEVICE@[@@@@"     @B@@@@" DEFIJS
)@@G@@NE CODES INSENSITIVE OR SHIFTING    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@DEFINE    TS\TF   JT
)@@G@@= 0,      " PAPER TAPE FEED   @E@@@@          TS\RET  = O'20',  " RETURNJU
)@@G@@ (END-OF-LINE CODE)     @E@@@@          TS\SB   = O'10',  " SPACEBAND (IJV
)@@G@@NTER-WORD SPACE)  @B@@@@          TS\ELEV = O'04',  " ELEVATE     @D@@@@JW
)@@G@@          TS\UC   = O'66',  " UPPER CASE OR SHIFT     @D@@@@          TSJX
)@@G@@\LC   = O'76',  " LOWER CASE OR UNSHIFT   @B@@@@          TS\THIN = O'01JY
)@@G@@',  " THIN SPACE  @B@@@@          TS\SS   = O'11',  " SUPERSHIFT  @E@@@@JZ
)@@G@@          TS\LM   = O'05',  " LOWER MAGAZINE OR PAPER FEED  @F@@@@      KA
)@@G@@    TS\VRUL = O'45',  " VERTICAL RULE OR EM PRECEDENT CODE  @B@@@@      KB
)@@G@@    TS\EN   = O'35',  " EN SPACE    @E@@@@          TS\IS   = O'75',  " KC
)@@G@@INSERT SPACE OR QUAD CENTER   @B@@@@          TS\UR   = O'63',  " UPPER KD
)@@G@@RAIL  @B@@@@          TS\EM   = O'13',  " EM SPACE    @B@@@@          TSKE
)@@G@@\QL   = O'33',  " QUAD LEFT   @B@@@@          TS\STOP = O'27',  " STOP OKF
)@@G@@R BELL@B@@@@          TS\LR   = O'67',  " LOWER RAIL  @E@@@@          TSKG
)@@G@@\UM   = O'37',  " UPPER MAGAZINE OR QUAD RIGHT  @C@@@@          TS\RO   KH
)@@G@@= O'77';  " RUBOUT OR DELETE  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" DEFINE CODES SENSITIVEKI
)@@G@@ TO SHIFTING@[@@@@"     @ @@@@DEFINE    TS\A = O'06',  " A  @ @@@@      KJ
)@@G@@    TS\B = O'62',  " B  @ @@@@          TS\C = O'34',  " C  @ @@@@      KK
)@@G@@    TS\D = O'22',  " D  @ @@@@          TS\E = O'02',  " E  @ @@@@      KL
)@@G@@    TS\F = O'32',  " F  @ @@@@          TS\G = O'64',  " G  @ @@@@      KM
)@@G@@    TS\H = O'50',  " H  @ @@@@          TS\I = O'14',  " I  @ @@@@      KN
)@@G@@    TS\J = O'26',  " J  @ @@@@          TS\K = O'36',  " K  @ @@@@      KO
)@@G@@    TS\L = O'44',  " L  @ @@@@          TS\M = O'70',  " M  @ @@@@      KP
)@@G@@    TS\N = O'30',  " N  @ @@@@          TS\O = O'60',  " O  @ @@@@      KQ
)@@G@@    TS\P = O'54',  " P  @ @@@@          TS\Q = O'56',  " Q  @ @@@@      KR
)@@G@@    TS\R = O'24',  " R  @ @@@@          TS\S = O'12',  " S  @ @@@@      KS
)@@G@@    TS\T = O'40',  " T  @ @@@@          TS\U = O'16',  " U  @ @@@@      KT
)@@G@@    TS\V = O'74',  " V  @ @@@@          TS\W = O'46',  " W  @ @@@@      KU
)@@G@@    TS\X = O'72',  " X  @ @@@@          TS\Y = O'52',  " Y  @ @@@@      KV
)@@G@@    TS\Z = O'42',  " Z  @A@@@@          TS\QUOTE  = O'21',  " '   @B@@@@KW
)@@G@@          TS\EMLD   = O'51',  " EM LEADER @A@@@@          TS\COMMA  = O'KX
)@@G@@31',  " ,   @A@@@@          TS\PERIOD = O'71',  " .   @B@@@@          TSKY
)@@G@@\ENLD   = O'57';  " EN LEADER @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" DEFINE CODES SENSITIVEKZ
)@@G@@ TO SHIFTING;  LOWER CASE, UPPER CASE.    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@DEFINE    TSLA
)@@G@@\1 = O'07',  " 1, 1/8   @A@@@@          TS\2 = O'47',  " 2, 1/4   @A@@@@LB
)@@G@@          TS\3 = O'03',  " 3, 3/8   @A@@@@          TS\4 = O'25',  " 4, LC
)@@G@@1/2   @A@@@@          TS\5 = O'41',  " 5, 5/8   @A@@@@          TS\6 = OLD
)@@G@@'53',  " 6, 3/4   @A@@@@          TS\7 = O'17',  " 7, 7/8   @C@@@@      LE
)@@G@@    TS\8 = O'15',  " 8, - (LONG DASH)     @A@@@@          TS\9 = O'61', LF
)@@G@@ " 9, &     @A@@@@          TS\0 = O'55',  " 0, ?     @A@@@@          TSLG
)@@G@@\COLON = O'65',  " ;, : @A@@@@          TS\PAREN = O'43',  " ), ( @A@@@@LH
)@@G@@          TS\SIGNS = O'23',  " -, + @A@@@@          TS\DOLEX = O'07';  "LI
)@@G@@ $, ! @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" LEADING DEFINITIONS   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DEFINELJ
)@@G@@    MAX\LEAD = 99; " MAXIMUM LEAD IN ONE REQUEST@[@@@@"     @H@@@@DECLARLK
)@@G@@E   LEAD: DISTANCE STATIC IMPORTED ('LEDDEV'); " PASSED BY FD-SELECT    LL
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@DECLARE   LAST\LEAD: WORD INTEGER STATIC; @[@@@@"     LM
)@@G@@@ @@@@" MISCELLANEOUS DEFINITIONS   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@DEFINE    EM\SPACELN
)@@G@@ = 18,@^@@@@          EN\SPACE = 9, @ @@@@          THIN\SPACE = 6;     LO
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@DECLARE   *: MAPPED STATIC    @B@@@@          [EX\FONTLP
)@@G@@: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER@B@@@@          ,IN\FONT: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGERLQ
)@@G@@@B@@@@          ,EX\SIZE: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER@B@@@@          ,IN\SIZELR
)@@G@@: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER@]@@@@          ];@[@@@@"     @C@@@@DECLARE   WILS
)@@G@@DTH\FACTOR: WORD INTEGER STATIC;    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   *(128): LT
)@@G@@MAPPED STATIC IMPORTED ('TSXVAL')   @B@@@@          [TS\SHIFT: 18 BIT COLU
)@@G@@NDITION,    @C@@@@           TS\CHAR : 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER];  @[@@@@LV
)@@G@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL (EJECT);  @D@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\TYPESETTER EXPOLW
)@@G@@RTED ('TSINIT')   @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          UNIT\DEVICE\WIDTH := 1;   LX
)@@G@@@H@@@@          UNIT\INTERNAL\WIDTH := PICA\DISTANCE//18;  " SPACING IN LY
)@@G@@1/18 EM     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" SET STANDARD MARGINS  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@LZ
)@@G@@          PAGE\HEIGHT := INCH\DISTANCE * 11;    @C@@@@          PAGE\WIDMA
)@@G@@TH := INCH\DISTANCE * 8.5;    @B@@@@          TOP\MARGIN := INCH\DISTANCMB
)@@G@@E;    @B@@@@          BOTTOM\MARGIN := INCH\DISTANCE; @B@@@@          LEMC
)@@G@@FT\MARGIN := INCH\DISTANCE;   @B@@@@          RIGHT\MARGIN := INCH\DISTAMD
)@@G@@NCE;  @A@@@@          SET\ALL\AREA\LINE\WIDTHS; @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" SET ME
)@@G@@STANDARD LEADING  @[@@@@"     @G@@@@          UNIT\LEADING := POINT\DISTMF
)@@G@@ANCE//2;  " LEADING IS 1/2 POINT    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" DEFINE SECTION LMG
)@@G@@EADING@[@@@@"     @B@@@@          SECTION\LEADING\BEFORE(1) := 0; @E@@@@MH
)@@G@@          SECTION\LEADING\AFTER(1) := SKIP\DISTANCE * 3;    @E@@@@      MI
)@@G@@    SECTION\LEADING\BEFORE(2) := SKIP\DISTANCE * 2;   @D@@@@          SEMJ
)@@G@@CTION\LEADING\AFTER(2) := SKIP\DISTANCE;  @D@@@@          SECTION\LEADINMK
)@@G@@G\BEFORE(3) := SKIP\DISTANCE; @D@@@@          SECTION\LEADING\AFTER(3) :ML
)@@G@@= SKIP\DISTANCE;  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" CONFIGURE DEVICE SWITCHES.  @[@@@@MM
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@          PAGE\OFFSET := 0;  " VIRTUAL AND PHYSICAL PAGE THEMN
)@@G@@ SAME @E@@@@          DEVICE\BACKSPACES := FALSE; " WE CAN'T BACKSPACE  MO
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DEVICE\LETTER\SPACES := TRUE; " CAN LETTERSPACE   @E@@@@MP
)@@G@@          DEVICE\JUSTIFIES := TRUE; " IT JUSTIFIES ITSELF   @F@@@@      MQ
)@@G@@    DEVICE\HYPHEN\CHAR := MINUS; " STANDARD HYPHEN CHAR     @C@@@@      MR
)@@G@@    MUTILATE := FALSE; " DO NOT MUTILATE  @B@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE INITMS
)@@G@@IALIZE\TYPESETTER @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PAGEUP\TYPESETTER EXPORTEDMT
)@@G@@ ('TSTOPFRM')     @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          SKIP := 0;  " KILL ANY IMPMU
)@@G@@ENDING SKIP @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO 20 DO @E@@@@             PACK\MV
)@@G@@TS\CHARACTER(TS\TF);  " RUN OUT LEADER    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" RESET FONTMW
)@@G@@ STYLE AND SIZE   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          NEW\FONT := EX\FONT;  " GEMX
)@@G@@T CURRENT FONT    @E@@@@          EXTERNAL\FONT\FOR\HANDLER;  " OUTPUT FMY
)@@G@@ONT CODE    @E@@@@          NEW\CHAR\WIDTH := EX\SIZE;  " GET CURRENT SIMZ
)@@G@@ZE    @E@@@@          EXTERNAL\WIDTH\FOR\HANDLER;  " OUTPUT SIZE CODE   NA
)@@G@@@B@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE PAGEUP\TYPESETTER     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDNB
)@@G@@URE LINE\FEED\TYPESETTER EXPORTED ('TSLEADNG')  @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      NC
)@@G@@@A@@@@DECLARE   OUT\LEAD: WORD INTEGER,   @A@@@@          TEMP    : WORDND
)@@G@@ INTEGER;   @[@@@@      @B@@@@          OUT\LEAD := LEAD//UNIT\LEADING; NE
)@@G@@@A@@@@          IF OUT\LEAD NE 0 THEN     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@NF
)@@G@@             PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\SS);  " START CONTROL SEQUENCE  @B@@@@NG
)@@G@@             IF OUT\LEAD NE LAST\LEAD THEN@^@@@@              BEGIN     NH
)@@G@@@E@@@@                PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\S);  " SET LEADING     @B@@@@NI
)@@G@@                PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\L);  @C@@@@                IF OUT\LNJ
)@@G@@EAD GT MAX\LEAD THEN    @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @E@@@@            NK
)@@G@@       PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\9); " PACK MAXIMUM  @E@@@@                  NL
)@@G@@ PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\9); " OF 99 POINTS  @C@@@@                   PACK\NM
)@@G@@TS\CHARACTER(TS\0);     @C@@@@                   WHILE OUT\LEAD GT MAX\LNN
)@@G@@EAD DO@ @@@@                    BEGIN     @G@@@@                      PANO
)@@G@@CK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\L);  " DO MAX LINE SPACE     @C@@@@                  NP
)@@G@@    PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\S);  @D@@@@                      OUT\LEAD := OUNQ
)@@G@@T\LEAD - MAX\LEAD;@^@@@@                    END;@E@@@@                  NR
)@@G@@ PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\S);  " RESET LEADING@C@@@@                   PACK\NS
)@@G@@TS\CHARACTER(TS\L);     @^@@@@                 END;   @B@@@@            NT
)@@G@@    TEMP := OUT\LEAD//100;    @D@@@@                TRANSLATE\AND\PACK\TNU
)@@G@@S\CHARACTER(TEMP);@G@@@@                TRANSLATE\AND\PACK\TS\CHARACTER(NV
)@@G@@OUT\LEAD//10-10*TEMP);  @E@@@@                IF OUT\LEAD-(OUT\LEAD//10)NW
)@@G@@*10 NE 0 THEN     @C@@@@                   PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\1);     NX
)@@G@@@^@@@@                ELSE    @C@@@@                   PACK\TS\CHARACTERNY
)@@G@@(TS\0);     @F@@@@                LAST\LEAD := OUT\LEAD; " REMEMBER LASTNZ
)@@G@@ LEAD DONE  @#@@@@              END;@E@@@@             PACK\TS\CHARACTEROA
)@@G@@(TS\L);  " DO THE LEADING     @B@@@@             PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\S)OB
)@@G@@;     @E@@@@             PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\SS);  " END THE SEQUENCE  OC
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE LINE\FEED\TYPESETTER  OD
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE TYPESETTER\TYPESIZE\CHANGE EXPORTED ('TSINSIOE
)@@G@@ZE')  @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          SCAN(CTRM+ALLOW\DST+EVAL);@ @@@@      OF
)@@G@@    IF CSDLEN NE 1 THEN @A@@@@             WARNING(W\DIR\SYNTAX); @#@@@@OG
)@@G@@          ELSE    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             NEW\CHAR\WIOH
)@@G@@DTH := 10*DNUM(1)//POINT\DISTANCE;  @B@@@@             IF NEW\CHAR\WIDTHOI
)@@G@@ LT 50 OR   @B@@@@                NEW\CHAR\WIDTH GT 720 THEN@B@@@@      OJ
)@@G@@          WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\POINT); @C@@@@             ELSE IF ERROR\STAOK
)@@G@@TUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN@^@@@@              BEGIN     @G@@@@                IFOL
)@@G@@ NEW\CHAR\WIDTH GE 130 THEN  " ROUND TO POINT SIZE    @F@@@@            OM
)@@G@@       NEW\CHAR\WIDTH := (NEW\CHAR\WIDTH//10)*10;     @D@@@@            ON
)@@G@@    ELSE  " ROUND TO LOWER HALF POINT     @E@@@@                   NEW\COO
)@@G@@HAR\WIDTH := (NEW\CHAR\WIDTH//5)*5; @F@@@@                PUT\FUNCTION\IOP
)@@G@@NTO\WORD(FUNC\WIDTH,NEW\CHAR\WIDTH);@E@@@@                CHANGE\SIZE\PAOQ
)@@G@@RAMETERS(NEW\CHAR\WIDTH);     @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           EOR
)@@G@@ND;   @C@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE TYPESETTER\TYPESIZE\CHANGE  @[@@@@"     OS
)@@G@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE PACK\TYPESETTER\LINE EXPORTED ('TSOUTPUT')  @[@@@@BEGIN OT
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @B@@@@DECLARE   CHARACTER\SPACE: WORD INTEGER;  @[@@@@      OU
)@@G@@@C@@@@          FOR I := LINE\START TO LINE\END DO    @#@@@@           BOV
)@@G@@EGIN  @C@@@@             IF LINE\BUFFER(I) EQ BLANK THEN    @^@@@@      OW
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @G@@@@                CHARACTER\SPACE := LINE\CHAR\WIDOX
)@@G@@TH(I)//WIDTH\FACTOR;    @D@@@@                WHILE CHARACTER\SPACE GT EOY
)@@G@@M\SPACE DO  @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @C@@@@                   PACK\OZ
)@@G@@TS\CHARACTER(TS\EM);    @F@@@@                   CHARACTER\SPACE := CHARPA
)@@G@@ACTER\SPACE - EM\SPACE; @^@@@@                 END;   @D@@@@            PB
)@@G@@    WHILE CHARACTER\SPACE GT EN\SPACE DO  @^@@@@                 BEGIN  PC
)@@G@@@C@@@@                   PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\EN);    @F@@@@            PD
)@@G@@       CHARACTER\SPACE := CHARACTER\SPACE - EN\SPACE; @^@@@@            PE
)@@G@@     END;   @D@@@@                WHILE CHARACTER\SPACE GT THIN\SPACE DOPF
)@@G@@@^@@@@                 BEGIN  @C@@@@                   PACK\TS\CHARACTERPG
)@@G@@(TS\THIN);  @G@@@@                   CHARACTER\SPACE := CHARACTER\SPACE PH
)@@G@@- THIN\SPACE;     @^@@@@                 END;   @C@@@@                IFPI
)@@G@@ CHARACTER\SPACE GT 0 THEN    @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @G@@@@      PJ
)@@G@@             PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\SS);  " START ADDING UNIT SPACE @C@@@@PK
)@@G@@                   WHILE CHARACTER\SPACE GT 1 DO@ @@@@                  PL
)@@G@@  BEGIN     @F@@@@                      PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\A);  " ADD PM
)@@G@@UNIT SPACE  @C@@@@                      PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\U);  @F@@@@PN
)@@G@@                      CHARACTER\SPACE := CHARACTER\SPACE - 1;     @^@@@@PO
)@@G@@                    END;@E@@@@                   PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\SSPP
)@@G@@);  " END SEQUENCE@^@@@@                 END;   @#@@@@              END;PQ
)@@G@@@C@@@@             ELSE  " JUST STUFF THE CHARACTER   @F@@@@            PR
)@@G@@    TRANSLATE\AND\PACK\TS\CHARACTER(LINE\BUFFER(I));  @#@@@@           EPS
)@@G@@ND;   @B@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE PACK\TYPESETTER\LINE  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PT
)@@G@@PROCEDURE OUTPUT\TYPESETTER\LINE EXPORTED ('TSENDLIN')@[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@PU
)@@G@@          PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\SS);  " START END-OF-LINE SEQUENCE @A@@@@PV
)@@G@@          PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\E);  @A@@@@          PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TSPW
)@@G@@\L);  @D@@@@          PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\SS);  " END SEQUENCE   @B@@@@PX
)@@G@@END; " OF PROCEDURE OUTPUT\TYPESETTER\LINE@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE HAPY
)@@G@@NDLE\TRANSPARENT\OUTPUT EXPORTED ('TSTNSDAT')   @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      PZ
)@@G@@@ @@@@DECLARE   CHAR: WORD INTEGER; @[@@@@      @B@@@@          WHILE TRQA
)@@G@@ANSPARENT\OUTPUT DO     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             CHAR QB
)@@G@@:= GET\TRANSPARENT\CHARACTER; @D@@@@             IF TRANSPARENT\OUTPUT TQC
)@@G@@HEN  " STUFF IT   @E@@@@                PACK\TS\CHARACTER(CHAR);  " SENDQD
)@@G@@ IT OFF     @ @@@@           END;  " WHILE LOOP @C@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURQE
)@@G@@E HANDLE\TRANSPARENT\OUTPUT   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE INTERNAL\FONT\QF
)@@G@@FOR\HANDLER EXPORTED ('TSINFONT')   @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          SCAN(EVAQG
)@@G@@L+CTRM+ALLOW\INT);@B@@@@          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 AND   @E@@@@QH
)@@G@@             (DNUM(1) GE 1 AND DNUM(1) LE 8) THEN  " OK     @#@@@@      QI
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @G@@@@             CHANGE\CHARACTER\WIDTH\TABLES(DNUM(1));  QJ
)@@G@@" SET NEW FONT    @E@@@@             PUT\FUNCTION\INTO\WORD(FUNC\FONT,DNQK
)@@G@@UM(1));     @#@@@@           END;   @^@@@@          ELSE  " ERROR @B@@@@QL
)@@G@@             WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\FONT);     @C@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE INTEQM
)@@G@@RNAL\FONT\FOR\CHANDLER  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" PROCEDURE TO CHANGE THE TYPEQN
)@@G@@SETTER INCORE CHARACTER WIDTH TABLES@[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE CHANGE\CQO
)@@G@@HARACTER\WIDTH\TABLES(NEW\FONT: WORD INTEGER)   @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@END; "QP
)@@G@@ OF PROCEDURE CHANGE\CHARACTER\WIDTH\TABLES     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDQQ
)@@G@@URE EXTERNAL\FONT\FOR\HANDLER EXPORTED ('TSEXFONT')   @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@QR
)@@G@@          EX\FONT := NEW\FONT;  " SET NEW EXTERNAL FONT     @D@@@@      QS
)@@G@@    PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\SS);  " SUPERSHIFT     @B@@@@          PACK\TS\QT
)@@G@@CHARACTER(TS\F);  " FONT@F@@@@          TRANSLATE\AND\PACK\TS\CHARACTER(QU
)@@G@@EX\FONT);  " GRID NUMBER@F@@@@          PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\SS);  " SUPQV
)@@G@@ERSHIFT TO END SEQUENCE @C@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE EXTERNAL\FONT\FOR\HANDQW
)@@G@@LER   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE EXTERNAL\HEIGHT\FOR\HANDLER EXPORTED (QX
)@@G@@'TSEXHGHT') BEGIN END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE EXTERNAL\WIDTH\FOR\HQY
)@@G@@ANDLER EXPORTED ('TSEXWIDT')  @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      @ @@@@DECLARE   TEQZ
)@@G@@MP: WORD INTEGER; @[@@@@      @E@@@@          EX\SIZE := NEW\CHAR\WIDTH;RA
)@@G@@  " SET NEW POINT SIZE  @D@@@@          PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\SS);  " SUPRB
)@@G@@ERSHIFT     @C@@@@          PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\P);  " POINT SIZE@C@@@@RC
)@@G@@          IF EX\SIZE-(EX\SIZE//10)*10 NE 0 THEN @D@@@@             PACK\RD
)@@G@@TS\CHARACTER(TS\H); " HALF SIZE     @A@@@@          TEMP := EX\SIZE//100RE
)@@G@@;     @C@@@@          TRANSLATE\AND\PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TEMP);@F@@@@      RF
)@@G@@    TRANSLATE\AND\PACK\TS\CHARACTER(EX\SIZE//10-10*TEMP);   @F@@@@      RG
)@@G@@    PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\SS);  " SUPERSHIFT TO END SEQUENCE @G@@@@      RH
)@@G@@    WIDTH\FACTOR := EX\SIZE//18;  " INTERNAL CONVERSION FACTOR    @C@@@@RI
)@@G@@END; " OF PROCEDURE EXTERNAL\WIDTH\FOR\HANDLER  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDRJ
)@@G@@URE START\OF\TAKE\FOR\HANDLER EXPORTED ('TSSTRTAK')   @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@RK
)@@G@@          IF OUTPUT\MEDIA EQ MEDIA\PUNCH THEN   @ @@@@             INITIRL
)@@G@@ALIZE\PUNCH;@C@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE START\OF\TAKE\FOR\HANDLER   @[@@@@RM
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE END\OF\TAKE\FOR\HANDLER EXPORTED ('TSENDTAK')     RN
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          FOR I:= 1 TO 40 DO  @B@@@@             PACK\RO
)@@G@@TS\CHARACTER(TS\TF);    @F@@@@          PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\STOP);  " PRP
)@@G@@UT IN STOP CHARACTER    @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO 200 DO@E@@@@      RQ
)@@G@@       PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\TF);  " RUN OUT LEADER    @C@@@@END; " OF PRRR
)@@G@@OCEDURE END\OF\TAKE\FOR\HANDLER     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE ESCAPE\FRS
)@@G@@OR\HANDLER EXPORTED ('TSESCAPE') BEGIN END;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THISRT
)@@G@@ PROCEDURE PACKS ONE TYPESETTER CHARACTER AT A TIME.  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@RU
)@@G@@PROCEDURE PACK\TS\CHARACTER(CHARACTER: WORD INTEGER)  @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@RV
)@@G@@      @H@@@@DECLARE   CHARS\OUTPUT: WORD INTEGER STATIC; " TOTAL CHARS ORW
)@@G@@UTPUT SINCE RETURN@[@@@@      @B@@@@          IF CHARACTER EQ TS\RET THERX
)@@G@@N     @D@@@@             CHARS\OUTPUT := 0; " NO CHARACTERS OUTPUT@C@@@@RY
)@@G@@          PACK\OUTPUT\CHARACTER(CHARACTER);     @C@@@@          CHARS\OURZ
)@@G@@TPUT := CHARS\OUTPUT + 1;     @B@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE PACK\TS\CHARACTESA
)@@G@@R     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE TRANSLATES AND PACKS TYPESETTERSB
)@@G@@ CHARACTERS.@[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE TRANSLATE\AND\PACK\TS\CHARACTER(SC
)@@G@@ASCII\CHAR: WORD INTEGER)     @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      @A@@@@DECLARE   CHSD
)@@G@@ARACTER: WORD INTEGER;  @[@@@@      @B@@@@          IF TS\SHIFT(ASCII\CHSE
)@@G@@AR) THEN    @D@@@@             PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\UC);  " UPPER CASE  SF
)@@G@@@H@@@@          PACK\TS\CHARACTER(TS\CHAR(ASCII\CHAR));  " PACK TRANSLATSG
)@@G@@ED CHARACTER@D@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE TRANSLATE\AND\PACK\TS\CHARACTER   SH
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE CHANGES THE POINT SIZE PARAMETERS    SI
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE CHANGE\SIZE\PARAMETERS(NEW\CHAR\WIDTH: DISTASJ
)@@G@@NCE)  @]@@@@BEGIN END;  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" UNUSED ENTRY POINTS FOR TYPESK
)@@G@@SETTER HANDLER.   @[@@@@"     @H@@@@PROCEDURE TYPESETTER\SUPERIOR\BEGIN SL
)@@G@@      EXPORTED ('TSDSIB')   BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE TYPESETTER\SUPSM
)@@G@@ERIOR\SWITCH      EXPORTED ('TSDSIS')   BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE TYSN

)@@G@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@END         EXPORTED ('TSDSIE')   BEGIN END;    SP
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@I));  @#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@END; "SQ

)@@G@@ BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER]; @[@@@@"     @#@@@@" LOCAL STORAGE   @[@@@@"     UH
)@@G@@@I@@@@DECLARE   FOTO\SPACE\WIDTH(6): WORD INTEGER STATIC; " CURRENT EXTEUI
)@@G@@RNAL SPACE WID    @[@@@@      @H@@@@DECLARE   WIDTH: WORD STATIC INTEGERUJ
)@@G@@ := 0; " ACCUMULATED HORIZONTAL WIDTH     @H@@@@DECLARE   LETTER\SPACE: UK
)@@G@@WORD STATIC INTEGER := 0; " CURRENT LETTER SPACING    @[@@@@      @[@@@@UL
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@" COUNT CHARACTERS OUTPUT TO INSURE THAT THERE ARE ATLEAST 1UM
)@@G@@9     @A@@@@" CHARACTERS BETWEEN EOL GROUPS     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DECLARUN
)@@G@@E   CHARS\OUTPUT: WORD INTEGER STATIC := 0;     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" COUNUO
)@@G@@T NUMBER OF JUSTIFICATION WORD SPACES     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   NUUP
)@@G@@MBER\OF\JWS: WORD INTEGER STATIC := 0;    @B@@@@DECLARE   JWS\WIDTH: DISUQ
)@@G@@TANCE STATIC := 0;@[@@@@      @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" FOR EACH OF DISK, RINGUR
)@@G@@, AND LENS WE MUST MAINTAIN BOTH AN INTERNAL    @F@@@@" AND AN EXTERNAL US
)@@G@@VALUE.  THE INTERNAL VALUE IS WHAT IS CURRENTLY @G@@@@" IN EFFECT INSIDEUT
)@@G@@ DPS.  THE EXTERNAL VALUE IS WHAT IS CURRENTLY IN     @H@@@@" EFFECT WITUU
)@@G@@H THE HARDWARE.  THEY MAY BE DIFFERENT BECAUSE DPS INTERNALLY     @G@@@@UV
)@@G@@" WILL BE AHEAD OF THE HARDWARE SINCE WE MUST BUILD A LINE AT A TIME FORUW
)@@G@@@A@@@@" THE HARDWARE BEFORE IT IS OUTPUT. @[@@@@"     @C@@@@DECLARE   INUX
)@@G@@\DISK: WORD INTEGER STATIC := 0;    @C@@@@DECLARE   EX\DISK: WORD INTEGEUY
)@@G@@R STATIC := 0;    @[@@@@      @C@@@@DECLARE   IN\RING: WORD INTEGER STATUZ
)@@G@@IC := 0;    @C@@@@DECLARE   EX\RING: WORD INTEGER STATIC := 0;    @[@@@@VA
)@@G@@      @C@@@@DECLARE   IN\LENS: WORD INTEGER STATIC := 10;   @C@@@@DECLARVB
)@@G@@E   EX\LENS: WORD INTEGER STATIC := 10;   @[@@@@      @B@@@@DECLARE   PIVC
)@@G@@CLET: WORD INTEGER STATIC;    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@DEFINE    SPLICE = 3; " VD
)@@G@@CHARS TO OUTPUT FOR SPLICE ZONE     @E@@@@DEFINE    MINCHARS = 19; " MINVE
)@@G@@ CHARS BETWEEN EOL GROUPS     @ @@@@DEFINE    FOTO\NUM\LENS = 19; @[@@@@VF
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@DECLARE   LENS\MAGNIFY(FOTO\NUM\LENS): WORD REAL@^@@@@      VG
)@@G@@    STATIC := [   @F@@@@          " 1" 0.50, " 2" 0.55, " 3" 0.60, " 4" VH
)@@G@@0.65, " 5" 0.70,  @F@@@@          " 6" 0.75, " 7" 0.80, " 8" 0.85, " 9" VI
)@@G@@0.90, "10" 1.00,  @F@@@@          "11" 1.10, "12" 1.20, "13" 1.40, "14" VJ
)@@G@@1.60, "15" 1.80,  @E@@@@          "16" 2.00, "17" 2.40, "18" 3.00, "19" VK
)@@G@@3.60 ];     @[@@@@      @A@@@@DEFINE     FOTO\FEED         = O'7' @B@@@@VL
)@@G@@          ,FOTO\RUBOUT       = O'377'     @A@@@@          ,FOTO\DISK1   VM

)@@G@@'     @B@@@@          ,FOTO\OUTER        = O'203'     @A@@@@          ,FWB
)@@G@@OTO\LENS         = O'31'@B@@@@          ,LENS1             = O'120'     WC
)@@G@@@B@@@@          ,LENS2             = O'320'     @A@@@@          ,LENS3  WD

)@@G@@ENS): 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER STATIC @C@@@@          !*(FOTO\NUM\LENS): 9WP
)@@G@@ BIT LOGICAL := [ @E@@@@          LENS1,  LENS2,  LENS3,  LENS4,  LENS5,WQ
)@@G@@  LENS6,    @E@@@@          LENS7,  LENS8,  LENS9,  LENS10, LENS11, LENSWR
)@@G@@12,   @E@@@@          LENS13, LENS14, LENS15, LENS16, LENS17, LENS18,   WS
)@@G@@@^@@@@          LENS19 ];     @[@@@@      @D@@@@DECLARE   RING\CODE(2): WT
)@@G@@9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER STATIC @ @@@@          !*(2): 9 BIT LOGICAL@B@@@@WU
)@@G@@           := [ FOTO\INNER , FOTO\OUTER ];@[@@@@      @D@@@@DECLARE   DIWV
)@@G@@SK\CODE(5): 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER STATIC @A@@@@          !*(5): 9 BIT LWW
)@@G@@OGICAL := [ @F@@@@          FOTO\DISK1,FOTO\DISK2,FOTO\DISK3,FOTO\DISK4,WX
)@@G@@FOTO\DISK5];@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THE FOLLOWING IS THE POINT SIZE OF THE CWY
)@@G@@HARACTERS ON EACH DISK  @F@@@@" THEY ARE FIXED FOR EACH DISK BUT MAY BE WZ
)@@G@@10, 15, OR 20 POINTS.   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@DECLARE   DISK\SIZE(5): 9 BIT XA
)@@G@@UNSIGNED INTEGER STATIC @A@@@@           IMPORTED ('DISKSIZE');   @[@@@@XB
)@@G@@      @D@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\FOTOTRONIC EXPORTED ('FOTOINIT') @[@@@@XC
)@@G@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          PICLET := PICA\DISTANCE//6XD
)@@G@@4; " 64 PICLETS IN PICA @H@@@@          UNIT\LEADING := POINT\DISTANCE//XE
)@@G@@4; " LEADING IN 1/4 POINT UNITS     @A@@@@          UNIT\DEVICE\WIDTH :=XF
)@@G@@ 1; " @G@@@@          UNIT\INTERNAL\WIDTH := PICLET; " HARDWARE WORKS INXG
)@@G@@ PICLETS    @D@@@@          SET\NEW\INTERNAL\FONT(1); " DEFAULT FONT 1  XH
)@@G@@@D@@@@          SET\NEW\INTERNAL\LENS(10); " DEFAULT LENS 10@F@@@@      XI
)@@G@@    BUILD\INTERNAL\WIDTH\TABLES; " SETUP ALL TABLES NEEDED  @[@@@@"     XJ
)@@G@@@^@@@@" SET STANDARD MARGINS  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@          TOP\MARGIN := XK
)@@G@@INCH\DISTANCE;    @B@@@@          BOTTOM\MARGIN := INCH\DISTANCE; @C@@@@XL
)@@G@@          PAGE\HEIGHT := INCH\DISTANCE * 11;    @C@@@@          PAGE\WIDXM
)@@G@@TH := INCH\DISTANCE * 8.5;    @B@@@@          LEFT\MARGIN := INCH\DISTANXN
)@@G@@CE;   @B@@@@          RIGHT\MARGIN := INCH\DISTANCE;  @A@@@@          SEXO
)@@G@@T\ALL\AREA\LINE\WIDTHS; @E@@@@          DEVICE\BACKSPACES := FALSE; " WEXP
)@@G@@ CAN'T BACKSPACE  @E@@@@          DEVICE\LETTER\SPACES := TRUE; " CAN LEXQ
)@@G@@TTERSPACE   @D@@@@          DEVICE\JUSTIFIES := TRUE; " IT JUSTIFIES    XR
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DEVICE\HYPHEN\CHAR := MINUS; " STANDARD HYPHEN CHAR     XS
)@@G@@@C@@@@          MUTILATE := FALSE; " DO NOT MUTILATE  @B@@@@          PAXT
)@@G@@GE\OFFSET := 0; " NO OFFSET   @B@@@@END; " PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\FOTOTRONXU
)@@G@@IC    @[@@@@      @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" ACCUMULATE THE LEADING FOR THE FOTXV
)@@G@@OTRONIC     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE FOTOTRONIC\LEADING EXPORTED ('FOXW
)@@G@@TOLEADNG')  @[@@@@BEGIN @G@@@@          LEAD := LEAD + LEADING\FOR\DEVICXX
)@@G@@E;        " ACCUMULATE LEADING@A@@@@END; " PROCEDURE FOTOTRONIC\LEADING XY
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE FOTOTRONIC\START\OF\TAKE EXPORTED ('FOTOSTRTXZ
)@@G@@AK')  @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" INITIALIZE STYLE AND PRIMARY LEADIYA
)@@G@@NG    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          CASEENTRY OUTPUT\MEDIA    @ @@@@      YB
)@@G@@    CASE MEDIA\PUNCH:   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @ @@@@             INITIYC
)@@G@@ALIZE\PUNCH;@A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO 20 DO    @G@@@@            YD
)@@G@@    PACK\FOTOTRONIC\CHARACTER(FOTO\FEED); " RUN OUT FEEDER  @#@@@@      YE
)@@G@@     END;   @C@@@@          CASE MEDIA\FILE, MEDIA\COPYVFILE:     @A@@@@YF
)@@G@@             FOR I := 1 TO 180 DO   @G@@@@                PACK\FOTOTRONIYG
)@@G@@C\CHARACTER(FOTO\FEED); " RUN OUT LEADER  @#@@@@          ENDCASE;@E@@@@YH
)@@G@@          LEAD := INCH\DISTANCE; " RUN OUT ONE INCH OF PAPER@C@@@@      YI
)@@G@@    CLOSE\FOTOTRONIC\LINE; " DUMMY HEADER @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" BE SURE TOYJ
)@@G@@ OUTPUT NEW CODES SO CLEAR OLD DISK AND RING    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@      YK
)@@G@@    EX\DISK := 0; @^@@@@          EX\RING := 0; @C@@@@          NEW\FONTYL
)@@G@@ := FONT; " GET CURRENT FONT  @E@@@@          CHANGE\FOTO\HARDWARE\FONT;YM
)@@G@@ " OUTPUT HARDWARE CODE @E@@@@          NEW\CHAR\WIDTH := IN\LENS; " GETYN
)@@G@@ CURRENT LENS     @F@@@@          CHANGE\FOTO\HARDWARE\LENS; " OUTPUT HAYO
)@@G@@RDWARE LENS CODES @ @@@@END; " PROCEDURE START\OF\TAKE@[@@@@"     @[@@@@YP
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE FOTOTRONIC\END\OF\TAKE EXPORTED ('FOTOENDTAK')    YQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@          CLOSE\FOTOTRONIC\LINE; " MAKE FINAL CLOSE OUYR
)@@G@@T     @C@@@@          IF OUTPUT\MEDIA EQ MEDIA\PUNCH OR     @C@@@@      YS
)@@G@@       OUTPUT\MEDIA EQ MEDIA\COPYVFILE OR @C@@@@             OUTPUT\MEDIYT
)@@G@@A EQ MEDIA\FILE THEN    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @G@@@@             LEAD YU
)@@G@@:= 3*63 * POINT\DISTANCE; " SPACE UP FOR FILM CUT     @^@@@@" GENERATES YV
)@@G@@3 EOL GROUPS@D@@@@             CLOSE\FOTOTRONIC\LINE; " SHIP IT OFF     YW
)@@G@@@F@@@@             PACK\FOTOTRONIC\CHARACTER(FOTO\CUT\FILM); " CUT FILM YX
)@@G@@@D@@@@             CLOSE\FOTOTRONIC\LINE; " SHIP IT OFF     @G@@@@      YY
)@@G@@       PACK\FOTOTRONIC\CHARACTER(FOTO\MONITOR); " STOP THE MACHINE@D@@@@YZ
)@@G@@             CLOSE\FOTOTRONIC\LINE; " SHIP IT OFF     @A@@@@            ZA
)@@G@@ FOR I := 1 TO 180 DO   @G@@@@                PACK\FOTOTRONIC\CHARACTER(ZB
)@@G@@FOTO\FEED); " RUN OUT TRAILER @#@@@@           END;   @C@@@@          OUZC
)@@G@@TPUT\PACKED\LINE; " CLOSE LAST LINE @ @@@@END; " PROCEDURE END\OF\TAKE  ZD
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE OUTPUTS THE HARDWARE CODE FOR A FONT ZE
)@@G@@CHANGE@E@@@@" THE FONT NUMBER (1 TO 10) MUST BE PASSED IN NEW\FONT.     ZF
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE CHANGE\FOTO\HARDWARE\FONT EXPORTED ('FOTOEXFZG
)@@G@@ONT') @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      @A@@@@DECLARE   NEW\RING: WORD INTEGER    ZH
)@@G@@@A@@@@          ,NEW\DISK: WORD INTEGER;  @[@@@@      @D@@@@          NEZI
)@@G@@W\DISK := (NEW\FONT+1)//2; " COMPUTE DISK @D@@@@          NEW\RING := 1 ZJ
)@@G@@+ MOD(NEW\FONT,2); " GET RING @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" HENCE FONT 1=RING1,DISZK
)@@G@@K1  FONT2=RING2,DISK1   @D@@@@"       FONT 3=RING1,DISK2 FONT4=RING2,DISZL
)@@G@@K2 ETC.     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@          IF EX\DISK NE NEW\DISK THEN     ZM
)@@G@@@E@@@@             PACK\FOTOTRONIC\CHARACTER(DISK\CODE(NEW\DISK));@B@@@@ZN
)@@G@@          IF EX\RING NE NEW\RING THEN     @E@@@@             PACK\FOTOTRZO
)@@G@@ONIC\CHARACTER(RING\CODE(NEW\RING));@D@@@@          EX\DISK := NEW\DISK;ZP
)@@G@@ " SAVE FOR NEXT TIME   @A@@@@          EX\RING := NEW\RING; "    @B@@@@ZQ
)@@G@@          COMPUTE\WIDTH\CONVERSION\FACTOR;@B@@@@END; " PROCEDURE CHANGE\ZR
)@@G@@FOTO\HARDWARE\FONT@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE OUTPUTS THE HARDWARZS
)@@G@@E POINT SIZE (LENS) CHANGES   @E@@@@" IT EXPECTS THE LENS NUMBER (1 TO 1ZT
)@@G@@9) IN NEW\CHAR\WIDTH    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE CHANGE\FOTO\HARDWAREZU
)@@G@@\LENS EXPORTED ('FOTOEXHGHT');@[@@@@BEGIN @G@@@@          PACK\FOTOTRONIZV
)@@G@@C\CHARACTER(FOTO\LENS); " INDICATE LENS CHANGE  @F@@@@          PACK\FOTZW
)@@G@@OTRONIC\CHARACTER(LENS\CODE(NEW\CHAR\WIDTH));   @F@@@@          EX\LENS ZX
)@@G@@:= NEW\CHAR\WIDTH; " SAVE HARDWARE LENS CODE    @B@@@@          COMPUTE\ZY
)@@G@@WIDTH\CONVERSION\FACTOR;@B@@@@END; " PROCEDURE CHANGE\FOTO\HARDWARE\LENSZZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" PROCEDURE TO VERIFY A REQUESTED FOTOTRONIC FONT CHANAA
)@@G@@GE    @A@@@@"  ONLY AN INTERNAL CHANGE IS MADE. @D@@@@"   A REQUEST IS QAB
)@@G@@UEUED TO HAVE A HARDWARE FUNCTION   @F@@@@"    SENT AT A LATER TIME WHENAC
)@@G@@ THE CHARACTERS ARE ACTUALLY OUTPUT.@[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE INTERNALAD
)@@G@@\FOTOTRONIC\FONT\CHANGE EXPORTED ('FOTOINFONT') @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@      AE
)@@G@@    SCAN(EVAL+CTRM+ALLOW\INT);@B@@@@          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 AF
)@@G@@AND   @D@@@@             (DNUM(1) GE 1 AND DNUM(1) LE 10) THEN    @^@@@@AG
)@@G@@           BEGIN " OK   @J@@@@             SET\NEW\INTERNAL\FONT(DNUM(1)AH
)@@G@@); " COMPUTE NEW DISK AND RING FOR NEW FONT     @F@@@@             BUILDAI
)@@G@@\INTERNAL\WIDTH\TABLES; " CHANGE WIDTH TABLES   @E@@@@             PUT\FAJ
)@@G@@UNCTION\INTO\WORD(FUNC\FONT,DNUM(1));     @#@@@@           END;   @^@@@@AK
)@@G@@          ELSE " ERROR  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             WARNIAL
)@@G@@NG(W\ILLEGAL\FONT);     @#@@@@           END;   @C@@@@END; " PROCEDURE IAM
)@@G@@NTERNAL\FOTOTRONIC\FONT\CHANGE@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" HERE WE READ THE CARD AN
)@@G@@GIVEN ON A TYPESIZE CHANGE AND CHECK@F@@@@" TO INSURE THAT IT IS A VALIDAO
)@@G@@ LENS SIZE. IF SO, CHANGE INTERNAL  @C@@@@" TABLES AND ALSO PUT A FUNCTIAP
)@@G@@ON INTO THE WORD. @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE INTERNAL\FOTOTRONIC\LENS\CAQ
)@@G@@HANGE EXPORTED ('FOTOINSIZE') @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          SCAN(CTRM+ALLOAR
)@@G@@W\INT+EVAL);@ @@@@          IF CSDLEN NE 1 THEN @A@@@@             WARNIAS
)@@G@@NG(W\DIR\SYNTAX); @#@@@@          ELSE    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@AT
)@@G@@             IF DNUM(1) GT FOTO\NUM\LENS OR DNUM(1) LE 0 THEN     @B@@@@AU
)@@G@@                WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\POINT); @#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@AV
)@@G@@          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@AW
)@@G@@             SET\NEW\INTERNAL\LENS(DNUM(1)); " SET NEW LENS @F@@@@      AX
)@@G@@       BUILD\INTERNAL\WIDTH\TABLES; " CHANGE WIDTH TABLES   @E@@@@      AY
)@@G@@       PUT\FUNCTION\INTO\WORD(FUNC\HEIGHT, DNUM(1));  @#@@@@           EAZ
)@@G@@ND;   @C@@@@END; " PROCEDURE INTERNAL\FOTOTRONIC\LENS\CHANGE@E@@@@PROCEDBA
)@@G@@URE PACK\FOTOTRONIC\CHARACTER(CHARACTER: WORD INTEGER)@[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@BB
)@@G@@          PACK\CHARACTER(CHARACTER); " OUTPUT THE CHARACTER @G@@@@      BC
)@@G@@    CHARS\OUTPUT := CHARS\OUTPUT + 1; " INCREMENT CHARS OUTPUT    @B@@@@BD
)@@G@@END; " PROCEDURE PACK\FOTOTRONIC\CHARACTER@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE CLBE
)@@G@@OSE\FOTOTRONIC\LINE EXPORTED ('FOTOENDLIN')     @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      BF
)@@G@@@B@@@@DECLARE   INTEGER\POINTS: WORD INTEGER;   @ @@@@DECLARE   PICAS: WBG
)@@G@@ORD INTEGER;@ @@@@DECLARE   PICS: WORD INTEGER; @[@@@@      @ @@@@      BH
)@@G@@    INCLUDE(DEBUGCODE); @B@@@@           DISPLAY('TOTWID',TOTAL\WIDTH); BI
)@@G@@@D@@@@           DISPLAY('TOTPLT',TOTAL\WIDTH//PICLET);     @E@@@@      BJ
)@@G@@     DISPLAY('TOTPIC',TOTAL\WIDTH//PICA\DISTANCE);    @B@@@@           DBK
)@@G@@ISPLAY('MAXWDI',MAX\WIDTH);   @D@@@@           DISPLAY('MAXPIC',MAX\WIDTBL
)@@G@@H//PICA\DISTANCE);@C@@@@           DISPLAY('MAXPLT',MAX\WIDTH//PICLET); BM
)@@G@@@B@@@@           DISPLAY('LINWID',LINE\WIDTH);  @E@@@@           DISPLAYBN
)@@G@@('LINPIC',LINE\WIDTH//PICA\DISTANCE);     @C@@@@           DISPLAY('LINPBO
)@@G@@LT',LINE\WIDTH//PICLET);@B@@@@           DISPLAY('WRDWID',WORD\WIDTH);  BP
)@@G@@@C@@@@           DISPLAY('WRDPLT',WORD\WIDTH//PICLET);@E@@@@           DBQ
)@@G@@ISPLAY('WRDPIC',WORD\WIDTH//PICA\DISTANCE);     @D@@@@           TOTAL\WBR
)@@G@@IDTH := 0; " CLEAR FOR NEXT LINE    @#@@@@          RESUME; @]@@@@CLOSE\BS
)@@G@@LINE: @J@@@@          FOR I := 1 TO (MINCHARS - CHARS\OUTPUT) DO " OUTPUBT
)@@G@@T ANY REQUIRED SLACK ZONE     @B@@@@             PACK\CHARACTER(FOTO\FEEBU
)@@G@@D);   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" OUTPUT THE 6 CHARACTERS OF THE END OF LINE SEQBV
)@@G@@UENCE @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          IF NUMBER\OF\JWS EQ 0 THEN@F@@@@      BW
)@@G@@       PACK\CHARACTER(FOTO\EOL\NOJUST); " NO JUSTIFICATION  @#@@@@      BX
)@@G@@    ELSE    @E@@@@             PACK\CHARACTER(FOTO\EOL\ACCEPT); " JUSTIFBY
)@@G@@Y     @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @#@@@@" COMPUTE LEADING @[@@@@"     @F@@@@BZ
)@@G@@          PACK\CHARACTER(INVERT(16*((4*MOD(LEAD,POINT\DISTANCE))//@A@@@@CA
)@@G@@             POINT\DISTANCE)));     @F@@@@          INTEGER\POINTS := LECB
)@@G@@AD//POINT\DISTANCE; " INTEGER POINTS@F@@@@          LEAD := INTEGER\POINCC
)@@G@@TS; " SAVE REMAINING LEAD COUNT     @D@@@@          IF INTEGER\POINTS GTCD
)@@G@@ 63 THEN " TRUNCATE     @E@@@@             INTEGER\POINTS := 63; " MAX LCE
)@@G@@EADING 63 POINTS  @H@@@@          PACK\CHARACTER(INVERT(INTEGER\POINTS))CF
)@@G@@; " OUTPUT INTEGER POINTS     @F@@@@          LEAD := LEAD - INTEGER\POICG
)@@G@@NTS; " COMPUTE REMAINING LEAD @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THE NEXT THREE CODES OCH
)@@G@@UTPUT CONTROL THE JUSTIFICATION     @C@@@@" 1. OUTPUT NUMBER OF JUSTIFICCI
)@@G@@ATION WORD SPACES @B@@@@"    REALLY NUMBER-1   AND ZERO = O'374'  @[@@@@CJ
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@" 2. OUTPUT THE REMAINING SPACE ON THE LINE, REQUIRES TWO COCK
)@@G@@DES   @C@@@@"    FIRST OF TWO CODES IS PICLETS = PICAS/64   @E@@@@"    ACL
)@@G@@CTUALLY THE CODE IS PICLETS-1 HENCE THERE IS NO ZERO  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@CM
)@@G@@" 3. OUTPUT WHOLE PICAS, MAX = 63   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          IF NUMBECN
)@@G@@R\OF\JWS EQ 0 THEN " NO JUSTIFICATION     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@CO
)@@G@@             PACK\CHARACTER(O'374'); " OUTPUT ZERO JWS@C@@@@            CP
)@@G@@ PACK\CHARACTER(0); " ZERO PICLETS  @C@@@@             PACK\CHARACTER(0)CQ
)@@G@@; " ZERO PICAS    @B@@@@           END; " NO JUSTIFICATION CODES  @#@@@@CR
)@@G@@          ELSE    @C@@@@           BEGIN " OUTPUT OF JUSTIFICATION CODESCS
)@@G@@@E@@@@             PACK\CHARACTER(INVERT(NUMBER\OF\JWS-1)); "     @G@@@@CT
)@@G@@             PICAS := JWS\WIDTH//PICA\DISTANCE; " COMPUTE INTEGER PICAS CU
)@@G@@@G@@@@             PICS := (JWS\WIDTH//PICLET) - PICAS*64; " REMANING PICV
)@@G@@CLETS @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" PICLETS ARE ALWAYS INCREMENTED BY THE HARDWARECW
)@@G@@ THEREFORE  @E@@@@" IT IS IMPOSSIBLE TO OUTPUT 0 PICLETS.  INSTEAD, WE OCX
)@@G@@UTPUT @E@@@@" 64 (ACTUALLY 64-1) AND DECREMENT THE PICAS BY ONE, GIVING CY
)@@G@@@^@@@@" THE SAME FINAL ANSWER.@[@@@@"     @D@@@@             IF PICS EQ CZ
)@@G@@0 THEN " CANNOT HAVE ZERO     @^@@@@              BEGIN     @B@@@@      DA
)@@G@@          PICS := 64; " MAX PICLETS @H@@@@                PICAS := PICASDB
)@@G@@ - 1; " DECREMENT PICAS FOR INCREASE IN PICLETS @#@@@@              END;DC
)@@G@@@C@@@@             PICS := PICS - 1; " DECREMENT ONE  @C@@@@            DD
)@@G@@ PACK\CHARACTER(INVERT(PICS)); "    @E@@@@             PACK\CHARACTER(INDE
)@@G@@VERT(PICAS)); " INTEGER PICAS @C@@@@           END; " OUTPUT OF JUSTIFICDF
)@@G@@ATION CODES @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" OUTPUT TAPE SPLICING ZONE   @[@@@@"     DG
)@@G@@@A@@@@          FOR I := 1 TO SPLICE DO " @B@@@@             PACK\CHARACDH
)@@G@@TER(FOTO\FEED); " @H@@@@          CHARS\OUTPUT := 6 + SPLICE; " OUTPUT EDI
)@@G@@OL GROUP (6) + SPLICE SO FAR  @D@@@@          WIDTH := 0; " NO HORIZONTADJ
)@@G@@L SPACING YET     @E@@@@          NUMBER\OF\JWS := 0; " NO JUSTIFICATIONDK
)@@G@@ SPACES YET @C@@@@          JWS\WIDTH := 0; " CLEAR WIDTH TOO     @[@@@@DL
)@@G@@"     @G@@@@" SINCE WE ONLY DO 63 AND 3/4 POINTS OF LEADING MAX IN ONE EDM
)@@G@@OL GROUP    @G@@@@" CHECK FOR MORE LEADING AND IF SO LOOP BACK TO OUTPUTDN
)@@G@@ MORE EOL GROUPS  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          IF LEAD GT 0 THEN " MORE LDO
)@@G@@EADING TO DO@#@@@@           BEGIN  @G@@@@             LEAD := LEAD * PODP
)@@G@@INT\DISTANCE; " GET BACK INTERNAL UNITS   @C@@@@             GOTO CLOSE\DQ
)@@G@@LINE; " REPEAT OUTPUT   @#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@          LEAD := DR
)@@G@@0; " CLEAR LEAD COUNT   @B@@@@END; " PROCEDURE CLOSE\FOTOTRONIC\LINE    DS
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" MOVE THE CHARACTERS FROM THE LINE\BUFFER TO THE PACKDT
)@@G@@ED    @#@@@@" OUTPUT LINE     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PACK\FOTOTRONIDU
)@@G@@C\LINE EXPORTED ('FOTOOUTPUT')@[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          FOR I := LINE\DV
)@@G@@START TO LINE\END DO    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             INCLUDW
)@@G@@DE(DEBUGCODE);    @C@@@@              ODISPLAY('ASCHAR',LINE\BUFFER(I));DX
)@@G@@@D@@@@              DISPLAY('CHARW',LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(I));    @E@@@@      DY
)@@G@@        DISPLAY('EXWID',LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(I)//PICLET);  @F@@@@            DZ
)@@G@@  TOTAL\WIDTH := TOTAL\WIDTH +LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(I);     @^@@@@            EA
)@@G@@ RESUME;    @F@@@@             IF LINE\BUFFER(I) EQ FUNC\SPACEBAND THEN EB
)@@G@@" USE JWS   @^@@@@              BEGIN     @D@@@@                NUMBER\OEC
)@@G@@F\JWS := NUMBER\OF\JWS + 1;   @E@@@@                JWS\WIDTH := JWS\WIDED
)@@G@@TH + LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(I);@F@@@@                PACK\FOTOTRONIC\CHARACTER(EE
)@@G@@FOTO\JWS); " OUTPUT JWS @C@@@@              END; " CHECK FOR SPACEBAND FEF
)@@G@@UNC   @F@@@@             ELSE IF LINE\BUFFER(I) EQ FUNC\LETTER\SPACE THEEG
)@@G@@N     @^@@@@              BEGIN     @D@@@@                LETTER\SPACE :EH
)@@G@@= LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(I);   @C@@@@              END; " SETTING LETTER SPACINEI
)@@G@@G     @D@@@@             ELSE IF LINE\BUFFER(I) EQ BLANK THEN     @G@@@@EJ
)@@G@@                WIDTH := WIDTH + LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(I); " GET DESIRED WIDTHEK
)@@G@@@E@@@@             ELSE " OUTPUT ACCUMULATED WIDTH THEN CHARACTER @^@@@@EL
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" HANDLE BLANKS SPECIALLY     EM
)@@G@@@G@@@@" THE ASCII CHARACTER CODES 1 TO 5 CONTAIN THE POSSIBLE SPACE CODEEN
)@@G@@S     @ @@@@" FROM WIDEST TO NARROWEST.   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@            EO
)@@G@@    IF WIDTH GT 0 THEN " DUMP OUT ACCUMULATED WIDTH   @^@@@@            EP
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @H@@@@                   FOR J := 2 TO 6 DO " LOOP OVER POSSEQ
)@@G@@IBLE WIDTH CHARACTERS   @ @@@@                    BEGIN     @F@@@@      ER
)@@G@@                IF FOTO\SPACE\WIDTH(J) EQ 0 THEN ERROR;     @E@@@@      ES
)@@G@@                WHILE WIDTH GE FOTO\SPACE\WIDTH(J) DO @ @@@@            ET
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@                         WIDTH := WIDTH - FOTO\SEU
)@@G@@PACE\WIDTH(J); "  @D@@@@                         PACK\FOTOTRONIC\CHARACTEV
)@@G@@ER(   @G@@@@                            FOTO\OUTPUT\CHAR(J)); " OUTPUT TEW
)@@G@@HE SPACE    @C@@@@                       END; " OF WHILE LOOP     @^@@@@EX
)@@G@@                    END;@C@@@@                 END; " TEST FOR WIDTH TO EY
)@@G@@OUTPUT@[@@@@"     @ @@@@" NOW PACK THAT CHARACTER     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@EZ
)@@G@@                PACK\FOTOTRONIC\CHARACTER(FOTO\OUTPUT\CHAR( @F@@@@      FA
)@@G@@             LINE\BUFFER(I)+1)); " DO OUTPUT CONVERSION TOO @[@@@@"     FB
)@@G@@@G@@@@" LETTER SPACING IS ADDED AFTER EVERY PRINTABLE (NONSPACE) CHARACTFC
)@@G@@ER    @[@@@@"     @I@@@@                WIDTH := WIDTH + LETTER\SPACE; "FD
)@@G@@ ADD LETTER SPACE AFTER CHARACTER   @C@@@@              END; " OF OUTPUTFE
)@@G@@TING CHARACTER    @C@@@@           END; " OF FOR LOOP OVER ALL OUTPUT   FF
)@@G@@@B@@@@END; " PROCEDURE PACK\FOTOTRONIC\LINE     @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" OUTPFG
)@@G@@UT TRANSPARENT DATA     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE FOTO\TRANSPARENT\OUTFH
)@@G@@PUT EXPORTED ('FOTOTNSDAT')   @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      @ @@@@DECLARE   CHFI
)@@G@@AR: WORD INTEGER; @[@@@@      @B@@@@          WHILE TRANSPARENT\OUTPUT DFJ
)@@G@@O     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             CHAR := GET\TRANSPARENTFK
)@@G@@\CHARACTER; @D@@@@             IF TRANSPARENT\OUTPUT THEN " STUFF IT    FL
)@@G@@@F@@@@                PACK\FOTOTRONIC\CHARACTER(CHAR); " SEND IT OFF    FM
)@@G@@@ @@@@           END; " WHILE LOOP  @B@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE TRANSPARENFN
)@@G@@T OUTPUT    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" PROCEDURE TO TO TOP OF FORMS FOR FOTOTROFO
)@@G@@NIC   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE TOP\OF\FORM\FOR\FOTO EXPORTED ('FOTOTOFP
)@@G@@PFRM')@[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          LEAD := 0; " KILL ANY PENDING LEADING FQ
)@@G@@@^@@@@" DO NOTHING ELSE NOW   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE TOP\FR
)@@G@@OF\FORM     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" PROCEDURE TO INVERT 8 BITS TO SEND TO FOFS
)@@G@@TOTRONIC    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE INVERT(CHAR: WORD INTEGER) RESULFT
)@@G@@T WORD INTEGER    @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@DECLARE    IN: 9 BIT INTEGER  @B@@@@FU
)@@G@@          !IN\BIT(9): 1 BIT CONDITION     @ @@@@          ,OUT: 9 BIT INFV
)@@G@@TEGER @B@@@@          !OUT\BIT(9): 1 BIT CONDITION;   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@FW
)@@G@@          IN := CHAR;   @ @@@@          OUT := 0; " CLEAR IT@ @@@@      FX
)@@G@@    FOR I := 2 TO 9 DO  @B@@@@             OUT\BIT(11-I) := IN\BIT(I);  FY
)@@G@@@^@@@@          RETURN(OUT);  @^@@@@END; " PROCEDURE INVERT @[@@@@"     FZ
)@@G@@@F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE COMPUTES THE CURRENT WIDTH CONVERSTION FACTOR    GA
)@@G@@@E@@@@" TO CONVERT INTERNAL SPACING WIDTHS TO DEVICE UNITS FOR    @B@@@@GB
)@@G@@" OUTPUTTING THE CORRECT SPACING CODES    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THIS SUBROGC
)@@G@@UTINE MUST BE CALLED WHENEVER THE EXTERNAL@B@@@@" LENS OR EXTERNAL DISK GD
)@@G@@IS CHANGED!!!!!   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@PROCEDURE COMPUTE\WIDTH\CONVERSION\FGE
)@@G@@ACTOR @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@DECLARE   TEMP: WORD INTEGER; " FOR BUG IN 4R1 PGF
)@@G@@LUS COMPILER CBC  @A@@@@DECLARE   IU\DU\SAVE: WORD INTEGER; @[@@@@"     GG
)@@G@@@G@@@@          IU\DU\SAVE := IU\DU\FACTOR; " SAVE CURRENT CONVERSION FAGH
)@@G@@CTOR  +@@@@[+@@@@@@H@@@@          TEMP := DISK\SIZE(EX\DISK) * POINT\DISGI
)@@G@@TANCE * LENS\MAGNIFY(EX\LENS);@H@@@@          IU\DU\FACTOR := TEMP // 32GJ
)@@G@@; " FIX FOR BAD CODE IN 4R1 PLUS COMPILER @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          FOGK
)@@G@@R I := 2 TO 6 DO " MOVE SPACE WIDTHS@#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@      GL
)@@G@@       CASEENTRY NEW\FONT     @^@@@@             CASE 1:    @G@@@@      GM
)@@G@@          FOTO\SPACE\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\ONE(I));@^@@@@GN
)@@G@@             CASE 2:    @G@@@@                FOTO\SPACE\WIDTH(I) := INTGO
)@@G@@ERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\TWO(I));@^@@@@             CASE 3:    @H@@@@      GP
)@@G@@          FOTO\SPACE\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\THREE(I));    GQ
)@@G@@@^@@@@             CASE 4:    @H@@@@                FOTO\SPACE\WIDTH(I) GR
)@@G@@:= INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\FOUR(I));     @^@@@@             CASE 5:    GS
)@@G@@@H@@@@                FOTO\SPACE\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\FIGT
)@@G@@VE(I));     @^@@@@             CASE 6:    @G@@@@                FOTO\SPAGU
)@@G@@CE\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\SIX(I));@^@@@@             CASE GV
)@@G@@7:    @H@@@@                FOTO\SPACE\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FGW
)@@G@@ONT\SEVEN(I));    @^@@@@             CASE 8:    @H@@@@                FOGX
)@@G@@TO\SPACE\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\EIGHT(I));    @^@@@@      GY
)@@G@@       CASE 9:    @H@@@@                FOTO\SPACE\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\GZ
)@@G@@WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\NINE(I));     @^@@@@             CASE 10:   @G@@@@      HA
)@@G@@          FOTO\SPACE\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\TEN(I));@^@@@@HB
)@@G@@             ENDCASE;   @ @@@@           END; " FOR LOOP    @F@@@@      HC
)@@G@@    IU\DU\FACTOR := IU\DU\SAVE; " RESTORE CURRENT FACTOR    @C@@@@END; "HD
)@@G@@ PROCEDURE COMPUT\WIDTH\CONVERSION\FACTOR @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THIS PROCEHE
)@@G@@DURE IS CALLED TO SET A NEW INTERNAL FONT @D@@@@" IT COMPUTES THE ASSOCIHF
)@@G@@ATED INTERNAL RING AND DISK   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE SET\NEW\INTERNHG
)@@G@@AL\FONT(NEW\FONT: WORD INTEGER)     @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          FONT := HH
)@@G@@NEW\FONT; " SAVE NEW FONT     @E@@@@          IN\DISK := (FONT+1)//2; " HI
)@@G@@COMPUTE NEW DISK NUMBER @F@@@@          IN\RING := 1 + MOD(FONT,2); " COHJ
)@@G@@MPUTE NEW RING NUMBER   @B@@@@END; " PROCEDURE SET\NEW\INTERNAL\FONT    HK
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@" PROCEDURE CALLED TO SET A NEW INTERNAL LENS SIZE    HL
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE SET\NEW\INTERNAL\LENS(NEW\LENS: WORD INTEGERHM
)@@G@@)     @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          IN\LENS := NEW\LENS; " SAVE IT  @B@@@@HN
)@@G@@END; " OF PROCEDURE SET\NEW\INTERNAL\LENS @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEHO
)@@G@@DURE CHANGES THE INTERNAL PARAMETERS ASSOCIATED @ @@@@" WITH A LENS OR FHP
)@@G@@ONT CHANGE. @F@@@@" IT MUST BE CALLED AFTER ANY INTERNAL LENS OR FONT CHHQ
)@@G@@ANGE!!!!!!! @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THE WIDTH OF THE FOTOTRONIC HR
)@@G@@CHARACTERS (BRASS) IS SPECIFIED IN  @F@@@@" RELATIVE UNITS.   ONE RELATIHS
)@@G@@VE UNIT IS 1/32 THE WIDTH OF AN EM. @C@@@@" HENCE 32 RELATIVE WIDTH UNITHT
)@@G@@S = THE POINT SIZE@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @I@@@@" THIS SUBROUTINE MUST BHU
)@@G@@E CALLED WHENEVER THE INTERNAL SIZE OR FONT IS CHANGED!!!!! @[@@@@"     HV
)@@G@@@B@@@@PROCEDURE BUILD\INTERNAL\WIDTH\TABLES     @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     HW
)@@G@@@B@@@@" FIRST COMPUTE INTERNAL SIZE PARAMETERS  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@      HX
)@@G@@    TYPESIZE\WIDTH :=   @H@@@@             DISK\SIZE(IN\DISK) * POINT\DIHY
)@@G@@STANCE * LENS\MAGNIFY(IN\LENS);     @C@@@@          COLUMN\DISTANCE := THZ
)@@G@@YPESIZE\WIDTH;    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" CHANGE LEADING TO TYPESIZE\WIDTH +IA
)@@G@@ 2 POINTS   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          LEADING := TYPESIZE\WIDTH + 2 * IB
)@@G@@POINT\DISTANCE;   @A@@@@          SKIP\DISTANCE := LEADING; @C@@@@      IC
)@@G@@    TYPESIZE\HEIGHT := TYPESIZE\WIDTH;    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @[@@@@ID
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@          IU\DU\FACTOR := TYPESIZE\WIDTH // 32; @[@@@@"     IE
)@@G@@@C@@@@" NOW COMPUTE NEW INTERNAL CHARACTER WIDTHS     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@IF
)@@G@@          CASEENTRY FONT " MOVE NEW WIDTH TABLE @ @@@@          CASE 1: IG
)@@G@@" FONT ONE  @A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO 256 DO   @F@@@@            IH
)@@G@@    CHAR\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\ONE(I));@ @@@@          CAII
)@@G@@SE 2: " FONT TWO  @A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO 256 DO   @F@@@@      IJ
)@@G@@          CHAR\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\TWO(I));@ @@@@      IK
)@@G@@    CASE 3: " FONT THREE@A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO 256 DO   @G@@@@IL
)@@G@@                CHAR\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\THREE(I));    IM
)@@G@@@ @@@@          CASE 4: " FONT FOUR @A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO 256IN
)@@G@@ DO   @G@@@@                CHAR\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\FOIO
)@@G@@UR(I));     @ @@@@          CASE 5: " FONT FIVE @A@@@@             FOR IIP
)@@G@@ := 1 TO 256 DO   @G@@@@                CHAR\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(IQ
)@@G@@FOTO\FONT\FIVE(I));     @ @@@@          CASE 6: " FONT SIX  @A@@@@      IR
)@@G@@       FOR I := 1 TO 256 DO   @F@@@@                CHAR\WIDTH(I) := INTIS
)@@G@@ERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\SIX(I));@ @@@@          CASE 7: " FONT SEVEN@A@@@@IT
)@@G@@             FOR I := 1 TO 256 DO   @G@@@@                CHAR\WIDTH(I) IU
)@@G@@:= INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\SEVEN(I));    @ @@@@          CASE 8: " FONTIV
)@@G@@ EIGHT@A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO 256 DO   @G@@@@                CHIW
)@@G@@AR\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\EIGHT(I));    @ @@@@          CAIX
)@@G@@SE 9: " FONT NINE @A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO 256 DO   @G@@@@      IY
)@@G@@          CHAR\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\NINE(I));     @ @@@@IZ
)@@G@@          CASE 10: " FONT TEN @A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO 256 DO   JA
)@@G@@@F@@@@                CHAR\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH(FOTO\FONT\TEN(I));JB
)@@G@@@#@@@@          ENDCASE;@D@@@@          SPACEBAND\WIDTH := CHAR\WIDTH(BLJC
)@@G@@ANK+1);     @J@@@@          UNIT\INTERNAL\SPACE := CHAR\WIDTH(6); " MIN JD
)@@G@@FOTO PHYSICAL SPACE THIS PT SIZE    @C@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE BUILD\INTEJE
)@@G@@RNAL\WIDTH\TABLES @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" ************* UNUSED ENTRY POINTS JF
)@@G@@GO HERE *******************   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" UNUSED ENTJG
)@@G@@RY POINTS FOR FOTOTRONIC HANDLER.   @[@@@@"     @H@@@@PROCEDURE FOTO\EXTJH
)@@G@@ERNAL\WIDTH\CHANGE    EXPORTED ('FOTOEXWIDT') BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDJI
)@@G@@URE FOTO\SUPERIOR\INFERIOR\BEGIN  EXPORTED ('FOTODSIB')   BEGIN END;    JJ
)@@G@@@H@@@@PROCEDURE FOTO\SUPERIOR\INFERIOR\SWITCH EXPORTED ('FOTODSIS')   BEJK
)@@G@@GIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE FOTO\SUPERIOR\INFERIOR\END    EXPORTED ('FOTJL
)@@G@@ODSIE')   BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE FOTO\ESCAPE\FOR\HANDLER       EXJM
)@@G@@PORTED ('FOTOESCAPE') BEGIN END;    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@      JN
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" ENTRY POINT FOR GENERAJO
)@@G@@LIZED BATCH PRINTER FINAL DEVICE HANDLER. @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COJP
)@@G@@PY ('FD-DEF',IMPORTED); @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS MODULE CONTAINS THE SINJQ
)@@G@@GLE ENTRY POINT FOR THIS FINAL DEVICE     @F@@@@" HANDLER.  IT CALLS THEJR
)@@G@@ APPROPRIATE ENTRY POINT ACCORDING TO THE @B@@@@" FUNCTION CODE PLACED IJS
)@@G@@N FD\FUNCTION.    @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THE CHARACTERS 'GENERALIZED...' ANJT
)@@G@@D 'PR' ARE CHANGED FOR EACH DEVICE. @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIJU
)@@G@@ZE\HANDLER IMPORTED ('PRINIT');     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE OUTPUT\FJV
)@@G@@OR\HANDLER IMPORTED ('PROUTPUT');   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE LEADING\JW
)@@G@@FOR\HANDLER IMPORTED ('PRLEADNG');  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE TOP\OF\FJX
)@@G@@ORM\FOR\HANDLER IMPORTED ('PRTOPFRM');    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE INJY
)@@G@@TERNAL\FONT\FOR\HANDLER IMPORTED ('PRINFONT');  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDJZ
)@@G@@URE EXTERNAL\FONT\FOR\HANDLER IMPORTED ('PREXFONT');  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@KA

)@@G@@R;    @B@@@@          CASE FD\TRANSPARENT\OUTPUT:     @B@@@@            SW
)@@G@@ TRANSPARENT\DATA\FOR\HANDLER;@#@@@@          ENDCASE;@ @@@@END; " PARSESX
)@@G@@\HANDLER\FUNCTION @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@LIZE: @A@@@@             INITIALIZE\SY
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);SZ
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('DURA-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CTA
)@@G@@ARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CHAR-SIZE',IMPORTED);    TB
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('GETPUT-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('GTC
)@@G@@ETPUT-PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('SCAN-PROCS',IMPORTED);   TD
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('STAGING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('STE
)@@G@@YMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('TITLE-DEF',IMPORTED);    TF
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('UTG
)@@G@@NIT-COMMON',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  TH
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\PUNCH IMPORTED ('PUINTI
)@@G@@IT'); @[@@@@      @E@@@@PROCEDURE LOAD\STANDARD\BALL\TABLE IMPORTED ('DUTJ
)@@G@@RAFONT1');  @[@@@@      @E@@@@PROCEDURE LOAD\GERMAN\BALL\TABLE IMPORTED TK
)@@G@@('DURAFONT2');    @[@@@@      @E@@@@PROCEDURE LOAD\EBCDIC\APL\BALL\TABLETL
)@@G@@ IMPORTED ('DURAFONT3');@[@@@@      @F@@@@PROCEDURE LOAD\DUAL\GOTHIC\BALTM
)@@G@@L\TABLE IMPORTED ('DURAFONT4');     @[@@@@      @E@@@@PROCEDURE LOAD\SCRTN
)@@G@@IPT\BALL\TABLE IMPORTED ('DURAFONT5');    @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @C@@@@TO
)@@G@@PROCEDURE OUTPUT\PACKED\LINE IMPORTED ('OPL');  @[@@@@      @C@@@@PROCEDTP
)@@G@@URE PACK\CHARACTER(CHAR: WORD INTEGER)    @A@@@@           IMPORTED ('PATQ
)@@G@@KCHR');     @[@@@@      @F@@@@DECLARE   OUTPUT\SHIFTED: CONDITION STATICTR
)@@G@@ EXPORTED ('OUTSHIFT'); @[@@@@      @D@@@@DECLARE   *(128): MAPPED STATITS
)@@G@@C IMPORTED ('DURCHR')   @A@@@@          [SHIFT: BIT CONDITION,    @A@@@@TT
)@@G@@           NOSHIFT: BIT CONDITION,  @ @@@@           *: 7 BIT LOGICAL,  TU
)@@G@@@A@@@@           DURA\CODE: 9 BIT LOGICAL,@ @@@@           *: 18 BIT LOGTV
)@@G@@ICAL];@[@@@@      @B@@@@DECLARE    NEW\LINE: 6 BIT CONDITION;     @C@@@@TW
)@@G@@DECLARE   SKIP: WORD INTEGER STATIC IMPORTED;   @[@@@@      @F@@@@DECLARTX
)@@G@@E LEADING\FOR\DEVICE: DISTANCE STATIC IMPORTED ('LEDDEV');  @[@@@@"     TY
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @C@@@@PROCEDURE PACK\DURA\LINE EXPORTED ('DURAOUTZ
)@@G@@TPUT')@[@@@@      @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          FOR I := LINE\START TO LINUA
)@@G@@E\END DO    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             IF LINE\BUFFER(I)UB
)@@G@@ EQ BLANK THEN    @^@@@@              BEGIN     @G@@@@                FOUC
)@@G@@R K := 1 TO LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(I) // SPACEBAND\WIDTH DO  @A@@@@            UD
)@@G@@       OUTPUT(BLANK);   @#@@@@              END;@C@@@@             ELSE UE
)@@G@@" OUTPUT NON-BLANK CHARACTER  @B@@@@                OUTPUT(LINE\BUFFER(IUF
)@@G@@));   @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECUG
)@@G@@T);   @A@@@@PROCEDURE OUTPUT(CHAR: WORD INTEGER)@[@@@@      @[@@@@      UH
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          IF OUTPUT\SHIFTED THEN    @#@@@@           BUI
)@@G@@EGIN  @E@@@@             IF NOT SHIFT(CHAR) THEN " MUST UNSHIFT DURA    UJ
)@@G@@@^@@@@              BEGIN     @B@@@@                OUTPUT\SHIFTED := FAUK
)@@G@@LSE;  @E@@@@                PACK\CHARACTER(DURA\NOSHIFT); " SHIFT DOWN  UL
)@@G@@@#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@          ELSE " OUM
)@@G@@UTPUT IN UNSHIFTED MODE @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@             IF NOUN
)@@G@@T NOSHIFT(CHAR) THEN " MUST SHIFT   @^@@@@              BEGIN     @B@@@@UO
)@@G@@                OUTPUT\SHIFTED := TRUE;   @D@@@@                PACK\CHAUP
)@@G@@RACTER(DURA\SHIFT); " SHIFT UP@#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           EUQ
)@@G@@ND;   @F@@@@          PACK\CHARACTER(DURA\CODE(CHAR)); " OUTPUT CHARACTEUR
)@@G@@R     @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" DO THE DURA LEADING HERE    @[@@@@US
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE DURA\LEADING EXPORTED ('DURALEADNG')  @[@@@@BEGIN UT
)@@G@@@E@@@@          SKIP := SKIP + LEADING\FOR\DEVICE//SKIP\DISTANCE; @ @@@@UU
)@@G@@          IF NEW\LINE THEN    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@            UV
)@@G@@ SKIP := SKIP - 1; " DECREMENT SKIP AFTER NEW LINE    @A@@@@            UW
)@@G@@ NEW\LINE := FALSE;     @#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@          IF SKIP UX
)@@G@@GT 0 THEN   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO SKIUY
)@@G@@P DO  @B@@@@                PACK\CHARACTER(DURA\LF);  @^@@@@            UZ
)@@G@@ SKIP := 0; @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" NOW VA
)@@G@@SEND OUT THE NEWLINE FUNCTION TO THE DURA @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PRVB
)@@G@@OCESS\DURA\END\OF\LINE EXPORTED ('DURAENDLIN')  @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@      VC
)@@G@@    PACK\CHARACTER(DURA\CR); " OUTPUT NEW LINE CHARACTER    @F@@@@      VD
)@@G@@    NEW\LINE := TRUE; " SET NEW LINE FOR PROPER SPACING     @[@@@@END;  VE
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE DURA\START\OF\TAKE EXPORTED ('DURASTRTAK')  VF
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          IF OUTPUT\MEDIA EQ MEDIA\PUNCH THEN   @ @@@@VG
)@@G@@             INITIALIZE\PUNCH;@[@@@@"     @^@@@@" RUN OUT SOME LEADER   VH
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@          OUTPUT\LENGTH := 0; @ @@@@          FOR I :=VI
)@@G@@ 1 TO 20 DO @B@@@@             PACK\CHARACTER(DURA\FEED);   @B@@@@      VJ
)@@G@@    PACK\CHARACTER(DURA\NOSHIFT);   @A@@@@          OUTPUT\SHIFTED := FAVK
)@@G@@LSE;  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE DURA\END\OF\TAVL
)@@G@@KE EXPORTED ('DURAENDTAK')    @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          PACK\CHARACTERVM
)@@G@@(DURA\CR);  @C@@@@          PACK\CHARACTER(DURA\STOP); " STOP DURA@ @@@@VN
)@@G@@          FOR I := 1 TO 40 DO @C@@@@             PACK\CHARACTER(DURA\FEEVO
)@@G@@D); " FEED  @ @@@@          OUTPUT\PACKED\LINE; @#@@@@          RETURN; VP
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" END OF PAGE STOP DURA SO THAT A NEW PAGEVQ
)@@G@@ CAN BE INSERTED  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE PAGEUP\DURA EXPORTED ('DURVR
)@@G@@ATOPFRM')   @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO 10 DO @B@@@@      VS
)@@G@@       PACK\CHARACTER(DURA\FEED);   @A@@@@          PACK\CHARACTER(DURA\VT
)@@G@@STOP);@ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO 10 DO @B@@@@             PACK\CHARACVU
)@@G@@TER(DURA\FEED);   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE CHECK\DURA\FONVV
)@@G@@T\CHANGE EXPORTED ('DURAINFONT')    @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          SCAN(EVAVW
)@@G@@L+CTRM+ALLOW\INT);@B@@@@          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN  @A@@@@VX
)@@G@@             IF DNUM(1) LE 0 OR     @A@@@@                DNUM(1) GT 5 TVY
)@@G@@HEN   @^@@@@              BEGIN     @B@@@@                WARNING(W\ILLEVZ
)@@G@@GAL\FONT);  @B@@@@                ERROR\PRINTED := TRUE;    @#@@@@      WA
)@@G@@        END;@#@@@@             ELSE @^@@@@              BEGIN     @E@@@@WB
)@@G@@                PUT\FUNCTION\INTO\WORD(FUNC\FONT,DNUM(1));  @A@@@@      WC
)@@G@@          CASEENTRY DNUM(1)   @^@@@@                CASE 1: @C@@@@      WD
)@@G@@             LOAD\STANDARD\BALL\TABLE;    @^@@@@                CASE 2: WE
)@@G@@@B@@@@                   LOAD\GERMAN\BALL\TABLE;@^@@@@                CAWF
)@@G@@SE 3: @C@@@@                   LOAD\EBCDIC\APL\BALL\TABLE;  @^@@@@      WG
)@@G@@          CASE 4: @C@@@@                   LOAD\DUAL\GOTHIC\BALL\TABLE; WH
)@@G@@@^@@@@                CASE 5: @B@@@@                   LOAD\SCRIPT\BALL\WI
)@@G@@TABLE;@^@@@@                ENDCASE;@#@@@@              END;@[@@@@END;  WJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\DURA\FONT\CHANGE EXPORTEWK
)@@G@@D ('DURAEXFONT')  @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          IF OUTPUT\SHIFTED THEN    WL
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             PACK\CHARACTER(DURA\NOSHIFT);WM
)@@G@@ " SHIFT DOWN     @B@@@@             OUTPUT\SHIFTED := FALSE;     @#@@@@WN
)@@G@@           END;   @G@@@@          PACK\CHARACTER(DURA\STOP); " STOP AND WO
)@@G@@WAIT FRO BALL CHANGE    @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" UNUSED ENTRY POIWP
)@@G@@NTS FOR DURA HANDLER.   @[@@@@"     @H@@@@PROCEDURE DURA\INTERNAL\SIZE\CWQ
)@@G@@HANGE     EXPORTED ('DURAINSIZE') BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE DURA\EXTWR
)@@G@@ERNAL\HEIGHT\CHANGE   EXPORTED ('DURAEXHGHT') BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDWS
)@@G@@URE DURA\EXTERNAL\WIDTH\CHANGE    EXPORTED ('DURAEXWIDT') BEGIN END;    WT
)@@G@@@H@@@@PROCEDURE DURA\SUPERIOR\INFERIOR\BEGIN  EXPORTED ('DURADSIB')   BEWU
)@@G@@GIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE DURA\SUPERIOR\INFERIOR\SWITCH EXPORTED ('DURWV
)@@G@@ADSIS')   BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE DURA\SUPERIOR\INFERIOR\END    EXWW
)@@G@@PORTED ('DURADSIE')   BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE DURA\ESCAPE\FOR\HANDWX
)@@G@@LER       EXPORTED ('DURAESCAPE') BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE DURA\TRAWY
)@@G@@NSPARENT\OUTPUT       EXPORTED ('DURATNSDAT') BEGIN END;    @[@@@@"     WZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@TERM; ___@@@ERNAL\WIDTH\CHANGE    EXPORTED ('DURAEXWIDT') BEGIN ENXA
)@@G@@D;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE DURA\SUPERIOR\INFERIOR\BEGIN  EXPORTED ('DURADSIB'XB
)@@G@@)   BEGIN END;    @H@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@XC
)@@G@@" THIS MODULE CONTAINS THE ROUTINES WHICH ARE FINAL DEVICE  @F@@@@" DEPEXD
)@@G@@NDENT.  IT SETS THE GLOBAL LOCATION 'FD\FUNCTION' TO THE    @E@@@@" REQUXE
)@@G@@ESTED FUNCTION INDEX (INIT,JUSTIFY,OUTPUT, ETC) THEN  @E@@@@" CALLS THE XF
)@@G@@CURRENTLY ACTIVE FINAL DEVICE HANDLER.  EACH    @E@@@@" DEVICE HANDLER HXG
)@@G@@AS ONLY A SINGLE ENTRY POINT INORDER TO   @D@@@@" REDUCE THE OVERHEAD ASXH
)@@G@@SOCIATED WITH SEGMENTATION    @#@@@@" OR BANKING.     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@XI
)@@G@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPXJ
)@@G@@ORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@      XK
)@@G@@    COPY ('CONVERT-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-PROC'XL
)@@G@@,IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('DEVICE-NAMES',IMPORTED); @A@@@@      XM
)@@G@@    COPY ('FD-DEF',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('GETPUT-PROCS',IMPORXN
)@@G@@TED); @B@@@@          COPY ('PRINT-DEF',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COXO
)@@G@@PY ('STAGING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('RUN-DATA-DEF',IMPORXP
)@@G@@TED); @B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-COMMON',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COXQ
)@@G@@PY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@      @F@@@@DECLARE   FD\FUNCTION: WXR
)@@G@@ORD INTEGER STATIC EXPORTED ('FUNC');     @[@@@@      @G@@@@DECLARE   LEXS
)@@G@@ADING\FOR\DEVICE: WORD INTEGER STATIC EXPORTED ('LEDDEV');  @[@@@@"     XT
)@@G@@@A@@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED; " $$$DEBUG@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" DEFINE THEXU
)@@G@@ SINGLE ENTRY POINT FOR EACH FINAL DEVICE HANDLER HERE@[@@@@"     @E@@@@XV
)@@G@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\PRINTER\OUTPUT      IMPORTED ('PRFDFUNC');@F@@@@PROCEDXW
)@@G@@URE PROCESS\PRINTRONIX\OUTPUT   IMPORTED ('PRTXFDFUNC');    @F@@@@PROCEDXX

)@@G@@URE PROCESS\FOTOTRONIC\OUTPUT   IMPORTED ('FOTOFDFUNC');    @F@@@@PROCEDYD
