)@@G@@    CARRAIGE\RETURN = O'15';  @A@@@@DEFINE    DELETE\CHAR = O'177';     UY
)@@G@@@ @@@@DEFINE    UNDERLINE = O'137'; @ @@@@DEFINE    SPACE = O'200';     UZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @[@@@@      @[@@@@"     @#@@@@" LOCAL STORAGE   @[@@@@"     VA
)@@G@@@C@@@@DECLARE   HORIZONTAL: WORD INTEGER STATIC := 0; @[@@@@      @D@@@@VB
)@@G@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\PRINTRONIX EXPORTED ('PRTXINIT') @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@VC
)@@G@@          UNIT\DEVICE\WIDTH := 1; " @E@@@@          NEW\CHAR\WIDTH := 10VD
)@@G@@; " TEN CHARACTERS PER INCH   @B@@@@          CHANGE\CHARS\PER\INCH; " SVE
)@@G@@ET IT @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" SET STANDARD MARGINS  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@      VF
)@@G@@    TOP\MARGIN := INCH\DISTANCE;    @B@@@@          BOTTOM\MARGIN := INCVG
)@@G@@H\DISTANCE; @C@@@@          PAGE\HEIGHT := INCH\DISTANCE * 11;    @C@@@@VH
)@@G@@          PAGE\WIDTH := INCH\DISTANCE * 8.5;    @B@@@@          LEFT\MARVI
)@@G@@GIN := INCH\DISTANCE;   @B@@@@          RIGHT\MARGIN := INCH\DISTANCE;  VJ
)@@G@@@A@@@@          SET\ALL\AREA\LINE\WIDTHS; @F@@@@          NEW\CHAR\HEIGHVK
)@@G@@T := 6; " SET 6 LINES PER INCH STANDARD   @B@@@@          CHANGE\LINES\PVL
)@@G@@ER\INCH; " SET IT @F@@@@          PAGE\OFFSET := INCH\DISTANCE * 2.4; " VM
)@@G@@OFFSET 2.4 INCHES @E@@@@          DEVICE\BACKSPACES := FALSE; " WE CAN'TVN
)@@G@@ BACKSPACE  @F@@@@          DEVICE\LETTER\SPACES := FALSE; " CANNOT LETTVO
)@@G@@ERSPACE     @D@@@@          DEVICE\JUSTIFIES := FALSE; " WE MUST DO IT  VP
)@@G@@@F@@@@          DEVICE\HYPHEN\CHAR := MINUS; " STANDARD HYPHEN CHAR     VQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@          MUTILATE := TRUE; " FORMAT OVERSTRIKES FOR PRINTER@[@@@@VR
)@@G@@END;  @[@@@@      @ @@@@PROCEDURE PAGEUP\PRINTRONIX   @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@VS
)@@G@@          PACK\CHARACTER(FORM\FEED);@ @@@@          SKIP := 0; " NO SKIPVT
)@@G@@@B@@@@          OUTPUT\LINE; " DUMP OUT THE LINE@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     VU
)@@G@@@B@@@@" DO ACTUAL LINE FEEDS FOR THE PRINTRONIX @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDVV
)@@G@@URE LINE\FEED\PRINTRONIX EXPORTED ('PRTXLEADNG')@[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@      VW
)@@G@@    SKIP := - SKIP + LEADING\FOR\DEVICE // SKIP\DISTANCE;   @A@@@@      VX
)@@G@@    FOR I := 1 TO SKIP DO     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@            VY
)@@G@@ PACK\CHARACTER(LINE\FEED);   @#@@@@           END;   @^@@@@          SKVZ
)@@G@@IP := 0;    @^@@@@          OUTPUT\LINE;  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@WA
)@@G@@PROCEDURE CHANGE\LINES\PER\INCH     @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@          SKIP\DISWB
)@@G@@TANCE := INTERNAL // NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT;     @G@@@@          LINES\PER\INCHWC
)@@G@@ := NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT; " SET FOR OUTPUT HANDLER   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" SET WD
)@@G@@STANDARD LEADING FOR LINE PRINTRONIX@[@@@@"     @A@@@@          LEADING WE
)@@G@@:= SKIP\DISTANCE; @C@@@@          TYPESIZE\HEIGHT := SKIP\DISTANCE;     WF
)@@G@@@B@@@@          UNIT\LEADING := SKIP\DISTANCE;  @B@@@@          SECTION\WG
)@@G@@LEADING\BEFORE(1) := 0; @E@@@@          SECTION\LEADING\AFTER(1) := SKIPWH
)@@G@@\DISTANCE * 3;    @E@@@@          SECTION\LEADING\BEFORE(2) := SKIP\DISTWI
)@@G@@ANCE * 2;   @D@@@@          SECTION\LEADING\AFTER(2) := SKIP\DISTANCE;  WJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@          SECTION\LEADING\BEFORE(3) := SKIP\DISTANCE; @D@@@@      WK
)@@G@@    SECTION\LEADING\AFTER(3) := SKIP\DISTANCE;  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     WL
)@@G@@@A@@@@PROCEDURE CHANGE\CHARS\PER\INCH     @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          IUWM
)@@G@@\DU\FACTOR := INTERNAL // NEW\CHAR\WIDTH; @F@@@@          UNIT\INTERNAL\WN
)@@G@@WIDTH := IU\DU\FACTOR*UNIT\DEVICE\WIDTH;  @B@@@@          COLUMN\DISTANCWO
)@@G@@E := IU\DU\FACTOR;@C@@@@          SPACEBAND\WIDTH := COLUMN\DISTANCE;   WP
)@@G@@@C@@@@          TYPESIZE\WIDTH := COLUMN\DISTANCE;    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@WQ
)@@G@@" INITIALIZE CHARACTER SIZES  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO WR
)@@G@@256 DO@C@@@@             CHAR\WIDTH(I) := SPACEBAND\WIDTH;  @H@@@@      WS
)@@G@@    CHAR\WIDTH(BACKSPACE+1) := - SPACEBAND\WIDTH; " BACKSPACE WIDTH     WT
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" PACK THE CHARACTERS JUST GIVEN INTO THE WU
)@@G@@LINE  @F@@@@" THE LINE IS NOT ACTUALLY OUTPUT UNTIL THE END\OF\LINE SUBRWV
)@@G@@OUTINE@]@@@@" IS CALLED @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PACK\PRINTRONIX\LINEWW
)@@G@@ EXPORTED ('PRTXOUTPUT')@[@@@@ BEGIN@[@@@@"     @B@@@@" PACK FROM LINE\BWX
)@@G@@UFFER TO OUTPUT\CARD    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          IF TRANSPARENT\OUTPUWY
)@@G@@T THEN@C@@@@             FOR I := LINE\START TO LINE\END DO @C@@@@      WZ
)@@G@@          PACK\CHARACTER(LINE\BUFFER(I)); @#@@@@          ELSE    @#@@@@XA
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO HORIZONTAL DO " FILL XB
)@@G@@SPACES NEEDED FR  @^@@@@              BEGIN     @B@@@@                PAXC
)@@G@@CK\CHARACTER(BLANK);    @#@@@@              END;@ @@@@             HORIZXD
)@@G@@ONTAL := 0; @C@@@@             FOR I := LINE\START TO LINE\END DO @^@@@@XE
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @F@@@@                IF LINE\BUFFER(I) EQ BLANKXF
)@@G@@ OR " HANDLE BLANKS     @G@@@@                   LINE\BUFFER(I) EQ FUNC\XG
)@@G@@SPACEBAND THEN " HANDLE BLANKS@^@@@@                 BEGIN  @G@@@@      XH
)@@G@@             FOR K := 1 TO LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(I)//SPACEBAND\WIDTH DO @C@@@@XI
)@@G@@                      PACK\CHARACTER(BLANK);    @^@@@@                 EXJ
)@@G@@ND;   @C@@@@                ELSE " ALL OTHER CHARACTERS     @D@@@@      XK
)@@G@@             PACK\CHARACTER(LINE\BUFFER(I));    @#@@@@              END;XL
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" CLOSE THE LINE AXM
)@@G@@ND OUTPUT IT TO THE FINAL MEDIUM    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" DUMP THE LINE OUXN
)@@G@@T  BUT FIRST BLANK FILL THE LAST WORD     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE OUXO
)@@G@@TPUT\PRINTRONIX\LINE EXPORTED ('PRTXENDLIN')    @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@      XP
)@@G@@    FOR I := 1 TO SKIP+1 DO   @B@@@@             PACK\CHARACTER(LINE\FEEXQ
)@@G@@D);   @^@@@@          SKIP := 0;    @A@@@@          OUTPUT\LINE; " DUMP XR
)@@G@@LINE  @E@@@@          SKIP := 1; " REMEMBER THAT WE SKIPPED DOWN ONE    XS
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" HERE WE MAKE INTERNAL ADJUSTMENTS DUE TOXT
)@@G@@ A TYPESIZE CHANGE@D@@@@" ASSUMING OF COURSE THAT THE CHANGE IS LEGITIMAXU
)@@G@@TE.   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PRINTRONIX\TYPESIZE\CHANGE EXPORTED ('XV
)@@G@@PRTXINSIZE')@[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@DECLARE TLEN: WORD INTEGER;   @ @@@@DECLARXW
)@@G@@E TNUM(2): WORD INTEGER;@ @@@@          NEW\CHAR\WIDTH := 0;@A@@@@      XX
)@@G@@    NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT := 0;     @D@@@@          SCAN(CTRM+ALLOW\DST+COMA+AXY
)@@G@@LLOW\INT+EVAL);   @H@@@@          TLEN := CSDLEN;    " SAVE THESE VALUESXZ
)@@G@@ AND THEN CALL SCANNER AGAIN  @ @@@@          TNUM(1) := DNUM(1); @ @@@@YA
)@@G@@          TNUM(2) := DNUM(2); @F@@@@          SCAN(CTRM+ALLOW\INT+EVAL);YB
)@@G@@ " THIS TIME PICK THEM ALL UP @^@@@@          CASEENTRY TLEN@#@@@@      YC
)@@G@@    CASE 0: @A@@@@             IF CSDLEN EQ 1 THEN    @C@@@@            YD
)@@G@@    NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT := DNUM(1);     @#@@@@          CASE 1: @#@@@@      YE
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @B@@@@             NEW\CHAR\WIDTH := TNUM(1);   @A@@@@      YF
)@@G@@       IF CSDLEN EQ 1 THEN    @C@@@@                NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT := DYG
)@@G@@NUM(1);     @A@@@@             IF CSDLEN GT 1 THEN    @A@@@@            YH
)@@G@@    NEW\CHAR\WIDTH := 0;@#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@          CASE 2: YI
)@@G@@@A@@@@             IF CSDLEN EQ 0 THEN    @^@@@@              BEGIN     YJ
)@@G@@@B@@@@                NEW\CHAR\WIDTH := TNUM(1);@C@@@@                NEYK
)@@G@@W\CHAR\HEIGHT := TNUM(2);     @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@          ENYL
)@@G@@DCASE;@E@@@@          IF (NEW\CHAR\WIDTH NE 0 OR NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT NE 0)  YM
)@@G@@@C@@@@             AND ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN    @#@@@@           BYN
)@@G@@EGIN  @E@@@@             IF (NEW\CHAR\WIDTH EQ 0 OR NEW\CHAR\WIDTH EQ 10YO
)@@G@@@G@@@@                  OR NEW\CHAR\WIDTH EQ 12) AND (NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT EQYP
)@@G@@ 0    @G@@@@                  OR NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT EQ 6 OR NEW\CHAR\HEIGHTYQ
)@@G@@ EQ 8) THEN @^@@@@              BEGIN     @C@@@@                IF NEW\CYR
)@@G@@HAR\WIDTH NE 0 THEN     @B@@@@                   CHANGE\CHARS\PER\INCH; YS
)@@G@@@C@@@@                IF NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT NE 0 THEN    @B@@@@            YT
)@@G@@       CHANGE\LINES\PER\INCH; @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           EYU
)@@G@@ND;   @#@@@@          ELSE    @A@@@@             WARNING(W\DIR\SYNTAX); YV
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE TOP\OF\FORM\FOR\PRINTRONIX EXPORYW
)@@G@@TED ('PRTXTOPFRM')@[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          PAGEUP\PRINTRONIX;  @[@@@@YX
)@@G@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE END\OF\TAKE\FOR\PRINTRONIX EXPORTED ('YY
)@@G@@PRTXENDTAK')@[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@          PAGEUP\PRINTRONIX;  @[@@@@END;  YZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" UNUSED ENTRY POINTS FOR PRINTRONIX HANDLER.   @[@@@@ZA
)@@G@@"     @H@@@@PROCEDURE PRINTRONIX\START\OF\TAKE      EXPORTED ('PRTXSTRTAZB
)@@G@@K') BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE PRINTRONIX\INTERNAL\FONT      EXPORTEDZC
)@@G@@ ('PRTXINFONT') BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE PRINTRONIX\EXTERNAL\FONT  ZD
)@@G@@    EXPORTED ('PRTXEXFONT') BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE PRINTRONIX\EXTZE
)@@G@@ERNAL\HEIGHT    EXPORTED ('PRTXEXHGHT') BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE PRZF
)@@G@@INTRONIX\EXTERNAL\WIDTH     EXPORTED ('PRTXEXWIDT') BEGIN END;    @H@@@@ZG
)@@G@@PROCEDURE PRINTRONIX\SUPERIOR\BEGIN     EXPORTED ('PRTXDSIB')   BEGIN ENZH
)@@G@@D;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE PRINTRONIX\SUPERIOR\SWITCH    EXPORTED ('PRTXDSIS'ZI
)@@G@@)   BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE PRINTRONIX\SUPERIOR\END       EXPORTEDZJ
)@@G@@ ('PRTXDSIE')   BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE PRINTRONIX\ESCAPE\FOR\HANDZK
)@@G@@LER EXPORTED ('PRTXESCAPE') BEGIN END;    @H@@@@PROCEDURE PRINTRONIX\TRAZL
)@@G@@NSPARENT\OUTPUT EXPORTED ('PRTXTNSDAT') BEGIN END;    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@ZM
)@@G@@TERM; ___@@@LUMN\DISTANCE;    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" INITIALIZE CHARACTER SZN
)@@G@@IZES  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          FOR I := 1 TO *[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULEZO
)@@G@@;     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS ELEMENT CONTAINS ROUTINES TO MATERIALIZE ZP
)@@G@@VALUES FOR AND SET@F@@@@" VALUES INTO 'EXECUTED VARIABLES', THOSE FOR WHZQ
)@@G@@ICH THE EXECUTION @F@@@@" OF SUBROUTINES IS REQUIRED TO DEFINE OR CHANGEZR
)@@G@@ THEIR VALUES.    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" EXECUTED VARIABLES AND THEIR INDICZS
)@@G@@ES ARE DEFINED IN THE ASSEMBLY@F@@@@" LANGUAGE ELEMENT SYS-SYMBOLS AND PZT
)@@G@@LUS PROCEDURE SYMBOL-DEF.     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINESZU
)@@G@@',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@      ZV
)@@G@@    COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-PROC'ZW
)@@G@@,IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('IO-PROCS',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@      ZX
)@@G@@    COPY ('SCAN-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('STAGING-DEF',ZY
)@@G@@IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@      ZZ
)@@G@@    COPY ('UNIT-COMMON',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',AA
)@@G@@IMPORTED);  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(DESC: MACHINEAB
)@@G@@ WORD POINTER     @C@@@@                            ,WORD: INTEGER WORD)AC
)@@G@@@A@@@@          IMPORTED ('PUTWRDDESC');  @[@@@@"     @ [@@@PROCEDURE ERAD
)@@G@@ROR IMPORTED;     @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@AE
)@@G@@DECLARE   XVAR\DESC(2): LOCATABLE INTEGER WORD; @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" GET AF
)@@G@@THE VALUE OF AN EXECUTED VARIABLE.  THIS IS CALLED IN THE SCANNER @G@@@@AG
)@@G@@" AND IS EXPECTED TO RETURN A POINTER TO THE DESCRIPTOR FOR THE VALUE.  AH
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE COMPUTE\EXECUTED\VARIABLE(INDEX: INTEGER WORAI
)@@G@@D)    @E@@@@          EXPORTED ('COMPXVAR') RESULT MACHINE POINTER WORD AJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@DECLARE   XVAR\PTR: MACHINE WORD POINTER; @B@@@@DECLARAK
)@@G@@E   DATE\AND\TIME: WORD INTEGER     @B@@@@          ![MONTH: 6 BIT UNSIGAL
)@@G@@NED INTEGER @B@@@@           ,DAY: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER   @B@@@@      AM
)@@G@@     ,YEAR: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER  @B@@@@          ,TIME: 18 BIT UNSIGNAN
)@@G@@ED INTEGER];@ @@@@DECLARE    HOURS: WORD INTEGER@ @@@@          ,MINS: WAO
)@@G@@ORD INTEGER @ @@@@          ,SECS: WORD INTEGER;@A@@@@DECLARE   AREA\SAVAP
)@@G@@E: MACHINE POINTER@ @@@@          ,VERTICAL: DISTANCE;@[@@@@"     @C@@@@AQ
)@@G@@          XVAR\DESC(1) := 0; " CLEAR MISC FIELDS@B@@@@          XVAR\PTRAR
)@@G@@ := LOC( XVAR\DESC(1) );@D@@@@          DTYP(XVAR\PTR) := TYPDST; " ASSUAS
)@@G@@ME DISTANCE @D@@@@          DLEN(XVAR\PTR) := 0; " LENGTH ZERO INITIALLYAT
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DADR(XVAR\PTR) := DS\PTR; " ON TEMP DATA STACK    @ @@@@AU
)@@G@@          CASEENTRY INDEX     @C@@@@          CASE XVAR\HPOS: " HORIZONTAV
)@@G@@AL POSITION @A@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC     @E@@@@            AW
)@@G@@ (XVAR\PTR,LINE\WIDTH+WORD\WIDTH+LEFT\INDENT);  @B@@@@          CASE XVAAX
)@@G@@R\LMAR: " LEFT MARGIN   @D@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR,LAY
)@@G@@EFT\MARGIN);@B@@@@          CASE XVAR\RMAR: " RIGHT MARGIN  @E@@@@      AZ
)@@G@@       PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR,RIGHT\MARGIN);     @B@@@@          CABA
)@@G@@SE XVAR\LIND: " LEFT INDENT   @D@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVARBB
)@@G@@\PTR,LEFT\INDENT);@B@@@@          CASE XVAR\RIND: " RIGHT INDENT  @E@@@@BC
)@@G@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR,RIGHT\INDENT);     @B@@@@      BD
)@@G@@    CASE XVAR\DATE: " RETURN DATE   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@      BE
)@@G@@       DTYP(XVAR\PTR) := TYPINT; " THIS IS AN INTEGER @D@@@@            BF
)@@G@@ DATE\AND\TIME := GET\TDATE; " GET TDATE  @F[@@@             PUT\WORD\INBG
)@@G@@TO\DESC(XVAR\PTR,MONTH); " STUFF MONTH    @C@@@@             PUT\WORD\INBH
)@@G@@TO\DESC(XVAR\PTR,DAY);  @D@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR,YBI
)@@G@@EAR+1964);  @#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@          CASE XVAR\TIME: " REBJ
)@@G@@TURN TIME   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             DTYP(XVAR\PTR) :=BK
)@@G@@ TYPINT; " THIS IS AN INTEGER @D@@@@             DATE\AND\TIME := GET\TDBL
)@@G@@ATE; " GET TDATE  @G[@@@             HOURS := TIME//3600; " SECONDS PASTBM
)@@G@@ MIDNITE/3600 = HOURS   @C@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR,HBN
)@@G@@OURS);@F@@@@             MINS := (TIME-HOURS*3600)//60; " COMPUTE MINUTEBO
)@@G@@S     @C@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR,MINS); @D@@@@      BP
)@@G@@       SECS := TIME - HOURS*3600 - MINS*60;     @C@@@@             PUT\WBQ
)@@G@@ORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR,SECS); @F@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVARBR
)@@G@@\PTR,TIME); " PUT TIME TOO    @#@@@@           END;   @C@@@@          CABS
)@@G@@SE XVAR\NCOL: " NUMBER OF COLUMNS   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@      BT
)@@G@@       DTYP(XVAR\PTR) := TYPINT;    @E@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESBU
)@@G@@C(XVAR\PTR,NUMBER\OF\COLUMNS);@#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@          CABV
)@@G@@SE XVAR\GWID: " GUTTER WIDTH  @E@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVARBW
)@@G@@\PTR,GUTTER\WIDTH);     @D@@@@          CASE XVAR\CCOL: " CURRENT COLUMNBX
)@@G@@ NUMBER     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             DTYP(XVAR\PTR) :=BY
)@@G@@ TYPINT;    @E@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR,COLUMN\NUMBERBZ
)@@G@@);    @#@@@@           END;   @E@@@@          CASE XVAR\VPOS: " VPOS$ VECA
)@@G@@RTICAL POSITION ON PAGE @#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@             AREA\CB
)@@G@@SAVE := AREA\PTR;  " SAVE CURRENT AREA POINTER  @E@@@@             AREA\CC
)@@G@@PTR := LOC(TEXT\AREA);  " GO TO TEXT AREA @D@@@@             VERTICAL :=CD
)@@G@@ AREA\VPOS\START+AREA\VPOS;   @D@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVARCE
)@@G@@\PTR,VERTICAL);   @E@@@@             AREA\PTR := AREA\SAVE;  " RESTORE ACF
)@@G@@REA POINTER @#@@@@           END;   @C@@@@          CASE XVAR\LEAD: " CUCG
)@@G@@RRENT LEADING     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@             PUT\WORD\INCH
)@@G@@TO\DESC(XVAR\PTR,ROUND\HEIGHT(LEADING));  @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@CI
)@@G@@          CASE XVAR\JUST: " JUSTIFY$@#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@      CJ
)@@G@@       DTYP(XVAR\PTR) := TYPINT; " OUTPUT INTEGER     @G@@@@            CK
)@@G@@ PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR, CVT\COND\TO\INTE(JUSTIFY) );  @#@@@@      CL
)@@G@@     END;   @A@@@@          CASE XVAR\NOSP: " NOSPACE$@#@@@@           BCM
)@@G@@EGIN  @E@@@@             DTYP(XVAR\PTR) := TYPINT; " OUTPUT INTEGER     CN
)@@G@@@G@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR, CVT\COND\TO\INTE(NOSPACECO
)@@G@@) );  @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          CASE XVAR\FILL: " FILL$   CP
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             DTYP(XVAR\PTR) := TYPINT; " OCQ
)@@G@@UTPUT INTEGER     @G@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR, CVT\COCR
)@@G@@ND\TO\INTE(FILL) );     @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          CASE XVACS
)@@G@@R\COMP: " COMPACT$@#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             DTYP(XVAR\PCT
)@@G@@TR) := TYPINT; " OUTPUT INTEGER     @G@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESCU
)@@G@@C(XVAR\PTR, CVT\COND\TO\INTE(COMPACT) );  @#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@CV
)@@G@@          CASE XVAR\HYPHEN: " HYPHEN$     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@CW
)@@G@@             DTYP(XVAR\PTR) := TYPINT; " OUTPUT INTEGER     @G@@@@      CX
)@@G@@       PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR, CVT\COND\TO\INTE(HYPHEN) );   @#@@@@CY
)@@G@@           END;   @B@@@@          CASE XVAR\CENTER: " CENTER$     @#@@@@CZ
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             DTYP(XVAR\PTR) := TYPINT; " OUTPUT DA
)@@G@@INTEGER     @G@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR, CVT\COND\TO\DB
)@@G@@INTE(CENTER) );   @#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@          CASE XVAR\RIGHDC
)@@G@@TF: " RIGHTF$     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             DTYP(XVAR\PDD
)@@G@@TR) := TYPINT; " OUTPUT INTEGER     @G@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESDE
)@@G@@C(XVAR\PTR, CVT\COND\TO\INTE(RIGHTF) );   @#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@DF
)@@G@@          CASE XVAR\FORMAT: " FORMAT$     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@DG
)@@G@@             DTYP(XVAR\PTR) := TYPINT; " OUTPUT INTEGER     @H@@@@      DH
)@@G@@       PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR, CVT\COND\TO\INTE(FORMATTING) );     DI
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          CASE XVAR\PROOF: " PROOF$ @#@@@@DJ
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             DTYP(XVAR\PTR) := TYPINT; " OUTPUT DK
)@@G@@INTEGER     @G@@@@             PUT\WORD\INTO\DESC(XVAR\PTR, CVT\COND\TO\DL
)@@G@@INTE(PROOFING) ); @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@          CASE *: @B@@@@DM
)@@G@@           BEGIN " ERROR IN XVAR INDEX    @B@@@@             DISPLAY('BADN
)@@G@@DXVR',INDEX);     @^@@@@             ERROR;     @A@@@@           END; " DO
)@@G@@BAD XVAR INDEX    @#@@@@          ENDCASE;@ @@@@          RETURN(XVAR\PTDP
)@@G@@R);   @A@@@@END; " OF COMPUTE\EXECUTED\VARIABLE @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   DQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @H@@@@" SET A NEW VALUE INTO AN EXECUTED VARIABLE.  THIS IS DR
)@@G@@CALLED FROM THE LET     @H@@@@" COMMAND/DIRECTIVE AND IS PASSED THE XVARDS
)@@G@@ INDEX AND THE NEW VALUE DESCR.     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDURE SET\EXECDT
)@@G@@UTED\VARIABLE     @D@@@@             (INDEX: INTEGER WORD " XVAR INDEX TDU
)@@G@@O SET @G@@@@             ,VALUE: MACHINE WORD POINTER) " TO DESCRIPTOR FDV
)@@G@@OR NEW VALUE@ @@@@          EXPORTED ('SETXVR') @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     DW
)@@G@@@G@@@@" BRANCH ON XVAR PASSED.  THE CONTINGENCY CASE IS USED TO DETECT XDX
)@@G@@VARS  @C@@@@" WHICH ARE NOT CONFIGURED AS USER-CHANGABLE.   @[@@@@"     DY
)@@G@@@ @@@@          CASEENTRY INDEX     @A@@@@          CASE XVAR\COMP: " CODZ
)@@G@@MPACT$@#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@"            DUMP\DESCRIPTOR('CMPSETEA

)@@G@@EFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@EL
)@@G@@          COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CHAR-SIEM
)@@G@@ZE',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('OUTPUT-PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@EN
)@@G@@          COPY ('PHOTON-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('STAGINGEO
)@@G@@-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @F@@@@PROCEDURE GET\TRANSPARENEP
)@@G@@T\CHARACTER IMPORTED ('GETTRANSCHAR')     @A@@@@             RESULT WORDEQ
)@@G@@ INTEGER;   @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @E@@@@DEFINE    MAX\SPACE = 15; " MAER
)@@G@@X HORIZONTAL SPACE IN ONE CODE@D@@@@DEFINE    MAX\CODES = 200; " MAXIMUMES
)@@G@@ CODES ON ONE LINE@[@@@@      @G@@@@DECLARE   FUNNY\MODE: WORD CONDITIONET
)@@G@@ STATIC IMPORTED ('FUNNYMODE');     @[@@@@      @F@@@@DECLARE WIDTH\FACTEU
)@@G@@OR: WORD INTEGER STATIC EXPORTED ('PHOWIDFAC'); @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROEV
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" PACK\PHOTON\LINE IS GIVEN CONTROL WHEN CEW
)@@G@@HARACTERS ARE TO BE OUTPUT.   @G@@@@" IT OPERATES BY FIRST OUTPUTTING THEX
)@@G@@E WIDTH VALUE ASSOCIATED WITH THE   @G@@@@" CHARACTER (WHICH MAY RESULT EY
)@@G@@IN MULTIPLE WIDTH CODES), FOLLOWED BY THE @G@@@@" CHARACTER TO BE OUTPUTEZ
)@@G@@. SPACES ARE SUPRESSED (ONLY WIDTH IS SENT).    @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" NOTEFA
)@@G@@: FOR PHOTON DEBUG, A NULL WIDTH CODE (0200) AND A SPACE (040) ARE@A@@@@FB
)@@G@@" SENT WHEN OUTPUTTING A LONG WIDTH.@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PACK\PHOFC
)@@G@@TON\LINE EXPORTED ('PH7445OUTPUT')  @[@@@@BEGIN @H@@@@DECLARE   CHARACTEFD
)@@G@@R\SPACE: WORD INTEGER; " CHARACTER WIDTH IN PHOTON UNITS    @[@@@@"     FE
)@@G@@@C@@@@          FOR I := LINE\START TO LINE\END DO    @B@@@@           BFF
)@@G@@EGIN " LOOP TO PACK CHARACTERS@G@@@@             CHARACTER\SPACE := LINEFG
)@@G@@\CHAR\WIDTH(I) // WIDTH\FACTOR;     @D@@@@             WHILE CHARACTER\SFH
)@@G@@PACE GT MAX\SPACE DO    @C@@@@              BEGIN " BREAK UP LARGE SPACIFI
)@@G@@NG    @F@@@@                CHARACTER\SPACE := CHARACTER\SPACE - MAX\SPAFJ
)@@G@@CE;   @F@@@@                PACK\PHOTON\CHARACTER(PH\WIDTH\CODE + MAX\SPFK
)@@G@@ACE); @C@@@@              END; " BREAK UP LARGE SPACING     @B@@@@      FL
)@@G@@       IF CHARACTER\SPACE GT 0 THEN @G@@@@                PACK\PHOTON\CHFM
)@@G@@ARACTER(PH\WIDTH\CODE + CHARACTER\SPACE); @C@@@@             IF LINE\BUFFN
)@@G@@FER(I) EQ BLANK THEN    @F@@@@                PACK\PHOTON\CHARACTER(92) FO
)@@G@@" PACK BLANK CHARACTER  @#@@@@             ELSE @C@@@@                IFFP
)@@G@@ LINE\BUFFER(I) EQ 92 THEN    @H@@@@                   PACK\PHOTON\CHARAFQ
)@@G@@CTER(32) " TURN 92 (\) INTO QUOTE (32)    @^@@@@                ELSE    FR
)@@G@@@H@@@@                   PACK\PHOTON\CHARACTER(LINE\BUFFER(I)); " PACK NFS
)@@G@@ONBLANK     @B@@@@           END; " LOOP TO PACK CHARACTERS @^@@@@END; "FT
)@@G@@ PACK\PHOTON\LINE @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" PACK\PHOTON\CHARACTER IS GIVEN CONFU
)@@G@@TROL ON EACH CHARACTER OUTPUT.@F@@@@" AS THERE IS A MAXIMUM NUMBER OF POFV
)@@G@@SITIONS IN THE PHOTON BUFFER, @G@@@@" THIS ROUTINE ATTEMPTS TO BREAK UP FW
)@@G@@LONG LINES INTO MULTIPLE BUFFER     @G@@@@" LOADS. IT DOES THIS BY OUTPUFX
)@@G@@TTING WIDTH CODES TO RE-ESTABLISH THE     @F@@@@" HORIZONTAL POSITION FOFY
)@@G@@R THE SECOND PASS. (CODE UNDEBUGGED).     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PAFZ
)@@G@@CK\PHOTON\CHARACTER(CHARACTER: WORD INTEGER)    @A@@@@           EXPORTEGA
)@@G@@D ('PACKPHCHAR')  @[@@@@BEGIN @G@@@@DECLARE   HORIZONTAL\SPACE: WORD INTGB
)@@G@@EGER STATIC; " ACCUMULATE SPACE     @H@@@@DECLARE   CHARS\OUTPUT: WORD IGC
)@@G@@NTEGER STATIC; " TOTAL CHARS OUTPUT SINCE CR    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@      GD
)@@G@@    IF CHARACTER EQ PH\CR THEN@ @@@@           BEGIN " RESET ON CR@D@@@@GE
)@@G@@             HORIZONTAL\SPACE := 0; " NO SPACE YET    @D@@@@            GF
)@@G@@ CHARS\OUTPUT := 0; " NO CHARACTERS OUTPU @ @@@@           END; " RESET GG
)@@G@@ON CR @C@@@@          IF (CHARACTER GE PH\WIDTH\CODE) AND   @E@@@@      GH
)@@G@@       (CHARACTER LE (PH\WIDTH\CODE+MAX\SPACE)) THEN  @A@@@@            GI
)@@G@@ HORIZONTAL\SPACE :=    @F@@@@                HORIZONTAL\SPACE + (CHARACGJ
)@@G@@TER - PH\WIDTH\CODE);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@          PACK\OUTPUT\CHARACTEGK
)@@G@@R(CHARACTER); " SEND CHAR TO PHOTON @G@@@@          CHARS\OUTPUT := CHARGL
)@@G@@S\OUTPUT + 1; " COUNT CHARACTERS SENT     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@          IFGM
)@@G@@ CHARS\OUTPUT GT MAX\CODES THEN " TEST BUFFER OVERFLOW@D@@@@           BGN
)@@G@@EGIN " CHARACTER OVERFLOW, BREAK UP LINE  @C@@@@             CHARS\OUTPUGO
)@@G@@T := 0; " RESET COUNTER @E@@@@             PACK\OUTPUT\CHARACTER(PH\CR);GP
)@@G@@ " CLOSE LINE     @D@@@@             WHILE HORIZONTAL\SPACE GT MAX\SPACEGQ
)@@G@@ DO   @E@@@@              BEGIN " LOOP TO RESTORE HORIZONTAL POSITION   GR
)@@G@@@F@@@@                HORIZONTAL\SPACE := HORIZONTAL\SPACE - MAX\SPACE; GS
)@@G@@@F@@@@                PACK\OUTPUT\CHARACTER(PH\WIDTH\CODE + MAX\SPACE); GT
)@@G@@@D@@@@                CHARS\OUTPUT := CHARS\OUTPUT + 1;     @E@@@@      GU
)@@G@@        END; " LOOP TO RESTORE HORIZONTAL POSITION    @G@@@@            GV
)@@G@@ PACK\OUTPUT\CHARACTER(PH\WIDTH\CODE + HORIZONTAL\SPACE);   @C@@@@      GW
)@@G@@       CHARS\OUTPUT := CHARS\OUTPUT + 1;  @A@@@@             HORIZONTAL\GX
)@@G@@SPACE := 0; @D@@@@           END; " CHARACTER OVERFLOW, BREAK UP LINE   GY
)@@G@@@ @@@@END; " PACK\PHOTON\CHARACTER  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" TERMINATE THE CUGZ
)@@G@@RRENT LINE  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE CLOSE\PHOTON\LINE EXPORTED ('PH7HA
)@@G@@445ENDLIN') @[@@@@BEGIN @G@@@@          PACK\PHOTON\CHARACTER(PH\CR); " HB
)@@G@@TELL PHOTON LINE COMPLETE     @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@      @[@@@@"     @B@@@@HC
)@@G@@" PROCEDURE TO HANDLE TRANSPARENT OUTPUT  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE HAHD
)@@G@@NDLE\TRANSPARENT\OUTPUT EXPORTED ('PH7445TNSDAT')     @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@HE
)@@G@@      @ @@@@DECLARE   CHAR: WORD INTEGER; @[@@@@      @B@@@@          WHHF
)@@G@@ILE TRANSPARENT\OUTPUT DO     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@            HG
)@@G@@ CHAR := GET\TRANSPARENT\CHARACTER; @D@@@@             IF TRANSPARENT\OUHH
)@@G@@TPUT THEN " STUFF IT    @E@@@@                PACK\OUTPUT\CHARACTER(CHARHI
)@@G@@); " SEND IT OFF  @ @@@@           END; " WHILE LOOP  @B@@@@END; " OF PRHJ
)@@G@@OCEDURE TRANSPARENT OUTPUT    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" UNUSED ENTRY POINTS FOHK
)@@G@@R PHOTON HANDLER. @[@@@@"     @H@@@@PROCEDURE PHOTON\EXTERNAL\HEIGHT\CHAHL
)@@G@@NGE   EXPORTED ('PH7445EXHGHT') BEGIN END;@H@@@@PROCEDURE PHOTON\SUPERIOHM
)@@G@@R\INFERIOR\BEGIN  EXPORTED ('PH7445DSIB')   BEGIN END;@H@@@@PROCEDURE PHHN
)@@G@@OTON\SUPERIOR\INFERIOR\SWITCH EXPORTED ('PH7445DSIS')   BEGIN END;@H@@@@HO
)@@G@@PROCEDURE PHOTON\SUPERIOR\INFERIOR\END    EXPORTED ('PH7445DSIE')   BEGIHP
)@@G@@N END;@H@@@@PROCEDURE PHOTON\ESCAPE\FOR\HANDLER       EXPORTED ('PH7445EHQ
)@@G@@SCAPE') BEGIN END;@[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@OR: WORD INTEGER STATIC HR
)@@G@@EXPORTED ('PHOWIDFAC'); @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     HS
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS MODULE TAKES CAREHT
)@@G@@ OF PROCESSING THE END OF PAGE CONDITON   @F@@@@" IT WILL OUTPUT THE PHYHU
)@@G@@SICAL PAGEUP AND THEN THE TOP MARGIN AND  @C@@@@" ANY REQUIRED HEADING WHV
)@@G@@ITH PAGENUMBERS ETC.    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPOHW
)@@G@@RTED);@D@@@@ COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED);       " ***** DEBUG   @B@@@@HX
)@@G@@          COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CHAR-SIHY
)@@G@@ZE',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@HZ
)@@G@@          COPY ('CONVERT-PROC',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('CORE-PRIA
)@@G@@OCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('FD-PROCS',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@IB
)@@G@@          COPY ('FTNOTE-PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('GETPUT-IC
)@@G@@DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('GETPUT-PROCS',IMPORTED); @A@@@@ID
)@@G@@          COPY ('IO-DEF1',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('MACRO-DEF',IMIE
)@@G@@PORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@      IF
)@@G@@    COPY ('PACKET-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('PUSH-PROCS',IIG
)@@G@@MPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SKIP-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@      IH
)@@G@@    COPY ('STAGING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-DEF',III
)@@G@@MPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@      IJ
)@@G@@    COPY ('TITLE-DEF',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-COMMON',IK
)@@G@@IMPORTED);  @[@@@@      @ @@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED;     @[@@@@      IL
)@@G@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE DO\END\OF\LINE\PROCESSING IMPORTED ('EOLPRO');    @[@@@@IM
)@@G@@      @D@@@@PROCEDURE DO\TOP\FUNCTIONS IMPORTED ('DOTOPFUNCS');   @[@@@@IN
)@@G@@      @D@@@@PROCEDURE FORCE\END\OF\PARAGRAPH IMPORTED ('FOREOL'); @[[@@@IO
)@@G@@      @C@@@@PROCEDURE OUTPUT\AREA\TEXT IMPORTED ('OUTEXT'); @[@@@@      IP
)@@G@@@C@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\ENDKEEP IMPORTED ('ENDKEEP'); @[@@@@      @D@@@@IQ
)@@G@@PROCEDURE SAVE\TOP\FUNCTION(FUNCTION: WORD INTEGER,   @E@@@@            IR
)@@G@@ VALUE: WORD INTEGER) IMPORTED ('SAVETOPFUNC'); @[@@@@      @C@@@@DECLARIS
)@@G@@E   SKIP: WORD INTEGER STATIC IMPORTED;   @[@@@@      @[@@@@"     @C@@@@IT
)@@G@@" GOTO THE NEXT COLUMN IF NO MORE PUT OUT PAGE  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDIU
)@@G@@URE FORCE\END\OF\COLUMN EXPORTED ('FOREOC')     @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@      IV
)@@G@@    CASEENTRY AREA\TYPE @^@@@@          CASE TEXT:    @#@@@@           BIW
)@@G@@EGIN  @H@@@@             IF NEXT\AREA\PTR NE NULL\PTR THEN  " WE HAVE A IX
)@@G@@STACKED FLOAT     @A@@@@                PROCESS\ENDKEEP;    @#@@@@      IY
)@@G@@       ELSE @B@@@@                PROCESS\END\OF\COLUMN;    @#@@@@      IZ
)@@G@@     END;   @^@@@@          CASE FOOTNOTE:@B@@@@             PROCESS\FOOJA
)@@G@@TNOTE\OVERFLOW;   @^@@@@          CASE KEEP:    @ @@@@             PROCEJB
)@@G@@SS\ENDKEEP; @#@@@@          ENDCASE;@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THISJC
)@@G@@ PROCEDURE DOES THE END OF COLUMN PROCESSING.   @[@@@@      @D@@@@PROCEDJD
)@@G@@URE PROCESS\END\OF\COLUMN EXPORTED ('PROEOC')   @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      JE
)@@G@@@C@@@@DECLARE   CPTR(*): MAPPED BASED(COLUMN\LIST\PTR)@C@@@@            JF
)@@G@@       [TAIL: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER@D@@@@                   ,HEAD: 18 BJG
)@@G@@IT MACHINE POINTER]     @C@@@@          ,LPTR: WORD MACHINE POINTER BASEJH
)@@G@@D;    @[@@@@      @G@@@@          IF NUMBER\OF\COLUMNS GT 1 THEN " SAVE JI
)@@G@@PTR TO END OF COLUMN    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             TAIL(JJ
)@@G@@COLUMN\NUMBER) := TAIL\PTR; " SAVE POINTER@C@@@@             INCLUDE (DEJK
)@@G@@BUG\CODE, NO SOURCE);   @F@@@@             SNAP ('PTRS', NUMBER\OF\COLUMJL
)@@G@@NS, COLUMN\LIST\PTR);   @^@@@@             RESUME;    @#@@@@           EJM
)@@G@@ND;   @D@@@@          IF COLUMN\NUMBER LT NUMBER\OF\COLUMNS THEN  @#@@@@JN
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             COLUMN\NUMBER := COLUMN\NUMBER+1;  JO
)@@G@@@ @@@@             SET\AREA\VPOS(0);@G@@@@             PUSH\AT\EQUATE(COJP
)@@G@@L\EQUATE); " PUSH TOP OF COLUMN EQUATE    @#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@JQ
)@@G@@          ELSE  " END OF PAGE @A@@@@             FORCE\END\OF\PAGE;     JR
)@@G@@@A@@@@          COLUMN\EMPTY := TRUE;     @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @G@@@@JS
)@@G@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO DUMP OUT THE TEXT IN THE CURRENT AREA     JT
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\AREA\BREAK  @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@      JU
)@@G@@    OUTPUT\AREA\TEXT;   @E@@@@          COLUMN\NUMBER := 1;         " REJV
)@@G@@SET COLUMN COUNT  @E@@@@          HEAD\PTR := NULL\PTR;       " CLEAR SAJW
)@@G@@VE\TEXT\PTR @A@@@@          TAIL\PTR := NULL\PTR;     @E@@@@          SEJX
)@@G@@T\AREA\VPOS(0);           " RESET AREA POSITIONS@A@@@@          SET\AREAJY
)@@G@@\REL\VPOS(0);     @A@@@@          INITIALIZE\LINE\ASSEMBLY; @A@@@@      JZ
)@@G@@    COLUMN\EMPTY := TRUE;     @ @@@@END; " OF AREA BREAK PROCEDURE@[@@@@KA
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO CREATE A ZONE BREAK     @D@@@@KB
)@@G@@"  A ZONE BREAK CASUSES ALL TEXT SET ON THE PAGE UPTO @A@@@@" THE CURRENKC
)@@G@@T AREA TO B DUMPED OUT. @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\ZONE\BREAK EKD
)@@G@@XPORTED ('PROZONEBRK')  @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @B@@@@DECLARE   AREA\SAVKE
)@@G@@E: WORD MACHINE POINTER;@[@@@@"     @A@@@@          IF NOT FIRST\PAGE THKF
)@@G@@EN    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@             FORCE\END\OF\PARAGRAPH;KG
)@@G@@ " CREATE PARAGRAPH BREAK     @B@@@@             INCLUDE\ALL\FLOATS := TKH
)@@G@@RUE;  @D@@@@             PROCESS\ENDKEEP; " FORCE OUT ANY KEEPS   @F@@@@KI
)@@G@@             AREA\SAVE := AREA\PTR; " SAVE CURRENT AREA POINTER   @F@@@@KJ
)@@G@@             AREA\PTR := FIRST\AREA; " POINT TO FIRST FIXED AREA  @C@@@@KK
)@@G@@             WHILE AREA\PTR NE NULL\PTR AND     @F@@@@                ARKL
)@@G@@EA\PTR NE AREA\SAVE DO " LOOP UPTO CURRENT AREA @^@@@@              BEGIKM
)@@G@@N     @C@@@@                PROCESS\AREA\BREAK; " DUMP AREA @F@@@@      KN
)@@G@@          AREA\PTR := FIXED\AREA\PTR; " POINT TO NEXT AREA  @B@@@@      KO
)@@G@@        END; " LOOPING OVER AREAS   @C@@@@             " WE AREA BACK INKP
)@@G@@ OUR CURRENT AREA @F@@@@             IF AREA\PTR NE NULL\PTR THEN " DUMPKQ
)@@G@@ CURRENT AREA     @^@@@@              BEGIN     @C@@@@                PRKR
)@@G@@OCESS\AREA\BREAK; " BREAK AREA@#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           EKS
)@@G@@ND;   @ @@@@END; " OF PROCESS\ZONE\BREAK  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" PUT OUT THKT
)@@G@@E LAST PAGE AND PERFORM A TOP OF PAGE     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE FOKU
)@@G@@RCE\END\OF\PAGE EXPORTED ('FOREOP') @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          IF NOT PKV
)@@G@@AGE\EMPTY THEN      " OUTPUT PAGE   @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@      KW
)@@G@@       PUT\OUT\FOOTING;         " DO FOOTING    @F@@@@             PUTOUKX
)@@G@@T\LAST\PAGE;        " DUMP PAGE IF BUFFERED     @G@@@@             PAGEUKY
)@@G@@P\POS := VERTICAL\POSITION; " SAVE CURRENT POSITION   @ @@@@            KZ
)@@G@@ PERFORM\PAGEUP;  @A@@@@             IF NOT FIRST\PAGE THEN @G@@@@      LA
)@@G@@          PAGE\NUMBER := PAGE\NUMBER +1; " UPDATE PAGE NUMBER     @E@@@@LB
)@@G@@             SET\VERTICAL\POSITION(0); " SET AT TOP OF PAGE @G@@@@      LC
)@@G@@       PUSH\AT\EQUATE(COL\EQUATE); " INSERT TOP OF COLUMN EQUATE  @G@@@@LD
)@@G@@             PUSH\AT\EQUATE(TOP\EQUATE); " INSERT TOP OF PAGE EQUATE    LE
)@@G@@@D@@@@             END\OF\AREA := FALSE;    " START NEW AREA@A@@@@      LF
)@@G@@       PAGE\EMPTY := TRUE;    @A@@@@             FIRST\PAGE := FALSE;   LG
)@@G@@@ @@@@             DO\TOP\FUNCTIONS;@#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  LH
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\OUT\HEADING EXPOLI
)@@G@@RTED ('PUTOUTHEDING')   @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      @A@@@@DECLARE   TOP\LEADLJ
)@@G@@ING: DISTANCE;    @B@@@@DECLARE   CENTER\INDEX: WORD INTEGER;     @A@@@@LK
)@@G@@DECLARE   CENTER\WIDTH: DISTANCE;   @B@@@@DECLARE   AREA\SAVE: WORD MACHLL
)@@G@@INE POINTER;@[@@@@      @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" ASSUME WE ARE POSITIONED AT LM
)@@G@@TOP OF PAGE @[@@@@"     @F@@@@          AREA\SAVE := AREA\PTR;      " SALN
)@@G@@VE CURRENT AREA POINTER @E@@@@          AREA\PTR := LOC(HEADING\AREA); "LO
)@@G@@ USE HEADING AREA @D@@@@          PUSH\WORD\BUFFER;           " SAVE WALLP
)@@G@@AB    @D@@@@          IF FIRST\PAGE THEN          " MUST DO PAGEUP@#@@@@LQ
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             PAGE\EMPTY := FALSE;     " FORCE ITLR
)@@G@@ TO DO IT   @E@@@@             FORCE\END\OF\PAGE;       " DO PHYSICAL PALS
)@@G@@GEUP  @#@@@@           END;   @D@@@@          IF PAGE\NUMBER EQ 0 THEN  LT
)@@G@@  " **** TEMP     @H@@@@             PAGE\NUMBER := 1;        " SHOULD NLU
)@@G@@OT NEED BUT SOMETIMES IS ZERO @E@@@@          IF HEADING\REQUESTED THEN LV
)@@G@@" PUT OUT HEADING INFO  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             TOP\LLW
)@@G@@EADING := TOP\MARGIN//2+TYPESIZE\HEIGHT;  @D@@@@             PERFORM\LEALX
)@@G@@DING(TOP\LEADING,FUNC\LEADU); @A@@@@             IF ODD\PAGE\FACING AND LY
)@@G@@@G@@@@                (MOD(PAGE\NUMBER,2) EQ 0) THEN " NUMBER ON LEFT OFLZ
)@@G@@ PAGE @D@@@@                IF NOT NUMBER\BOTTOM\OF\PAGE THEN     @F@@@@MA
)@@G@@                   INSERT\PAGE\NUMBER; " INSERT THE PAGE NUMBER   @F@@@@MB
)@@G@@             IF CENTER\HEADING THEN   " SAVE CURRENT POSITION     @^@@@@MC
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @F@@@@                PUT\FUNCTION\INTO\WORD(FUNMD
)@@G@@C\BLANK,0); " SPACE     @E@@@@                CENTER\INDEX := WORD\INDEXME
)@@G@@; " SAVE POINTER  @E@@@@                CENTER\WIDTH := WORD\WIDTH; " SAMF
)@@G@@VE WIDTH TOO@#@@@@              END;@F@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO HEAMG
)@@G@@DING\LENGTH DO " INSERT HEADING     @H@@@@                PUT\CHARACTER\MH
)@@G@@INTO\NEXT\WORD(HEADING(I)); " PUT CHARACTER     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" NOW MI
)@@G@@INSERT AMOUNT OF SPACE INFRONT OF THE HEADING TO CENTER IT  @[@@@@"     MJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@             IF CENTER\HEADING THEN   " COMPUTE CENTERING SPACE   MK
)@@G@@@^@@@@              BEGIN     @E@@@@                CENTER\WIDTH := (AREML
)@@G@@A\WIDTH-WORD\WIDTH+     @D@@@@                   CENTER\WIDTH)//2 - CENTMM
)@@G@@ER\WIDTH;   @F@@@@                NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(CENTER\INDEX) := ROUNDMN
)@@G@@\WIDTH(     @A@@@@                   CENTER\WIDTH);   @C@@@@" UPDATE WORMO
)@@G@@D WIDTH TO INCLUDE CENTERING SPACE  @G@@@@             WORD\WIDTH := WORMP
)@@G@@D\WIDTH + NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(CENTER\INDEX);  @#@@@@              END;@B@@@@MQ
)@@G@@             IF NOT ODD\PAGE\FACING OR    @C@@@@                (MOD(PAGMR
)@@G@@E\NUMBER,2) EQ 1) THEN  @^@@@@              BEGIN     @C@@@@            MS
)@@G@@    IF HEADING\LENGTH GT 0 THEN     @E@@@@                   FLUSH\FROM\MT
)@@G@@HERE;   " FLUSH PAGE NUMBER   @D@@@@                IF NOT NUMBER\BOTTOMMU
)@@G@@\OF\PAGE THEN     @D@@@@                   INSERT\PAGE\NUMBER; " INSERT MV
)@@G@@IT    @#@@@@              END;@F@@@@             PERFORM\LEADING(TOP\MARMW
)@@G@@GIN-TOP\LEADING,FUNC\LEADU);  @#@@@@           END;   @D@@@@          ELMX
)@@G@@SE  " BE SURE TO LEAD TO BOTTOM OF HEADING@D@@@@             PERFORM\LEAMY
)@@G@@DING(TOP\MARGIN,FUNC\LEADU);  @G@@@@          INHIBIT\INDENT := TRUE;   MZ
)@@G@@  " INHIBIT ANY TEMPORARY MARGINS   @E@@@@          MOVE\NEXT\WORD\TO\LINA
)@@G@@NE;     " OUTPUT BUILT LINE   @D@@@@          END\OF\PARAGRAPH := TRUE; NB
)@@G@@  " DO NOT JUSTIFY@F@@@@          INHIBIT\LEADING := TRUE;    " SET FOR NC
)@@G@@EOL PROCESSING    @B@@@@          DO\END\OF\LINE\PROCESSING;  "   @F@@@@ND
)@@G@@          POP\WORD\BUFFER;            " RESURRECT CURRENT LINE    @G@@@@NE
)@@G@@          AREA\PTR := AREA\SAVE;      " RESTORE PREVIOUS AREA POINTER   NF
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" PROCEDURE TO PUT OUT THE FOOTING ON THE NG
)@@G@@PAGE  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE PUT\OUT\FOOTING     @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@NH
)@@G@@DECLARE   CENTER\INDEX:  WORD INTEGER;    @A@@@@DECLARE   CENTER\WIDTH: NI
)@@G@@DISTANCE;   @B@@@@DECLARE   AREA\SAVE: WORD MACHINE POINTER;@[@@@@"     NJ
)@@G@@@D@@@@          IF FOOTING\REQUESTED AND NOT FIRST\PAGE THEN@#@@@@      NK
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @E@@@@             AREA\SAVE := AREA\PTR;   " SAVE CURRENT ANL
)@@G@@REA   @H@@@@             AREA\PTR := LOC(FOOTING\AREA); " USE FOOTING ARNM
)@@G@@EA FOR FOOTING    @E@@@@             PUSH\WORD\BUFFER;        " GET CLEANN
)@@G@@N WORK AREA @[@@@@"     @H@@@@             PERFORM\LEADING(BOTTOM\MARGINNO
)@@G@@//2+TYPESIZE\HEIGHT,FUNC\LEADU);    @A@@@@             IF ODD\PAGE\FACINNP
)@@G@@G AND @G@@@@                (MOD(PAGE\NUMBER,2) EQ 0) THEN " NUMBER ON LNQ
)@@G@@EFT OF PAGE @C@@@@                IF NUMBER\BOTTOM\OF\PAGE THEN   @F@@@@NR
)@@G@@                   INSERT\PAGE\NUMBER; " INSERT THE PAGE NUMBER   @F@@@@NS
)@@G@@             IF CENTER\FOOTING THEN   " SAVE CURRENT POSITION     @^@@@@NT
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @F@@@@                PUT\FUNCTION\INTO\WORD(FUNNU
)@@G@@C\BLANK,0); " PUT SPACE @C@@@@                CENTER\INDEX := WORD\INDEXNV
)@@G@@;     @C@@@@                CENTER\WIDTH := WORD\WIDTH;     @#@@@@      NW
)@@G@@        END;@F@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO FOOTING\LENGTH DO " INSERT NX
)@@G@@FOOTING     @H@@@@                PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD(FOOTING(INY
)@@G@@)); " STUFF CHARACTER   @F@@@@             IF CENTER\FOOTING THEN   " CONZ
)@@G@@MPUT CENTERING SPACE    @^@@@@              BEGIN     @E@@@@            OA
)@@G@@    CENTER\WIDTH := (AREA\WIDTH-WORD\WIDTH+     @D@@@@                  OB
)@@G@@ CENTER\WIDTH)//2 - CENTER\WIDTH;   @F@@@@                NEXT\CHAR\WIDTOC
)@@G@@H(CENTER\INDEX) := ROUND\WIDTH(     @A@@@@                   CENTER\WIDTOD
)@@G@@H);   @E@@@@                WORD\WIDTH := WORD\WIDTH + NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH( OE
)@@G@@@A@@@@                   CENTER\INDEX);   @ @@@@              END; " CENOF
)@@G@@TERING@B@@@@             IF NOT ODD\PAGE\FACING OR    @C@@@@            OG
)@@G@@    (MOD(PAGE\NUMBER,2) EQ 1) THEN  @^@@@@              BEGIN     @C@@@@OH
)@@G@@                IF FOOTING\LENGTH GT 0 THEN     @E@@@@                  OI
)@@G@@ FLUSH\FROM\HERE;   " FLUSH PAGE NUMBER   @C@@@@                IF NUMBEOJ
)@@G@@R\BOTTOM\OF\PAGE THEN   @D@@@@                   INSERT\PAGE\NUMBER; " IOK
)@@G@@NSERT IT    @#@@@@              END;@A@@@@             INHIBIT\INDENT :=OL
)@@G@@ TRUE;@A@@@@             MOVE\NEXT\WORD\TO\LINE;@E@@@@             END\OOM
)@@G@@F\PARAGRAPH := TRUE; " NO JUSTIFICATION   @F@@@@             INHIBIT\LEAON
)@@G@@DING := TRUE;  " SET FOR EOL PROCESSING   @B@@@@             DO\END\OF\LOO
)@@G@@INE\PROCESSING;   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@             POP\WORD\BUFFER;       OP
)@@G@@  " RESURRECT CURRENT LINE    @G@@@@             AREA\PTR := AREA\SAVE; OQ
)@@G@@  " RESTORE PREVIOUS AREA POINTER   @#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@END; "OR
)@@G@@ OF PUT\OUT\FOOTING     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" PROCEDURE TO CONVERT AND INSOS
)@@G@@ERT PAGE NUMBER   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE INSERT\PAGE\NUMBER  @[@@@@OT
)@@G@@BEGIN @[@@@@      @H@@@@DEFINE    PLEN =  6;                  " INSERT 6OU
)@@G@@ CHARACTERS FOR PAGE NAME     @[@@@@      @D@@@@DECLARE   PAGE\NAME(6): OV
)@@G@@9 BIT LOGICAL MAPPED STATIC   @C@@@@          ! *: 6 ASCII CHARACTERS :=OW
)@@G@@ 'PAGE  ';  @[@@@@      @B@@@@          IF CHAPTER\NUMBER(1) NE 0 OR    OX
)@@G@@@B@@@@             START\PAGE\NUMBERING THEN    @#@@@@           BEGIN  OY
)@@G@@@F@@@@             IF EDIT\CHAP\NUMBER THEN " EDIT CHAPTER NUMBER TOO   OZ
)@@G@@@^@@@@              BEGIN     @B@@@@                FOR I := 1 TO PLEN DPA
)@@G@@O     @F@@@@                   PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD(PAGE\NAME(I)PB
)@@G@@);    @F@@@@                CONVERT\AND\INSERT\NUMBER(CHAPTER\NUMBER(1))PC

)@@G@@UMBER(PAGE\NUMBER);     @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     PF

)@@G@@\AREA\PTR;  " GET NEXT AREA   @A@@@@           END; " OF LOOP OVER AREASPP

)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" RE-INITIALIZE LINE ASSEMBLY IN ORIGINAL AREA TO PICK UP   PR

)@@G@@ OF INITIALIZE INTERNAL TABLES AND FILES  @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS ROUTIRQ
)@@G@@NE IS CALLED TO ENTER A LINEAR LIST OF DESCRIPTORS INTO     @F@@@@" A BIRR
)@@G@@NARY TREE.  THE LIST IS SET UP AT ASSEMBLY TIME IN ELEMENT  @#@@@@" SYS-RS
)@@G@@SYMBOLS.    @[@@@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE ENTER\LIST(CHAIN: MACHINE WORD PRT
)@@G@@OINTER   " TO LINEAR LIST     @G@@@@                    ,%ROOT: LOCATABLRU
)@@G@@E MACHINE WORD POINTER)  " TO TREE  @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   POINT: MRV
)@@G@@ACHINE WORD POINTER; " TO THIS ENTRY@D@@@@DECLARE   PNEXT: MACHINE WORD RW
)@@G@@POINTER; " TO NEXT ENTRY@[@@@@"     @D@@@@          POINT := CHAIN; " GERX
)@@G@@T FIRST THING TO ENTER  @D@@@@          WHILE POINT NE NULL\PTR DO " ENTRY
)@@G@@ER THEM     @B@@@@           BEGIN " TO ENTER 'THIS' ENTRY  @E@@@@      RZ
)@@G@@       PNEXT := SRLK(POINT); " GET NEXT TO RELEASE    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@SA
)@@G@@" INITIAL SYSTEM SYMBOL TABLE IS NULL, SO THERE SHOULD NEVER BE   @B@@@@SB
)@@G@@" A NODE RETURNED FROM THE SEARCH ROUTINE.@[@@@@"     @F@@@@            SC
)@@G@@ IF SEARCH\FOR\NODE( ROOT,STYP(POINT),SLEN(POINT),    @E@@@@            SD
)@@G@@    LOC(SNAM(POINT)) ) NE NULL\PTR THEN ERROR;  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" ENTESE
)@@G@@R SYSTEM SYMBOL INTO BINARY TREE.   @[@@@@"     @H@@@@             ROOT SF
)@@G@@:= INSERT\NEW\NODE(ROOT,POINT); " INSERT NODE INTO CHAIN    @ @@@@      SG
)@@G@@       POINT := PNEXT;  @A@@@@           END; " OF ENTERING THIS  @A@@@@SH
)@@G@@"         PDISPLAY('ENTLST',ROOT);  @^@@@@END; " OF ENTER\LIST    @#@@@@SI
)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO INITIASJ
)@@G@@LIZE DBANK LOCATIONS SO THAT THE    @G@@@@" CHECKPOINT WRITTEN ON RETURNSK
)@@G@@ FROM THE I OPTION EDITOR HAS THE CORRECT @F@@@@" DATA FOR THE CHECKPOINSL
)@@G@@T.  (FORMERLY DONE AT TOP OF 'FORMAT').   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE INSM
)@@G@@IT\FORMAT\DATA    @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" MAKE SURE WE ARE IN TESN
)@@G@@XT AREA.    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          IF (AREA\PTR NE LOC(TEXT\AREA)) SO
)@@G@@THEN ERROR; @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" INITIALIZE ALL CHANGEABLE MODES   @[@@@@SP
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@          PAGE\NUMBER := 1; " START AT PAGE ONE @E@@@@      SQ
)@@G@@    SET\VERTICAL\POSITION(0);   " START AT TOP OF PAGE@F@@@@          SESR
)@@G@@T\AREA\VPOS(0);           " CLEAR LOCAL AREA POSITION @A@@@@          SESS
)@@G@@T\AREA\REL\VPOS(0);     @E@@@@          COLUMN\NUMBER := 1;         " REST
)@@G@@SET COLUMN COUNTER@E@@@@          GUTTER\WIDTH := 0;          " CLEAR GUSU
)@@G@@TTER WIDTH  @F@@@@          NUMBER\OF\COLUMNS := 1;     " SET SINGLE COLSV
)@@G@@UMN MODE    @F@@@@          SPACE\REMAINING := 0;       " CLEAR FOR HYPHSW
)@@G@@EN MODE     @G@@@@          CHARS\THIS\LINE := 2;       " SET CHARS TO RSX
)@@G@@EMAIN ON LINE     @H@@@@          CHARS\NEXT\LINE := 2;       " AND CHARSY
)@@G@@S TO BE MOVED TO NEXT LINE    @D@@@@          LEFT\INDENT := 0;         SZ
)@@G@@  " *****TEMP     @C@@@@          RIGHT\INDENT := 0;          " ****TEMPTA
)@@G@@@ @@@@          BALANCING := FALSE; @ @@@@          CENTER := FALSE;    TB
)@@G@@@ @@@@          COMPACT := TRUE;    @A@@@@          DISTRIBUTION := TRUETC
)@@G@@;     @^@@@@          FILL := TRUE; @ @@@@          HYPHEN := FALSE;    TD
)@@G@@@ @@@@          JUSTIFY := TRUE;    @B@@@@          JUSTIFY\FROM\RIGHT :TE
)@@G@@= FALSE;    @ @@@@          LEFT\FLAG := FALSE; @ @@@@          NOSPACE TF
)@@G@@:= FALSE;   @ @@@@          RIGHTF := FALSE;    @A@@@@          AREA\UNDTG
)@@G@@ERLINE := FALSE;  @^@@@@END; " INIT\FORMAT\DATA @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@END; "TH
)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULE;     @E@@@@DEFINE    READ\SNAP  = FALSE; " SNAPTI
)@@G@@SHOT CHECKPOINT READS   @E@@@@DEFINE    WRITE\SNAP = FALSE; " SNAPSHOT CTJ
)@@G@@HECKPOINT WRITES  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS ELEMENT CONTAINS ROUTINES TO TK
)@@G@@TAKE CHECKPOINTS OF DPS AT    @F@@@@" STRATEGIC TIMES SO THAT THE SESSIOTL
)@@G@@N CAN BE RECOVERED IN THE     @A@@@@" EVENT OF SYSTEM (OR DPS) CRASHES. TM
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" ROUTINES ARE ALSO DEFINED HERE TO TAKE VARIABLE CHECTN
)@@G@@KPOINTS     @^@@@@" DURING A FORMAT PASS. @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COTO
