)@@G@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE ERROR IMPORTED;     @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECUE
)@@G@@T);   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" WRITE DPS STATUS CHECKPOINT FOR RECOVERY IN CAUF
)@@G@@SE OF SYSTEM@^@@@@" OR PROGRAM CRASH.     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE CHUG
)@@G@@ECKPOINT\DPS(STATE: INTEGER WORD    @C@@@@                        ,FIRSTUH
)@@G@@: INTEGER WORD    @C@@@@                        ,LAST: INTEGER WORD)    UI
)@@G@@@ @@@@            EXPORTED ('CKPT') @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   PACKET: UJ
)@@G@@MACHINE POINTER; " TO IO PACKET     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          RECOVERYUK
)@@G@@\IDENT := DPS\ABSOLUTE\ID;    @ @@@@          DPS\STATUS := STATE;@ @@@@UL
)@@G@@          FRST\UNIT := FIRST; @ @@@@          LAST\UNIT := LAST;  @[@@@@UM
)@@G@@"     @A@@@@          FORCE\WRITE\OF\BIT\MAPS;  @A@@@@          WRITE\UNUN
)@@G@@IT\DIRECTORY;     @ @@@@          WRITE\FILE\HEADER;  @D@@@@          PAUO
)@@G@@CKET := LOC(GENPKT); " USE GENERAL PACKET @F@@@@          DRUM\ADDR(PACKUP
)@@G@@ET) := 1; " REC BUF SECTOR 1 OF SCRFIL    @C@@@@          FUNCTION(PACKEUQ
)@@G@@T) := IO\FUNC\WRITE;    @A@@@@          WORD\COUNT(PACKET) := 28; @D@@@@UR
)@@G@@          BUFFER\ADDR(PACKET) := LOC(RECOVERY\BUFFER);@D@@@@          IOUS
)@@G@@WWEC(PACKET); " WRITE RECOVERY BUFFER     @^@@@@END; " CHECKPOINT\DPS   UT
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IUU
)@@G@@S CALLED TO TAKE A GLOBAL CHECKPOINT AT THE END @G@@@@" OF A FORMAT PASSUV
)@@G@@.  FRVS AND COMMAND VARIABLES WILL BE CHECKPOINTED.   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@UW
)@@G@@PROCEDURE WRITE\GLOBAL\CKPT EXPORTED ('CKGLWR') @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     UX
)@@G@@@ @@@@          INCLUDE(WRITE\SNAP);@A@@@@             DISPLAY('CKGLWR',UY
)@@G@@0);   @#@@@@          RESUME; @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" OPEN OUTPUT TO CHECKPOUZ
)@@G@@INT FILE.   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          CKPT\IMAGE\PTR := ALLOCATE\CORE(VA
)@@G@@1+MAX\DATA\IMAGE);@E@@@@          CKPT\PKT := NULL\PTR; " SO FILE WILL IVB
)@@G@@NITIALIZE   @F@@@@          INITIALIZE\FILE( %CKPT\PKT , %CKPT\IMAGE\PTRVC
)@@G@@ , 0 );     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" WRITE CHECKPOINT OF FWD REF SYMBOLS.    VD
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@          WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CTYP\GLOBAL,0); " WRITE SYMVE
)@@G@@BOL HEADER  @E@@@@          WRITE\FRV\CKPT(GLOBAL\SYMBOLS); " CHECKPOINTVF
)@@G@@ FRVS @E@@@@          WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CTYP\END,0); " WRITE END IMAGE   VG
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@" WRITE CHECKPOINT OF COMMAND SYMBOLS.    @[@@@@"     VH
)@@G@@@F@@@@          WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CTYP\COMMAND,0); " WRITE SYMBOL HEADER VI
)@@G@@@D@@@@          WRITE\COMMAND\CKPT(COMMAND\SYMBOLS); " TEMP @E@@@@      VJ
)@@G@@    WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CTYP\END,0); " WRITE END IMAGE   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@VK
)@@G@@" CLOSE AND UPDATE CHECKPOINT.@[@@@@"     @C@@@@          CLOSE\FILE(CKPVL
)@@G@@T\PKT); " CLOSE FILE    @G@@@@          HEADER\GLOBAL\CKPT :=: START\DRUVM
)@@G@@M\ADDR(CKPT\PKT); " SWITCH    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THE FOLLOWING CODE MAYVN
)@@G@@ BE ENABLED WHEN THE RELEASE\FILE   @^@@@@" ROUTINE IS WRITTEN.   @[@@@@VO
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@"         IF START\DRUM\ADDR(CKPT\PKT) NE 0 THEN@A@@@@"     VP
)@@G@@       RELEASE\FILE(CKPT\PKT);@[@@@@"     @D@@@@          RELEASE\CORE(CVQ
)@@G@@KPT\PKT); " RELEASE PACKET    @^@@@@END; " WRITE\GLOBAL\CKPT@[@@@@"     VR
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" WRITE CHECKPOINT OF FORWARD REFERENCE VARIABLES (FRVVS
)@@G@@S)    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\FRV\CKPT(NODE: MACHINE POINTER) VT
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          IF (NODE NE NULL\PTR) THEN@C@@@@           BVU
)@@G@@EGIN " TO 'VISIT' THIS VARIABLE     @E@@@@             WRITE\FRV\CKPT( SVV
)@@G@@LLK(NODE) ); " DO LEFT SUBTREE@D@@@@             IF DREF(NODE) THEN " ITVW
)@@G@@ IS FWD REF SYMBOL@D@@@@              BEGIN " TO CREATE CHECKPOINT FOR SVX
)@@G@@YMBOL @F@@@@                WRITE\SYMBOL\CKPT(NODE); " WRITE SYMBOL NAMEVY
)@@G@@ INFO @D@@@@              END; " CREATING CHECKPOINT FOR VARIABLE @E@@@@VZ
)@@G@@             WRITE\FRV\CKPT( SRLK(NODE) ); " DO RITE SUBTREE@A@@@@      WA
)@@G@@     END; " OF 'VISITING' NODE@^@@@@END; " WRITE\FRV\CKPT   @[@@@@"     WB
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@" WRITE CHECKPOINT OF COMMAND SYMBOLS     @[@@@@"     WC
)@@G@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\COMMAND\CKPT(NODE: MACHINE POINTER)   @[@@@@BEGIN WD
)@@G@@@A@@@@          IF (NODE NE NULL\PTR) THEN@C@@@@           BEGIN " TO 'VWE
)@@G@@ISIT' THIS VARIABLE     @G@@@@             WRITE\COMMAND\CKPT( SLLK(NODEWF
)@@G@@) ); " VISIT LEFT SUBTREE     @F@@@@             WRITE\SYMBOL\CKPT(NODE)WG
)@@G@@; " WRITE SYMBOL NAME INFO    @G@@@@             WRITE\COMMAND\CKPT( SRLWH
)@@G@@K(NODE) ); " VISIT RITE SUBTREE     @A@@@@           END; " OF 'VISITINGWI
)@@G@@' NODE@ @@@@END; " WRITE\COMMAND\CKPT     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@WJ
)@@G@@"     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED AT UNIT BREAKS TO TAKWK
)@@G@@E A UNIT CHECKPOINT     @B@@@@" OF ALL NON-FORWARD-REFERENCE SYMBOLS.   WL
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\UNIT\CKPT EXPORTED ('CKUNWR')   @E@@@@WM
)@@G@@          RESULT INTEGER WORD " DRUM ADDRESS OF CHECKPOINT  @[@@@@BEGIN WN
)@@G@@@E@@@@DECLARE   UNIT\CKPT: INTEGER WORD; " DRUM ADDRESS OF CKPT   @[@@@@WO
)@@G@@"     @ @@@@          INCLUDE(WRITE\SNAP);@A@@@@             DISPLAY('CKWP
)@@G@@UNWR',0);   @#@@@@          RESUME; @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" OPEN CHECKPOINT WQ
)@@G@@FILE. @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          UNIT\CKPT := 0; " CLEAR IT@E@@@@      WR
)@@G@@    CKPT\IMAGE\PTR := ALLOCATE\CORE(1+MAX\DATA\IMAGE);@E@@@@          CKWS
)@@G@@PT\PKT := NULL\PTR; " SO FILE WILL INITIALIZE   @F@@@@          INITIALIWT
)@@G@@ZE\FILE( %CKPT\PKT , %CKPT\IMAGE\PTR , 0 );     @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" WRITWU
)@@G@@E CHECKPOINT OF UNIT COMMON VARIABLES.    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          WRWV
)@@G@@ITE\UNIT\COMMON;  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" WRITE CHECKPOINT OF ACTION TABLE. WW
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@          WRITE\ACTION\CKPT;  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" WRITWX
)@@G@@E CHECKPOINT OF NON-FRV SYMBOLS.    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@          WRITE\CKWY
)@@G@@PT\IMAGE(CTYP\GLOBAL,0); " WRITE SYMBOL HEADER  @G@@@@          WRITE\NOWZ
)@@G@@N\FRV\CKPT(GLOBAL\SYMBOLS); " CHECKPOINT NON FRVS     @E@@@@          WRXA
)@@G@@ITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CTYP\END,0); " WRITE END IMAGE   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" CLOSXB
)@@G@@E AND UPDATE CHECKPOINT.@[@@@@"     @C@@@@          CLOSE\FILE(CKPT\PKT)XC
)@@G@@; " CLOSE FILE    @F@@@@          UNIT\CKPT := START\DRUM\ADDR(CKPT\PKT)XD
)@@G@@; " GET ADDRESS   @D@@@@          RELEASE\CORE(CKPT\PKT); " RELEASE PACKXE
)@@G@@ET    @B@@@@          RETURN(UNIT\CKPT); " TO CALLER  @^@@@@END; " WRITEXF
)@@G@@\UNIT\CKPT  @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" WRITE CHECKPOINT OF NON FORWXG
)@@G@@ARD REFERENCE VARIABLES @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\NON\FRV\CKPT(NXH
)@@G@@ODE: MACHINE POINTER)   @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          IF (NODE NE NULL\PTRXI
)@@G@@) THEN@C@@@@           BEGIN " TO 'VISIT' THIS VARIABLE     @G@@@@      XJ
)@@G@@       WRITE\NON\FRV\CKPT( SLLK(NODE) ); " VISIT LEFT SUBTREE     @E@@@@XK
)@@G@@             IF NOT DREF(NODE) THEN " IF NOT FWD REF SYMBOL @F@@@@      XL
)@@G@@          WRITE\SYMBOL\CKPT(NODE); " WRITE SYMBOL NAME INFO @G@@@@      XM
)@@G@@       WRITE\NON\FRV\CKPT( SRLK(NODE) ); " VISIT RITE SUBTREE     @A@@@@XN
)@@G@@           END; " OF 'VISITING' NODE@ @@@@END; " WRITE\NON\FRV\CKPT     XO
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @ @@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\UNIT\COMMON   @[@@@@BEGIN XP
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @A@@@@" WRITE SINGLE INTEGER VARIABLES.   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@XQ
)@@G@@          WRITE\UHDR\INT(CTYP\PAGE,PAGE\NUMBER);@B@@@@          WRITE\UHXR
)@@G@@DR\INT(CTYP\FONT,FONT); @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\INT(CTYP\HEADL,HEADINXS
)@@G@@G\LENGTH);  @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\INT(CTYP\FOOTL,FOOTING\LENGTH);  XT
)@@G@@@D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\INT(CTYP\CHTHI,CHARS\THIS\LINE); @D@@@@      XU
)@@G@@    WRITE\UHDR\INT(CTYP\CHNXT,CHARS\NEXT\LINE); @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" WRITXV
)@@G@@E SINGLE DISTANCE VARIABLES.  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DSTXW
)@@G@@(CTYP\PTSIZE,TYPESIZE\WIDTH); @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\PAGWIDXX
)@@G@@,PAGE\WIDTH);     @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\PAGHIT,PAGE\HEIGHTXY
)@@G@@);    @C@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\LEAD,LEADING);    @D@@@@      XZ
)@@G@@    WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\SPREM,SPACE\REMAINING); @E@@@@          WRITE\UHYA
)@@G@@DR\DST(CTYP\VPOSN,VERTICAL\POSITION);     @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" WRITE CONDYB
)@@G@@ITION VARIABLES.  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\LFLAG,YC
)@@G@@LEFT\FLAG); @E@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\NUMBOT,NUMBER\BOTTOM\OF\YD
)@@G@@PAGE);@E@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\EDCHAP,EDIT\CHAP\NUMBER);     YE
)@@G@@@E@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\STPAGE,START\PAGE\NUMBERING); @D@@@@YF
)@@G@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\ODDPAG,ODD\PAGE\FACING);@D@@@@          WRYG
)@@G@@ITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\HEADC,CENTER\HEADING);  @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CNDYH
)@@G@@(CTYP\FOOTC,CENTER\FOOTING);  @E@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\HEADR,YI
)@@G@@HEADING\REQUESTED);     @E@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\FOOTR,FOOTINYJ
)@@G@@G\REQUESTED);     @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" WRITE MULTI-WORD VARIABLES. @[@@@@YK
)@@G@@"     @F@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CKPT(CTYP\CHAP,9,LOC(CHAPTER\NUMBER(1))YL
)@@G@@);    @G@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CKPT(CTYP\HEADT,MAX\HDG\WORDS,LOC(HEADIYM
)@@G@@NG\CORE));  @G@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CKPT(CTYP\FOOTT,MAX\HDG\WORDS,LOCYN
)@@G@@(FOOTING\CORE));  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" FOR CHECKPOINTING AREA PARAMETERS YO
)@@G@@MAKE SURE THAT CURRENT  @A@@@@" OUTPUT IS GOING TO THE TEXT AREA. @[@@@@YP
)@@G@@"     @C@@@@          IF (AREA\TYPE NE TEXT) THEN ERROR;    @F@@@@      YQ
)@@G@@    IF (BUFFER\TEXT OR INHIBIT\DISTRIBUTION) THEN ERROR;    @[@@@@"     YR
)@@G@@@C@@@@" WRITE CHECKPOINT OF AREA-BASED UNIT ITEMS.    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@YS
)@@G@@" WRITE SINGLE INTEGER VARIABLES.   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          WRITE\UHYT
)@@G@@DR\INT(CTYP\COLNM,COLUMN\NUMBER);   @E@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\INT(CTYP\YU
)@@G@@COLNT,NUMBER\OF\COLUMNS);     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" WRITE SINGLE DISTANCE YV
)@@G@@VARIABLES.  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\GUTRW,GUTTERYW
)@@G@@\WIDTH);    @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\LINDE,LEFT\INDENT);     YX
)@@G@@@D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\RINDE,RIGHT\INDENT);    @C@@@@      YY
)@@G@@    WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\AVPOS,AREA\VPOS); @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DSTYZ
)@@G@@(CTYP\AREAHT,AREA\HEIGHT);    @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\AREAWDZA
)@@G@@,AREA\WIDTH);     @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\ARVPOS,AREA\REL\VPZB
)@@G@@OS);  @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\AVPOSS,AREA\VPOS\START);@D@@@@ZC
)@@G@@          WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\LFTOFF,LEFT\OFFSET);    @D@@@@          WRZD
)@@G@@ITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\TOPMAR,TOP\MARGIN);     @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DSTZE
)@@G@@(CTYP\BOTMAR,BOTTOM\MARGIN);  @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\LFTMARZF
)@@G@@,LEFT\MARGIN);    @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\DST(CTYP\RGTMAR,RIGHT\MARGIZG
)@@G@@N);   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" WRITE SINGLE CONDITIONS.    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@ZH
)@@G@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\BALFL,BALANCING); @C@@@@          WRITE\UHZI
)@@G@@DR\CND(CTYP\CENFL,CENTER);    @C@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\COMFL,ZJ
)@@G@@COMPACT);   @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\DISFL,DISTRIBUTION);    ZK
)@@G@@@B@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\FILFL,FILL);@C@@@@          WRITE\UHZL
)@@G@@DR\CND(CTYP\HYPFL,HYPHEN);    @C@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\JUSFL,ZM
)@@G@@JUSTIFY);   @E@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\JUSTRT,JUSTIFY\FROM\RIGHZN
)@@G@@T);   @C@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\NOSFL,NOSPACE);   @C@@@@      ZO
)@@G@@    WRITE\UHDR\CND(CTYP\RITEF,RIGHTF);    @D@@@@          WRITE\UHDR\CNDZP
)@@G@@(CTYP\UNDOT,AREA\UNDERLINE);  @^@@@@END; " WRITE\UNIT\COMMON@#@@@@CONTROZQ
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO ZR
)@@G@@WRITE A CHECKPOINT IMAGE FOR  @A@@@@" THE NAMED SYMBOL PASSED IN NODE.  ZS
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\SYMBOL\CKPT(NODE: MACHINE POINTER)    ZT
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   SNAME\PTR: MACHINE POINTER; " TO SYMBOL NAMEZU
)@@G@@@F@@@@DECLARE   SNAME(1): INTEGER WORD BASED(SNAME\PTR); " SYMBOL NAME  ZV
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@          CKPT\DESC(1) := 0;  @ @@@@          CKPT\DESZW
)@@G@@C(2) := 0;  @D@@@@          CKPT\DTYP := DTYP(NODE); " COPY ALL FIELDS  ZX
)@@G@@@A@@@@          CKPT\DSBT := DSBT(NODE);  @A@@@@          CKPT\DCTL := DZY
)@@G@@CTL(NODE);  @A@@@@          CKPT\STYP := STYP(NODE);  @A@@@@          CKZZ
)@@G@@PT\SLEN := SLEN(NODE);  @A@@@@          CKPT\DLEN := DLEN(NODE);  @E@@@@AA
)@@G@@          SNAME\PTR := LOC( SNAM(NODE) ); " SET NAME POINTER@B@@@@      AB
)@@G@@    FOR I := 1 TO SLEN(NODE) DO     @D@@@@             CKPT\NAME(I) := SAC
)@@G@@NAME(I); " COPY NAME    @G@@@@          WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CTYP\SYMBOL,SLEAD
)@@G@@N(NODE)+2); " WRITE IMAGE     @D@@@@          CASEENTRY DTYP(NODE) " WHAAE
)@@G@@T IS DATA TYPE    @A@@@@          CASE TYPNUL: BEGIN END;   @A@@@@      AF
)@@G@@    CASE TYPINT,TYPDST,TYPSTR:@F@@@@             WRITE\DATA\CKPT( DESC\DAG
)@@G@@ATA\LEN(NODE) , DADR(NODE) ); @^@@@@          CASE TYPTAB:  @ @@@@      AH
)@@G@@     BEGIN " TO DO TABLE@F@@@@             WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CTYP\TABLE,0AI
)@@G@@); " WRITE SYMBOL HEADER@D@@@@             WRITE\NODE\CKPT( DADR(NODE) ,AJ
)@@G@@ TRUE );    @E@@@@             WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CTYP\END,0); " WRITE ENDAK
)@@G@@ IMAGE@ @@@@           END; " OF TABLE    @#@@@@          CASE *: @#@@@@AL
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             PDISPLAY('CKWR01',NODE);     @^@@@@AM
)@@G@@             ERROR;     @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@          ENDCASE;AN
)@@G@@@^@@@@END; " WRITE\SYMBOL\CKPT@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" WRITE CHECAO
)@@G@@KPOINT OF NODES IN A TABLE    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\NODE\CKPAP
)@@G@@T(NODE: MACHINE POINTER @C@@@@                         ,DO\ALL: CONDITIOAQ
)@@G@@N)    @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          IF (NODE NE NULL\PTR) THEN@C@@@@      AR
)@@G@@     BEGIN " TO 'VISIT' THIS VARIABLE     @H@@@@             WRITE\NODE\AS
)@@G@@CKPT( SLLK(NODE) , DO\ALL ); " VISIT LEFT SUBTREE     @D@@@@            AT
)@@G@@ IF DO\ALL " OR ( SMAD(NODE) NE 0 ) " THEN@B@@@@                WRITE\SYAU
)@@G@@MBOL\CKPT(NODE);  @H@@@@             WRITE\NODE\CKPT( SRLK(NODE) , DO\ALAV
)@@G@@L ); " VISIT RITE SUBTREE     @A@@@@           END; " OF 'VISITING' NODEAW
)@@G@@@^@@@@END; " WRITE\NODE\CKPT  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@AX
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO WRITE A CHECKPOINT OF THE DATAAY
)@@G@@@#@@@@" IN A VARIABLE.  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\DATA\CKPT     AZ
)@@G@@@D@@@@             (DATA\LEN: INTEGER WORD " LENGTH OF DATA @E@@@@      BA
)@@G@@       ,DATA\ADR: MACHINE POINTER) " LOCATION OF DATA @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@BB
)@@G@@DECLARE   DATA\PTR: MACHINE POINTER; " TO DATA WORD   @F@@@@DECLARE   DABC
)@@G@@TA: INTEGER WORD BASED(DATA\PTR); " DATA TO BE CKPTED @F@@@@DECLARE   LABD
)@@G@@ST\IMAGE\LEN: INTEGER WORD; " LENGTH OF LAST IMAGE    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@BE
)@@G@@          DATA\PTR := DATA\ADR; " START AT ADDRESS PASSED   @[@@@@"     BF
)@@G@@@E@@@@" FIRST OUTPUT THE NUMBER OF LONG IMAGES NEEDED TO DUMP MOST@^@@@@BG
)@@G@@" OF THE DATA ITEM.     @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          FOR I := 1 TO DATA\LBH
)@@G@@EN // MAX\DATA\IMAGE DO @B@@@@           BEGIN " TO OUTPUT LONG IMAGE   BI
)@@G@@@C@@@@             FOR J := 1 TO MAX\DATA\IMAGE DO    @A@@@@            BJ
)@@G@@  BEGIN " TO COPY A WORD@B@@@@                CKPT\DATA\INT(J) := DATA; BK
)@@G@@@B@@@@                DATA\PTR := DATA\PTR + 1; @A@@@@              END;BL
)@@G@@ " OF COPYING WORD@E@@@@             WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CTYP\DATA,MAX\DATABM
)@@G@@\IMAGE);    @B@@@@           END; " OF OUTPUTING LONG IMAGE @[@@@@"     BN
)@@G@@@B@@@@" IF ANY MORE TO DO OUTPUT SHORT IMAGE.   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@      BO
)@@G@@    LAST\IMAGE\LEN := MOD(DATA\LEN,MAX\DATA\IMAGE);   @B@@@@          IFBP
)@@G@@ (LAST\IMAGE\LEN) GT 0 THEN   @B@@@@           BEGIN " TO OUTPUT LAST IMBQ
)@@G@@AGE   @C@@@@             FOR J := 1 TO LAST\IMAGE\LEN DO    @A@@@@      BR
)@@G@@        BEGIN " TO COPY A WORD@B@@@@                CKPT\DATA\INT(J) := BS
)@@G@@DATA; @B@@@@                DATA\PTR := DATA\PTR + 1; @B@@@@            BT
)@@G@@  END; " OF COPYING A WORD    @E@@@@             WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CTYP\DBU
)@@G@@ATA,LAST\IMAGE\LEN);    @C@@@@           END; " OF OUTPUTTING LAST DATA BV
)@@G@@IMAGE @^@@@@END; " WRITE\DATA\CKPT  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     BW
)@@G@@@E@@@@" WRITE A CHECKPOINT OF THE ACTION TABLE (EQUATES ET AL).   @[@@@@BX
)@@G@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\ACTION\CKPT   @[@@@@BEGIN @F@@@@          WRBY
)@@G@@ITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CTYP\ACTION,0); " BEGIN ACTION CKPT    @A@@@@          FOBZ
)@@G@@R ICHAR := 1 TO 256 DO  @ @@@@           BEGIN " DUMP INDEX @C@@@@      CA
)@@G@@       IF ACTION(ICHAR) NE NULL\PTR THEN  @G@@@@                WRITE\ACCB
)@@G@@TION\TREE(ACTION(ICHAR)); " DUMP NORMAL ACTIONS @D@@@@             IF PECC
)@@G@@QU\ACTION(ICHAR) NE NULL\PTR THEN   @H@@@@                WRITE\ACTION\TCD
)@@G@@REE(PEQU\ACTION(ICHAR)); " DUMP PEQU ACTIONS    @ @@@@           END; " CE
)@@G@@DUMP INDEX  @E@@@@          WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CTYP\END,0); " END ACTION CCF
)@@G@@KPT   @^@@@@END; " WRITE\ACTION\CKPT@[@@@@"     @A@@@@" WRITE A SINGLE ACG
)@@G@@CTION TABLE NODE. @C@@@@" WRITE ACTION TABLE TREE TO CHECKPOINT FILE.   CH
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\ACTION\TREE(NODE: MACHINE POINTER)    CI
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          IF (NODE NE NULL\PTR) THEN@ @@@@           BCJ
)@@G@@EGIN " DUMP NODE  @F@@@@             WRITE\ACTION\TREE( SLLK(NODE) ); " CK
)@@G@@VISIT LEFT SUBTREE@G@@@@             IF DCTL(NODE) NE PUT\CTL THEN " DONCL
)@@G@@T CHECKPOINT KLUGES     @E@@@@                WRITE\SYMBOL\CKPT(NODE); "CM
)@@G@@ DUMP NODE VALUE  @G@@@@             WRITE\ACTION\TREE( SRLK(NODE) ); " CN
)@@G@@VISIT RIGHT SUBTREE     @ @@@@           END; " DUMP NODE   @^@@@@END; "CO
)@@G@@ WRITE\ACTION\TREE@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@CP
)@@G@@" WRITE ONE INTEGER WORD FROM ARGUMENT.   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE WRCQ
)@@G@@ITE\UHDR\INT@E@@@@             (CKPT\ID: INTEGER WORD " ID FOR CHECKPOINCR
)@@G@@T     @D@@@@             ,DATA\WORD: INTEGER WORD " DATA TO WRITE @#@@@@CS
)@@G@@             )    @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@          CKPT\DATA\INT(1) := DATA\WCT
)@@G@@ORD; " SET DATA WORD    @D@@@@          WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CKPT\ID,1); " OCU
)@@G@@NE WORD     @B@@@@"         ODISPLAY('WUHINT',DATA\WORD);   @^@@@@END; "CV
)@@G@@ WRITE\UHDR\INT   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" WRITE ONE DISTANCE WORCW
)@@G@@D FROM ARGUMENT.  @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\UHDR\DST@E@@@@      CX
)@@G@@       (CKPT\ID: INTEGER WORD " ID FOR CHECKPOINT     @D@@@@            CY
)@@G@@ ,DATA\WORD: DISTANCE " DATA TO WRITE     @#@@@@             )    @[@@@@CZ
)@@G@@BEGIN @E@@@@          CKPT\DATA\DST(1) := DATA\WORD; " SET DATA WORD    DA
)@@G@@@D@@@@          WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CKPT\ID,1); " ONE WORD     @B@@@@"     DB
)@@G@@    ODISPLAY('WUHDST',DATA\WORD);   @^@@@@END; " WRITE\UHDR\DST   @[@@@@DC
)@@G@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" WRITE ONE CONDITION WORD FROM ARGUMENT. @[@@@@DD
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\UHDR\CND@E@@@@             (CKPT\ID: INTEGERDE
)@@G@@ WORD " ID FOR CHECKPOINT     @E@@@@             ,DATA\WORD: WORD CONDITDF
)@@G@@ION " DATA TO WRITE     @#@@@@             )    @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@      DG
)@@G@@    CKPT\DATA\CND(1) := DATA\WORD; " SET DATA WORD    @D@@@@          WRDH
)@@G@@ITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CKPT\ID,1); " ONE WORD     @B@@@@"         ODISPLAY('WUHCDI
)@@G@@ND',DATA\WORD);   @^@@@@END; " WRITE\UHDR\CND   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     DJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@" WRITE CONSTANT AMOUNT OF DATA FROM DBANK.  NOTE THAT IT MUST    DK
)@@G@@@^@@@@" FIT IN ONE DATA IMAGE.@[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\UHDR\CKPDL
)@@G@@T(CKPT\ID: INTEGER WORD " IMAGE TYPE@F@@@@                         ,DATADM
)@@G@@\LEN: INTEGER WORD " LENGTH IN WORDS@F@@@@                         ,DATADN
)@@G@@\ADR: MACHINE POINTER) " ADDRESS    @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@DECLARE   DATA(1):DO
)@@G@@ INTEGER WORD BASED(DATA\ADR);@[@@@@"     @A@@@@          FOR I := 1 TO DP
)@@G@@DATA\LEN DO @F@@@@             CKPT\DATA\INT(I) := DATA(I); " COPY DATA DQ
)@@G@@TO IMAGE    @C@@@@          WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE(CKPT\ID,DATA\LEN);   @^@@@@DR
)@@G@@END; " WRITE\UHDR\CKPT  @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IDS
)@@G@@S CALLED TO WRITE THE CHECKPOINT IMAGE    @ @@@@" INTO THE CHECKPOINT FIDT
)@@G@@LE.   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE WRITE\CKPT\IMAGE    @F@@@@            DU
)@@G@@ (CKPT\ID: INTEGER WORD " TYPE OF CHECKPOINT IMAGE    @F@@@@            DV
)@@G@@ ,DATA\LEN: INTEGER WORD) " LENGTH OF DATA (IN WORDS) @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@DW
)@@G@@          CKPT\TYPE := CKPT\ID;     @C@@@@          CKPT\SPARE := 0; " CDX
)@@G@@LEAR SPARE FIELD  @F@@@@          IF (DATA\LEN GT MAX\DATA\IMAGE) THEN EDY
)@@G@@RROR; " $$$DEBUG  @ @@@@          INCLUDE(WRITE\SNAP);@D@@@@            DZ
)@@G@@ SNAP('CKPTWR',DATA\LEN+1,CKPT\IMAGE\PTR);@#@@@@          RESUME; @D@@@@EA
)@@G@@          WRITE\FILE(CKPT\PKT , 4*(DATA\LEN+1) );     @^@@@@END; " WRITEEB
)@@G@@\CKPT\IMAGE @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THISEC
)@@G@@ PROCEDURE IS CALLED WHEN DPS SIGNS ON, ITS FUNCTION IS TO  @F@@@@" READED
)@@G@@ IN THE GLOBAL CHECKPOINT AND INITIALIZE THE SYMBOL TABLE.  @[@@@@"     EE
)@@G@@@C@@@@PROCEDURE READ\GLOBAL\CKPT EXPORTED ('CKGLRD')  @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@EF
)@@G@@"     @ @@@@          INCLUDE(READ\SNAP); @A@@@@             DISPLAY('CKEG
)@@G@@GLRD',0);   @#@@@@          RESUME; @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          IF (HEADEH
)@@G@@ER\GLOBAL\CKPT NE 0) THEN     @C@@@@             READ\CKPT(HEADER\GLOBALEI
)@@G@@\CKPT);     @ @@@@END; " READ\GLOBAL\CHECKPOINT @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     EJ
)@@G@@@^@@@@" READ UNIT CHECKPOINT. @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE READ\UNIT\CKPTEK
)@@G@@(UNIT: INTEGER WORD) EXPORTED('CKUNRD')   @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   ADEL
)@@G@@DRESS: INTEGER WORD; " ADDRESS OF CKPT    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@          INEM
)@@G@@CLUDE(READ\SNAP); @A@@@@             DISPLAY('CKUNRD',0);   @#@@@@      EN
)@@G@@    RESUME; @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          ADDRESS := GET\DIRECTORY\CKPT\ADEO
)@@G@@DRESS(UNIT);@A@@@@          IF (ADDRESS NE 0) THEN    @D@@@@            EP
)@@G@@ READ\CKPT(ADDRESS); " READ UNIT CKPT     @^@@@@END; " READ\UNIT\CKPT   EQ
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IER
)@@G@@S CALLED TO READ ANY TYPE OF CHECKPOINT.  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE REES
)@@G@@AD\CKPT(ADDRESS: INTEGER WORD) " DRUM ADDRESS OF CKPT @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@ET
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" FOR CHECKPOINTING AREA PARAMETERS MAKE SURE THAT CURRENT  EU
)@@G@@@A@@@@" OUTPUT IS GOING TO THE TEXT AREA. @[@@@@"     @C@@@@          IFEV
)@@G@@ (AREA\TYPE NE TEXT) THEN ERROR;    @F@@@@          IF (BUFFER\TEXT OR IEW
)@@G@@NHIBIT\DISTRIBUTION) THEN ERROR;    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          CKPT\IMAEX
)@@G@@GE\PTR := ALLOCATE\CORE(1+MAX\DATA\IMAGE);@D@@@@          CKPT\PKT := NUEY
)@@G@@LL\PTR; " SO ALLOCATED BY FILE@G@@@@          INITIALIZE\FILE( %CKPT\PKTEZ
)@@G@@ , %CKPT\IMAGE\PTR , ADDRESS );     @D@@@@          READ\CKPT\IMAGE; " RFA
)@@G@@EAD THE FIRST IMAGE IN  @B@@@@          WHILE NOT END\FILE(CKPT\PKT) DO FB
)@@G@@@A@@@@           BEGIN " TO LOOK AT IMAGE @C@@@@             CASEENTRY CFC
)@@G@@KPT\TYPE " WHAT TYPE    @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\GLOBAL:@F@@@@      FD
)@@G@@          GLOBAL\SYMBOLS := READ\TREE\CKPT(GLOBAL\SYMBOLS); @A@@@@      FE
)@@G@@       CASE CTYP\COMMAND:     @G@@@@                COMMAND\SYMBOLS := RFF
)@@G@@EAD\TREE\CKPT(COMMAND\SYMBOLS);     @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\ACTION:FG
)@@G@@@A@@@@                READ\ACTION\CKPT;   @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\PFH
)@@G@@AGE:  @C@@@@                PAGE\NUMBER := READ\UHDR\INT;   @ @@@@      FI
)@@G@@       CASE CTYP\FONT:  @B@@@@                FONT := READ\UHDR\INT;    FJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@             CASE CTYP\HEADL: @C@@@@                HEADING\LENGTHFK
)@@G@@ := READ\UHDR\INT;@ @@@@             CASE CTYP\FOOTL: @C@@@@            FL
)@@G@@    FOOTING\LENGTH := READ\UHDR\INT;@ @@@@             CASE CTYP\CHTHI: FM
)@@G@@@D@@@@                CHARS\THIS\LINE := READ\UHDR\INT;     @ @@@@      FN
)@@G@@       CASE CTYP\CHNXT: @D@@@@                CHARS\NEXT\LINE := READ\UHFO
)@@G@@DR\INT;     @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\LFLAG: @C@@@@                LEFP
)@@G@@FT\FLAG := READ\UHDR\CND;     @[@@@@"     @]@@@@" DISTANCES @[@@@@"     FQ
)@@G@@@ @@@@             CASE CTYP\SPREM: @D@@@@                SPACE\REMAININFR
)@@G@@G := READ\UHDR\DST;     @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\PTSIZE:@C@@@@      FS
)@@G@@          TYPESIZE\WIDTH := READ\UHDR\DST;@ @@@@             CASE CTYP\PFT
)@@G@@AGWID:@C@@@@                PAGE\WIDTH := READ\UHDR\DST;    @ @@@@      FU
)@@G@@       CASE CTYP\PAGHIT:@C@@@@                PAGE\HEIGHT := READ\UHDR\DFV
)@@G@@ST;   @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\LEAD:  @B@@@@                LEADING FW
)@@G@@:= READ\UHDR\DST; @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\VPOSN: @D@@@@            FX
)@@G@@    SET\VERTICAL\POSITION(READ\UHDR\DST); @[@@@@"     @]@@@@" CONDITIONSFY
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\NUMBOT:@E@@@@                NUFZ
)@@G@@MBER\BOTTOM\OF\PAGE := READ\UHDR\CND;     @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\EGA
)@@G@@DCHAP:@D@@@@                EDIT\CHAP\NUMBER := READ\UHDR\CND;    @ @@@@GB
)@@G@@             CASE CTYP\STPAGE:@D@@@@                START\PAGE\NUMBERINGGC
)@@G@@ := READ\UHDR\CND;@ @@@@             CASE CTYP\ODDPAG:@D@@@@            GD
)@@G@@    ODD\PAGE\FACING := READ\UHDR\CND;     @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\HGE
)@@G@@EADC: @C@@@@                CENTER\HEADING := READ\UHDR\CND;@ @@@@      GF
)@@G@@       CASE CTYP\FOOTC: @C@@@@                CENTER\FOOTING := READ\UHDGG
)@@G@@R\CND;@ @@@@             CASE CTYP\HEADR: @D@@@@                HEADING\GH
)@@G@@REQUESTED := READ\UHDR\CND;   @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\FOOTR: @D@@@@GI
)@@G@@                FOOTING\REQUESTED := READ\UHDR\CND;   @[@@@@"     @#@@@@GJ
)@@G@@" MULTI-WORD DATA.@[@@@@"     @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\HEADT: @F@@@@GK
)@@G@@                READ\UHDR\CKPT(MAX\HDG\WORDS,LOC(HEADING\CORE));  @ @@@@GL
)@@G@@             CASE CTYP\FOOTT: @F@@@@                READ\UHDR\CKPT(MAX\HGM
)@@G@@DG\WORDS,LOC(FOOTING\CORE));  @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\CHAP:  @E@@@@GN
)@@G@@                READ\UHDR\CKPT(9,LOC(CHAPTER\NUMBER(1)));   @[@@@@"     GO
)@@G@@@#@@@@" THINGS IN AREAS @[@@@@"     @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\COLNM: GP
)@@G@@@C@@@@                COLUMN\NUMBER := READ\UHDR\INT; @ @@@@            GQ
)@@G@@ CASE CTYP\COLNT: @D@@@@                NUMBER\OF\COLUMNS := READ\UHDR\IGR
)@@G@@NT;   @[@@@@"     @]@@@@" DISTANCES @[@@@@"     @ @@@@             CASE GS
)@@G@@CTYP\GUTRW: @C@@@@                GUTTER\WIDTH := READ\UHDR\DST;  @ @@@@GT
)@@G@@             CASE CTYP\LINDE: @C@@@@                LEFT\INDENT := READ\GU
)@@G@@UHDR\DST;   @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\RINDE: @C@@@@                RIGV
)@@G@@GHT\INDENT := READ\UHDR\DST;  @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\AVPOS: @C@@@@GW
)@@G@@                SET\AREA\VPOS(READ\UHDR\DST);   @ @@@@             CASE GX
)@@G@@CTYP\AREAHT:@C@@@@                AREA\HEIGHT := READ\UHDR\DST;   @ @@@@GY
)@@G@@             CASE CTYP\AREAWD:@C@@@@                AREA\WIDTH := READ\UGZ
)@@G@@HDR\DST;    @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\ARVPOS:@D@@@@                SEHA
)@@G@@T\AREA\REL\VPOS(READ\UHDR\DST);     @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\AVPOSS:HB
)@@G@@@D@@@@                AREA\VPOS\START := READ\UHDR\DST;     @ @@@@      HC
)@@G@@       CASE CTYP\LFTOFF:@C@@@@                LEFT\OFFSET := READ\UHDR\DHD
)@@G@@ST;   @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\TOPMAR:@C@@@@                TOP\MARGHE
)@@G@@IN := READ\UHDR\DST;    @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\BOTMAR:@C@@@@      HF
)@@G@@          BOTTOM\MARGIN := READ\UHDR\DST; @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\LHG
)@@G@@FTMAR:@C@@@@                LEFT\MARGIN := READ\UHDR\DST;   @ @@@@      HH
)@@G@@       CASE CTYP\RGTMAR:@C@@@@                RIGHT\MARGIN := READ\UHDR\HI
)@@G@@DST;  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" SINGLE CONDITION VARIABLES. @[@@@@"     @ @@@@HJ
)@@G@@             CASE CTYP\BALFL: @C@@@@                BALANCING := READ\UHHK
)@@G@@DR\CND;     @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\CENFL: @B@@@@                CEHL
)@@G@@NTER := READ\UHDR\CND;  @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\COMFL: @B@@@@      HM
)@@G@@          COMPACT := READ\UHDR\CND; @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\DISFL: HN
)@@G@@@C@@@@                DISTRIBUTION := READ\UHDR\CND;  @ @@@@            HO
)@@G@@ CASE CTYP\FILFL: @B@@@@                FILL := READ\UHDR\CND;    @ @@@@HP
)@@G@@             CASE CTYP\HYPFL: @B@@@@                HYPHEN := READ\UHDR\HQ
)@@G@@CND;  @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\JUSFL: @B@@@@                JUSTIFY HR
)@@G@@:= READ\UHDR\CND; @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\JUSTRT:@D@@@@            HS
)@@G@@    JUSTIFY\FROM\RIGHT := READ\UHDR\CND;  @ @@@@             CASE CTYP\NHT
)@@G@@OSFL: @B@@@@                NOSPACE := READ\UHDR\CND; @ @@@@            HU
)@@G@@ CASE CTYP\RITEF: @B@@@@                RIGHTF := READ\UHDR\CND;  @ @@@@HV
)@@G@@             CASE CTYP\UNDOT: @C@@@@                AREA\UNDERLINE := REHW
)@@G@@AD\UHDR\CND;@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" THE ALTERNATIVE CASE CAUSES AN INTERNAL HX
)@@G@@ERROR.@[@@@@"     @^@@@@             CASE *:    @A@@@@              BEGIHY
)@@G@@N " ERROR HANDLING@E@@@@                PDISPLAY('CKRD01',CKPT\PKT); " DHZ
)@@G@@IAGNOSE     @^@@@@                ERROR;  @A@@@@              END; " ERRIA
)@@G@@OR HANDLING @^@@@@             ENDCASE;   @B@@@@           END; " OF LOOIB
)@@G@@KING AT IMAGE     @C@@@@          CLOSE\FILE(CKPT\PKT); " CLOSE FILE    IC
)@@G@@@C@@@@          RELEASE\CORE(CKPT\PKT); " RELEASE CORE@E@@@@          SEID
)@@G@@T\ALL\AREA\LINE\WIDTHS; " DO THE RIGHT THING    @#@@@@END; " READ\CKPT  IE
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO IF
)@@G@@READ CHECKPOINTS OF AN ARBITRARY    @D@@@@" TABLE, WHICH IS PASSED AND RIG
)@@G@@ETURNED AS AN ARGUMENT. @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE READ\TREE\CKPT(TREE:IH
)@@G@@ MACHINE POINTER) " TO ROOT OF TREE @D@@@@          RESULT MACHINE POINTII
)@@G@@ER " TO NEW ROOT OF TREE@[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   SYMBOL: MACHINE POINIJ
)@@G@@TER; " TO SYMTAB ENTRY  @C@@@@DECLARE   ROOT: MACHINE POINTER; " TO NEW IK
)@@G@@ROOT  @[@@@@"     @^@@@@          ROOT := TREE; @B@@@@          READ\CKPIL
)@@G@@T\IMAGE; " READ IMAGE IN@B@@@@          WHILE (CKPT\TYPE NE CTYP\END) DOIM
)@@G@@@C@@@@           BEGIN " PROCESSING CHECKPOINT IMAGE  @C@@@@            IN
)@@G@@ IF (CKPT\TYPE NE CTYP\SYMBOL) THEN @ @@@@              BEGIN " ERROR   IO
)@@G@@@E@@@@                PDISPLAY('CKRD02',CKPT\PKT); " DIAGNOSE     @B@@@@IP
)@@G@@                ERROR; " AND ERROR OFF    @ @@@@              END; " ERRIQ
)@@G@@OR    @#@@@@             ELSE @C@@@@              BEGIN " RECONSTITUTINGIR
)@@G@@ VARIABLE   @D@@@@                SYMBOL := SEARCH\FOR\NODE( ROOT ,     IS
)@@G@@@F@@@@                   CKPT\STYP , CKPT\SLEN , LOC( CKPT\NAME(1) ) ); IT
)@@G@@@C@@@@                IF (SYMBOL EQ NULL\PTR) THEN    @B@@@@            IU
)@@G@@     BEGIN " CREATING SYMBOL  @C@@@@                   SYMBOL := CKPT\CRIV
)@@G@@EATE\SYMBOL;@F@@@@                   ROOT := INSERT\NEW\NODE(ROOT,SYMBOLIW
)@@G@@); " INSERT @B@@@@                 END; " CREATING SYMBOL   @F@@@@      IX
)@@G@@          CASEENTRY CKPT\DTYP " WHAT SHOULD DATA TYPE BE    @ @@@@      IY
)@@G@@          CASE TYPNUL:  @D@@@@                   READ\CKPT\IMAGE; " SKIPIZ
)@@G@@ PAST IMAGE @B@@@@                CASE TYPINT,TYPDST,TYPSTR:@F@@@@      JA
)@@G@@             READ\DATA\CKPT(SYMBOL); " READ DATA INTO SYMBOL@ @@@@      JB
)@@G@@          CASE TYPTAB:  @E@@@@                   READ\TABLE\CKPT(SYMBOL)JC
)@@G@@; " HANDLE TABLE  @^@@@@                CASE *: @A@@@@                 BJD
)@@G@@EGIN " ERROR CASE @E@@@@                   PDISPLAY('CKRD03',CKPT\PKT); JE
)@@G@@" DIAGNOSE  @B@@@@                   ERROR; " AND ERROR OFF @A@@@@      JF
)@@G@@           END; " ERROR CASE  @^@@@@                ENDCASE;@C@@@@      JG
)@@G@@        END; " RECONSTITUTING VARIABLE    @C@@@@           END; " PROCESJH
)@@G@@SING CHECKPOINT IMAGE   @C@@@@          READ\CKPT\IMAGE; " READ PAST ENDJI
)@@G@@ IMAGE@A@@@@          RETURN(ROOT); " TO CALLER @^@@@@END; " READ\TREE\CJJ
)@@G@@KPT   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" READ CKPT OF 'TABLE' DATA ITEM.   @[@@@@"     JK
)@@G@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE READ\TABLE\CKPT(SYMBOL: MACHINE POINTER)    @[@@@@BEGIN JL
)@@G@@@A@@@@          RELEASE\VALUE(SYMBOL);    @C@@@@          DTYP(SYMBOL) :JM
)@@G@@= CKPT\DTYP; " COPY TYPE@C@@@@          DSBT(SYMBOL) := CKPT\DSBT; " SUBJN
)@@G@@TYPE  @C@@@@          DLEN(SYMBOL) := CKPT\DLEN; " LENGTH   @C@@@@      JO
)@@G@@    READ\CKPT\IMAGE; " SKIP NAME IMAGE    @B@@@@          IF CKPT\TYPE NJP
)@@G@@E CTYP\TABLE THEN @A@@@@           BEGIN " ERROR HANDLING   @D@@@@      JQ
)@@G@@       PDISPLAY('CKRD04',CKPT\PKT); " DIAGNOSE  @A@@@@             ERRORJR
)@@G@@; " AND ERROR OFF @A@@@@           END; " ERROR HANDLING    @B@@@@      JS
)@@G@@    DADR(SYMBOL) := READ\TREE\CKPT  @C@@@@          ( DADR(SYMBOL) ); " JT
)@@G@@READ IN TABLE     @^@@@@END; " READ\TABLE\CKPT  @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   JU
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" READ ACTION TABLE CHECKPOINT AND REBUILDJV
)@@G@@ ACTION TABLES.   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE READ\ACTION\CKPT    @[@@@@JW
)@@G@@BEGIN @A@@@@DECLARE   ACTION\TEMP: INTEGER WORD @^@@@@          !*: MAPPJX
)@@G@@ED    @D@@@@             [ACTION\CHAR: 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER     @B@@@@JY
)@@G@@             ,*: 27 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER];@[@@@@"     @C@@@@          REJZ
)@@G@@AD\CKPT\IMAGE; " SKIP BEGIN IMAGE   @B@@@@          WHILE (CKPT\TYPE NE KA
)@@G@@CTYP\END) DO@A@@@@           BEGIN " PROCESS IMAGE    @C@@@@            KB
)@@G@@ IF (CKPT\TYPE NE CTYP\SYMBOL) THEN @ @@@@              BEGIN " ERROR   KC
)@@G@@@F@@@@                PDISPLAY('CKRD05',CKPT\IMAGE\PTR); " DIAGNOSE     KD
)@@G@@@^@@@@                ERROR;  @ @@@@              END " ERROR     @#@@@@KE
)@@G@@             ELSE @A@@@@              BEGIN " PROCESS SYMBOL@G@@@@      KF
)@@G@@          ACTION\TEMP := CKPT\NAME(1); " GET ACTION CHARACTER     @E@@@@KG
)@@G@@                CASEENTRY CKPT\DCTL " WHAT TYPE OF CONTROL  @ @@@@      KH
)@@G@@          CASE PUT\CTL: @F@@@@                 BEGIN " ERROR (SHOULD NEVKI
)@@G@@ER HAVE BEEN CKPTED)    @D@@@@                   PDISPLAY('CKRD06',CKPT\KJ
)@@G@@IMAGE\PTR); @ @@@@                   ERROR;     @ @@@@                 EKK
)@@G@@ND; " ERROR @ @@@@                CASE PEQU\CTL:@D@@@@                  KL
)@@G@@ PEQU\ACTION( ACTION\CHAR+1 ) :=    @G@@@@                      READ\ACTKM
)@@G@@ION\NODE( PEQU\ACTION(ACTION\CHAR+1) );   @ @@@@                CASE DIDKN
)@@G@@\CTL: @D@@@@                 BEGIN " SPECIAL HANDLING FOR DID     @C@@@@KO
)@@G@@                   ACTION( ACTION\CHAR+1 ) :=   @F@@@@                  KP
)@@G@@    READ\ACTION\NODE( ACTION(ACTION\CHAR+1) );  @E@@@@                  KQ
)@@G@@ DID := ACTION\CHAR; " SET GLOBAL DID     @C@@@@                 END; " KR
)@@G@@SPECIAL HANDLING FOR DID@^@@@@                CASE *: @C@@@@            KS
)@@G@@       ACTION( ACTION\CHAR+1 ) :=   @F@@@@                      READ\ACTKT
)@@G@@ION\NODE( ACTION(ACTION\CHAR+1) );  @^@@@@                ENDCASE;@A@@@@KU
)@@G@@              END; " PROCESS SYMBOL @A@@@@           END; " PROCESS IMAGKV
)@@G@@E     @C@@@@          READ\CKPT\IMAGE; " TO SKIP END IMAGE  @^@@@@END; "KW
)@@G@@ READ\ACTION\CKPT @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" READ NODE FOR ACTION TKX
)@@G@@ABLE AND REBUILD. @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE READ\ACTION\NODE(TREE: MACKY
)@@G@@HINE POINTER)     @C@@@@          RESULT MACHINE POINTER " TO NEW TREE  KZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@DECLARE   ROOT: MACHINE POINTER;    @A@@@@DECLARE   NOLA
)@@G@@DE: MACHINE POINTER;    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@          ROOT:=TREE;   @A@@@@LB
)@@G@@          NODE := SEARCH\FOR\NODE   @E@@@@             (ROOT,CKPT\STYP,CLC
)@@G@@KPT\SLEN, LOC(CKPT\NAME(1)) );@A@@@@          IF (NODE EQ NULL\PTR) THENLD
)@@G@@@A@@@@           BEGIN " CREATE NEW NODE  @B@@@@             NODE := CKPLE
)@@G@@T\CREATE\SYMBOL;  @C@@@@             ROOT := INSERT\NEW\NODE(ROOT,NODE);LF
)@@G@@@A@@@@           END; " CREAE NEW NODE    @D@@@@          CASEENTRY CKPTLG
)@@G@@\DTYP " WHAT IS DATA TYPE     @^@@@@          CASE TYPNUL:  @C@@@@      LH
)@@G@@       READ\CKPT\IMAGE; " SKIP THIS IMAGE @A@@@@          CASE TYPINT,TYLI
)@@G@@PDST,TYPSTR:@E@@@@             READ\DATA\CKPT(NODE); " READ IN STORED DALJ
)@@G@@TA    @#@@@@          CASE *: @^@@@@           BEGIN " ERROR@C@@@@      LK
)@@G@@       PDISPLAY('CKRD07',CKPT\IMAGE\PTR); @^@@@@             ERROR;     LL
)@@G@@@^@@@@           END; " ERROR @#@@@@          ENDCASE;@A@@@@          RELM
)@@G@@TURN(ROOT); " TO CALLER @^@@@@END; " READ\ACTION\NODE @[@@@@"     @[@@@@LN
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" CREATE SYMBOL SPECIFIED BY THE CURRENT CHECKPOINT IMAGE.  LO
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE CKPT\CREATE\SYMBOL  @D@@@@          RESULT MLP
)@@G@@ACHINE POINTER " TO NEW SYMBOL CORE @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@DECLARE   SNAME\PTLQ
)@@G@@R: MACHINE POINTER; " TO SYMBOL NAME@D@@@@DECLARE   SNAME(1): INTEGER WOLR
)@@G@@RD BASED(SNAME\PTR);    @D@@@@DECLARE   SYMBOL: MACHINE POINTER; " TO SYLS
)@@G@@MTAB ENTRY  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          SYMBOL := ALLOCATE\CORE(STH\LEN LT
)@@G@@+ CKPT\SLEN);     @E@@@@          STYP(SYMBOL) := CKPT\STYP; " SET SUBSCLU
)@@G@@RIPT TYPE   @E@@@@          SLEN(SYMBOL) := CKPT\SLEN; " SET SUBSCRIPT LLV
)@@G@@ENGTH @A@@@@          DCTL(SYMBOL) := CKPT\DCTL;@F@@@@          SNAME\PTLW
)@@G@@R := LOC( SNAM(SYMBOL) ); " SET NAME POINTER    @A@@@@          FOR I :=LX
)@@G@@ 1 TO CKPT\SLEN DO@E@@@@             SNAME(I) := CKPT\NAME(I); " COPY SYLY
)@@G@@MBOL NAME   @B@@@@          RETURN(SYMBOL); " TO CALLER     @ @@@@END; "LZ
)@@G@@ CKPT\CREATE\SYMBOL     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     MA
)@@G@@@E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO READ THE DATA FOR A VARIABLE. @[@@@@MB
)@@G@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE READ\DATA\CKPT(SYMBOL: MACHINE POINTER) " TO SYMTAMC
)@@G@@B ENTRY     @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@DECLARE   DATA\PTR: MACHINE POINTER; " TO MD
)@@G@@DATA  @C@@@@DECLARE   DATA\END: MACHINE POINTER; " $$$DEBUG @C@@@@DECLARME
)@@G@@E   DATA: INTEGER WORD BASED(DATA\PTR);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@MF
)@@G@@" SOMEDAY THIS SHOULD DO THE SAME THING AS SET\VALUE, THAT IS,    @B@@@@MG
)@@G@@" CHECK IF OLD VALUE BUFFER IS LONG ENUF. @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          REMH
)@@G@@LEASE\VALUE(SYMBOL); " RELASE OLD VALUE   @A@@@@          DTYP(SYMBOL) :MI
)@@G@@= CKPT\DTYP;@A@@@@          DSBT(SYMBOL) := CKPT\DSBT;@D@@@@          DLMJ
)@@G@@EN(SYMBOL) := CKPT\DLEN; " COPY LENGTH    @F@@@@          DADR(SYMBOL) :MK
)@@G@@= ALLOCATE\CORE( DESC\DATA\LEN(SYMBOL) ); @ @@@@          READ\CKPT\IMAGML
)@@G@@E;    @E@@@@          DATA\PTR := DADR(SYMBOL); " START AT DATA ADDRESS MM
)@@G@@@G@@@@          DATA\END := DADR(SYMBOL) + DESC\DATA\LEN(SYMBOL); " $$$DMN
)@@G@@EBUG  @C@@@@          WHILE (CKPT\TYPE EQ CTYP\DATA) DO     @B@@@@      MO
)@@G@@     BEGIN " PROCESSING DATA IMAGES @C@@@@             FOR I := 1 TO CKPMP
)@@G@@T\IMAGE\LEN-1 DO  @C@@@@              BEGIN " STORING NEXT DATA WORD    MQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@                IF (DATA\PTR GT DATA\END) THEN " $$$DEBUG   @A@@@@MR
)@@G@@                 BEGIN " $$$DEBUG   @E@@@@                   PDISPLAY('DMS
)@@G@@T1PTR',DATA\PTR); " $$$DEBUG  @E@@@@                   PDISPLAY('DT1END'MT
)@@G@@,DATA\END); " $$$DEBUG  @A@@@@                   ERROR; " $$$DEBUG@A@@@@MU
)@@G@@                 END; " $$$DEBUG    @D@@@@                DATA := CKPT\DMV
)@@G@@ATA\INT(I); " COPY WORD @F@@@@                DATA\PTR := DATA\PTR + 1; MW
)@@G@@" INCREMENT POINTER     @C@@@@              END; " STORING NEXT DATA WORMX
)@@G@@D     @C@@@@             READ\CKPT\IMAGE; " GET NEXT IMAGE  @B@@@@      MY
)@@G@@     END; " PROCESSING DATA IMAGES  @D@@@@          IF (DATA\PTR NE DATAMZ
)@@G@@\END) THEN " $$$DEBUG   @ @@@@           BEGIN " $$$DEBUG   @D@@@@      NA
)@@G@@       PDISPLAY('DT2PTR',DATA\PTR); " $$$DEBUG  @D@@@@             PDISPNB
)@@G@@LAY('DT2END',DATA\END); " $$$DEBUG  @ @@@@             ERROR; " $$$DEBUGNC
)@@G@@@ @@@@           END; " $$$DEBUG    @^@@@@END; " READ\DATA\CKPT   @#@@@@ND
)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" READ CHECKPOINT OF ONENE
)@@G@@-WORD INTEGER.    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE READ\UHDR\INT @ @@@@      NF
)@@G@@    RESULT INTEGER WORD @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@DECLARE   DATA\WORD: INTEGER WNG
)@@G@@ORD;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@          IF (CKPT\IMAGE\LEN NE 2) THEN ERROR; "NH
)@@G@@ $$$DEBUG   @D@@@@          DATA\WORD := CKPT\DATA\INT(1); " GET WORD   NI
)@@G@@@C@@@@          READ\CKPT\IMAGE; " GET NEXT IMAGE     @B@@@@"         ODNJ
)@@G@@ISPLAY('RUHINT',DATA\WORD);   @B@@@@          RETURN(DATA\WORD); " TO CANK
)@@G@@LLER  @^@@@@END; " READ\UHDR\INT    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" READNL
)@@G@@ CHECKPOINT OF ONE-WORD DISTANCE.   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE READ\UHDNM
)@@G@@R\DST @ @@@@          RESULT DISTANCE     @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@DECLARE   DANN
)@@G@@TA\WORD: DISTANCE;@[@@@@"     @E@@@@          IF (CKPT\IMAGE\LEN NE 2) TNO
)@@G@@HEN ERROR; " $$$DEBUG   @D@@@@          DATA\WORD := CKPT\DATA\DST(1); "NP

)@@G@@"         ODISPLAY('RUHDST',DATA\WORD);   @B@@@@          RETURN(DATA\WONR
)@@G@@RD); " TO CALLER  @^@@@@END; " READ\UHDR\DST    @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     NS
)@@G@@@A@@@@" READ ONE-WORD CONDITION VARIABLE. @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE RENT
)@@G@@AD\UHDR\CND @A@@@@          RESULT WORD CONDITION     @[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@NU
)@@G@@DECLARE   DATA\WORD: WORD CONDITION;@[@@@@"     @E@@@@          IF (CKPTNV
)@@G@@\IMAGE\LEN NE 2) THEN ERROR; " $$$DEBUG   @D@@@@          DATA\WORD := CNW
)@@G@@KPT\DATA\CND(1); " GET WORD   @C@@@@          READ\CKPT\IMAGE; " GET NEXNX
)@@G@@T IMAGE     @B@@@@"         ODISPLAY('RUHCND',DATA\WORD);   @B@@@@      NY
)@@G@@    RETURN(DATA\WORD); " TO CALLER  @^@@@@END; " READ\UHDR\CND    @[@@@@NZ
)@@G@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" READ CHECKPOINT OF UNIT COMMON DATA     @[@@@@OA
)@@G@@"     @G@@@@PROCEDURE READ\UHDR\CKPT(DATA\LEN: INTEGER WORD " LENGTH FOROB
)@@G@@ ERROR CHECK@G@@@@                        ,DATA\ADR: MACHINE POINTER) " OC
)@@G@@TO DATA IN DBANK  @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@DECLARE   DATA(1): INTEGER WORD BASEOD
)@@G@@D(DATA\ADR);@[@@@@"     @F@@@@          IF (CKPT\IMAGE\LEN NE DATA\LEN+1OE
)@@G@@) THEN ERROR; " $$$DEBUG@A@@@@          FOR I := 1 TO DATA\LEN DO @B@@@@OF
)@@G@@             DATA(I) := CKPT\DATA\INT(I); @ @@@@          READ\CKPT\IMAGOG
)@@G@@E;    @^@@@@END; " READ\UHDR\CKPT   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THISOH
)@@G@@ PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO READ THE NEXT IMAGE OF THE FILE     @A@@@@" CONTOI
)@@G@@AINING CHECKPOINT IMAGES.     @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE READ\CKPT\IMAGOJ
)@@G@@E     @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@DECLARE   TEMP: LOCATABLE INTEGER WORD; " IMAGE OK
)@@G@@LEN IN CHARS@[@@@@"     @D@@@@          IF END\FILE(CKPT\PKT) THEN ERROROL
)@@G@@; " $$$DEBUG@D@@@@          READ\FILE(CKPT\PKT,%TEMP); " READ IMAGE     OM
)@@G@@@F@@@@          CKPT\IMAGE\LEN := (TEMP+3)//4; " IMAGE LENGTH IN WORDS  ON
)@@G@@@ @@@@          INCLUDE(READ\SNAP); @E@@@@             SNAP('CKPTRD',CKPOO
)@@G@@T\IMAGE\LEN,CKPT\IMAGE\PTR);  @#@@@@          RESUME; @^@@@@END; " READ\OP
)@@G@@CKPT\IMAGE  @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@CATE\CCOVERY BUFFER     @^@@@@END; " CHECKOQ
)@@G@@POINT\DPS   @#@@@@CONTRO*[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@MODULE@[@@@@      @[@@@@"     OR
)@@G@@@D@@@@" THIS MODULE PROCESSES THE '.CONTROL EQU' DIRECTIVE  @[@@@@"     OS
)@@G@@@A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@A@@@@ COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPOT
)@@G@@ORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('ACTION-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@      OU
)@@G@@    COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CHAR-SIZE',IMOV
)@@G@@PORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('CONTROL-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@      OW
)@@G@@    COPY ('CONVERT-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-PROC'OX
)@@G@@,IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('CORE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@      OY
)@@G@@    COPY ('DIRECT-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('GETPUT-DEF',IOZ
)@@G@@MPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('GETPUT-PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@@      PA
)@@G@@    COPY ('MACRO-DEF',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPPB
)@@G@@ORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('PUSH-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@      PC
)@@G@@    COPY ('PRINT-DEF',IMPORTED);    @B@@@@          COPY ('STAGING-DEF',PD
)@@G@@IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('SCAN-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@      PE
)@@G@@    COPY ('SYMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-PROCS'PF
)@@G@@,IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @[@@@@      PG
)@@G@@@F@@@@PROCEDURE SET\CONTROL(CTL\TYPE\WANTED: WORD INTEGER) IMPORTED     PH
)@@G@@@^@@@@          ('SETCTL');   @[@@@@      @C@@@@PROCEDURE GET\NEXT\CHAR PI
)@@G@@IMPORTED ('GETCHR');    @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @[@@@@"     @#@@@@" LOCAPJ
)@@G@@L STORAGE   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@DEFINE    MAX\LEVEL = 10; " MAXIMUM EQU LEPK
)@@G@@VEL   @[D@@@"     @C@@@@"   .CONTROL EQU,'<CHARS>',<E1>,<E2>,...,<EN>   PL
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" DEFINES AN EQUATE WHERE <CHARS> IN THE TEXT STREAM WPM
)@@G@@ILL   @E@@@@" BE CONVERTED TO THE STRING COMPOSED OF THE CONCATENATED   PN
)@@G@@@D@@@@" STRING AND INTEGER EXPRESSIONS <E1> THROUGH <EN>.   @[@@@@"     PO
)@@G@@@C@@@@" .CONTROL EQU,'XX','ANYTHING',0132,0131,0130   @D@@@@" WILL CONVEPP
)@@G@@RT XX TO ANYTHINGZYX IN THE TEXT STREAM.  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE DEPQ
)@@G@@FINE\EQUATE(EQU\TYPE: WORD INTEGER) @A[@@@           EXPORTED ('DEFINEQUPR
)@@G@@ATE') @[@@@@BEGIN @ @@@@DECLARE   SIZE: WORD INTEGER; @C@@@@DECLARE   ICPS
)@@G@@B\SAVE: WORD MACHINE POINTER; "     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@          SCAN(EVAPT
)@@G@@L+CTRM+ALLOW\STR+CNUM+CSTR); " DO LITERAL CONVERSION  @B@@@@          IFPU
)@@G@@ ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN  @#^@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@            PV
)@@G@@ SET\CONTROL(EQU\TYPE); " SET UP THE HEADER     @C@@@@             SIZE PW
)@@G@@:= ICBH\LEN + (CSDLEN+3)//4;  @G@@@@             DADR(CTL\PTR) := ALLOCAPX
)@@G@@TE\CORE(SIZE); " GET MIN CORE NEEDED@E@@@@             DLEN(CTL\PTR) := PY
)@@G@@SIZE; " NR OF WORDS ATTACHED  @F@@@@             DTYP(CTL\PTR) := TYPINTPZ
)@@G@@; " FOR LACK OF A BETTER NAME @B@@@@             DCTL(CTL\PTR) := EQU\TYQA
)@@G@@PE;   @D@@@@             ICB\SAVE := ICB\PTR; " SAVE CURRENT ICB  @F@@@@QB
)@@G@@             ICB\PTR := DADR(CTL\PTR); " POINT TO CONTROL CARD    @B@@@@QC
)@@G@@             CARD\TYPE := EQUATE\CARD;    @ @@@@             CARD\REFS :QD
)@@G@@= 1;  @A@@@@             CARD\LENGTH := CSDLEN; @C@@@@             FOR IQE
)@@G@@ := 1 TO SIZE-ICBH\LEN DO     @C@@@@                INPUT\CARD\WORD(I) :QF
)@@G@@= DWORD(I); @C@@@@             ICB\PTR := ICB\SAVE; " RESTORE ICB @D@@@@QG
)@@G@@           END; " OF THEN CLAUSE OF 'IF ERROR\ ...'   @^@@@@END; " OF DEQH
)@@G@@FINE\EQUATE @[I@@@"     @B(@@@PROCEDURE SEARCH\EQUS(CHARS: WORD INTEGER,QI
)@@G@@@G@@@@           HEAD\LINK: WORD MACHINE POINTER) EXPORTED ('SEARCHEQUS'QJ
)@@G@@)     @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      @B@@@@DECLARE   LINK: MACHINE WORD POINTERQK
)@@G@@;     @ @@@@DECLARE   *: MAPPED BASED     @C@@@@          [BACK\LINK: 18QL
)@@G@@ BIT MACHINE POINTER,   @C@@@@           FORWARD\LINK: 18 BIT MACHINE POQM
)@@G@@INTER,@A@@@@          EQU\CHARS: WORD INTEGER]; @[@@@@      @[@@@@"     QN
)@@G@@@^@@@@" BEGIN EXECUTABLE CODE @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          FOUND\EQUATE :QO
)@@G@@= FALSE;    @A@@@@          INSERT\PTR := HEAD\LINK;  @E@@@@          LIQP
)@@G@@NK := FORWARD\LINK(HEAD\LINK); " GET FIRST ITEM @]@@@@SEARCH\LOOP:@A@@@@QQ
)@@G@@          IF LINK NE NULL\PTR THEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@      QR
)@@G@@       IF EQU\CHARS(LINK) GE CHARS THEN   @^@@@@              BEGIN     QS
)@@G@@@C@@@@                IF EQU\CHARS(LINK) EQ CHARS THEN@^@@@@            QT
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @B@@@@                   FOUND\PTR := LINK;     @B@@@@      QU
)@@G@@             FOUND\EQUATE := TRUE;  @^@@@@                 END;   @#@@@@QV
)@@G@@              END;@#@@@@             ELSE @^@@@@              BEGIN     QW
)@@G@@@A@@@@                INSERT\PTR := LINK; @F@@@@                LINK := QX
)@@G@@FORWARD\LINK(LINK); "LOOK AT NEXT ITEM    @A@@@@                GOTO SEAQY
)@@G@@RCH\LOOP;   @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  QZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" HERE IS THE HEART OF THE WORK. SEARCH THRA
)@@G@@E TREES FOR @C@@@@" THE CURRENT CHARACTER AND THE NEXT CHARACTER  @D@@@@RB
)@@G@@" IF NOT FOUND, SEARCH FOR THE CURRENT CHARACTER AND  @D@@@@" A BLANK FORC
)@@G@@R THE NEXT CHARACTER. IF STILL NOT FOUND  @B@@@@" THEN RETURN A PUT\CTL.RD
)@@G@@ IF IT IS FOUND   @ @@@@" TAKE APPROPRIATE ACTION.    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@RE
)@@G@@PROCEDURE GET\ACTION\INDEX EXPORTED ('GETACTINDEX')   @A@@@@            RF
)@@G@@ RESULT WORD INTEGER    @[^@@@BEGIN @G@@@[          CTL\IDX := PUT\CTL; RG
)@@G@@" IF NOT FOUND JUST PUT THE CHARACTER     @F@[@@DECLARE   INDEX: WORD INRH
)@@G@@TEGER; " THE CONTROL TYPE TO BE RETURNED  @[@[@@      @E@[@@          IFRI
)@@G@@ ACTION\TABLE(CHARACTER+1) EQ NULL\PTR THEN     @E@@@[          IF (ACTIRJ
)@@G@@ON\TABLE(CHARACTER+1) NE NULL\PTR) THEN   @ @@@[           BEGIN " LOOKURK
)@@G@@P     @E@[@@             RETURN(PUT\CTL); " NOTHING HERE, RETURN PUT    RL
)@@G@@@E@[@@          CTL\PTR := NULL\PTR; " START OUT WITH NOTHING     @E@@@[RM
)@@G@@             CTL\PTR := NULL\PTR; " START OUT WITH NOTHING  @D@[@@      RN
)@@G@@    CTL\WORD := NULL\CTL\WORD; " SET UP CTL\WORD@E@@@[             CTL\WRO
)@@G@@ORD := NULL\CTL\WORD; " SET UP CTL\WORD   @A@[@@          CTL\CHAR(1) :=RP
)@@G@@ CHARACTER; @B@@@[             CTL\CHAR(1) := CHARACTER;    @^@[@@      RQ
)@@G@@    GET\NEXT\CHAR;@ @@@[             GET\NEXT\CHAR;   @A@[@@          CTRR
)@@G@@L\CHAR(2) := CHARACTER; @B@@@[             CTL\CHAR(2) := CHARACTER;    RS
)@@G@@@F@[@@          FIRST\INPUT\COLUMN := PREVIOUS\CARD\PTR EQ NULL\PTR AND RT
)@@G@@@G@@@[             FIRST\INPUT\COLUMN := (PREVIOUS\CARD\PTR EQ NULL\PTR)RU
)@@G@@ AND  @F@[@@             CARD\INDEX EQ 3; " JUST GOT FIRST TWO CHARACTERRV
)@@G@@S     @F@@@[                (CARD\INDEX EQ 3); " JUST GOT FIRST TWO CHARRW
)@@G@@ACTERS@D@[@@          IF FIRST\INPUT\COLUMN THEN " SEARCH FOR PEQU@E@@@[RX
)@@G@@             IF FIRST\INPUT\COLUMN THEN " SEARCH FOR PEQU   @I@[@@      RY
)@@G@@       SEARCH\FOR\CONTROL(PEQU\ACTION(CTL\CHAR(1)+1)); " SEARCH PEQU TRERZ
)@@G@@E     @H@@@[                SEARCH\FOR\CONTROL(PEQU\ACTION(CTL\CHAR(1)+1SA
)@@G@@)); " SEARCH PEQUS@G@[@@          IF CTL\PTR EQ NULL\PTR THEN " NOT FOUNSB
)@@G@@D SO TRY OTHER CHARS    @F@@@[             IF (CTL\IDX EQ PUT\CTL) THEN SC
)@@G@@" NOT FOUND SO TRY EQUS @#@[@@           BEGIN  @H@[@@             SEARCSD
)@@G@@H\FOR\CONTROL(ACTION(CTL\CHAR(1)+1)); " SEARCH REGULAR TREE @G@@@[      SE
)@@G@@          SEARCH\FOR\CONTROL(ACTION(CTL\CHAR(1)+1)); " SEARCH EQUS@B@[@@SF
)@@G@@           END; " SEARCH NONPEQU TREE     @D@[@@          IF CTL\PTR EQ SG
)@@G@@NULL\PTR THEN " NOT FOUND     @E@[@@             INDEX := PUT\CTL; " MAKSH
)@@G@@E IT A PUT CHARACTER    @ @[@@          ELSE " GET INDEX    @C@[@@      SI
)@@G@@       INDEX := DCTL(CTL\PTR); " GET INDEX@A@[@@          IF CTL\CHAR\LESJ
)@@G@@N EQ 1 THEN @B@@@[             IF CTL\CHAR\LEN EQ 1 THEN    @#@[@@      SK
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @^@@@[              BEGIN     @F@[@@             BACKUP\CHARSL
)@@G@@ACTER; " BACKPUP TO PREVIOUS CHARACTER    @F@@@[                BACKUP\CSM
)@@G@@HARACTER; " BACKPUP TO PREVIOUS CHARACTER @E@[@@             CHARACTER :SN
)@@G@@= CTL\CHAR(1); " RESET CHARACTER    @E@@@[                CHARACTER := CSO
)@@G@@TL\CHAR(1); " RESET CHARACTER @B@[@@           END; " RESET CHARACTER POSP
)@@G@@INTER @C@@@[              END; " RESET CHARACTER POINTER    @[@[@@      SQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@[@@" CERTAIN CONTROL TYPES REQUIRE SPECIAL ACTION. THESE SR
)@@G@@ARE THE     @C@@@[" CERTAIN CONTROL TYPES REQUIRE SPECIAL ACTION. @F@[@@SS
)@@G@@" ONES THAT HAVE DATA ATTACHED TO THEM THAT MUST BE PROCESSED.    @[@@@@ST
)@@G@@"     @ @[@@          CASEENTRY INDEX     @ @@@[             CASEENTRY CSU
)@@G@@TL\IDX@[@[@@      @[I[@@"     @E@[@@" FOR TABS WE HAVE TO SET 'NUMBER\OFSV
)@@G@@\TABS' AND 'TAB\PTR'    @[@[@@"     @^@[@@          CASE TAB\CTL: @ @@@[SW
)@@G@@             CASE TAB\CTL:    @#@[@@           BEGIN  @^@@@[            SX

)@@G@@                NUMBER\OF\TABS := DLEN(CTL\PTR);@B@[@@             TAB\PSZ

)@@G@@@ @[@@           END; " OF CASE TAB @#@@@[              END;@[@[@@      TB
)@@G@@@[@[@@"     @F@[@@" FOR EQU'S CHECK TO SEE IF LEVEL IS TOO HIGH AND IF NTC
)@@G@@OT INSERT   @ @[@@" THE EQU CARD INTO THE CHAIN @[@[@@"     @A@[@@      TD
)@@G@@    CASE EQU\CTL, PEQU\CTL:   @A@@@[             CASE EQU\CTL, PEQU\CTL:TE
)@@G@@@#@[@@           BEGIN  @^@@@[              BEGIN     @C@[@@            TF
)@@G@@ IF CARD\LEVEL GE MAX\LEVEL THEN    @G@@@[                IF (CARD\LEVELTG
)@@G@@ GE MAX\LEVEL) THEN " IF LEVEL TOO DEEP   @^@[@@              BEGIN     TH
)@@G@@@^@@@[                 BEGIN  @B@[@@                WARNING(W\EQU\LEVEL)TI
)@@G@@;     @B@@@[                   WARNING(W\EQU\LEVEL);  @#@[@@            TJ
)@@G@@  END;@^@@@[                 END;   @#@[@@             ELSE @^@@@[      TK
)@@G@@          ELSE    @ @[@@                INSERT\EQU;   @E@@@[            TL
)@@G@@       INSERT\EQU; " PUT IT INTO THE INPUT CHAIN@#@[@@           END;   TM
)@@G@@@#@@@[              END;@[@[@@      @#@[@@          ENDCASE;@^@@@[      TN
)@@G@@       ENDCASE;   @^@@@[           END; " LOOKUP@^@[@@          RETURN(ITO
)@@G@@NDEX);@ @@@[          RETURN(CTL\IDX);    @ @[@@END; " OF GET\ACTION\INDTP
)@@G@@EX    @^@@@[END; " GET\ACTION\INDEX @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" PROCEDURE TO SEATQ
)@@G@@RCH FOR A CONTROL SEQUENCE    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE SEARCH\FOR\CONTR
)@@G@@TROL(TREE\HEAD: MACHINE WORD POINTER)     @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@DECLARE   CTTS
)@@G@@L\WORD\SAVE: WORD INTEGER; "  @[@@@@"     @H@@@@          CTL\WORD\SAVE TT
)@@G@@:= CTL\WORD; " SAVE THE CONTROL CHARACTERS SCANNED    @E@@@@          CTTU
)@@G@@L\CHAR\LEN := 2; " START WITH 2 CHARACTER SEARCH@[@@@@"     @G@@@@      TV
)@@G@@    CTL\PTR := SEARCH\FOR\NODE(TREE\HEAD,TYPSTR,1,LOC(CTL\WORD)); @[@@@@TW
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" **** NOTE: THE FOLLOWING IF STATEMENTS MAY BE CHANGED     TX
)@@G@@@D@@@@" **** WHEN A 'CONTROL CLEAR' ACTUALLY PURGES THE     @E@@@@" ****TY
)@@G@@ DEFINITION FROM THE TREE.  AT THAT POINT IT SHOULD   @F@@@@" **** CHANGTZ
)@@G@@ED TO 'IF CTL\CHAR\LEN EQ 2 AND CTL\PTR EQ NULL\PTR'  @C@@@@" **** RATHEUA
)@@G@@R THAN THE TWO IF STATEMENTS NOW.   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@          IF CTL\CUB
)@@G@@HAR\LEN EQ 2 THEN " NO MORE SEARCHING WITH ONE CHAR   @G@@@@            UC
)@@G@@ IF CTL\PTR EQ NULL\PTR OR DCTL(CTL\PTR) EQ PUT\CTL THEN    @F@@@@      UD
)@@G@@        BEGIN " TRY THE SEARCH WITH THE SECOND CHAR A NULL  @A@@@@      UE
)@@G@@          CTL\CHAR\LEN := 1;  @C@@@@                CTL\CHAR(2) := NULL\UF
)@@G@@CTL\CHAR;   @H@@@@                CTL\PTR := SEARCH\FOR\NODE(TREE\HEAD,TUG
)@@G@@YPSTR,1,LOC(CTL\WORD)); @#@@@@              END;@G@@@@          CTL\WORDUH
)@@G@@ := CTL\WORD\SAVE; " RESTORE BOTH CONTROL CHARACTERS  @E@@@[          IFUI
)@@G@@ (CTL\PTR NE NULL\PTR) THEN " IF WE FOUND ONE   @F@@@[             CTL\IUJ
)@@G@@DX := DCTL(CTL\PTR); " RETURN ITS TYPE IN GLOBAL@B@[@@END; " OF PROCEDURUK
)@@G@@E SEARCH\FOR\CONTROL    @ @@@[END; " SEARCH\FOR\CONTROL     @[@@@@      UL
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" INSERT THE EQU AT CTL\PTR INTO THE CARD CHAIN @[@@@@UM
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE INSERT\EQU    @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@DECLARE   ICB\SAVEUN
)@@G@@: WORD MACHINE POINTER; @[@@@@"     @D@@@@          ICB\SAVE := ICB\PTR;UO
)@@G@@ " SAVE CURRENT ICB     @E@@@@          ICB\PTR := DADR(CTL\PTR); " POINUP
)@@G@@T TO CONTROL CARD @F@@@@          IF CARD\REFS GT 1 THEN " SOMEONE ELSE UQ
)@@G@@IS USING IT, ERROR@#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             ICB\PTR := UR
)@@G@@ICB\SAVE; " RESTORE ICB @C@@@@             WARNING(W\EQU\LEVEL); " TELL US
)@@G@@USER  @A@@@@           END; " OF THEN CLAUSE    @D@@@@          ELSE " JUT
)@@G@@UST PUSH EQUATE CARD ONTO STACK     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@      UU
)@@G@@       ICB\PTR := ICB\SAVE; " RESTORE ICB @D@@@@             PUSH\THIS\IUV
)@@G@@CB(EQUATE\CARD,DADR(CTL\PTR));@D@@@@             END\OF\INPUT\CARD := FAUW
)@@G@@LSE; " ALLOW READ @E@@@@             CARD\INDEX := 1; " START AT FIRST CUX
)@@G@@HARACTER    @A@@@@           END; " OF ELSE CLAUSE    @^@@@@END; " OF INUY
)@@G@@SERT\EQU    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" PROCEDURE TO INSERT TRANSPARENT CODES INUZ
)@@G@@ THE OUTPUT STREAM@[@@@@"     @ @@@@"   .INSERT <E1>,<E2>,...,<EN>@[@@@@VA
)@@G@@"     @A@@@@" .INSERT 0123,'ABC',59,040,'TEXT'  @C@@@@" WILL INSERT SABCVB
)@@G@@; TEXT IN THE TEXT STREAM.    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\INSERTVC
)@@G@@\DIRECTIVE EXPORTED ('PROINSDIR')   @[@@@@BEGIN @G@@@@          SCAN(EVAVD
)@@G@@L+CTRM+ALLOW\STR+CNUM+CSTR); " DO LITERAL CONVERSION  @B@@@@          IFVE
)@@G@@ ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @D@@@@            VF
)@@G@@ PUT\FUNCTION\INTO\WORD(FUNC\TRANSPARENT, @E@@@@                CVT\PTR\VG
)@@G@@TO\INTE(MOVE\SCANNED\TO\CARD) );    @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  VH
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @#@@@@" EDIT DIRECTIVE  @[[@@@"     @ @@@@"   .EDIT <E1>,<E2VI
)@@G@@>,...,<EN>  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@" .EDIT 'TEXT',046,'MORE'     @C@@@@" WILLVJ
)@@G@@ EDIT TEXT38MORE INTO THE TEXT STREAM.    @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PRVK
)@@G@@OCESS\EDIT\DIRECTIVE EXPORTED ('PROEDITDIR')    @[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@      VL
)@@G@@    GET\EDIT\TEXT; " GET TEXT TO BE PRINTED     @A@@@@          SCAN\TO\VM
)@@G@@DIRECTIVE\END; "  @B@@@@          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN  @#@@@@VN
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@             IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\O) THEN " PUVO
)@@G@@T IN OUTPUT STREAM@B@@@@                FOR I := 1 TO CSDLEN DO   @E@@@@VP
)@@G@@                   PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD(DCHR(I));   @B@@@@      VQ
)@@G@@       ELSE " PUT INTO INPUT STREAM @E@@@@                MOVE\STRING\TOVR
)@@G@@\CARD; " PUT IN INPUT CARD    @#@@@@           END;   @E@@@@          FLVS
)@@G@@USH\DIRECTIVE\IMAGE := FALSE; " INHIBIT FLUSH   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     VT
)@@G@@@A@@@@"   .DISPLAY <E1>,<E2>,...,<EN>     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" .DISPLAY 'VU
)@@G@@DEBUG AID',1@B@@@@" WILL DISPLAY DEBUG AID1 ON THE TERMINAL.@[@@@@"     VV
)@@G@@@D@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\DISPLAY EXPORTED ('PRODISPLAY')     @[@@@@BEGIN VW
)@@G@@@F@@@@          SCAN(EVAL+CTRM+CSTR+ALLOW\STR); " SCAN AND GET STRING   VX
)@@G@@@E@@@@          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN " WE CAN PRINT IT  @D@@@@VY
)@@G@@             PRINT(CSDADR,CSDLEN,1); " PRINT STRING   @A@@@@END; " OF PRVZ
)@@G@@OCESS\DISPLAY\COMMAND   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" USED BY EDIT\DIRECTIVE AND DWA
)@@G@@ISPLAY\COMMAND.   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE GET\EDIT\TEXT @[@@@@BEGIN WB
)@@G@@@B@@@@          SCAN(EVAL+CTRM+CSTR+ALLOW\STR); @D@@@@          IF ERRORWC
)@@G@@\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 OR FORMATTING THEN@C@@@@           BEGIN " TO LOOK AT WD
)@@G@@SCANNER RETURN    @D@@@@             ERROR\STATUS\CODE := 0; " CLEAR ERRWE
)@@G@@ORS   @D@@@@             IF CSDLEN GT MAX\INPUT\CHAR\LEN THEN     @B@@@@WF
)@@G@@                CONTROL\ERROR := ERROR3;  @C@@@@           END; " OF LOOWG
)@@G@@KING AT SCANNER RETURN  @^@@@@END; " OF GET\EDIT\TEXT @[@@@@"     @C@@@@WH
)@@G@@" GOT EDIT NOW PUT IT INTO A NEW INPUT CARD     @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDWI
)@@G@@URE MOVE\STRING\TO\CARD @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          PUSH\ICB(EQUATE\CARDWJ
)@@G@@); " GET NEW CARD @A@@@@          CARD\LENGTH := CSDLEN;    @B@@@@      WK
)@@G@@    FOR I := 1 TO CARD\LENGTH DO    @B@@@@             INPUT\CARD(I) := WL
)@@G@@DCHR(I);    @D@@@@          END\OF\INPUT\CARD := FALSE; " ALLOW SCAN    WM
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@" PROCEDURE TO SEARCH FOR A CONTROL SEQUENWN
)@@G@@CE    @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE SEARCH\FOR\CON*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULEWO
)@@G@@;     @G@@@@" THIS MODULE CONTAINS ALL THE COPIES WITHOUT THE IMPORTED QWP
)@@G@@UALIFIER    @G@@@@" THIS HELPS ELIMINATE CONFUSION AS TO WHICH ELEMENTS WQ
)@@G@@NEED IMPORTED AND @E@@@@" WHICH DON'T.  THE RULE IS THAT WE USE IMPORTEDWR
)@@G@@ ON ALL     @C@@@@" COPYS IN ALL ELEMENTS EXCEPT IN THIS ONE.     @[@@@@WS
)@@G@@"     @ @@@@          COPY ('DEFINES');   @G@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-WT
)@@G@@DEF');        " THIS MUST PRECEDE CONVERT-DEF   @ @@@@          COPY ('AWU

)@@G@@);    @ @@@@          COPY ('MACRO-DEF'); @ @@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEXB
)@@G@@F');  @A@@@@          COPY ('OPERATOR-DEF');    @A@@@@          COPY ('PXC
)@@G@@HOTON-DEF'); "    @A@@@@          COPY ('RUN-DATA-DEF');    @ @@@@      XD

)@@G@@DEF');@G@@@@DECLARE   FUNNY\MODE: WORD CONDITION STATIC EXPORTED ('FUNNYXI
)@@G@@MODE');     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)^@)*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULEXJ
)@@G@@;     @E@@@@" THIS MODULE CONTAINS PROCEDURES TO UNPACK THE INPUT TEXT, XK
)@@G@@@D@@@@" ASSEMBLE WORDS, AND CONCATENATE THEM IN AN OUTPUT   @#@@@@" STAGXL
)@@G@@ING AREA.   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" THE CHARACTERS ARE TAKEN ONE AT A TIME FXM
)@@G@@ROM THE     @D@@@@" PACKED 'INPUT\CARD' AND TRANSFERED TO THE TEMPORARY XN
)@@G@@@F@@@@" UNPACKING AREA 'NEXT\WORD'.  AT THE SAME TIME THE CHARACTER     XO
)@@G@@@E@@@@" WIDTHS ARE OBTAINED AND ACCUMULATED FROM THE FINAL DEVICE @]@@@@XP
)@@G@@" TABLES.   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" AFTER A WORD HAS BEEN ASSEMBLED THE 'MOVXQ
)@@G@@E\NEXT\WORD\TO\LINE'    @F@@@@" PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO MOVE THE UNPACKEDXR
)@@G@@ SINGLE WORD TO THE     @D@@@@" UNPACKED LINE ASSEMBLY AREA.  THE 'WORD\XS
)@@G@@WIDTH' S ARE@E@@@@" ACCUMULATED UNTIL THE DESIRED 'LINE\WIDTH' IS OBTAINXT
)@@G@@ED.   @E@@@@" AFTER APPROPRIATE JUSTIFICATION ETC, THE FINAL DEVICE     XU
)@@G@@@D@@@@" HANDLER WILL BE CALLED BY ANOTHER PROCEDURE TO DO   @D@@@@" THE XV
)@@G@@FINAL PACKING OF THE LINE INTO 'OUTPUT\CARD' AND@B@@@@" TO SHIP IT OFF TXW
)@@G@@O THE FINAL DEVICE.     @E@@@@"      NOTE: CHARACTERS PASS THROUGH FOUR XX
)@@G@@STAGES INDICATED  @F@@@@"      BY THE NAMES GIVEN THE ASSOCIATED VARIABLXY
)@@G@@ES.  THEY ARE:    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@"           CARD, WORD, LINE, AND OUXZ
)@@G@@TPUT. @[@@@@"     @F@@@@"      CARD AND OUTPUT ARE PACKED QUARTER WORDS,YA
)@@G@@ WORD AND LINE    @A@@@@"       ARE UNPACKED QUARTER WORDS. @[@@@@"     YB
)@@G@@@A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('ACTION-YC
)@@G@@DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@YD
)@@G@@          COPY ('CORE-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('CONTROLYE
)@@G@@-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-PROC',IMPORTED); @B@@@@YF
)@@G@@          COPY ('CHAR-SIZE',IMPORTED);    @E@@@@          COPY ('CARD-DEYG
)@@G@@F',IMPORTED); " GET I/O CARD DEFS   @D@@@@          COPY ('EDIT-DEF',IMPYH

)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-DEF',IMPORTED);     @[@@@@      @[@@@@      YP
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @D@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\END\OF\LINE IMPORTED ('PROEOL');    YQ
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @E@@@@DECLARE    WORD\OVERFLOW: 6 BIT CONDITION STATIC := FAYR
)@@G@@LSE   @E@@@@          ,LINE\OVERFLOW: 6 BIT CONDITION STATIC := FALSE   YS
)@@G@@@^@@@@                      ; @[@@@@      @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEYT
)@@G@@DURE IS CALLED TO MOVE THE NEXT WORD INTO THE OUTPUT  @E@@@@" LINE AND TYU
)@@G@@O PROCESS THE END OF LINE ETC. WHEN THE LINE    @E@@@@" IS FULL.  IT ALLYV
)@@G@@SO CHECKS FOR WORDS THAT ARE TOO LONG TO  @#@@@@" FIT IN ANY LINE.@[@@@@YW
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE OUTPUT\NEXT\WORD EXPORTED ('OUTPUTWORD')    @[@@@@YX
)@@G@@BEGIN @[@@@@      @A@@@@          MOVE\NEXT\WORD\TO\LINE;   @F@@@@      YY
)@@G@@    IF LINE\FULL OR END\OF\PARAGRAPH THEN " OUTPUT LINE     @#@@@@      YZ
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @C@@@@             IF HYPHEN THEN " CALL HYPHENATOR   @F@@@@ZA
)@@G@@                ATTEMPT\HYPHENATION; " TRY TO HYPHEN CURRENT WORD @A@@@@ZB
)@@G@@             PROCESS\END\OF\LINE;   @A@@@@             CHECK\FOR\LONG\WOZC
)@@G@@RD;   @F@@@@             MOVE\NEXT\WORD\TO\LINE; " MOVE RESIDUE FROM LASZD
)@@G@@T LINE@#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE OUTPUT\NEXT\WORDZE
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@" PROCEDURE TO STASH THE NEXT WORD IN THE OUTPUT BUFFEZF
)@@G@@R     @D@@@@" IF NO MORE ROOM SET LINE\FULL TRUE.  THE LAST WORD  @D@@@@ZG
)@@G@@" WAS NOT STASHED SO THIS PROCEDURE MUST BE RECALLED. @C@@@@" NOTE: UNLEZH
)@@G@@SS SPECIAL CIRCUMSTANCES CALL FOR IT@D@@@@" THIS ROUTINE SHOULD NOT BE CZI
)@@G@@ALLED BUT INSTEAD CALL  @E@@@@" OUTPUT\NEXT\WORD WHICH DOES ALL THE NECEZJ
)@@G@@SSARY CHECKING.   @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE MOVE\NEXT\WORD\TO\LINE EXPZK
)@@G@@ORTED ('MOVNWL')  @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @B@@@@DECLARE   I: WORD INTEGEZL
)@@G@@R; " LOOP COUNTER @E@@@@          DECLARE  LI: WORD INTEGER; " TEMPORARYZM
)@@G@@ LINE INDEX @B@@@@DECLARE   BLANKS\ONLY: WORD CONDITION;    @[@@@@"     ZN
)@@G@@@A@@@@          IF WORD\INDEX EQ 0 THEN   @D@@@@             GOTO NORMALZO
)@@G@@\RETURN; " RETURN IMMEDIATELY @D@@@@          IF (WORD\DSI\MODE NE DSI\MZP
)@@G@@ODE\NONE) THEN    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@             PUT\FUNC\INZQ
)@@G@@TO\WORD(FUNC\DSIE,0); " ERROR RECOVERY    @C@@@@             WORD\DSI\MOZR
)@@G@@DE := DSI\MODE\NONE;    @#@@@@           END;   @D@@@@          IF INHIBZS
)@@G@@IT\INDENT THEN " USE FULL WIDTH     @B@@@@             MAX\WIDTH := AREAZT
)@@G@@\WIDTH;     @E@@@@          ELSE IF INHIBIT\LEFT\INDENT THEN " DON'T USEZU
)@@G@@ LEFT @D@@@@             MAX\WIDTH := AREA\WIDTH - RIGHT\INDENT;  @C@@@@ZV
)@@G@@          ELSE " TEXT IS LIMITED BY BOTH INDENTS@F@@@@             MAX\WZW
)@@G@@IDTH := AREA\WIDTH - LEFT\INDENT - RIGHT\INDENT;@D@@@@          IF (LINEZX
)@@G@@\WIDTH+WORD\WIDTH) GT MAX\WIDTH THEN@#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@      ZY
)@@G@@       LINE\FULL := TRUE;     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" IF THE LINE IS FULL ANZZ
)@@G@@D NEXT\WORD IS ALL BLANK OR BREAK FUNCS THEN    @D@@@@" PURGE IT SO WE DAA
)@@G@@ON'T GENERATE EXTRA BLANK LINES.    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@             I := AB
)@@G@@0; " INITIALIZE LOOP COUNTER  @D@@@@             BLANKS\ONLY := TRUE; " AC
)@@G@@ALL BLANKS SO FAR @D@@@@             WHILE I LT WORD\INDEX AND BLANKS\ONAD
)@@G@@LY DO @^@@@@              BEGIN     @D@@@@                I := I + 1; " AE
)@@G@@INCREMENT LOOP COUNTER  @D@@@@                IF NEXT\WORD(I) NE FUNC\BLAF
)@@G@@ANK AND     @D@@@@                   NEXT\WORD(I) NE FUNC\SPACEBAND AND AG
)@@G@@@D@@@@                   NEXT\WORD(I) NE FUNC\BREAK THEN    @G@@@@      AH
)@@G@@             BLANKS\ONLY := FALSE; " FOUND NON BLANK OR BREAK     @#@@@@AI
)@@G@@              END;@G@@@@             IF BLANKS\ONLY THEN " PURGE NEXT\WOAJ

)@@G@@    GOTO NORMAL\RETURN; " RETURN NOW@#@@@@              END;@C@@@@      AL

)@@G@@NEVER FIT IN LINE @^@@@@              BEGIN     @D@@@@                TRAO

)@@G@@PH := TRUE; " OUTPUT LINE NOW @C@@@@                PRINT\LINE\OVERFLOW\AQ

)@@G@@READ OF NEXT CARD @A@@@@              END; " WORD TRUNCATION@B@@@@      AS
)@@G@@     END; " CHECK FOR WORD WON'T FIT@I@@@@          IF (LINE\INDEX + WORAT
)@@G@@D\INDEX) GT MAX\LINE\LEN THEN " TOO MANY CHARACTER    @#@@@@           BAU
)@@G@@EGIN  @H@@@@             WORD\INDEX := MAX\LINE\LEN - LINE\INDEX; " TRUNAV

)@@G@@             TRUNCATE\WORD; " MAKE WORD FIT INTO LINE @D@@@@            AX
)@@G@@ LINE\FULL := TRUE; " OUTPUT THIS LINE    @E@@@@           END; " CHECK AY

)@@G@@);    @A@@@@             ELSE IF RIGHTF THEN    @D@@@@                PUBC
)@@G@@T\FUNC\INTO\LINE(FUNC\FLUSH,0);     @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@"     BD
)@@G@@@E@@@@" LOOP THROUGH ALL CHARACTERS IN NEXT\WORD MOVING THEM TO   @E@@@@BE

)@@G@@"     @D@@@@          LI := LINE\INDEX; " GET CURRENT LINE POINTER@B@@@@BJ

)@@G@@NT) THEN " FONT CHANGE  @D@@@@                   LINE\FONT := NEXT\CHAR\BU
)@@G@@WIDTH(I);   @H@@@@                ELSE IF (NEXT\WORD(I) EQ FUNC\HEIGHT) BV
)@@G@@THEN " TYPESIZE CHANGE  @E@@@@                   LINE\TYPE\HITE := NEXT\BW
)@@G@@CHAR\WIDTH(I);    @H@@@@                ELSE IF (NEXT\WORD(I) EQ FUNC\WIBX
)@@G@@DTH) THEN " TYPESIZE CHANGE   @E@@@@                   LINE\TYPE\WIDE :=BY
)@@G@@ NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(I);    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" IF SPACEBAND CONVERT TO BLANBZ

)@@G@@) EQ FUNC\SPACEBAND THEN "    @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @B@@@@      CB

)@@G@@                      LINE\BUFFER(LI) := BLANK; " TURN INTO A BLANK     CK
)@@G@@@C@@@@                    END; " TWO SPACEBAND TEST   @C@@@@            CL
