)@@G@@9(G@@D9!D@@A9(G@@FC00^@F*[S@@@*SDFF*@E@@@@MODULE; " HYPHENATE (IF POSSIBKZ
)@@G@@LE) THE WORD IN NEXT\WORD.    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          COPY ('DEFINESLA
)@@G@@',IMPORTED);+@@@@[+@@@@@+@@@@[+@@@@@@B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPLB
)@@G@@ORTED);     +@@@@[+@@@@@@B@@@@          COPY ('CHAR-SIZE',IMPORTED);    LC
)@@G@@+@@@@[+@@@@@@B@@@@          COPY ('CONVERT-PROC',IMPORTED); +@@@@[+@@@@@LD
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('EDIT-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('GLE
)@@G@@ETPUT-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('HYPHEN-DEF',IMPORTED);   LF
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('STAGING-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('SLG
)@@G@@YMBOL-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('SYMBOL-PROCS',IMPORTED); LH
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE MOVE\NEXT\WORD\TO\LINE IMPORTED ('MOVNWL'); LI
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@" SHIFT ACTION EQUIVALENCES   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@DEFINELJ
)@@G@@    RESTORE     = 4,    @ @@@@          SHIFT\LEFT  = 2,    @ @@@@      LK
)@@G@@    SHIFT\RIGHT = 1;    @[@@@@"     @A@@@@" END SHIFT ACTION EQUIVALENCELL
)@@G@@S     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@DEFINE    FLNG = 50,    @^@@@@          HLNG = 2LM
)@@G@@*FLNG,@^@@@@          SLNG = 6*FLNG;@D@@@@DECLARE   TABLE\PTR : STATIC MLN
)@@G@@ACHINE WORD POINTER     @D@@@@          ,USE\TBL\PTR : STATIC MACHINE WOLO
)@@G@@RD POINTER; @A@@@@DECLARE   *: BASED(TABLE\PTR) MAPPED@B@@@@          [ALP
)@@G@@CTION\FLGS: [*: 3 BIT LOGICAL @D@@@@                        ,SUFFIX\FLG LQ
)@@G@@: 3 BIT CONDITION]@B@@@@          ,ENTRY\LNG  : 3 BIT LOGICAL     @B@@@@LR
)@@G@@          ,NUM\ENTRIES: 9 BIT LOGICAL     @B@@@@          ,FOUND\LNK  : LS
)@@G@@9 BIT LOGICAL     @B@@@@          ,NOT\FND\LNK: 9 BIT LOGICAL     @C@@@@LT
)@@G@@          ,FND\TBL\PTR: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER  @C@@@@          ,NOT\FNDLU
)@@G@@\PTR: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER  @C@@@@          ,FULL\WRD(FLNG)   : 36 BITLV
)@@G@@ LOGICAL    @C@@@@          !HALF\WRD(HLNG)   : 18 BIT LOGICAL    @C@@@@LW
)@@G@@          !SIXTH\WRD(SLNG)  :  6 BIT LOGICAL];  @E@@@@DECLARE   KEY\DERILX
)@@G@@VATIVE(26): STATIC 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER @C@@@@                        LY
)@@G@@  IMPORTED ('KEY');     @C@@@@DECLARE   *(676): MAPPED STATIC IMPORTED (LZ
)@@G@@'DG') @E@@@@          [LOCK\BITS: 3 BIT LOGICAL, DIGRAM: 3 BIT LOGICAL];MA
)@@G@@@E@@@@DECLARE   TYPE: STATUS(S'VOWEL',S'CONSONANT',S'ORTHOGRAPH', @D@@@@MB
)@@G@@          S'BLANK',S'APOSTROPHE',S'NOT\ACCEPTABLE');  @A@@@@DECLARE   CHMC
)@@G@@R: STATIC WORD INTEGER  @A@@@@          ,PTR: STATIC WORD INTEGER @C@@@@MD
)@@G@@          ,RIGHT\POINTER: STATIC WORD INTEGER   @C@@@@          ,BREAK\IME
)@@G@@NDEX: STATIC WORD INTEGER     @C@@@@          ,WORD\WIDTH\LEFT: STATIC DMF
)@@G@@ISTANCE     @B@@@@          ,SPACE\LEFT: STATIC DISTANCE    @C@@@@      MG
)@@G@@    ,DEVICE\HYPHEN\WIDTH: STATIC DISTANCE @B@@@@          ,LNG\STRING: SMH
)@@G@@TATIC WORD INTEGER@C@@@@          ,DG\PTR: STATIC 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGERMI
)@@G@@@E@@@@          ,LAST\LOCK\BITS: STATIC 3 BIT MACHINE LOGICAL     @D@@@@MJ
)@@G@@          ,DG\VALUE: STATIC 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER    @E@@@@          ,LMK
)@@G@@AST\DG\VALUE: STATIC 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER     @B@@@@          ,STRING:ML
)@@G@@ 36 BIT MACHINE INTEGER;@D@@@@DECLARE   FORWARD\LINK: STATIC 9 BIT MACHIMM
)@@G@@NE LOGICAL  @B@@@@          !*: MAPPED [*: 1 BIT LOGICAL    @D@@@@      MN
)@@G@@               ,REENTER\SEARCH: 1 BIT CONDITION @D@@@@                  MO
)@@G@@   ,HYPHEN\EXIT: 1 BIT CONDITION    @D@@@@                     ,SHIFT\ACMP
)@@G@@TION: 3 BIT LOGICAL     @D@@@@                     ,SHIFT\COUNT: 3 BIT LMQ
)@@G@@OGICAL];    @B@@@@DECLARE   STRIP\SUFFIX: STATIC CONDITION  @B@@@@      MR
)@@G@@    ,INITIAL\ENTRY: STATIC CONDITION@B@@@@          ,SUFFIX\FOUND: STATIMS
)@@G@@C CONDITION @C@@@@          ,BREAKPOINT\FOUND: STATIC CONDITION   @C@@@@MT
)@@G@@          ,ORTHOGRAPH\FOUND: STATIC CONDITION;  @B@@@@DECLARE   NODE: STMU
)@@G@@ATIC MACHINE POINTER    @A@@@@          ,CORE: WORD INTEGER BASED @D@@@@MV
)@@G@@          ,SYMBOL(32): STATIC 9 BIT MACHINE LOGICAL   @D@@@@          !SMW
)@@G@@YMWRD(8): LOCATABLE MACHINE WORD INTEGER  @D@@@@          ,VECTOR(12): SMX
)@@G@@TATIC 9 BIT MACHINE LOGICAL   @B@@@@          !VECWRD(3): MACHINE WORD IMY
)@@G@@NTEGER@B@@@@          ,SYM\LEN: STATIC WORD INTEGER   @B@@@@          ,VMZ
)@@G@@INDEX: STATIC WORD INTEGER;   @C@@@@DECLARE   TEMPS  : [VOWELS     : WORNA
)@@G@@D INTEGER   @C@@@@                   ,CONSONANTS : WORD INTEGER]  @E@@@@NB
)@@G@@                  ![TEST\STRING: 36 BIT MACHINE INTEGER     @E@@@@      NC
)@@G@@             ,ENTRY      : 36 BIT MACHINE INTEGER]    @C@@@@            ND
)@@G@@      ![ILLEGAL\CHRS  : WORD INTEGER@C@@@@                   ,INDEX     NE
)@@G@@ : WORD INTEGER]; @B@@@@          INCLUDE (DEBUG\CODE, NO SOURCE);@E@@@@NF
)@@G@@DECLARE   HYPHEN\VECTOR(12): STATIC 9 BIT MACHINE LOGICAL   @C@@@@      NG
)@@G@@    ,VECTOR\INDEX: STATIC WORD INTEGER;   @D@@@@PROCEDURE DISPLAY\NEXT\WNH
)@@G@@ORD IMPORTED ('DISNXTWRD');   @#@@@@          RESUME; @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECNI
)@@G@@T);   @ @@@@PROCEDURE TRYHYPHEN EXPORTED  @[@@@@"     @[@@@@BEGIN @^@@@@NJ
)@@G@@" BEGIN PROCEDURE BODY  @B@@@@          INCLUDE (DEBUG\CODE, NO SOURCE);NK
)@@G@@@A@@@@             DISPLAY\NEXT\WORD;     @#@@@@          RESUME; @ @@@@NL
)@@G@@          IF NOT HYPHEN THEN  @^@@@@             RETURN;    @A@@@@      NM
)@@G@@    ORTHOGRAPH\FOUND:=FALSE;  @D@@@@          IF NEXT\WORD(WORD\INDEX) ENN
)@@G@@Q FUNC\BLANK OR   @E@@@@             NEXT\WORD(WORD\INDEX) EQ FUNC\SPACENO
)@@G@@BAND THEN   @B@@@@             RIGHT\POINTER:=WORD\INDEX-1; @#@@@@      NP
)@@G@@    ELSE    @B@@@@             RIGHT\POINTER:=WORD\INDEX;   @ @@@@      NQ
)@@G@@    PTR:=RIGHT\POINTER; @ @@@@          ILLEGAL\CHRS:=0;    @B@@@@      NR
)@@G@@    WORD\WIDTH\LEFT:=WORD\WIDTH;    @^@@@@          VINDEX:=0;    @ @@@@NS
)@@G@@          FOR I:=1 TO PTR DO  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@            NT
)@@G@@ CHR:=NEXT\WORD(I);     @ @@@@             GET\CHR\TYPE;    @B@@@@      NU
)@@G@@       IF TYPE EQ S'ORTHOGRAPH' THEN@^@@@@              BEGIN     @B@@@@NV
)@@G@@                ORTHOGRAPH\FOUND:=TRUE;   @A@@@@                VINDEX:=NW
)@@G@@VINDEX+1;   @A@@@@                VECTOR(VINDEX+1):=I;@ @@@@            NX
)@@G@@    ITERATE I;    @#@@@@              END;@B@@@@             IF TYPE EQ NY
)@@G@@S'APOSTROPHE' THEN@^@@@@              BEGIN     @C@@@@                IFNZ
)@@G@@ PTR EQ RIGHT\POINTER THEN    @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @D@@@@      OA
)@@G@@             FOR J:=RIGHT\POINTER TO I BY -1 DO @H@@@@                  OB
)@@G@@    WORD\WIDTH\LEFT:=WORD\WIDTH\LEFT-NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(J);    @B@@@@      OC
)@@G@@             RIGHT\POINTER:=I-1;    @^@@@@                 END;   @^@@@@OD
)@@G@@                ELSE    @C@@@@                   ILLEGAL\CHRS:=ILLEGAL\COE
)@@G@@HRS+1;@#@@@@              END;@#@@@@             ELSE @C@@@@            OF
)@@G@@    IF TYPE EQ S'NOT\ACCEPTABLE' OR @B@@@@                   TYPE EQ S'BOG
)@@G@@LANK' THEN  @C@@@@                   ILLEGAL\CHRS:=ILLEGAL\CHRS+1;@#@@@@OH
)@@G@@           END;   @A@@@@          IF ORTHOGRAPH\FOUND THEN  @#@@@@      OI
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @ @@@@             VINDEX:=VINDEX+1;@A@@@@             VECTOOJ
)@@G@@R(1):=VINDEX;     @B@@@@             WORD\WIDTH\LEFT:=WORD\WIDTH; @A@@@@OK
)@@G@@             RIGHT\POINTER:=PTR;    @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@      OL
)@@G@@    ELSE    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             IF ILLEGAL\CHRS GOM
)@@G@@T 0 THEN    @^@@@@                RETURN; @#@@@@           END;   @]@@@@ON
)@@G@@SET\LIMITS: @F@@@@          DEVICE\HYPHEN\WIDTH:=CHAR\WIDTH( DEVICE\HYPHOO
)@@G@@EN\CHAR+1 );@F@@@@          SPACE\LEFT:=MAX\WIDTH-LINE\WIDTH-DEVICE\HYPHOP
)@@G@@EN\WIDTH;   @B@@@@          INCLUDE (DEBUG\CODE, NO SOURCE);@F@@@@      OQ
)@@G@@       SPACE\LEFT:=0;  " FORCE FIND ON ALL HYPHEN POINTS    @ @@@@      OR
)@@G@@       VECTOR\INDEX:=1; @A@@@@             HYPHEN\VECTOR(1):=PTR; @#@@@@OS
)@@G@@          RESUME; @F@@@@          IF (MAX\WIDTH*SPACE\REMAINING) GT (100OT
)@@G@@*SPACE\LEFT) THEN @^@@@@             RETURN;    @ @@@@          INITIAL\OU
)@@G@@ENTRY:=TRUE;@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @#@@@@FIND\BREAK\POINT: @^@@@@      OV
)@@G@@    HYPHENATE;    @A@@@@          IF BREAKPOINT\FOUND THEN  @#@@@@      OW
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @C@@@@             INCLUDE (DEBUG\CODE, NO SOURCE);   @C@@@@OX
)@@G@@                VECTOR\INDEX:=VECTOR\INDEX+1;   @E@@@@                HYOY
)@@G@@PHEN\VECTOR(VECTOR\INDEX):=BREAK\INDEX;   @^@@@@             RESUME;    OZ
)@@G@@@E]@@@             FOR I:=RIGHT\POINTER TO BREAK\INDEX+1 BY -1 DO @G@@@@PA
)@@G@@                WORD\WIDTH\LEFT:=WORD\WIDTH\LEFT-NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(I);    PB
)@@G@@+@@@@[+@@@@@@D@@@@             IF (WORD\WIDTH\LEFT GT SPACE\LEFT) OR    PC
)@@G@@@D@@@@                (BREAK\INDEX LT CHARS\THIS\LINE) OR   @F@@@@      PD
)@@G@@          (WORD\INDEX-BREAK\INDEX LE CHARS\NEXT\LINE) THEN  @^@@@@      PE
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @B@@@@                INITIAL\ENTRY:=FALSE;     @C@@@@PF
)@@G@@                RIGHT\POINTER:=BREAK\INDEX;     @B@@@@                GOPG
)@@G@@TO FIND\BREAK\POINT;    @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@             ELSE PH
)@@G@@@A@@@@                GOTO END\HYPHEN;    @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@PI
)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @]@@@@GIVE\UP:    @B@@@@          INCLUDE (DEBUG\CODE,PJ
)@@G@@ NO SOURCE);@C@@@@             HYPHEN\VECTOR(VECTOR\INDEX+1):=0;  @^@@@@PK
)@@G@@             EDIT\OPEN; @C@@@@             FOR I:=VECTOR\INDEX TO 1 BY -PL
)@@G@@1 DO  @^@@@@              BEGIN     @C@@@@                INDEX:=HYPHEN\PM
)@@G@@VECTOR(I+1)+1;    @E@@@@                FOR J:=INDEX TO HYPHEN\VECTOR(I)PN
)@@G@@ BY 1 DO    @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @B@@@@                   CHR:=PO
)@@G@@NEXT\WORD(J);     @B@@@@                   EDIT\CHARACTER(CHR);   @^@@@@PP
)@@G@@                 END;   @ @@@@                IF I GT 1 THEN@^@@@@      PQ
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@                   GET\CHR\TYPE;    @C@@@@      PR
)@@G@@             IF TYPE NE S'ORTHOGRAPH' THEN@C@@@@                      EDPS
)@@G@@IT\CHARACTER(MINUS);    @^@@@@                 END;   @#@@@@            PT
)@@G@@  END;@ @@@@             EDIT\PRINT (1);  @#@@@@          RESUME; @#@@@@PU
)@@G@@          RETURN; @]@@@@END\HYPHEN: @E@@@@          PTR:=WORD\INDEX+1;  PV
)@@G@@" POINT TO FIRST UNUSED SPACE @C@@@@          BREAK\INDEX:=WORD\INDEX-BRPW
)@@G@@EAK\INDEX;  @D@@@@          WORD\WIDTH\LEFT:=WORD\WIDTH-WORD\WIDTH\LEFT;PX
)@@G@@@C@@@@          WORD\INDEX:=WORD\INDEX-BREAK\INDEX;   @D@@@@          WOPY
)@@G@@RD\WIDTH:=WORD\WIDTH-WORD\WIDTH\LEFT;     @A@@@@          IF ORTHOGRAPH\PZ
)@@G@@FOUND THEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             IF NEXT\WORD(WORDQA
)@@G@@\INDEX) NE FUNC\HYPHEN THEN   @A@@@@                GOTO MOVE\TO\LINE;  QB
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @E@@@@          ELSE  " MAKE SPACE FOR HYPHEN IFQC
)@@G@@ NOT FUNC\HYPHEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             WORD\INDEX:QD
)@@G@@=WORD\INDEX+1;  " PLUS 1 FOR HYPHEN @G@@@@             NEXT\WORD(PTR):=NQE
)@@G@@EXT\WORD(WORD\INDEX);  " SAVE CHARACTER   @F@@@@             NEXT\CHAR\WQF
)@@G@@IDTH(PTR):=NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(WORD\INDEX);   @#@@@@           END;   @H@@@@QG
)@@G@@          WORD\WIDTH:=WORD\WIDTH+DEVICE\HYPHEN\WIDTH;  " ADD HYPHEN WIDTQH
)@@G@@H     @G@@@@          NEXT\WORD(WORD\INDEX):=DEVICE\HYPHEN\CHAR;  " INSEQI
)@@G@@RT HYPHEN   @E@@@@          NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(WORD\INDEX):=DEVICE\HYPHEN\WQJ
)@@G@@IDTH; @#@@@@MOVE\TO\LINE:     @ @@@@          INDEX:=WORD\INDEX;  @A@@@@QK
)@@G@@          MOVE\NEXT\WORD\TO\LINE;   @A@@@@          WORD\INDEX:=BREAK\INQL
)@@G@@DEX;  @B@@@@          WORD\WIDTH:=WORD\WIDTH\LEFT;    @G@@@@          IFQM
)@@G@@ NOT ORTHOGRAPH\FOUND THEN  " RETRIEVE DISPLACED CHARACTER  @#@@@@      QN
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @C@@@@             NEXT\WORD(INDEX):=NEXT\WORD(PTR);  @E@@@@QO
)@@G@@             NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(INDEX):=NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(PTR);  @C@@@@      QP
)@@G@@       INDEX:=INDEX-1;  " RESET INDEX     @#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@QQ
)@@G@@          FOR I:=1 TO WORD\INDEX BY 1 DO  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@QR
)@@G@@             NEXT\WORD(I):=NEXT\WORD(INDEX+I);  @E@@@@             NEXT\QS
)@@G@@CHAR\WIDTH(I):=NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(INDEX+I);  @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@QT
)@@G@@          RETURN; @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@QU
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE GET\CHR\TYPE  @[@@@@ BEGIN@B@@@@          IF CHR GQV
)@@G@@E ASCII\LOWER\A AND     @B@@@@             CHR LE ASCII\LOWER\Z THEN    QW
)@@G@@@B@@@@             IF CHR EQ ASCII\LOWER\A OR   @B@@@@                CHQX
)@@G@@R EQ ASCII\LOWER\E OR   @B@@@@                CHR EQ ASCII\LOWER\I OR   QY
)@@G@@@B@@@@                CHR EQ ASCII\LOWER\O OR   @B@@@@                CHQZ
)@@G@@R EQ ASCII\LOWER\U OR   @B@@@@                CHR EQ ASCII\LOWER\Y THEN RA
)@@G@@@A@@@@                TYPE:=S'VOWEL';     @#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@RB
)@@G@@                TYPE:=S'CONSONANT'; @#@@@@          ELSE    @ @@@@      RC
)@@G@@       CASEENTRY CHR    @D@@@@                CASE MINUS, FUNC\HYPHEN, FRD
)@@G@@UNC\BREAK:  @B@@@@                   TYPE:=S'ORTHOGRAPH';   @E@@@@      RE
)@@G@@          CASE BLANK, FUNC\BLANK, FUNC\SPACEBAND:     @A@@@@            RF
)@@G@@       TYPE:=S'BLANK';  @ @@@@                CASE QUOTE:   @B@@@@      RG
)@@G@@             TYPE:=S'APOSTROPHE';   @^@@@@                CASE *: @C@@@@RH
)@@G@@                   TYPE:=S'NOT\ACCEPTABLE';     @^@@@@             ENDCARI
)@@G@@SE;   @#@@@@          RETURN; @[@@@@ END; @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECRJ
)@@G@@T);   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE HYPHENATE     @[@@@@ BEGIN@ @@@@      RK
)@@G@@    PTR:=RIGHT\POINTER; @A@@@@          BREAKPOINT\FOUND:=FALSE;  @E@@@@RL
)@@G@@          IF NOT ORTHOGRAPH\FOUND AND INITIAL\ENTRY THEN    @#@@@@      RM
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @B@@@@             IF TABP NE NULL\PTR THEN     @^@@@@      RN
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @A@@@@                SYM\LEN:=(PTR+3)//4;@B@@@@      RO
)@@G@@          FOR I:=1 TO SYM\LEN DO    @A@@@@                   SYMWRD(I):=RP
)@@G@@0;    @A@@@@                FOR I:=1 TO PTR DO  @C@@@@                  RQ
)@@G@@ SYMBOL(I):=NEXT\WORD(I);     @D@@@@                NODE:=SEARCH\FOR\NODRR
)@@G@@E(TABP,TYPSTR,    @C@@@@                      SYM\LEN,LOC(SYMWRD(1)));  RS
)@@G@@@E@@@@                IF NODE NE NULL\PTR THEN  " WE'VE GOT WORD  @^@@@@RT
)@@G@@                 BEGIN  @C@@@@                   FOR I:=1 TO DLEN(NODE) RU
)@@G@@DO    @D@@@@                      VECWRD(I):=CORE(DADR(NODE)+I-1);@B@@@@RV
)@@G@@                   VINDEX:=VECTOR(1);     @^@@@@                 END;   RW
)@@G@@@#@@@@              END;@A@@@@             IF VINDEX EQ 0 THEN    @^@@@@RX
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @G@@@@                IF WORD\INDEX LT 6 THEN  "RY
)@@G@@ DON'T HYPHENATE SHORT WORDS  @ @@@@                   RETURN;    @A@@@@RZ
)@@G@@                STRIP\SUFFIX:=TRUE; @B@@@@                REENTER\SEARCHSA
)@@G@@:=FALSE;    @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@      SB
)@@G@@    IF VINDEX GT 0 THEN @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             IF VISC
)@@G@@NDEX EQ 1 THEN    @^@@@@                RETURN; @A@@@@             PTR:=SD
)@@G@@VECTOR(VINDEX);   @ @@@@             VINDEX:=VINDEX-1;@ @@@@            SE
)@@G@@ GOTO BREAK\FOUND;@#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          WHILE STRIP\SUSF
)@@G@@FFIX DO     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             SEARCH\DERIVATIVESG
)@@G@@\TABLES;    @A@@@@             IF HYPHEN\EXIT THEN    @^@@@@            SH
)@@G@@  BEGIN     @D@@@@                HYPHEN\EXIT:=FALSE;  " CLEAR EXIT FLAGSI
)@@G@@@A@@@@                GOTO CHECK\LEFT;    @#@@@@              END;@E@@@@SJ
)@@G@@             IF INITIAL\ENTRY AND NOT SUFFIX\FOUND THEN     @^@@@@      SK
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @E@@@@                IF NEXT\WORD(PTR) EQ ASCII\LOWERSL
)@@G@@\S THEN     @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @ @@@@                   PTR:=SM
)@@G@@PTR-1;@B@@@@                   STRIP\SUFFIX:=TRUE;    @^@@@@            SN
)@@G@@     END;   @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@CONTROSO
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @^@@@@SEARCH\DIGRAM\TABLE:    @D@@@@          IF NEXT\WORD(PSP
)@@G@@TR) EQ ASCII\LOWER\E THEN     @C@@@@             PTR:=PTR-1;  " STRIP OFSQ
)@@G@@F SILENT E  @A@@@@          FOR I:=PTR TO 3 BY -1 DO  @#@@@@           BSR
)@@G@@EGIN  @A@@@@             CHR:=NEXT\WORD(I);     @ @@@@             GET\CSS
)@@G@@HR\TYPE;    @B@@@@             IF TYPE EQ S'VOWEL' THEN     @^@@@@      ST
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @^@@@@                PTR:=I; @A@@@@                GOSU
)@@G@@TO LOOKUP\DIGRAMS;@#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@SV
)@@G@@          RETURN; @#@@@@LOOKUP\DIGRAMS:   @ @@@@          LAST\LOCK\BITSSW
)@@G@@:=0;  @ @@@@          LAST\DG\VALUE:=0;   @A@@@@          FOR I:=PTR TO SX
)@@G@@2 BY -1 DO  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @^@@@@             DG\PTR:=I; @A@@@@SY
)@@G@@             LOOKUP\DIGRAM\VALUE;   @A@@@@             IF DG\VALUE NE 0 SZ
)@@G@@THEN  @^@@@@              BEGIN     @A@@@@                PTR:=I-2+DG\VATA
)@@G@@LUE;  @A@@@@                GOTO CHECK\LEFT;    @#@@@@              END;TB
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@          RETURN; @]@@@@CHECK\LEFT: @^@@@@TC
)@@G@@          VOWELS:=0;    @^@@@@          CONSONANTS:=0;@A@@@@          FOTD
)@@G@@R I:=PTR TO 1 BY -1 DO  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             CHR:=TE
)@@G@@NEXT\WORD(I);     @ @@@@             GET\CHR\TYPE;    @B@@@@            TF
)@@G@@ IF TYPE EQ S'VOWEL' THEN     @A@@@@                VOWELS:=VOWELS+1;   TG
)@@G@@@B@@@@             IF TYPE EQ S'CONSONANT' THEN @B@@@@                COTH
)@@G@@NSONANTS:=CONSONANTS+1; @A@@@@             IF VOWELS GE 1 AND     @A@@@@TI
)@@G@@                CONSONANTS GE 1 THEN@A@@@@                GOTO BREAK\FOUTJ
)@@G@@ND;   @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@          RETURN; @]@@@@BREAK\FOUND:TK
)@@G@@@ @@@@          BREAK\INDEX:=PTR;   @A@@@@          BREAKPOINT\FOUND:=TRTL
)@@G@@UE;   @#@@@@          RETURN; @[@@@@ END; @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECTM
)@@G@@T);   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDURE SEARCH\DERIVATIVE\TABLES  @[@@@@ BEGINTN
)@@G@@@ @@@@          STRIP\SUFFIX:=FALSE;@ @@@@          SUFFIX\FOUND:=FALSE;TO
)@@G@@@E@@@@          BREAK\INDEX:=PTR;  " SAVE POINTER FOR RESTORE     @A@@@@TP
)@@G@@          IF REENTER\SEARCH THEN    @B@@@@             GOTO CONCATENATE\TQ
)@@G@@STRING;     @ @@@@          IF PTR LE 3 THEN    @^@@@@             RETURTR
)@@G@@N;    @B@@@@          INDEX:=NEXT\WORD(PTR-1)-O'140'; @C@@@@          USTS
)@@G@@E\TBL\PTR:=KEY\DERIVATIVE(INDEX);   @^@@@@CONCATENATE\STRING:     @^@@@@TT
)@@G@@          STRING:=0;    @^@@@@          INDEX:=PTR-5; @ @@@@          IFTU
)@@G@@ INDEX LE 0 THEN  @^@@@@             INDEX:=1;  @B@@@@          FOR I:=ITV
)@@G@@NDEX TO PTR BY 1 DO     @E@@@@             STRING:=STRING*2**6+(NEXT\WORTW
)@@G@@D(I)-O'133');     @A@@@@          LNG\STRING:=PTR-INDEX+1;  @#@@@@MATCH\TX
)@@G@@ENTRIES:    @#@@@@          MATCH;  @A@@@@          IF FORWARD\LINK EQ 0TY
)@@G@@ THEN @^@@@@             RETURN;    @]@@@@NEXT\LEVEL: @A@@@@          CATZ
)@@G@@SEENTRY SHIFT\ACTION    @ @@@@             CASE RESTORE:    @^@@@@      UA
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @H@@@@                STRIP\SUFFIX:=FALSE;  " OVERRIDEUB
)@@G@@ TABLE TO PREVENT LOOPING     @A@@@@                PTR:=BREAK\INDEX;   UC
)@@G@@@^@@@@                RETURN; @#@@@@              END;@ @@@@            UD
)@@G@@ CASE SHIFT\LEFT: @B@@@@                PTR:=PTR-SHIFT\COUNT;     @ @@@@UE
)@@G@@             CASE SHIFT\RIGHT:@B@@@@                PTR:=PTR+SHIFT\COUNTUF
)@@G@@;     @#@@@@          ENDCASE;@ @@@@          IF HYPHEN\EXIT THEN @#@@@@UG
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             IF REENTER\SEARCH THEN @D@@@@      UH
)@@G@@          STRIP\SUFFIX:=TRUE;  " OVERRIDE TABLE @^@@@@             RETURUI
)@@G@@N;    @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          IF SHIFT\COUNT EQ 0 THEN  UJ
)@@G@@@A@@@@             GOTO MATCH\ENTRIES;    @#@@@@          ELSE    @B@@@@UK
)@@G@@             GOTO CONCATENATE\STRING;     @[@@@@ END; @[@@@@"     @#@@@@UL
)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @#@@@@PROCEDURE MATCH   @[@@@@ BEGIN@#@@@@UM
)@@G@@MATCH\STRING:     @ @@@@          FORWARD\LINK:=0;    @B@@@@          IFUN
)@@G@@ USE\TBL\PTR EQ NULL\PTR THEN @^@@@@             RETURN;    @A@@@@      UO
)@@G@@    TABLE\PTR:=USE\TBL\PTR;   @ @@@@          CASEENTRY ENTRY\LNG @^@@@@UP
)@@G@@             CASE 6:    @A@@@@                TEST\STRING:=STRING;@^@@@@UQ
)@@G@@             CASE 5:    @C@@@@                TEST\STRING:=STRING(7 TO 3UR
)@@G@@6);   @^@@@@             CASE 4:    @C@@@@                TEST\STRING:=SUS
)@@G@@TRING(13 TO 36);  @^@@@@             CASE 3:    @C@@@@                TEUT
)@@G@@ST\STRING:=STRING(19 TO 36);  @^@@@@             CASE 2:    @C@@@@      UU
)@@G@@          TEST\STRING:=STRING(25 TO 36);  @^@@@@             CASE 1:    UV
)@@G@@@C@@@@                TEST\STRING:=STRING(31 TO 36);  @C@@@@            UW
)@@G@@ CASE 0:  " FORCE FIND ON NULL ENTRY@A@@@@                GOTO STRING\FOUX
)@@G@@UND;  @#@@@@          ENDCASE;@B@@@@          FOR I:=1 TO NUM\ENTRIES BYUY
)@@G@@ 1 DO @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             CASEENTRY ENTRY\LNG    UZ
)@@G@@@ @@@@                CASE 4, 5, 6: @B@@@@                   ENTRY:=FULLVA
)@@G@@\WRD(I);    @ @@@@                CASE 2, 3:    @B@@@@                  VB
)@@G@@ ENTRY:=HALF\WRD(I);    @^@@@@                CASE 1: @B@@@@            VC
)@@G@@       ENTRY:=SIXTH\WRD(I);   @^@@@@             ENDCASE;   @B@@@@      VD
)@@G@@       IF TEST\STRING LT ENTRY THEN @B@@@@                GOTO STRING\NOVE
)@@G@@T\FOUND;    @B@@@@             IF TEST\STRING EQ ENTRY THEN @A@@@@      VF
)@@G@@          GOTO STRING\FOUND;  @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@STRING\NOT\FVG
)@@G@@OUND: @A@@@@          FORWARD\LINK:=NOT\FND\LNK;@A@@@@          USE\TBL\VH
)@@G@@PTR:=NOT\FND\PTR; @#@@@@          RETURN; @#@@@@STRING\FOUND:     @ @@@@VI
)@@G@@          SUFFIX\FOUND:=TRUE; @A@@@@          STRIP\SUFFIX:=SUFFIX\FLG; VJ
)@@G@@@A@@@@          FORWARD\LINK:=FOUND\LNK;  @A@@@@          USE\TBL\PTR:=FVK
)@@G@@ND\TBL\PTR; @#@@@@          RETURN; @[@@@@ END; @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROVL
)@@G@@L (EJECT);  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE LOOKUP\DIGRAM\VALUE @[@@@@ BEGINVM
)@@G@@@C@@@@          INDEX:=NEXT\WORD(DG\PTR-1)-O'141';    @D@@@@          INVN
)@@G@@DEX:=INDEX*26+(NEXT\WORD(DG\PTR)-O'140'); @A@@@@          DG\VALUE:=DIGRVO
)@@G@@AM(INDEX);  @F@@@@          LAST\LOCK\BITS:=LAST\LOCK\BITS LAND LOCK\BITVP
)@@G@@S(INDEX);   @B@@@@          IF LAST\LOCK\BITS EQ 0 THEN     @#@@@@      VQ
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @C@@@@             LAST\LOCK\BITS:=LOCK\BITS(INDEX);  @B@@@@VR
)@@G@@             IF LAST\DG\VALUE NE 0 THEN   @D@@@@                DG\VALUEVS
)@@G@@:=2;  " TAKE LAST BREAKPOINT  @#@@@@             ELSE @C@@@@            VT
)@@G@@    IF LAST\LOCK\BITS NE 0 THEN     @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @C@@@@VU
)@@G@@                   LAST\DG\VALUE:=DG\VALUE;     @A@@@@                  VV
)@@G@@ DG\VALUE:=0;     @^@@@@                 END;   @#@@@@           END;   VW
)@@G@@@#@@@@          ELSE    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             DG\VAVX
)@@G@@LUE:=LAST\LOCK\BITS//2; @C@@@@             LAST\LOCK\BITS:=0;  " CLEAR LVY
)@@G@@OCK   @ @@@@             LAST\DG\VALUE:=0;@#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@VZ
)@@G@@          RETURN; @[@@@@ END; @[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@    CASE 2, WA
)@@G@@3:    @B@@@@                   ENTRY:=HALF\WRD(I);    @^@@@@            WB
)@@G@@    CASE 1: @B@@@@                   ENTRY:=SIXT)@@[U@@[@K@@/K@@@@/K@@@[WC

)@@G@@@D@@@]" INTERNAL VARIABLES USED BY THIS DEVICE HANDLER.     @[@@@]"     TC
)@@G@@@G@@@]" CHAR AND WIDTH CODES FOR MERGENTHALER FONTS ARE IN ELEMENT M202-TD
)@@G@@FONTS.@G@@@]" THE FOLLOWING STATIC TABLE DEFINES THE PROPERTIES OF THE FTE
)@@G@@ONTS. FIELD @F@@@]" FDT\CDTP PROVIDES THE POINTERS TO THE (DYNAMIC) CDT TF
)@@G@@TABLES.     @[@@@]"     @G@@@]DECLARE   MAX\FONT\NUM: STATIC INTEGER WORTG
)@@G@@D IMPORTED ('M202FONTN');     @[@@@]"     @G@@@]DECLARE   *(*): STATIC MTH
)@@G@@APPED IMPORTED ('M202FONTS') " IN M202-FONTS    @G@@@]             [FDT\TI
)@@G@@FLAG: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER " ELECTRONIC SLANT FLAG  @G@@@]            TJ
)@@G@@ ,FDT\WIDE: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER " CONSTANT WIDTH FONT    @E@@@]      TK
)@@G@@       ,*:        6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER " UNUSED     @G@@@]            TL
)@@G@@ ,FDT\CDTP: 18 BIT MACHINE POINTER " TO CDT FOR THIS FONT   @#@@@]      TM
)@@G@@       ];   @[@@@]"     @B@@@]" FONT FLAGS FOUND IN FIELD FDT\FLAG.     TN
)@@G@@@D@@@]" ** MUST CORRESPOND TO THOSE IN MODULE M202-FONTS! **@[@@@]"     TO
)@@G@@@D@@@]DEFINE    IROMAN = 0;     " ROMAN (NON-ITALIC) FONT   @E@@@]DEFINETP

)@@G@@ALIC = 2;     " REAL ITALIC - ONLY SLANT SIMU CHARACTERS    @[@@@]"     TR
)@@G@@@H@@@]" FDT\CDTP FOR THE CURRENT FONT PROVIDES A POINTER TO THE ACTUAL CTS
)@@G@@HARACTER    @H@@@]" DEFINITION TABLE OR CDT. SO THAT WE MAY INDEX WITH TTT
)@@G@@HE CHARACTER CODE, THIS @I@@@]" TABLE IS IMPLICITLY BASED ON POINTER CDTTU
)@@G@@\POINTER, WHICH MUST BE CORRECTLY SET.    @[@@@]"     @H@@@]DECLARE   CDTV
)@@G@@T\POINTER: MACHINE WORD POINTER; " TEMP PTR TO ACTUAL FONTDEF     @[@@@]TW
)@@G@@"     @C@@@]DECLARE   *(256): MAPPED BASED(CDT\POINTER)     @H@@@]      TX
)@@G@@       [CDT\TYPE: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER " CHARACTER TYPE/ACTION FLAG   TY
)@@G@@@H@@@]             ,CDT\WIDE: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER " CHARACTER WIDTH ITZ
)@@G@@N REL UNITS @H@@@]             ,CDT\JUMP: 6 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER " BASELUA
)@@G@@INE JUMP TO BE APPLIED  @H@@@]             ,CDT\FONT: 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTUB
)@@G@@EGER " FONT IN WHICH CHAR APPEARS   @G@@@]             ,CDT\CODE: 9 BIT UC
)@@G@@UNSIGNED INTEGER " MACHINE CHARACTER CODE @#@@@]             ];   @[@@@]UD
)@@G@@"     @B@@@]" CHARACTER TYPES FOUND IN FIELD CDT\TYPE.@D@@@]" ** MUST COUE
)@@G@@RRESPOND TO THOSE IN MODULE M202-FONTS! **@[@@@]"     @G@@@]DEFINE    NOUF
)@@G@@RMAL = O'0';              " NORMAL CHARACTER (CODE 1-255).  @G@@@]DEFINEUG
)@@G@@    SIMULA = O'1';              " SIMLUATE ITALICS FOR THIS CHAR  @E@@@]UH
)@@G@@DEFINE    VERULE = O'3';              " VERTICAL RULING     @F@@@]DEFINEUI
)@@G@@    HMRULE = O'4';              " HORIZONTAL 'EM' RULING    @F@@@]DEFINEUJ
)@@G@@    HNRULE = O'5';              " HORIZONTAL 'EN' RULING    @[@@@]"     UK
)@@G@@@#@@@]CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@]"     @H@@@]" THERE ARE THREE DIFFERENT COUL
)@@G@@PIES OF MOST DEVICE-HANDLER DATA. THE INTERNAL  @H@@@]" COPY IS USED SYNUM
)@@G@@CHRONOUSLY WITH SCRIPT INPUT, TO PERFORM FONT AND TYPESIZE  @H@@@]" CHANUN
)@@G@@GES. THE EXTERNAL COPY IS USED TO ACTUALLY DRIVE OUTPUT, AND IS SYNCED  UO
)@@G@@@H@@@]" WITH CHANGES DURING CHARACTER OUTPUT. MOST OF THE DEVICE HANDLERUP
)@@G@@ IS SYNCED  @H@@@]" WITH THE OUTPUT, THE INTERNAL DATA IS VERBOTEN. THE UQ
)@@G@@DEVICE COPY OF A DATA   @H@@@]" ITEM IS GENERALLY USED TO PLAY VIRTUAL GUR
)@@G@@AMES, TO AVOID OUTPUTTING MORE CODES@ @@@]" THAN ARE ACTUALLY NEEDED.   US
)@@G@@@[@@@]"     @I@@@]" THE INTERNAL VARIABLES ARE USED TO PASS INFORMATION UT
)@@G@@FROM THE TYPESIZE SCANNER     @F@@@]" TO THE ROUTINES THAT RESET DEVICE UU
)@@G@@HEIGHT AND WIDTH PARAMETERS.  @[@@@]"     @E@@@]DECLARE   IN\HITE: INTEGUV
)@@G@@ER WORD;      " INTERNAL TYPE HEIGHT@E@@@]DECLARE   IN\WIDE: INTEGER WORUW
)@@G@@D;      " INTERNAL TYPE WIDTH @F@@@]DECLARE   IN\LEAD: INTEGER WORD;    UX
)@@G@@  " INTERNAL LEADING VALUE    @[@@@]"     @G@@@]" THE EXTERNAL VARIABLESUY
)@@G@@ HOLD THE CURRENT STATE OF THE OUTPUT CHANNEL.  @F@@@]" COMPARISONS ARE UZ
)@@G@@MADE TO THE DEVICE VARIABLES TO PACK UP MULTIPLE@H@@@]" CHANGES OR COMMAVA
)@@G@@NDS INTO A SINGLE COMMAND, AND TO AVOID REDUNDANT CHANGES.  @[@@@]"     VB
)@@G@@@H@@@]DECLARE   EX\VPOS: INTEGER WORD;      " LOGICAL Y POSITION IN QUARVC
)@@G@@TER POINTS  @H@@@]DECLARE   EX\HPOS: INTEGER WORD;      " LOGICAL X POSIVD
)@@G@@TION IN 7800THS INCH    @E@@@]DECLARE   EX\HITE: INTEGER WORD;      " EXVE
)@@G@@TERNAL TYPE HEIGHT@E@@@]DECLARE   EX\WIDE: INTEGER WORD;      " EXTERNALVF
)@@G@@ TYPE WIDTH @H@@@]DECLARE   CW\WIDE: INTEGER WORD;      " COPY OF ABOVE VG
)@@G@@FOR CONST WIDTH FONT    @D@@@]DECLARE   EX\FONT: INTEGER WORD;      " EXVH
)@@G@@TERNAL FONT @[@@@]"     @H@@@]" EX\ITAL\NORM IS THE DESIRED STATE OF THEVI
)@@G@@ SIMULATE ITALIC FLAG FOR NORMAL    @H@@@]" CHARACTERS IN THE CURRENT FOVJ
)@@G@@NT. EX\ITAL\SIMU IS SAME FOR CHARS BROUGHT INTO @B@@@]" AN ITALIC FONT FVK
)@@G@@ROM A NON-ITALIC FONT.  @[@@@]"     @G@@@]DECLARE   EX\ITAL\NORM: INTEGEVL

)@@G@@INTEGER WORD; " ITALIC FLAG FOR SIMU CHARS@[@@@]"     @H@@@]" THE DEVICEVN
)@@G@@ VARIABLES HOLD THE ACTUAL STATE OF THE TYPESETTING MACHINE AND   @G@@@]VO

)@@G@@@#@@@]" OUTPUT COMMANDS.@[@@@]"     @H@@@]DECLARE   DV\VPOS: INTEGER WORVQ

)@@G@@E   DV\HITE: INTEGER WORD;      " HEIGHT OF TYPE DEVICE IS SETTING@G@@@]VT
)@@G@@DECLARE   DV\WIDE: INTEGER WORD;      " WIDTH OF TYPE DEVICE IS SETTING VU
)@@G@@@G@@@]DECLARE   DV\FONT: INTEGER WORD;      " DEVICE FONT DEVICE IS SETTVV
)@@G@@ING   @H@@@]DECLARE   DV\ITAL: INTEGER WORD;      " CURRENT STATE OF DEVVW
)@@G@@ICES ITALIC FLAG  @[@@@]"     @D@@@]" PARSE\INDEX IS A GLOBAL USED BY M2VX
)@@G@@02\INTERNAL\SIZE. @[@@@]"     @A@@@]DECLARE   PARSE\INDEX: INTEGER WORD;VY
)@@G@@@[@@@]"     @G@@@]" DSI\CHAR CONTAINS ZERO IF NORMAL TEXT IS BEING SET, VZ
)@@G@@AND A NONZERO     @G@@@]" LINOTRON CONTROL CODE IF SUPERSCRIPTS OR SUBSCWA
)@@G@@RIPTS ARE BEING SET.    @[@@@]"     @A@@@]DECLARE   DSI\CHAR: INTEGER WOWB
)@@G@@RD;   @[@@@]"     @G@@@]" ABS\WIDE CONTAINS THE ABSOLUTE WIDTH OF THE LAWC
)@@G@@ST CHARACTER TYPESET.   @[@@@]"     @A@@@]DECLARE   ABS\WIDE: INTEGER WOWD
)@@G@@RD;   @[@@@]"     @G@@@]" BS\FLAG IS SET IFF THE LAST CHAR SEEN WAS A BAWE
)@@G@@CKSPACE (OVERPRINT).    @[@@@]"     @A@@@]DECLARE   BS\FLAG: WORD CONDITWF
)@@G@@ION;  @[@@@]"     @H@@@]" NUM\OUT CONTAINS THE NUMBER OF CHARS SENT SINCWG
)@@G@@E THE LAST END OF LINE FUNC.  @[@@@]"     @A@@@]DECLARE   NUM\OUT: INTEGWH
)@@G@@ER WORD;    @[@@@]"     @G@@@]" LETTER\SPACE HOLDS THE CURRENT AMOUNT OFWI
)@@G@@ LETTERSPACING TO BE USED.    @[@@@]"     @D@@@]DECLARE   LETTER\SPACE: WJ
)@@G@@STATIC INTEGER WORD := 0;     @[@@@]"     @#@@@]CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@]WK
)@@G@@"     @F@@@]" ALL CHARACTER OUTPUT IS DIVERTED THROUGH THIS PROCEDURE SOWL
)@@G@@ THE  @G@@@]" VARIABLE NUM\OUT IS PROPERLY INCREMENTED TO REFLECT THE NUWM
)@@G@@MBER OF     @F@@@]" CHARACTERS OUTPUT SINCE THE LAST END OF LINE FUNCTIOWN
)@@G@@N.  SEE THE @B@@@]" CODE IN M202\PACK THAT TESTS NUM\OUT.   @[@@@]"     WO
)@@G@@@D@@@]PROCEDURE PACK\CHARACTER(CHARACTER: INTEGER WORD)     @[@@@]BEGIN WP
)@@G@@@F@@@]          NUM\OUT := NUM\OUT + 1; " INCREMENT CHARACTER COUNTER   WQ
)@@G@@@[@@@]"     @G@@@]INCLUDE(DEBUG\OUTPUT); ODISPLAY('PAKCHR',CHARACTER); RWR
)@@G@@ESUME; " **DEBUG**@[@@@]"     @H@@@]INCLUDE(NORMAL\OUTPUT); PACK\OUTPUT\WS
)@@G@@CHARACTER(CHARACTER); RESUME; " **DEBUG** @[@@@]"     @^@@@]END; " PACK\WT
)@@G@@CHARACTER   @[@@@]"     @C@@@]PROCEDURE PACK\TAPEFEEDS(NUMBER: INTEGER WWU
)@@G@@ORD)  @[@@@]BEGIN @[@@@]"     @G@@@]INCLUDE(DEBUG\OUTPUT); ODISPLAY('PKFWV
)@@G@@EED',NUMBER); RESUME; " **DEBUG**   @[@@@]"     @^@@@]INCLUDE(NORMAL\OUTWW
)@@G@@PUT); @A@@@]           FOR I := 1 TO NUMBER DO  @G@@@]              PACKWX
)@@G@@\OUTPUT\CHARACTER(M2FEED); " PACK TAPE FEED CHARACTER @]@@@]RESUME;     WY
)@@G@@@[@@@]"     @^@@@]END; " PACK\TAPEFEEDS   @[@@@]"     @E@@@]" THIS PROCEWZ
)@@G@@DURE IS USED TO END A LOGICAL OUTPUT BUFFER.    @[@@@]"     @^@@@]PROCEDXA
)@@G@@URE BREAK\LINE    @[@@@]BEGIN @E@@@]          PACK\CHARACTER(ENDLIN); " XB
)@@G@@OUTPUT LINE END CODE    @D@@@]          NUM\OUT := 0; " CLEAR CHARACTER XC
)@@G@@COUNTER     @D@@@]          DV\HPOS := 0; " SET DEVICE AT ZERO POSITION XD
)@@G@@@#@@@]END; " BREAK\LINE @[@@@]"     @G@@@]" THIS PROCEDURE CONVERTS A 15XE
)@@G@@ BIT SIGNED NUMBER INTO THE TWO OR THREE  @E@@@]" BYTE SEQUENCE NECESSARXF
)@@G@@Y TO DRIVE THE PHOTOTYPESETTER.     @G@@@]" IF THE ARGUMENT IS LESS THANXG
)@@G@@ 128, ONE BYTE MAY BE USED TO EXPRESS     @F@@@]" THE ARGUMENT TO THE FUXH
)@@G@@NCTION. IF THE ARGUMENT IS NEGATIVE OR IS @F@@@]" GREATER THAN 128, THE XI
)@@G@@LOW ORDER 7 BITS ARE OUTPUT (MARKED BY THE@G@@@]" HIGH ORDER OR 0'200' BXJ
)@@G@@IT) THEN THE HIGH ORDER 8. NEGATIVE NUMBERS ARE @G@@@]" EXPRESSED IN TWOXK
)@@G@@'S COMPLEMENT FORM, THE ADD OF 2**15 CONVERTS FROM THE@B@@@]" THE UNIVACXL
)@@G@@ 1100 ONE'S COMPLEMENT FORMAT.@[@@@]"     @ @@@]PROCEDURE PACK\FUNCTION\XM
)@@G@@TWO   @E@@@]             (FUNCTION: INTEGER WORD " FUNCTION LEADIN BYTE XN
)@@G@@@G@@@]             ,ARGUMENT: INTEGER WORD " 15 BIT SIGNED INTEGER ARG TXO
)@@G@@O FN  @#@@@]             )    @[@@@]BEGIN @D@@@]DEFINE    TWOP15 = 32768XP
)@@G@@; " TWO TO THE 15TH POWER     @[@@@]"     @E@@@]DECLARE   VALBUF: INTEGEXQ
)@@G@@R WORD " ARGUMENT STORED INTO HERE  @^@@@]          !*: MAPPED    @A@@@]XR
)@@G@@             [*: 21 BIT INTEGER     @G@@@]             ,HIPART: 8 BIT INXS
)@@G@@TEGER " HIGH-ORDER 8 BITS OF ARGUMENT     @F@@@]             ,LOPART: 7 XT
)@@G@@BIT INTEGER " LOW-ORDER 7 BITS OF ARGUMENT@#@@@]             ];   @[@@@]XU
)@@G@@"     @ @@@]DECLARE   BYTE1: INTEGER WORD;@ @@@]DECLARE   BYTE2: INTEGERXV
)@@G@@ WORD;@[@@@]"     @E@@@]          PACK\CHARACTER(FUNCTION); " OUTPUT THEXW
)@@G@@ FUNCTION   @F@@@]          VALBUF := TWOP15 + ARGUMENT; " GET ARGUMENT XX
)@@G@@INTEGER     @D@@@]          BYTE1 := HIPART; " ISOLATE HIGH-ORDER 8 BITSXY
)@@G@@@C@@@]          BYTE2 := LOPART; " AND LO-ORDER 7 BITS@E@@@]          IFXZ
)@@G@@ (BYTE1 NE 0) THEN " TEST FOR TWO-BYTE SEQUENCE @C@@@]           BEGIN "YA
)@@G@@ OUTPUT FIRST AND SET SECOND  @E@@@]             PACK\CHARACTER(128+BYTEYB
)@@G@@2); " LOW 7 WITH FLAG   @D@@@]             BYTE2 := BYTE1; " SET OTHER OYC
)@@G@@UTPUT BYTE  @C@@@]           END; " OUTPUT FIRST AND SET SECOND   @D@@@]YD
)@@G@@          PACK\CHARACTER(BYTE2); " OUTPUT OTHER BYTE  @^@@@]END; " PACK\YE
)@@G@@FUNCTION\TWO@[@@@]"     @#@@@]CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@]"     @G@@@]" CONVYF
)@@G@@ERT FROM DPS INTERNAL DISTANCE TO HORIZONTAL MOVEMENT INCREMENTS, @A@@@]YG
)@@G@@" WHICH ARE IN UNITS OF 1/7800"     @[@@@]"     @B@ @]PROCEDURE DEVICE\SYH
)@@G@@KIP(INPDIST: DISTANCE)  @B@@@ PROCEDURE DEVICE\SKIP(INDIST: DISTANCE)   YI
)@@G@@@ @@@]          RESULT INTEGER WORD;@[@@@]BEGIN @A@ @]DECLARE   OUTSKIP:YJ
)@@G@@ INTEGER WORD;    @[@@@]"     @E@A@ " **** NOTE: THIS ROUTINE "KNOWS" THYK
)@@G@@E VALUE OF INTERNAL.    @E@@@A" **** NOTE: THIS ROUTINE 'KNOWS' THE VALUYL
)@@G@@E OF INTERNAL.    @[@@@ "     @E@ @]          OUTSKIP := 2*((3900*INPDISYM
)@@G@@T)//INCH\DISTANCE);     @ @ @]          RETURN(OUTSKIP);    @D@@@       YN
)@@G@@    RETURN(INDIST//120); " INTERNAL/7800 = 120  @#@@@]END; " DEVICE\SKIPYO
)@@G@@@[@@@]"     @G@@@]" TRUNCATE FIRST ARGUMENT TO BE BETWEEN SECOND AND THIYP
)@@G@@RD ARGUMENTS.     @[@@@]"     @ @@@]PROCEDURE TRUNCATE\TYPESIZE   @A@@@]YQ
)@@G@@          (INPSIZE: INTEGER WORD    @A@@@]          ,MINSIZE: INTEGER WOYR
)@@G@@RD    @A@@@]          ,MAXSIZE: INTEGER WORD    @A@@@]          )  RESULYS
)@@G@@T INTEGER WORD;   @[@@@]BEGIN @A@@@]DECLARE   OUTSIZE: INTEGER WORD;    YT
)@@G@@@[@@@]"     @B@@@]          IF (INPSIZE GT MAXSIZE) THEN    @A@@@]      YU
)@@G@@       OUTSIZE := MAXSIZE     @C@@@]          ELSE IF (INPSIZE LT MINSIZYV
)@@G@@E) THEN     @A@@@]             OUTSIZE := MINSIZE     @#@@@]          ELYW
)@@G@@SE    @A@@@]             OUTSIZE := INPSIZE;    @ @@@]          RETURN(OYX
)@@G@@UTSIZE);    @^@@@]END; " TRUNCATE\TYPESIZE@[@@@]"     @I@@@]" DEVICE POSYY
)@@G@@ITIONING IN THE HORIZONTAL (X) DIMENSION IS CONTROLLED IN A VIRTUAL     YZ
)@@G@@@H@@@]" FASHION BY TWO VARIABLES, EX\HPOS AND DV\HPOS. THESE VARIABLES AZA
)@@G@@RE KEPT IN  @H@@@]" UNITS OF 7800 DEVICE UNITS, OR ROUGHLY 8 TIMES THE MZB
)@@G@@OVE PRECISION OF 1/975" @H@@@]" BEFORE CHARACTERS ARE SET, THE VALUES ARZC
)@@G@@E COMPARED AND IF UNEQUAL AN X MOVE @H@@@]" FUNCTION IS SENT TO BRING THZD
)@@G@@E DV\HPOS BACK TO EX\HPOS. SKIPS AND OTHER X    @E@@@]" DIMENSION POSITIZE
)@@G@@ONING MERELY CHANGES THE VALUE OF EX\HPOS.@[@@@]"     @^@@@]PROCEDURE DEZF
)@@G@@VICE\HPOS;  @[@@@]BEGIN @D@@@]DECLARE   HOWFAR: INTEGER WORD; " HOW FAR ZG
)@@G@@TO MOVE     @[@@@]"     @B@@@]          HOWFAR := (EX\HPOS-DV\HPOS)//8; ZH
)@@G@@@A@@@]          IF (HOWFAR NE 0) THEN     @H@@@]             PACK\FUNCTIZI
)@@G@@ON\TWO(M2RXPS,HOWFAR); " ACTUALLY POSITION DEVICE     @G@#@]          DVZJ
)@@G@@\HPOS := EX\HPOS; " AND RESET ACTUAL POSITION TO VIRTUAL    @B@@@#      ZK
)@@G@@    DV\HPOS := DV\HPOS+8*HOWFAR;    @#@@@]END; " DEVICE\HPOS@[@@@]"     ZL
)@@G@@@^@@@]PROCEDURE DEVICE\VPOS   @[@@@]BEGIN @F@@@]          PACK\FUNCTION\ZM
)@@G@@TWO(M2RYPS,EX\VPOS-DV\VPOS); " DO LEADING @E@@@]          DV\VPOS := EX\ZN
)@@G@@VPOS; " SET NEW DEVICE POSITION     @#@@@]END; " DEVICE\VPOS@[@@@]"     ZO
)@@G@@@#@@@]CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@]"     @F@@@]" DEVICE\FONT\CHANGE UNCONDITIZP
)@@G@@ONALLY CHANGES THE DEVICE FONT.     @[@@@]"     @D@@@]PROCEDURE DEVICE\FZQ
)@@G@@ONT(NEW\DEVICE\FONT: INTEGER WORD)  @[@@@]BEGIN @^@@@]          BREAK\LIZR
)@@G@@NE;   @H@@@]          DV\FONT := NEW\DEVICE\FONT;        " SET NEW EXTERZS
)@@G@@NAL FONT CODE     @F@@@]          PACK\CHARACTER(M2FONT);            " OZT
)@@G@@UTPUT FUNCTION TO @F@@@]          PACK\CHARACTER(DV\FONT);           " CZU
)@@G@@HANGE DEVICE FONT @^@@@]"         BREAK\LINE;   @#@@@]END; " DEVICE\FONTZV
)@@G@@@[@@@]"     @F@@@]" DEVICE\ITAL UNCONDITIONALLY CHANGES THE ELECTRONIC SZW

)@@G@@UT A HORIZONTAL RULING FUNCTION WITH SPECIFIED PARAMETERS.  @[@@@]"     AV
)@@G@@@H@@@]PROCEDURE HORIZONTAL\RULE(RULE\TYPE: INTEGER WORD, RULE\THICK: INTAW
)@@G@@EGER WORD)  @[@@@]BEGIN @C@@@]          IF (DV\ITAL NE 0) THEN DEVICE\ITAX
)@@G@@AL(0);@G@@@]          PACK\FUNCTION\TWO(RULE\TYPE, RULE\SIZE(RULE\THICK*AY
)@@G@@DV\HITE) ); @^@@@]END; " HORIZONTAL\RULE  @[@@@]"     @F@@@]" OUTPUT A VAZ
)@@G@@ERTICAL RULING FUNCTION WITH SPECIFIED PARAMETERS.    @G@@@]" BECAUSE CHBA
)@@G@@ARACTER WIDTHS ARE IN 1/54 EM UNITS AND RULING WIDTHS ARE IN@G@@@]" QUARBB
)@@G@@TER-POINTS WE HAVE A PROBLEM.  IT IS NOT POSSIBLE TO CONTROL RULE @G@@@]BC
)@@G@@" WIDTHS AS FINELY AS CHARACTER WIDTHS.  WHAT WE DO HERE IS TO 'PUNT'.  BD
)@@G@@@F@@@]" WE COMPUTE THE WIDTH IN BOTH DEVICE UNITS AND QUARTER POINTS.   BE
)@@G@@@F@@@]" WE THEN COMPUTE THE 'SLACK' THAT REPRESENTS THE ROUNDOFF ERROR. BF
)@@G@@@G@@@]" THIS IS THE AMOUNT THE RULING WILL FALL SHORT OF WHAT IT SHOULD BG
)@@G@@BE.   @G@@@]" WE THEN MOVE THE DEVICE POSITION 'DV\HPOS' BACK BY THIS SLBH
)@@G@@ACK AMOUNT. @E@@@]" DPS WILL THEN CAUSE A SKIP OF THE PROPER AMOUNT OF SBI
)@@G@@PACE  @B@@@]" BEFORE THE NEXT CHARACTER IS TYPESET.   @H@@@]" NOTE ROUTIBJ
)@@G@@NE 'RULE\WIDTH' ABOVE ROUNDS A ZERO WIDTH RULE UP TO WIDTH ONE.   @D@@@]BK
)@@G@@" THEREFORE IT IS POSSIBLE FOR 'SLACK' TO BE NEGATIVE.@[@@@]"     @D@@@]BL
)@@G@@PROCEDURE VERTICAL\RULE(RULE\THICK: INTEGER WORD)     @[@@@]BEGIN @E@@@]BM
)@@G@@DECLARE   DU\WIDE: INTEGER WORD; " WIDTH IN 7800THS INCH    @E@@@]DECLARBN
)@@G@@E   QP\WIDE: INTEGER WORD; " WIDTH IN QUARTER POINTS  @ @@@]DECLARE   SLBO
)@@G@@ACK: INTEGER WORD;@[@@@]"     @C@@@]          IF (DV\ITAL NE 0) THEN DEVBP
)@@G@@ICE\ITAL(0);@B@@@]          DU\WIDE := RULE\THICK*CW\WIDE;  @B@@@]      BQ
)@@G@@    QP\WIDE := RULE\SIZE(DU\WIDE);  @B@@@]          SLACK := DU\WIDE-27*BR
)@@G@@QP\WIDE;    @A@@@]"         DISPLAY('SLACK',SLACK);   @G@@@]          PABS
)@@G@@CK\FUNCTION\TWO(M2SHGT,DV\HITE+4); " EXPAND TYPEHEIGHT BY 2 @D@@@]      BT
)@@G@@    PACK\FUNCTION\TWO(M2VRUL,QP\WIDE); " RULE   @G@@@]          PACK\FUNBU
)@@G@@CTION\TWO(M2SHGT,DV\HITE);   " RESTORE TYPEHEIGHT     @F@@@]          DVBV
)@@G@@\HPOS := DV\HPOS-SLACK; " ADJUST FOR ROUND-OFF ERRORS @^@@@]END; " VERTIBW
)@@G@@CAL\RULE    @[@@@]"     @#@@@]CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@]"     @[@@@]"     BX
)@@G@@@B@@@]" INITIALIZATION OF FINAL DEVICE HANDLER. @H@@@]" THIS ROUTINE IS BY
)@@G@@RESPONSIBLE FOR SETTING UP THE DPS DBANK LOCATIONS WHICH    @H@@@]" CONTBZ
)@@G@@ROL THE JUSTIFICATION AND TYPESETTING ROUTINES.  NOTE THAT IT DOES NOT  CA

)@@G@@"     @H@@@]" THESE ROUTINES ARE USED TO SET AND CHANGE TYPESETTER FONTSGF
)@@G@@. BECAUSE OF THE  @H@@@]" DESIGN OF THE DPS DEVICE HANDLERS, THERE ARE TGG

)@@G@@PROCEDURE M202\INTERNAL\SIZE EXPORTED ('M202INSIZE') " **EXCALL** @[@@@]IA
)@@G@@BEGIN @A@@@]DECLARE   NEW\HITE: INTEGER WORD;   @A@@@]DECLARE   NEW\WIDEIB
)@@G@@: INTEGER WORD;   @A@@@]DECLARE   NEW\LEAD: INTEGER WORD;   @[@@@]"     IC
)@@G@@@F@@@]INCLUDE(DEBUG\INPUT); DISPLAY('M2ISIZ',0); RESUME; " **DEBUG**    ID
)@@G@@@[@@@]"     @ @@@]          PARSE\INDEX := 0;   @E@@@]          CSDLEN :IE
)@@G@@= 0; " SO SIZE\PARSE SCANS AT LEAST ONCE  @I@@@]          NEW\WIDE := M2IF
)@@G@@02\SIZE\PARSE(     20     ,MIN\CHAR\SIZE,MAX\CHAR\SIZE);    @I@@@]      IG
)@@G@@    NEW\HITE := M202\SIZE\PARSE( NEW\WIDE   ,MIN\CHAR\SIZE,MAX\CHAR\SIZEIH
)@@G@@);    @I@@@]          NEW\LEAD := M202\SIZE\PARSE( NEW\HITE+4 ,     0   II
)@@G@@    ,   5*72*2    );    @B@@@]          IF (ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0) THENIJ
)@@G@@@^@@@]           BEGIN " SET  @G@@@]INCLUDE(DEBUG\INPUT); DISPLAY('M2ISSIK
)@@G@@H',NEW\WIDE); RESUME; " **DEBUG**   @G@@@]INCLUDE(DEBUG\INPUT); DISPLAY(IL
)@@G@@'M2ISSV',NEW\HITE); RESUME; " **DEBUG**   @G@@@]INCLUDE(DEBUG\INPUT); DIIM
)@@G@@SPLAY('M2ISSK',NEW\LEAD); RESUME; " **DEBUG**   @B@@@]             IF (NIN
)@@G@@EW\WIDE NE IN\WIDE) THEN@^@@@]              BEGIN     @A@@@]            IO
)@@G@@    IN\WIDE := NEW\WIDE;@B@@@]                SET\WIDTH\PARAMETERS;     IP
)@@G@@@G@@@]                PUT\FUNCTION\INTO\WORD( FUNC\WIDTH  , TYPESIZE\WIDIQ
)@@G@@TH ); @#@@@]              END;@G@@@]             IF (NEW\HITE NE IN\HITEIR
)@@G@@) OR (NEW\LEAD NE IN\LEAD) THEN     @^@@@]              BEGIN     @A@@@]IS
)@@G@@                IN\HITE := NEW\HITE;@A@@@]                IN\LEAD := NEWIT
)@@G@@\LEAD;@B@@@]                SET\HEIGHT\PARAMETERS;    @G@@@]            IU
)@@G@@    PUT\FUNCTION\INTO\WORD( FUNC\HEIGHT , TYPESIZE\HEIGHT );@#@@@]      IV
)@@G@@        END;@^@@@]           END; " SET   @ @@@]END; " M202\INTERNAL\SIZIW
)@@G@@E     @[@@@]"     @D@@@]" CHANGE EXTERNAL SIZE SYNCHRONOUSLY WITH OUTPUTIX
)@@G@@.     @[@@@]"     @F@@@]PROCEDURE M202\EXTERNAL\WIDTH EXPORTED ('M202EXWIY
)@@G@@IDT') " **EXCALL**@[@@@]BEGIN @[@@@]"     @H@@@]INCLUDE(DEBUG\INPUT); DIIZ
)@@G@@SPLAY('M2XWID',NEW\CHAR\WIDTH); RESUME; " **DEBUG**   @[@@@]"     @E@@@]JA

)@@G@@    CW\WIDE := EX\WIDE; " SET FOR CONSTANT-WIDTH@ @@@]END; " M202\EXTERNJC
)@@G@@AL\WIDTH    @[@@@]"     @G@@@]PROCEDURE M202\EXTERNAL\HEIGHT EXPORTED ('JD
)@@G@@M202EXHGHT') " **EXCALL**     @[@@@]BEGIN @[@@@]"     @H@@@]INCLUDE(DEBUJE

)@@G@@@ @@@]END; " M202\EXTERNAL\HEIGHT   @[@@@]"     @#@@@]CONTROL(EJECT);   JH
)@@G@@@[@@@]"     @G@@@]" THIS PROCEDURE IS USED BY M202\INTERNAL\SIZE TO RETUJI
)@@G@@RN THE PROPER     @F@@@]" TYPESIZE DEPENDING ON THE DATATYPE RETURNED FRJJ
)@@G@@OM THE SCANNER. IF@G@@@]" AN UNQUALIFIED INTEGER IS PASSED, THAT IS THE JK
)@@G@@NUMBER OF CHARACTERS    @F@@@]" PER INCH TO SET, SO THE TYPESIZE IS INCHJL
)@@G@@ DISTANCE DIVIDED BY N. @E@@@]" IF A DISTANCE IS GIVEN, THAT IS THE ACTUJM
)@@G@@AL DIMENSION.     @[@@@]"     @ @@@]PROCEDURE M202\SIZE\PARSE     @F@@@]JN
)@@G@@             (DEFAULT: INTEGER WORD " DEFAULT SIZE IF NONE GIVEN  @G@@@]JO
)@@G@@             ,MINSIZE: INTEGER WORD  " MINIMUM SIZE THAT CAN BE ACCEPTEDJP
)@@G@@@G@@@]             ,MAXSIZE: INTEGER WORD) " MAXIMUM SIZE THAT CAN BE ACJQ
)@@G@@CEPTED@E@@@]          RESULT INTEGER WORD " HALF POINTS FOR MERGENTHALERJR
)@@G@@@[@@@]BEGIN @F@@@]DECLARE   TEMP\SIZE: INTEGER WORD; " CHARACTER SIZE INJS
)@@G@@ HALF POINTS@H@@@]DECLARE   CHAR\SIZE: INTEGER WORD; " CHARACTER SIZE INJT
)@@G@@ HALF POINTS (RESULT)   @[@@@]"     @A@@@]          TEMP\SIZE := DEFAULTJU
)@@G@@;     @B@@@]          PARSE\INDEX := PARSE\INDEX + 1; @G@@@]          IFJV
)@@G@@ (PARSE\INDEX GT CSDLEN) AND (ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0) THEN  @#@@@]      JW
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @H@@@]             SCAN(EVAL+CTRM+COMA+ALLOW\INT+ALLOW\DST);JX
)@@G@@ " SCAN FOR TYPESIZE    @ @@@]             PARSE\INDEX := 1;@#@@@]      JY
)@@G@@     END;   @G@@@]          IF (PARSE\INDEX LE CSDLEN) AND (ERROR\STATUSJZ
)@@G@@\CODE EQ 0) THEN  @#@@@]           BEGIN  @D@@@]             CASEENTRY CKA
)@@G@@SDTYP " WHAT DATA TYPE IS IT  @G@@@]             CASE TYPNUL: BEGIN END;KB
)@@G@@ " NULL RETURNED - TAKE DEFAULT     @ @@@]             CASE TYPINT:     KC
)@@G@@@C@@@]                IF (DNUM(PARSE\INDEX) EQ 0) THEN@A@@@]            KD
)@@G@@       TEMP\SIZE := 0   @^@@@]                ELSE    @D@@@]            KE
)@@G@@       TEMP\SIZE := ( 2*INCH\DISTANCE ) //@F@@@]                      ( KF
)@@G@@DNUM(PARSE\INDEX)*POINT\DISTANCE ) - 4;   @I@@@]             CASE TYPDSTKG
)@@G@@: TEMP\SIZE := ( 2*DDST(PARSE\INDEX) )//POINT\DISTANCE;     @C@@@]      KH
)@@G@@       CASE *: WARNING(W\DIR\SYNTAX);     @^@@@]             ENDCASE;   KI
)@@G@@@#@@@]           END;   @[@@@]"     @E@@@]" CHECK FOR SIZE LIMITS AND ISKJ
)@@G@@SUE DIAGNOSTIC IF NECESSARY.  @[@@@]"     @B@@@]"         DISPLAY('CHRSIKK
)@@G@@Z',TEMP\SIZE);    @[@@@]"     @G@@@]          CHAR\SIZE := TRUNCATE\TYPEKL
)@@G@@SIZE(TEMP\SIZE,MINSIZE,MAXSIZE);    @B@@@]          IF (CHAR\SIZE NE TEMKM
)@@G@@P\SIZE) THEN@B@@@]             WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\POINT);    @[@@@]"     KN
)@@G@@@B@@@]          RETURN(CHAR\SIZE); " TO CALLER  @^@@@]END; " M202\SIZE\PKO
)@@G@@ARSE  @[@@@]"     @#@@@]CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@]"     @G@@@]" THIS ROUTIKP
)@@G@@NE **MUST** BE CALLED WHENEVER THE TYPE HEIGHT IS CHANGED   @H@@@]" (AS KQ
)@@G@@WELL AS AT DEVICE HANDLER INITIALIZATION). IT RECOMPUTES VARIOUS DATA   KR
)@@G@@@F@@@]" ITEMS REQUIRED BY DPS, INCLUDING LEADING (SETS SPACING TO 1!).  KS
)@@G@@@ @@@]" INPUTS ARE: IN\HITE IN\LEAD @[@@@]"     @A@@@]PROCEDURE SET\HEIGKT
)@@G@@HT\PARAMETERS     @[@@@]BEGIN @E@@@]          TYPESIZE\HEIGHT := (IN\HITKU
)@@G@@E*POINT\DISTANCE)//2;   @E@@@]          SKIP\DISTANCE   := (IN\LEAD*POINKV
)@@G@@T\DISTANCE)//2;   @F@@@]          LEADING := SKIP\DISTANCE; " SET BASIC KW
)@@G@@LEADING DISTANCE  @B@@@]          SECTION\LEADING\BEFORE(1) := 0; @E@@@]KX
)@@G@@          SECTION\LEADING\AFTER(1) := SKIP\DISTANCE * 3;    @E@@@]      KY
)@@G@@    SECTION\LEADING\BEFORE(2) := SKIP\DISTANCE * 2;   @D@@@]          SEKZ
)@@G@@CTION\LEADING\AFTER(2) := SKIP\DISTANCE;  @D@@@]          SECTION\LEADINLA
)@@G@@G\BEFORE(3) := SKIP\DISTANCE; @D@@@]          SECTION\LEADING\AFTER(3) :LB
)@@G@@= SKIP\DISTANCE;  @ @@@]END; " SET\HEIGHT\PARAMETERS  @[@@@]"     @H@@@]LC
)@@G@@" THIS ROUTINE **MUST** BE CALLED WHENEVER THE FONT OR TYPE WIDTH IS CHALD
)@@G@@NGED  @H@@@]" (AS WELL AS AT DEVICE HANDLER INITIALIZATION). IT RECOMPUTLE
)@@G@@ES VARIOUS DATA   @G@@@]" ITEMS REQUIRED BY DPS, AND ALSO RESETS THE CHALF
)@@G@@RACTER WIDTH TABLE.     @ @@@]" INPUTS ARE: IN\WIDE FONT    @[@@@]"     LG
)@@G@@@ @@@]PROCEDURE SET\WIDTH\PARAMETERS@[@@@]BEGIN @[@@@]"     @E@@@]      LH
)@@G@@    TYPESIZE\WIDTH := (IN\WIDE*POINT\DISTANCE)//2;    @C@@@]          COLI
)@@G@@LUMN\DISTANCE := TYPESIZE\WIDTH;    @G@@@]          IU\DU\FACTOR := TYPELJ
)@@G@@SIZE\WIDTH//54; " DEVICE WIDTHS IN 1/54 EM@[@@@]"     @D@@@]" SET WIDTHSLK
)@@G@@ OF ALL CHARACTERS INTO CHAR\WIDTH TABLE. @[@@@]"     @G@@@]          CDLL
)@@G@@T\POINTER := FDT\CDTP(FONT); " PICK UP POINTER TO CHAR TABLE@F@@@]      LM
)@@G@@    IF (FDT\WIDE(FONT) NE 0) THEN " IF CONSTANT WIDTH FONT  @E@@@]      LN
)@@G@@       FOR I := 1 TO 256 DO " CONSTANT-WIDTH FONTS    @F@@@]            LO
)@@G@@    CHAR\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH( FDT\WIDE(FONT) );@#@@@]          ELLP
)@@G@@SE    @C@@@]             FOR I := 1 TO 256 DO " NORMAL FONTS@F@@@]      LQ
)@@G@@          CHAR\WIDTH(I) := INTERNAL\WIDTH( CDT\WIDE(I) );   @[@@@]"     LR
)@@G@@@H@@@]" THE WIDTH OF THE BACKSPACE CHARACTER IS ZERO AS A FLAG TO THE OVLS
)@@G@@ERPRINT     @A@@@]" ALGORITHMS MUCH HIGHER UP IN DPS. @[@@@]"     @B@@@]LT
)@@G@@          CHAR\WIDTH(BACKSPACE+1) := 0;   @[@@@]"     @H@@@]" THE INITIALU
)@@G@@L SPACEBAND WIDTH IS A PARAMETER OF THE FONT. IT IS TAKEN FROM    @G@@@]LV
)@@G@@" THE WIDTH CODED FOR THE SPACE CHARACTER. IT MAY BE MODIFIED BY CODING LW
)@@G@@@C@@@]" THE CONTROL WORDSPACE DIRECTIVE (WHICH SEE).  @[@@@]"     @G@@@]LX
)@@G@@          SPACEBAND\WIDTH := CHAR\WIDTH(BLANK+1); " INITIAL SPACEBAND   LY
)@@G@@@ @@@]END; " SET\WIDTH\PARAMETERS   @[@@@]"     @#@@@]CONTROL(EJECT);   LZ
)@@G@@@[@@@]"     @H@@@]" THESE PROCEDURES ARE CALLED TO ACCOMPLISH SUPERSCRIPMA
)@@G@@TING AND SUBSCRIPTING.  @[@@@]"     @D@@@]PROCEDURE M202\DSIB EXPORTED (MB
)@@G@@'M202DSIB') " **EXCALL**@[@@@]BEGIN @[@@@]"     @G@@@]INCLUDE(DEBUG\INPUMC
)@@G@@T); DISPLAY('M2DSIB',DSI\SELECT); RESUME; " **DEBUG** @[@@@]"     @E@@@]MD
)@@G@@          IF (DSI\SELECT=0) THEN " IF SUPERSCRIPT WANTED    @F@@@]      ME
)@@G@@       DSI\CHAR := M2DSUP; " SET SUPERIOR (SUPERSCRIPT)     @#@@@]      MF

)@@G@@RIPT) @#@@@]END; " M202\DSIB  @[@@@]"     @D@@@]PROCEDURE M202\DSIS EXPOMH
)@@G@@RTED ('M202DSIS') " **EXCALL**@[@@@]BEGIN @[@@@]"     @H@@@]INCLUDE(DEBUMI

)@@G@@"     @G@@@]" TRANSFER CHARACTERS FROM LINE BUFFER TO DEVICE (I.E. TYPESMV
)@@G@@ET LETTERS).@[@@@]"     @E@@@]PROCEDURE M202\PACK EXPORTED ('M202OUTPUT'MW
)@@G@@) " **EXCALL**    @[@@@]BEGIN @H@@@]DECLARE   ASCII\CHAR: INTEGER WORD; MX
)@@G@@         " INTERNAL (ASCII) CHARACTER CODE@H@@@]DECLARE   REL\WIDE: INTEMY
)@@G@@GER WORD;            " RELATIVE WIDTH OF CHARACTER    @[@@@]"     @I@@@]MZ
)@@G@@" THESE VARIABLES ARE ONLY USED FOR CHARACTER COERCION IN CONSTANT-WIDTHNA
)@@G@@ FONTS.     @[@@@]"     @H@@@]DECLARE   CONSTANT\WIDTH: INTEGER WORD;   NB
)@@G@@   " WIDTH TO WHICH TO COERCE CHARS @I@@@]DECLARE   CONSTANT\WIDTH\SKIP:NC
)@@G@@ INTEGER WORD; " AMOUNT TO BE SKIPPED AROUND CHAR     @[@@@]"     @H@@@]ND
)@@G@@          CDT\POINTER := FDT\CDTP(EX\FONT); " CANNOT CHANGE WITHIN THIS NE
)@@G@@PROC  @[@@@]"     @C@@@]          CONSTANT\WIDTH := FDT\WIDE(EX\FONT);  NF
)@@G@@@H@@@]          CONSTANT\WIDTH\SKIP := 0;         " AND IF NOT CW FONT SNG
)@@G@@TAYS ZERO ! @[@@@]"     @D@@@]" LOOP THROUGH THE CHARACTER POSITIONS TO NH
)@@G@@BE TYPESET. @[@@@]"     @C@@@]          FOR I := LINE\START TO LINE\END NI
)@@G@@DO    @ @@@]           BEGIN " SET LBUF(I)@B@@@]             ASCII\CHAR NJ
)@@G@@:= LINE\BUFFER(I);@C@@@]             IF (ASCII\CHAR EQ FUNC\VSB) THEN   NK
)@@G@@@^@@@]                ERROR;  @[@@@]"     @G@@@]INCLUDE(DEBUG\INPUT); ODNL
)@@G@@ISPLAY('M2CHAR',ASCII\CHAR); RESUME; " **DEBUG**@[@@@]"     @C@@@]" CASENM
)@@G@@ BY CASE ANALYSIS OF CHARACTER TO BE SET. @[@@@]"     @B@@@]            NN
)@@G@@ IF (ASCII\CHAR EQ BLANK) THEN@[@@@]"     @B@@@]" CASE 1: SPACEBAND OR BNO
)@@G@@LANK TO BE SET.   @[@@@]"     @^@@@]              BEGIN     @G@@@]      NP
)@@G@@          EX\HPOS := EX\HPOS + DEVICE\SKIP( LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(I) ); @ @@@]NQ
)@@G@@                ABS\WIDE := 0;@A@@@]                BS\FLAG := FALSE;   NR
)@@G@@@#@@@]              END @D@@@]             ELSE IF (ASCII\CHAR EQ BACKSPNS
)@@G@@ACE) THEN   @[@@@]"     @C@@@]" CASE 2: BACKSPACE - SET FLAG AND CONTINUNT
)@@G@@E.    @[@@@]"     @^@@@]              BEGIN     @B@@@]                BSNU
)@@G@@\FLAG := (ABS\WIDE NE 0)@#@@@]              END @E@@@]             ELSE NV
)@@G@@IF (ASCII\CHAR EQ FUNC\LETTER\SPACE) THEN @[@@@]"     @E@@@]" CASE 3: LENW
)@@G@@TTERSPACE FUNCTION - SET LETTERSPACE VARIABLE.  @[@@@]"     @^@@@]      NX
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @F@@@]                LETTER\SPACE := DEVICE\SKIP( LINNY
)@@G@@E\CHAR\WIDTH(I) ) @#@@@]              END @F@@@]             ELSE IF (ASNZ
)@@G@@CII\CHAR EQ UNDERLINE) AND BS\FLAG THEN   @[@@@]"     @F@@@]" CASE 4: BAOA
)@@G@@CKSPACE UNDERLINE, COERCE UNDERLINE TO CHAR WIDTH.    @[@@@]"     @^@@@]OB
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @D@@@]                EX\WIDE := CDT\WIDE(UNDERLOC
)@@G@@INE+1);     @B@@@]                IF (DSI\CHAR NE 0) THEN   @C@@@]      OD
)@@G@@             EX\WIDE := (3*EX\WIDE)//4;   @C@@@]                EX\WIDE OE
)@@G@@:= ABS\WIDE//EX\WIDE;   @C@@@]                EX\WIDE := TRUNCATE\TYPESIOF
)@@G@@ZE    @E@@@]                   (EX\WIDE,MIN\CHAR\SIZE,MAX\CHAR\SIZE);   OG
)@@G@@@C@@@]                IF (EX\WIDE NE DV\WIDE) THEN    @B@@@]            OH
)@@G@@       DEVICE\WIDE\CHANGE;    @F@@@]                PACK\CHARACTER(M2OVPOI
)@@G@@R); " OUPUT OVERPRINT FUNCTION@F@@@]                IF (DSI\CHAR NE 0) TOJ
)@@G@@HEN PACK\CHARACTER(DSI\CHAR); @D@@@]                IF (CDT\JUMP(UNDERLIOK
)@@G@@NE+1) NE 0) THEN  @G@@@]                   PACK\FUNCTION\TWO(M2RJMP,CDT\OL
)@@G@@JUMP(UNDERLINE+1)-32);  @A@@@]                PACK\FUNCTION\TWO   @G@@@]OM
)@@G@@                   (M2HREN,RULE\SIZE(CDT\CODE(UNDERLINE+1)*EX\HITE));   ON
)@@G@@@A@@@]                EX\WIDE := CW\WIDE; @A@@@]                BS\FLAG OO
)@@G@@:= FALSE;   @#@@@]              END @#@@@]             ELSE @[@@@]"     OP
)@@G@@@B@@@]" CASE 5: TYPESET AN ACTUAL CHARACTER.    @[@@@]"     @ @@@]      OQ
)@@G@@        BEGIN " TYPESET @D@@@]                REL\WIDE := CDT\WIDE(ASCIIOR
)@@G@@\CHAR+1);   @C@@@]                IF (CONSTANT\WIDTH EQ 0) THEN   @C@@@]OS
)@@G@@                   ABS\WIDE := REL\WIDE*EX\WIDE;@^@@@]                ELOT
)@@G@@SE    @^@@@]                 BEGIN  @F@@@]                   EX\WIDE := OU
)@@G@@(CW\WIDE*CONSTANT\WIDTH)//REL\WIDE; @C@@@]                   EX\WIDE := OV
)@@G@@TRUNCATE\TYPESIZE @D@@@]                      (EX\WIDE,MIN\CHAR\SIZE,CW\OW
)@@G@@WIDE);@B@@@]                   CONSTANT\WIDTH\SKIP := @G@@@]            OX
)@@G@@          (CW\WIDE*CONSTANT\WIDTH-EX\WIDE*REL\WIDE)//2;     @D@@@]      OY
)@@G@@             ABS\WIDE := CW\WIDE*CONSTANT\WIDTH;@^@@@]                 EOZ
)@@G@@ND;   @C@@@]                IF (EX\VPOS NE DV\VPOS) THEN    @A@@@]      PA
)@@G@@             DEVICE\VPOS;     @A@@@]                IF BS\FLAG THEN     PB

)@@G@@TIMUM) THEN BREAK\LINE; @E@@@]                   EX\HPOS := EX\HPOS+CONSPG
)@@G@@TANT\WIDTH\SKIP;  @G@@@]                   IF (EX\HPOS NE DV\HPOS) THEN PH

)@@G@@ND;   @H@@@]                IF (CDT\JUMP(ASCII\CHAR+1) NE 0) THEN       PP
)@@G@@  " BASELINE JUMP @H@@@]                   PACK\FUNCTION\TWO(M2RJMP, CDTPQ
)@@G@@\JUMP(ASCII\CHAR+1)-32 );     @[@@@]"     @C@@@]" SELECT ON CHARACTER TYPR

)@@G@@                   IF (EX\ITAL\NORM NE DV\ITAL) THEN DEVICE\ITAL(EX\ITALPV
)@@G@@\NORM);     @H@@@]                   IF (CDT\CODE(ASCII\CHAR+1) GT 127) PW
)@@G@@THEN  " IF EXTENDED CHAR@H@@@]                      PACK\CHARACTER(M2XCHPX
)@@G@@R);               " OUTPUT FLAG     @I@@@]                   PACK\CHARACPY
)@@G@@TER(CDT\CODE(ASCII\CHAR+1));  " OUTPUT ACTUAL CODE    @^@@@]            PZ
)@@G@@     END;   @D@@@]                CASE SIMULA:    " SIMULATE ITALIC     QA
)@@G@@@^@@@]                 BEGIN  @I@@@]                   IF (EX\ITAL\SIMU QB
)@@G@@NE DV\ITAL) THEN DEVICE\ITAL(EX\ITAL\SIMU);     @H@@@]                  QC
)@@G@@ IF (CDT\CODE(ASCII\CHAR+1) GT 127) THEN  " IF EXTENDED CHAR@H@@@]      QD
)@@G@@                PACK\CHARACTER(M2XCHR);               " OUTPUT FLAG     QE
)@@G@@@I@@@]                   PACK\CHARACTER(CDT\CODE(ASCII\CHAR+1));  " OUTPQF
)@@G@@UT ACTUAL CODE    @^@@@]                 END;   @H@@@]                CAQG

)@@G@@          CASE HNRULE: HORIZONTAL\RULE(M2HREN, CDT\CODE(ASCII\CHAR+1) );QI
)@@G@@@G@@@]                CASE VERULE: VERTICAL\RULE( CDT\WIDE(ASCII\CHAR+1)QJ
)@@G@@ );   @G@@@]                CASE *: ERROR; " FATAL ERROR IN FONT TABLES QK
)@@G@@OR CODE     @^@@@]                ENDCASE;@A@@@]                IF BS\FLQL
)@@G@@AG THEN     @A@@@]                   BS\FLAG := FALSE @^@@@]            QM
)@@G@@    ELSE    @^@@@]                 BEGIN  @G@@@]                   DV\HPQN

)@@G@@                 END;   @ @@@]              END; " TYPESET  @ @@@]      QQ
)@@G@@     END; " SET LBUF(I) @#@@@]END; " M202\PACK  @#@@@]CONTROL(EJECT);   QR

)@@G@@ THIS @G@@@[. ROUTINE WILL INTERCEPT CALLS THRU DEFINED ENTRY POINTS, ANXI
)@@G@@D OPTIONALLY@G@@@[. LOAD OVERLAY SEGMENTS AND/OR CHANGE BANKS TO ACCESS XJ
)@@G@@THE REQUIRED CODE.@[@@@[.     @F@@@[. NOTE THAT FOR SIMPLICITY AND TO SAXK
)@@G@@VE CODE, THIS ROUTINE DESTROYS@F@@@[. REGISTER A3, WHICH IS VOLATILE DURXL
)@@G@@ING THE PLUS CALLING SEQUENCE.@F@@@[. ANOTHER VERSION EXISTS WHICH USES XM
)@@G@@SLJ AND DESTROYS NO REGISTERS.@[@@@[.     @G@@@[. THIS ROUTINE ALSO ASSUXN
)@@G@@MES THAT RETURN IS TO 0,X11 ON BANKED CALLS.    @E@@@[. THE RETURN IS IRXO
)@@G@@RELEVENT ON SEGMENT CALLS, AS THERE IS NO @C@@@[. DIVERSION OF THE RETURXP
)@@G@@N SEQUENCE PERFORMED.   @[@@@[.     @^@@@[. BEN CRANSTON 8/8/78   @^@ @[XQ
)@@G@@. LAST MODIFIED 8/8/78  @^@@@ . LAST MODIFIED 8/17/78 @[@@@[/.    @[@@@[XR
)@@G@@.     @D@@@[. THIS TABLE DEFINES THE ENTRY POINTS INTERCEPTED.    @C@@@[XS
)@@G@@. THE FORMAT OF THE 'IC' PROCEDURE CALL IS:     @[@@@[.     @C@ @[. ENTRXT
)@@G@@Y$IC* IC      [*]ENTRY[,SEGMENT] 'ENTRY' .@C@@@ . ENTRY* IC      [*]ENTRXU
)@@G@@Y$IC[,SEGMENT] 'ENTRY' .@[@@@[.     @]@@@[. WHERE:    @[@@@ .     @E@ @[XV
)@@G@@.  ENTRY$IC - IS THE ENTRY POINT REFERENCED BY ALL CALLERS. @E@@@ .  ENTXW
)@@G@@RY - IS THE ENTRY POINT REFERENCED BY ALL CALLERS.    @[@@@ .     @D@ @[XX
)@@G@@.  ENTRY - IS THE ACTUAL ENTRY POINT TO BE CALLED.    @D@@@ .  ENTRY$IC XY
)@@G@@- IS THE ACTUAL ENTRY POINT TO BE CALLED. @F@@@[.   IF THE LEADING ASTERXZ
)@@G@@ISK IS AFFIXED, CODE WILL BE GENERATED    @F@@@[.   TO SWITCH BANKS, IF YA
)@@G@@NECESSARY, WHEN THE ROUTINE IS CALLED     @A@@@[.   AND WHEN THE ROUTINEYB
)@@G@@ RETURNS.   @[@@@ .     @E@@@[.  SEGMENT - IS THE OVERLAY SEGMENT TO BE YC
)@@G@@LOADED (IF NOT    @C@@@[.   ALREADY LOADED) WHEN THE ROUTINE IS CALLED. YD
)@@G@@@[@@@ .     @F@@@[.  'ENTRY' - IS THE FIELDATA NAME OF THE ENTRY POINT, YE
)@@G@@WHICH IS    @C@@@[.   ONLY GENERATED IF PARAMETER 'SPEAK' IS ON.  @[@@@[YF
)@@G@@.     @B@@@[P         PROC      *2                .   @B@@@[IC*       NAYG
)@@G@@ME                        .   @E@@@[BF        EQU       P(1,*1)         YH
)@@G@@  . SET IF BANKED CALL  @E@@@[F         FORM      1,17,18           . FOYI
)@@G@@RMAT OF WORD 2    @[@@@[.     @F@@@[          LMJ       A3,ICALL        YJ
)@@G@@  . CALL INTERCEPT HANDLER    @D@@@[          F         BF,P(1,2),P(1,1)YK
)@@G@@  . FLAG,SEG,BANK @[@@@[.     @B@@@[. IF BANKED CALL, GENERATE TWO MORE YL
)@@G@@WORDS @[@@@[.     @E@@@[          ON        BF                . ONLY FORYM
)@@G@@ BANKED CALL@E@@@[          +         0,BDICALL$+P(1,1) . BDI OF BANK TOYN
)@@G@@ BASE @F@@@[          +         0                 . X11 SAVE FOR BANKED YO
)@@G@@CALL  @E@@@[          OFF       BF                . ONLY FOR BANKED CALLYP
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @E@@@[. IF 'SPEAK', GENERATE NAME OF INTERCEPTED ENTRY POINTYQ
)@@G@@.     @[@@@[.     @D@@@[          ON        SPEAK             . ONLY FORYR
)@@G@@ SPEAK@E@@@[N(0)      EQU       P(2,1)++0D        . DOUBLE PRECISION    YS
)@@G@@@D@@@[I DO 12 , DO (N(0)*/-66)=0 ,N(0) EQU N(0)*/6+05 . LJSF@G@@@[      YT
)@@G@@    +         N(0)              . GENERATE NAME OF ENTRY POINT    @D@@@[YU
)@@G@@          OFF       SPEAK             . ONLY FOR SPEAK@[@@@[.     @D@@@[YV
)@@G@@          END                         . PROCEDURE IC  @[@@@ /.    @[@@@[YW
)@@G@@.     @#@@@[. INTERCEPT TABLE @[@@@[.     @F@^@[WARNING*  IC        *WARYX

)@@G@@ TABLE@[@@@[/.    @[@@@[.     @B@@@[. DEFINITIONS FOR THE INTERCEPT TABLDV
)@@G@@E.    @[@@@[.     @D@@@[IPCJMP    EQUF      0                 . CALL JUMDW
)@@G@@P     @D@@@[IPCOFF    EQUF      IPCJMP+1          . CALL OFFSET   @F@@@[DX
)@@G@@IPBNKF    EQUF      1                 . TEST FOR BANK PRESENT     @D@@@[DY
)@@G@@IPCSEG    EQUF      1,,H1             . CALLED SEG ID @E@@@[IPCEPT    EQDZ
)@@G@@UF      1,,H2             . CALLED ENTRY POINT  @A@@@[. ONLY PRESENT FOREA
)@@G@@ BANKED CALLS     @E@@@[IPCBDW    EQUF      2                 . BDI CONTEB
)@@G@@ROL WORD    @D@@@[IPCBDI    EQUF      2,,H2             . CALLED BDI    EC
)@@G@@@D@@@[IPRJMP    EQUF      2                 . RETURN JUMP   @D@@@[IPROFFED
)@@G@@    EQUF      IPRJMP+1          . RETURN OFFSET @G@@@[IPSAVE    EQUF    EE
)@@G@@  3                 . SAVE FOR CALLER'S BDI,ADDRESS   @[@@@[.     @A@@@[EF
)@@G@@. GLOBAL DATA FOR INTERCEPT ROUTINE.@[@@@[.     @D@@@[ICSAVE    RES     EG
)@@G@@  2                 . SAVE FOR A0-A1@F@@@[CMIBDI    +         0         EH
)@@G@@        . CURRENT MAIN IBANK BDI    @E@@@[ICCALL    LMJ       A3,ICALL  EI
)@@G@@        . CALL SUBROUTINE JUMP@F@@@[ICRETN    LMJ       A3,IRETN        EJ
)@@G@@  . RETURN SUBROUTINE JUMP    @[@@@[.     @ @@@[. TO AVOID OBSCURING THEEK
)@@G@@ CODE.@[@@@[.     @B@@@[P         PROC      *0                .   @B@@@[EL
)@@G@@BNKSPK*   NAME                        .   @B@@@[          ON        SPEAEM
)@@G@@K             .   @B@@@[          TZ        BNKSPF            .   @B@@@[EN

)@@G@@SEGSPK*   NAME                        .   @B@@@[          ON        SPEAER
)@@G@@K             .   @B@@@[          TZ        SEGSPF            .   @B@@@[ES
)@@G@@          SLJ       SEGSPR            .   @B@@@[          OFF       SPEAET
)@@G@@K             .   @D@@@[          END                         . PROC SEGEU

)@@G@@SPK   @[@@@[/.    @]@@@[$(1)      . @[@@@[.     @^@@@[. THE INTERCEPT ROFA
)@@G@@UTINE.@[@@@[.     @]@@@[ICALL     . @E@@@[          DS        A0,ICSAVE FB
)@@G@@        . SAVE RETURN ADDRESS @E@@@[          L,U       A1,0,A3         FC
)@@G@@  . GET PACKET ADDRESS  @E@@@[          AN,U      A1,IPCOFF         . SUFD
)@@G@@BTRACT CALL OFFSET@F@@@[          L         A3,IPCEPT,A1      . LOAD ENTFE
)@@G@@RY POINT ADDRESS  @E@@@[          TN        IPBNKF,A1         . TEST BANFF
)@@G@@KED FLAG    @H@@@[          J         ICA020            . IF POSITIVE, NFG
)@@G@@O BANKS TO WORRY ABOUT  @[@@@[.     @^@@@[. POSSIBLY SWITCH BANKS.@[@@@[FH
)@@G@@.     @D@@@[          L         A0,IPCBDI,A1      . GET CALL BDI  @E@@@[FI
)@@G@@          JZ        A0,ICA020         . IF ZERO, NO LIJ     @F@@@[      FJ
)@@G@@    TNE       A0,CMIBDI         . IS BANK ALREADY BASED     @D@@@[      FK
)@@G@@    J         ICA020            . IF SO, NO LIJ @B@@@[          BNKSPK  FL
)@@G@@                    .   @D@@@[          LSSL      A0,18             . MOFM
)@@G@@VE BDI TO H1@D@@@[          LIJ       A0,$+1            . BASE BANK     FN
)@@G@@@F@@@[          LXM,U     A0,0,X11          . GET FINAL RETURN ADDRESS  FO
)@@G@@@G@@@[          S         A0,IPSAVE,A1      . AND SAVE FOR RETURN ROUTINFP
)@@G@@E     @D@@@[          SSL       A0,18             . MOVE BDI TO H2@F@@@[FQ
)@@G@@          S         A0,CMIBDI         . SET NEW MAIN IBANK BDI    @D@@@[FR
)@@G@@          L         A0,IPCBDW,A1      . GET 0,BDI WORD@F@@@[          S FS
)@@G@@        A0,IPCJMP,A1      . AND OVERLAY CALL JUMP     @E@@@[          L FT
)@@G@@        A0,ICRETN         . GET RETURN CALL     @F@@@[          S       FU
)@@G@@  A0,IPRJMP,A1      . AND SET UP RETURN JUMP    @F@@@[          L,U     FV
)@@G@@  X11,IPRJMP,A1     . POINT X11 AT RETURN JUMP  @]@@@[ICA020    . @[@@@[FW
)@@G@@.     @^@@@[. POSSIBLY LOAD SEGMENT.@[@@@[.     @D@@@[          L       FX
)@@G@@  A0,IPCSEG,A1      . GET SEGMENT ID@E@@@[          LSSL      A0,2      FY
)@@G@@        . MAKE INTO SLT INDEX @C@@@[          L,U       A0,0,A0         FZ
)@@G@@  . CLEAR H1@E@@@[          JZ        A0,ICA030         . IF ZERO, NO SEGA
)@@G@@GMENT @F@@@[          TN        SLT$,A0           . IS SEGMENT ALREADY LGB
)@@G@@OADED @D@@@[          J         ICA030            . YES - NO LOAD @B@@@[GC
)@@G@@          SSL       A0,2              .   @B@@@[          SEGSPK        GD
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@[          L,U       A1,ICA030         . ELSE JUMGE
)@@G@@P TO RETURN @E@@@[          ER        LOAD$             . AND LOAD SEGMEGF
)@@G@@NT    @]@@@[ICA030    . @E@@@[          DL        A0,ICSAVE         . REGG
)@@G@@STORE REGISTERS   @G@@@[          J         0,A3              . AND CONTGH
)@@G@@INUE TO CALLED ROUTINE  @[@@@[.     @D@@@[. THIS ROUTINE RECIEVES CONTROGI
)@@G@@L ON BANKED RETURN.     @[@@@[.     @]@@@[IRETN     . @D@@@[          DSGJ
)@@G@@        A0,ICSAVE         . SAVE REGISTERS@E@@@[          L,U       A1,0GK
)@@G@@,A3           . GET PACKET ADDRESS  @E@@@[          AN,U      A1,IPROFF GL
)@@G@@        . SUBTRACT OFFSET     @B@@@[          RTNSPK                    GM
)@@G@@  .   @D@@@[          L         A0,IPCJMP,A1      . GET CALL BDI  @D@@@[GN
)@@G@@          S         A0,IPCBDW,A1      . AND RESTORE IT@D@@@[          L GO
)@@G@@        A0,ICCALL         . GET CALL JUMP @D@@@[          S         A0,IGP
)@@G@@PCJMP,A1      . AND RESTORE IT@F@@@[          L         A3,IPSAVE,A1    GQ
)@@G@@  . GET RETURN ADDRESS AND BDI@E@@@[          DL        A0,ICSAVE       GR
)@@G@@  . RESTORE REGISTERS   @E@@@[          LIJ       A3,0,A3           . REGS
)@@G@@TURN TO CALLER    @[@@@[/.    @[@@@[.     @F@@@[. THESE ROUTINES ARE ONLGT
)@@G@@Y GENERATED WHEN PARAMETER 'SPEAK' IS ON. @[@@@[.     @B@@@[          ONGU
)@@G@@        SPEAK             .   @[@@@[.     @]@@@[$(0)      . @B@@@[BNKSPRGV
)@@G@@    +         0                 .   @B@@@[          J         BSP010    GW
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@[SEGSPR    +         0                 .   @B@@@[      GX
)@@G@@    J         SSP010            .   @B@@@[RTNSPR    +         0         GY
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@[          J         RSP010            .   @B@@@[SPKOPNGZ
)@@G@@    +         0                 .   @B@@@[          J         SOP010    HA
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@[SPA0      RES       1                 .   @B@@@[SPA1  HB
)@@G@@    RES       1                 .   @B@@@[SPA2      RES       1         HC
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@[SPA3      RES       1                 .   @B@@@[SPA4  HD
)@@G@@    RES       1                 .   @B@@@[SPA5      RES       1         HE
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@[SPR1      RES       1                 .   @B@@@[SPR2  HF

)@@G@@        .   @B@@@[SPX11     RES       1                 .   @B@@@[SPEDITHH
)@@G@@    E$PKT     14,SPBUFF         .   @B@@@[SPBUFF    RES       14        HI
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@[SPKPCW    +         0116,SPBUFF       .   @[@@@[.     HJ
)@@G@@@D@@@[SPKFLG    +         BNKSPK,SEGSPK,RTNSPK,0,0,0 . FLAGS@B@@@[BNKSPFHK
)@@G@@    EQUF      SPKFLG,,S1        .   @B@@@[SEGSPF    EQUF      SPKFLG,,S2HL
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@[RTNSPF    EQUF      SPKFLG,,S3        .   @[@@@[.     HM
)@@G@@@]@@@[$(1)      . @[@@@[.     @D@@@[SPMODN    'INTERCEPT&'              HN
)@@G@@  . MODULE NAME   @D@@@[BSMSKL    '(BNKSPK) FROM &!& TO &!& VIA & ''&'' HO
)@@G@@&' .  @E@@@[SSMSKL    '(SEGSPK) FROM & TO & LOADING & VIA & ''&'' &' .  HP
)@@G@@@D@@@[RSMSKL    '(RTNSPK) FROM &!? TO &!& VIA & ''&'' &' .  @[@@@[/.    HQ
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @]@@@[BSP010    . @D@@@[          SLJ       SPKOPN          HR
)@@G@@  . OPEN SPEAK    @C@@@[          E$MSG     BSMSKL            . SKELETONHS
)@@G@@@C@@@[          E$OCTV    CMIBDI            . FROM BDI@B@@@[          E$HT
)@@G@@MSGR                      .   @D@@@[          E$OCTF    6,SPX11,,H2     HU

)@@G@@                    .   @D@@@[          E$OCTF    6,SPA3,,H2        . TOHX
)@@G@@ ADDRESS    @E@@@[          L         A0,BNKSPR         . GET RETURN ADDHY
)@@G@@RESS  @E@@@[          J         SPKCLS            . CLOSE AND PRINT     HZ
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @]@@@[SSP010    . @D@@@[          SLJ       SPKOPN          IA

)@@G@@@D@@@[          L         A0,SPX11,,H2      . FROM ADDRESS  @D@@@[      IC
)@@G@@    L         A1,SPA1           . PACKET ADDRESS@E@@@[          TNE,U   ID

)@@G@@        .   @B@@@[          E$MSGR                      .   @D@@@[      IG

)@@G@@          DL        A0,SPA0           .   @B@@@[          DL        A2,SJQ

)@@G@@@F@@@@PROCEDURE PACK\CHARACTER(CHAR: WORD INTEGER) IMPORTED ('PAKCHR'); KI
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @F@@@@PROCEDURE GET\TRANSPARENT\CHARACTER IMPORTED ('GETTRANKJ
)@@G@@SCHAR')     @A@@@@             RESULT WORD INTEGER;   @[@@@@      @[@@@@KK
)@@G@@      @B@@@@PROCEDURE OUTPUT\LINE IMPORTED ('OPL');   @[@@@@      @D@@@@KL
)@@G@@PROCEDURE PR\PAGEUP\TERMINAL IMPORTED ('PAGUPT');     @[@@@@      @C@@@@KM
)@@G@@PROCEDURE PR\PAGEUP\FILE IMPORTED ('PAGUPF');   @[@@@@      @E@@@@PROCEDKN
)@@G@@URE SET\ALL\AREA\LINE\WIDTHS IMPORTED ('SETALLINWID');@[@@@@      @F@@@@KO
)@@G@@DECLARE   LEADING\FOR\DEVICE: DISTANCE STATIC IMPORTED ('LEDDEV');@[@@@@KP
)@@G@@      @C@@@@DECLARE   SKIP: WORD INTEGER STATIC IMPORTED;   @[@@@@      KQ
)@@G@@@H@@@@DECLARE   XXXX: WORD INTEGER; " GETS RID OF COLLECTOR ERRORS WHEN KR
)@@G@@NO DBANK    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE INITIALIZE\PROOFER EXPORTED ('PRKS
)@@G@@OOFINIT')   @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@          DEVICE\BACKSPACES := FALSE; " WEKT
)@@G@@ CAN'T BACKSPACE  @F@@@@          DEVICE\LETTER\SPACES := FALSE; " CANNOKU
)@@G@@T LETTERSPACE     @D@@@@          DEVICE\JUSTIFIES := FALSE; " WE MUST DKV
)@@G@@O IT  @F@@@@          DEVICE\HYPHEN\CHAR := MINUS; " STANDARD HYPHEN CHAKW
)@@G@@R     @E@@@@          MUTILATE := TRUE; " FORMAT OVERSTRIKES FOR PRINTERKX
)@@G@@@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@      @D@@@@PROCEDURE PAGEUP\PROOFER EXPORTED ('PROOFTKY
)@@G@@OPFRM')     @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          IF OUTPUT\MEDIA EQ MEDIA\HERE THKZ
)@@G@@EN    @A@@@@             PR\PAGEUP\TERMINAL;    @D@@@@          ELSE IF LA
)@@G@@OUTPUT\MEDIA EQ MEDIA\FILE THEN     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @ @@@@      LB
)@@G@@       PR\PAGEUP\FILE;  @D@@@@             SKIP := -1; " COMPENSATE FOR LC
)@@G@@PROOFER     @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" DO ALD
)@@G@@CTUAL LINE FEEDS FOR THE PROOFER    @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE LINE\FEELE
)@@G@@D\PROOFER EXPORTED ('PROOFLEADNG')  @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@["     @F@@@[" FIX LF
)@@G@@FOR DIVIDE OVERFLOW BUG IN M202 .TYPESIZE #,#,0PT PROOF.    @[@@@["     LG
)@@G@@@B@@@[          IF (SKIP\DISTANCE NE 0) THEN    @F@[@@          SKIP := LH
)@@G@@SKIP + LEADING\FOR\DEVICE // SKIP\DISTANCE;     @F@@@[             SKIP LI
)@@G@@:= SKIP + LEADING\FOR\DEVICE // SKIP\DISTANCE;  @#@@@[          ELSE    LJ
)@@G@@@ @@@[             SKIP := SKIP+1;  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDLK
)@@G@@URE CHANGE\LINES\PER\INCH     @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@          SKIP\DISTANCE LL
)@@G@@:=INCH\DISTANCE // NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT; @G@@@@          LINES\PER\INCH := NELM
)@@G@@W\CHAR\HEIGHT; " SET FOR OUTPUT HANDLER   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" SET STANDALN
)@@G@@RD LEADING FOR LINE PROOFER   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          LEADING := SKILO
)@@G@@P\DISTANCE; @C@@@@          TYPESIZE\HEIGHT := SKIP\DISTANCE;     @B@@@@LP
)@@G@@          UNIT\LEADING := SKIP\DISTANCE;  @B@@@@          SECTION\LEADINLQ
)@@G@@G\BEFORE(1) := 0; @E@@@@          SECTION\LEADING\AFTER(1) := SKIP\DISTALR
)@@G@@NCE * 3;    @E@@@@          SECTION\LEADING\BEFORE(2) := SKIP\DISTANCE *LS
)@@G@@ 2;   @D@@@@          SECTION\LEADING\AFTER(2) := SKIP\DISTANCE;  @D@@@@LT
)@@G@@          SECTION\LEADING\BEFORE(3) := SKIP\DISTANCE; @D@@@@          SELU
)@@G@@CTION\LEADING\AFTER(3) := SKIP\DISTANCE;  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @A@@@@LV
)@@G@@PROCEDURE CHANGE\CHARS\PER\INCH     @[@@@@BEGIN @E@@@@          IU\DU\FALW
)@@G@@CTOR :=INCH\DISTANCE // NEW\CHAR\WIDTH;   @F@@@@          UNIT\INTERNAL\LX
)@@G@@WIDTH := IU\DU\FACTOR*UNIT\DEVICE\WIDTH;  @B@@@@          COLUMN\DISTANCLY
)@@G@@E := IU\DU\FACTOR;@C@@@@          SPACEBAND\WIDTH := COLUMN\DISTANCE;   LZ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @ @@@@" INITIALIZE CHARACTER SIZES  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@      MA
)@@G@@    FOR I := 1 TO 256 DO@C@@@@             CHAR\WIDTH(I) := SPACEBAND\WIMB
)@@G@@DTH;  @H@@@@          CHAR\WIDTH(BACKSPACE+1) := - SPACEBAND\WIDTH; " BAMC
)@@G@@CKSPACE WIDTH     @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" PACK THE CHARACTERS JUMD
)@@G@@ST GIVEN INTO THE LINE  @F@@@@" THE LINE IS NOT ACTUALLY OUTPUT UNTIL THME
)@@G@@E END\OF\LINE SUBROUTINE@]@@@@" IS CALLED @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE PAMF
)@@G@@CK\PROOFER\LINE EXPORTED ('PROOFOUTPUT')  @[@@@@BEGIN @G@@@@DECLARE   CHMG
)@@G@@AR\CODE: 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER;  " CHARACTER/FUNCTION CODE @H@@@@DECLARMH
)@@G@@E   CHAR\WIDE: DISTANCE;                " CHARACTER WIDTH IN DISTANCE   MI
)@@G@@@H@@@@DECLARE   BLANK\WIDE: 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER; " WIDTH IN TERMS OF MJ
)@@G@@BLANK CODES @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" PACK FROM LINE\BUFFER TO OUTPUT\CARD    MK
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@          FOR I := LINE\START TO LINE\END DO    @ @@@@ML
)@@G@@           BEGIN " TYPESET    @B@@@@             CHAR\CODE := LINE\BUFFEMM
)@@G@@R(I); @G@@@@             IF (CHAR\CODE GT BLANK) AND (CHAR\CODE LT RUBOUMN
)@@G@@T) THEN     @F@@@@                PACK\CHARACTER( CHAR\CODE ); " OUTPUT MO
)@@G@@NORMAL CHAR @I@@@@             ELSE IF (CHAR\CODE EQ BLANK) OR (CHAR\CODMP
)@@G@@E EQ FUNC\SPACEBAND) THEN     @A@@@@              BEGIN " SPACE BAND    MQ
)@@G@@@H@@@@                CHAR\WIDE := LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(I); " PICK UP CHARACTMR
)@@G@@ER WIDTH    @H@@@@                BLANK\WIDE := CHAR\WIDE//SPACEBAND\WIDMS
)@@G@@TH; " NUMBER OF BLANKS  @F@@@@                IF (CHAR\WIDE GT 0) AND (BMT
)@@G@@LANK\WIDE EQ 0) THEN    @E@@@@                   BLANK\WIDE := 1; " OUTPMU
)@@G@@UT AT LEAST ONE   @C@@@@                FOR J := 1 TO BLANK\WIDE DO     MV
)@@G@@@G@@@@                   PACK\CHARACTER(BLANK); " OUTPUT SPACE FOR SPACEMW
)@@G@@BAND  @A@@@@              END; " SPACE BAND     @D@@@@             ELSE MX
)@@G@@IF (CHAR\CODE EQ BACKSPACE) THEN    @F@@@@                PACK\CHARACTERMY
)@@G@@( CHAR\CODE ); " OUTPUT CHARACTER   @E@@@@             ELSE " CHARACTER MZ
)@@G@@IS OUT OF DEFINED ASCII RANGE @G@@@@                PACK\CHARACTER( TRUNNA
)@@G@@CATED\CHARACTER ); " QUESTION MARK ?@ @@@@           END; " TYPESET     NB
)@@G@@@^@@@@END; " PACK\PROOFER\LINE@[@@@@"     @B@@@@" PROCEDURE TO HANDLE TRNC
)@@G@@ANSPARENT OUTPUT  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE HANDLE\TRANSPARENT\OUTPUT ND
)@@G@@EXPORTED ('PROOFTNSDAT')@[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      @ @@@@DECLARE   CHAR: WONE
)@@G@@RD INTEGER; @[@@@@      @B@@@@          WHILE TRANSPARENT\OUTPUT DO     NF
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             CHAR := GET\TRANSPARENT\CHARANG
)@@G@@CTER; @D@@@@             IF TRANSPARENT\OUTPUT THEN " STUFF IT    @D@@@@NH
)@@G@@                PACK\CHARACTER(CHAR); " SEND IT OFF   @ @@@@           ENI
)@@G@@ND; " WHILE LOOP  @B@@@@END; " OF PROCEDURE TRANSPARENT OUTPUT    @[@@@@NJ
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@" CLOSE THE LINE AND OUTPUT IT TO THE FINAL MEDIUM    @[@@@@NK
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" DUMP THE LINE OUT  BUT FIRST BLANK FILL THE LAST WORD     NL
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE OUTPUT\PROOFER\LINE EXPORTED ('PROOFENDLIN')NM
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @A@@@@          OUTPUT\LINE; " DUMP LINE  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@NN
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@" HERE WE MAKE INTERNAL ADJUSTMENTS DUE TO A TYPESIZE CHANGENO
)@@G@@@D@@@@" ASSUMING OF COURSE THAT THE CHANGE IS LEGITIMATE.   @[@@@@"     NP
)@@G@@@E@@@@PROCEDURE PROOFER\TYPESIZE\CHANGE EXPORTED ('PROOFINSIZE')  @[@@@@NQ
)@@G@@BEGIN @ @@@@          DISPLAY('PROOFT',0);@ @@@@END; " PROOFER\TYPESIZE\NR
)@@G@@CHANGE@[@@@@"     @B@@@@" UNUSED ENTRY POINTS FOR PROOFER HANDLER.@[@@@@NS
)@@G@@"     @H@@@@PROCEDURE PROOF\START\OF\TAKE            EXPORTED ('PROOFSTRNT
)@@G@@TAK') BEGIN END;  @H@@@@PROCEDURE PROOF\END\OF\TAKE              EXPORTENU
)@@G@@D ('PROOFENDTAK') BEGIN END;  @H@@@@PROCEDURE PROOF\INTERNAL\FONT\CHANGENV
)@@G@@     EXPORTED ('PROOFINFONT') BEGIN END;  @H@@@@PROCEDURE PROOF\EXTERNALNW
)@@G@@\FONT\CHANGE     EXPORTED ('PROOFEXFONT') BEGIN END;  @H@@@@PROCEDURE PRNX
)@@G@@OOF\EXTERNAL\HEIGHT\CHANGE   EXPORTED ('PROOFEXHGHT') BEGIN END;  @H@@@@NY
)@@G@@PROCEDURE PROOF\EXTERNAL\WIDTH\CHANGE    EXPORTED ('PROOFEXWIDT') BEGIN NZ
)@@G@@END;  @H@@@@PROCEDURE PROOF\SUPERIOR\INFERIOR\BEGIN  EXPORTED ('PROOFDSIOA
)@@G@@B')   BEGIN END;  @H@@@@PROCEDURE PROOF\SUPERIOR\INFERIOR\SWITCH EXPORTEOB
)@@G@@D ('PROOFDSIS')   BEGIN END;  @H@@@@PROCEDURE PROOF\SUPERIOR\INFERIOR\ENOC

)@@G@@OR\HANDLER       EXPORTED ('PROOFESCAPE') BEGIN END;  @[@@@@"     @[@@@@OE
)@@G@@TERM; ___@@@STANCE;     @F@@@[             SKIP := SKIP + LEADING\FOR\DEOF
)@@G@@VICE // SKIP\DISTANCE;  @#@@@[          ELSE    @ @@@[             SKIP OG
)@@G@@:= SKIP+1;  @[@@@@END;  )@@[#]@[]@ ]@D]@D]@CK)#@@@@@@@C9K@@[[[@@@@C9@@@!OH
