)@@G@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@B@@@[          AXR$                        .   @E@@@[      PO
)@@G@@    ELT$                        . GET INFOR$ EQUATES  @E@@@[          ASPP
)@@G@@MDEF                      . GET PARTBL EQUS     @[@@@[.     @F@@@[. THISPQ
)@@G@@ ELEMENT CONTAINS ROUTINES TO ACCESS THE INPUT AND OUTPUT   @G@@@[. ELEMPR
)@@G@@ENTS OF THE PROCESSOR CALL CARD.  IT BUILDS A PARAMETER TABLE     @G@@@[PS
)@@G@@. SPECIFYING THE ELEMENTS TO BE OUTPUT, AND ACTUALLY COPIES THE INPUT   PT
)@@G@@@A@@@[. ELEMENT INTO THE SCRATCHFILE.     @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @E@@@[PU
)@@G@@. FUNCTION TO GENERATE IMMEDIATE OR LITERAL FOR OPTION MASK @[@@@[.     PV
)@@G@@@B@@@[F         FUNC                        .   @B@@@[OPT*      NAME    PW
)@@G@@                    .   @B@@@[Z         EQU       F(1)              .   PX
)@@G@@@F@@@[          DO        (Z<-1*/17+1)++(Z>1*/18-2)++(Z=-0) , END (+Z) .PY
)@@G@@@F@@@[          END       + (I$ 0,U+(Z<0),,,3**Z*/-16,0177777**Z) .     PZ
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @A@@@[. TEST FOR OPTION OR NO OPTION GIVEN@[@@@[.     @B@@@[QA
)@@G@@P         PROC                        .   @B@@@[TON*      NAME      045 QB
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@[TOFF*     NAME      044               .   @B@@@[QC
)@@G@@JON*      NAME      0144              .   @B@@@[JOFF*     NAME      0145QD
)@@G@@              .   @D@@@[          L         A5,RUNOPTS        . GET OPTIQE
)@@G@@ON    @E@@@[          I$        P(0,0)**077,,5,,,OPT(1*/('Z'-P(1,1))) . QF
)@@G@@@D@@@[          DO        P(0,0)>077 , J P(1,2),P(1,3) .    @B@@@[      QG
)@@G@@    END                         .   @[@@@[.     @ @@@[. FORCE OPTION INTQH
)@@G@@O RUNOPTS   @[@@@[.     @B@@@[P         PROC                        .   QI
)@@G@@@B@@@[SET*      NAME                        .   @B@@@[          L       QJ
)@@G@@  A0,RUNOPTS        .   @D@@@[          I$        040,,,,,OPT(1*/('Z'-P(QK
)@@G@@1,1))) .    @B@@@[          S         A1,RUNOPTS        .   @B@@@[      QL
)@@G@@    END                         .   @[@@@[.     @[@@@[.     @C@@@[. DEFIQM
)@@G@@NE BITS PASSED TO THE FIASG$ ROUTINE.     @[@@@[.     @F@@@[EUBIT     EQQN
)@@G@@U       004               . REQUIRE EXCLUSIVE USE     @F@@@[RPBIT     EQQO
)@@G@@U       010               . REQUIRE READ PERMISSION   @F@@@[WPBIT     EQQP
)@@G@@U       020               . REQUITE WRIT PERMISSION   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[QQ
)@@G@@. UPON RETURN FROM FIASG$ AN FITEM$ PACKET FOR FILE IN FIPKT$ .   @[@@@[QR
)@@G@@.     @E@@@[FXQUAL    EQU       FIPKT$+4          . EXTERNAL QUALIFIER  QS
)@@G@@@D@@@[FXFILE    EQU       FIPKT$+2          . AND FILENAME  @D@@@^FXCYCLQT
)@@G@@    EQUF      FIPKT$+6,,H2      . AND FILE CYCLE@[@@@[/.    @[@@@[.     QU
)@@G@@@]@@@[. READ INFOR@B@@@[. COMPUTE USER-ID DEPENDING ON TAG DEFUID @ @@@[QV
)@@G@@. BUILD RUN DATA AREA (RDA)   @[@@@[.     @D@@@[PCTOID    EQUF      PCTBQW
)@@G@@UF+0          . ORIGINAL RUNID@E@@@[PCTGID    EQUF      PCTBUF+1        QX
)@@G@@  . GENERATED RUNID     @C@@@[PCTPRJ    EQUF      PCTBUF+021        . PRQY
)@@G@@OJECT @D@@@[PCTACT    EQUF      PCTBUF+023        . ACCOUNT NUMBER@E@@@[QZ
)@@G@@PCTTYP    EQUF      PCTBUF+030,,S2    . PROGRAM TYPE (4/5/6)@[@@@[.     RA
)@@G@@@B@@@[GETRDA*   INSTRS                      .   @B@@@[          SUBEGIN RB
)@@G@@  SAVE              .   @[@@@[.     @D@@@[. GET FIRST 28 WORDS OF THE PCRC
)@@G@@T INTO INFOR BUFFER.    @[@@@[.     @B@@@[          L         A0,(28,INFRD
)@@G@@OR)     .   @B@@@[          ER        PCT$              .   @[@@@[.     RE
)@@G@@@E@@@[          L         A0,PCTGID         . GET GENERATED RUNID @C@@@[RF
)@@G@@          S         A0,RUNID          . SAVE IT @[@@@[.     @^@@@[. NOW RG
)@@G@@GET HIS SITE ID   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[          L         A0,(2,INFOPKT)  RH
)@@G@@  . GET THE ACW FOR THE PACKET@E@@@[          ER        INFO$           RI
)@@G@@  . GET THE SITE ID     @[@@@[.     @E@@@[. GET USER ID FOR SCRATCH FILERJ
)@@G@@ QUALIFIER AND OTHER USES.    @[@@@[.     @E@@@[          LMJ       X11,RK
)@@G@@GETUSERID     . GET UNIQUE USER ID  @C@@@[          DS        A0,USERID RL
)@@G@@        . STORE IT@[@@@[.     @F@@@[. @ IN LAST CHAR OF ACCOUNT NUMBER MRM
)@@G@@EANS UOM PRIVELIGED.  I GUESS @C@@@[. WE WANT THEM TO BE ABLE TO USE DPSRN
)@@G@@ TOO HUH ?  @[@@@[.     @D@@@[          L,U       A0,' '            . GERO
)@@G@@T BLANK     @D@@@[          TNZ,S6    USERID+1          . IS HE PRIVL   RP
)@@G@@@D@@@[          S,S6      A0,USERID+1       . YES - STUFF IT@C@@@[.     RQ
)@@G@@    P$RINT    (0102,USERID)     . PRINT IT@[@@@[.     @B@@@[. GET REAL RRR
)@@G@@UN TYPE (UNIVAC BROKE 0136).  @[@@@[.     @D@@@[          L         A0,PRS
)@@G@@CTTYP         . GET RUN TYPE  @F@@@[          L,U       A1,0            RT
)@@G@@  . TENATIVELY CLEAR DEMAND   @C@@@[          TNE,U     A0,4            RU
)@@G@@  . DEMAND? @D@@@[          L,U       A1,1              . SET DEMAND    RV
)@@G@@@F@@@[          S         A1,REALDEMAND     . SET REAL (NO OPTION) STATERW
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @B@@@[. NOW READ INFOR (INTERNAL FORMAT) TABLE. @[@@@[.     RX
)@@G@@@B@@@[          L         A0,(28,INFOR)     .   @E@@@[          LMJ     RY
)@@G@@  X11,RINF$         . READ INFOR TABLE    @E@@@[          J         RDA0RZ
)@@G@@90            . A MISTAKE WAS MADE  @[@@@[.     @A@@@[. SET BATCH/DEMANDSA
)@@G@@ FLAG AND OPTIONS.@[@@@[.     @D@@@[          L         A0,INFOR        SB
)@@G@@  . GET OPTIONS   @D@@@[          S         A0,RUNOPTS        . SET OPTISC
)@@G@@ONS   @E@@@[          TZ        REALDEMAND        . IS HE BATCH JOB     SD
)@@G@@@F@@@[          J         RDA030            . NO - CHECK FOR SWITCH     SE
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @D@@@[. HE IS REALLY BATCH - CHECK FOR SWITCH TO DEMAND     SF
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @E@@@[          JON       'T',RDA040        . IF HE WANTS DESG
)@@G@@MAND  @F@@@[          J         RDA050            . NO, SET 'B' OPTION (SH
)@@G@@BATCH)@[@@@[.     @C@@@[. DEMAND RUN.  CHECK TO SEE IF HE WANTS BATCH.  SI
)@@G@@@[@@@[.     @E@@@[RDA030    JON       'B',RDA050        . REQUESTING BATSJ
)@@G@@CH ?  @[@@@[.     @^@@@[. HE REALLY WANTS DEMAND@[@@@[.     @]@@@[RDA040SK
)@@G@@    . @E@@@[          L,U       A0,1              . NO - SET FLAG WHICH SL
)@@G@@@D@@@[          S         A0,DEMAND         . SEZ DEMAND    @E@@@[      SM
)@@G@@    SET       'T'               . SET DEMAND MODE     @C@@@[          J SN
)@@G@@        RDA060            . LEAVE   @[@@@[.     @^@@@[. HE REALLY WANTS SO
)@@G@@BATCH @[@@@[.     @]@@@[RDA050    . @E@@@[          SZ        DEMAND    SP
)@@G@@        . CLEAR DEMAND FLAG   @E@@@[          SET       'B'             SQ
)@@G@@  . SET FLAG FOR BATCH  @]@@@[RDA060    . @B@@@[.         P$RINT    (010SR
)@@G@@1,RUNDATA)    .   @B@@@[          SUBRETURN RESTORE           .   @[@@@[SS
)@@G@@.     @C@@@[. PROCESSOR CALL ERROR.  RINF$ GIVES US A PCW.  @[@@@[.     ST
)@@G@@@B@@@[RDA090    INSTRS                      .   @E@@@[          ER      SU
)@@G@@  PRINT$            . PRINT ERROR MESSAGE @C@@@[          J         INTESV
)@@G@@RR            . AND EXIT@[@@@[/.    @[@@@[.     @]@@@[$(1)      . @[@@@[SW
)@@G@@.     @A@@@[. ASSIGN SPEC1 AND SPEC2 FILES.     @[@@@[.     @#@@@[ASGFILSX
)@@G@@ES* INSTRS  @B@@@[          SUBEGIN   SAVE              .   @F@@@[      SY
)@@G@@    SZ        NOSP2             . CLEAR 'NO SPEC2' FLAG     @E@@@[      SZ
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,2              . SEARCH FOR SPEC2    @C@@@[          LMTA
)@@G@@J       X11,SELT$         . IN INFOR@E@@@[          S         X11,NOSP2 TB
)@@G@@        . SET NO SPEC2 FLAG   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[. ASSIGN SPEC1 FILE FIRSTC
)@@G@@T, BECAUSE IF FILES ARE THE SAME THIS IS  @F@@@[. WHERE THE KEYS ARE.  WTD
)@@G@@E HAVE ALREADY LOOKED FOR SPEC2 SO WE KNOW@F@@@[. IF WE NEED WRITE PERMITE
)@@G@@SSION/EXCLUSIVE USE OR NOT.  THE ONE CASE @F@@@[. THAT IS NOT COVERED ISTF
)@@G@@ WHEN THE 'I' OPTION IS FORCED BECAUSE THE@G@@@[. ELEMENT SPECIFIED IN STG
)@@G@@PEC1 IS NOT THERE.  IN THIS CASE WE MUST DO     @G@@@[. ANOTHER CALL TO TH
)@@G@@FIASG$ TO SET THE EXCLUSIVE USE.  THE @FREE CODES     @F@@@[. ARE 'OR' ETI
)@@G@@D, BECAUSE OF BITMASK CONSTRUCTION OF FREE CODE.  ONE @A@@@[. CALL THEN TJ
)@@G@@SUFFICES TO FREE IT.    @[@@@[.     @]@@@[GSP100    . @F@@@[          L,TK
)@@G@@U       A0,1              . GET SPEC1 INFORMATION     @D@@@[          LMTL
)@@G@@J       X11,SELT$         . FROM INFOR    @E@@@[          J         GSP1TM
)@@G@@20            . USE PREVIOUS NAME   @E@@@[          L         A0,(RPBIT,TN
)@@G@@ELT$)   . NEED READ PERMISSION@E@@@[          TON       'I'             TO
)@@G@@  . IF 'I' OPTION OR    @E@@@[          TZ        NOSP2             . OUTP
)@@G@@TPUT TO SPEC1 THEN@F@@@[          LXI,U     A0,WPBIT+RPBIT+EUBIT . NEED TQ
)@@G@@EXCLUSIVE USE     @G@@@[          FIASG                       . ASSIGN STR
)@@G@@PEC1 FILE (IF NECESSARY)@E@@@[          S         A4,IFREE          . SATS
)@@G@@VE @FREE CODE     @F@@@[          DS        A1,IFILE          . SAVE INTTT
)@@G@@ERNAL FILE NAME   @F@@@[          LMJ       X11,FIDIAG$       . ISSUE WATU
)@@G@@RNING DIAGNOSTIC  @F@@@[          JN        A5,INTERR         . EXIT IF TV
)@@G@@FATAL ASSIGN ERROR@[@@@[.     @C@@@[. GET SPEC1 ELEMENT AND VERSION, ANDTW
)@@G@@ PFS FOR IT.@[@@@[.     @E@@@[          DL        A0,ENAME          . GETX
)@@G@@T ELEMENT NAME    @D@@@[          TNZ       ENL               . WAS IT GTY
)@@G@@IVEN  @D@@@[          J         GSP910            . NO - ERROR    @E@@@[TZ
)@@G@@          DS        A0,IELE           . SET INPUT ELEMENT   @E@@@[      UA
)@@G@@    DL        A0,EVER           . GET VERSION NAME    @D@@@[          TNUB
)@@G@@Z       EVL               . WAS IT GIVEN  @E@@@[          DL        A0,(UC
)@@G@@'            ') . NO, USE SPACES    @E@@@[          DS        A0,IVERS  UD
)@@G@@        . SET INPUT VERSION   @G@@@[          JON       'I',GSP110      UE
)@@G@@  . IF 'I' OPTION NO PFS OR SPEC2   @F@@@[          L,U       A0,IN     UF
)@@G@@        . SEARCH FOR INPUT NAME     @E@@@[          L,U       A1,7      UG
)@@G@@        . SET TYPE TO OMNIBUS @B@@@[          S,S3      A1,5,A0         UH
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@[          ER        PFS$              . SEARCH FOR ELEMENT  UI
)@@G@@@E@@@[          JZ        A2,GSP150         . IF NORMAL CONTINUE  @[@@@[UJ
)@@G@@.     @F@@@[. PFS ERROR 1 IS ELEMENT NOT FOUND.  ANYTHING ELSE IS AN ERRUK
)@@G@@OR.   @[@@@[.     @D@@@[          TE,U      A2,1              . NOT FOUNUL
)@@G@@D     @D@@@[          J         GSP940            . NO - ERROR    @[@@@[UM
)@@G@@.     @E@@@[. NO ELEMENT BY THIS NAME.  FORCE 'I' OPTION AND KLUGE TO   UN
)@@G@@@A@@@[. GET EXCLUSIVE USE ON INPUT FILE.  @[@@@[.     @D@@@[          SEUO
)@@G@@T       'I'               . SET I OPTION  @E@@@[          TZ        NOSPUP
)@@G@@2             . WAS THERE SPEC2 ?   @E@@@[          J         GSP110    UQ
)@@G@@        . IF NOT WE GOT PERMS @D@@@[          FIASG     ELT$,'XRW'      UR
)@@G@@  . ASSIGN FILE   @G@@@[          DS        A1,RFILE          . SET USE US
)@@G@@NAME IN OUTPUT FILE TOO @E@@@[          S         A4,RFREE          . SAUT
)@@G@@VE FREE CODE TEMP @G@@@[          LMJ       X11,FIDIAG$       . DIAGNOSEUU
)@@G@@ BEFORE WE TRASH A5     @F@@@[          JN        A5,INTERR         . EXUV
)@@G@@IT IF FATAL ASSIGN ERROR@D@@@[          L         A0,RFREE          . SEUW
)@@G@@T FREE CODE @E@@@[          OR        A0,IFREE          . TO FREE INPUT UX
)@@G@@FILE  @B@@@[          S         A1,IFREE          .   @F@@@[          SZUY
)@@G@@        RFREE             . SET NO FREE OF OUTPUT FILE@[@@@[/.    @[@@@[UZ
)@@G@@.     @G@@@[. IF OUTPUT TO SPEC1 (I OPTION) DONT ALLOW SPEC2. (NOTE FALLVA
)@@G@@-THRU).     @[@@@[.     @]@@@[GSP110    . @E@@@[          TNZ       NOSPVB
)@@G@@2             . DONT ALLOW SPEC2    @G@@@[          LMJ       X11,GSP900VC
)@@G@@        . ISSUE WARNING SPEC2 IGNORED     @E@@@[          J         GSP2VD
)@@G@@00            . AND BUILD RO FIELD  @[@@@[.     @E@@@[. IF NO SPEC1 FILEVE
)@@G@@ FOUND, USE OUTPUT SPEC FROM LAST DPS CALL@A@@@[. WHICH IS SAVED IN RECOVF
)@@G@@VERY BUFFER.@[@@@[.     @]@@@[GSP120    . @D@@@[          L         A0,RVG
)@@G@@ECBFR         . GET LABEL     @D@@@[          TE        A0,DPSAID       VH
)@@G@@  . SAME LEVEL ?  @D@@@[          J         GSP910            . NO - SKIVI
)@@G@@P     @F@@@[          L         A0,RECBFR+4       . GET OPTIONS FROM LASVJ
)@@G@@T CALL@E@@@[          JZ        A0,GSP910         . 050 IN S1 IF ALL OFFVK
)@@G@@@E@@@[          S         A0,RUNOPTS        . SET NEW OPTIONS     @E@@@[VL
)@@G@@          L         A0,(1,RECBFR+14)  . BT BACK TO ELT$     @B@@@[      VM
)@@G@@    L         A1,(1,ELT$)       .   @B@@@[          L,U       R1,14     VN
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@[          BT        A1,0,*A0          .   @E@@@[      VO
)@@G@@    FIASG     ELT$,'XRW'        . ASSIGN OUTPUT FILE  @D@@@[          DSVP
)@@G@@        A1,IFILE          . SET FILE NAME @D@@@[          S         A4,IVQ
)@@G@@FREE          . AND FREE CODE @E@@@[          LMJ       X11,FIDIAG$     VR
)@@G@@  . DIAGNOSE ERRORS     @F@@@[          JN        A5,INTERR         . EXVS
)@@G@@IT IF FATAL ASSIGN ERROR@E@@@[          DL        A0,RECBFR+23      . XFVT
)@@G@@ER ELEMENT AND    @E@@@[          DS        A0,IELE           . VERSION VU
)@@G@@NAMES FROM  @D@@@[          DL        A0,RECBFR+25      . SAVED ELT$ TO VV
)@@G@@@C@@@[          DS        A0,IVERS          . PARTBL  @F@@@[          L,VW
)@@G@@U       A0,IN             . SEARCH FOR INPUT NAME     @E@@@[          L,VX
)@@G@@U       A1,7              . SET TYPE TO OMNIBUS @B@@@[          S,S3    VY
)@@G@@  A1,5,A0           .   @E@@@[          ER        PFS$              . SEVZ
)@@G@@ARCH FOR ELEMENT  @D@@@[          JNZ       A2,GSP940         . CANNOT FWA
)@@G@@IND IT@G@@@[          S         X11,NOSP2         . SET FLAG NOT TO LOOKWB
)@@G@@ AT SPEC2   @[@@@[.     @F@@@[. IF SPEC1 ELEMENT FOUND STORE TEXT ADDRESWC
)@@G@@S AND PROCESS SPEC2.    @D@@@]. (LEVEL 37 FIX: LOAD TEXT ADDRESS FROM PFWD
)@@G@@ PACKET).   @[@@@[.     @]@@@[GSP150    . @]@#@] SLJ TON$   @E@#@]      WE
)@@G@@    L         A1,9,A0           . LOAD SECTOR ADDRESS @E@@@#          L WF
)@@G@@        A1,10,A0          . LOAD SECTOR ADDRESS @F@@@[          S       WG
)@@G@@  A1,ITXTADD        . SET INPUT TEXT ADDRESS    @[@@@[.     @F@@@[. IF TWH
)@@G@@HERE WAS NO 'I' OPTION AND SPEC1 ELEMENT WAS FOUND THEN     @ @@@[. OUTPWI
)@@G@@UT WILL GO TO SPEC2.    @[@@@[.     @E@@@[          TNZ       NOSP2     WJ
)@@G@@        . WAS THERE SPEC2     @E@@@[          J         GSP210          WK
)@@G@@  . YES - PROCESS IT    @[@@@[/.    @[@@@[.     @A@@@[. NO SPEC2 GIVEN. WL
)@@G@@ DUPLICATE SPEC1. @[@@@[.     @]@@@[GSP200    . @E@@@[          DL      WM
)@@G@@  A0,IFILE          . SET FILE NAME TO    @D@@@[          DS        A0,RWN
)@@G@@FILE          . SPEC1 FILE    @B@@@[          SZ        RFREE           WO
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@[          DL        A0,IELE           . DUPLICATE ELEMENT   WP
)@@G@@@B@@@[          DS        A0,RELE           .   @B@@@[          DL      WQ
)@@G@@  A0,IVERS          .   @B@@@[          DS        A0,RVERS          .   WR
)@@G@@@D@@@[          J         GSP220            . AND DO PFWL   @[@@@[.     WS
)@@G@@@^@@@[. PROCESS SPEC2 NAME.   @[@@@[.     @]@@@[GSP210    . @E@@@[      WT
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,2              . GET SPEC2 AGAIN     @D@@@[          LMWU
)@@G@@J       X11,SELT$         . SEARCH INFOR  @F@@@[          ER        ERR$WV
)@@G@@              . FUNNY, IT WAS THERE BEFORE@B@@@[          FIASG     ELT$WW

)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE PEW
)@@G@@ROCESSES BOTH THE LET DIRECTIVE AND THE LET     @F@@@@" COMMAND.  THE COEX
)@@G@@NDITION ARGUMENT IS PASSED AS TRUE FROM ELEMENT @C@@@@" COMMANDS AND FALEY
)@@G@@SE FROM ELEMENT DIRECTIVES.   @E@@@@" THE ONLY DIFFERANCE IS THAT VARIABEZ
)@@G@@LES CREATED BY THE LET  @F@@@@" COMMAND ITSELF WILL BE CREATED AS COMMANFA
)@@G@@D OR DOCUMENT SYMBOLS.  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\LET(COMMAND:FB
)@@G@@ CONDITION) EXPORTED ('PROLETCD')   @[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@"     @D@@@@      FC
)@@G@@    SCAN(ALLOW\NAM); " SCAN FOR SYMBOL NAME     @E@@@@          IF (ERROFD
)@@G@@R\STATUS\CODE NE 0) OR " IF SCAN ERROR    @D@@@@             (CSDTYP NE FE
)@@G@@TYPNAM) OR " NOT NAME-LABEL   @D@@@@             (CSDLEN EQ 0) THEN " ORFF
)@@G@@ BAD NAME-LABEL   @B@@@@             DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR1;   @#@@@@FG
)@@G@@          ELSE    @A@@@@           BEGIN " CHECK SYMBOL TYPE@E@@@@      FH
)@@G@@       MONOCASE(SCANNED); " CONVERT IT TO MONOCASE    @E@@@@            FI
)@@G@@ IF (CSDSBT EQ 0) THEN " NO DOLLAR SIGN AT END  @D@@@@                PRFJ
)@@G@@OCESS\USER\LET(COMMAND); " PASS FLAG@C@@@@             ELSE " SYMBOL ENDFK
)@@G@@ED WITH DOLLAR    @E@@@@                PROCESS\SYSTEM\LET; " SET SYSTEMFL
)@@G@@ VARIABLE   @A@@@@           END; " CHECK SYMBOL TYPE @#@@@@END; " PROCEFM
)@@G@@SS\LET@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" PROCESS STORE INTO USER VARIABLE (IN CSDESC)  FN
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\USER\LET(COMMAND: CONDITION)  @[@@@@FO
)@@G@@BEGIN @H@@@@DECLARE   LEFT\VAR: MACHINE POINTER; " TO SYMBOL TABLE ENTRYFP
)@@G@@ FOR LEFT VAR     @G@@@@DECLARE   STORE\OK: CONDITION; " FALSE FOR FRV DFQ
)@@G@@URING NON-FORMAT PASS   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@          LEFT\VAR := LOOKUP\SFR
)@@G@@YMBOL(MONOCASE\PTR); " LOOK UP IN TABLES  @C@@@@          SKIP\BLANKS; "FS
)@@G@@ ALLOW BLANKS AFTER NAME@[@@@@"     @G@@@@" IF VARIABLE IS MARKED AS FRVFT
)@@G@@ AND THIS IS NOT A FORMATTING PASS, THEN  @C@@@@" CLEAR STORE\OK TO INHIFU
)@@G@@BIT THE STORE OPERATION.@C@@@@" NOTE, HOWEVER, THAT SOME PARSING IS DONEFV
)@@G@@.     @G@@@[" ALSO NOTE PATCH TO ***ALWAYS*** ALLOW COMMAND LET TO CHANGFW
)@@G@@E DATA.     @G@@@[" DOES NOT FORCE REWRITE OF CHECKPOINT SO CHANGE LOST FX
)@@G@@WHEN DPS EXITS.   @[@@@@"     @ @[@@          STORE\OK := TRUE;   @ @@@[FY
)@@G@@          STORE\OK := TRUE;   @B@[@@          IF (LEFT\VAR NE NULL\PTR) FZ
)@@G@@THEN  @G@@@[          IF (LEFT\VAR NE NULL\PTR) AND NOT(COMMAND OR FORMAGA
)@@G@@TTING) THEN @C@@@[             STORE\OK := NOT( DREF(LEFT\VAR) ); @H@[@@GB
)@@G@@             STORE\OK := FORMATTING OR NOT DREF(LEFT\VAR); " CHECK FRV FGC
)@@G@@LAG   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" IF CHARACTER IS OPEN PAREN PARSE TABLE STORE  GD
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @C@@@@          IF (CHARACTER EQ OPEN\PAREN) THEN     @ @@@@GE
)@@G@@           BEGIN " TABLE STORE@D@@@@             LEFT\VAR := PARSE\TABLEGF
)@@G@@\STORE(LEFT\VAR); @F@@@@             SKIP\BLANKS; " ALLOW BLANKS BETWEENGG
)@@G@@ TABLE REFERENCES @ @@@@           END; " TABLE STORE @[@@@@"     @E@@@@GH
)@@G@@" PARSE\TABLE\STORE SHOULD NOT RETURN NULL\POINTER UNLESS AN@G@@@@" ERROGI
)@@G@@R STATUS CODE IS SET.  IF THIS IS NOT DONE A DOCUMENT VARIABLE    @A@@@@GJ
)@@G@@" MAY BE INADVERTANTLY CREATED.     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@          IF (ERROGK
)@@G@@R\STATUS\CODE EQ 0) THEN@ @@@@           BEGIN " CONTINUE   @[@@@@"     GL
)@@G@@@E@@@@" IF CHARACTER IS NOW OPEN BRACKET PROCESS SUBSCRIPTING     @B@@@@GM
)@@G@@" OTHERWISE PROCESS NORMAL DATA STORE.    @[@@@@"     @C@@@@            GN
)@@G@@ IF (CHARACTER EQ OPEN\BRACKET) THEN@F@@@@                PERFORM\SUBSCRGO
)@@G@@IPTED\STORE(LEFT\VAR,STORE\OK);     @#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@      GP
)@@G@@        BEGIN " NORMAL LET    @E@@@@                IF (LEFT\VAR EQ NULLGQ
)@@G@@\PTR) THEN " WE MAKE ONE@B@@@@                 BEGIN " CREATE VARIABLE  GR
)@@G@@@G@@@@                   IF COMMAND THEN " CREATE COMMAND OR DOCUMENT VAGS
)@@G@@R     @G@@@@                      LEFT\VAR:=CREATE\COMMAND\VARIABLE(MONOGT
)@@G@@CASE\PTR);  @^@@@@                   ELSE @G@@@@                      LEGU
)@@G@@FT\VAR:=CREATE\DOCUMENT\VARIABLE(MONOCASE\PTR); @B@@@@                 EGV
)@@G@@ND; " CREATE VARIABLE   @A@@@@                IF STORE\OK THEN    @ @@@@GW
)@@G@@                 BEGIN " DO IT@E@@@@                   SCAN\ASSIGNMENT; GX
)@@G@@" SCAN := AND VALUE     @D@@@@                   IF (ERROR\STATUS\CODE EGY
)@@G@@Q 0) THEN   @G@@@@                      SET\VALUE(LEFT\VAR,SCANNED); " PGZ
)@@G@@ERFORM ASSIGNMENT @ @@@@                 END; " DO IT @A@@@@            HA
)@@G@@  END; " NORMAL LET     @ @@@@          END; " CONTINUE     @^@@@@END; "HB
)@@G@@ PROCESS\USER\LET @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@HC
)@@G@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED WHEN OPEN PAREN IS ON LEFT SIDE OF :=  @F@@@@HD
)@@G@@" IF A VALID TABLE REFERENCE RETURNS POINTER TO ENTRY SELECTED.   @F@@@@HE
)@@G@@" NOTE THAT ACTUAL DATA STORE IS DONE IN PROCESS\USER\LET, ABOVE. @[@@@@HF
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PARSE\TABLE\STORE(TABLE\PTR: MACHINE POINTER)     HG
)@@G@@@D@@@@          RESULT MACHINE POINTER " TO SELECTED ENTRY  @[@@@@BEGIN HH
)@@G@@@E@@@@DECLARE   RESULT\POINTER: MACHINE POINTER; " TO TABLE ENTRY @F@@@@HI
)@@G@@DECLARE   SUB\LEN: INTEGER WORD; " LENGTH OF SUBSCRIPT IN WORDS   @[@@@@HJ
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@          RESULT\POINTER := NULL\PTR; " INITIALLY NULL@G@@@@HK
)@@G@@          IF (TABLE\PTR EQ NULL\PTR) OR (DTYP(TABLE\PTR) NE TYPTAB) THENHL
)@@G@@@F@@@@             DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR3; " NOTHING TO STORE INTO   HM
)@@G@@@#@@@@          ELSE    @A@@@@           BEGIN " SUBSCRIPT SCAN   @G@@@@HN
)@@G@@             SCAN(EVAL+ALLOW\INT+ALLOW\STR+ALLOW\DST); " SCAN SUBSCRIPT HO
)@@G@@@C@@@@             IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE NE 0 THEN     @G@@@@            HP
)@@G@@    DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR6; " ERROR SCANNING SUBSCRIPT   @#@@@@      HQ
)@@G@@       ELSE @B@@@@              BEGIN " SUBSCRIPT CHECK     @G@@@@      HR
)@@G@@          SUB\LEN := DESC\DATA\LEN(SCANNED); " GET WORD LENGTH    @F@@@@HS
)@@G@@                IF (SUB\LEN GT 63) OR (CSDTYP EQ TYPNUL) THEN     @G@@@@HT
)@@G@@                   DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR7; " DONT ALLOW TYPELESS NULLHU
)@@G@@@^@@@@                ELSE    @C@@@@                 BEGIN " ENTRY PRESEHV
)@@G@@NT CHECK    @D@@@@                   RESULT\POINTER := SEARCH\FOR\NODE  HW
)@@G@@@H@@@@                      (DADR(TABLE\PTR),CSDTYP,SUB\LEN,CSDADR); " SHX
)@@G@@EARCH TREE  @I@@@@                   IF (RESULT\POINTER EQ NULL\PTR) THEHY
)@@G@@N " IT ISNT THERE ALREADY     @B@@@@                    BEGIN " INSERT EHZ
)@@G@@NTRY  @F@@@@                      RESULT\POINTER := CREATE\NEW\NODE(SCANIA
)@@G@@NED); @E@@@@                      DADR(TABLE\PTR) := INSERT\NEW\NODE    IB
)@@G@@@I@@@@                         ( DADR(TABLE\PTR) , RESULT\POINTER ); " IIC
)@@G@@NSERT NEW ENTRY   @I@@@@                      DLEN(TABLE\PTR) := DLEN(TAID
)@@G@@BLE\PTR) + 1; " INCREMENT COUNT     @B@@@@                    END; " INSIE
)@@G@@ERT ENTRY   @C@@@@                 END; " ENTRY PRESENT CHECK     @A@@@@IF
)@@G@@              END; " SUBSCRIPT CHECK@A@@@@           END; " SUBSCRIPT SCIG
)@@G@@AN    @A@@@@          RETURN(RESULT\POINTER);   @^@@@@END; " PARSE\TABLEIH
)@@G@@\STORE@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IS CALLED WHEN OPENII
)@@G@@ BRACKET IS ON LEFT SIDE OF :=@[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDURE PERFORM\SUBSCRIJ
)@@G@@IPTED\STORE @G@@@@             (LEFT\VAR: MACHINE POINTER " VARIABLE TO IK
)@@G@@BE STORED INTO    @G@@@@             ,STORE\OK: CONDITION) " FALSE IF FRIL
)@@G@@V AND NOT FORMATTING    @[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@DECLARE   SUBSCRIPT\FORM: INTEIM
)@@G@@GER WORD    @F@@@@            ![BSUB: 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER " START DAIN
)@@G@@TA POSITION @F@@@@             ,ESUB: 18 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER " END DATAIO
)@@G@@ POSITION   @#@@@@             ];   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@DECLARE   TPTR: MAIP
)@@G@@CHINE POINTER; " TO AREA TO STORE INTO    @C@@@@DECLARE   TNUM(*): INTEGIQ
)@@G@@ER WORD BASED(TPTR);    @D@@@@DECLARE   TCHR(*): 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER IR
)@@G@@BASED(TPTR);@[@@@@"     @G@#@@          IF (LEFT\VAR EQ NULL\PTR) THEN "IS
)@@G@@ NOTHING TO STORE INTO !!     @B@@@#          IF (LEFT\VAR EQ NULL\PTR) IT
)@@G@@THEN  @B@#@@             DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR3;   @D@@@#            IU
)@@G@@ DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR3; " SYNTAX ERROR@#@@@@          ELSE    @A@@@@IV
)@@G@@           BEGIN " SCAN SUBSCRIPT   @E@@@@             SCAN(EVAL+ALLOW\IIW
)@@G@@NT); " SCAN FOR SUBSCRIPT     @D@#@]             DISPLAY('LETYPE',DTYP(SIX
)@@G@@CANNED)); " $$$   @D@#@]             ODISPLAY('ERSUBC',ERROR\STATUS\CODEIY
)@@G@@);    @C@#@]             DUMP\DESCRIPTOR('SCANNED',SCANNED);@E@#@@      IZ
)@@G@@       IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE NE 0 THEN " SCANNER ERROR @C@@@#            JA
)@@G@@ IF (ERROR\STATUS\CODE NE 0) THEN   @B@#@@                DIRECTIVE\ERROJB
)@@G@@R := ERROR6;@E@@@#                DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR6; " SCANNER EJC
)@@G@@RROR  @D@@@#             ELSE IF (DTYP(SCANNED) NE TYPINT) THEN   @G@@@#JD
)@@G@@                DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR17; " SUBSC TYPE NOT INTEGER    JE
)@@G@@@#@@@@             ELSE @C@#@@              BEGIN " SUBSCRIPT EXPRESSIONJF
)@@G@@ CHECK@B@@@#              BEGIN " EVAL SUBSCRIPT FORM @J@#@@            JG
)@@G@@    SUBSCRIPT\FORM := PARSE\SUBSCRIPT(LEFT\VAR,SCANNED); " EVALUATE SUBSJH
)@@G@@CR    @H@@@#                SUBSCRIPT\FORM := PARSE\SUBSCRIPT(LEFT\VAR,SJI
)@@G@@CANNED); " TEST IT@C@@@@                IF (ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0) THENJJ
)@@G@@@B@@@@                 BEGIN " SCAN ASSIGNMENT  @E@@@@                  JK
)@@G@@ SCAN\ASSIGNMENT; " SCAN := AND VALUE     @D@@@@                   IF CSJL
)@@G@@DTYP NE DTYP(LEFT\VAR) THEN   @C@#@@                      DIRECTIVE\ERROJM
)@@G@@R := ERROR4;@G@@@#                      DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR4; " TYPJN
)@@G@@ES DONT MATCH     @^@@@@                   ELSE @B@@@@                  JO
)@@G@@  BEGIN " PERFORM STORE @H@@@@                      TPTR := DADR(LEFT\VAJP
)@@G@@R); " GET POINTER TO STORE AREA     @D@@@@                      IF CSDLEJQ
)@@G@@N+BSUB GT ESUB+1 THEN   @D@#@@                         DIRECTIVE\ERROR :JR
)@@G@@= ERROR8;   @F@@@#                         DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR8; " JS
)@@G@@OUT OF RANGE@ @@@@                      ELSE    @B@@@@                  JT
)@@G@@     BEGIN " FRV CHECK  @B@@@@                         IF STORE\OK THEN JU
)@@G@@@D@@@@                            CASEENTRY DTYP(LEFT\VAR)  @C@@@@      JV
)@@G@@                      CASE TYPINT,TYPDST: @D@@@@                        JW
)@@G@@       FOR I := 1 TO CSDLEN DO@E@@@@                                  TNJX
)@@G@@UM(BSUB-1+I) := DNUM(I);@B@@@@                            CASE TYPSTR:  JY
)@@G@@@D@@@@                               FOR I := 1 TO CSDLEN DO@E@@@@      JZ
)@@G@@                            TCHR(BSUB-1+I) := DCHR(I);@A@@@@            KA
)@@G@@                CASE *: @E@@@@                               DIRECTIVE\EKB
)@@G@@RROR := ERROR3;   @A@@@@                            ENDCASE;@B@@@@      KC
)@@G@@                 END; " FRV CHECK   @B@@@@                    END; " PERKD
)@@G@@FORM STORE  @B@@@@                 END; " SCAN ASSIGNMENT   @C@#@@      KE
)@@G@@        END; " SUBSCRIPT EXPRESSION CHECK @B@@@#              END; " EVAKF
)@@G@@L SUBSCRIPT FORM  @A@@@@           END; " SCAN SUBSCRIPT    @A@@@@END; "KG
)@@G@@ PERFORM\SUBSCRIPTED\STORE    @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@KH
)@@G@@"     @G@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE PROCESSES STORES INTO SYSTEM VARIABLES.  ASKI
)@@G@@ OF THIS    @G@@@@" TIME, ONLY XVARS ARE ALLOWED TO BE SET.  CHECKS FOR KJ
)@@G@@CONSISTENCY ARE   @E@@@@" IN ROUTINE SET\EXECUTED\VARIABLE IN MODULE OPEKK
)@@G@@R-XVARS.    @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\SYSTEM\LET  @[@@@@BEGIN KL
)@@G@@@H@@@@DECLARE   LEFT\VAR: MACHINE POINTER; " TO SYMBOL TABLE ENTRY FOR LKM
)@@G@@EFT VAR     @[@@@@"     @G@@@@          LEFT\VAR := LOOKUP\SYSTEM\SYMBOLKN
)@@G@@(MONOCASE\PTR); " LOOK IT UP  @B@@@@          IF (LEFT\VAR EQ NULL\PTR) KO
)@@G@@THEN  @F@@@@             DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR3; " NOTHING TO STORE IKP
)@@G@@NTO   @#@@@@          ELSE    @ @@@@           BEGIN " TYPE CHECK @E@@@@KQ
)@@G@@             CASEENTRY DTYP(LEFT\VAR) " WHAT TYPE IS IT     @ @@@@      KR
)@@G@@       CASE TYPXVR:     @ @@@@              BEGIN " SET XVAR@E@@@@      KS
)@@G@@          SCAN\ASSIGNMENT; " SCAN := AND NEW VALUE    @C@@@@            KT
)@@G@@    IF (ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0) THEN@H@@@@                   SET\EXECUTEKU
)@@G@@D\VARIABLE(DLEN(LEFT\VAR),SCANNED); " SET VALUE @ @@@@              END;KV
)@@G@@ " SET XVAR @^@@@@             CASE *:    @F@@@@                DIRECTIVKW
)@@G@@E\ERROR := ERROR3; " NOTHING TO STORE INTO@^@@@@             ENDCASE;   KX
)@@G@@@ @@@@           END; " TYPE CHECK  @ @@@@END; " PROCESS\SYSTEM\LET     KY
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE IKZ
)@@G@@S CALLED TO SKIP BLANKS @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE SKIP\BLANKS   @[@@@@LA
)@@G@@BEGIN @F@@@@          WHILE (CHARACTER EQ BLANK) AND NOT END\OF\INPUT\CALB
)@@G@@RD DO @A@@@@             GET\NEXT\CHARACTER;    @C@@@@          IF END\OLC
)@@G@@F\INPUT\CARD THEN " AN ERROR  @B@@@@             DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROLD
)@@G@@R2;   @#@@@@END; " SKIP\BLANKS@[@@@@"     @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCELE
)@@G@@DURE IS CALLED TO SCAN THE := AND RIGHT-PART    @^@@@@" OF ALL ASSIGNMENLF
)@@G@@TS.   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE SCAN\ASSIGNMENT     @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@LG
)@@G@@          SKIP\BLANKS; " ALLOW BLANKS BEFORE := @B@@@@          IF DIRECLH
)@@G@@TIVE\ERROR EQ 0 THEN    @E@@@@             IF CHARACTER EQ COLON THEN " LI
)@@G@@FIRST PART OF :=  @^@@@@              BEGIN     @D@@@@                GELJ
)@@G@@T\NEXT\CHARACTER; " MAKE SURE ITS = @B@@@@                IF CHARACTER ELK
)@@G@@Q EQUL THEN @G@@@@                SCAN(EVAL+CTRM+ALLOW\INT+ALLOW\STR+ALLLL
)@@G@@OW\DST+ALLOW\TAB);@^@@@@                ELSE    @C@@@@                  LM
)@@G@@ DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR10;  @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@            LN
)@@G@@ ELSE @F@@@@                DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR11; " NO := SEEN IS LO
)@@G@@ERROR @^@@@@END; " SCAN\ASSIGNMENT  @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@NG TO STORE INTO !LP

)@@G@@YMBOL-PROCS',IMPORTED); @B@@@[          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  NS
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @G@@@@" THIS MODULE PROCESSES THE DECLARE DIRECTIVE, WHICH INT
)@@G@@S USED TO DEFINE  @#@@@@" DPS VARIABLES.  @D@@@@"   .DECLARE[,<OPTIONS>]NU
)@@G@@ <VAR1>[,<VAR2>,...,<VARN>]   @ @@@@" THE PERMITTED OPTIONS ARE   @^@@@@NV
)@@G@@"         C - COMMAND   @^@@@@"         D - DOCUMENT  @H@@@@"         F NW
)@@G@@- FORWARD REFERENCE (CHANGE DURING FORMAT ONLY, NO ERROR, UNBOUND)@G@@@@NX
)@@G@@"         U - UNBOUND (I.E. NOT RESTORED DURING DOCUMENT PROCESSING)    NY
)@@G@@@G@@@@"         B - BOUND TO UNIT (SAVED AND RESTORED AT UNIT BOUNDARIESNZ
)@@G@@)     @D@@@@"         P - PERMANENT (SAVE AT SESSION TERMINATION) @A@@@@OA
)@@G@@"         T - TEMPORARY (NOT SAVED) @ @@@@"         L - LOCAL TO MACRO  OB
)@@G@@@E@@@@"         H - DEFINE ONE LEVEL HIGHER THAN CURRENT MACRO    @F@@@@OC
)@@G@@"         G - GLOBAL (PUSHES DEFINITION TO EITHER DOC OR KEYBOARD)@[@@@@OD
)@@G@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\DECLARE\DIRECTIVE EXPORTED ('PRODECLARE') OE
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @B@@@@          IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\H) THEN  @G@@@@      OF
)@@G@@       PROCESS\DECLARATION(DOC\GLOBAL); " PUSH DEF UP ONE LEVEL   @C@@@@OG
)@@G@@          ELSE IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\L) THEN   @C@@@@             PROCEOH
)@@G@@SS\DECLARATION(DOC\LOCAL);    @C@@@@          ELSE IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCIOI
)@@G@@I\F) THEN   @B@@@@             PROCESS\DECLARATION(DOC\FRV);@#@@@[      OJ
)@@G@@    ELSE    @A@@@[             WARNING(W\DIR\SYNTAX); @C@@@@END; " PROROOK
)@@G@@CEDURE PROCESS\DECLARE\DIRECTIVE    @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@OL
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@)@@[F]@[]@^K)]K@K)#K@@@@OM
)@@G@@/K@@@@/,0@@@[[[@@^C9@@@]/-@@@DC[@@@[C;0@@]/\)@@@/K@@@@AA@@@@)@D[F]@CK@K)ON
)@@G@@#K^C@)@@@@@@;D@@@]C[@@@[/K@@@@/,0@@@[[[@@^C9@@@#/-@@@K;D@@@)C[@@@]AB@@@@OO
)@@G@@)@M[F@[]@H@[]@L@@@@@@@@@/K@@@@/,0@@@[[[@@^C9@@@D/K@@@@/,0@@@[[[@@^C9@@@[OP
)@@G@@/-@@@RAC@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@OQ
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@^@@A@@E@@ @@O@@[@@S@@@@@E@@@@C@@@V@@@@@@@@@@@@OR
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@PLS$EPI1    PLS$PRO1    DIRDEF      PROVARDEC   WARNING$LIJ OS
)@@G@@PRODECLARE  @@[@@@@@@@@[@@PM7Y@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[S@@@*SDFF*@]@@@@MODULEOT
)@@G@@;     @E@@@@" THIS MODULE CONTAINS PROCEDURES TO UNPACK THE INPUT TEXT, OU
)@@G@@@D@@@@" ASSEMBLE WORDS, AND CONCATENATE THEM IN AN OUTPUT   @#@@@@" STAGOV
)@@G@@ING AREA.   @[@@@@"     @C@@@@" THE CHARACTERS ARE TAKEN OE AT A TIME FROW
)@@G@@OM THE@D@@@@" PACKED 'INPUT\CARD' AND TRANSFERED TO THE TEMPORARY @F@@@@OX
)@@G@@" UNPACKING AREA 'NEXT\WORD'.  AT THE SAME TIME THE CHARACTER     @E@@@@OY
)@@G@@" WIDTHS ARE OBTAINED AND ACCUMULATED FROM THE FINAL DEVICE @]@@@@" TABLOZ
)@@G@@ES.   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" AFTER A WORD HAS BEEN ASSEMBLED THE 'MOVE\NEXTPA
)@@G@@\WORD\TO\LINE'    @F@@@@" PROCEDURE IS CALLED TO MOVE THE UNPACKED SINGLPB
)@@G@@E WORD TO THE     @D@@@@" UNPACKED LINE ASSEMBLY AREA.  THE 'WORD\WIDTH'PC
)@@G@@ S ARE@E@@@@" ACCUMULATED UNTIL THE DESIRED 'LINE\WIDTH' IS OBTAINED.   PD
)@@G@@@E@@@@" AFTER APPROPRIATE JUSTIFICATION ETC, THE FINAL DEVICE     @D@@@@PE
)@@G@@" HANDLER WILL BE CALLED BY ANOTHER PROCEDURE TO DO   @D@@@@" THE FINAL PF
)@@G@@PACKING OF THE LINE INTO 'OUTPUT\CARD' AND@B@@@@" TO SHIP IT OFF TO THE PG
)@@G@@FINAL DEVICE.     @E@@@@"      NOTE: CHARACTERS PASS THROUGH FOUR STAGESPH
)@@G@@ INDICATED  @F@@@@"      BY THE NAMES GIVEN THE ASSOCIATED VARIABLES.  TPI
)@@G@@HEY ARE:    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@"           CARD, WORD, LINE, AND OUTPUT. PJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @F@@@@"      CARD AND OUTPUT ARE PACKED QUARTER WORDS, WORD PK
)@@G@@AND LINE    @A@@@@"       ARE UNPACKED QUARTER WORDS. @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PL
)@@G@@          COPY ('DEFINES',IMPORTED);@B@@@@          COPY ('ACTION-DEF',IPM
)@@G@@MPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('BREAK-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @A@@@@  COPYPN
)@@G@@('DEBUG-PROCS',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('CORE-PROCS',IMPORTEPO
)@@G@@D);   @B@@@@          COPY ('CONTROL-DEF',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPP
)@@G@@PY ('CONVERT-PROC',IMPORTED); @B@@@@          COPY ('CHAR-SIZE',IMPORTEDPQ
)@@G@@);    @E@@@@          COPY ('CARD-DEF',IMPORTED); " GET I/O CARD DEFS   PR
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('DIRECT-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('GPS
)@@G@@ETPUT-DEF',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('AREA-DEF',IMPORTED);     PT
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('PRINT-PROCS',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('PPU
)@@G@@USH-PROCS',IMPORTED);   @B@@@@          COPY ('STAGING-DEF',IMPORTED);  PV
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('STAT-DEF',IMPORTED);     @B@@@@          COPY ('UPW
)@@G@@NIT-COMMON',IMPORTED);  @B@@@@          COPY ('WARNING-DEF',IMPORTED);  PX
)@@G@@@B@@@@          COPY ('UNIT-DEF',IMPORTED);     @[@@@@      @[@@@@      PY
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @C@@@@PROCEDURE READ\NEXT\CARD IMPORTED ('READ');     @[@@@@PZ
)@@G@@      @D@@@@PROCEDURE GET\ACTION\INDEX IMPORTED('GETACTINDEX')    @^@@@@QA
)@@G@@RESULT WORD INTEGER;    @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @F@@@@PROCEDURE LINE\EMPQB
)@@G@@TY IMPORTED ('LINEMT') RESULT WORD CONDITION;   @[@@@@      @D@@@@PROCEDQC
)@@G@@URE DO\EOI\FUNCTIONS IMPORTED ('DOEOIFUNC');    @[@@@@      @C@@@@PROCEDQD
)@@G@@URE PROCESS\DIRECTIVE IMPORTED ('PRODIR');@[@@@@      @C@@@@PROCEDURE GEQE
)@@G@@T\NEXT\CHAR IMPORTED ('GETCHR');    @[@@@@      @D@@@@PROCEDURE BACKUP\CQF
)@@G@@HARACTER IMPORTED ('BACKUPCHAR');   @[@@@@      @F@@@@PROCEDURE PUT\CHARQG
)@@G@@ACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD IMPORTED ('PUTCHRNXTWD');  @[@@@@      @D@@@@PROCEDQH
)@@G@@URE PUT\FUNC\INTO\WORD(FUNCTION: WORD INTEGER,  @D@@@@             VALUEQI
)@@G@@: DISTANCE) IMPORTED ('PUTFUNWORD');@[@@@@      @[@@@@      @D@@@@PROCEDQJ
)@@G@@URE GET\NEXT\CHARACTER IMPORTED ('GETCHR');     @[@@@@      @E@@@@PROCEDQK
)@@G@@URE PROCESS\ESCAPE\SEQUENCE IMPORTED ('DEVICESC');    @[@@@@      @[@@@@QL
)@@G@@      @[@@@@      @C@@@@PROCEDURE ASSEMBLE\NEXT\WORD EXPORTED ('ASBLNW')QM
)@@G@@@[@@@@BEGIN @[@@@@      @B@@@@DECLARE   ACTION\SWITCH: WORD INTEGER;    QN
)@@G@@@H@@@@DECLARE   LEADING\BLANK: WORD CONDITION; " SET WHEN SCANNING LEADIQO
)@@G@@NG BLANKS   @D@@@@DECLARE   TAB\FOUND: WORD CONDITION; " SET TO DO TAB  QP
)@@G@@@E@@@@DECLARE   NEXT\TAB: DISTANCE; " ROUNDED VALUE OF NEXT TAB   @ @@@@QQ
)@@G@@DECLARE   DSET: DISTANCE;     @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" BEGIN CODE EXECUTION  QR
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @E@@@@          LEADING\BLANK := TRUE; " SCANNING LEADING BLQS
)@@G@@ANKS  @A@@@@          IF FUNC\PENDING NE 0 THEN @#@@@@           BEGIN  QT
)@@G@@@C@@@@             ACTION\SWITCH := FUNC\PENDING;     @E@@@@            QU
)@@G@@ FUNC\PENDING := 0; " CLEAR PENDING FUNCTION    @G@@@@             FIRSTQV
)@@G@@\INPUT\COLUMN := FALSE; " ASSUME NOT AT BEGINNING NOW @A@@@@            QW
)@@G@@ GOTO CHARACTER\ACTION; @#@@@@           END;   @]@@@@NEXT\CARD:  @D@@@@QX
)@@G@@          IF END\OF\INPUT\CARD THEN   " GET NEW ONE   @#@@@@           BQY
)@@G@@EGIN  @A@@@@             IF EOI\CARD\READ THEN "@^@@@@              BEGIQZ
)@@G@@N     @D@@@@                EOI\CARD\READ := FALSE; " NO CARD YET @C@@@@RA
)@@G@@                DO\EOI\FUNCTIONS; " DO THEM     @#@@@@              END;RB
)@@G@@@ @@@@             READ\NEXT\CARD;  @A@@@@             IF END\OF\UNIT THRC
)@@G@@EN    @^@@@@                RETURN; @D@@@@             GET\NEXT\CHARACTERD
)@@G@@R; " GET FIRST CHARACTER@E@@@@             IF CHARACTER EQ PERIOD AND CARE
)@@G@@RD\INDEX EQ 2 THEN@F@@@@                GOTO DIRECTIVE\CHARACTER; " PROCRF
)@@G@@ESS DIRECTIVE     @D@@@@             EOI\CARD\READ := TRUE; " GOT CARD FRG
)@@G@@OR EOI@E@@@@             GOTO GOT\CHARACTER; " PROCESS FIRST CHARACTER  RH
)@@G@@@#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@      @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" UNPACK THE NEXT RI
)@@G@@WORD INTO NEXT\WORD     @[@@@@"     @#@@@@NEXT\CHARACTER:   @D@@@@      RJ
)@@G@@    GET\NEXT\CHARACTER; " GET ANOTHER CHARACTER @F@@@@          FIRST\INRK
)@@G@@PUT\COLUMN := FALSE; " NOLONGER IN FIRST COLUMN @#@@@@GOT\CHARACTER:    RL
)@@G@@@E@@@@          IF END\OF\INPUT\CARD THEN " PROCESS END OF CARD   @#@@@@RM
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" GOT END OF INPUT CARD @[@@@@"     RN
)@@G@@@E@@@@             IF NOSPACE OR " DON'T TERMINATE WORD ON EOC    @G@@@@RO
)@@G@@                CARD\ENDED\WITH\DIRECTIVE THEN " DON'T TERMINATE WORD   RP
)@@G@@@A@@@@                GOTO NEXT\CARD;     @H@@@@             IF FILL ANDRQ
)@@G@@ WORD\INDEX EQ 0 THEN " FILLING AND NO WORD FOUND     @E@@@@            RR
)@@G@@    GOTO NEXT\CARD; " GO TO NEXT INPUT CARD     @G@@@@             ELSE RS
)@@G@@IF NOT FILL THEN " CANNOT MOVE WORDS FROM LINE TO LINE@^@@@@            RT
)@@G@@  BEGIN     @H@@@@                IF CARD\LENGTH EQ 0 THEN " BLANK CARD RU
)@@G@@NEED SOMETHING TO OUTPUT@H@@@@                   PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXTRV
)@@G@@\WORD; " PUT AT LEAST ONE BLANK CHAR@D@@@@                END\OF\PARAGRARW
)@@G@@PH := TRUE; " BREAK LINE@#@@@@              END;@F@@@@             GOTO RX
)@@G@@BREAK; " END OF INPUT CARD CAUSES WORD BREAK    @#@@@@           END;   RY
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @B@@@@" NOT END OF CARD, GOT NEXT CHARACTER     @[@@@@"     RZ
)@@G@@@C@@@@          ACTION\SWITCH := GET\ACTION\INDEX;    @E@@@@          GOSA
)@@G@@TO CHARACTER\ACTION;   " TAKE APPROPRIATE ACTION@[@@@@      @D@@@@SWITCHSB
)@@G@@    CHARACTER\ACTION = CASE ACTION\SWITCH OF    @ @@@@          [BACKSPASC
)@@G@@CE\CHARACTER@ @@@@           ,BREAK\CHARACTER   @ @@@@           ,CENTERSD
)@@G@@\CHARACTER  @D@@@@           ,* " THIS IS DEQU AND CAN'T EXIST HERE     SE
)@@G@@@A@@@@           ,DIRECTIVE\CHARACTER     @F@@@@           ,NEXT\CHARACTSF
)@@G@@ER " EQU, REQUIRES NEXT CHARACTER FETCH   @ @@@@           ,ESCAPE\CHARASG
)@@G@@CTER  @ @@@@           ,FLUSH\CHARACTER   @ @@@@           ,HYPHEN\CHARASH
)@@G@@CTER  @ @@@@           ,LNEXT\CHARACTER   @ @@@@           ,NON\TRIVIAL\SI
)@@G@@BLANK @E@@@@           ,NEXT\CHARACTER " PEQU, GOT GET NEXT CHARACTER   SJ
)@@G@@@ @@@@           ,NORMAL\CHARACTER  @ @@@@           ,TAB\CHARACTER     SK
)@@G@@@A@@@@           ,UNDERLINE\CHARACTER     @F@@@@           ,* " THIS IS SL
)@@G@@WIDTH AND HAS NOT BEEN IMPLEMENTED YET    @^@@@@          ,DSUP\CHAR    SM
)@@G@@@^@@@@          ,DINF\CHAR    @^@@@@          ,DSIS\CHAR    @^@@@@      SN
)@@G@@    ,DSIE\CHAR    @#@@@@           ];     @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @[@@@@SO
)@@G@@"     @^@@@@" BACKSPACE CHARACTER   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@BACKSPACE\CHARACTESP
)@@G@@R:    @C@@@@          PUT\FUNC\INTO\WORD(FUNC\BACKSPACE,0); @E@@@@      SQ
)@@G@@    PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD; " STUFF BACKSPACE   @D@@@@          GOSR
)@@G@@TO NEXT\CHARACTER; " GET NEXT CHARACTER   @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" GOTO A WORSS
)@@G@@D BREAK CHARACTER, CREATES WORD BREAK BUT NO SPACE    @[@@@@"     @#@@@@ST
)@@G@@BREAK\CHARACTER:  @E@@@@          PUT\FUNC\INTO\WORD(FUNC\BREAK,0); " SESU
)@@G@@T FUNCTION  @A@@@@          GOTO UNPACKED; " RETURN   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@SV
)@@G@@" CENTER REMAINDER OF LINE    @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CENTER\CHARACTER: @C@@@@SW
)@@G@@          PUT\FUNC\INTO\WORD(FUNC\CENTER,0);    @ @@@@          GOTO NEXSX
)@@G@@T\CHARACTER;@[@@@@"     @F@@@@" FOUND DIRECTIVE CALL (EITHER PERIOD IN CSY
)@@G@@OL ONE OR BACKSLASH)    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@DIRECTIVE\CHARACTER:    @ @@@@SZ
)@@G@@          DIRECTIVE := TRUE;  @ @@@@          PROCESS\DIRECTIVE;  @F@@@@TA
)@@G@@          IF WORD\BREAK OR REMOTE\BREAK THEN " RETURN TO HANDLE   @#@@@@TB
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @ @@@@             GOTO UNPACKED;   @#@@@@           ETC
)@@G@@ND;   @C@@@@          ELSE " CONTINUE INPUT CHARACTER SCAN  @A@@@@      TD
)@@G@@       GOTO NEXT\CHARACTER;   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" SPECIAL ESCAPE SEQUENCTE
)@@G@@E, CALL FD HANDLER@[@@@@"     @#@@@@ESCAPE\CHARACTER: @A@@@@          PRTF
)@@G@@OCESS\ESCAPE\SEQUENCE;  @ @@@@          GOTO NEXT\CHARACTER;@[@@@@"     TG
)@@G@@@B@@@@" FLUSH REMAINDER OF LINE TO THE RIGHT    @[@@@@"     @#@@@@FLUSH\TH
)@@G@@CHARACTER:  @C@@@@           PUT\FUNC\INTO\WORD(FUNC\FLUSH,0);    @ @@@@TI
)@@G@@          GOTO NEXT\CHARACTER;@[@@@@"     @C@@@@" HYPHEN WORD AT THIS CHTJ
)@@G@@ARACTER IF NECESSARY    @E@@@@"          THE CHARACTER WILL NEVER APPEARTK
)@@G@@ IN THE OUTPUT    @[@@@@"     @#@@@@HYPHEN\CHARACTER: @E@@@@          PUTL
)@@G@@T\FUNC\INTO\WORD(FUNC\HYPHEN,0); " SET FUNCTION @E@@@@          GOTO NEXTM
)@@G@@T\CHARACTER; " THROW AWAY THIS CHARACTER  @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" LITERAL NETN
)@@G@@XT:  NEXT CHARACTER IS ITSELF @[@@@@"     @#@@@@LNEXT\CHARACTER:  @^@@@@TO
)@@G@@          GET\NEXT\CHAR;@D@@@@          PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD; " TP
)@@G@@STUFF IT    @H@@@@          LEADING\BLANK := FALSE; " TERMINATE LEADING TQ
)@@G@@BLANK SCAN IF STILL SET @D@@@@          GOTO NEXT\CHARACTER; " GET ANOTHTR
)@@G@@ER CHARACTER@[@@@@"     @A@@@@" NON COMPRESSABLE BLANK CHARACTER  @[@@@@TS
)@@G@@"     @#@@@@NON\TRIVIAL\BLANK:@E@@@@          IF FIRST\INPUT\COLUMN AND TT
)@@G@@NOT LINE\EMPTY THEN     @A@@@@           BEGIN " FORCE END OF LINE@B@@@@TU
)@@G@@             FUNC\PENDING := NTB\CTL;     @B@@@@             END\OF\PARATV
)@@G@@GRAPH := TRUE;    @ @@@@             GOTO UNPACKED;   @#@@@@           ETW
)@@G@@ND;   @E@@@@          ELSE " PROCESS NONTRIVIAL BLANK NOT IN COL ONE    TX
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@             CHARACTER := BLANK; " MAKE THTY
)@@G@@E CHARACTER A BLANK     @D@@@@             PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD;TZ
)@@G@@ " STUFF IT @#@@@@           END;   @D@@@@          GOTO NEXT\CHARACTER;UA
)@@G@@ " GET NEXT CHARACTER   @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" NORMAL CHARACTER, PUT IT INTUB
)@@G@@O NEXT WORD @D@@@@" BUT FIRST CHECK FOR WORD BREAK AND LEADING BLANKS   UC
)@@G@@@[@@@@"     @#@@@@NORMAL\CHARACTER: @E@@@@          IF CHARACTER EQ BLANUD
)@@G@@K THEN " DO SPECIAL CHECKING  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@            UE
)@@G@@ IF LEADING\BLANK THEN " STILL NO NONBLANKS FOUND YET @^@@@@            UF
)@@G@@  BEGIN     @C@@@@                IF COMPACT THEN " THROW IT AWAY @F@@@@UG
)@@G@@                   GOTO NEXT\CHARACTER; " AND GET NEXT CHARACTER  @B@@@@UH
)@@G@@              END; " LEADING BLANK TEST   @D@@@@             ELSE " TRAIUI
)@@G@@LING BLANK CAUSES WORD BREAK  @^@@@@              BEGIN     @B@@@@      UJ
)@@G@@          GOTO BREAK; " BREAK WORD  @#@@@@              END;@ @@@@      UK
)@@G@@     END; " BLANK TEST  @A@@@@          ELSE " CHARACTER NOT BALNK@F@@@@UL
)@@G@@             LEADING\BLANK := FALSE; " NO MORE LEADING BLANK SCAN @E@@@@UM
)@@G@@          PUT\CHARACTER\INTO\NEXT\WORD; " STUFF CHARACTER   @C@@@@      UN
)@@G@@    GOTO NEXT\CHARACTER; " GET NEXT ONE   @#@@@@TAB\CHARACTER:    @G@@@@UO
)@@G@@          IF NOT FIRST\INPUT\COLUMN OR LINE\EMPTY THEN " SEARCH FOR TAB UP
)@@G@@@C@@@@           BEGIN " SEARCH FOR NEXT TAB STOP     @[@@@@"     @^@#@@UQ
)@@G@@" FIND NEXT TAB STOP    @G@@@#" SEARCH FOR NEXT EFFECTIVE TAB STOP.  IF UR
)@@G@@TAB FOUND AT LARGER POSITION  @G@@@#" THAN CURRENT POSITION, IT IS UNCONUS
)@@G@@DITIONALLY TAKEN.  IF TAB IS FOUND  @G@@@#" *AT* CURRENT POSITION, IT ISUT
)@@G@@ ONLY TAKEN IF IT IS IMMEDIATELY TO THE   @G@@@#" RIGHT OF WHITE SPACE (UU
)@@G@@FUNCTION SPACE\CODE) OR IF IT IS THE VERY FIRST @D@@@#" THING ON THE LINUV
)@@G@@E (THIS HANDLES TABSTOP AT ZERO!).  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@             TAB\FUW
)@@G@@OUND := FALSE; " NO TAB FOUND YET   @F@#@@             NUM\BLANKS := 0; UX
)@@G@@        " START JUSTIFICATION HERE  @F@@@#             NUM\BLANKS := 0; UY
)@@G@@   " *** START JUSTIFICATION HERE   @C@@@@             FOR J := 1 TO NUMUZ
)@@G@@BER\OF\TABS DO    @^@#@@              BEGIN     @A@@@#              BEGIVA
)@@G@@N " FIND TAB STOP @G@@@@                NEXT\TAB := ROUND\WIDTH(TABSTOP(VB
)@@G@@J)); " GET NEXT TAB STOP@H@@@@                IF LINE\WIDTH+WORD\WIDTH LVC
)@@G@@T NEXT\TAB THEN " TAB TO NEXT STOP  @^@#@@                 BEGIN  @D@@@@VD
)@@G@@                   TAB\FOUND := TRUE; " MARK TO TAB   @^@#@@            VE
)@@G@@     END;   @H@@@@                ELSE IF LINE\WIDTH+WORD\WIDTH EQ NEXT\VF
)@@G@@TAB THEN " ALREADY THERE@^@#@@                 BEGIN  @B@@@#            VG
)@@G@@     BEGIN " TEST TAB HERE    @G@@@@                   IF WORD\INDEX GT VH
)@@G@@0 THEN " CHECK LAST CHAR IN WORD    @ @#@@                    BEGIN     VI
)@@G@@@F@#@@                      IF SPACE\CODE(NEXT\WORD(WORD\INDEX)) THEN   VJ
)@@G@@@G@@@#                      TAB\FOUND := SPACE\CODE(NEXT\WORD(WORD\INDEXVK
)@@G@@));   @D@#@@                         TAB\FOUND := TRUE; " GOT ONE @B@#@@VL
)@@G@@                    END; " CHECKING WORD  @H@@@#                   ELSE VM
)@@G@@IF LINE\INDEX GT USER\LINE\START THEN " THEN IN LINE  @G@#@@            VN
)@@G@@       ELSE IF SPACE\CODE(LINE\BUFFER(LINE\INDEX)) THEN     @G@@@#      VO
)@@G@@                TAB\FOUND := SPACE\CODE(LINE\BUFFER(LINE\INDEX)); @B@@@#VP
)@@G@@                   ELSE " COLUMN ZERO TAB @D@#@@                      TAVQ
)@@G@@B\FOUND := TRUE; " GOT TAB    @D@@@#                      TAB\FOUND := TVR
)@@G@@RUE; " GOT TAB    @C@#@@                 END; " OF EQUAL TO TABSTOP     VS
)@@G@@@B@@@#                 END; " TEST TAB HERE     @D@@@@                IFVT
)@@G@@ TAB\FOUND THEN " DO THE TAB HERE   @^@#@@                 BEGIN  @B@@@#VU
)@@G@@                 BEGIN " PERFORM TABBING  @D@@@@                   ADD\SVV
)@@G@@PACE\TO\NEXT\WORD( FUNC\TAB , @E@@@@                      NEXT\TAB - WORVW
)@@G@@D\WIDTH - LINE\WIDTH ); @G@#@@                      INHIBIT\LEFT\INDENT VX
)@@G@@:= TRUE;  " INHIBIT INDENTION @G@@@#                   INHIBIT\LEFT\INDEVY
)@@G@@NT := TRUE;  " INHIBIT INDENTION    @H@#@@                      LEADING\VZ
)@@G@@BLANK := TRUE; " SCAN THRU ANY LEADING BLANKS   @G@@@#                  WA
)@@G@@ LEADING\BLANK := TRUE; " SCAN THRU ANY LEADING BLANKS@B@@@@            WB
)@@G@@       GOTO NEXT\CHARACTER;   @C@#@@                 END; " ADD SPACE FOWC
)@@G@@R THE TAB   @B@@@#                 END; " PERFORM TABBING   @C@#@@      WD
)@@G@@        END; " OF LOOP OVER TAB STOPS     @A@@@#              END; " FINWE
)@@G@@D TAB STOP  @B@@@@           END; " SEARCH FOR TAB STOP     @[@@@@"     WF
)@@G@@@F@@@@" EITHER TAB CHARACTER FOUND IN COLUMN ONE => MUST CAUSE LINE     WG
)@@G@@@E@@@@" BREAK AND PROCESS TAB AFTER BREAK, OR NO TAB STOP FOUND.  @F@@@@WH
)@@G@@" IN EITHER CASE, CAUSE LINE BREAK AND REMEMBER TO PROCESS TAB    @A@@@@WI
)@@G@@" THE NEXT TIME GET-WORD IS CALLED. @[@@@@"     @A@@@@          FUNC\PENWJ
)@@G@@DING := TAB\CTL;  @F@@@@          END\OF\PARAGRAPH := TRUE;        " FORWK
)@@G@@CE END OF LINE    @A@@@@          GOTO BREAK; " BREAK WORD  @[@@@@"     WL
)@@G@@@A@@@@" BEGIN OR END OF UNDERLINED FIELD  @[@@@@"     @^@@@@UNDERLINE\CHWM
)@@G@@ARACTER:    @C@@@@          PUT\FUNC\INTO\WORD(FUNC\UNDERLINE,0); @ @@@@WN
)@@G@@          GOTO NEXT\CHARACTER;@[@@@@"     @ @@@@" BEGIN SUPERIOR (SUPERSWO
)@@G@@CRIPT)@[@@@@"     @]@@@@DSUP\CHAR:  @ @@@@"         DISPLAY('GWDSUP',0);WP
)@@G@@@D@@@@          IF (WORD\DSI\MODE EQ DSI\MODE\NONE) THEN    @#@@@@      WQ
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @F@@@@             WORD\DSI\MODE := DSI\MODE\AONE; " NORMAL WR
)@@G@@SUPERSCRIPT @G@@@@             WORD\DSI\START := WORD\WIDTH; " SAVE WIDTWS
)@@G@@H FOR COMPUTATION @F@@@@             WORD\DSI\FIRST := 0; " ZERO LENGTH WT
)@@G@@OF FIRST PART     @G@@@@             PUT\FUNC\INTO\WORD(FUNC\DSIB,0); " WU
)@@G@@TELL DEVICE ABOUT IT    @#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@          GOTO NEXWV
)@@G@@T\CHARACTER;@[@@@@"     @ @@@@" BEGIN INFERIOR (SUBSCRIPT)  @[@@@@"     WW
)@@G@@@]@@@@DINF\CHAR:  @ @@@@"         DISPLAY('GWDINF',0);@D@@@@          IFWX
)@@G@@ (WORD\DSI\MODE EQ DSI\MODE\NONE) THEN    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@WY
)@@G@@             WORD\DSI\MODE := DSI\MODE\AONE; " NORMAL SUBSCRIPT   @G@@@@WZ
)@@G@@             WORD\DSI\START := WORD\WIDTH; " SAVE WIDTH FOR COMPUTATION XA
)@@G@@@F@@@@             WORD\DSI\FIRST := 0; " ZERO LENGTH OF FIRST PART     XB
)@@G@@@G@@@@             PUT\FUNC\INTO\WORD(FUNC\DSIB,1); " TELL DEVICE ABOUT XC
)@@G@@IT    @#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@          GOTO NEXT\CHARACTER;@[@@@@XD
)@@G@@"     @A@@@@" DISPLAY SUPERIOR/INFERIOR SWITCH  @[@@@@"     @]@@@@DSIS\CXE
)@@G@@HAR:  @H@@@@          DSET := (WORD\WIDTH-WORD\DSI\START); " COMPUTE LENXF
)@@G@@GTH OF FIRST PART @A@@@@"         DISPLAY('GWDSIS',DSET);   @D@@@@      XG
)@@G@@    IF (WORD\DSI\MODE EQ DSI\MODE\AONE) THEN    @#@@@@           BEGIN  XH
)@@G@@@G@@@@             WORD\DSI\MODE := DSI\MODE\ATWO; " STATUS IN SECOND PAXI
)@@G@@RT    @G@@@@             WORD\DSI\FIRST := WORD\WIDTH; " SET WIDTH OF FIXJ
)@@G@@RST PART    @H@@@@             PUT\FUNC\INTO\WORD(FUNC\DSIS,DSET); " TELXK
)@@G@@L DEVICE TO SKIP BACK   @G@@@@             WORD\WIDTH := WORD\DSI\START;XL
)@@G@@ " RESET WIDTH FOR SECOND PART@#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@          GOXM
)@@G@@TO NEXT\CHARACTER;@[@@@@"     @^@@@@" END SUPERIOR/INFERIOR @[@@@@"     XN
)@@G@@@]@@@@DSIE\CHAR:  @I@@@@          DSET := (WORD\DSI\FIRST-WORD\WIDTH); "XO
)@@G@@ COMPUTE SHORTAGE OF SECOND PART    @F@@@@          IF (DSET LT 0) THEN XP
)@@G@@" IF SECOND PART IS LONGER THEN     @B@@@@             DSET := 0; " NO SXQ
)@@G@@HORTAGE     @A@@@@"         DISPLAY('GWDSIE',DSET);   @D@@@@          IFXR
)@@G@@ (WORD\DSI\MODE NE DSI\MODE\NONE) THEN    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @F@@@@XS
)@@G@@             WORD\DSI\MODE := DSI\MODE\NONE; " STATUS NORMAL AGAIN@H@@@@XT
)@@G@@             PUT\FUNC\INTO\WORD(FUNC\DSIE,DSET); " TELL DEVICE TO SKIP RXU
)@@G@@ITE   @H@@@@             WORD\WIDTH := WORD\WIDTH + DSET; " AND ACCOUNT XV
)@@G@@FOR SKIP IN WORD  @#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@          GOTO NEXT\CHARXW
)@@G@@ACTER;@[@@@@"     @A@@@@" CREATE WORD BREAK BEFORE RETURNING@[@@@@"     XX
)@@G@@@[@@@@BREAK:@B@@@@          IF SENTENCE\TERMINATOR THEN     @C@@@@      XY
)@@G@@       BREAK\SENTENCE; " SENTENCE BREAK   @#@@@@          ELSE    @C@@@@XZ
)@@G@@             BREAK\WORD; " SIMPLE WORD BREAK    @[@@@@"     @B@@@@" ALL YA
)@@G@@DONE UNPACKING THIS WORD OR LINE    @[@@@@"     @]@@@@UNPACKED:   @F@@@@YB
)@@G@@          WORD\BREAK := FALSE; " WORD BREAK PROCESSING FINISHED   @D@@@@YC
)@@G@@          STAT\CHARS\IN := STAT\CHARS\IN + WORD\INDEX;@C@@@@          STYD
)@@G@@AT\WORDS\IN := STAT\WORDS\IN + 1;   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @F@@@@" RETUYE
)@@G@@RN TRUE IF LAST CHARACTER IS SENTENCE TERMINATOR SO THAT WE @D@@@@" CAN YF
)@@G@@PUT A DOUBLE SPACE ON THE END OF EACH SENTENCE. @[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDYG
)@@G@@URE SENTENCE\TERMINATOR RESULT WORD CONDITION   @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@      YH
)@@G@@    IF NEXT\WORD(WORD\INDEX) EQ PERIOD OR @D@@@@             NEXT\WORD(WYI
)@@G@@ORD\INDEX) EQ QUESTION OR     @D@@@@             NEXT\WORD(WORD\INDEX) EYJ
)@@G@@Q EXCLAMATION THEN@#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             IF END\OF\IYK
)@@G@@NPUT\CARD THEN    @E@@@@                RETURN(TRUE); " YES SENTENCE TERYL
)@@G@@MINATOR     @B@@@@             ELSE " LOOK FOR ANOTHER SPACE@^@@@@      YM
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @D@@@@                GET\NEXT\CHAR; " GET ANOTHER CHAYN
)@@G@@RACTER@B@@@@                IF CHARACTER EQ BLANK THEN@E@@@@            YO
)@@G@@       RETURN(TRUE); " YES, END OF SENTENCE     @B@@@@                ELYP
)@@G@@SE " NOT END OF SENTENCE@^@@@@                 BEGIN  @D@@@@            YQ
)@@G@@       BACKUP\CHARACTER; " RESTORE POINTER@^@@@@                 END;   YR
)@@G@@@#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           END;   @C@@@@          RETURN(FYS
)@@G@@ALSE); " NOT END OF SENTENCE  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" PROCEDURE YT
)@@G@@TO PUT FUNCTION INTO WORD FOR SENTENCE BREAK    @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDYU
)@@G@@URE BREAK\SENTENCE@[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          PUT\FUNC\INTO\WORD(FUNC\SPYV
)@@G@@ACEBAND,    @E@@@@             ROUND\WIDTH(SPACEBAND\WIDTH*SENTENCE\SPACYW
)@@G@@E));  @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @D@@@@" PROCEDURE TO PUT FUNCTION INTO WORYX
)@@G@@D FOR WORD BREAK  @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE BREAK\WORD    @[@@@@BEGIN YY
)@@G@@@C@@@@          PUT\FUNC\INTO\WORD(FUNC\SPACEBAND,    @D@@@@            YZ
)@@G@@ ROUND\WIDTH(SPACEBAND\WIDTH*WORD\SPACE));@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@ZA
)@@G@@" ADD HORIZONTAL SPACING  IN INTERNAL UNITS     @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDZB
)@@G@@URE ADD\SPACE\TO\NEXT\WORD    @G@@@@          (SPFUN: INTEGER WORD " TYPZC
)@@G@@E OF SPACING FUNCTION TO INSERT     @E@@@@          ,SPACE: DISTANCE) " ZD
)@@G@@AMOUNT OF SPACE TO INSERT     @ @@@@          EXPORTED ('ADSPNW') @[@@@@ZE
)@@G@@BEGIN @ @@@@DECLARE   ADD\WIDTH: DISTANCE;@[@@@@      @B@@@@          ADZF
)@@G@@D\WIDTH := ROUND\WIDTH(SPACE);@C@@@@          WORD\WIDTH := WORD\WIDTH +ZG
)@@G@@ ADD\WIDTH; @H@@@@          PUT\FUNC\INTO\WORD(SPFUN,ADD\WIDTH); " FUNC ZH
)@@G@@PASSED (TAB OR BLANK)   @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @E@@@@" THIS PROCEDURE TZI
)@@G@@ESTS IF THE ARGUMENT IS A DPS SPACING CODE@[@@@["     @E@#@[" CBC 3/2/82ZJ
)@@G@@ ALLOW FUNC\NOP AND FUNC\LETTER\SPACE SO THAT A @E@#@["            TAB SZK
)@@G@@ET AT ZERO CAN WORK (SEE SPACE\CODE TEST  @C@#@["            ON LINE\BUFZL
)@@G@@FER(LINE\INDEX) ABOVE!) @[@#@@"     @C@@@@PROCEDURE SPACE\CODE(CHR\TO\TEZM
)@@G@@ST: WORD INTEGER) @A@@@@             RESULT WORD CONDITION  @[@@@@BEGIN ZN
)@@G@@@A@@@@          CASEENTRY CHR\TO\TEST     @D@]@@          CASE BLANK, FUZO
)@@G@@NC\BLANK, FUNC\SPACEBAND:     @D@#@]          CASE BLANK, FUNC\BLANK, FUZP
)@@G@@NC\SPACEBAND,     @D@@@#          CASE BLANK, FUNC\BLANK, FUNC\SPACEBANDZQ
)@@G@@:     @C@#@]               FUNC\NOP, FUNC\LETTER\SPACE:     @ @@@@      ZR
)@@G@@       RETURN(TRUE);    @B@]@[          CASE FUNC\NOP: RETURN(TRUE);    ZS
)@@G@@@#@@@@          CASE *: @ @@@@             RETURN(FALSE);   @#@@@@      ZT
)@@G@@    ENDCASE;@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@    IF)@@[M^C@^C@K@K)]@@C40@@@ZU

)@@G@@"     @^@@@@DEFINE    FLNG = 50,    @^@@@@          HLNG = 2*FLNG,@^@@@@CN
)@@G@@          SLNG = 6*FLNG;@D@@@@DECLARE   TABLE\PTR : STATIC MACHINE WORD CO

)@@G@@@B@@@@          !*: MAPPED [*: 1 BIT LOGICAL    @D@@@@                  DO

)@@G@@XIT: 1 BIT CONDITION    @D@@@@                     ,SHIFT\ACTION: 3 BIT DQ
)@@G@@LOGICAL     @D@@@@                     ,SHIFT\COUNT: 3 BIT LOGICAL];    DR
)@@G@@@B@@@@DECLARE   STRIP\SUFFIX: STATIC CONDITION  @B@@@@          ,INITIALDS
)@@G@@\ENTRY: STATIC CONDITION@B@@@@          ,SUFFIX\FOUND: STATIC CONDITION DT
)@@G@@@C@@@@          ,BREAKPOINT\FOUND: STATIC CONDITION   @C@@@@          ,ODU
)@@G@@RTHOGRAPH\FOUND: STATIC CONDITION;  @B@@@@DECLARE   NODE: STATIC MACHINEDV
)@@G@@ POINTER    @A@@@@          ,CORE: WORD INTEGER BASED @D@@@@          ,SDW
)@@G@@YMBOL(32): STATIC 9 BIT MACHINE LOGICAL   @D@@@@          !SYMWRD(8): LODX
)@@G@@CATABLE MACHINE WORD INTEGER  @D@@@@          ,VECTOR(12): STATIC 9 BIT DY

)@@G@@C WORD INTEGER;   @C@@@@DECLARE   TEMPS  : [VOWELS     : WORD INTEGER   EB
)@@G@@@C@@@@                   ,CONSONANTS : WORD INTEGER]  @E@@@@            EC
)@@G@@      ![TEST\STRING: 36 BIT MACHINE INTEGER     @E@@@@                  ED

)@@G@@GER]; @B@@@@          INCLUDE (DEBUG\CODE, NO SOURCE);@E@@@@DECLARE   HYEG
)@@G@@PHEN\VECTOR(12): STATIC 9 BIT MACHINE LOGICAL   @C@@@@          ,VECTOR\EH
)@@G@@INDEX: STATIC WORD INTEGER;   @D@@@@PROCEDURE DISPLAY\NEXT\WORD IMPORTEDEI
)@@G@@ ('DISNXTWRD');   @#@@@@          RESUME; @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @ @@@@EJ
)@@G@@PROCEDURE TRYHYPHEN EXPORTED  @[@@@@"     @[@@@@BEGIN @^@@@@" BEGIN PROCEK
)@@G@@EDURE BODY  @B@@@@          INCLUDE (DEBUG\CODE, NO SOURCE);@A@@@@      EL
)@@G@@       DISPLAY\NEXT\WORD;     @#@@@@          RESUME; @ @@@@          IFEM
)@@G@@ NOT HYPHEN THEN  @^@@@@             RETURN;    @^@@@@          VINDEX:=EN
)@@G@@0;    @ @@@@          ILLEGAL\CHRS:=0;    @A@@@@          ORTHOGRAPH\FOUEO
)@@G@@ND:=FALSE;  @B@@@@          WORD\WIDTH\LEFT:=WORD\WIDTH;    @A@@@@      EP
)@@G@@    RIGHT\POINTER:=WORD\INDEX;@B@@@@          CHR:=NEXT\WORD(RIGHT\POINTEQ
)@@G@@ER);  @^@@@@          GET\CHR\TYPE; @A@@@@          IF (TYPE EQ S'BLANK'ER
)@@G@@) THEN@H@@@@           BEGIN " IGNORE (BUT DO NOT SUBTRACT WIDTH) ONE TRES
)@@G@@AILING SPACEBAND  @C@@@@             RIGHT\POINTER:=RIGHT\POINTER-1;    ET
)@@G@@@C@@@@             CHR:=NEXT\WORD(RIGHT\POINTER);     @ @@@@            EU
)@@G@@ GET\CHR\TYPE;    @#@@@@           END;   @[@@@@"     @G@@@@" IGNORE (BUEV
)@@G@@T DO NOT FORGET) ANY NUMBER OF TRAILING PUNCTUATION MARKS.  @E@@@@" THISEW
)@@G@@ REPLACES CODE THAT CHECKED FOR S'APOSTROPHE' BELOW.  @[@@@@"     @C@@@@EX
)@@G@@          WHILE (TYPE EQ S'PUNCTUATION') DO     @#@@@@           BEGIN  EY
)@@G@@@H@@@@             WORD\WIDTH\LEFT:=WORD\WIDTH\LEFT-NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(RIGHEZ
)@@G@@T\POINTER); @C@@@@             RIGHT\POINTER:=RIGHT\POINTER-1;    @C@@@@FA
)@@G@@             CHR:=NEXT\WORD(RIGHT\POINTER);     @ @@@@             GET\CFB
)@@G@@HR\TYPE;    @#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@          PTR:=RIGHT\POINTER; FC
)@@G@@@ @@@@          FOR I:=1 TO PTR DO  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@      FD
)@@G@@       CHR:=NEXT\WORD(I);     @ @@@@             GET\CHR\TYPE;    @B@@@@FE
)@@G@@             IF TYPE EQ S'ORTHOGRAPH' THEN@^@@@@              BEGIN     FF
)@@G@@@B@@@@                ORTHOGRAPH\FOUND:=TRUE;   @A@@@@                VIFG
)@@G@@NDEX:=VINDEX+1;   @A@@@@                VECTOR(VINDEX+1):=I;@ @@@@      FH
)@@G@@          ITERATE I;    @#@@@@              END;@G@@@@             IF (TFI
)@@G@@YPE EQ S'NOT\ACCEPTABLE') OR (TYPE EQ S'BLANK') OR    @C@@@@            FJ
)@@G@@    (TYPE EQ S'PUNCTUATION') THEN   @C@@@@                ILLEGAL\CHRS:=FK
)@@G@@ILLEGAL\CHRS+1;   @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          IF ORTHOGRAPH\FL
)@@G@@FOUND THEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @ @@@@             VINDEX:=VINDEX+1;FM
)@@G@@@A@@@@             VECTOR(1):=VINDEX;     @B@[@@             WORD\WIDTH\FN
)@@G@@LEFT:=WORD\WIDTH; @C@@@[" CBC 12/13/81 WORD\WIDTH\LEFT:=WORD\WIDTH;     FO
)@@G@@@A@@@@             RIGHT\POINTER:=PTR;    @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@FP
)@@G@@          ELSE    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             IF ILLEGAL\FQ
)@@G@@CHRS GT 0 THEN    @^@@@@                RETURN; @#@@@@           END;   FR
)@@G@@@]@@@@SET\LIMITS: @F@@@@          DEVICE\HYPHEN\WIDTH:=CHAR\WIDTH( DEVICFS
)@@G@@E\HYPHEN\CHAR+1 );@F@@@@          SPACE\LEFT:=MAX\WIDTH-LINE\WIDTH-DEVICFT
)@@G@@E\HYPHEN\WIDTH;   @B@@@@          INCLUDE (DEBUG\CODE, NO SOURCE);@F@@@@FU
)@@G@@             SPACE\LEFT:=0;  " FORCE FIND ON ALL HYPHEN POINTS    @ @@@@FV
)@@G@@             VECTOR\INDEX:=1; @A@@@@             HYPHEN\VECTOR(1):=PTR; FW
)@@G@@@#@@@@          RESUME; @F@@@@          IF (MAX\WIDTH*SPACE\REMAINING) GFX
)@@G@@T (100*SPACE\LEFT) THEN @^@@@@             RETURN;    @ @@@@          INFY
)@@G@@ITIAL\ENTRY:=TRUE;@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @#@@@@FIND\BREAK\POINT: @^@@@@FZ
)@@G@@          HYPHENATE;    @A@@@@          IF BREAKPOINT\FOUND THEN  @#@@@@GA
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             INCLUDE (DEBUG\CODE, NO SOURCE);   GB
)@@G@@@C@@@@                VECTOR\INDEX:=VECTOR\INDEX+1;   @E@@@@            GC
)@@G@@    HYPHEN\VECTOR(VECTOR\INDEX):=BREAK\INDEX;   @^@@@@             RESUMGD
)@@G@@E;    @[@@@]"     @G@@@]" COMPUTE WIDTH OF PORTION OF WORD TO THE RIGHT GE
)@@G@@OF THE BREAK POINT.     @C@@@]" (CHARACTERS AND *SOME* FUNCTIONS HAVE WIGF
)@@G@@DTHS) @[@@@]"     @E@@@@             FOR I:=RIGHT\POINTER TO BREAK\INDEXGG
)@@G@@+1 BY -1 DO @F@@@]                IF (NEXT\WORD(I) LT FUNC\OFFSET) OR   GH
)@@G@@ " CHARACTER@H@@@]                   (NEXT\WORD(I) EQ FUNC\SPACEBAND) ORGI
)@@G@@ " EXPANDABLE BLANK     @H@@@]                   (NEXT\WORD(I) EQ FUNC\BGJ
)@@G@@LANK) OR     " NON-EXPANDABLE BLANK @F@@@]                   (NEXT\WORD(GK
)@@G@@I) EQ FUNC\TAB) THEN     " TAB?     @G@]@@                WORD\WIDTH\LEFGL
)@@G@@T:=WORD\WIDTH\LEFT-NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(I);    @G@@@]                   WORD\GM
)@@G@@WIDTH\LEFT:=WORD\WIDTH\LEFT-NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(I); @[@@@]"     @G@@@]" MAKEGN
)@@G@@ DECISION WHETHER TO TAKE THIS BREAKPOINT OR SEARCH FOR ANOTHER.  @[@@@]GO
)@@G@@"     @D@@@@             IF (WORD\WIDTH\LEFT GT SPACE\LEFT) OR    @D@@@@GP
)@@G@@                (BREAK\INDEX LT CHARS\THIS\LINE) OR   @F@@@@            GQ
)@@G@@    (WORD\INDEX-BREAK\INDEX LE CHARS\NEXT\LINE) THEN  @^@@@@            GR
)@@G@@  BEGIN     @B@@@@                INITIAL\ENTRY:=FALSE;     @C@@@@      GS
)@@G@@          RIGHT\POINTER:=BREAK\INDEX;     @B@@@@                GOTO FINGT
)@@G@@D\BREAK\POINT;    @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@GU
)@@G@@                GOTO END\HYPHEN;    @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@CONTROGV
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @]@@@@GIVE\UP:    @B@@@@          INCLUDE (DEBUG\CODE, NO SOGW
)@@G@@URCE);@C@@@@             HYPHEN\VECTOR(VECTOR\INDEX+1):=0;  @^@@@@      GX
)@@G@@       EDIT\OPEN; @C@@@@             FOR I:=VECTOR\INDEX TO 1 BY -1 DO  GY
)@@G@@@^@@@@              BEGIN     @C@@@@                INDEX:=HYPHEN\VECTORGZ
)@@G@@(I+1)+1;    @E@@@@                FOR J:=INDEX TO HYPHEN\VECTOR(I) BY 1 HA
)@@G@@DO    @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @B@@@@                   CHR:=NEXT\WHB
)@@G@@ORD(J);     @B@@@@                   EDIT\CHARACTER(CHR);   @^@@@@      HC
)@@G@@           END;   @ @@@@                IF I GT 1 THEN@^@@@@            HD
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @A@@@@                   GET\CHR\TYPE;    @C@@@@            HE
)@@G@@       IF TYPE NE S'ORTHOGRAPH' THEN@C@@@@                      EDIT\CHAHF
)@@G@@RACTER(MINUS);    @^@@@@                 END;   @#@@@@              END;HG
)@@G@@@ @@@@             EDIT\PRINT (1);  @#@@@@          RESUME; @#@@@@      HH
)@@G@@    RETURN; @]@@@@END\HYPHEN: @E@@@@          PTR:=WORD\INDEX+1;  " POINHI
)@@G@@T TO FIRST UNUSED SPACE @C@@@@          BREAK\INDEX:=WORD\INDEX-BREAK\INHJ
)@@G@@DEX;  @D@@@@          WORD\WIDTH\LEFT:=WORD\WIDTH-WORD\WIDTH\LEFT;@C@@@@HK
)@@G@@          WORD\INDEX:=WORD\INDEX-BREAK\INDEX;   @D@@@@          WORD\WIDHL
)@@G@@TH:=WORD\WIDTH-WORD\WIDTH\LEFT;     @A@@@@          IF ORTHOGRAPH\FOUND HM
)@@G@@THEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             IF NEXT\WORD(WORD\INDEXHN
)@@G@@) NE FUNC\HYPHEN THEN   @A@@@@                GOTO MOVE\TO\LINE;  @#@@@@HO
)@@G@@           END;   @E@@@@          ELSE  " MAKE SPACE FOR HYPHEN IF NOT FHP
)@@G@@UNC\HYPHEN  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @E@@@@             WORD\INDEX:=WORD\HQ
)@@G@@INDEX+1;  " PLUS 1 FOR HYPHEN @G@@@@             NEXT\WORD(PTR):=NEXT\WOHR
)@@G@@RD(WORD\INDEX);  " SAVE CHARACTER   @F@@@@             NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(PHS
)@@G@@TR):=NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(WORD\INDEX);   @#@@@@           END;   @H@@@@      HT
)@@G@@    WORD\WIDTH:=WORD\WIDTH+DEVICE\HYPHEN\WIDTH;  " ADD HYPHEN WIDTH     HU
)@@G@@@G@@@@          NEXT\WORD(WORD\INDEX):=DEVICE\HYPHEN\CHAR;  " INSERT HYPHV
)@@G@@HEN   @E@@@@          NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(WORD\INDEX):=DEVICE\HYPHEN\WIDTH; HW
)@@G@@@#@@@@MOVE\TO\LINE:     @ @@@@          INDEX:=WORD\INDEX;  @A@@@@      HX
)@@G@@    MOVE\NEXT\WORD\TO\LINE;   @A@@@@          WORD\INDEX:=BREAK\INDEX;  HY
)@@G@@@B@@@@          WORD\WIDTH:=WORD\WIDTH\LEFT;    @G@@@@          IF NOT OHZ
)@@G@@RTHOGRAPH\FOUND THEN  " RETRIEVE DISPLACED CHARACTER  @#@@@@           BIA
)@@G@@EGIN  @C@@@@             NEXT\WORD(INDEX):=NEXT\WORD(PTR);  @E@@@@      IB
)@@G@@       NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(INDEX):=NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(PTR);  @C@@@@            IC
)@@G@@ INDEX:=INDEX-1;  " RESET INDEX     @#@@@@           END;   @B@@@@      ID
)@@G@@    FOR I:=1 TO WORD\INDEX BY 1 DO  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@      IE
)@@G@@       NEXT\WORD(I):=NEXT\WORD(INDEX+I);  @E@@@@             NEXT\CHAR\WIF
)@@G@@IDTH(I):=NEXT\CHAR\WIDTH(INDEX+I);  @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@      IG
)@@G@@    RETURN; @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     IH
)@@G@@@^@@@@PROCEDURE GET\CHR\TYPE  @[@@@@ BEGIN@B@@@@          IF CHR GE ASCIII
)@@G@@I\LOWER\A AND     @B@@@@             CHR LE ASCII\LOWER\Z THEN    @B@@@@IJ
)@@G@@             IF CHR EQ ASCII\LOWER\A OR   @B@@@@                CHR EQ AIK
)@@G@@SCII\LOWER\E OR   @B@@@@                CHR EQ ASCII\LOWER\I OR   @B@@@@IL
)@@G@@                CHR EQ ASCII\LOWER\O OR   @B@@@@                CHR EQ AIM
)@@G@@SCII\LOWER\U OR   @B@@@@                CHR EQ ASCII\LOWER\Y THEN @A@@@@IN
)@@G@@                TYPE:=S'VOWEL';     @#@@@@             ELSE @A@@@@      IO
)@@G@@          TYPE:=S'CONSONANT'; @#@@@@          ELSE    @ @@@@            IP
)@@G@@ CASEENTRY CHR    @D@@@@                CASE MINUS, FUNC\HYPHEN, FUNC\BRIQ
)@@G@@EAK:  @B@@@@                   TYPE:=S'ORTHOGRAPH';   @E@@@@            IR
)@@G@@    CASE BLANK, FUNC\BLANK, FUNC\SPACEBAND:     @A@@@@                  IS
)@@G@@ TYPE:=S'BLANK';  @F@@@@                CASE QUOTE, DOUBLE\QUOTE, COMMA,IT
)@@G@@ SEMICOLON, COLON,@E@@@@                     PERIOD, QUESTION, EXCLAMATIIU
)@@G@@ON, STAR,   @C@@@@                     CLOSE\PAREN, CLOSE\BRACE:  @B@@@@IV
)@@G@@                   TYPE:=S'PUNCTUATION';  @^@@@@                CASE *: IW
)@@G@@@C@@@@                   TYPE:=S'NOT\ACCEPTABLE';     @^@@@@            IX
)@@G@@ ENDCASE;   @#@@@@          RETURN; @[@@@@ END; @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROIY
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @^@@@@PROCEDURE HYPHENATE     @[@@@@ BEGIN@ @@@@IZ
)@@G@@          PTR:=RIGHT\POINTER; @A@@@@          BREAKPOINT\FOUND:=FALSE;  JA
)@@G@@@E@@@@          IF NOT ORTHOGRAPH\FOUND AND INITIAL\ENTRY THEN    @#@@@@JB
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             IF TABP NE NULL\PTR THEN     @^@@@@JC
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @A@@@@                SYM\LEN:=(PTR+3)//4;@B@@@@JD
)@@G@@                FOR I:=1 TO SYM\LEN DO    @A@@@@                   SYMWRJE
)@@G@@D(I):=0;    @A@@@@                FOR I:=1 TO PTR DO  @C@@@@            JF
)@@G@@       SYMBOL(I):=NEXT\WORD(I);     @D@@@@                NODE:=SEARCH\FJG
)@@G@@OR\NODE(TABP,TYPSTR,    @C@@@@                      SYM\LEN,LOC(SYMWRD(1JH
)@@G@@)));  @E@@@@                IF NODE NE NULL\PTR THEN  " WE'VE GOT WORD  JI
)@@G@@@^@@@@                 BEGIN  @C@@@@                   FOR I:=1 TO DLEN(JJ
)@@G@@NODE) DO    @D@@@@                      VECWRD(I):=CORE(DADR(NODE)+I-1);JK
)@@G@@@B@@@@                   VINDEX:=VECTOR(1);     @^@@@@                 EJL
)@@G@@ND;   @#@@@@              END;@A@@@@             IF VINDEX EQ 0 THEN    JM
)@@G@@@^@@@@              BEGIN     @G@@@@                IF WORD\INDEX LT 6 TJN
)@@G@@HEN  " DON'T HYPHENATE SHORT WORDS  @ @@@@                   RETURN;    JO
)@@G@@@A@@@@                STRIP\SUFFIX:=TRUE; @B@@@@                REENTER\JP
)@@G@@SEARCH:=FALSE;    @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           END;   @ @@@@JQ
)@@G@@          IF VINDEX GT 0 THEN @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@            JR
)@@G@@ IF VINDEX EQ 1 THEN    @^@@@@                RETURN; @A@@@@            JS
)@@G@@ PTR:=VECTOR(VINDEX);   @ @@@@             VINDEX:=VINDEX-1;@ @@@@      JT
)@@G@@       GOTO BREAK\FOUND;@#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          WHILE STJU
)@@G@@RIP\SUFFIX DO     @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@             SEARCH\DERIJV
)@@G@@VATIVE\TABLES;    @A@@@@             IF HYPHEN\EXIT THEN    @^@@@@      JW
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @D@@@@                HYPHEN\EXIT:=FALSE;  " CLEAR EXIJX
)@@G@@T FLAG@A@@@@                GOTO CHECK\LEFT;    @#@@@@              END;JY
)@@G@@@E@@@@             IF INITIAL\ENTRY AND NOT SUFFIX\FOUND THEN     @^@@@@JZ
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @E@@@@                IF NEXT\WORD(PTR) EQ ASCIIKA
)@@G@@\LOWER\S THEN     @^@@@@                 BEGIN  @ @@@@                  KB
)@@G@@ PTR:=PTR-1;@B@@@@                   STRIP\SUFFIX:=TRUE;    @^@@@@      KC
)@@G@@           END;   @#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@KD
)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @^@@@@SEARCH\DIGRAM\TABLE:    @D@@@@          IF NEXT\KE
)@@G@@WORD(PTR) EQ ASCII\LOWER\E THEN     @C@@@@             PTR:=PTR-1;  " STKF
)@@G@@RIP OFF SILENT E  @A@@@@          FOR I:=PTR TO 3 BY -1 DO  @#@@@@      KG
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @A@@@@             CHR:=NEXT\WORD(I);     @ @@@@            KH
)@@G@@ GET\CHR\TYPE;    @B@@@@             IF TYPE EQ S'VOWEL' THEN     @^@@@@KI
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @^@@@@                PTR:=I; @A@@@@            KJ
)@@G@@    GOTO LOOKUP\DIGRAMS;@#@@@@              END;@#@@@@           END;   KK
)@@G@@@#@@@@          RETURN; @#@@@@LOOKUP\DIGRAMS:   @ @@@@          LAST\LOCKL
)@@G@@K\BITS:=0;  @ @@@@          LAST\DG\VALUE:=0;   @A@@@@          FOR I:=PKM
)@@G@@TR TO 2 BY -1 DO  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @^@@@@             DG\PTR:=I; KN
)@@G@@@A@@@@             LOOKUP\DIGRAM\VALUE;   @A@@@@             IF DG\VALUEKO
)@@G@@ NE 0 THEN  @^@@@@              BEGIN     @A@@@@                PTR:=I-2KP
)@@G@@+DG\VALUE;  @A@@@@                GOTO CHECK\LEFT;    @#@@@@            KQ
)@@G@@  END;@#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@          RETURN; @]@@@@CHECK\LEFT: KR
)@@G@@@^@@@@          VOWELS:=0;    @^@@@@          CONSONANTS:=0;@A@@@@      KS
)@@G@@    FOR I:=PTR TO 1 BY -1 DO  @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@            KT
)@@G@@ CHR:=NEXT\WORD(I);     @ @@@@             GET\CHR\TYPE;    @B@@@@      KU
)@@G@@       IF TYPE EQ S'VOWEL' THEN     @A@@@@                VOWELS:=VOWELSKV
)@@G@@+1;   @B@@@@             IF TYPE EQ S'CONSONANT' THEN @B@@@@            KW
)@@G@@    CONSONANTS:=CONSONANTS+1; @A@@@@             IF VOWELS GE 1 AND     KX
)@@G@@@A@@@@                CONSONANTS GE 1 THEN@A@@@@                GOTO BREKY
)@@G@@AK\FOUND;   @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@          RETURN; @]@@@@BREAK\KZ
)@@G@@FOUND:@ @@@@          BREAK\INDEX:=PTR;   @A@@@@          BREAKPOINT\FOULA
)@@G@@ND:=TRUE;   @#@@@@          RETURN; @[@@@@ END; @[@@@@"     @#@@@@CONTROLB
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @A@@@@PROCEDURE SEARCH\DERIVATIVE\TABLES  @[@@@@LC
)@@G@@ BEGIN@ @@@@          STRIP\SUFFIX:=FALSE;@ @@@@          SUFFIX\FOUND:=LD
)@@G@@FALSE;@E@@@@          BREAK\INDEX:=PTR;  " SAVE POINTER FOR RESTORE     LE
)@@G@@@A@@@@          IF REENTER\SEARCH THEN    @B@@@@             GOTO CONCATLF
)@@G@@ENATE\STRING;     @ @@@@          IF PTR LE 3 THEN    @^@@@@            LG
)@@G@@ RETURN;    @B@@@@          INDEX:=NEXT\WORD(PTR-1)-O'140'; @C@@@@      LH
)@@G@@    USE\TBL\PTR:=KEY\DERIVATIVE(INDEX);   @^@@@@CONCATENATE\STRING:     LI
)@@G@@@^@@@@          STRING:=0;    @^@@@@          INDEX:=PTR-5; @ @@@@      LJ
)@@G@@    IF INDEX LE 0 THEN  @^@@@@             INDEX:=1;  @B@@@@          FOLK
)@@G@@R I:=INDEX TO PTR BY 1 DO     @E@@@@             STRING:=STRING*2**6+(NELL
)@@G@@XT\WORD(I)-O'133');     @A@@@@          LNG\STRING:=PTR-INDEX+1;  @#@@@@LM
)@@G@@MATCH\ENTRIES:    @#@@@@          MATCH;  @A@@@@          IF FORWARD\LINLN
)@@G@@K EQ 0 THEN @^@@@@             RETURN;    @]@@@@NEXT\LEVEL: @A@@@@      LO
)@@G@@    CASEENTRY SHIFT\ACTION    @ @@@@             CASE RESTORE:    @^@@@@LP
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @H@@@@                STRIP\SUFFIX:=FALSE;  " OVLQ
)@@G@@ERRIDE TABLE TO PREVENT LOOPING     @A@@@@                PTR:=BREAK\INDLR
)@@G@@EX;   @^@@@@                RETURN; @#@@@@              END;@ @@@@      LS
)@@G@@       CASE SHIFT\LEFT: @B@@@@                PTR:=PTR-SHIFT\COUNT;     LT
)@@G@@@ @@@@             CASE SHIFT\RIGHT:@B@@@@                PTR:=PTR+SHIFTLU
)@@G@@\COUNT;     @#@@@@          ENDCASE;@ @@@@          IF HYPHEN\EXIT THEN LV
)@@G@@@#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             IF REENTER\SEARCH THEN @D@@@@LW
)@@G@@                STRIP\SUFFIX:=TRUE;  " OVERRIDE TABLE @^@@@@            LX
)@@G@@ RETURN;    @#@@@@           END;   @A@@@@          IF SHIFT\COUNT EQ 0 LY
)@@G@@THEN  @A@@@@             GOTO MATCH\ENTRIES;    @#@@@@          ELSE    LZ
)@@G@@@B@@@@             GOTO CONCATENATE\STRING;     @[@@@@ END; @[@@@@"     MA
)@@G@@@#@@@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@@"     @#@@@@PROCEDURE MATCH   @[@@@@ BEGINMB
)@@G@@@#@@@@MATCH\STRING:     @ @@@@          FORWARD\LINK:=0;    @B@@@@      MC
)@@G@@    IF USE\TBL\PTR EQ NULL\PTR THEN @^@@@@             RETURN;    @A@@@@MD
)@@G@@          TABLE\PTR:=USE\TBL\PTR;   @ @@@@          CASEENTRY ENTRY\LNG ME
)@@G@@@^@@@@             CASE 6:    @A@@@@                TEST\STRING:=STRING;MF
)@@G@@@^@@@@             CASE 5:    @C@@@@                TEST\STRING:=STRING(MG
)@@G@@7 TO 36);   @^@@@@             CASE 4:    @C@@@@                TEST\STRMH
)@@G@@ING:=STRING(13 TO 36);  @^@@@@             CASE 3:    @C@@@@            MI
)@@G@@    TEST\STRING:=STRING(19 TO 36);  @^@@@@             CASE 2:    @C@@@@MJ
)@@G@@                TEST\STRING:=STRING(25 TO 36);  @^@@@@             CASE MK
)@@G@@1:    @C@@@@                TEST\STRING:=STRING(31 TO 36);  @C@@@@      ML
)@@G@@       CASE 0:  " FORCE FIND ON NULL ENTRY@A@@@@                GOTO STRMM
)@@G@@ING\FOUND;  @#@@@@          ENDCASE;@B@@@@          FOR I:=1 TO NUM\ENTRMN
)@@G@@IES BY 1 DO @#@@@@           BEGIN  @A@@@@             CASEENTRY ENTRY\LMO
)@@G@@NG    @ @@@@                CASE 4, 5, 6: @B@@@@                   ENTRYMP
)@@G@@:=FULL\WRD(I);    @ @@@@                CASE 2, 3:    @B@@@@            MQ
)@@G@@       ENTRY:=HALF\WRD(I);    @^@@@@                CASE 1: @B@@@@      MR
)@@G@@             ENTRY:=SIXTH\WRD(I);   @^@@@@             ENDCASE;   @B@@@@MS
)@@G@@             IF TEST\STRING LT ENTRY THEN @B@@@@                GOTO STRMT
)@@G@@ING\NOT\FOUND;    @B@@@@             IF TEST\STRING EQ ENTRY THEN @A@@@@MU
)@@G@@                GOTO STRING\FOUND;  @#@@@@           END;   @#@@@@STRINGMV
)@@G@@\NOT\FOUND: @A@@@@          FORWARD\LINK:=NOT\FND\LNK;@A@@@@          USMW
)@@G@@E\TBL\PTR:=NOT\FND\PTR; @#@@@@          RETURN; @#@@@@STRING\FOUND:     MX
)@@G@@@ @@@@          SUFFIX\FOUND:=TRUE; @A@@@@          STRIP\SUFFIX:=SUFFIXMY
)@@G@@\FLG; @A@@@@          FORWARD\LINK:=FOUND\LNK;  @A@@@@          USE\TBL\MZ
)@@G@@PTR:=FND\TBL\PTR; @#@@@@          RETURN; @[@@@@ END; @[@@@@"     @#@@@@NA
)@@G@@CONTROL (EJECT);  @[@@@@"     @ @@@@PROCEDURE LOOKUP\DIGRAM\VALUE @[@@@@NB
)@@G@@ BEGIN@C@@@@          INDEX:=NEXT\WORD(DG\PTR-1)-O'141';    @D@@@@      NC
)@@G@@    INDEX:=INDEX*26+(NEXT\WORD(DG\PTR)-O'140'); @A@@@@          DG\VALUEND
)@@G@@:=DIGRAM(INDEX);  @F@@@@          LAST\LOCK\BITS:=LAST\LOCK\BITS LAND LONE
)@@G@@CK\BITS(INDEX);   @B@@@@          IF LAST\LOCK\BITS EQ 0 THEN     @#@@@@NF
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @C@@@@             LAST\LOCK\BITS:=LOCK\BITS(INDEX);  NG
)@@G@@@B@@@@             IF LAST\DG\VALUE NE 0 THEN   @D@@@@                DGNH
)@@G@@\VALUE:=2;  " TAKE LAST BREAKPOINT  @#@@@@             ELSE @C@@@@      NI
)@@G@@          IF LAST\LOCK\BITS NE 0 THEN     @^@@@@                 BEGIN  NJ
)@@G@@@C@@@@                   LAST\DG\VALUE:=DG\VALUE;     @A@@@@            NK
)@@G@@       DG\VALUE:=0;     @^@@@@                 END;   @#@@@@           ENL
)@@G@@ND;   @#@@@@          ELSE    @#@@@@           BEGIN  @B@@@@            NM
)@@G@@ DG\VALUE:=LAST\LOCK\BITS//2; @C@@@@             LAST\LOCK\BITS:=0;  " CNN
)@@G@@LEAR LOCK   @ @@@@             LAST\DG\VALUE:=0;@#@@@@           END;   NO
)@@G@@@#@@@@          RETURN; @[@@@@ END; @[@@@@"     @[@@@@TERM; ___@@@1 BY -NP
)@@G@@)@@[M@K)@K)[@@@@@@A]L@@ A[[@@^A@1@@#C;0@@B/\)@@@/K@@@@N[[@@AR]L@@ R[[@@^NQ
)@@G@@R@1@@#AA@@@@)@E[EK)]^[[KO ]@H[@@@@@@[[K@@BC[K@M1 @@@@M @@@@- @@@@)/-K@@@NR
