)@@G@@    L,U       R1,9              . LOOP 10 TIMES MAX   @D@@@@RID       CSUD
)@@G@@F       FREE              . FREE OLD FILES@D@@@@          TOP       A0,(UE
)@@G@@1*/33)        . ALREADY FREE? @D@@@@          JGD       R1,RID          UF
)@@G@@  . NO, LOOP MORE @F@@@@          CSF       CAT               . CATALOG UG
)@@G@@A NEW OUTPUT FILE @E@@@@          CSF       ASG               . ASSIGN TUH
)@@G@@HE FILE     @F@@@@          CSF       USE               . PUT USE NAME OUI
)@@G@@N THE FILE  @D@@@@          SUBRETURN                   . AND RETURN    UJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. SYM THE OUTPUT PRINT FILE   @[@@@@.     UK
)@@G@@@B@@@@SYMOUTF*  INSTRS                      .   @F@@@@          SUBEGIN,UL
)@@G@@3 SAVE              . 2 ARGS AND 1 SAVE LOCATION@D@@@@          DL      UM
)@@G@@  A0,OPKT           . GET FILENAME  @E@@@@          DS        A0,FIPKT  UN
)@@G@@        . STORE IN PACKET     @E@@@@          L         A0,(9,FIPKT)    UO
)@@G@@  . PREP FOR FITEM$     @F@@@@          ER        FITEM$            . GEUP
)@@G@@T QUAL, NAME AND F-CYCLE@D@@@@          L         A0,FIOPTS         . GEUQ
)@@G@@T FILE OPTS @G@@@@          LSSL      A0,1              . PUT TEMP FILE UR
)@@G@@FLAG IN UPPER A0  @I@@@@          JN        A0,SYM200         . IF TEMP US
)@@G@@FILE CANNOT SYM AND CANNOT FREE     @G@@@@          SSL       A0,1+'Z'-'UT
)@@G@@K'      . PUT KOPTION BIT IN LOW ORDER BIT@F@@@@          JB        A0,SUU
)@@G@@YM300         . JUMP IF K-OPTION FILE     @G@@@@          E$DIT     EDPKUV
)@@G@@T             . OPEN EDITING TO CREATE SYM IMAGE@D@@@@          E$MSG   UW
)@@G@@  SYMIM             . INSERT '@SYM' @E@@@@          TZ        SYMDEL    UX
)@@G@@        . IF ZERO ADD ',U'    @E@@@@          J         SYM010          UY
)@@G@@  . SKIP IF NON-ZERO    @H@@@@          E$FD1     (',U')            . ADUZ
)@@G@@D ',U' SO THAT IT ISN'T DELETED     @D@@@@SYM010    E$MSGR              VA
)@@G@@        . INSERT ' '    @E@@@@          E$FD2     FIQUAL            . PUVB
)@@G@@T IN QUALIFIER    @D@@@@          E$MSGR                      . PUT IN 'VC
)@@G@@*'    @E@@@@          E$FD2     FINAME            . PUT IN FILE NAME    VD
)@@G@@@D@@@@          E$MSGR                      . PUT IN '('    @F@@@@      VE
)@@G@@    L         A0,FICYCLE        . GET ABSOLUTE F-CYCLE #    @E@@@@      VF
)@@G@@    AND,U     A0,FICYMASK       . CLEAR OUT WRONG BITS@E@@@@          S VG
)@@G@@        A1,SYMSAVE        . SAVE SOMEPLACE GOOD @D@@@@          E$DECV  VH
)@@G@@  SYMSAVE           . PUT IN F-CYCLE@E@@@@          E$MSGR              VI
)@@G@@        . CONTINUE MSG ('),') @F@@@@          E$DECV    NROFCOPIES      VJ
)@@G@@  . PUT IN NR OF COPIES TO SYM@E@@@@          E$MSGR                    VK
)@@G@@  . CONTINUE WITH ','   @E@@@@          L         A0,(DEFPR)        . GEVL
)@@G@@T DEFAULT PRINTER @E@@@@          TNZ       SYMSITE           . IS SITE VM
)@@G@@GIVEN ZERO? @G@@@@          S         A0,SYMSITE        . YES, PUT IN DEVN
)@@G@@FAULT PRINTER     @F@@@@          E$FD1     SYMSITE           . PUT IN SVO
)@@G@@ITE ID TO SYM TO  @D@@@@          E$MSGR                      . FINISH UVP
)@@G@@P MSG @D@@@@          E$DITX                      . END OF EDITING@[@@@@VQ
)@@G@@.     @#@@@@. NOW SYM THE FILE@[@@@@.     @H@@@@          CSF       FREEVR
)@@G@@R             . FREE,R THE FILE FIRST TO UPDATE MFD   @F@@@@          L,VS
)@@G@@U       A0,LINE           . GET RESULT OF EDITING     @C@@@@          ERVT
)@@G@@        CSF$              . @SYM IT @D@@@@          JNZ       A0,SYM100 VU
)@@G@@        . ANY ERRORS?   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@. NO ERRORS PRINT A MSG AND EXVV
)@@G@@IT WITH A ZERO IN A0    @ @@@@. AFTER FREE,A'ING THE FILE   @[@@@@.     VW
)@@G@@@E@@@@          DL        A0,OPKT           . GET BACK USE NAME   @F@@@@VX
)@@G@@          DS        A0,FREEANAME      . PUT IN PLACE FOR NAME     @C@@@@VY
)@@G@@          CSF       FREEA             . FREE IT @D@@@@          L       VZ
)@@G@@  A0,RUNID          . GET RUNID     @F@@@@          S         A0,RIDH2  WA
)@@G@@        . STORE AWAY H2 OF RUNID    @E@@@@          SSL       A0,18     WB
)@@G@@        . GET H1 OF RUNID     @E@@@@          S         A0,RIDH1        WC
)@@G@@  . PUT AWAY H1 OF RUNID@E@@@@          L         A0,SYMSITE        . GEWD
)@@G@@T SITE FOR MSG    @E@@@@          S         A0,SID            . PUT AWAYWE
)@@G@@ FOR MSG    @D@@@@          L         A0,SYMOK          . GET PCW OF MSGWF
)@@G@@@D@@@@          ER        PRINT$            . PRINT OK MSG  @F@@@@      WG
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,0              . ZERO A0 BEFORE RETURN     @E@@@@      WH
)@@G@@    J         SYM999            . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@WI
)@@G@@. AT THIS POINT WE HAVE A SYM ERROR OF SOME KIND, REASSIGN THE FILE     WJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@. AND CHECK TO SEE IF ERROR IS A BAD SITE.  IF SO PRINT OUR MSG   WK
)@@G@@@E@@@@. AND RETURN.  IF NOT, LET SOMEONE ELSE PRINT AN ERROR MSG  @[@@@@WL
)@@G@@.     @]@@@@SYM100.     @D@@@@          S         A0,SYMSAVE        . SAWM
)@@G@@VE A0 FIRST @H@@@@          L,U       A0,ASG            . GET @ASG IMAGEWN
)@@G@@ FOR ER CSF$ (DON'T USE @H@@@@          ER        CSF$              . PRWO
)@@G@@OC CSF AS C$SF CHECKS FOR BITS)     @E@@@@          L         A0,SYMSAVEWP
)@@G@@        . GET BACK ERROR CODE @E@@@@          TE,U      A0,BADSITE      WQ
)@@G@@  . IS IT BAD SITE?     @E@@@@          J         SYM400            . NOWR
)@@G@@, OTHER ERROR     @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. BAD SITE TO SYM TO, PRINT BAD SITEWS
)@@G@@ MSG AND RETURN WITH A0=BADSITE     @[@@@@.     @D@@@@          L       WT
)@@G@@  A0,SYMSITE        . GET SITE AGAIN@D@@@@          S         A0,SYMMSG WU
)@@G@@        . STORE IN MSG  @D@@@@          L         A0,SYMPCW         . GEWV
)@@G@@T ERROR PCW @D@@@@          ER        PRINT$            . PRINT MSG     WW
)@@G@@@F@@@@          L,U       A0,BADSITE        . GET BACK BAD SITE CODE    WX
)@@G@@@E@@@@          J         SYM999            . RETURN TO CALLER    @[@@@@WY
)@@G@@.     @D@@@@. FITEM$ SHOWED FILE IS TEMP FILE. CANNOT SYM OR FREE @C@@@@WZ
)@@G@@. SET A0 TO CANNOT SYM TEMP FILE CODE AND RETURN@[@@@@.     @]@@@@SYM200XA
)@@G@@.     @E@@@@          P$RINT    SYMPCW1           . PRINT ERROR MSG     XB
)@@G@@@G@@@@          L,U       A0,TEMPFILE       . GET CODE FOR TEMP FILE ERRXC
)@@G@@OR    @E@@@@          J         SYM999            . RETURN TO CALLER    XD
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. K-OPTION FILE. SET APPROPRIATE ERROR AND RETURN     XE
)@@G@@@ @@@@. CANNOT FREE THIS FILE EITHER@[@@@@.     @]@@@@SYM300.     @E@@@@XF
)@@G@@          P$RINT    SYMPCW2           . PRINT ERROR MSG     @D@@@@      XG
)@@G@@    L,U       A0,KOPTION        . GET ERROR CODE@D@@@@          J       XH
)@@G@@  SYM999            . AND RETURN    @[@@@@.     @]@@@@SYM400.     @E@@@@XI
)@@G@@          S         A0,A1             . SAVE SOMEPLACE NICE @E@@@@      XJ
)@@G@@    P$RINT    SYMPCW2           . PRINT ERROR MSG     @E@@@@          L XK
)@@G@@        A0,A1             . RESTORE ERROR CODE  @C@@@@          J       XL
)@@G@@  SYM999            . GO HOME @[@@@@.     @C@@@@SYM999    SUBRETURN RESTXM
)@@G@@ORE           . RETURN  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          DATA                XN
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@SYMMSG1   'CANNOT PRINT TEMPORARY FILE' . XO
)@@G@@@D@@@@SYMPCW1   +         0100+SYMPCW1-SYMMSG1,SYMMSG1 .    @G@@@@SYMMSGXP
)@@G@@2   'FILE IS NOT CATALOGUED OR CANNOT BE FOUND IN DIRECTORY' .    @D@@@@XQ
)@@G@@SYMPCW2   +         0100+SYMPCW2-SYMMSG2,SYMMSG2 .    @[@@@@/.    @ @@@@XR
)@@G@@. DELETE THE OUTPUT PRINT FILE@[@@@@.     @B@@@@DELETEOUTF* INSTRS      XS
)@@G@@              .   @B@@@@          SUBEGIN   SAVE              .   @D@@@@XT
)@@G@@          CSF       DELETE            . DELETE FILE   @B@@@@DEL999    SUXU
)@@G@@BRETURN RESTORE           .   @[@@@@/.    @D@@@@. THIS SUBROUTINE PUTS TXV
)@@G@@HE IMAGE INTO THE OUTPUT FILE @A@@@@.   IT CREATES AN EXEC8 PRINT FILE  XW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @D@@@@.     PUTIMG(LOC(IMAGE) , #CHARS, #OF-LINES-TO-SKIP)  XX
)@@G@@@[[@@@.     @B@@@@PUTIMG*   INSTRS                      .   @D@@@@      XY
)@@G@@    SUBEGIN,3 SAVE              . SAVE REGISTERS@C@@@@          L       XZ
)@@G@@  A0,SKPCNT         . GET SKIP@D@@@@          TP        A0              YA
)@@G@@  . IF NEGATIVE   @C@@@@          SZ        SKPCNT            . CLEAR ITYB
)@@G@@@E@@@@          TNZ       FUNNYMODE         . FUNNY MODE OUTPUT?  @C]@@@YC
)@@G@@          J         PUTIMG20          . NO, SKIP@E@@@@          L       YD
)@@G@@  A0,SKPCNT         . GET LINES TO SKIP   @C@@@@          LMJ       X11,YE
)@@G@@GETLFPCW      . GET SKIP@F@@@@          SZ        SKPCNT            . CLYF
)@@G@@EAR REMAINING SKIP COUNT@E@@@@          JZ        A0,PUTIMG20       . SKYG
)@@G@@IP IF NOTHING     @C@@@@          LMJ       X11,PUTOUTPUT     . PUT IT  YH
)@@G@@@]@@@@PUTIMG20.   @D@@@@          L         A1,LEN            . GET LENGYI
)@@G@@TH    @C@@@@          A,U       A1,3              . ROUND UP@E@@@@      YJ
)@@G@@    SSL       A1,2              . DIVIDE BY 4 = WORDS @F@@@@          L YK
)@@G@@        A0,SKPCNT         . GET CURRENT SKIP COUNT    @D[@@@          TPYL
)@@G@@        A0                . IF NEGATIVE   @C@@@@          L,U       A0,0YM
)@@G@@              . USE ZERO@D@@@@          LSSL      A0,6              . POYN
)@@G@@SITION IT   @E@@@@          A,U       A0,,A1            . ADD WORD COUNTYO
)@@G@@ IN A1@D@@@@          LSSL      A0,18             . SHIFT INTO H1 @E@@@@YP
)@@G@@          LXM       A0,IMADD          . GET IMAGE ADDRESS   @D@@@@      YQ
)@@G@@    L         A1,RUNOPTS        . GET OPTIONS   @E@@@@          TEP     YR
)@@G@@  A1,(1*/('Z'-'O')) . O FOR OUTPUT LIST   @E@@@@          ER        APRIYS
)@@G@@NT$           . YES, PRINT IT FIRST @C@@@@          LMJ       X11,PUTOUTYT
)@@G@@PUT     . PUT IT  @B[@@@          SUBRETURN RESTORE           .   @[@@@@YU
)@@G@@/.    @[@@@@.     @^@@@@. PUT THE NEXT IMAGE OUT@[@@@@.     @B@@@@PUTOUTYV
)@@G@@PUT INSTRS                      .   @B@@@@          S         X11,PUTLNKYW
)@@G@@        .   @G@@@@          JZ        A0,PUT999         . RETURN IF NOTHYX
)@@G@@ING TO OUTPUT     @D@@@@          S         A0,TEMP1          . SAVE ARGYY
)@@G@@UMENTS@D@@@@          L         A5,A0             . GET ARGUMENTS @F@@@@YZ
)@@G@@          LDSL      A4,12             . CHANGE PCW TO FILE CW     @B@@@@ZA
)@@G@@          LSSL      A4,24             .   @B@@@@          SSL       A5,3ZB
)@@G@@0             .   @B@@@@          DSC       A4,12             .   @B@@@@ZC
)@@G@@          JZ        A4,PUT999         .   @D@@@@          A,U       A4,1ZD
)@@G@@              . ADD ASCII BIT @E@@@@          S         A4,OCW          ZE
)@@G@@  . SET CONTROL WORD    @E@@@@          TZ        FUNNYMODE         . FUZF
)@@G@@NNY MODE OUTPUT?  @G@@@@          J         PUT100            . YES, SKIZG
)@@G@@P MUTULATION ROUTINE    @E@@@@          TZ        BACKSPACE         . ANZH
)@@G@@Y BACKSPACES?     @F@@@@          TNZ       MUTILATE          . CAN WE MZI
)@@G@@UTILATE THE LINE  @E@@@@          J         PUT100            . NO, SKIPZJ
)@@G@@ MUTILATION @E@@@@          L,H2      A0,TEMP1          . GET IMAGE ADDRZK
)@@G@@ESS   @E@@@@          A,S2      A0,OCW            . ADD IMAGE LENGTH    ZL
)@@G@@@D@@@@          LN,U      A1,1              . GET TERM FLAG @C@@@@      ZM
)@@G@@    S         A1,,A0            . SET IT  @E@@@@PUT020    L,H2      A0,TZN
)@@G@@EMP1          . GET IMAGE ADDRESS   @E@@@@          L,S2      A1,OCW    ZO
)@@G@@        . GET IMAGE LENGTH    @E@@@@          L,U       A2,OUTIMAG      ZP
)@@G@@  . OUTPUT IMAGE ADDRESS@G@@@@          L,U       A3,,A0            . REZQ
)@@G@@MAINDER GOES TO INPUT IMAGE   @F@@@@          L,U       A4,0777         ZR
)@@G@@  . GET END OF LINE CHARACTER @D@@@@          LMJ       X11,MULINE      ZS
)@@G@@  . MUTILATE LINE @F@@@@          S,S2      A0,OCW            . SET OUTPZT
)@@G@@UT IMAGE LENGTH   @D@@@@          S         A1,TEMP2          . SAVE REMZU
)@@G@@AINDER@F@@@@          L,U       A0,OUTIMAG        . GET OUTPUT IMAGE ADDZV
)@@G@@RESS  @E@@@@          S         A0,IMAGADDR       . SET IN I/O PACKET   ZW
)@@G@@@D@@@@          L,U       A0,OPKT           . OUTPUT ADDRESS@E@@@@      ZX
)@@G@@    S         A0,PSDFO$$        . SET IN PLUS DBANK   @C@@@@          LMZY
)@@G@@J       X11,PSDFO         . OUTPUT  @E@@@@          L         A0,TEMP2  ZZ
)@@G@@        . GET REMAINDER LENGTH@E@@@@          SZ,S3     OCW             AA
)@@G@@  . ZERO SKIP COUND     @F@@@@          SZ,S4     OCW               . SKAB
)@@G@@IP COUNT IS S3 AND S4   @D@@@@          S,S2      A0,OCW            . SEAC
)@@G@@T AS LENGTH @F@@@@          JNZ       A0,PUT020         . LOOP IF ANY MOAD
)@@G@@RE IMAGE    @C@@@@          J         PUT999            . RETURN  @[@@@@AE
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@. NO BACKSPACES SO SIMPLY OUTPUT THE LINE @[@@@@.     @]@@@@AF
)@@G@@PUT100.     @E@@@@          L,H2      A0,TEMP1          . GET IMAGE ADDRAG
)@@G@@ESS   @E@@@@          S         A0,IMAGADDR       . SET IN I/O PACKET   AH
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L,U       A0,OPKT           . GET PACKET ADDRESS  @F@@@@AI
)@@G@@          S         A0,PSDFO$$        . PUT IN ARGUMENT TO CALL   @D@@@@AJ
)@@G@@          LMJ       X11,PSDFO         . WRITE IT OUT  @]@@@@PUT999    . AK
)@@G@@@E@@@@          L         X11,PUTLNK        . GET RETURN ADDRESS  @C@@@@AL
)@@G@@          J         0,X11             . RETURN  @[@@@@.     @B@@@@      AM
)@@G@@    DATA                        .   @B@@@@TEMP1     +         0         AN
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@TEMP2     +         0                 .   @B@@@@PUTLNKAO
)@@G@@    RES       1                 .   @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. THISAP
)@@G@@ SUBROUTINE SUBMITS THE PLUS IMAGE TO BE A PRINT CONTROL    @[@@@@.     AQ
)@@G@@@B@[@@PUTPCN*   INSTRS                      .   @B@@@[WRTPCN*   INSTRS  AR
)@@G@@                    .   @D@@@@          SUBEGIN,3 SAVE              . SAAS
)@@G@@VE REGISTERS@D[@@@          L         A1,LEN            . GET LENGTH    AT
)@@G@@@C@@@@          A,U       A1,3              . ROUND UP@E@@@@          SSAU
)@@G@@L       A1,2              . DIVIDE BY 4 = WORDS @F@@@@          S,S2    AV
)@@G@@  A1,CW060          . STORE IN CONTROL WORD     @E@@@@          L       AW
)@@G@@  A0,IMADD          . GET IMAGE ADDRESS   @E@@@@          S         A0,IAX
)@@G@@MAGADDR       . SAVE ADDRESS PART   @E@@@@          L         A4,CW060  AY
)@@G@@        . GET CONTROL WORD    @F@@@@          S         A4,OCW          AZ
)@@G@@  . SET OUTPUT CONTROL WORD   @E@@@@          L,U       A0,OPKT         BA
)@@G@@  . GET PACKET ADDRESS  @C@@@@          S         A0,PSDFO$$        . SEBB
)@@G@@T IT  @C@@@@          LMJ       X11,PSDFO         . OUPUT IT@]@@@@PCN999BC
)@@G@@    . @C@@@@          SUBRETURN RESTORE           . RETURN  @[@@@@.     BD
)@@G@@@B@@@@          DATA                        .   @E@@@@CW060     +       BE
)@@G@@  060,0,0,0,0,1     . APRTCN$ CONTROL WORD@[@@@@.     @D@@@@. THIS ROUTIBF
)@@G@@NE DOES A SKIP TO THE TOP OF THE NEXT PAGE@[@@@@.     @D@@@@PAGUPF*   INBG
)@@G@@STRS                      . PAGEUP FILE   @D@@@@          SUBEGIN,3 SAVEBH
)@@G@@              . SAVE REGISTERS@F[@@@          L,U       A0,OPKT         BI
)@@G@@  . OUTPUT PACKET ADDRESS     @C@@@@          S         A0,PSDFO$$      BJ
)@@G@@  . SET IT  @G@@@@          S         A0,IMAGADDR       . SET DUMMY OUTPBK
)@@G@@UT IMAGE ADDRESS  @F@@@@          L         A1,(000077770001) . GET STANBL
)@@G@@DARD FORM FEED    @C@@@@          S         A1,OCW            . SET IT  BM
)@@G@@@C@@@@          LMJ       X11,PSDFO         . OUTPUT  @C@@@@          LNBN
)@@G@@,U      A0,1              . GET -1  @H@@@@          S         A0,SKIP   BO
)@@G@@        . SET TO INHIBIT SKIP ON FIRST PRINT    @]@@@@UPF999    . @B@@@@BP
)@@G@@          SUBRETURN RESTORE           .   @[@@@@.     @B@@@@          DABQ
)@@G@@TA                        .   @D@@@@SKIP*     +         0               BR
)@@G@@  . SKIP COUNT    @B@@@@          END                         .   ___@@@BS
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          S         X11,PUTLNK        .   @G@@@@      BT
)@@G@@    JZ        A0,PUT999         . RETURN IF NOTH)[@[O@/V]@K##ECOK@@@[@@@BU

)@@G@@HARS\PER\INCH; " SET IT @[@@@@"     @^@@@@" SET STANDARD MARGINS  @[@@@@XH
)@@G@@"     @B@@@@          TOP\MARGIN := INCH\DISTANCE;    @B@@@@          BOXI
)@@G@@TTOM\MARGIN := INCH\DISTANCE; @C@@@@          PAGE\HEIGHT := INCH\DISTANXJ
)@@G@@CE * 11;    @C@@@@          PAGE\WIDTH := INCH\DISTANCE * 8.5;    @B@@@@XK
)@@G@@          LEFT\MARGIN := INCH\DISTANCE;   @B@@@@          RIGHT\MARGIN :XL
)@@G@@= INCH\DISTANCE;  @A@@@@          SET\ALL\AREA\LINE\WIDTHS; @F@@@@      XM
)@@G@@    NEW\CHAR\HEIGHT := 8; " SET 8 LINES PER INCH STANDARD   @B@@@@      XN

)@@G@@DISTANCE * 2.4; " OFFSET 2.4 INCHES @E@@@@          DEVICE\BACKSPACES :=XP
)@@G@@ FALSE; " WE CAN'T BACKSPACE  @F@@@@          DEVICE\LETTER\SPACES := FAXQ
)@@G@@LSE; " CANNOT LETTERSPACE     @D@@@@          DEVICE\JUSTIFIES := FALSE;XR
)@@G@@ " WE MUST DO IT  @F@@@@          DEVICE\HYPHEN\CHAR := MINUS; " STANDARXS
)@@G@@D HYPHEN CHAR     @E@@@@          MUTILATE := TRUE; " FORMAT OVERSTRIKESXT
)@@G@@ FOR PRINTER@[@@@@END;  @[@@@@      @C@@@@PROCEDURE PAGEUP\PR770 EXPORTEXU
)@@G@@D ('PR770TOPFRM') @[@@@@BEGIN @C@@@@          IF OUTPUT\MEDIA EQ MEDIA\HXV

)@@G@@" DO ACTUAL LINE FEEDS FOR THE PR770@[@@@@"     @D@@@@PROCEDURE LINE\FEEYA

)@@G@@SKIP + LEADING\FOR\DEVICE // SKIP\DISTANCE;     @[@@@@END;  @[@@@@"     YC

)@@G@@"     @A@@@@" PROCESS FONT CHANGE FOR THE 770   @[@@@@"     @ @@@@"   .FYX
)@@G@@ONT <BAND-ID>  IN HEX   @[@@@@"     @E@@@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\PR770\FONT\CYY
)@@G@@HECK EXPORTED ('PR770INFONT');@[@@@@BEGIN @D@@@@          SCAN(EVAL+CTRMYZ
)@@G@@+ALLOW\STR); " PICK UP NAME   @B@@@@          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 ZA
)@@G@@AND   @A@@@@             DLEN(SCANNED) EQ 2 THEN@#@@@@           BEGIN  ZB

)@@G@@ OUTPUT\PCN(LOC(BAND\CHANGE),BAND\LENGTH);@#@@@@           END;   @^@@@@ZE

)@@G@@M THE TEXT SETTING COMPLEX    @D@@@[" WHEN A DIRECTIVE IS ENCOUNTERED.  GF
)@@G@@IT FIRST SEARCHES @E@@@[" THE DEFINED MACROS, THEN THE DPS DIRECTIVES, TGG
)@@G@@HEN FINALLY @E@@@[" CALLS SEARCH\FOR\UNDEFINED MACROS TO SEARCH ALL DEFIGH
)@@G@@NED   @C@@@[" LIBRARY FILES FOR THE DIRECTIVE IN QUESTION.  @[@@@["     GI
)@@G@@@C@@@[PROCEDURE PROCESS\DIRECTIVE EXPORTED ('PRODIR') @[@@@[BEGIN @F@@@[GJ
)@@G@@          ERROR\STATUS\CODE := 0;     " CLEAR ANY PREVIOUS ERRORS @E@@@[GK
)@@G@@          FLUSH\DIRECTIVE\IMAGE := TRUE; " SET FOR FLUSH    @[@@@["     GL
)@@G@@@E@@@[          IF CHARACTER EQ PERIOD AND CARD\INDEX EQ 2 THEN   @B@@@[GM
)@@G@@             EMBEDDED\DIRECTIVE := FALSE; @B@@@[          ELSE " SINGLE GN
)@@G@@LINE DIRECTIVE    @B@@@[             EMBEDDED\DIRECTIVE := TRUE;  @F@@@[GO
)@@G@@          SCAN(CTRM+CNAM+ALLOW\NAM);  " ALLOW ONLY NAME/LABEL     @E@@@[GP
)@@G@@          IF (EMBEDDED\DIRECTIVE OR CSDTYP NE TYPNUL) AND   @H@@@[      GQ
)@@G@@       ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN    " NOT COMMENT AND LEGAL SYNTAX    GR
)@@G@@@D@@@[           BEGIN                      " IS NOT COMMENT@G@@@[      GS
)@@G@@       SEARCH\FOR\DEFINED\MACRO; " CHECK TO SEE IF MACRO CALL     @A@@@[GT
)@@G@@             IF NOT MACRO\FOUND THEN@E@@@[              BEGIN           GU
)@@G@@        " TO SEARCH DIRECTIVES@D@@@[                DIRECTIVE\INDEX := KGV
)@@G@@EYWORD\SEARCH     @F@@@[                   ( LOC(DIRECTIVE\NAMES) , MAXDGW
)@@G@@IR , ENABLE\AB ); @F@@@[                IF DIRECTIVE\INDEX LE MAXDIR THEGX
)@@G@@N " DPS DIRECTIVE @E@@@[                   PROCESS\DPS\DIRECTIVE(DIRECTIGY
)@@G@@VE\INDEX);  @^@@@[                ELSE    @G@@@[                 BEGIN  GZ
)@@G@@              " TO SEARCH FOR UNDEFINED MACRO   @C@@@[                  HA
)@@G@@ SEARCH\FOR\UNDEFINED\MACRO;  @B@@@[                   IF NOT MACRO\FOUNHB
)@@G@@D THEN@D@@@[                      WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\DIRECTIVE);   @D@@@[HC
)@@G@@                 END; " OF SEARCH FOR UNDEFINED MACRO @C@@@[            HD
)@@G@@  END; " OF SEARCHING DIRECTIVES    @B@@@[           END; " OF TEST FOR HE
)@@G@@COMMENT     @B@@@[          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE NE 0 THEN  @E@@@[      HF
)@@G@@     BEGIN                      " TO DIAGNOSE ERROR   @F@@@[            HG
)@@G@@ IF NOT ERROR\PRINTED THEN " PRINT GENERAL MESSAGE    @B@@@[            HH
)@@G@@    WARNING(W\DIR\SYNTAX);    @ @@@[             PRINT\ERROR\MSG; @F@@@[HI
)@@G@@             PRINT\INPUT\CARD;        " ALWAYS PRINT BAD CARD     @#@@@[HJ
)@@G@@           END;   @[@@@["     @F@@@[" IF DIRECTIVE PUSHES CARD SET FLUSHHK
)@@G@@\DIRECTIVE\IMAGE TO FALSE !!!!@[@@@["     @E@@@[          IF FLUSH\DIRECHL
)@@G@@TIVE\IMAGE THEN " NO CARDS PUSHED SO@E@@@[           BEGIN              HM
)@@G@@        " TO FLUSH THE IMAGE  @C@@@[             SCAN\TO\DIRECTIVE\END; HN
)@@G@@  " SCAN    @B@@@[           END; " OF FLUSHING DIRECTIVE   @F@@@[      HO
)@@G@@    DIRECTIVE := FALSE;         " TURN OFF DIRECTIVE MODE   @E@@@[      HP
)@@G@@    IF PENDING\AT NE 0 THEN     " MUST PUSH SOME AT   @#@@@[           BHQ
)@@G@@EGIN  @B@@@[             FOR I := 1 TO NUM\ATS DO     @^@@@[            HR
)@@G@@  BEGIN     @D@@@[                IF DO\AT(I) THEN      " FORCE IT NOW  HS
)@@G@@@^@@@[                 BEGIN  @C@@@[                   DO\AT(I) := FALSEHT
)@@G@@; " TURN OFF@C@@@[                   PUSH\AT\EQUATE(I); " PUSH IT @^@@@[HU
)@@G@@                 END;   @F@@@[              END                     " FOHV
)@@G@@R LOOP OVER ATS SET     @B@@@[           END; " TEST FOR PENDING ATS    HW
)@@G@@@^@@@[END; " PROCESS\DIRECTIVE@#@@@[CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@["     @F@@@[HX
)@@G@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\DPS\DIRECTIVE(DIRECTIVE\INDEX: INTEGER WORD)    @[@@@[HY
)@@G@@BEGIN @[@@@["     @D@@@[" IF OPTIONS ARE GIVEN THEN BUILD AN OPTIONS MASHZ
)@@G@@K     @[@@@["     @F@@@[          DIRECTIVE\OPT\WORD(1) := 0; " SET OPTIIA
)@@G@@ONS ALL FALSE     @B@@@[          DIRECTIVE\OPT\WORD(2) := 0;     @B@@@[IB
)@@G@@          DIRECTIVE\OPT\WORD(3) := 0;     @A@@@[          OPTIONS\GIVEN IC
)@@G@@:= FALSE;   @A@@@[          IF CHARACTER EQ COMMA THEN@F@@@[           BID
)@@G@@EGIN                      " TO SCAN OPTIONS LETTERS   @A@@@[            IE
)@@G@@ OPTIONS\GIVEN := TRUE; @F@@@[             SCAN(CTRM+ALLOW\NAM);    " SCIF
)@@G@@AN DIRECTIVE OPTIONS    @A@@@[             CONVERT\TO\MONOCASE;   @E@@@[IG
)@@G@@             FOR I := 1 TO NAME\LEN DO " BUILD OPTION MASK  @E@@@[      IH
)@@G@@          DIRECTIVE\OPT(MONOCASE\CHAR(I)) := TRUE;    @B@@@[           EII
)@@G@@ND; " OF SCANNING OPTIONS     @D@@@[          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 IJ
)@@G@@THEN " NO ERROR SO@E@@@[           BEGIN                      " TO PROCEIK
)@@G@@SS DIRECTIVE@D@@@[             CASEENTRY DIRECTIVE\INDEX " DO DIRECTIVE IL
)@@G@@@A@@@[             CASE 1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9:@G@@@[                PROCESS\IM
)@@G@@SECTIONING\DIRECTIVE(DIRECTIVE\INDEX); " .1-.9  @E@@@[             CASE IN
)@@G@@10: PROCESS\TITLE\DIRECTIVE; " .0 'TITLE' @F@@@[             CASE ACCEPTIO
)@@G@@\DIRECTIVE:     PROCESS\ACCEPT\DIRECTIVE; @F@@@[             CASE ASSUMEIP
)@@G@@\DIRECTIVE:     PROCESS\ASSUME\DIRECTIVE; @F@@@[             CASE AT\DIRIQ
)@@G@@ECTIVE:         PROCESS\AT\DIRECTIVE;     @F@@@[             CASE COMMENIR
)@@G@@T\DIRECTIVE:    DIRECTIVE\ERROR := 0;     @F@@@[             CASE COLUMNIS
)@@G@@\DIRECTIVE:     PROCESS\COLUMN\DIRECTIVE; @F@@@[             CASE CONTROIT
)@@G@@L\DIRECTIVE:    PROCESS\CONTROL\DIRECTIVE;@G@@@[             CASE DATA\DIU
)@@G@@IRECTIVE:       DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR20;     @F@@@[             CASE IV
)@@G@@DECLARE\DIRECTIVE:    PROCESS\DECLARE\DIRECTIVE;@G@@@[             CASE IW
)@@G@@DEFER\DIRECTIVE:      DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR20;     @G@@@[            IX
)@@G@@ CASE DELAY\DIRECTIVE:      DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR20;     @E@@@[      IY
)@@G@@       CASE DISPLAY\DIRECTIVE:    PROCESS\DISPLAY;    @F@@@[            IZ
)@@G@@ CASE EDIT\DIRECTIVE:       PROCESS\EDIT\DIRECTIVE;   @F@@@[            JA
)@@G@@ CASE EJECT\DIRECTIVE:      PROCESS\EJECT\DIRECTIVE;  @F@@@[            JB
)@@G@@ CASE ENDF\DIRECTIVE:       PROCESS\ENDF\DIRECTIVE;   @F@@@[            JC
)@@G@@ CASE ENDK\DIRECTIVE:       PROCESS\ENDK\DIRECTIVE;   @F@@@[            JD
)@@G@@ CASE ENDT\DIRECTIVE:       PROCESS\ENDT\DIRECTIVE;   @F@@@[            JE
)@@G@@ CASE FLAG\DIRECTIVE:       PROCESS\FLAG\DIRECTIVE;   @F@@@[            JF
)@@G@@ CASE FONT\DIRECTIVE:       PROCESS\FONT\DIRECTIVE;   @G@@@[            JG
)@@G@@ CASE FOOTNOTE\DIRECTIVE:   PROCESS\FOOTNOTE\DIRECTIVE;     @G@@@[      JH
)@@G@@       CASE HLINE\DIRECTIVE:      DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR20;     @F@@@[JI
)@@G@@             CASE HSKIP\DIRECTIVE:      PROCESS\HSKIP\DIRECTIVE;  @F@@@[JJ
)@@G@@             CASE INCLUDE\DIRECTIVE:    PROCESS\INCLUDE\DIRECTIVE;@F@@@[JK
)@@G@@             CASE INDENT\DIRECTIVE:     PROCESS\INDENT\DIRECTIVE; @F@@@[JL
)@@G@@             CASE INSERT\DIRECTIVE:     PROCESS\INSERT\DIRECTIVE; @F@@@[JM
)@@G@@             CASE KEEP\DIRECTIVE:       PROCESS\KEEP\DIRECTIVE;   @F@@@[JN
)@@G@@             CASE LET\DIRECTIVE:        PROCESS\LET\DIRECTIVE;    @G@@@[JO
)@@G@@             CASE LEXICON\DIRECTIVE:    PROCESS\DICTIONARY\ENTRIES;     JP
)@@G@@@F@@@[             CASE MARGINS\DIRECTIVE:    PROCESS\MARGINS\DIRECTIVE;JQ
)@@G@@@H@@@[             CASE OFF\DIRECTIVE:        PROCESS\ON\OFF(FALSE); " TJR
)@@G@@URN OFF     @G@@@[             CASE ON\DIRECTIVE:         PROCESS\ON\OFFJS
)@@G@@(TRUE); " TURN ON @G@@@[             CASE POSITION\DIRECTIVE:   PROCESS\JT
)@@G@@POSITION\DIRECTIVE;     @G@@@[             CASE PAGESIZE\DIRECTIVE:   PRJU
)@@G@@OCESS\PAGESIZE\DIRECTIVE;     @G@@@[             CASE PAUSE\DIRECTIVE:  JV
)@@G@@    DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR20;     @G@@@]             CASE PCTL\DIRECTIJW
)@@G@@VE:       PROCESS\PRINT\CONTROL\DIRECTIVE;@F@@@[             CASE RESET\JX
)@@G@@DIRECTIVE:      PROCESS\RESET\DIRECTIVE;  @I@@@[             CASE RESTORJY
)@@G@@E\DIRECTIVE:    PROCESS\RESET\DIRECTIVE; " COMPATABILITY    @F@@@[      JZ
)@@G@@       CASE SKIP\DIRECTIVE:       PROCESS\SKIP\DIRECTIVE;   @F@@@[      KA
)@@G@@       CASE SPACING\DIRECTIVE:    PROCESS\SPACING\DIRECTIVE;@F@@@[      KB
)@@G@@       CASE TABLE\DIRECTIVE:      PROCESS\TABLE\DIRECTIVE;  @F@@@[      KC
)@@G@@       CASE TOC\DIRECTIVE:        PROCESS\TOC\DIRECTIVE;    @G@@@[      KD
)@@G@@       CASE TYPESIZE\DIRECTIVE:   PROCESS\TYPESIZE\DIRECTIVE;     @F@@@[KE
)@@G@@             CASE UNIT\DIRECTIVE:       PROCESS\UNIT\DIRECTIVE;   @G@@@[KF
)@@G@@             CASE VLINE\DIRECTIVE:      DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR20;     KG
)@@G@@@G@@@[             CASE WAIT\DIRECTIVE:       DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR20KH
)@@G@@;     @G@@@[             CASE *:                    ERROR; " BAD CONFIGUKI
)@@G@@RATION !!!  @^@@@[             ENDCASE;   @C@@@[           END; " OF PROKJ
)@@G@@CESSING DPS DIRECTIVE   @ @@@[END; " PROCESS\DPS\DIRECTIVE  @#@@@[CONTROKK
)@@G@@L(EJECT);   @[@@@["     @C@@@[" THESE ROUTINES HANDLE THE DPS DIRECTIVESKL
)@@G@@.     @[@@@["     @G@@@["   .ACCEPT '<TEXT>'    DOES A TREAD TO TERMINALKM
)@@G@@ AND INPUTS TO TEXT     @[@@@["     @A@@@[PROCEDURE PROCESS\ACCEPT\DIRECKN
)@@G@@TIVE  @[@@@[BEGIN @D@@@[          IF HARD\EOF THEN            " CANNOT RKO
)@@G@@EAD   @#@@@[           BEGIN  @D@@@[             WARNING(W\NO\MORE\DATA)KP
)@@G@@; " NO DATA GIVEN @#@@@[           END;   @A@@@[          ELSE " DO TYPEKQ
)@@G@@ AND READ   @#@@@[           BEGIN  @F@@@[             SCAN(EVAL+CTRM+CSKR
)@@G@@TR+ALLOW\STR); " SCAN FOR PROMPT    @F@@@[             SCAN\TO\DIRECTIVEKS
)@@G@@\END;   " GET TO END OF THIS CARD   @D@@@[             PUSH\ICB(ACCEPT\CKT
)@@G@@ARD);   " GET NEW CARD  @B@@@[             TYPE\AND\READ(CSDADR,CSDLEN);KU
)@@G@@@C@@@[             IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\N) THEN     @E@@@[            KV
)@@G@@    POP\ICB;              " THROW AWAY ANY INPUT@#@@@[             ELSE KW
)@@G@@@F@@@[                FLUSH\DIRECTIVE\IMAGE := FALSE; " INHIBIT FLUSH   KX
)@@G@@@#@@@[           END;   @A@@@[END; " PROCESS\ACCEPT\DIRECTIVE     @[@@@[KY
)@@G@@"     @B@@@["   .ASSUME[,A/R] <HORIZONTAL>,<VERTICAL> @[@@@["     @A@@@[KZ
)@@G@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\ASSUME\DIRECTIVE  @[@@@[BEGIN @ @@@[DECLARE   VERTICALLA
)@@G@@: DISTANCE; @A@@@[DECLARE   HORIZONTAL: DISTANCE;     @[@@@["     @B@@@[LB
)@@G@@          IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\A) THEN  @#@@@[           BEGIN  @D@@@[LC
)@@G@@             HORIZONTAL := WIDTH\NUMBER(LINE\WIDTH);  @E@@@[            LD
)@@G@@ VERTICAL := HEIGHT\NUMBER(VERTICAL\POSITION);  @C@@@[             IF ERLE
)@@G@@ROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN     @^@@@[              BEGIN     @C@@@[      LF
)@@G@@          SET\VERTICAL\POSITION(VERTICAL);@E@@@[                SET\AREALG
)@@G@@\VPOS(VERTICAL-AREA\VPOS\START);    @B@@@[                LINE\WIDTH := LH
)@@G@@HORIZONTAL; @#@@@[              END;@#@@@[           END;   @C@@@[      LI
)@@G@@    ELSE IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\R) THEN   @C@@@[           BEGIN " RELATLJ
)@@G@@IVE POSITION UPDATE     @E@@@[             HORIZONTAL := WIDTH\NUMBER(0)LK
)@@G@@; " GET HORIZONTAL@E@@@[             VERTICAL := HEIGHT\NUMBER(0); " GETLL
)@@G@@ VERTICAL   @C@@@[             IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN     @^@@@[LM
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @D@@@[                UPDATE\VERTICAL\POSITION(VLN
)@@G@@ERTICAL);   @C@@@[                UPDATE\AREA\VPOS(VERTICAL);     @D@@@[LO
)@@G@@                LINE\WIDTH := LINE\WIDTH + HORIZONTAL;@#@@@[            LP
)@@G@@  END;@#@@@[           END;   @#@@@[          ELSE    @B@@@[            LQ
)@@G@@ DIRECTIVE\ERROR := ERROR3;   @A@@@[END; " PROCESS\ASSUME\DIRECTIVE     LR
)@@G@@@#@@@[CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@["     @A@@@["   .COLUMNS <N>,<GUTTER-WIDTHLS
)@@G@@>     @[@@@["     @A@@@[PROCEDURE PROCESS\COLUMN\DIRECTIVE  @[@@@[BEGIN LT
)@@G@@@B@@@[DECLARE   AREA\SAVE: MACHINE WORD POINTER;@[@@@[      @D@@@[      LU
)@@G@@    PROCESS\ZONE\BREAK; " CREATE ZONE BREAK     @F@@@[          SCAN(EVALV
)@@G@@L+COMA+CTRM+ALLOW\INT);  " GET NUMBER OF COLUMNS@B@@@[          NUMBER\OLW
)@@G@@F\COLUMNS := DNUM(1);   @F@@@[          GUTTER\WIDTH := WIDTH\NUMBER(0);LX
)@@G@@  " GET GUTTER\WIDTH    @B@@@[          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE NE 0 OR    LY
)@@G@@@A@@@[             GUTTER\WIDTH LT 0 OR   @E@@@[             NUMBER\OF\CLZ
)@@G@@OLUMNS LT 1 THEN    " BAD DIRECTIVE @#@@@[           BEGIN  @A@@@[      MA
)@@G@@       NUMBER\OF\COLUMNS := 1;@A@@@[             GUTTER\WIDTH := 0;     MB
)@@G@@@A@@@[             WARNING(W\BAD\COLUMNS);@#@@@[           END;   @F@@@[MC
)@@G@@          SET\LINE\WIDTH;             " SET WIDTH THIS AREA ONLY  @A@@@[MD
)@@G@@          BUFFER\TEXT := FALSE;     @F@@@[          AREA\SAVE := AREA\PTME
)@@G@@R;      " SAVE CURRENT AREA POINTER @E@@@[          AREA\PTR := FIRST\ARMF
)@@G@@EA; " POINT TO FIRST AREA     @B@@@[          WHILE AREA\PTR NE NULL\PTRMG
)@@G@@ DO   @#@@@[           BEGIN  @C@@@[             IF NUMBER\OF\COLUMNS GTMH
)@@G@@ 1 THEN     @E@@@[                BUFFER\TEXT := TRUE;  " SET GLOBAL FLAMI
)@@G@@G     @E@@@[             AREA\PTR := FIXED\AREA\PTR;   " GET NEXT AREA  MJ
)@@G@@@#@@@[           END;   @E@@@[          AREA\PTR := AREA\SAVE;      " REMK
)@@G@@STORE AREA POINTER@A@@@[END; " PROCESS\COLUMN\DIRECTIVE     @[@@@["     ML
)@@G@@@#@@@[CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@["     @^@@@["   .EJECT[,I/U/C] <D>  @[@@@[MM
)@@G@@"     @A@@@[PROCEDURE PROCESS\EJECT\DIRECTIVE   @[@@@[BEGIN @ @@@[DECLARMN
)@@G@@E   REMAINING: DISTANCE @A@@@[          ,SAVE\LINE: CONDITION;    @[@@@[MO
)@@G@@"     @F@@@[          REMAINING := HEIGHT\NUMBER(BIG\DISTANCE); " GET ARMP
)@@G@@GUMENT@B@@@[          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN  @#@@@[           BMQ
)@@G@@EGIN  @G@@@[             IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\N) THEN " INHIBIT INITIAMR
)@@G@@L PAGEUP    @H@@@[                FIRST\PAGE := FALSE;  " NOLONG ON FIRSMS
)@@G@@T PAGE (INHIBITS PAGEUP)@A@@@[             ELSE  " REGULAR EJECT  @^@@@[MT
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @B@@@[                CHECK\FOR\LINE\BREAK;     MU
)@@G@@@C@@@[                IF NOT CAN\SKIP(REMAINING) THEN @^@@@[            MV
)@@G@@     BEGIN  @C@@@[                   SAVE\LINE := NOT LINE\EMPTY; @D@@@[MW
)@@G@@                   IF SAVE\LINE THEN  " I OPTION EJECT@B@@@[            MX
)@@G@@          PUSH\WORD\BUFFER;   @D@@@[                   IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(MY
)@@G@@ASCII\U) THEN     @ @@@[                    BEGIN     @B@@@[            MZ
)@@G@@          IF PAGE\EMPTY THEN  @ @@@[                       BEGIN  @G@@@[NA
)@@G@@                         PUT\OUT\HEADING;     " BE SURE TO PRINT HEADINGNB
)@@G@@@F@@@[                         PAGE\EMPTY := FALSE; " GUARANTEE PAGEUP  NC
)@@G@@@ @@@[                       END;   @E@@@[                      COLUMN\END
)@@G@@MPTY := FALSE;  " EJECT COLUMN@^@@@[                    END;@F@@@[      NE
)@@G@@             IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\C) THEN  " COLUMN EJECT @ @@@[      NF
)@@G@@              BEGIN     @C@@@[                      IF NOT COLUMN\EMPTY NG
)@@G@@THEN  @ @@@[                       BEGIN  @C@@@[                        NH
)@@G@@ IF BUFFER\TEXT THEN    @E@@@[                            INHIBIT\DISTRINI
)@@G@@BUTION := TRUE;   @F@@@[                         FORCE\END\OF\COLUMN;  "NJ
)@@G@@ OUTPUT COLUMN    @ @@@[                       END;   @^@@@[            NK
)@@G@@        END;@E@@@[                   ELSE FORCE\END\OF\PAGE;  " OUTPUT PNL
)@@G@@AGE   @A@@@[                   IF SAVE\LINE THEN@B@@@[                  NM
)@@G@@    POP\WORD\BUFFER;    @C@@@[                 END;  " OF CONDITIONAL EJNN
)@@G@@ECT   @B@@@[              END;  " OF REGULAR EJECT    @B@@@[           ENO
)@@G@@ND;  " OF ARGUMENT ERROR CHECK@ @@@[END; " PROCESS\EJECT\DIRECTIVE@#@@@[NP
)@@G@@CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@["     @^@@@["   .FLAG,[I] '<CHAR>'  @[@@@["     NQ
)@@G@@@A@@@[PROCEDURE PROCESS\FLAG\DIRECTIVE    @[@@@[BEGIN @[@@@[      @ @@@[NR
)@@G@@DECLARE   FLAG: WORD INTEGER; @[@@@[      @D@@@[          SCAN(CTRM+EVALNS
)@@G@@+ALLOW\STR);  " GET A STRING  @D@@@[          IF CSDTYP NE TYPSTR OR CSDNT
)@@G@@LEN GT 1 THEN     @A@@@[             WARNING(W\DIR\SYNTAX); @ @@@[      NU
)@@G@@    IF CSDLEN EQ 0 THEN @C@@@[             FLAG := BLANK;  " FORCE A BLANV
)@@G@@NK    @#@@@[          ELSE    @ @@@[             FLAG := DCHR(1); @B@@@[NW
)@@G@@          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN  @#@@@[           BEGIN  @A@@@[NX
)@@G@@             CHECK\FOR\LINE\BREAK;  @A@@@[             IF FLAG EQ BLANK NY
)@@G@@THEN  @^@@@[              BEGIN     @B@@@[                IF CHARS\IN\LINZ
)@@G@@NE THEN     @H@@@[                   SAVE\EOL\FUNCTION(EOL\FUNC\LEFT\FLAOA
)@@G@@G,0); " TURN OFF AT EOL @C@@@[                ELSE  " TURN OFF IMMEDIATEOB
)@@G@@LY    @B@@@[                   LEFT\FLAG := FALSE;    @#@@@[            OC
)@@G@@  END;@ @@@[             ELSE " TURN ON   @^@@@[              BEGIN     OD
)@@G@@@H@@@[                IF LEFT\MARGIN LT 2*SPACEBAND\WIDTH+CHAR\WIDTH(FLAOE
)@@G@@G+1) THEN   @C@@@[                   WARNING(W\NO\FLAG\SPACE);    @^@@@[OF
)@@G@@                ELSE    @^@@@[                 BEGIN  @B@@@[            OG
)@@G@@       LEFT\FLAG := TRUE;     @B@@@[                   FLAG\CHAR := FLAGOH
)@@G@@;     @^@@@[                 END;   @#@@@[              END;@#@@@[      OI
)@@G@@     END;   @ @@@[END; " PROCESS\FLAG\DIRECTIVE @[@@@["     @#@@@["   .FOJ
)@@G@@ONT <N>     @[@@@["     @A@@@[PROCEDURE PROCESS\FONT\DIRECTIVE    @[@@@[OK
)@@G@@BEGIN @F@@@[          PROCESS\INTERNAL\FONT\CHANGE; " CHANGE FONT INTERNOL
)@@G@@ALLY  @ @@@[END; " PROCESS\FONT\DIRECTIVE @[@@@["     @E@@@[" SKIP A SPEOM
)@@G@@CIFIED DISTANCE IN THE HORIZONTAL DIRECTION.    @[@@@["     @^@@@["   .HON
)@@G@@SKIP <DISTANCE>   @[@@@["     @A@@@[PROCEDURE PROCESS\HSKIP\DIRECTIVE   OO
)@@G@@@[@@@[BEGIN @H@@@[          ADD\SPACE\TO\NEXT\WORD( FUNC\BLANK , WIDTH\NOP
)@@G@@UMBER(0) ); " NEAT HUH? @ @@@[END; " PROCESS\HSKIP\DIRECTIVE@[@@@["     OQ
)@@G@@@#@@@[CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@["     @B@@@["  INCLUDE TEXT FROM AN EXTERNOR
)@@G@@AL FILE.    @[@@@["     @C@@@["   .INCLUDE[,S] <FILE-NAME>.<ELEMENT-NAMEOS
)@@G@@>     @[@@@["     @A@@@[PROCEDURE PROCESS\INCLUDE\DIRECTIVE @[@@@[BEGIN OT
)@@G@@@A@@@["         IF EMBEDDED\DIRECTIVE THEN@#@@@["          BEGIN  @B@@@[OU
)@@G@@"            WARNING(W\ILLEGAL\EMBEDDED); @#@@@["          END;   @#@@@[OV
)@@G@@"         ELSE    @#@@@[           BEGIN  @C@@@[             IF DIRECTIVOW
)@@G@@E\OPT(ASCII\S) THEN     @^@@@[              BEGIN     @B@@@[            OX
)@@G@@    PROCESS\INCLUDE\SYMBOLIC; @#@@@[              END;@#@@@[            OY
)@@G@@ ELSE @^@@@[              BEGIN     @C@@@[                WARNING(W\ILLEOZ
)@@G@@GAL\OPTIONS);     @#@@@[              END;@#@@@[          END;    @A@@@[PA
)@@G@@END; " PROCESS\INCLUDE\DIRECTIVE    @[@@@["     @A@@@["   .INDENT[,T/I/DPB
)@@G@@] <LEFT>,<RIGHT>  @[@@@["     @A@@@[PROCEDURE PROCESS\INDENT\DIRECTIVE  PC
)@@G@@@[@@@[BEGIN @[@@@["     @ @@@[DECLARE   LEFT: DISTANCE;     @ @@@[DECLARPD
)@@G@@E   RIGHT: DISTANCE;    @[@@@["     @A@@@[          CHECK\FOR\LINE\BREAKPE
)@@G@@;     @A@@@[          LEFT := WIDTH\NUMBER(0);  @A@@@[          RIGHT :=PF
)@@G@@ WIDTH\NUMBER(0); @B@@@[          IF (LEFT\INDENT + LEFT) LT 0 OR @D@@@[PG
)@@G@@             (RIGHT\INDENT + RIGHT) LT 0 THEN " ERROR @#@@@[           BPH
)@@G@@EGIN  @C@@@[             WARNING(W\BAD\MARGINS);  " TELL HIM@#@@@[      PI
)@@G@@     END;   @E@@@[          ELSE IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN " CONTINPJ
)@@G@@UE    @#@@@[           BEGIN  @F@@@[             IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\PK
)@@G@@D) THEN " DEFERRED INDENT     @^@@@[              BEGIN     @F@@@[      PL
)@@G@@          SAVE\EOL\FUNCTION(EOL\FUNC\LEFT\INDENT,LEFT);     @F@@@[      PM
)@@G@@          SAVE\EOL\FUNCTION(EOL\FUNC\RIGHT\INDENT,RIGHT);   @#@@@[      PN
)@@G@@        END;@B@@@[             ELSE " NON-DEFERED INDENT    @^@@@[      PO
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @[@@@["     @G@@@[" IF TEMP INDENT THEN SAVE FUNCTION PP
)@@G@@TO PUT INDENT BACK AT END OF LINE   @[@@@["     @E@@@[                IFPQ
)@@G@@ DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\T) THEN " TEMP INDENT@^@@@[                 BEGIN  PR
)@@G@@@F@@@[                   SAVE\EOL\FUNCTION(EOL\FUNC\LEFT\INDENT,-LEFT); PS
)@@G@@@G@@@[                   SAVE\EOL\FUNCTION(EOL\FUNC\RIGHT\INDENT,-RIGHT)PT
)@@G@@;     @A@@@[                 END; " TEMP INDENT @D@@@[                LEPU
)@@G@@FT\INDENT := LEFT\INDENT + LEFT;    @D@@@[                RIGHT\INDENT :PV
)@@G@@= RIGHT\INDENT + RIGHT; @C@@@[              END; " OF NON-DEFERRED INDENPW
)@@G@@TS    @A@@@[           END; " OF ERROR CHECK    @A@@@[END; " PROCESS\INDPX
)@@G@@ENT\DIRECTIVE     @[@@@["     @#@@@[CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@["     @B@@@[PY
)@@G@@"   .LET <USER-VARIABLE> := <EXPRESSION>  @[@@@["     @A@@@[PROCEDURE PRPZ
)@@G@@OCESS\LET\DIRECTIVE     @[@@@[BEGIN @E@@@[          IF FORMATTING OR NOTQA
)@@G@@ DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\F) THEN  @F@@@[             PROCESS\LET(FALSE);    QB
)@@G@@         " IN ELEMENT LET     @ @@@[END; " PROCESS\LET\DIRECTIVE  @[@@@[QC
)@@G@@"     @B@@@["   .MARGINS <LEFT>,<RIGHT>,<TOP>,<BOTTOM>@[@@@["     @A@@@[QD
)@@G@@PROCEDURE PROCESS\MARGINS\DIRECTIVE @[@@@[BEGIN @[@@@["     @^@@@[DECLARQE
)@@G@@E   TOP: DISTANCE;@ @@@[DECLARE   BOTTOM: DISTANCE;   @ @@@[DECLARE   LEQF
)@@G@@FT: DISTANCE;     @ @@@[DECLARE   RIGHT: DISTANCE;    @[@@@["     @C@@@[QG
)@@G@@          LEFT := WIDTH\NUMBER(LEFT\MARGIN);    @C@@@[          RIGHT :=QH
)@@G@@ WIDTH\NUMBER(RIGHT\MARGIN);  @C@@@[          TOP := HEIGHT\NUMBER(TOP\MQI
)@@G@@ARGIN);     @D@@@[          BOTTOM := HEIGHT\NUMBER(BOTTOM\MARGIN);     QJ
)@@G@@@B@@@[          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN  @#@@@[           BEGIN  QK
)@@G@@@[@@@["     @^@@@[" CHECK THAT THEY ARE OK@[@@@["     @C@@@[            QL
)@@G@@ IF PAGE\WIDTH-LEFT-RIGHT LE 0 OR   @C@@@[                PAGE\HEIGHT-TOQM

)@@G@@@F@@@[                CHECK\FOR\LINE\BREAK; " END LINE IF NO I OPTION   QU
)@@G@@@#@@@[              END;@#@@@[           END;   @A@@@[END; " PROCESS\MARQV
)@@G@@GINS\DIRECTIVE    @#@@@[CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@["     @^@@@[" ON\OFF DIRQW
)@@G@@ECTIVES     @[@@@["     @A@@@["   .ON[,T/I] <MODE1>,<MODE2>,...   @[@@@[QX

)@@G@@URE PROCESS\ON\OFF(TURN\IT\ON: WORD CONDITION)  @[@@@[BEGIN @F@@@[      QZ
)@@G@@    CHECK\FOR\LINE\BREAK;       " SEE IF I OPTION GIVEN     @E@@@[      RA

)@@G@@AMES) , MAX\ON\OFF , ENABLE\AB );   @E@@@[             CASEENTRY ON\OFF\RF
)@@G@@INDEX   " SELECT WHICH ONE    @A@@@[             CASE ON\OFF\BALANCING: RG

)@@G@@ON\OFF\CENTER:    @^@@@[              BEGIN     @C@@@[                IFRI

)@@G@@ON\OFF\HYPHEN:    @^@@@[              BEGIN     @E@@@[                IFRX
)@@G@@ DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\T) THEN " SAVE IT    @D@@@[                   SAVE\RY

)@@G@@TE(HYPHEN) );     @B@@@[                HYPHEN := TURN\IT\ON;     @#@@@[SA
)@@G@@              END;@A@@@[             CASE ON\OFF\JUSTIFY:   @^@@@[      SB

)@@G@@@^@@@[             ENDCASE;   @E@@@[             SCAN(CTRM+ALLOW\NAM);  SS
)@@G@@  " PICK UP SWITCH NAME @A@@@[           END; " OF LOOP OVER NAMES@ @@@[ST

)@@G@@T);   @[@@@["     @F@@@["   .POSITION <LEFT>      DEFINES AMOUNT OF VIRTSW
)@@G@@UAL PAGE OFFSET   @[@@@["     @A@@@[PROCEDURE PROCESS\POSITION\DIRECTIVESX
)@@G@@@[@@@[BEGIN @ @@@[DECLARE   POSITION: DISTANCE; @[@@@["     @B@@@[      SY

)@@G@@ EQ 0 THEN " SET IT     @#@@@[           BEGIN  @A@@@[             PROCETA

)@@G@@CTION(EOL\FUNC\RIGHT\INDENT); @#@@@[           END;   @ @@@[END; " PROCEUI
)@@G@@SS\RESET\DIRECTIVE@[@@@["     @#@@@[CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@["     @^@@@[UJ
)@@G@@"   .SKIP[,I/U/V] <D>   @[@@@["     @A@@@[PROCEDURE PROCESS\SKIP\DIRECTIUK
)@@G@@VE    @[@@@[BEGIN @E@@@[DECLARE   MIN\HEIGHT: DISTANCE; " MINIMUM HEIGHTUL
)@@G@@ TO SKIP    @E@@@[DECLARE   MAX\HEIGHT: DISTANCE; " MAXIMUM HEIGHT TO SKUM
)@@G@@IP    @G@@@[DECLARE   REMAINING: DISTANCE;  " DISTANCE REMAINING IN THISUN
)@@G@@ COLUMN     @E@@@[DECLARE   CARRYOVER: DISTANCE;  " CARRY OVER TO NEXT CUO
)@@G@@OLUMN @E@@@[DECLARE   FUNC: 9 BIT UNSIGNED INTEGER; " LEAD FUNCTION     UP
)@@G@@@A@@@[DECLARE   SAVE\LINE: CONDITION;     @[@@@["     @B@@@[          MIUQ
)@@G@@N\HEIGHT := HEIGHT\NUMBER(0); @D@@@[          MAX\HEIGHT := HEIGHT\NUMBEUR
)@@G@@R(BIG\DISTANCE);  @B@@@[          IF ERROR\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN  @#@@@[US
)@@G@@           BEGIN  @A@@@[             CHECK\FOR\LINE\BREAK;  @F@@@[      UT
)@@G@@       IF DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\U) THEN " UNCONDITIONAL SKIP  @A@@@[      UU
)@@G@@          FUNC := FUNC\LEADU; @#@@@[             ELSE @A@@@[            UV
)@@G@@    FUNC := FUNC\LEAD;  @B@@@[             CARRYOVER := MIN\HEIGHT;     UW
)@@G@@@D@@@[             IF NOT CAN\SKIP(CARRYOVER+LEADING) THEN  @^@@@[      UX
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @D@@@[                REMAINING := AREA\HEIGHT-AREA\VPUY
)@@G@@OS;   @D@@@[                CARRYOVER := MIN\HEIGHT-REMAINING;    @C@@@[UZ
)@@G@@                SAVE\LINE := NOT LINE\EMPTY;    @A@@@[                IFVA
)@@G@@ SAVE\LINE THEN   @A@@@[                   PUSH\WORD\BUFFER;@C@@@[      VB
)@@G@@          INSERT\LEADING(REMAINING,FUNC); @B@@@[                DO\END\OVC
)@@G@@F\LINE\PROCESSING;@A@@@[                FORCE\END\OF\COLUMN;@[@@@["     VD
)@@G@@@B@@@[" CARRYOVER MAY NOT EXCEED AREA DEPTH.    @[@@@["     @C@@@[      VE
)@@G@@          IF CARRYOVER GT AREA\HEIGHT THEN@C@@@[                   CARRYVF
)@@G@@OVER := AREA\HEIGHT;    @A@@@[                IF SAVE\LINE THEN   @A@@@[VG
)@@G@@                   POP\WORD\BUFFER; @#@@@[              END;@C@@@[      VH
)@@G@@       INSERT\LEADING(CARRYOVER,FUNC);    @[@@@["     @E@@@[" IF MAXIMUMVI
)@@G@@ SPECIFIED AND LEGAL, POST SLACK (MAX-MIN) IN A @ @@@[" VERTICAL-SPACEBAVJ
)@@G@@ND FUNCTION.@[@@@["     @C@@@[             IF (MAX\HEIGHT LT BIG\DISTANCVK
)@@G@@E) AND@C@@@[                (MAX\HEIGHT GT MIN\HEIGHT) THEN @^@@@[      VL
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @H@@@[                LINE\BUFFER(VSB\POS) := FUNC\VSBVM
)@@G@@; " MARK THIS LINE AS VSB     @G@@@[                LINE\CHAR\WIDTH(VSB\VN
)@@G@@POS) := MAX\HEIGHT - MIN\HEIGHT;    @#@@@[              END;@#@@@[      VO
)@@G@@     END;   @ @@@[END; " PROCESS\SKIP\DIRECTIVE @[@@@["     @^@@@["   .SVP
)@@G@@PACING[,I] <D>    @[@@@["     @A@@@[PROCEDURE PROCESS\SPACING\DIRECTIVE VQ
)@@G@@@[@@@[BEGIN @A@@@[DECLARE   NEW\SPACING: DISTANCE;    @[@@@["     @C@@@[VR

)@@G@@\STATUS\CODE EQ 0 THEN  @#@@@[           BEGIN  @A@@@[             CHECKVT

)@@G@@LEADING     @#@@@[           END;   @A@@@[END; " PROCESS\SPACING\DIRECTIVV
)@@G@@VE    @[@@@["     @#@@@[CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@["     @D@@@["   .TOC '<TVW

)@@G@@END; " PROCESS\TYPESIZE\DIRECTIVE   @[@@@["     @#@@@["   .UNIT <LEVEL> WC
)@@G@@@[@@@["     @D@@@[" CONDITIONALLY CAUSE UNIT BREAK WHEN FORMATTING TEXT.WD

)@@G@@" SECTIONING VECTOR, THEREFORE HE TESTS FOR FORMATTING.     @[@@@["     WF
)@@G@@@A@@@[PROCEDURE PROCESS\UNIT\DIRECTIVE    @[@@@[BEGIN @A@@@[          IFWG

)@@G@@@A@@@[                DISPLAY('UNISCN',0);@#@@@[             ELSE @F@@@[WL

)@@G@@           END; " SCAN FOR LEVEL    @A@@@[          FORCE\END\OF\PARAGRAWN
)@@G@@PH;   @ @@@[END; " PROCESS\UNIT\DIRECTIVE @[@@@["     @#@@@[CONTROL(EJECWO
)@@G@@T);   @[@@@["     @D@@@[" THESE ROUTINES ARE USED BY THE DIRECTIVE HANDLWP
)@@G@@ERS.  @[@@@["     @E@@@[" SCAN THE NEXT FIELD ON THE CARD FOR A NUMBER RWQ
)@@G@@EPRESENTING @A@@@[" COLUMNS   E.G.  A LEFT MARGIN     @[@@@["     @F@@@[WR
)@@G@@PROCEDURE WIDTH\NUMBER(DEFAULT: DISTANCE) EXPORTED ('WIDTHNUM')   @ @@@[WS
)@@G@@             RESULT DISTANCE  @[@@@[BEGIN @ @@@[DECLARE   NUMBER: DISTANWT
)@@G@@CE;   @D@@@[          NUMBER := DEFAULT;          " GET DEFAULT   @D@@@[WU
)@@G@@          SCAN(EVAL+COMA+CTRM+ALLOW\DST+CF\COL); "    @E@@@[          IFWV
)@@G@@ CSDTYP EQ TYPDST THEN    " DISTANCE RETURNED   @D@@@[             NUMBEWW
)@@G@@R := DDST(1);       " SO USE IT     @D@@@[          RETURN(NUMBER);     WX
)@@G@@        " GIVE NUMBER   @^@@@[END; " WIDTH\NUMBER     @[@@@["     @E@@@[WY
)@@G@@" SCAN THE NEXT FIELD ON THE CARD FOR A NUMBER REPRESENTING @B@@@[" VERTWZ
)@@G@@ICAL SKIPING   E.G.  A TOP MARGIN   @[@@@["     @B@@@[PROCEDURE HEIGHT\NXA
)@@G@@UMBER(DEFAULT: DISTANCE)@D@@@[             EXPORTED ('HEIGHTNUM') RESULTXB

)@@G@@\SKIP);     @E@@@[          IF CSDTYP EQ TYPDST THEN    " DISTANCE RETURXE
)@@G@@NED   @D@@@[             NUMBER := DDST(1);       " SO USE IT     @D@@@[XF
)@@G@@          RETURN(NUMBER);             " GIVE NUMBER   @^@@@[END; " HEIGHXG
)@@G@@T\NUMBER    @[@@@["     @[@@@["     @E@@@[" IF THE I OPTION IS NOT GIVENXH
)@@G@@ THEN FORCE AN END OF LINE    @[@@@["     @D@@@[PROCEDURE CHECK\FOR\LINEXI
)@@G@@\BREAK EXPORTED ('CHKLNBRK')  @[@@@[BEGIN @C@@@[          IF ERROR\STATUXJ
)@@G@@S\CODE EQ 0 THEN " OK   @C@@@[             IF NOT DIRECTIVE\OPT(ASCII\I)XK
)@@G@@ THEN @^@@@[              BEGIN     @E@@@[                OUTPUT\NEXT\WOXL
)@@G@@RD; " MOVE NEXT\WORD TO LINE  @B@@@[                FORCE\END\OF\PARAGRAXM
)@@G@@PH;   @#@@@[              END;@ @@@[END; " CHECK\FOR\LINE\BREAK   @[@@@[XN
)@@G@@"     @#@@@[CONTROL(EJECT);   @[@@@["     @B@@@[" CALCULATE NEW LINE WIDXO
)@@G@@TH PARAMATERS     @[@@@["     @C@@@[PROCEDURE SET\LINE\WIDTH EXPORTED ('XP
)@@G@@SETLINEWID')@[@@@[BEGIN @F@@@[          AREA\WIDTH := PAGE\WIDTH - RIGHTXQ
)@@G@@\MARGIN - LEFT\MARGIN;  @F[@@[          LEFT\OFFSET := ROUND\WIDTH(PAGE\XR
)@@G@@OFFSET+LEFT\MARGIN);    @ @@@[          CASEENTRY AREA\TYPE @^@@@[      XS
)@@G@@    CASE HEADER:  @#@@@[           BEGIN  @B@@@[             AREA\HEIGHTXT
)@@G@@ := TOP\MARGIN;   @A@@@[             AREA\VPOS\START := 0;  @#@@@[      XU
)@@G@@     END;   @^@@@[          CASE TEXT:    @#@@@[           BEGIN  @G@@@[XV
)@@G@@             AREA\HEIGHT := PAGE\HEIGHT - TOP\MARGIN - BOTTOM\MARGIN;   XW
)@@G@@@C@@@[             AREA\VPOS\START := TOP\MARGIN;     @H@@@[            XX
)@@G@@ IF VERTICAL\POSITION GT AREA\VPOS\START THEN " AREA WAS NOT EMPTY@^@@@[XY

)@@G@@\AREA\HEIGHT,AREA\HEIGHT);    @E@@@[                AREA\HEIGHT := AREA\YA
)@@G@@HEIGHT + AREA\VPOS\START@G@@@[                               - VERTICAL\YB
)@@G@@POSITION;  " GET NEW HEIGHT   @H@@@[                SAVE\TOP\FUNCTION(TOYC
)@@G@@P\FUNC\AREA\VPOS\START,AREA\VPOS\START);  @D@@@[                AREA\VPOYD
)@@G@@S\START := VERTICAL\POSITION; @F@@@[                IF NOT CAN\SKIP(LEADYE
)@@G@@ING) THEN  " AREA WAS FILLED  @B@@@[                   FORCE\END\OF\PAGEYF
)@@G@@;     @#@@@[              END;@#@@@[           END;   @^@@@[          CAYG
)@@G@@SE FOOTER:  @#@@@[           BEGIN  @B@@@[             AREA\HEIGHT := BOYH
)@@G@@TTOM\MARGIN;@E@@@[             AREA\VPOS\START := PAGE\HEIGHT - BOTTOM\MYI
)@@G@@ARGIN;@#@@@[           END;   @#@@@[          ENDCASE;@C[@@[          IFYJ
)@@G@@ COLUMN\LIST\PTR NE NULL\PTR THEN   @#@@@[           BEGIN  @C@@@[      YK
)@@G@@       RELEASE\CORE(COLUMN\LIST\PTR);     @E@@@[             COLUMN\LISTYL
)@@G@@\PTR := NULL\PTR;    " CLEAR POINTER@#@@@[           END;   @F@@@[      YM
)@@G@@    COLUMN\NUMBER := 1;         " ALWAYS RESET COLUMN\NUMBER@B@@@[      YN
)@@G@@    IF NUMBER\OF\COLUMNS GT 1 THEN  @#@@@[           BEGIN  @B@@@[      YO
)@@G@@       IF GUTTER\WIDTH EQ 0 THEN    @D@@@[                GUTTER\WIDTH :YP
)@@G@@= ROUND\WIDTH(AREA\WIDTH@E@@@[                                //(7*NUMBEYQ
)@@G@@R\OF\COLUMNS-1)); @H@@@[             SCRATCH(1) := (AREA\WIDTH-(NUMBER\OYR
)@@G@@F\COLUMNS-1)*GUTTER\WIDTH)    @C@@@[                         //NUMBER\OFYS
)@@G@@\COLUMNS;   @F@@@[             IF SCRATCH(1) LE 0 THEN  " BAD COLUMNS DIYT
)@@G@@RECTIVE     @^@@@[              BEGIN     @F@@@[                NUMBER\OYU
)@@G@@F\COLUMNS := 1;  " RESET COLUMNS TO 1     @E@@@[                GUTTER\WYV
)@@G@@IDTH := 0;    " CLEAR GUTTER\WIDTH  @B@@@[                WARNING(W\BAD\YW
)@@G@@COLUMNS);   @#@@@[              END;@#@@@[             ELSE @^@@@[      YX
)@@G@@        BEGIN     @F@@@[                AREA\WIDTH := SCRATCH(1);  " SETYY

)@@G@@        . EDIT DATE     @D@@@@          E$MSGR                      . PUWO

)@@G@@@E@@@@          E$SKIP    - 3               . BACK-UP OVER SECONDS@E@@@@WQ
)@@G@@          E$MSGR                      . GET CLOSING BRACKET @[@@@@.     WR
)@@G@@@E@@@@          E$FD2     RELE              . EDIT ELEMENT NAME   @D@@@@WS

)@@G@@E       A0,('      ')     . BLANKS? @E@@@@          J         ON20      WU
)@@G@@        . YES, NO VERSION     @D@@@@          E$CHAR    '/'             WV

)@@G@@NAME  @E@@@@ON20      .                           . END SIGNON MESSAGE  WX
)@@G@@@F@@@@          E$MSGR                      . BE SURE TO BLANK SECONDS  WY
)@@G@@@D@@@@          J         RETURN            . THEN RETURN   @[@@@@.     WZ

)@@G@@C[@C[@C[@C[@C[@C[@C[@C@ *[S@@@*SDFF*@[@@@@.     @A@@@@. UNIVERSITY OF MAYE
)@@G@@RYLAND EDIT$ PROCS@F@@@@. MODIFIED BY JEFF JEWETT FROM THE ORIGINAL CLASYF
)@@G@@SIC BY D. ZAVE.   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@. REASONS FOR MODIFICATIONS:  @[@@@@YG
)@@G@@.     @A@@@@. 1) TO ALLOW 18 BIT UFIELDS. E.G.  @[@@@@.     @D@@@@.     YH
)@@G@@    E$FD1     'RES',,U          . I$ OR BUST    @C@@@@.   GENERATES A 'TYI
)@@G@@' FLAG WHEN USING STOCK EDIT$P@[@@@@.     @B@@@@. 2) TO ALLOW EQUF'D J-DYJ
)@@G@@ESIGNATOR. E.G.   @[@@@@.     @ @@@@.   A     EQUF      BLIP,,S3  @B@@@@YK
)@@G@@.         E$COL     BLIP              .   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.   STOCK EDYL
)@@G@@IT$P GENERATES A 'T' FLAG. SOUND INCREDIBLE, BUT IT'S @G@@@@.   TRUE. WHYM
)@@G@@AT PAIN EXISTS IS DUE ALMOST ENTIRELY TO THE ILL-CONSIDERED @G@@@@.   (SYN
)@@G@@ORRY, DAREK) 'U' DEFAULT J-DESIGNATOR. IN THE ABOVE EXAMPLE THE   @F@@@@YO
)@@G@@.   STOCK EDIT$P 'SEES' NO EXPLICIT J-DESIG (E.G. BLIP,,J) AND SO @ @@@@YP
)@@G@@.   TRIES TO FORCE A 'U' IN.  @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. 3) EXTENSIONS TO HANDLYQ
)@@G@@E OUR ADDITIONAL ROUTINES AND PACKET FIELDS.    @[@@@@.     @G@@@@. NOTEYR
)@@G@@ THAT MODIFICATIONS (1) AND (3) ARE REFLECTED IN A SIGNIFICANTLY  @F@@@@YS
)@@G@@. LARGER E$AD. IF THE STOCK ASSEMBLER ALLOWED ONE TO 'OR' OFF     @H@@@@YT
)@@G@@. NON-RELOCATABLE FIELDS (A PERFECTLY REASONABLE REQUEST, WE THINK), THEYU
)@@G@@N     @B@@@@. THE PROC WOULD BE SUBSTANTIALLY SMALLER.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@YV
)@@G@@. NOTE: WE BELIEVE THAT THIS PROC IS COMPATIBLE WITH STOCK UNIVAC @F@@@@YW
)@@G@@. ASM AND MASM. WE MIGHT BE WRONG. ANY COMPLAINTS, SUGGESTIONS, OR@E@@@@YX
)@@G@@. EFFUSIVE DEMOSTRATIONS OF PRAISE SHOULD BE FORWARDED TO:  @[@@@@.     YY
)@@G@@@^@@@@.         JEFF JEWETT   @^@@@@.         SYSTEMS STAFF @A@@@@.     YZ

)@@G@@@B@@@@.         COLLEGE PARK, MARYLAND   20742  @[@@@@/.    @F@@@@.     ZB
)@@G@@    INTERNAL PACKET DEFINITIONS FOR USE BY EDIT$ ROUTINES   @[@@@@.     ZC
)@@G@@@#@@@@          DEF     @G@@@@E$VER$$   EQU       '010176'          . UOZD
)@@G@@M VERSION (FIELDATA DATE)     @E@@@@A$EDIT$   EQU       1               ZE
)@@G@@  . SIMULATE AEDIT$.    @D@@@@PX        EQU        1                . PAZF

)@@G@@TER   @D@@@@WX        EQU        3                . WORD POINTER  @]@@@@ZH
)@@G@@          . @E@@@@PKT       EQUF      0,PX                PACKET LOCATIOZI

)@@G@@    EQU       5                 . THIS IS Q4 OR T3    @]@@@@          . ZL
)@@G@@@F@@@@EMSGC     EQUF      PKT,,S2             EMSG$ SIGNAL CHARACTER    ZM
)@@G@@@D@@@@IL        EQUF      PKT,,S3             IMAGE LENGTH  @D@@@@ILOC  ZN
)@@G@@    EQUF      PKT,,H2             IMAGE LOCATION@E@@@@SAV1W     EQU     ZO
)@@G@@  PKT+1             . FULLWORD SAVE AREA  @F@@@@SAV1H1    EQUF      SAV1ZP
)@@G@@W,,H1           SAVE AREA FOR RETURN POINT@F@@@@SAV1H2    EQUF      SAV1ZQ
)@@G@@W,,XH2        . ANCILLARY RETURN SAVE     @G@@@@FPS       EQUF      PKT+ZR
)@@G@@2,,S1           SCALE FOR FLOATING POINT EDIT   @G@@@@FPR       EQUF    ZS
)@@G@@  PKT+2,,S2           FLOATING POINT ROUNDING OPTION  @H@@@@CIM       EQZT
)@@G@@UF      PKT+2,,S3           SAVE AREA FOR EMSG$ CHARACTER INDEX   @G@@@@ZU
)@@G@@EASCII    EQUF      PKT+2,,H2         . SOMETHING ASCII:QWM,EASC,EASCIN ZV
)@@G@@@F@@@@EASC      EQUF      PKT+2,,S4         . ASCII (QUARTERWORD) FLAG  ZW
)@@G@@@E@@@@EASCIN    EQUF      PKT+2,,S5         . ASCII INPUT FLAG    @E@@@@ZX
)@@G@@QWM       EQUF      PKT+2,,S6         . QUARTERWORD MODE    @G@@@@WIM   ZY
)@@G@@    EQUF      PKT+3,,H1           SAVE AREA FOR EMSG$ WORD INDEX  @E@@@@ZZ
)@@G@@SAVE1     EQUF      PKT+3,,H2           SAVE AREA FOR PX    @E@@@@SAVE2 AA
)@@G@@    EQU       PKT+4               SAVE AREA FOR CX    @G@@@@ADRASC    EQAB
)@@G@@UF      PKT+5,,H1         . NON-XLATING ASCII ENTRY POINT   @H@@@@SAVE3 AC
)@@G@@    EQUF      PKT+5,,H2           SAVE AREA FOR WX (RIGHT HALF ONLY)    AD
)@@G@@@H@@@@DPC       EQUF      PKT+6,,S1           CHARACTER FOR DOUBLE PRECIAE
)@@G@@SION SCALE  @H@@@@SPC       EQUF      PKT+6,,S2           CHARACTER FOR AF
)@@G@@SINGLE PRECISION SCALE  @D@@@@SIGN      EQUF      PKT+6,,S3           SIAG
)@@G@@GN INDICATOR@G@@@@NDP       EQUF      PKT+6,,S4         . DIGITS BEFORE AH
)@@G@@DECIMAL POINT     @G@@@@EMSGCA    EQUF      PKT+6,,QT         . EMSG$ ASAI
)@@G@@CII SIGNAL CHARACTER    @G@@@@FZERO     EQUF      PKT+7,,S1           FLAJ
)@@G@@OATING POINT ZERO INDICATOR   @E@@@@FCOL      EQUF      PKT+7,,S2       AK
)@@G@@    FINAL COLUMN OR ZERO@G@@@@NDF       EQUF      PKT+7,,S3           DIAL
)@@G@@GITS FOLLOWING DECIMAL POINT  @D@@@@SCALE     EQUF      PKT+7,,XH2      AM
)@@G@@    POWER OF TEN  @G@@@@VALUE     EQU       PKT+8             . DBLWRD SAN
)@@G@@AVE AREA FOR DIGITS     @I@@@@DPCA      EQUF      PKT+10,,Q1        . ASAO
)@@G@@CII CHARACTER FOR DOUBLE PRECISION SCA    @I@@@@SPCA      EQUF      PKT+AP
)@@G@@10,,Q2        . ASCII CHARACTER FOR SINGLE PRECISION SCA    @E@@@@ETBL  AQ
)@@G@@    EQUF      PKT+10,,XH2       . CONVERSION TABLE    @G@@@@ADRASCX   EQAR
)@@G@@U       PKT+11            . FD/ASCII XLATING ENTRY POINT    @G@@@@XAF   AS
)@@G@@    EQUF      ADRASCX,,S1       . EXTENDED ASCII-FD TRANSLATION   @F@@@@AT
)@@G@@SAV12W    EQUF      PKT+12            . ASCII ROUTINE SAVE AREA   @G@@@@AU
)@@G@@ADRXALF   EQU       PKT+13            . CASE-PRESRVNG XLATING E. P.     AV
)@@G@@@]@@@@          . @B@@@@E$DEF*    PROC      *0,0              .   @G@@@@AW
)@@G@@          TYPE      TYPE$REP          . OUR GUARENTEE: NO IBANK STORES  AX
)@@G@@@D@@@@STORE*    EQUF      0,*CX             . STORE CHAR    @B@@@@      AY
)@@G@@    END                         .   @[@@@@/.    @^@@@@.   THE UOM EDIT$ AZ
)@@G@@PACKET@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.    THE SIX TO FOURTEEN WORD EDIT$ PACKET CONTABA
)@@G@@INS USER-DEFINED  @F@@@@.    PARAMETERS, AND INTERNAL FLAGS USED BY THE BB
)@@G@@EDIT$ ROUTINES.   @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.    EDIT$ USES THE FOLLOWING PACKETBC
)@@G@@. WORDS 6 THROUGH 9 ARE NEEDED@G@@@@.    BY THE FLOATING POINT ROUTINES.BD
)@@G@@ WORDS 6 THROUGH 12 ARE REQUIRED    @E@@@@.    FOR ASCII CAPABILITIES. EBE
)@@G@@XTENDED ASCII DEMANDS WORD 13.@[@@@@.     @F@@@@.   ....................BF
)@@G@@......................................... @F@@@@. 0 :         : *EMSGC  BG
)@@G@@:   *IL   :            *ILOC            : @F@@@@.   ....................BH
)@@G@@......................................... @F@@@@. 1 :            SAV1H1 BI
)@@G@@          :           SAV1H2            : @F@@@@.   ....................BJ
)@@G@@......................................... @F@@@@. 2 :  *FPS   :  *FPR   BK
)@@G@@:   CIM   :  *EASC  : *EASCIN :   QWM   : @F@@@@.   ....................BL
)@@G@@......................................... @F@@@@. 3 :             WIM   BM
)@@G@@          :            SAVE1            : @F@@@@.   ....................BN
)@@G@@......................................... @F@@@@. 4 :                   BO
)@@G@@        SAVE2                           : @F@@@@.   ....................BP
)@@G@@......................................... @F@@@@. 5 :            ADRASC BQ
)@@G@@          :            SAVE3            : @F@@@@.   ....................BR
)@@G@@......................................... @F@@@@. 6 :  *DPC   :  *SPC   BS
)@@G@@:  SIGN   :   NDP   :      *EMSGCA      : @F@@@@.   ....................BT
)@@G@@......................................... @F@@@@. 7 :  ZERO   :  FCOL   BU
)@@G@@:   NDF   :            SCALE            : @F@@@@.   ....................BV
)@@G@@......................................... @F@@@@. 8 :                   BW
)@@G@@                                        : @F@@@@.   .                   BX
)@@G@@        VALUE                           . @F@@@@. 9 :                   BY
)@@G@@                                        : @F@@@@.   ....................BZ
)@@G@@......................................... @F@@@@. 10:    *DPCA     :    CA
)@@G@@*SPCA     :            *ETBL            : @F@@@@.   ....................CB
)@@G@@......................................... @F@@@@. 11:  *XAF   : NOT USEDCC
)@@G@@:    0    :           ADRASCX           : @F@@@@.   ....................CD
)@@G@@......................................... @F@@@@. 12:                   CE
)@@G@@        SAV12W                          : @F@@@@.   ....................CF
)@@G@@......................................... @F@@@@. 13: NOT USED: NOT USEDCG
)@@G@@:    0    :           ADRXALF           : @F@@@@.   ....................CH
)@@G@@......................................... @[@@@@.     @F@@@@.    THE STACI
)@@G@@RRED PACKET FIELDS ARE SET BY THE USER; THE OTHERS ARE@ @@@@.    USED INCJ
)@@G@@TERNALLY BY EDIT$.@[@@@@.     @[@@@@/.    @G@@@@.   EXTERNAL DEFINITIONSCK
)@@G@@  (FOR JOE USER). JOE SUPPLIES PACKET ADDRESS.  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@P$    CL
)@@G@@    PROC      *1                . FIELD IS ADDR OF PACKET   @B@@@@E$FIELCM
)@@G@@DS* NAME                        .   @[@@@@.     @D@@@@PKT       EQUF    CN
)@@G@@  P$(1,1),P$(1,2)   . DEFINE STUFF  @[@@@@.     @C@@@@QT        EQU     CO
)@@G@@  05                . Q4 OR T3@F@@@@EMSGC*    EQUF      PKT,,12         CP
)@@G@@    EMSG$ SIGNAL CHARACTER    @D@@@@IL*       EQUF      PKT,,11         CQ
)@@G@@    IMAGE LENGTH  @D@@@@ILOC*     EQUF      PKT,,01             IMAGE LOCR
)@@G@@CATION@G@@@@FPS*      EQUF      PKT+2,,13           SCALE FOR FLOATING PCS
)@@G@@OINT EDIT   @G@@@@FPR*      EQUF      PKT+2,,12           FLOATING POINTCT
)@@G@@ ROUNDING OPTION  @F@@@@EASC*     EQUF      PKT+2,,10         . ASCII (QCU
)@@G@@UARTERWORD) FLAG  @E@@@@EASCIN*   EQUF      PKT+2,,9          . ASCII INCV
)@@G@@PUT FLAG    @H@@@@DPC*      EQUF      PKT+6,,13           CHARACTER FOR CW
)@@G@@DOUBLE PRECISION SCALE  @H@@@@SPC*      EQUF      PKT+6,,12           CHCX
)@@G@@ARACTER FOR SINGLE PRECISION SCALE  @G@@@@EMSGCA*   EQUF      PKT+6,,QT CY
)@@G@@        . EMSG$ ASCII SIGNAL CHARACTER    @I@@@@DPCA*     EQUF      PKT+CZ
)@@G@@10,,07        . ASCII CHARACTER FOR DOUBLE PRECISION SC     @I@@@@SPCA* DA
)@@G@@    EQUF      PKT+10,,04        . ASCII CHARACTER FOR SINGLE PRECISION SDB
)@@G@@C     @E@@@@ETBL*     EQUF      PKT+10,,003       . CONVERSION TABLE    DC
)@@G@@@G@@@@XAF*      EQUF      PKT+11,,13        . EXTENDED ASCII-FD TRANSLATDD
)@@G@@ION   @D@@@@          END                         . ALL FOR YOU   @[@@@@DE
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@.   ASCII XLATION DEFS. CALL AFTER E$DEF. @[@@@@.     @B@@@@DF
)@@G@@          DEF                         .   @D@@@@LAHEAD(WX) EQUF     PKT+DG
)@@G@@13,,H1        . LOOKAHEAD     @C@@@@LAHEAD(CX) EQUF     PKT+7,,H2       DH
)@@G@@  . FOR XAF @E@@@@CHARPT    EQUF      VALUE,,H1         . CHARACTER POINDI
)@@G@@TER   @D@@@@CXRET     EQUF      VALUE,,H2         . CX RETURN     @E@@@@DJ
)@@G@@FINRET    EQUF      VALUE+1,,H1       . FINAL X11 RETURN    @G@@@@BLNKADDK
)@@G@@R   EQUF      PKT+7,,H1         . ADDR OF LAST NON-BLANK CHAR     @D@@@@DL
)@@G@@IMGMD     EQUF      PKT+11,,S2        . IMAGE MODE    @E@@@@EFDFG     EQDM
)@@G@@UF      PKT+11,,S3        . EFD[1,2,3]$ FLAG    @B@@@@E$APROC*  PROC    DN
)@@G@@  *0,0              .   @B@@@@          END                         .   DO
)@@G@@@[@@@@/.    @F@@@@. ORIGINAL GENERALIZED ADDRESSING PROC, INCLUDED FOR CDP
)@@G@@OMPLETENESS.@[@@@@.     @G@@@@.  +(E$AD S,T U) SCANS P$(S,T) FOR UFIELD,DQ
)@@G@@ P$(S,T+1) FOR EXPLICIT XREG, @G@@@@.         P$(S,T+2) FOR EXPLICIT J-DDR
)@@G@@ESIGNATOR. UFIELD MAY BE EQUFFED. IF@D@@@@.         NO J-DESIG FOUND, THDS
)@@G@@EN DEFAULT U IS USED.   @F@@@@.  +(E$AD0 S,T U) PERFORMS AS ABOVE, BUT ODT
)@@G@@NLY P$(S,T) IS SCANNED. @E@@@@.         THERE ARE NO EXPLICIT XREG OR J-DU
)@@G@@DESIG FIELDS.     @[@@@@.     @F@@@@. DECODE A U-FIELD INTO ITS CONSTITUDV
)@@G@@ENT ELEMENTS. THIS PROC USES  @G@@@@. SUBTRACTION TO AVOID SPURIOUS R-FLDW
)@@G@@AGS WHICH MIGHT OTHERWISE ARISE.    @F@@@@. IN ADDITION, IT DOES NOT ALTDX
)@@G@@ER THE FORM OF THE ORIGINAL U-FIELD,@F@@@@. SINCE IT IS UNKNOWN WHETHER DY
)@@G@@THE U FIELD ALREADY HAS FORM OR NOT.@[@@@@.     @E@@@@. I HAVE NO SCRUPLDZ
)@@G@@ES, SO MUCH OF THIS PROC WAS SNARFED FROM @^@@@@. PAT HAGERTY'S STRUC$. EA
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @]@@@@        DEF @E@@@@G$JBIT(1) EQU 1*/29                 EB
)@@G@@  . J-DESIGNATOR BITS   @^@@@@G$JBIT(2) EQU 1*/28     @^@@@@G$JBIT(3) EQEC
)@@G@@U 1*/27     @^@@@@G$JBIT(4) EQU 1*/26     @D@@@@G$XBIT(1) EQU 1*/21     ED
)@@G@@              . XREG BITS     @^@@@@G$XBIT(2) EQU 1*/20     @^@@@@G$XBITEE
)@@G@@(3) EQU 1*/19     @^@@@@G$XBIT(4) EQU 1*/18     @C@@@@G$HIBI(1) EQU 1*/1EF
)@@G@@7                   . HBIT    @C@@@@G$HIBI(2) EQU 1*/16                 EG
)@@G@@  . IBIT    @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@Q         PROC      *2,0      EH
)@@G@@        .   @G@@@@E$AD*     NAME      1                 . COMPUTE GENERAEI
)@@G@@LIZED ADDRESS     @F@@@@E$AD0*    NAME      0                 . PROCESS EJ
)@@G@@ONE FIELD ONLY    @F@@@@MF   EQU  Q(0,0)                      . TRUE IF EK
)@@G@@MANY-SUBFIELDS    @C@@@@S    EQU  Q(1,1)                      . FIELD   EL
)@@G@@@C@@@@T    EQU  Q(1,2)                      . SUBFIELD@H@@@@HBIT EQU P$(EM
)@@G@@S,*T+1)*MF                . ON IF UFIELD,*XREG : ZERO IF E$AD0    @H@@@@EN
)@@G@@IBIT EQU P$(S,*T)*MF                  . ON IF *UFIELD      : ZERO IF E$AEO
)@@G@@D0    @G@@@@. NOTE THAT WE CAN'T PROCESS THE NEXT 4 LINES AS P$(S,T+1)*(EP
)@@G@@EXISTENCE=1)@G@@@@. BECAUSE OF PROPAGATION OF FORMS. E.G. A*0 => ZERO WIEQ
)@@G@@TH FORM OF C.     @#@@@@. UGLY BUT TRUE.  @E@@@@ DO MF=0 ,XREG EQU  0   ER
)@@G@@              . EXPLICIT XREG SET 0 @F@@@@ DO MF=0 ,EXPJ EQU  0         ES
)@@G@@        . EXPLICIT J-DESIG SET 0    @H@@@@ DO MF ,XREG EQU  P$(S,T+1)   ET
)@@G@@        . IF NOT E$$A0 ,FETCH EXPLICIT XREG     @H@@@@ DO MF ,EXPJ EQU  EU
)@@G@@P$(S,T+2)           . IF NOT E$$A0 ,FETCH EXPLICIT J-DESIG  @C@@@@. OBTAEV
)@@G@@IN MANIPULATABLE UFIELD FROM ASM OR MASM. @D@@@@     ON   1-(+3>2>1)    EW
)@@G@@              . ON IF @ASM    @D@@@@IV(1) EQU +(P$(S,T))                EX
)@@G@@  . NO *'S, PLEASE@D@@@@     OFF                              . END OF @EY
)@@G@@ASM   @D@@@@     ON   +3>2>1                      . ON IF @MASM   @F@@@@EZ
)@@G@@IV(1) EQU $AP(P$(S,T))                . ONLY THE NON-REL PART     @D@@@@FA
)@@G@@     OFF                              . END OF @MASM  @[@@@@.     @F@@@@FB
)@@G@@JAY(1)  EQU     0                     . ASSUME NO EQUF'D J-SPEC   @F@@@@FC
)@@G@@ DO IV(1)>0377777777                  ; IF VALUE HAS EQUF'D J     @D@@@@FD
)@@G@@  ,K DO 4                             ; FOR ALL J-BITS@E@@@@    , DO (IVFE
)@@G@@(1)-JAY(1))>(G$JBIT(K)-1) ; IF CURRENT BIT ON   @E@@@@       ,JAY(1) EQUFF
)@@G@@ JAY(1)++G$JBIT(K)  . FOLD INTO RESULT    @G@@@@IV(1)   EQU     IV(1)-JAFG
)@@G@@Y(1)          . STRIP EQUF'D J FROM OPERAND     @E@@@@JAY(2)  EQU     EXFH
)@@G@@PJ++JAY(1)*/-26     . GET COMPLETE J-SPEC @F@@@@XRG(1)  EQU     0       FI
)@@G@@              . ASSUME NO EQUF'D X-SPEC   @F@@@@ DO IV(1)>0777777       FJ
)@@G@@              ; IF VALUE HAS EQUF'D X     @D@@@@  ,K DO 4               FK
)@@G@@              ; FOR ALL X-BITS@E@@@@    , DO (IV(1)-XRG(1))>(G$XBIT(K)-1FL
)@@G@@) ; IF CURRENT BIT ON   @E@@@@       ,XRG(1) EQU XRG(1)++G$XBIT(K)  . FOFM
)@@G@@LD INTO RESULT    @G@@@@IV(1)   EQU     IV(1)-XRG(1)          . STRIP EQFN
)@@G@@UF'D X FROM OPERAND     @E@@@@XRG(2)  EQU     XREG++XRG(1)*/-18     . GEFO
)@@G@@T COMPLETE X-SPEC @G@@@@ DO MF=1 , DO (JAY(2)=0)**(P$(S)<(T+2)) ,JAY(2) FP
)@@G@@EQU Q(2,1) . SET DEFALT @G@@@@ DO MF=0 , DO JAY(2)=0                  ,JFQ
)@@G@@AY(2) EQU Q(2,1) . SET DEFALT @F@@@@HIB(1)  EQU     0                   FR
)@@G@@  . ASSUME NO EQUF'D H/I BITS @F@@@@ DO  IV(1)>0177777                  FS
)@@G@@  ; IF VALUE HAS EQUF'D H OR I@G@@@@  ,K DO 2                           FT
)@@G@@  ; FOR BOTH BITS (OF I$ FORM INSTR)@E@@@@    , DO (IV(1)-HIB(1))>(G$HIBFU
)@@G@@I(K)-1) ; IF CURRENT BIT ON   @E@@@@       ,HIB(1) EQU HIB(1)++G$HIBI(K)FV
)@@G@@  . FOLD INTO RESULT    @F@@@@UF EQU +(P$(S,T))-HIB(1)-XRG(1)-JAY(1) . SFW
)@@G@@TRIP OFF J,X,HI BITS    @F@@@@HIB(1) EQU (HBIT*2)++IBIT++(HIB(1)*/-16) .FX
)@@G@@ ALIGN H AND I BITS     @G@@@@ DO IV(1)<0 ,HIB(1) EQU 3             . IFFY
)@@G@@ UFIELD IS NEG, H,I ARE BOTH 1@[@@@@.     @F@@@@  I$  0,JAY(2),0,XRG(2),FZ
)@@G@@HIB(1),UF . GENERATE THE EFFECTIVE UFIELD @D@@@@          END           GA
)@@G@@              . END OF E$AD   @[@@@@/.    @#@@@@. BEGIN USER PROCS@[@@@@GB
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1                .   @C@@@@E$APRT*   NAGC
)@@G@@ME      EAPRT$            . APRINT$ @E@@@@E$PRTG*   NAME      EPRTG$    GD
)@@G@@        . PRINT$ OR APRINT$   @F@@@@E$PRTGA*  NAME      EPRTGA$         GE
)@@G@@  . ASCII OR FIELDATA PRINT$  @D@@@@E$PRTA*   NAME      EPRTA$          GF
)@@G@@  . ASCII PRINT$  @G@@@@E$PRT*    NAME      EPRT$             . PRODUCE GG
)@@G@@LITERAL, PRINT, CLEAR   @C@@@@E$PRTI*   NAME      EPRTI$            . PRGH
)@@G@@INT   @D@@@@E$APRTI*  NAME      EAPRTI$           . ASCII PRINT   @D@@@@GI
)@@G@@E$CSF*    NAME      ECSF$             . CSF$ THINGIE  @H@@@@ DO P$(1)>1 GJ
)@@G@@, LA    12,+(E$AD 1,2 15) . LA[,XU]  A0,P$(1,2),P$(1,3),P$(1,4)   @E@@@@GK
)@@G@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    13,+(E$AD0 1,1 15) . LA,U  A1,P$(1,1)   @B@@@@      GL
)@@G@@    LMJ       11,P$(0,0)        .   @B@@@@          END                 GM
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *0,1      GN
)@@G@@        .   @E@@@@E$DITX*   NAME      0                 . CLOSE EDIT$ PAGO
)@@G@@CKET  @F@@@@E$COLN*   NAME      1                 . RETURN WITH COL NUM GP
)@@G@@IN A0 @F@@@@E$WRDN*   NAME      2                 . RETURN WITH WORD NUMGQ
)@@G@@ IN A0@F@@@@E$MSGR*   NAME      3                 . REENTER MESSAGE EDITGR
)@@G@@OR    @H@@@@E$CLEAR*  NAME      4                 . CLEAR OUTPUT BUFFER,GS
)@@G@@ SET COL TO 0     @D@@@@J         EQU       P$(0,0)           . TARGET AGT
)@@G@@DDRESS@B@@@@ DO J=0 , LMJ       11,EDITX$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=1 , LMGU
)@@G@@J       11,ECOLN$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=2 , LMJ       11,EWRDN$       GV
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@ DO J=3 , LMJ       11,EMSGR$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=4 , LMGW
)@@G@@J       11,ECLEAR$        .   @B@@@@          END                       GX
)@@G@@  .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *2              GY
)@@G@@  .   @E@@@@E$PAD*    NAME      0                 . PAD OUT CHARACTERS  GZ
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    12,+(E$AD 1,1 15) . LA[,XU]  A0,P$(1,1),P$(1,2HA
)@@G@@),P$(1,3)   @H@@@@ DO P$(2)>0 , LA    13,+(E$AD 2,1 15) . LA[,XU]  A1,P$HB
)@@G@@(2,1),P$(2,2),P$(2,3)   @B@@@@          LMJ       11,EPAD$          .   HC
)@@G@@@B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     HD
)@@G@@@B@@@@P$        PROC      *1                .   @G@@@@E$DIT*    NAME    HE
)@@G@@  1                 . ENTER AND OPEN EDIT$ PACKET     @H@@@@E$DITR*   NAHF
)@@G@@ME      2                 . REENTER EDIT$ PACKET AFTER E$DITX     @E@@@@HG
)@@G@@E$CHAR*   NAME      3                 . INSERT 1 CHARACTER  @F@@@@E$COL*HH
)@@G@@    NAME      4                 . MOVE TO SPECIFIED COL     @F@@@@E$SKIPHI
)@@G@@*   NAME      5                 . SKIP SPECIFIED NUM OF COLS@E@@@@E$MSG*HJ
)@@G@@    NAME      6                 . ENTER MESSAGE EDITOR@E@@@@E$MSKP*   NAHK
)@@G@@ME      7                 . SKIP MSG FIELDS     @B@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA  HL
)@@G@@  12,+(E$AD 1,1 15) .   @D@@@@J         EQU       P$(0,0)           . TAHM
)@@G@@RGET ADDRESS@B@@@@ DO J=1 , LMJ       11,EDIT$          .   @B@@@@ DO J=HN
)@@G@@2 , LMJ       11,EDITR$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=3 , LMJ       11,ECHAR$ HO
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@ DO J=4 , LMJ       11,ECOL$          .   @B@@@@ DO J=HP
)@@G@@5 , LMJ       11,ESKIP$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=6 , LMJ       11,EMSG$  HQ
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@ DO J=7 , LMJ       11,EMSKP$         .   @B@@@@      HR
)@@G@@    END                         .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$    HS
)@@G@@    PROC      *1                .   @D@@@@E$RASE*   NAME      0         HT
)@@G@@        . CLEAR BUFFER  @H@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    13,+(E$AD 1,1 15) . LAHU
)@@G@@[,XU]  A1,P$(1,1),P$(1,2),P$(1,3)   @B@@@@          LMJ       11,ERASE$ HV
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@/.    HW
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1                .   @D@@@@E$FD3*HX
)@@G@@    NAME      0                 . INSERT 3 WORDS@H@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA  HY
)@@G@@14,+(E$AD 1,1)+2    . LA       A2,P$(1,1)+2,P$(1,2),P$(1,3) @E@@@@E$FD2*HZ
)@@G@@    NAME      1                 . INSERT TWO WORDS    @G@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 IA
)@@G@@, DL    12,+(E$AD 1,1)    . DL       A0,P$(1,1),P$(1,2)     @D@@@@J     IB
)@@G@@    EQU       P$(0,0)           . TARGET ADDRESS@B@@@@ DO J=0 , LMJ     IC
)@@G@@  11,EFD3$          .   @B@@@@ DO J=1 , LMJ       11,EFD2$          .   ID
)@@G@@@B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     IE
)@@G@@@B@@@@P$        PROC      *2                .   @C@@@@E$PACKC*  NAME    IF
)@@G@@  0                 . PACK    @H@@@@ DO P$(1)>1 , LA    12,+(E$AD 1,2 15IG
)@@G@@) . LA[,XU]  A0,P$(1,2),P$(1,3),P$(1,4)   @F@@@@ DO P$(0)>1 , LXI   12,+IH
)@@G@@(E$AD0 0,1 15) . LXI[,XU]  A0,P$(0,1)     @E@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    13,+II
)@@G@@(E$AD0 1,1 15) . LA[,XU]  A1,P$(1,1)@H@@@@ DO P$(2)>0 , LA    14,+(E$AD IJ
)@@G@@2,1 15) . LA[,XU]  A2,P$(2,1),P$(2,2),P$(2,3)   @B@@@@          LMJ     IK
)@@G@@  11,EPACKC$        .   @B@@@@          END                         .   IL
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1                .   IM
)@@G@@@D@@@@E$COPY*   NAME      1                 . STRING COPY   @F@@@@E$PACKIN
)@@G@@*   NAME      2                 . STRING COPY WITH PACKING  @H@@@@ DO P$IO
)@@G@@(1)>1 , LA    12,+(E$AD 1,2 15) . LA[,XU]  A0,P$(1,2),P$(1,3),P$(1,4)   IP
)@@G@@@F@@@@ DO P$(0)>1 , LXI   12,+(E$AD0 0,1 15) . LXI[,XU]  A0,P$(0,1)     IQ
)@@G@@@E@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    13,+(E$AD0 1,1 15) . LA[,XU]  A1,P$(1,1)@D@@@@IR
)@@G@@J         EQU       P$(0,0)           . TARGET ADDRESS@B@@@@ DO J=1 , LMIS
)@@G@@J       11,ECOPY$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=2 , LMJ       11,EPACK$       IT
)@@G@@  .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@IU
)@@G@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1,1              .   @D@@@@E$FW*     NAIV
)@@G@@ME      0                 . EFORM$ WORD   @F@@@@I         DO        P$(1IW
)@@G@@) ,P$(0,0) EQU (P$(0,0)*/P$(1,I))++1 .    @B@@@@          +         P$(0IX
)@@G@@,0)           .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@IY
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1                .   @D@@@@IZ
)@@G@@E$MSKPR*  NAME      0                 . SKIP AND COPY @H@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 JA
)@@G@@, LA    12,+(E$AD 1,1 15) . LA[,XU]  A0,P$(1,1),P$(1,2),P$(1,3)   @D@@@@JB
)@@G@@          LMJ       11,EMSKP$         . SKIP MSG FIELD@C@@@@          LMJC
)@@G@@J       11,EMSGR$         . AND COPY@B@@@@          END                 JD
)@@G@@        .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *2        JE
)@@G@@        .   @G@@@@E$DECFL*  NAME      0                 . LEADING CHARS JF
)@@G@@- FIXED FORMAT    @H@@@@ DO P$(1)>1 , LA 12,+(E$AD 1,2)     . LA[,XU]  AJG
)@@G@@0,P$(1,1+I),P$(1,2+I),P$(1,3+I@E@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    13,+(E$AD0 1,1 1JH
)@@G@@5) . LA[,XU]  A1,P$(1,1)@H@@@@ DO P$(2)>0 , LA    14,+(E$AD 2,1 15) . LAJI
)@@G@@[,XU]  A2,P$(2,1),P$(2,2),P$(2,3)   @B@@@@          LMJ       11,EDECFL$JJ
)@@G@@        .   @B@@@@          END                         .   @[@@@@.     JK
)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1                .   @E@@@@E$OCTFJL
)@@G@@*   NAME      1                 . FIXED FORMAT OCTAL  @E@@@@E$DECF*   NAJM
)@@G@@ME      2                 . FIXED FORMAT DECIMAL@F@@@@E$HEXF*   NAME    JN
)@@G@@  3                 . FIXED FORMAT HEXADECIMAL  @H@@@@E$DECFZ*  NAME    JO
)@@G@@  4                 . FIXED FORMAT DECIMAL-LEADING ZEROES   @H@@@@E$DCFZJP
)@@G@@*   NAME      4                 . FIXED FORMAT DECIMAL-LEADING ZEROES   JQ
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO P$(1)>1 , LA    12,+(E$AD 1,2)    . LA[,XU]  A0,P$(1,2),P$(1,3JR
)@@G@@),P$(1,4)   @E@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    13,+(E$AD0 1,1 15) . LA[,XU]  A1,PJS
)@@G@@$(1,1)@D@@@@J         EQU       P$(0,0)           . TARGET ADDRESS@B@@@@JT
)@@G@@ DO J=1 , LMJ       11,EOCTF$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=2 , LMJ       11,EJU
)@@G@@DECF$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=3 , LMJ       11,EHEXF$         .   @B@@@@JV
)@@G@@ DO J=4 , LMJ       11,EDECFZ$        .   @B@@@@          END           JW
)@@G@@              .   @[@@@@/.    @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC      *1  JX
)@@G@@              .   @E@@@@E$DECV*   NAME      5                 . FREE FORJY
)@@G@@MAT DECIMAL @E@@@@E$OCTV*   NAME      6                 . FREE FORMAT OCJZ
)@@G@@TAL   @E@@@@E$HEXV*   NAME      7                 . FREE FORMAT HEX     KA
)@@G@@@F@@@@E$FD1*    NAME      8                 . INSERT 6 CHARS (1 WORD)   KB
)@@G@@@H@@@@ DO P$(1)>0 , LA    12,+(E$AD 1,1)    . LA[,XU]  A0,P$(1,1),P$(1,2KC
)@@G@@),P$(1,3)   @D@@@@J         EQU       P$(0,0)           . TARGET ADDRESSKD
)@@G@@@B@@@@ DO J=5 , LMJ       11,EDECV$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=6 , LMJ     KE
)@@G@@  11,EOCTV$         .   @B@@@@ DO J=7 , LMJ       11,EHEXV$         .   KF
)@@G@@@B@@@@ DO J=8 , LMJ       11,EFD1$          .   @B@@@@          END     KG
)@@G@@                    .   @[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @B@@@@P$        PROC    KH
)@@G@@  *2                .   @G@@@@E$FORMC*  NAME      EFORMC$           . FOKI
)@@G@@RM EDITING - SPECIFY CHARACTER@H@@@@ DO P$(2)>0 , LA    14,+(E$AD 2,1 15KJ
)@@G@@) . LA[,XU]  A2,P$(2,1),P$(2,2),P$(2,3)   @F@@@@E$FORM*   NAME      EFORKK

)@@G@@@[@@@@.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P$        PROC      *1  @H@@@@E$FLS1*   NALF

)@@G@@ED POINT FORMAT   @E@@@@P$(9)     EQU       1                 . INSTRUCTLJ

)@@G@@.     @[@@@@.     @^@@@@P$        PROC      *1  @F@@@@E$TIME*   NAME    LS
